msgctxt "0bfc1421-e48f-4e1a-948f-9c2fcf456146"
msgid "\\\"No, Kimo… it was a joke.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"안 돼... 키모. 그냥 농담이었어.\\\""

msgctxt "6f790599-858e-4850-a38b-0707e6548224"
msgid "\\\"No, Kimo... It was a joke.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"안 돼... 키모. 그냥 농담이었어.\\\""

msgctxt "672db183-0f64-490e-a619-05001560261f"
msgid "\\\"Yes. You must leave, Kimo.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그래... 떠나.\\\""

msgctxt "e2748a44-0e25-4367-b60f-3a141a039bb5"
msgid "\\\"Yes. You have to leave, Kimo.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그래... 떠나.\\\""

msgctxt "648fc230-4a65-49d3-8358-5ba094d23655"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do not despair! I'm glad to see you back. We'll think of something, I promise. "
"But for now, you must go rest.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"실망하지 마! 너를 다시 봐서 기뻐. 다른 걸 생각해보자. 일단 가서 쉬어.\\\""

msgctxt "8b6b0aca-c755-4709-b632-19cbf532cf28"
msgid "\\\"Don't make any rash decisions, Kimo. Let's talk about it later.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"섣부른 판단 하지마. 키모. 다음에 얘기하자.\\\""

msgctxt "b38261b8-f7f3-47ba-a4cb-6c9b3b8f2124"
msgid "\\\"Good riddance.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"속 시원하다.\\\""

msgctxt "2777c95a-53bb-4222-8969-dc79721d93bd"
msgid ""
"{n}Kimo bows elegantly, a broad smile dancing on his lips.{/n} \\\"It's ready. I "
"brought you something!\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}키모가 우아하게 인사했고 그녀의 입술에는 미소가 춤을 춥니다.{/n} \\\"준비 됐어. "
"너에게 보여줄게!\\\""

msgctxt "feebbe31-104c-4995-93c8-7cb5123be05b"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Kimo}Kimo{/d} bows awkwardly, a broad smile dancing on his lips.{/n} \\\"It "
"is ready. I brought you something!\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}키모가 어색하게 인사했고 그녀의 입술에는 미소가 춤을 춥니다.{/n} \\\"준비 됐어. "
"너에게 보여줄게!\\\""

msgctxt "d8c10572-d944-46ee-b491-7a97d75172c3"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Kimo}Kimo{/d} can barely contain his excitement.{/n} \\\"Here you go! I'm "
"all done! It's a very fine bow, I must say… Of course, I always try my best when "
"I'm making something for you. But I've never tried as hard as this! And the wood, "
"it's from... errr... a common friend of ours.\\\" {n}Kimo winks at you.{/n}"
msgstr ""
"{n}{d|Kimo}Kimo{/d}는 흥분을 감추지 못합니다.{/n} \\\"여기 있어! 모두 만들었어! 정"
"말 좋은 활이야... 물론. 너에게 만들어 줄 때는 최선을 다했어. 하지만 이렇게 노력한 "
"적은 없어! 그리고 이 나무는... 음... 내 친구 하나를 잡아서 만든 거야.\\\" {n}키모"
"가 당신에게 윙크합니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "8f765005-dec8-4cc1-bbef-6ae83755113b"
msgid "\\\"A special piece? Why, of course, my pleasure! What sort exactly?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"특별한 걸 만들어달라고? 물론 만들어 줄게! 어떤 장비가 필요해?\\\""

msgctxt "3624fdbf-b294-44a2-a2a9-e6ab33ce1da9"
msgid "\\\"Specific? Why, of course. With pleasure! But... what exactly?\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"특별한 걸 만들어달라고? 물론 만들어 줄게! 하지만... 어떤 장비가 필요해?\\\""

msgctxt "d3a58a70-1604-499a-bcbf-14aa9ec6fe21"
msgid "\\\"As you wish. I'll think of something.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네가 원하는 대로. 생각해 볼게.\\\""

msgctxt "120a3c52-939c-45eb-8c8d-04573ec1370b"
msgid "\\\"Fine. I will think of something.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"좋아. 생각해 볼게.\\\""

msgctxt "9b20373d-0473-42df-91f8-ebc2dea6052a"
msgid "{n}The elf gives a leisurely nod.{/n} \\\"Consider it done.\\\""
msgstr "{n}엘프는 끄덕입니다.{/n} \\\"생각해 볼게.\\\""

msgctxt "55c4ba10-002a-412f-ab2e-7ce6753afd4e"
msgid "{n}The elf gives a leisurely nod.{/n} \\\"I will do it.\\\""
msgstr "{n}엘프는 끄덕입니다.{/n} \\\"알겠어.\\\""

msgctxt "e7c2bd5e-7e0f-4acd-8adf-8a03ebe2143f"
msgid "\\\"You're welcome!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"천만에!\\\""

msgctxt "5a565952-c2f2-4343-9070-b65914668935"
msgid "\\\"You are welcome!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"천만에!\\\""

msgctxt "af1a766c-0b10-4b34-9939-835c40d60405"
msgid ""
"{n}Kimo looks at you with wide-open eyes, then looks around the throne room, then "
"stares at you again.{/n} \\\"So… does that mean… that I have to leave?\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}키모는 눈이 커져서 알현실 주위를 돌아보더니 당신을 다시 봅니다.{/n} \\\"그러니"
"까... 나보고 떠나라는 거야?\\\""

msgctxt "ea9a46da-8a69-4a3f-a01f-f9a8ff1731ba"
msgid ""
"{n}Kimo looks at you with wide eyes, looks around the throne room, then stares at "
"you again.{/n} \\\"So... does that mean... Do I have to leave?\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}키모는 눈이 커져서 알현실 주위를 돌아보더니 당신을 다시 봅니다.{/n} \\\"그러니"
"까... 나보고 떠나라는 거야?\\\""

msgctxt "b2ed2f56-e7e5-4822-902f-dadbc13a208e"
msgid "{n} The elf heaves a sigh of relief.{/n}"
msgstr "{n}엘프는 안도의 한숨을 쉽니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "01c33f70-3fb6-4a34-aa88-6605b9fefe66"
msgid "{n}The elf gives a sigh of relief.{/n}"
msgstr "{n}엘프는 안도의 한숨을 쉽니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "bd4df72a-581f-44f7-ad00-54ef8090fa27"
msgid ""
"\\\"Mhm. I see…\\\" {n}The elf furrows his brow in concentration.{/n} \\\"I do not "
"fully understand the laws of these lands… I just want to say I am very glad I met "
"you. And I'm sad that I have to leave. But, if that is what I must do… Farewell, "
"{name}!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"음... 알겠어.\\\" {n}엘프는 찡그립니다.{/n} \\\"이 땅의 법이 어떤지는 모르지"
"만... 너를 만나 즐거웠어. 떠나야 한다니 슬퍼. 하지만 가야 한다면... 안녕!\\\""

msgctxt "0340e993-0e77-40ad-b5f8-c0a2b88845af"
msgid ""
"{n}The elf furrows his brow in concentration.{/n} \\\"I do not fully understand "
"the laws of these lands... I just want to say that I am very glad I met you. And I "
"am sad that I have to leave. But, if that is what I must do... Farewell, {name}!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"음... 알겠어.\\\" {n}엘프는 찡그립니다.{/n} \\\"이 땅의 법이 어떤지는 모르지"
"만... 너를 만나 즐거웠어. 떠나야 한다니 슬퍼. 하지만 가야 한다면... 안녕!\\\""

msgctxt "772cff56-c2eb-43f4-a5c7-be2e6671f7de"
msgid ""
"{n}Just as he's about to leave, Kimo stops and turns to you.{/n} \\\"Oh, yes, by "
"the way! I needed to ask you something… Could you please help me?\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}그거 떠나려고 하자 키모는 멈춰서 당신을 봅니다.{/n} \\\"그래! 네게 묻고 싶은 게 "
"있어... 나를 도와주겠어?\\\""

msgctxt "1cec7140-abbc-45af-9a48-c530dc99b079"
msgid ""
"{n}Kimo coughs in his fist, clearly embarrassed.{/n} \\\"I almost forgot... "
"Please, come and talk to me! I... I have to ask you something. Something personal."
"\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}키모는 당황해서 기침을 합니다.{/n} \\\"잊고 있었어... 그럼 내게 와서 말해줘! 나"
"는... 묻고 싶은 게 있어. 개인적인 거야.\\\""

msgctxt "98a1a304-c486-4664-90ed-5c090e98e7ee"
msgid "\\\"Come to my place. I'll tell you everything.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"내 장소로 와줘. 모두 말해줄게.\\\""

msgctxt "9f30732f-6adf-401a-b551-bef7b471e573"
msgid "{n}Red as a lobster, Kimo leaves the throne room.{/n}"
msgstr "{n}키모는 랍스터처럼 얼굴이 붉어지더니 알현실을 떠납니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "d1df9ac3-a76c-40c1-81d1-9b772c0e3712"
msgid "{n}His face drawn and haggard, {d|Kimo}Kimo{/d} bows to you.{/n}"
msgstr "{n}키모는 시무룩해져서 당신에게 인사합니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "f7278bdd-6749-48a6-9e19-73358c34c241"
msgid ""
"\\\"Forgive me for not coming for so long. And please accept this humble gift – my "
"final gift to you.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"금방 떠나야 해서 미안해. 이 작은 선물을 받아줘. 마지막 선물이야.\\\""

msgctxt "9dc8bef1-e7c1-4e58-a13d-aa8fbdc2c112"
msgid ""
"\\\"She has rejected me. She will not listen to my pleas. My work has no sense "
"anymore – just as my life. I shall bid you farewell and leave these lands forever."
"\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"그녀가 내 부탁을 거절했어. 그녀는 내 부탁을 들어주지 않을 거야. 내 작업은 의미 "
"없어졌어. 이제 인사하고 영원히 이곳을 떠나야겠어.\\\""

msgctxt "3d7395d0-bcb3-475f-9adb-b5b3451ee179"
msgid "{n}Kimo shrugs.{/n} \\\"As you wish…\\\""
msgstr "{n}키모가 어깨를 으쓱합니다.{/n} \\\"원하는 대로...\\\""

msgctxt "da480211-ec7a-4ad5-b1c5-7699d5a000c7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Farewell, {name}. You've helped me on this path – but you couldn't have known "
"where it would lead me.\\\" {n}Kimo sighs deeply and leaves the throne room.{/n}"
msgstr ""
"\\\"안녕히. 내가 이 길에 오기까지 네 인도를 받았지만 그 길이 어디인지는 너는 모를 "
"거야.\\\" {n}키모는 깊은 한숨을 쉬고는 알현실을 떠납니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "57430050-dc1c-480c-b07d-022a322e7ec2"
msgid "\\\"You wanted to ask something of me…\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나에게 부탁하고 싶은 게 있다고 했지...\\\""

msgctxt "82dfa3a9-57c3-4784-9913-6c8b5d94560d"
msgid "\\\"Why did you want that flower so bad?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"왜 그렇게 꽃을 원하는 거야?\\\""

msgctxt "0065ffab-bedf-4229-bcd2-89fe05d597ae"
msgid "\\\"Where do you hail from, Kimo?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"너는 어디에서 왔지?\\\""

msgctxt "5e99f402-b2f0-47aa-98cb-6ace608c8a9b"
msgid "\\\"Where do you hail from, Kimo?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"너는 어디에서 왔지?\\\""

msgctxt "ba3fa6ac-9a2a-4057-b019-e395916c9d4e"
msgid "\\\"What made you leave Kyonin?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"왜 쿄닌을 떠난 거지?\\\""

msgctxt "9f46c9b4-e6c0-4c7d-b09c-3a4986cedcfa"
msgid "\\\"Why did you leave Kyonin?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"왜 쿄닌을 떠난 거지?\\\""

msgctxt "6f47916a-1831-41f2-ab2b-c61b55403d23"
msgid "\\\"And?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그리고?\\\""

msgctxt "b67d0481-0207-4d6a-8f77-ccb464d99480"
msgid "[Say nothing]"
msgstr "[아무 말도 하지 않습니다]"

msgctxt "81d4309f-3ba2-4d59-ab91-2025b7fb6573"
msgid "\\\"I see. No need to tell me anything, then.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"좋아. 나에게 말할 필요는 없어.\\\""

msgctxt "47fc43ed-528f-4312-884c-0569c0b381c6"
msgid "\\\"Are you going to tell me or what?''"
msgstr "\\\"말 할 거야? 말 거야?''"

msgctxt "0ccc52fb-6dfe-4d96-9198-b297d7a54653"
msgid "\\\"Kimo…\\\""
msgstr "\\\"Kimo…\\\""

msgctxt "a7a7b7f3-1401-4906-8e49-34eb3b89b740"
msgid "\\\"I'm happy for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9243f9f8-f235-49cf-b53a-f61c1ac124e1"
msgid "\\\"You can't be serious…\\\""
msgstr "\\\"장난이지?\\\""

msgctxt "73a70387-c748-41f5-9f1d-b712b15466bf"
msgid "\\\"I'm sick and tired of you!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나는 이제 네가 질렸어!\\\""

msgctxt "026c947d-c44a-44a7-9760-1a955fdde4c1"
msgid "\\\"I must go.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나는 가야 해.\\\""

msgctxt "1a52366c-74b6-4baf-bab4-eb0dfa8c2f2d"
msgid "\\\"What did you want to ask me?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나에게 무얼 부탁하고 싶지?\\\""

msgctxt "546928c9-975a-4ad4-9146-1cfebf388cfb"
msgid "\\\"Tell me exactly what you need.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네가 원하는 걸 말해줘.\\\""

msgctxt "acc61fdd-20eb-4134-8a9a-b64af80cb80c"
msgid "\\\"You seem to put a lot of trust in this hunter's opinion.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"사냥꾼의 의견을 너무 믿는 것 같군.\\\""

msgctxt "c2b71dce-dc5a-4eda-be23-1f055a4eaee1"
msgid "\\\"So be it.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그러라지.\\\""

msgctxt "d2aee2bd-0221-419d-b432-27a92364774f"
msgid "\\\"I'm not interested.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"흥미 없어.\\\""

msgctxt "72e325ed-62fc-4681-8e60-69e771fceb64"
msgid "\\\"I'll think about it.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"생각해보지.\\\""

msgctxt "7c2c51d7-767d-4ac5-a2fb-89370f055333"
msgid "\\\"Take a look – is this necklace any good?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"이 목걸이가 좋은 걸까?\\\""

msgctxt "463c76d3-fa3e-4d56-ac68-1d8106cc083c"
msgid "\\\"Tell me what went wrong between you two. You had a fight?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"너희 둘 사이에서 문슨 일이 있었는지 말해줘. 싸운 거야?\\\""

msgctxt "e166589f-b825-4795-aa52-42115feab34a"
msgid "\\\"What do you mean, she 'hid in her tree'?''"
msgstr "\\\"그녀의 나무에 숨었다니. 무슨 소리야?\\\""

msgctxt "7cd0a71f-ce23-4908-8cde-4d1c0f70fc0e"
msgid "\\\"Show me on the map where to find her.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"어디서 그녀를 찾아야 할지 지도에 표시해줘.\\\""

msgctxt "e58972ad-305f-4d2b-98a1-1386b8ae1914"
msgid "\\\"I see.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"알겠어.\\\""

msgctxt "009d85f8-b152-4510-8645-ed9b3686bf15"
msgid "\\\"I've had a chat with your dryad.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네 드라이어드와 대화했어.\\\""

msgctxt "2191321e-b238-478d-9284-96bdd9423aa9"
msgid "\\\"Go to her. She's waiting for you.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그녀에게 가. 너를 기다리고 있어.\\\""

msgctxt "9d4238d6-55b9-4df9-afdd-d4151d0458b6"
msgid "\\\"It didn't work out… Sorry, Kimo.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"소용이 없었어... 미안. 키모.\\\""

msgctxt "1fa5d884-5f32-4e7c-949f-07158fca9663"
msgid "\\\"It didn't work out... I'm sorry, Kimo.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"소용이 없었어... 미안. 키모.\\\""

msgctxt "28fd4c40-7fa6-4608-b4ce-84aa1600e118"
msgid "{n}Kimo smiles at you absent-mindedly.{/n} \\\"Good day!\\\""
msgstr "{n}키모가 멍하니 웃습니다.{/n} \\\"안녕.\\\""

msgctxt "64f4af5a-82fe-42b4-a4bf-f5aecbe97db9"
msgid "{n}{d|Kimo}Kimo{/d} smiles at you absentmindedly.{/n} \\\"Good day!\\\""
msgstr "{n}키모가 멍하니 웃습니다.{/n} \\\"안녕.\\\""

msgctxt "3cb84b3f-d877-4ef7-ad06-a40846cf08c8"
msgid ""
"{n}Kimo closes his eyes in reverie.{/n} \\\"Kyonin. The land of the elves. The "
"land of springs and forests. That is where I learned my craft…\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}키모가 떠올리듯 말합니다.{/n} \\\"쿄닌은 엘프의 땅이야. 봄과 숲의 땅이지. 거기"
"서 기술을 배웠어...\\\""

msgctxt "2d71b61a-c3a9-414c-ad31-4bec583f6cca"
msgid ""
"{n}Kimo closes his eyes in reverie.{/n} \\\"Kyonin. The land of the elves. The "
"land of springs and forests. That is where I learned my craft...\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}키모가 떠올리듯 말합니다.{/n} \\\"쿄닌은 엘프의 땅이야. 봄과 숲의 땅이지. 거기"
"서 기술을 배웠어...\\\""

msgctxt "6e9ad30d-ef20-4fb1-a828-75d75c0541c3"
msgid "\\\"You'd love it there. Everyone does.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"너도 거기 가면 좋아할 거야. 모두 좋아하지.\\\""

msgctxt "7207626e-da9d-4916-aeb5-8eb2c11c2642"
msgid "\\\"You would love it there. Everybody does.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"너도 거기 가면 좋아할 거야. 모두 좋아하지.\\\""

msgctxt "e5d91571-c287-47c0-82f8-114b3eea6151"
msgid ""
"\\\"But you must have been there already. And if not, then you should go! You "
"won't regret it.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"거기에 가봤을 테지. 그렇지 않다면 꼭 가봐! 후회하지 않을 거야.\\\""

msgctxt "144e1494-c0af-4a9f-9b62-6032091ee0e2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nobody made me leave!\\\" {n}Kimo gives you an embarrassed look.{/n} \\\"I "
"just woke up one day, looked out the window… and the road called. And I went!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"누구도 나를 떠나라고 할 수 없어!\\\" {n}키모는 당황하여 당신을 봅니다.{/n} \\"
"\"어느날 일어나서 창 밖을 봤는데... 길이 나를 부르더군. 그래서 떠났어.\\\""

msgctxt "196ccfe6-187a-4601-af4c-1cf7350f4933"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nobody made me leave.\\\" {n}Kimo glances at you sideways.{/n} \\\"I just woke "
"up one day, looked out the window... and the road called. And I went.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"누구도 나를 떠나라고 할 수 없어!\\\" {n}키모는 곁눈질로 당신을 봅니다.{/n} \\"
"\"어느날 일어나서 창 밖을 봤는데... 길이 나를 부르더군. 그래서 떠났어.\\\""

msgctxt "d3a0640d-4f6c-436a-b23f-e61821048f96"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh! I don't want to tell! But since you asked me, it would have been awkward "
"if I refused.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"오! 말하기 싫어! 하지만 물어봤으니 말해줘야지.\\\""

msgctxt "d3b9b449-9346-4c53-b48a-e0fa6a39edd9"
msgid "\\\"What?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"뭐?\\\""

msgctxt "682aa980-d0bf-4164-9bfa-c85e95295bba"
msgid ""
"\\\"But you must have been there already. And if not, then you should! You won't "
"regret it.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"거기에 가봤을 테지. 그렇지 않다면 꼭 가봐! 후회하지 않을 거야.\\\""

msgctxt "7ef5d980-edb3-433d-8ad0-8ff351925d3b"
msgid "\\\"Well… fine then.\\\" {n}The elf sounds somewhat disappointed.{/n}"
msgstr "\\\"좋아...\\\" {n}엘프는 실망한 것 같습니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "9db539cf-64c2-453e-91ae-ec01c5891327"
msgid "{n}The elf awkwardly picks at the ground with the toe-cap of his boot.{/n}"
msgstr "{n}엘프는 어색하게 땅만 발로 차고 있습니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "d2aabbc8-def5-4fd4-a9c0-fb46ae3e06ea"
msgid "\\\"Alright, alright…\\\" {n}The elf takes a deep breath.{/n}"
msgstr "\\\"좋아. 좋아...\\\" {n}엘프는 깊은 숨을 쉽니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "4f65185d-0a16-4cfa-924d-d6e4082f638d"
msgid "\\\"I… I am in love. With a lady in the forest.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나는... 사랑에 빠졌어. 숲의 여성과 말이야.\\\""

msgctxt "5400cda8-a948-42f7-8ae4-857afcb798ce"
msgid "\\\"Well…\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그럼…\\\""

msgctxt "9faa36d2-5401-4dd6-b4d9-a6f6e75f2378"
msgid ""
"\\\"That flower was for her. I cannot tell you who she is. But she had hidden "
"herself from me, and that is what darkens my days.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"그 꽃은 그녀를 위한 거야. 그녀가 누군지 말해줄게. 하지만 그녀는 나에게서 숨었"
"고 그 이후로 나는 우울했지.\\\""

msgctxt "4168301a-17f1-41bb-9815-efeac8986b40"
msgid "\\\"Thank you! If only I could be happy as well…\\\""
msgstr "\\\"고마워!\\\""

msgctxt "f6fb390a-d1d6-4ebc-91b0-b32c13ec8a01"
msgid "{n}{d|Kimo}Kimo{/d} gives you a dreary nod.{/n} \\\"Good day…\\\""
msgstr "{n}{d|Kimo}Kimo{/d}는 우울하게 당신을 봅니다.{/n} \\\"안녕…\\\""

msgctxt "40bb15d9-40ee-48df-8cb5-bcf94647c1a1"
msgid ""
"{n}Kimo looks at you with regret.{/n} \\\"Forgive me, friend! I did not wish to "
"disappoint you…\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}키모는 후회하는 눈빛으로 당신을 봅니다.{/n} \\\"용서해줘! 너를 실망시키고 싶지 "
"않았어...\\\""

msgctxt "b6f2a1d0-725f-404c-8952-3367c3b1be5c"
msgid "\\\"You won't believe this! It's about her!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"믿을 수 없을 거야! 그녀에 관한 거야!\\\""

msgctxt "a486ea7a-1d90-430b-ad4d-05070f80b4dd"
msgid "\\\"She finally agreed to go on a date with me! I need to get ready!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그녀가 마침내 나와 데이트를 하겠다고 해! 어서 준비해야겠다!\\\""

msgctxt "9856b0d1-9835-44fb-be5d-7db52eadac73"
msgid ""
"\\\"A hunter I know said that you only need one thing to woo a lady: a gift. "
"Maybe... maybe an emerald necklace would do! But I wouldn't even know where to "
"start looking for such a thing! Please, help me. I will repay you, I promise.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"아는 사냥꾼이 그러는데 여자는 선물을 보면 눈물을 흘린다는군... 에메랄드 목걸이"
"면 될 거야! 하지만 어디서 찾아야 할지 모르겠어! 도와줘. 보상은 할게.\\\""

msgctxt "ed090a64-64c5-4d5e-afc3-ddda4d441f52"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well… I don't really know… But surely, something that can't be found in every "
"shop or roadside tavern.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"음... 잘 모르겠어... 길가 주점이나 아무 가게에서 파는 물건은 아닐 거야...\\\""

msgctxt "9e2b63a6-cfad-40c5-b8e8-6469237473ae"
msgid ""
"\\\"He talks a lot, and the other villagers listen to him.\\\" {n}Kimo bends over "
"and whispers in a conspiratorial tone.{/n} \\\"To be completely honest, I "
"sometimes think that he's… you know… a bit slow.\\\" {n}The elf gives you a "
"meaningful glance, his eyebrows raised high.{/n} \\\"But he has a lot of "
"experience. He knows a lot of things that I have no idea about!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"그는 말이 많았고 다른 사람들이 그의 이야기를 듣고 있었지.\\\" {n}키모는 허리를 "
"숙여 조용히 당신에게 속삭입니다.{/n} \\\"솔직히 나는 가끔 그가... 좀 느리다고 생각"
"했어.\\\" {n}엘프는 당신에게 은근한 눈길을 줍니다.{/n} \\\"하지만 그는 경험이 많"
"지. 내가 모르는 것도 많이 알아!\\\""

msgctxt "1556d929-e086-4044-a875-f6a391b4f392"
msgid ""
"\\\"I knew it!\\\" {n}Kimo is as happy as a cat that's found a pot of cream.{/n} \\"
"\"You are always so kind! And I will help you in return – you'll see!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"알고 있었어!\\\" {n}키모는 물고기 만난 고양이처럼 행복해 합니다.{/n} \\\"너는 "
"항상 친절하구나! 너를 언젠가 도울게. 약속해!\\\""

msgctxt "532cdc7a-0ff7-4e73-8b85-54db1a1c00fd"
msgid ""
"{n}Kimo is scratching his head helplessly.{/n} \\\"Of course, {name}. As you wish! "
"Thanks for hearing me out…\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}키모는 머리를 긁습니다.{/n} \\\"물론. 네가 원하는 대로! 내 이야기를 들어주어 고"
"마워...\\\""

msgctxt "7c1e1cf3-b622-42f8-8bea-09eb84f2dd38"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, thank you so much! That's very noble of you – after all, you're so busy "
"all the time…\\\" {n}Kimo's face radiates wholehearted gratitude.{/n} \\\"Take as "
"much time as you need.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"오. 정말 고마워! 정말 친절하구나. 너는 항상 바빴는데...\\\" {n}키모의 얼굴은 붉"
"어집니다.{/n} \\\"편히 있다 가.\\\""

msgctxt "422ffede-61e2-43a1-8baf-49d6e89ed5d0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll come up with something so… so special…\\\" {n}Kimo's gaze wanders far "
"away.{/n}"
msgstr "\\\"특별한 무언가를 가져왔어...\\\" {n}키모는 시선을 돌립니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "48c22d11-90e4-4695-82a7-a74d1718f9d5"
msgid "{n}Kimo looks dumbfounded.{/n} \\\"How pretty!\\\""
msgstr "{n}키모는 멍청하게 웃습니다.{/n} \\\"정말 예쁘다!\\\""

msgctxt "7654d616-56a4-4ec4-9aa3-e294715f02e5"
msgid "{n}Kimo nods absent-mindedly.{/n}"
msgstr "{n}키모는 멍하니 끄덕입니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "5a6303be-6c03-493b-9be9-3a2fb5d4f46e"
msgid ""
"{n}A happy, dreamy smile blooms on the elf's face. The next moment, however, his "
"eyes widen, and huge beads of sweat cover his forehead.{/n}"
msgstr ""
"{n}엘프의 얼굴에 꿈꾸는 듯한 행복한 미소가 나타납니다. 하지만 그는 놀라서 땀을 흘리"
"기 시작합니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "2c03a34e-7252-47e8-930a-26f37e09cd51"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then… then I should go.\\\" {n}Kimo gulps and gives you a weary sideways look."
"{/n} \\\"Thanks, {name}. You've done me a great service. I already know how I "
"shall repay you – I'll make you a bow. The best bow in the world! But now I must "
"go.\\\" {n}Kimo exhales decisively and slowly walks away.{/n}"
msgstr ""
"\\\"그럼... 나는 이제 가야겠어.\\\" {n}키모는 침울 꿀꺽 삼키고는 시무룩한 표정을 짓"
"습니다.{/n} \\\"고마워. 나에게 잘 대해줘서. 나도 이제 보답할게. 세계에서 가장 좋은 "
"활을 만들어줄게! 하지만 지금은 가야 해.\\\" {n}키모는 한숨을 쉬고는 천천히 떠납니"
"다.{/n}"

msgctxt "9012d229-8bd5-47fb-a04d-869a74160b67"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't know… Everything went so well after our first date. We spent every day "
"together. We talked, we gathered flowers, we watched the clouds pass by… And then, "
"one evening, she said 'goodbye' – and hid herself inside her tree. She hasn't "
"shown her face or said a word to me ever since. No matter how many times I've "
"asked...\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"모르겠어... 첫 데이트 후로 잘 되어가고 있었어. 우리는 매일 함께 했지. 이야기도 "
"하고 꽃도 같이 모으고 하늘의 구름도 같이 보고... 그런데 어느 날 밤 그녀가 작별 인사"
"를 하고는 자기 나무에 숨어버렸어. 그 후로 말을 걸지도 모습을 보이지도 않아. 내가 얼"
"마나 많이 대화를 걸었는데...\\\""

msgctxt "fdbeb0c2-e743-49fb-8380-2e8e979ea507"
msgid ""
"{n}Kimo heaves another heavy sigh.{/n} \\\"She's a dryad… Her body and spirit are "
"tied to an oak. She takes care of it and protects it. I met her when I was in the "
"forest, trying to find my way to this settlement.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}키모는 깊은 한숨을 쉽니다.{/n} \\\"그녀는 드라이어드야... 몸과 영혼이 오크 나무"
"에 묶여있지. 그래서 나무를 보호해야 해. 정착지를 찾으러 이 숲에 왔다가 그녀를 만났"
"어.\\\""

msgctxt "08f59c5a-1c7e-459e-a285-67301548e193"
msgid ""
"\\\"But you can't help… Her heart knows no mercy. You cannot change her wooden "
"mind…\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"하지만 너는 나를 도울 수 없어... 그녀는 자비가 없거든. 너도 그녀의 마음을 돌리"
"지 못 할 거야...\\\""

msgctxt "06e2d4c9-0d2f-483b-a391-1c4cc50aeb0f"
msgid "\\\"And?\\\" {n}The elf's fingers are twisting into a knot.{/n}"
msgstr "\\\"그래서?\\\" {n}엘프는 손을 꼬으며 기다립니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "d8cf5eee-daf4-4039-9e0a-2648b9ae80ac"
msgid "\\\"It can't… it can't be! Thank you, {name}!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"오. 이럴 리가! 고마워!\\\""

msgctxt "a0d50bf5-a632-46ad-8efe-9ceaded680f9"
msgid "\\\"It... it cannot be! Thank you, {name}!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"오. 이럴 리가! 고마워!\\\""

msgctxt "f88c6203-7d7a-46f8-bfa1-203c8a6b19c5"
msgid "\\\"I knew this would happen. Thank you for at least trying...\\\""
msgstr "\\\"이렇게 될 줄 알았어. 그래도 고마워...\\\""

msgctxt "1006d6ef-def6-41b5-8bb2-338d53f03c77"
msgid ""
"\\\"I knew this would happen. Thank you for at least trying… It's time for me to "
"go. Far, far away from here.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"이렇게 될 줄 알았어. 그래도 고마워... 나는 이제 가야겠어. 아주 먼 곳으로.\\\""

msgctxt "3c9701d6-9941-4c9c-8d18-997f7d0b2cf4"
msgid ""
"\\\"I can't wait to get back to work, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}! I'm "
"so excited to see my new workshop...\\\""
msgstr "\\\"어서 가서 일하고 싶다! 내 새로운 작업장을 보게 되다니 흥분돼.\\\""

msgctxt "64d22c7b-9be3-49c8-bbdb-a361c979ee25"
msgid "\\\"Nice meeting you, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"안녕!\\\""

msgctxt "701f69b2-aa1c-432e-a7ca-5ded4cb62f8e"
msgid "\\\"That'll teach you!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"너도 알게 될 거야!\\\""

msgctxt "41d8c9f3-829a-470c-b0c0-db9f5006cec4"
msgid "\\\"Here! Help! Help!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"여기야! 도와줘! 도와줘!\\\""

msgctxt "af0efad3-86fa-47ca-968f-4c1727f5f893"
msgid "\\\"I should probably get going... Farewell!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나는 이제 가야겠어... 안녕!\\\""

msgctxt "56f306cb-ba04-4568-870d-503832cf9a69"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you so, so much, {name}. If it weren't for your help, I... oh well. I "
"think I'll stay here just a bit longer. Don't worry, I'll find my way back.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"정말 고마워. 네 도움이 없었다면... 오. 여기에 조금 더 머물러야 할 것 같아. 걱"
"정 마. 다시 돌아갈 길을 찾을 수 있으니.\\\""

msgctxt "8de0f9e7-a9fb-4080-b4ef-445df165ff13"
msgid "\\\"What heavenly beauty...\\\""
msgstr "\\\"정말 아름답구나...\\\""

msgctxt "f130c8ea-2321-4224-b278-e4cfa2c1929c"
msgid "\\\"What is the greatest goldsmith in Restov doing in this backwater?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"레스토브의 이 후미진 곳에서 최고로 황금을 잘 제련하는 자가 누구지?\\\""

msgctxt "4d9ce03a-ce19-47cb-a949-8ec203548ea7"
msgid "\\\"Why should I help you?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"왜 내가 너를 도와야 하지?\\\""

msgctxt "9918a383-e04f-435e-9651-30d793095b90"
msgid "\\\"Very well, you shall have your gemstone.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"좋아. 네 보석이 곧 생길 거야.\\\""

msgctxt "1e14bef6-1d1b-437c-8554-1482c99f5cc2"
msgid "\\\"I'll think about it.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"생각해 보지.\\\""

msgctxt "3fc22697-28b2-4c7c-9678-58a4ff2860a1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have many important matters to deal with. I'm sorry, but I can't help you.\\"
"\""
msgstr "\\\"많은 일이 있었어. 미안하지만 도와줄 수 없어.\\\""

msgctxt "4a4efe38-546c-402d-aa0a-6a5e83564dcb"
msgid "\\\"Please remind me what you asked for.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네가 무엇을 부탁했는지 다시 말해줘.\\\""

msgctxt "ad7bcfa3-968e-4597-b1fe-3c855efb27cf"
msgid "\\\"I am still looking for a suitable jewel.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"아직도 적당한 보석을 찾고 있어.\\\""

msgctxt "4545b456-7cda-4d06-a193-c689242e7d11"
msgid "\\\"Here is your emerald.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"여기 에메랄드다.\\\""

msgctxt "2b3ca990-934e-49b5-9cdf-edd3089bb0c7"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나는 가야 해.\\\""

msgctxt "a11dc391-3713-46b9-a8f0-51ebacbcb37b"
msgid ""
"\\\"There you are! I've wanted to see you in person for a long time – all of {g|"
"Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} is talking about your feats...\\\" {n}The girl is smiling "
"curiously. Sizing you up, she finally nods to you.{/n} \\\"Mim Wobblegander, the "
"greatest goldsmith in {g|Restov}Restov{/g}, at your service! Happy to meet the "
"ruler of this land!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"왔구나! 오랫동안 너를 보고 싶었어. {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}에서 네 얘기가 가득하더"
"군...\\\" {n}여성은 궁금한 듯 웃습니다. 당신을 훑어보고 그녀는 마침내 끄덕입니다.{/"
"n} \\\"나는 {g|Restov}Restov{/g}에서 최고로 황금을 잘 제련하는 Mim Wobblegander야. "
"이 땅의 지배자를 만나니 너무 좋아!\\\""

msgctxt "72e98800-8f38-44b6-8eb2-d861c822f633"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you wish, as you wish... Alas, I was thinking about staying for a while. "
"But on the other hand, there are so many other places I want visit!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"네가 원하는 대로... 아. 잠시 머물려고 했었는데. 하지만 내가 가고 싶은 곳은 정"
"말 많아!\\\""

msgctxt "d8b575ab-7735-4119-89ed-706103677348"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmmm. I suppose that'll have to do for now. I'm in no hurry to leave, anyways "
"– the marvelous views you have here are just too good!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"흠. 지금은 그걸로 충분해. 나는 좀 더 머무르겠어. 여기 경치는 정말 좋거든!\\\""

msgctxt "47447728-997b-43b0-aa01-8d5368bbe317"
msgid "\\\"Wonderful! I shall impatiently await your return.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"완벽해! 네가 돌아오기를 기다릴게.\\\""

msgctxt "d4016c8e-97e4-4d2b-9592-83a9cf2b1bef"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let's say... if I'm provided an appropriate place to work, I wouldn't mind "
"staying for a while, to draw upon the special inspiration that these lands give "
"me. Of course, I would express gratitude to my patron from time to time, with "
"gifts befitting {mf|his|her} status and my mastery.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"음... 내가 일을 하도록 허락을 받았다면 머물러야지. 물론 가끔 후원자에게 인사도 "
"하고 말이야.\\\""

msgctxt "696e09f8-7d33-46b3-aec1-85a8e68e2c04"
msgid ""
"\\\"Seeking recognition and inspiration! You see, not everyone in {g|Restov}"
"Restov{/g} realizes how unfairly destiny has divided its gifts between me and my "
"competitors. I got all the talent, you see, and they got all the glory and "
"respect. It's all nonsense, though – I'll soon remedy this irksome situation...\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"인정 받고 영감을 받기 위해서지! {g|Restov}Restov{/g}에서 나는 그다지 인정 받지"
"는 않았어. 나는 재능이 있고 그들은 존경을 받았지. 하지만 나는 그들 보다 더 나아질 "
"거야...\\\""

msgctxt "a9620594-f3d1-4426-853f-8e6b8fbc2a20"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know, it's quite beautiful here! The view of a lake, surrounded by "
"picturesque green forest, were inspiration for a lovely brooch design... I do have "
"a sapphire, but no green jewels, and I've no idea who can help me with this. We're "
"surrounded by simpletons here, who know nothing of sublime matters... except for "
"you, of course!\\\" {n}Mim looks at you meaningfully.{/n}"
msgstr ""
"\\\"여기는 정말 아름다운 곳이야! 숲으로 둘러싸인 아름다운 호수의 풍경이 내게 영감"
"을 불어넣어... 나는 사파이어가 있지만 에메랄드는 아니야. 누군가 나를 도와주었으면 "
"좋겠군. 여기는 멍청이들 뿐이라서 내가 하는 일을 이해 못해... 너를 제외하고는 말이"
"야.\\\" {n}밈은 당신을 바라봅니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "428f1421-f129-4c0d-8d8f-c8a88300c6b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Aha!\\\" {n}The girl looks at you with eager impatience.{/n} \\\"So what about "
"my request?\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"아하!\\\" {n}그 여성은 열정적으로 당신을 봅니다.{/n} \\\"그래서 내가 부탁한 건 "
"가져왔어?\\\""

msgctxt "5a370afa-f97a-4e73-ad18-974d0a9c9b0a"
msgid ""
"\\\"For an emerald. I plan to make a brooch that will combine the hues of these "
"lands – the blue of the cold lake and the green of the young pines. I do have a "
"sapphire, but I'm missing a green jewel...\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"에메랄드. 나는 이 땅의 아름다움을 담고 있는 브로치를 만들 거야. 차가운 호수의 "
"푸른색과 어린 나무 숲의 초록색을 담은. 나는 사파이어는 있지만 에메랄드가 없어...\\"
"\""

msgctxt "475ec262-26a1-45f6-9078-54778450b0a6"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim's eyes flash.{/n} \\\"Look at that color! And the size! An excellent "
"item... Finally I'll be able to bring my idea to life!\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}밈의 눈빛이 반짝입니다.{/n} \\\"이 색 좀 봐! 그리고 크기도! 정말 놀라운 물건이"
"야... 드디어 내 아이디어를 실현할 수 있겠어!\\\""

msgctxt "c06d1928-998d-47e1-af78-bc118c9c815d"
msgid "\\\"I see...\\\" {n}Mim sighs.{/n}"
msgstr "\\\"그래...\\\" {n}밈이 한숨을 쉽니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "ebe4200c-e9c8-4e13-9cd0-db3f6b5a9538"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful. I am ready to remain here and work for {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}. I only need a place to live and work. I've brought "
"all the necessary tools. All I need is four walls and a roof – and a salary, of "
"course, I do need to eat. But I'll make it up to you!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"완벽해. 나는 여기에 남아 너를 위해 일할 준비가 되었어. 나는 이제 살 곳과 일할 "
"곳만 있으면 돼. 나는 필요한 도구들은 가져왔지. 이제는 벽과 지붕 그리고 월급만 있으"
"면 돼. 물론 먹고 살아야지. 너를 위해 일할게!\\\""

msgctxt "287f84ea-3e60-4a03-ac1c-56475bbb8754"
msgid ""
"\\\"Besides, I'm mortally tired of {g|Restov}Restov{/g} dust and grayness. And the "
"view from here to the {g|Tors of Levenies}Tors of Levenies{/g} is beyond compare! "
"Just look at those peaks! Such mysterious power in their easy dignity!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"나는 {g|Restov}Restov{/g}의 먼지와 회색 풍경이 질렸어. 그리고 여기 {g|Tors of "
"Levenies}Tors of Levenies{/g} 쪽의 풍경은 정말 대단해! 봉우리들은 놀랍지! 정말 경이"
"로운 모습이야!\\\""

msgctxt "9100d61f-44b1-4245-9332-a532c2079dca"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's a commotion in a village by {g|Lake Silverstep}lake Silverstep{/g}! An "
"artisan you know has gone missing – {d|Mim}Mim{/d} Wobblegander. A local shepherd "
"saw her walking with a backpack toward the {g|Tors of Levenies}Tors of Levenies{/"
"g}, but didn't ask her where she was going.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"{g|Lake Silverstep}lake Silverstep{/g} 마을에서 소동이 있었어! 네가 알던 장인 "
"{d|Mim}Mim{/d} Wobblegander가 사라졌지. 그 지역의 사람이 보았는데 짐을 가지고 {g|"
"Tors of Levenies}Tors of Levenies{/g} 쪽으로 갔지만 정확히 어디로 가는지는 모른다는"
"군.\\\""

msgctxt "af3c8c51-0c20-4f0e-97c0-fb6ee2ee9a3e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think you should look for her. It's been a few days. She might have gotten "
"herself into a messy situation. I wish I knew what or where!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"그녀를 찾아봐야겠어. 며칠 되었어. 아마 곤란한 상황에 처했을 수도 있어. 소식을 "
"알았으면 좋겠는데!\\\""

msgctxt "7641a032-bd5c-4ff9-b6ba-74e9e24dd7a5"
msgid "\\\"Great. I can't wait to see your next creation.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"훌륭해. 네가 다음에 무얼 만들지 기대돼.\\\""

msgctxt "30111810-07ff-485b-b1ec-d3c4ba02ac98"
msgid "\\\"I wanted to order something specific from you.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네가 특별한 물건을 만들어주었으면 좋겠어.\\\""

msgctxt "2bc2c379-3aa4-43b6-8a58-0283aa9fa7f8"
msgid "\\\"Thank you. But I don't need your services any more.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"고마워. 하지만 지금 네 도움은 필요 없어.\\\""

msgctxt "f567045d-bda8-4d35-89bf-a563df4dce2b"
msgid "\\\"A ring.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"반지.\\\""

msgctxt "25a104bb-f3d9-4774-b5d6-869f0b333e08"
msgid "\\\"An amulet.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"목걸이.\\\""

msgctxt "cee76815-2cbb-4e4f-ba32-474b74517e27"
msgid "\\\"A headband.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"헤어 밴드.\\\""

msgctxt "a462b2a4-89a6-404a-9a45-a76e3d7ad828"
msgid "\\\"I will trust your inspiration.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네 영감을 믿을게.\\\""

msgctxt "d9968543-25b7-493b-896f-0c815bf01024"
msgid ""
"{n}The {d|Mim}goldsmith's{/d} face shines.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}! Please accept this humble gift as a token of my deep "
"affection... respect... and whatever else the rules tell me I'm supposed to say. I "
"very much hope you like it – I worked hard on it!\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}{d|Mim}goldsmith's{/d}의 얼굴이 빛납니다.{/n} \\\"안녕! 내 영감을 표현한 이 선물"
"을 받아줘... 네가 좋아했으면 좋겠어. 나는 열심히 만들었어!\\\""

msgctxt "57f89c51-a69a-4510-87cc-589f862ec60e"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim wrinkles her nose.{/n} \\\"You can't dictate genius... But well, I suppose "
"it's your right to try. What can I do for you?\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}밈은 찡그립니다.{/n} \\\"나는 천재가 아니야... 하지만 그렇게 불러도 돼. 무얼 해"
"줄까?\\\""

msgctxt "56388c2d-b711-46e5-86b7-c74397fa0b7c"
msgid ""
"{n}The master craftsman nods at you pensively.{/n} \\\"All right... I think I have "
"a draft somewhere...\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}장인은 당신을 보고 끄덕입니다.{/n} \\\"좋아... 어딘가 설계도가 있는데...\\\""

msgctxt "df5d9e89-a1ad-4174-abcc-cfe8d36a7c45"
msgid ""
"{n}Smiling broadly, Mim looks away.{/n} \\\"Believe me, I won't disappoint you.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}환하게 웃으면서 밈은 먼 곳을 봅니다.{/n} \\\"나를 믿어. 실망하지 않을 거야.\\\""

msgctxt "690e309c-ea0f-436e-9238-e20ba0cc30b4"
msgid ""
"{n}The master craftsman raises an eyebrow, surprised.{/n} \\\"What, is my jewelry "
"suddenly not good enough? You think too much of yourself... It's sad, too – I was "
"only getting started. Anyway, I'm sure that I'll find a grateful patron in a more "
"civilized land, who can appreciate creative work...\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}장인은 놀랍니다.{/n} \\\"내 보석으로 충분하지 않다고? 너는 너 밖에 모르는구"
"나... 나는 놀랐어. 어쨌든 다른 곳에서 후원자를 찾아 떠날 거야...\\\""

msgctxt "e7d0853c-b4c4-4ad2-b344-f9c62aca5ddd"
msgid ""
"\\\"As long as I'm here... I had this brilliant idea. It's going to be something "
"really special. Unique. Perhaps the best thing I've ever done...\\\" {n}Mim "
"brushes a forelock from her face.{/n} \\\"It's only... I can't say what it's going "
"to be EXACTLY...\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"내가 여기에 있는 한... 좋은 생각이 있어. 정말 특별한 물건이 될 거야. 아마도 내"
"가 만든 것 중에 최고가 될 거야...\\\" {n}밈은 머리를 쓸어넘깁니다.{/n} \\\"이건... "
"정확히 말할 수는 없지만...\\\""

msgctxt "0081e4fc-5a3f-4633-87d4-8a4d02988ca3"
msgid ""
"\\\"But I know how to figure it out. But to do this, I'll need you to grant me "
"three wishes. One is already fulfilled – there are two more to go. Please visit me "
"in my workshop and I'll tell you more.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"나는 방법을 알아. 하지만 네가 나의 세가지 소원을 들어줘야 해. 하나는 이미 들어"
"주었어. 나머지 두개가 필요해. 내 작업실에 들르면 더 말해줄게.\\\""

msgctxt "24f0c788-73d3-4707-a62b-1e750db653a1"
msgid ""
"{n}The {d|Mim}jeweler{/d} bows before you wearily. Her face is full of pride, "
"despite the dark circles under her eyes.{/n} \\\"It's ready, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Don't even ask how long it took me to craft "
"this thing... But I like the result!\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}{d|Mim}jeweler{/d}은 힘 없이 인사합니다. 그녀의 얼굴은 피곤함에도 불구하고 자신"
"감이 넘칩니다.{/n} \\\"준비 되었어. 이걸 만드느라 얼마나 걸렸는지는 묻지 마... 좋"
"은 물건이 될 거야!\\\""

msgctxt "2934b9f5-fb39-4e1b-84ea-7ddf5f52f047"
msgid ""
"\\\"I also wanted to tell you that I'm finally ready to start working on my "
"masterpiece! My wishes have been granted! Now I know what I must set myself at "
"creation, and hope I will be able to thank you for your help. Unless you require "
"me to make something else first...\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"내 작품을 만들기 위한 준비가 되었어! 내 소원이 이루어졌어! 이제 나는 만들 준비"
"를 해야 해. 네게 고맙다는 인사를 하고 싶어. 다른 부탁은 다음에 해줘...\\\""

msgctxt "37029196-dd5c-4a59-92c7-71c75c2c78c1"
msgid ""
"\\\"That means I can create my brilliant design... I can't wait to see your "
"delight when it's ready!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"그걸로 나는 멋진 모습의 물건을 만들 수 있어... 모두 만들어졌을 때 네 표정이 궁"
"금하다!\\\""

msgctxt "1fc46800-95e5-4728-9779-7d1d856c82ec"
msgid "\\\"Who taught you goldwork?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7da682c-874f-4a94-a30b-29ddbbed41e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"You mentioned I could grant you three wishes to help you create your "
"masterpiece.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네 작품을 만들기 위해 내가 세가지 부탁을 들어주어야 한다고 했지?\\\""

msgctxt "58b74f92-2165-4e61-a5b0-ead8da46941f"
msgid "\\\"Why did you decide to move here from Restov?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"왜 레스토브에서 여기로 왔지?\\\""

msgctxt "423723f0-552a-4c56-bf3d-f225459e6729"
msgid ""
"\\\"Isn't it difficult for a master craftsman from the capital to get used to "
"living in the country?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"수도에서는 장인이 살기가 힘든가?\\\""

msgctxt "dda54590-5b80-43b5-aa17-6964f0782bf4"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나는 가야 해.\\\""

msgctxt "faa386c0-323a-4b6b-af68-3792478efa64"
msgid "[Shake the bottle] \\\"Look what I've got!\\\""
msgstr "[병을 흔듭니다] \\\"내가 가져왔어!\\\""

msgctxt "0c1ea281-6cde-43a8-8891-4e2d26d65242"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't get how an alcoholic beverage can help you find inspiration...\\\""
msgstr "\\\"술을 먹으면서 어떻게 영감을 얻겠다는 건지 모르겠지만...\\\""

msgctxt "ff8a6b0b-3e18-43e7-b5f6-87e2a2e5e21d"
msgid "\\\"I see.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"알았어.\\\""

msgctxt "2179f10e-024a-4827-b36c-4490cfb7df8b"
msgid "\\\"Why did you have to go to Talon Peak all alone?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"왜 탈론 봉우리에 혼자 가야 했지?\\\""

msgctxt "cd21c0a7-4754-4ab0-ac1d-6ef5c23e93ef"
msgid "\\\"How did you learn to make magical items?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"마법 아이템 만드는 건 어디서 배웠어?\\\""

msgctxt "0d780c26-ad77-4c2b-9e8d-77b0b3f9b586"
msgid "\\\"Do you have enough customers here?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"장사는 잘 되나\\\""

msgctxt "34d130e0-9c58-403d-a316-2f732c0acdb5"
msgid "\\\"I see. Can we talk about something else?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"알았어. 다른 이야기를 해볼까?\\\""

msgctxt "d5a8dba0-7656-443f-8956-143cfdfe4724"
msgid "\\\"What about your third wish? You haven't come up with one, have you?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"세번째 부탁은 뭐지? 아직 생각 못 했어?\\\""

msgctxt "8c06e54c-a495-4895-a1e4-0b1712391fca"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Mim}Mim{/d} blinks vacantly.{/n} \\\"Oh, it's you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}. It's good to see you. What can I do for you?\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}{d|Mim}Mim{/d}는 눈을 깜빡입니다.{/n} \\\"오. 왔구나. 만나서 반가워. 뭐가 필요"
"해?\\\""

msgctxt "f17d5ac0-87a9-47e3-9ffb-8eb2ef0e62d7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ah, yes. That's very true. You've granted my first wish. As to the second... "
"They say that ink is the blood of science. In that case, alcohol is the blood of "
"creation.\\\" {n} The girl gives you a provocative look.{/n}"
msgstr ""
"\\\"아. 그래. 맞아. 네가 내 부탁 하나를 들어주었지. 두번째는... 누군가 잉크는 과학"
"의 피라는군. 그렇다면 창조의 피는 술이야.\\\" {n} 여성은 도발적으로 당신을 봅니다."
"{/n}"

msgctxt "3cc299d5-f301-4c3d-8f33-9c25fa3658e9"
msgid ""
"\\\"My father is a successful watchmaker. His shop supplies the richest families "
"of {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}. When I grew up and it was time to teach me, he decided to "
"'move from simple to complicated' – to start with the shell, then move on to "
"mechanisms. I learned how to make a golden chain, how to cast a perfectly smooth "
"case, how to etch and ornament and encrust with jewels... and entirely lost "
"interest in springs and gears!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"우리 아버지는 시계 제작자였어. 그의 가게에 {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}의 귀족들이 찾고"
"는 했지. 내가 컸을 때 아버지는 간단한 것부터 가르쳤어. 시계줄 부터 내부의 복잡한 장"
"치까지. 나는 어떻게 하면 시계가 부드럽게 가는지 시계를 어떻게 꾸미는지에 대해 배웠"
"어... 그리고 스프링과 기어 만드는 법을 배울 때 흥미를 완전히 잃어버렸지!\\\""

msgctxt "c58fa4e3-a862-470e-9dbc-44eac5b7e5ee"
msgid ""
"\\\"I didn't decide any such thing. I just realized all my hair will go gray of "
"boredom if I spend even one more day in {g|Restov}Restov's{/g} mud. I explained it "
"to my father, packed my things and struck off, over the hills and far away. I "
"stopped here mostly because for the scenery. The {g|Tors of Levenies}Tors of "
"Levenies{/g} are the most beautiful thing I have ever seen! I wish I could climb "
"{g|Talon Peak}Talon Peak{/g}... but I can't seem to find the time. And when I do "
"get a free day, the weather is always bad.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"나는 어떤 것도 결정하지 않았어. 나는 이대로 가다간 레스토브에서 늙어죽겠다는 생"
"각이 들었어. 나는 아버지를 설득하며 짐을 싸서 떠나겠다고 했지. 여기는 경치가 좋아"
"서 머물게 된 거야. {g|Tors of Levenies}Tors of Levenies{/g}는 최고의 경치를 자랑하"
"지! 탈론 봉우리에도 가보았으면 좋겠어... 하지만 아직 시간이 없어. 쉬는 날 날씨가 좋"
"으면 가 보려고.\\\""

msgctxt "a5a9543f-34c8-4a32-8230-53c5f4b870ee"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim sniffs.{/n} \\\"Do you mean, getting used to fresh air and clean water? To "
"wearing simple comfortable clothes every day and forgetting about make up? What "
"about not having to watch out for stinky horse piles and puddles wherever you "
"step? Oh yes, it's tough out here.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}밈은 코웃음을 칩니다.{/n} \\\"신선한 공기와 깨끗한 물에 적응하면 어떻겠냐고? 평"
"범한 옷을 입고 화장 없이 돌아다녀 보라고? 나는 길거리에 말 똥을 밟을 일이 없어서 너"
"무나 좋아. 바깥에서 살기란 너무 거칠어.\\\""

msgctxt "ffd58797-e75c-477e-846a-e3412b6c8eee"
msgid ""
"\\\"Bring me a bottle, if you please. Of either. It will fill my restless creative "
"spirit! Just one gulp, and I will pierce the abyss of existence with a stare... "
"sink down into the bottom of my soul... and finally comprehend what the hell I've "
"been trying to drag from it, into the world!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"병을 넘겨줘. 내 창작 욕구가 불타오를 거야! 한모금 삼키면 사물의 본질을 꿰뚫어보"
"는 통찰력이 생기지... 내 영혼이 바닥으로 고꾸라지는 기분이란... 그리고는 내가 만들"
"려는 것을 세상 밖으로 꺼낼 수 있게 될 거야!\\\""

msgctxt "e21cd1a2-445e-4818-bf6b-dec1b0ef4cb0"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl has an eager gleam in her eyes.{/n} \\\"Oh, I've been waiting for so "
"long! Thank you so much, {name}... um... {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|"
"Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}여성은 눈을 반짝입니다.{/n} \\\"오. 너무 오래 기다렸어! 정말 고마워...!\\\""

msgctxt "3fdd05d3-9052-4c51-998a-1d93abd34f70"
msgid ""
"\\\"In that case, you know nothing about the work of an artist, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! But no matter, everyone has their own "
"calling...\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"그렇다면 너는 예술 작품에 대해서는 아무것도 모르는구나! 모두 각자의 일이 있는 "
"법이지...\\\""

msgctxt "6cdaaaa2-4d39-4c0b-8201-48d73b77e0b3"
msgid "{n}Mim nods and looks at you expectantly.{/n}"
msgstr "{n}밈은 끄덕이고는 무언가 기대한다는 듯 당신을 봅니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "df604333-18c3-4937-bdce-12ef3ddfefa9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for asking, but your own orders are quite enough for me! I'm an "
"artist, not a craftsman. I don't feel the slightest desire to drudge over "
"tasteless trinkets for the wives of merchants and elderly pleasure seekers. "
"Besides, they wouldn't be able to afford my finest creations anyway...\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"물어봐주어 고마워. 네 주문을 받아들일게! 나는 장인이 아니라 예술가니까. 나는 돈"
"많은 상인의 부인이나 장신구를 수집하는 사람들의 물건을 만들어주며 시간을 보내고 싶"
"지는 않아. 그들은 내 작품을 가질 자격이 되지 않지...\\\""

msgctxt "adb15f5e-2b03-48bb-bfd9-6d07e0004b27"
msgid ""
"\\\"Father insisted, once he realized I wasn't going to work with mechanisms. He "
"said I needed 'to have at least some practical skill', and arranged my "
"apprenticeship with his old client – an grumpy old professor of transmutation. I "
"pouted for a long time, but now I'm grateful – that knowledge has actually come in "
"quite useful.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"아버지는 말하셨어. 그 때 나는 시계의 장치 만드는 방법을 이해하지 못했을 때였"
"지. 나는 최소한 쓸만한 기술은 얻어야 한다면서 나를 다른 고객이 가르치게 했어. 그는 "
"심술 궂은 교수였지. 나는 속상했지만 감사하기도 해. 그가 가르쳐준 기술이 유용했으니"
"까.\\\""

msgctxt "2285bb28-3f4d-49d4-a8c8-f26677df6394"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmm?\\\" {n}It seems that Mim has again been carried away by the sight of the "
"mountains.{/n} \\\"Oh yes, of course... Uhh... about what?\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"음?\\\" {n}밈은 산의 경치를 감상하는 것 같습니다.{/n} \\\"오. 그래. 맞아... 뭐"
"라고 그랬지?\\\""

msgctxt "a77a08c4-bbe2-4c99-be61-5b92cd4825c1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I... I don't completely understand it myself... I woke up that morning and "
"thought – it's now or never.\\\" {n}Mim sighs and shrugs.{/n} \\\"And it turns out "
"I was right!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"나는... 완전히 이해 못 했어... 나는 아침에 일어나 지금 아니면 기회가 없다고 생"
"각했지.\\\" {n}밈은 한숨을 쉬고는 어깨를 으쓱합니다.{/n} \\\"그리고 내 결정이 맞았"
"던 거야!\\\""

msgctxt "f34f530d-816b-461d-8f5f-06e3407702ba"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim laughs.{/n} \\\"I wish I knew the answer! But I never gave the decision a "
"second thought. I just grabbed my backpack and stepped out. And it all turned out "
"for the best!\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}밈이 웃습니다.{/n} \\\"내가 답을 알았으면 했어! 하지만 나는 내 생각을 바꾸지 않"
"았지. 나는 짐을 싸고 집을 떠났어. 그리고 그 결정은 최선이었지!\\\""

msgctxt "120009ab-2c9e-4fff-acb8-966eaae36368"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have to admit, I have no idea what my third wish should be. I'll tell you as "
"soon as I come up with something. Now if you'll excuse me – art can't wait!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"인정해야겠네. 내 세번째 부탁이 뭔지는 모르겠어. 생각나면 말해줄게. 이제 실례할"
"게. 예술 작업은 바쁘거든!\\\""

msgctxt "917cf997-373c-4bc9-8f34-8f830416b5c9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not yet. You can't rush the delicate movements of the soul. I can feel it "
"growing within me, and that's all for now.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"아직이야. 부추긴다고 작품이 나오는 건 아니야. 내 안에서 작품의 모습이 그려져. "
"이제는 그 모습이 완전히 그려졌고.\\\""

msgctxt "9e4a7e09-6dca-4886-8a77-8e58a297af99"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't mean the ordinary tavern booze. I need something delicate... rare... "
"like... like berry wine from {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}! Or even... Oh lord! Elven "
"absinth!\\\" {n}She slaps her head, freezes for a second – and starts speaking "
"faster and faster, and waving her hands in excitement.{/n} \\\"Why, of course! Why "
"didn't I think of that? Elves! They're so close to the nature. To be one with "
"nature! That's the unity I'm looking for!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"평범한 술집의 술을 말하는 게 아니야. 나는 맛있는 술을 원해... 귀하고... 쿄닌의 "
"와인이었으면 좋겠어! 아니면... 오! 엘프 압생트는 어떨까!\\\" {n}그녀는 자신의 머리"
"를 때리더니 잠시 얼어붙습니다. 그리고는 흥분해서 계속해서 말합니다.{/n} \\\"맞아! "
"왜 그 생각을 못했지! 엘프야! 엘프는 자연과 가장 가까운 존재지. 엘프가 내 영감을 불"
"어넣을 수 있어!\\\""

msgctxt "efe9e1f4-2239-4919-833b-77f06d71fbd0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not all of us were born for adventure, Mim. You'd better go back home.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"모두 모험을 하도록 태어나지는 않았어. 너는 그냥 집에 가는 게 좋겠다.\\\""

msgctxt "15df164e-1d57-46dc-b439-dbcc79ddda83"
msgid ""
"\\\"Everyone makes mistakes. But some give up, while others stand up and go on! "
"I'm going to climb this mountain, no matter what it takes. What about you?\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"모두가 실수를 하지. 누군가는 포기하지만 다른 사람들은 계속해서 버텨! 나는 무슨 "
"일이 있어도 산을 오르겠다고 생각했어. 너는 어때?\\\""

msgctxt "da3f6fa9-2595-47ac-8877-510d010b3aac"
msgid "\\\"What are you doing here?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"여기서 뭐해?\\\""

msgctxt "18b2cbf9-09de-4952-a6ca-d14155f9a171"
msgid "\\\"What's the matter here?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"여기서 뭐해?\\\""

msgctxt "fb15b843-3528-49e3-8207-acd0722538eb"
msgid "[Use magic] \\\"I have just the spell for you...\\\""
msgstr "[마법을 사용합니다] \\\"너에게 줄 마법이있어...\\\""

msgctxt "d662af16-5d10-4e23-b550-14776902bbdd"
msgid "\\\"Let me see.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"어디 보자.\\\""

msgctxt "d5c45f43-ec0e-4b9c-9714-d62536b9726b"
msgid "\\\"I can't help you right now.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"지금은 도와줄 수 없어.\\\""

msgctxt "1dda15f0-e67c-4240-be4b-ecb5aac73397"
msgid ""
"[Try fixing the dislocated joint] \\\"You didn't break your ankle, you twisted it. "
"Hold on for a second, all right?\\\""
msgstr ""
"[빠진 곳을 고치며] \\\"발목이 부러지지는 않고 뒤틀린 것 뿐이야. 잠깐 기다려.\\\""

msgctxt "b1d5a4e0-1468-4cdf-92ac-fb02662f5de6"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's no fracture – it's just dislocated. But I'm not sure I can fix it "
"myself...\\\""
msgstr "\\\"금 간 곳은 없어. 탈골된 것이지. 하지만 고칠 수 있을지는 모르겠군...\\\""

msgctxt "66b0564b-2cb9-4935-b2a9-ff1aebe69151"
msgid "\\\"About your ankle...\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네 발목 말이지...\\\""

msgctxt "172d525c-9a13-47a9-ae40-83f6629e8227"
msgid "Apologized for hurting Mim while trying to heal her leg."
msgstr "그녀의 다리를 고치려다 다치게 한 것을 사과합니다."

msgctxt "db881bf1-4cf7-4479-9fe6-c4006bb7173c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm sorry, I was trying to set it back in its socket. But it seems too badly "
"twisted.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"미안해. 나는 그저 뼈를 되돌리려던 것 뿐인데. 너무 많이 뒤틀린 것 같아.\\\""

msgctxt "521fc49e-82b2-4bdb-ae25-eb2c05492086"
msgid "Hurt Mim while trying to heal her leg – and laughed it off."
msgstr "그녀의 다리를 치료하다 말고 다치게 하고는 웃어넘겼습니다."

msgctxt "96c64671-8c52-4497-9a00-9487b42be928"
msgid "\\\"Ouch. That must have hurt.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"아이고. 아팠겠다.\\\""

msgctxt "a1ad8e29-07ee-4196-a9d6-34ab27e263b0"
msgid "Threatened to cut out Mim's tongue."
msgstr "밈의 입을 꿰메버리겠다고 협박합니다."

msgctxt "8ccb7283-141b-4704-bbe5-4c5ee45c116f"
msgid "\\\"Watch your tongue if you want to keep it.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"꿰메버리기 전에 입조심하는 게 좋을 거야.\\\""

msgctxt "f6d22c87-4fab-4feb-9ee6-f19aaeef71a5"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나는 가야 해.\\\""

msgctxt "85f978a6-9df3-4ff7-999d-2fd28b5295d6"
msgid "\\\"You decided to go on, even after you saw giant spiders?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"거대 거미를 보고서도 계속해서 가겠다는 거지?\\\""

msgctxt "c1bf60c9-8e6d-46d9-b2c5-b0c02a6c275f"
msgid "\\\"It's... it's you!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그건... 너야!\\\""

msgctxt "0dd106e3-73ff-4ad3-9f41-e0aaf6482c3d"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Mim}Mim's{/d} clothes are dirty, and her hair is matted.{/n} \\\"Good gods! "
"I feared I would... I would have to stay... here forever...\\\" {n}Tears are "
"running down her dirty cheeks, leaving light trails on her skin.{/n}"
msgstr ""
"{n}{d|Mim}Mim's{/d}의 옷은 더러웠고 그녀의 머리는 지저분해졌습니다.{/n} \\\"신이시"
"여! 아 제발... 나는 머물러야 해... 여기서 영원히...\\\" {n}눈물이 그녀의 더러운 뺨"
"에 흘렀고 눈물 자국을 남깁니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "f320e983-97a6-43ee-9a36-724407fd7a17"
msgid ""
"\\\"I... I wanted to climb {g|Talon Peak}Talon Peak{/g}. It was... a sudden "
"decision. I just thought, why put it off? Why ask for someone else to help, like I "
"always do? Why can't I just get my wish by myself? After all, I left father so I "
"could achieve everything on my own. So, I decided to climb the mountain alone. "
"Skies above, my pride nearly sent me to my grave!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"나는... {g|Talon Peak}Talon Peak{/g}에 오르고 싶었어. 그건... 갑작스러운 결정이"
"었어. 나는 왜 안 되냐고, 다른 사람에게 부탁하자고 생각했지. 결국 나는 아버지를 떠나"
"서 모든 걸 스스로 하기로 했어. 그래서 나는 산에 혼자 오르기로 결정한 거야. 내 자존"
"심 때문에 무덤으로 갈 뻔했네!\\\""

msgctxt "7d27a36b-9b7d-4da4-be37-6e65ede5e3ad"
msgid ""
"{n}A smile appears on Mim's pale face.{/n} \\\"After all, what good would an "
"ascent be if there weren't any obstacles along the way? I'm not giving up! Let's "
"go! To the top! You're coming with me, right?\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}밈의 창백한 얼굴에는 웃음이 나타납니다.{/n} \\\"결국. 어려움이 없다면 오르막이 "
"좋은 이유가 없지. 나는 포기하지 않아! 가자! 꼭대기로! 나와 같이 갈 거지?\\\""

msgctxt "21d7cce7-b0af-4a71-8149-8543992919b3"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim lowers her head and sighs heavily.{/n} \\\"You're... you're right. I should "
"know that my place is in the workshop with my tools. Just show me the way, and "
"I'll be off.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}밈은 고개를 숙이며 한숨을 쉽니다.{/n} \\\"너는... 네가 맞아. 나는 내 도구들과 함"
"께 작업장에 남아야지. 알겠어.\\\""

msgctxt "932a0e63-0255-4440-a9f3-3365d011f937"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think I broke my ankle... I was fighting some spiders, and stepped on a "
"stone, and it slipped, and I tripped and fell, and hit my ankle... I managed to "
"drive away the beasts, but it's still messed up. It hurts too much to walk on. I "
"crawled for several hours, but I couldn't...\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"발목이 부러진 것 같아... 거미와 싸우다가 돌을 밟아서 넘어져 발을 다쳤어... 짐승"
"을 쫓아냈지만 여전히 힘들어. 걸어가기는 너무 힘들어. 나는 몇시간을 걸어갔지만 못 걷"
"겠어...\\\""

msgctxt "d7c99a73-e9e6-46aa-b90c-095ed8102e6e"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim relaxes her shoulders in relief.{/n} \\\"Whew... That's much better. Thank "
"you so much!\\\""
msgstr "{n}밈은 안도로 어깨가 늘어집니다.{/n} \\\"휴... 훨씬 낫다. 정말 고마워!\\\""

msgctxt "fb094ddd-5b22-4c57-be43-151c3636a097"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim's ankle is swollen and red. It looks more like a dislocation than a "
"fracture. You palpate the area to find the bone intact.{/n}"
msgstr ""
"{n}밈의 발목은 부풀어올라 붉어졌습니다. 금이 간 것보다는 탈골된 것 같습니다. 당신"
"은 뼈가 멀쩡한지 니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "918cbfc0-679b-4069-b2fe-7db3e59ee3f0"
msgid "\\\"Think of something, please...\\\""
msgstr "\\\"음. 저기...\\\""

msgctxt "2ae140f6-aa8a-4a67-a734-9bfcc86f07ce"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim's ankle looks swollen and red. You'll need help of an expert medic...{/n}"
msgstr ""
"{n}밈의 발목은 부풀어올라 붉어졌습니다. 당신은 전문 의료사의 도움이 필요합니다...{/"
"n}"

msgctxt "573f263e-9249-4e73-a410-fe7d83c18d18"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wait, what... OUCH!\\\" {n}The joint clicks back into place.{/n} \\\"Oh... "
"well... It feels better... Much better! Thank you very much! Here, I'll try to get "
"up...\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"잠깐... 아야!\\\" {n}탈골된 부분에서 소리가 납니다.{/n} \\\"오... 좋아... 기분"
"이 나아졌어... 훨씬 좋아! 정말 고마워! 일어나볼게...\\\""

msgctxt "c1bdaac1-a4b7-412a-9f16-7ac398535073"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wait, what... OUCH! Devil's mercy, that hurts! What the hell do you think "
"you're doing?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"잠깐... 아야! 아파! 뭐하려고 하는 거야?\\\""

msgctxt "b98a32f6-3ba8-439a-a68b-2b51405f2d37"
msgid "{n}Mim looks away.{/n} \\\"I see. Well, thanks for trying to help.\\\""
msgstr "{n}밈이 다른 곳을 봅니다.{/n} \\\"알았어. 도와주어 고마워.\\\""

msgctxt "191a4fc6-5025-496f-be32-7837651ad75a"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim inhales, then breathes out slowly.{/n} \\\"Just... don't. All right?\\\""
msgstr "{n}밈이 천천히 한숨을 쉽니다.{/n} \\\"... 하지마. 알겠어?\\\""

msgctxt "fe9091d1-6133-4bd1-8ff2-c23c1ffdcab6"
msgid "\\\"So, the bones are intact... So that's good. I think.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"뼈가 멀쩡한 것 같은데... 괜찮은 것 같아.\\\""

msgctxt "1526769c-feae-47a4-923b-ffb2192ccbae"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim flinches and lowers her head.{/n} \\\"I'm sorry, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}. The pain is clouding my judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}밈은 고개를 숙입니다.{/n} \\\"미안해. 힘들어서 판단력이 흐려지는 것 같아.\\\""

msgctxt "de355536-6263-4ce1-adcc-7a412ba438eb"
msgid "{n}Mim looks at you with hope.{/n}"
msgstr "{n}밈은 기대를 담아 당신을 봅니다.{/n}"

msgctxt "5de8196e-63dc-4db4-b966-9f07a4300ef6"
msgid "\\\"Yes... I can walk now. But where should I go?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그래... 이제 걸을 수 있어. 하지만 어디로 가야 하지?\\\""

msgctxt "70532c7c-e88d-4468-bab7-7848fff2b895"
msgid ""
"\\\"Don't get me wrong, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. "
"I... I suddenly realized what my third wish would be. What I need to do, to find "
"my inspiration. I must climb {g|Talon Peak}Talon Peak{/g}! To see the world from "
"that height, to rise above myself... that's what my soul has been craving! But I "
"don't know if I can make it.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"오해하지 마. 나는... 갑자기 세번째 부탁이 떠올랐어. 내 영감을 찾기 위해 필요한 "
"세번째 것을 찾았어. 나는 {g|Talon Peak}Talon Peak{/g}로 올라야 해! 그 높이에서 세계"
"를 보고 나 자신을 높이는 거야... 그게 내 영혼이 필요로 한 것이었어! 하지만 할 수 있"
"을지 모르겠어.\\\""

msgctxt "21f4ec23-e69e-436d-a467-c7ff897e523b"
msgid "\\\"For heaven's sake, come back soon!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"곧 돌아와야 해!\\\""

msgctxt "c791554d-d8be-4e63-98d4-1515d611602c"
msgid ""
"{n}Mim's face turns red.{/n} \\\"I'm a mage! Before I tripped, I was handling them "
"just fine! They were still afraid to attack, the spineless creeps...\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}밈의 얼굴이 붉어집니다.{/n} \\\"나는 마법사야! 넘어지기 전에 손을 써뒀어! 그 녀"
"석들은 여전히 공격하기에는 무서운 녀석들이야...\\\""

msgctxt "63ce21d4-938e-4ccb-bb42-ec44ba2d7b24"
msgid "\\\"You fools! What is this, a revolt?! Drop your weapons!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"멍청아! 이게 뭐야?! 무기 내려!\\\""

msgctxt "050b30c3-70c1-4ad8-b074-a01435ebfd06"
msgid ""
"\\\"Without the support of the throne, we're no militia — we're just plain "
"thieves! That won't do!''"
msgstr "\\\"왕의 도움 없이 우리는 군인도 아니고 그냥 도둑일 뿐이야! 소용 없어!''"

msgctxt "6a4ac4a0-d04d-4d53-ad3b-775625277275"
msgid "\\\"There will be no mutiny!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"반란은 없다!\\\""

msgctxt "b9bc598e-1d8f-484e-b093-1288738d1ae2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Run back to your capital! This is my home, and I know best how to protect the "
"law here! You got that?!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"수도로 돌아가! 여기는 내 집이고 너희는 법을 지켜야 해! 알겠어?!\\\""

msgctxt "c611bd5f-fb26-40dc-99b2-6d1c9b7d09d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"What good is the state to us? We're the militia. We can fight for ourselves!\\"
"\""
msgstr "\\\"수도가 무슨 소용이야? 우리는 군인이다. 우리가 알아서 싸워!\\\""

msgctxt "cf1784bb-0c87-48a8-975d-b9aea469694a"
msgid "\\\"We plough this land! We should rule it as well!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"우리가 이 땅을 일궜다! 우리가 지배하는 건 당연해!\\\""

msgctxt "a85cab93-06da-4910-8d28-9f9c9b167e0c"
msgid "\\\"We're better off on our own!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"가는 게 낫겠어!\\\""

msgctxt "4da229c1-317a-479d-8d5a-5668a46dfb7a"
msgid "\\\"Why are we even wasting time on them? Let's kill these dogs!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"왜 우리가 시간을 버려야 하는 거지? 이 녀석들을 죽이자!\\\""

msgctxt "a4540c2c-99bc-405d-98e4-e14110d08123"
msgid "\\\"They're coming at us! Get ready, lads!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그들이 우리에게 온다! 준비해!\\\""

msgctxt "1491a55d-f418-46ee-a94a-e364b74200f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Drive off the rabble-rousers! We stand with the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}!"
"\\\""
msgstr "\\\"저리 꺼져라! 우리는 {name}도 있다!\\\""

msgctxt "91c16c94-ceeb-4ca8-badc-d1a3f9e7f82f"
msgid "\\\"Watch out, you scoundrels! It's the gallows for you!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"조심해. 멍청이들아! 교수대에 보내주마!\\\""

msgctxt "4e84315e-b2f7-4c00-9550-5619191ccded"
msgid "\\\"Drop your weapons! In the name of the law!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"무기를 버려라! 법의 이름 아래에!\\\""

msgctxt "c0fadcc8-76e3-4031-86bb-ca2bad2ab6c0"
msgid ""
"\\\"We stand for our homes, brothers! Hit them hard! Varnhold will be ours!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"우리는 집을 지키는 것이다! 그들을 공격하라! 반홀드는 우리 것이다!\\\""

msgctxt "fc96a047-08b5-47bd-975b-5501eda918be"
msgid ""
"\\\"For free Varnhold! Down with the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} and {mf|his|"
"her} dogs!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"자유로운 반홀드를 위해! {name}도 끝이다!\\\""

msgctxt "a1bb30ea-5543-4f89-bf72-e2f7cb9d2ef6"
msgid ""
"\\\"What the hell are you doing?! We're fighting for the same thing! For freedom! "
"For liberty!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"여기서 뭐하는 거야?! 우리는 같은 목적으로 싸우는 거야! 자유를 위해서!\\\""

msgctxt "2d51ec74-6d3d-4a5b-9da5-1b6ea55493cb"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나는 가야 해.\\\""

msgctxt "4bdc57dc-136b-422d-b6fa-aed8bcd601b1"
msgid "\\\"So, you were in a gang once?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1f0996b-e5cf-438a-9dc1-dd96f558e210"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about yourself.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"너에 대해 말해줘.\\\""

msgctxt "5d6c6ab6-9f0a-4ffc-a253-d6fe9783bd16"
msgid "\\\"I'd like to know more about your craft.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"너의 작품에 대해 더 알고 싶어.\\\""

msgctxt "0bf9f27c-25c6-41df-ae36-d192a6e12e99"
msgid "\\\"Why have you chosen to settle in Varnhold?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"왜 반홀드에 정착하기로 했지?\\\""

msgctxt "99f4cacd-2c9a-472c-9af6-82a11fc45891"
msgid "\\\"How's the militia doing?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"반홀드 민병대는 어때?\\\""

msgctxt "85c0ad11-1acd-4baa-b82c-06aa5b8e0b36"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Tirval}Tirval{/d} greets you with a friendly smile.{/n} \\\"Welcome! We've "
"just brought in a couple of new recruits. The guards are teaching them all they "
"need to know about standing night watch. And I'm busy making armor for the boys. "
"No one should fight bandits with a bare chest. Leather armor can do wonders. — It "
"won't make a lot of noise and give away your ambush, but it will protect you just "
"fine from a blade.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}{d|Tirval}Tirval{/d}은 친근한 미소로 당신을 봅니다.{/n} \\\"어서와! 여기 새로운 "
"신병 둘이 생겼군. 경비들이 야간 경비에 필요한 것을 그들에게 교육하고 있어. 나는 소"
"년들을 위해 갑옷을 만들어주느라 바빠. 도적과 싸우는데 갑옷은 있어야지. 가죽 갑옷이 "
"좋아. 소음도 나지 않고 매복하기에도 좋지만 검으로부터 보호도 할 수 있으니까.\\\""

msgctxt "828f5ed9-5285-4e49-a276-6db1db6745f3"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! What a surprise! It is "
"good to see you!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"오! {name}! 이럴 수가! 만나서 반가워!\\\""

msgctxt "0798d844-c3ff-4cb9-8e85-ec64713edba3"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Tirval}Tirval{/d} gives a sour grin.{/n} \\\"Not much to tell, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. And it's not a pretty story. I grew "
"up on the street in Daggermark. Not the best place to live, in case you didn't "
"know that already – especially for lonely children. But life teaches us a lot of "
"things. I was able to survive, then got involved with a gang and built up my life "
"from there, all on my own — not on my mom and dad's sweat and blood, or some fancy "
"title and a bunch of gold.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}{d|Tirval}Tirval{/d}은 당신에게 씁쓸한 미소를 짓습니다.{/n} \\\"별로 할 말은 없"
"어. 굉장한 이야기도 없지. 나는 Daggermark 길바닥에서 자랐어. 살기 좋은 동네는 아니"
"지. 특히 외로운 아이들에게는 말이야. 하지만 살면서 많은 것을 배울 수 있었어. 나는 "
"결국 살아남았고 어떤 패거리와 함께 하며 부모 없이 내 스스로 인생을 살아갔지. 돈이"
"나 명예도 없이 말이야.\\\""

msgctxt "cd48c5ed-ca08-429a-b881-be00341392d8"
msgid ""
"{n}Tirval gives you a suspicious look, but then chuckles and waves it off.{/n} \\"
"\"Oh yes, the mistakes of youth… There a lot of youngsters in Daggermark. Those "
"who can think on their feet join in packs. Street gangs fooling around, putting "
"the squeeze on merchants, all that. But that's long behind me now. And besides, we "
"never messed anyone over. Or better to say – we kept things in order. If anybody "
"tried to lean on our neighbors or started misbehaving, we took them in hand.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}Tirval은 당신을 의심스러운 눈길로 보지만 손을 흔들며 웃습니다.{/n} \\\"오. 그"
"래. 어린 시절의 실수였지... Daggermark에는 고아들이 많았으니까. 어쩔 수 없이 패거리"
"에 들어갔지. 깡패들은 돌아다니며 상인들의 돈을 갈취했어. 하지만 오래 전의 일이야. "
"그리고 우리는 누구도 괴롭히지 않았어. 우리는 질서를 지켰다고 할 수 있지. 누군가 우"
"리 이웃을 괴롭히려고 했다면 막아줬으니까.\\\""

msgctxt "863b14c7-3211-47b3-abc1-4d140b5540cf"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-elf's eyes glisten and dance.{/n} \\\"Leatherworking, you mean? With "
"pleasure. You see, the trick is to remove the hide so that the tendons don't stick "
"to it. Otherwise it will go brittle. Then you only need patience. — You let it "
"rest, you drench it in saltwater. That way you get sturdy leather – hard as wood, "
"but still flexible. If you wear that, you can rest easy even with some bastard "
"poking you with a blade. It's not steel, of course, but you won't be running "
"around the woods all day in steel – or sneaking up on someone from behind!"
msgstr ""
"{n}하프엘프의 눈이 빛납니다.{/n} \\\"가죽세공이라고 했어? 물론 좋지. 나의 비결은 살"
"코기에서 가죽을 제거하는 거야. 그렇지 않으면 다루기 힘들어. 인내심이 필요하지. 소금"
"물에 담구면 단단한 가죽이 만들어지지. 나무처럼 단단하지만 여전히 유연하지. 그걸 입"
"으면 칼에 찔려도 문제 없을 거야. 쇠가 아니라서 숲을 돌아다니고 적을 추적할 수도 있"
"지.\\\""

msgctxt "1318a31c-788f-41ec-9817-50915b75283f"
msgid ""
"\\\"People knew they could trust me, and that I've got my head screwed on right. "
"There were some who were ready to follow me – and I even thought about becoming a "
"bandit myself, but…\\\" {n}Tirval frowns, as if she remembered something shameful "
"and unpleasant.{/n} \\\"It wasn't meant to be, that's all. I left Daggermark, "
"traveled around a bit. At first I tried hunting, but then I picked up leatherwork. "
"And as it turns out, I'm pretty good at it. Become a real master, in fact. That "
"about covers it I guess.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"그들은 나를 믿었지. 이미 나를 따르고 있는 사람들도 있었어. 나는 도적이 되리라"
"는 생각도 했으니까. 하지만...\\\" {n}Tirval은 부끄러운 기억을 떠올리듯 얼굴을 찌푸"
"립니다.{/n} \\\"결국은 그렇게 되지 않았어. 나는 대거마크를 떠나 여행을 했지. 처음에"
"는 사냥도 했지만 가죽세공을 하기로 했어. 그런데 그게 나의 적성에 맞았지. 나는 장인"
"이 되었어.\\\""

msgctxt "d4c4f6e3-c4d5-4ccd-9b36-8df297efdd84"
msgid ""
"\\\"And then there's all the other equipment you need to survive a day in the "
"woods, or on the dark streets — and it's all made of leather as well. Without a "
"good pair of boots, the first snake will get you, if you haven't drowned in some "
"swamp already. And without gloves, every poisonous bush will leave its nasty marks "
"on your hands. And I won't even get started on belts — the most useful thing you "
"own, if you don't want to lose all your things while you're on the run. All in "
"all, it's a good craft to know — and it keeps bread on the table.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"숲이나 어두운 길목에서 생존하기 좋은 장비들도 있지. 모두 가죽으로 만든 거야. 좋"
"은 신발이 없으면 늪지를 피한다고 해도 우선 뱀에게 물리지. 장갑이 없으면 독풀에 손"
"이 상할 거야. 그리고 벨트가 가장 유용한 것인데 벨트가 있어야 도망칠 때 물건을 잃어"
"버리지 않아. 모두 좋은 기술들이고 유용한 것들이야.\\\""

msgctxt "dd235ad2-0b2b-45bd-9616-64e16e8b6bf8"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl's face darkens as she turns her eyes to the ground in silence.{/n} \\"
"\"I killed the wrong man. I thought he was a villain. A threat to those who were "
"under my protection. I couldn't forgive myself, so I left. I went wherever the "
"road would take me. As for Varnhold... I was just passing through when I suddenly "
"felt — 'this is it'. It felt like the place I could start a new life. An honest "
"life, a life lived by the law. And here I am.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}여성의 얼굴은 어두워집니다.{/n} \\\"엄한 사람을 죽였어. 그 사람이 악당이라고 생"
"각했는데. 내가 보호하는 사람들을 위협하는 자라고 생각했지. 나는 내 자신을 믿을 수 "
"없어서 떠났지. 그래서 갈 수 있는 어디든 돌아다녔어. 반홀드는... 내가 있어야 할 곳이"
"라고 느껴졌어. 새로운 삶을 시작할 수 있을 것 같았지. 법을 지키며 정직하게 사는 삶 "
"말이야. 그래서 정착했어.\\\""

msgctxt "c055dc37-4342-48a5-9950-60a0d277e758"
msgid ""
"\\\"Things have quieted down a bit. As soon as you showed force, everyone who used "
"to speak out turned quiet and obedient. Finally we're serving the people instead "
"of arguing among ourselves!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"상황이 많이 바뀌었어. 네가 힘을 행사하자 말하던 사람들이 조용해지고 복종하기 시"
"작했지. 마침내 우리는 다투는 대신 사람들을 지키게 된 거야!\\\""

msgctxt "5c5ea592-e15c-4cd0-abec-123dc288c586"
msgid ""
"\\\"Never been better, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! "
"Ever since we ran off the bandits from these lands, no other troublemakers have "
"been bold enough to set foot here. Peace and quiet rule in Varnhold — just as they "
"should!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"정말 좋아! 이 땅에서 도적들을 쫓아낸 후로 그들은 이곳에 발을 들이지 않았어. 반"
"홀드는 평화롭고 조용해!\\\""

msgctxt "56fd02e9-ca7b-4149-a123-2e4c8b54dbdf"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're doing fine. We train volunteers, keep the hotheads separated, catch "
"thieves… Don't worry, if anything goes wrong I'll let you know right away!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"잘 지내고 있어. 우리는 봉사자들을 훈련시키고 싸우는 사람들을 떼어내고 도둑들을 "
"잡지... 걱정 마. 무슨 일이 생기면 알려줄게!\\\""

msgctxt "81eade66-dec7-49cb-8b6d-dfac20bd983f"
msgid ""
"A magnificent set of leather armor, crafted from the hide of an unknown predator."
msgstr "어떤 맹수의 가죽으로 만들었는지는 모르지만 훌륭한 가죽 갑옷 세트입니다."

msgctxt "54c73e6b-3fc8-4c57-a090-87130ee47719"
msgid "Varnhold's Gratitude"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de83ded9-af46-48af-8d95-bd7cb6d6c086"
msgid ""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38338c8e-bc7a-4455-8e0f-153217be30dc"
msgid "\\\"Get to work on this special gift of yours.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"이 특별한 선물로 가서 일해.\\\""

msgctxt "94db0be3-2d73-4892-855c-b6a21e7104f6"
msgid "\\\"I thank you for your gift.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네 선물은 감사히 받겠어.\\\""

msgctxt "d259b0ab-30a4-4c71-a154-d801c99d65ab"
msgid "\\\"I'd like you to make something specific for me.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"나를 위해 무언가 만들어 줄 수 있어?\\\""

msgctxt "d52ecbbf-3534-40a2-9dba-295dab859aa1"
msgid "\\\"Tell me more about your idea.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네 생각에 대해 말해봐.\\\""

msgctxt "02e7315a-630f-4670-8e6e-adc51df840f5"
msgid "\\\"Leather armor.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"가죽 갑옷.\\\""

msgctxt "25fb657c-38e5-4b4d-8a05-2b4b2607df3a"
msgid "\\\"Leather gloves.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"가죽 장갑.\\\""

msgctxt "8c583bf9-09b4-4d25-967b-8399ef66d1f5"
msgid "\\\"A pair of fine boots.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"훌륭한 신발.\\\""

msgctxt "3404a5cc-7e3d-475a-a9af-cdca904d7495"
msgid "\\\"A good belt.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"좋은 벨트.\\\""

msgctxt "992e1283-ef5e-4337-90be-a3285c594941"
msgid "\\\"Show off your leatherworking skills — make a magical item for me.''"
msgstr "\\\"네 가죽 세공 솜씨를 발휘해봐. 나에게 마법 아이템을 만들어줘.\\\""

msgctxt "a34d280a-aced-42a4-bd95-e5923c5d455b"
msgid "\\\"On second thought, you can decide for yourself.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"다시 생각해보니 네가 결정하는 게 나을 거 같아.\\\""

msgctxt "82678b52-a62b-47e3-af6d-c5c24e4c4944"
msgid "\\\"I like this idea. I'll see whether I can make it happen.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"좋은 생각이야. 할 수 있는지 두고 보자.\\\""

msgctxt "b27dc3e9-e37a-4e1e-adbd-8b23b12832c7"
msgid "\\\"Varnhold does not need a militia.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"반홀드는 민병대가 필요하지 않아.\\\""

msgctxt "3fe18222-4334-4ae2-ae9f-529d032e094b"
msgid "\\\"Why don't you simply come and serve as my guards?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그냥 와서 내 경비가 되는 건 어때?\\\""

msgctxt "7892e94c-2396-4a41-a081-1e7aaa49750f"
msgid "\\\"'All manner of leather things'?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"모든 종류의 가죽 장비를 만드나?\\\""

msgctxt "feb52faf-cab2-4e54-b4ae-12662c83dc54"
msgid "\\\"I do not require your services any longer.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네 도움은 이제 필요치 않아.\\\""

msgctxt "1db321f4-0c4a-4d42-9b12-b7b46e41d4eb"
msgid ""
"{n}Before you is a boyish half-elf. Her tight-fitting leather outfit is full of "
"patches, and a large, mean-looking blade rests on her hip. A tattoo adorns the "
"woman's neck.{/n} \\\"On behalf of the simple folk of Varnhold, I greet you! My "
"name is Tirval. I am here to represent our community, to present you with a token "
"of our loyalty, and to humbly beg your help.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}당신 앞에는 보이시한 하프엘프가 서있습니다. 그녀는 몸에 달라붙는 가죽 갑옷을 입"
"었고 크고 날렵해보이는 칼집이 엉덩이 위에 걸터 있습니다. 그녀의 목에는 문신이 그려"
"졌습니다.{/n} \\\"반홀드의 주민을 대신해서 인사할게! 내 이름은 Tirval이야. 나는 우"
"리 모임을 대표해서 우리의 충성심을 보여주고 부탁을 하러 왔어.\\\""

msgctxt "69a74a15-7498-42f4-babb-b4b4c39b79a1"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Tirval}Tirval{/d} greets you with a half-bow.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, please, accept this new gift from me and the "
"Varnhold militia!\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}{d|Tirval}Tirval{/d}은 당신에게 인사합니다.{/n} \\\"{name}! 나와 반홀드 민병대"
"가 준비한 선물을 받아줘!\\\""

msgctxt "cd55176e-2af7-4323-96ed-1f64b7da5cc7"
msgid ""
"{n}With a bow, the half-elf hands you something wrapped in a piece of cloth. — It "
"is a set of leather armor.{/n} \\\"This is my finest creation, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I named it 'Varnhold's Gratitude'. No blade "
"shall wound your kind and generous heart, so long as this armor protects it.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}인사를 하며 하프엘프는 천으로 감싸진 무언가를 건냅니다. 그것은 가죽 갑옷 세트였"
"습니다.{/n} \\\"내 최고의 작품이야. {name}. 나는 이걸 반홀드의 감사라고 이름 지었"
"어. 어떤 검도 그 가죽을 뚫어 네 심장을 찌르지는 못할 거야.\\\""

msgctxt "35a40f09-5d36-4a3f-b20c-2ae5922c5382"
msgid ""
"\\\"And that is not all, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! "
"The Varnhold militia is proud to report that the region has been freed from "
"bandits, and order has been restored. We hit 'em so hard, they flew all the way to "
"Mendev! The people know it's all thanks to you. If you hadn't helped us to gather "
"the militia, the damn crooks would still be robbing and butchering us.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"그게 다가 아니야! 반홀드 민병대는 지역 도적들을 물리쳤고 반홀드는 질서를 되찾았"
"어. 그들은 멘데브로 도망을 갔지! 모두 네 덕분이야. 네가 우리를 도와 민병대를 조직하"
"지 않았다면 그 놈들이 우리를 도살하며 약탈하고 있었을 거야.\\\""

msgctxt "64c693d8-ed9a-45da-a6d7-d157af923ccf"
msgid ""
"{n}Tirval proudly hands over her gift and continues in a steady tone.{/n} \\\"We "
"ask you to let Varnhold assemble a militia of her own. Many of the locals are "
"eager to keep watch and defend their homes with weapons in hand — especially so "
"after the… well, you understand.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}Tirval은 선물을 자신 있게 건내며 말합니다.{/n} \\\"반홀드가 민병대를 조직할 수 "
"있게 해줘. 많은 주민들이 기꺼이 감시를 하고 집을 지키고 싶어해. 특히 그 일 이후에 "
"말이야...\\\""

msgctxt "fc81731a-ef6e-44e5-af9d-3b507d0de00b"
msgid ""
"\\\"We owe you a lot. And I would like to make something special for you. Not long "
"ago, I shot something down in the forest… I'm not even sure how to describe it. It "
"was like a dragon, only smaller. I've never seen a beast so fierce! Its hide is a "
"thing of beauty. And that's what I'll use for your gift. It will make the best "
"leather armor you've ever seen, let alone owned. Just say the word, and I'll start "
"working on it.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"네게 많은 빚을 졌어. 너에게 특별한 선물을 주고 싶어. 얼마 전 숲에서 무언가를 맞"
"춰 떨어뜨렸는데... 설명하기도 힘들다. 드래곤 같은데 작은 놈이야. 그런 거친 짐승은 "
"본 적이 없었어! 가죽은 정말 아름답더군. 그래서 그 가죽으로 네 선물을 만드려는 거"
"야. 네가 본 것 중 최고의 갑옷이 될 거야. 말만 하면 바로 작업을 시작할게.\\\""

msgctxt "0924b122-3a1e-410d-b202-0a3046883a8d"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-elf looks worried as she rubs the tattoo on her neck.{/n} \\\"I'm "
"sorry for everything that happened in Varnhold that day. It all seems quiet there "
"now. In any case, me and my people shall hold our word: we'll fight to the end for "
"our homes and our loved ones.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}하프엘프는 목의 문신을 만지며 걱정합니다.{/n} \\\"반홀드에서 일어난 일은 정말 유"
"감이야. 지금은 조용한 거 같아. 어떤 경우에도 우리는 우리의 집과 사랑하는 사람들을 "
"지키기 위해 싸울 거야.\\\""

msgctxt "8f2bfc6a-edfe-4627-add8-192ff477bf45"
msgid ""
"\\\"I shall work like never before! Trust me, you will not be disappointed!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"최선을 다하고 있어! 믿어줘. 실망하지 않을 거야!\\\""

msgctxt "5a6a7100-c2bb-4346-b5fa-50daf2c8d2f8"
msgid ""
"{n}Tirval smiles and nods.{/n} \\\"You're welcome. I hope it serves you well.\\\""
msgstr "{n}Tirval은 웃으며 끄덕입니다.{/n} \\\"천만에. 네가 좋아했으면 좋겠어.\\\""

msgctxt "54a43edc-a21c-4563-9efe-52d5d8569340"
msgid "\\\"You have my complete attention. What is it that you require?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그래. 원하는 게 뭐야?\\\""

msgctxt "877f26ca-81e6-4814-a22e-5f80176fe93f"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll try to keep it short. I come from a long way from here — Daggermark, that "
"is. We've never had too much in the way of law. But we always had order. It just "
"wasn't the guard that looked after it, it was the local bandits. Every village, "
"every quarter, they all had a gang of their own. They never touched anyone except "
"other gangsters that came by. They were just like the guard, you see, even though "
"no one ever gave them any authority. And if you don't have the authority, and you "
"carry a blade — well then you're a bandit.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"간단히 말할게. 나는 대거마크에서 먼 길을 왔어. 우리는 법의 보호를 받지 못했지. "
"하지만 우리는 항상 질서를 찾았어. 하지만 그건 경비가 아니라 지역 도적들 덕이야. 마"
"을마다 도적들이 무리를 지었지. 그들은 다른 도적들 말고는 누구도 괴롭히지 않아. 그들"
"은 권한이 없어도 경비 역할을 하지. 하지만 권한이 없는데 칼을 쓰는 녀석들이니 도적들"
"이라고 불리는 거지.\\\""

msgctxt "b17b2558-0239-44ca-b537-fcf1a0bf522a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Right. Something light, but still sturdy, and make sure it doesn't creak. No "
"problem, I've got everything I need.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"좋아. 가볍지만 단단하고 금이 가지 않는 것으로. 문제 없어. 필요한 건 다 있어.\\"
"\""

msgctxt "a3e3deda-b7d4-4b00-a40b-a7ab598f6af3"
msgid ""
"\\\"He-he, you'll love what I come up with, I promise. When it comes to leather, "
"I'm the best around.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"내가 무얼 만들었는지 알면 놀랄 거야. 가죽 세공은 내가 최고야.\\\""

msgctxt "b8742652-1764-4b67-ac8e-ed60587f89b4"
msgid "\\\"As you wish. I'll do my best.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"원하는 대로. 최선을 다할게.\\\""

msgctxt "75c2bb65-0bb3-4cfc-b3da-2fa974cc4171"
msgid ""
"\\\"You've sent your guard to Varnhold. But firstly, they're strangers here. "
"Second, they're not your best people. Think about it — who would ever want to get "
"posted all the way down here? So that's why there's are so many guards there and "
"so little order. As for us, we know the people we're dealing with. We can tell the "
"real thug from the harmless drunk who likes to tie one on and wave his fists "
"around. Who to watch because he's a dangerous fool, and who to watch because he's "
"an eager fool!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"반홀드에 경비를 보냈군. 그들은 여기에서는 이방인들이야. 그들이 최선도 아니고. "
"그들도 여기 와서 고생하고 싶지 않을 거야. 그래서 여기에 경비가 많아도 질서가 지켜지"
"지 않는 거지. 우리는 여기 사람들을 잘 알아. 우리는 누가 해로운 범죄자인지 알아볼 "
"수 있어. 어떤 녀석이 위험한지 알아볼 수 있다는 거지!\\\""

msgctxt "7a536202-6285-442e-8693-a40fecba8c64"
msgid ""
"\\\"Long story short, we've got our ways. So that's why I'm asking for your "
"permission and your help — we want to bring a few brave and quick-witted folks "
"together, and do everything by the book.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"간단히 말하자면 우리의 방식이 있어. 그래서 네게 권한을 요청하는 거야. 그리고 용"
"감하고 똑똑한 사람들이 필요해.\\\""

msgctxt "89651714-0c20-431a-bc07-84107d0fdbce"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness} took care to send "
"guards to Varnhold, and I am grateful for that. However, the townsfolk would sleep "
"better knowing that you've let us take the protection of our children and elders "
"into our own hands. I understand that this would require an investment from you, "
"but we will not remain in your debt for long. If there is a workshop where I can "
"work leather, I'd be more than happy to make all manner of things for you — I used "
"to make a living as a tanner back in Daggermark.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"반홀드에 경비를 보내준 것은 고마워. 하지만 지역 주민들은 우리 스스로 아이들과 "
"노인들을 지켜주기를 바랄 거야. 네가 도와주고 싶은 생각은 알겠지만 우리는 곧 도움이 "
"필요 없어질 거야. 내가 가죽 세공을 하는 작업실이 있으면 너에게 더 좋은 물건을 만들 "
"수 있어. 나는 대거마크에 있고는 하거든.\\\""

msgctxt "2e983036-18df-4b07-9653-63e99e9bc994"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! I hope to "
"hear from you soon.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"고마워! 네 답변을 곧 듣고 싶어.\\\""

msgctxt "ddd95575-50e7-452b-8d22-6a57268a59c6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ah…. I see. Well, you are in your rights.\\\" {n}The half-elf makes a sloppy "
"bow and turns away.{/n}"
msgstr ""
"\\\"아... 알겠어. 네 마음이지.\\\" {n}하프엘프는 인사를 하고는 힘 없이 물러납니다."
"{/n}"

msgctxt "ffa30d22-7d62-4245-9e6f-decd035f06ec"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-elf hesitates.{/n} \\\"You see… Right now, we're close to the people. "
"If we put on a uniform, well, they'll accuse us of selling out to the authorities. "
"And we wouldn't want that, would we?\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}하프 엘프가 주저합니다.{/n} \\\"너도 알다시피... 우리는 사람들과 가까워. 우리가 "
"유니폼을 입으면 그들은 우리가 팔려간 줄 알 거야. 우리는 그런 것은 원하지 않아. 그렇"
"지?\\\""

msgctxt "4ef12ccf-7983-4985-8ec7-ddd83c70e774"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-elf livens up.{/n} \\\"Oh yes – I'm a master leatherworker, after all! "
"Armor, boots — I make it all. I just can't find a proper place to practice my "
"craft. If you help me with that, I can work for you. But only if you satisfy my "
"request and help us organize a militia!\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}하프엘프가 자신 있게 말합니다.{/n} \\\"그래. 나는 가죽 세공 장인이야! 갑옷이나 "
"신발 모든 걸 만들어. 내 기술을 쓸 적절한 장소를 찾지 못했어. 네가 도와준다면 너를 "
"위해 일할 수도 있어. 하지만 내 부탁을 들어주고 우리의 민병대를 조직하게 해준다면 말"
"이야!\\\""

msgctxt "ad2d616e-e8ee-4dd6-91ed-b2056de8fc96"
msgid ""
"{n}Tirval speaks with pride in her voice.{/n} \\\"Thank you for supporting our "
"militia. We bought the best equipment, and we've already begun with drills. As it "
"happens, at the meeting I was elected captain. It must mean they trust me. Your "
"soldiers are training my people as we speak. If you hadn't stepped in to help, "
"none of this would have happened.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}Tirva은 자신있게 말합니다.{/n} \\\"우리 민병대를 조직할 수 있게 도와줘서 고마"
"워. 우리는 최고의 장비를 샀고 벌써 훈련을 하고 있어. 회의에서 나는 민병대 대장으로 "
"뽑혔어. 그들은 나를 믿는다는 얘기이겠지. 네 군인들은 우리 사람들을 훈련시키고 있"
"어. 네가 도와주지 않았다면 이렇게 되지 않았을 거야.\\\""

msgctxt "dd35825c-1a99-4e9c-ae29-11a6b21ac747"
msgid ""
"{n}Tirval purses her lips and remains silent for a few moments. She then "
"harrumphs, bow, and without a word, turns and walks away.{/n}"
msgstr ""
"{n}Tirval은 입술을 물고 잠시 조용히 있습니다. 그녀는 말 없이 활을 챙기고 걸어갑니"
"다.{/n}"

msgctxt "7932cc5a-204b-4236-9af7-a6e800b3f82a"
msgid ""
"\\\"But that was beside the point. I sincerely hope that my gift comes in handy. "
"Tell me if it's something special you need — I can make any wish come true!\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"그건 달라. 나는 너를 돕고 싶어. 네가 원하는 특별한 게 있다면 말해줘. 네 소원이 "
"이루어지도록 도와줄게!\\\""

msgctxt "a112a7d6-0997-465c-9079-256a7f4789a4"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-elf hands a wrapped parcel to you.{/n} \\\"I personally vouch for its "
"quality. I made it with my own hands, every stitch and cut. I hope you'll like it!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}하프엘프는 포장된 상자를 당신에게 건넵니다.{/n} \\\"특별히 만들었어. 내가 직접 "
"한땀 한땀 꿰메었지. 네가 좋아하길 바라!\\\""

msgctxt "b5369d36-b13f-4143-b330-bae2bf304eae"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I've just received word… Did you know that there's trouble brewing in "
"Varnhold? Their militia is at odds with itself! The captain cannot keep her "
"soldiers in line. According to her, they've gotten completely out of hand. – It "
"might even come to bloodshed! I think you should pay them a visit personally.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"{name}. 방금 들었어... 반홀드에 문제가 생긴 거 알아? 그쪽의 민병대가 서로 싸웠"
"어! 대장이 자신의 부하들을 단속하지 못했어. 그녀가 말하길 완전히 통제가 되지 않았다"
"는군. 유혈사태가 벌어질 뻔했다고 해! 네가 개인적으로 들려야 할 것 같아.\\\""

msgctxt "4d997539-cc88-4b0d-81cb-41fb4ccf8676"
msgid "[Call out to the man] \\\"You there, what do you want?\\\""
msgstr "[남성을 부릅니다] \\\"거기. 원하는 게 뭐야?\\\""

msgctxt "4e720f7e-18c6-42f2-9eb3-f712d33dda4e"
msgid "\\\"Tirvael, what is happening here?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"Tirval. 무슨 일이야?\\\""

msgctxt "e6c7914b-4629-40e5-b32f-095da457e1b1"
msgid "Demanded that Tirvael quenches the mutiny in the militia's ranks."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b654ee63-0a9f-4ac2-80ec-b9e0879fddb5"
msgid ""
"\\\"What are you waiting for, Tirvael? Take care of your people yourself, right "
"now!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ce3ea14-3972-405d-a70d-e7de7fa55183"
msgid "Gave all the power in Varnhold to the militia."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d8d42f4-4650-4b1a-a2cc-026ba799558c"
msgid "\\\"I agree. Let the militia take care of Varnhold on their own.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "334e55d2-8696-4332-86e9-8c6ab41de22c"
msgid "Executed the mutineers from the Varnhold militia."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7c2fc1d-cf6a-40bd-8c1b-f6766386654d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hang the troublemakers and disband the militia. I am the law in this land.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7725a1fc-9a85-4c80-974e-ae38102c39c5"
msgid "Disbanded the Varnhold militia."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "01290a2d-472b-4ddc-8443-ebb2a4eacb25"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let them live. But the militia will have to be disbanded. You are too "
"unreliable.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed44d92c-4e68-414f-be27-c4a56a888384"
msgid "Spared the members of the Varnhold militia."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "07631124-053d-45bb-8eee-188556a17f74"
msgid ""
"\\\"Place them under house arrest until they come to their senses. As for the "
"militia, I'll give you one more chance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "be3b3c3d-dcd5-45d4-acee-e11cf2772494"
msgid "\\\"Why hasn't this revolt already been dealt with, Tirval?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6d37563-dbf5-49d1-bc70-e58bb4b397a1"
msgid "Slaughtered the Varnhold militia."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bbf1b16c-8045-4286-8867-600509755479"
msgid ""
"[Attack] \\\"I'm sick and tired of you! It's time I took care of you myself!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4f9b0e29-90e9-401b-8a34-b9a7bd9a5f5a"
msgid ""
"{n}A fraught scene is playing out before you: {d|Tirval}Tirval{/d}, the captain of "
"the militia, is in a fiery argument with an angry man in heavy armor. Their hands "
"are on the hilts of their weapons, and their eyes are locked. Their stares are so "
"intense they could petrify a lesser warrior.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e7ece59-58ea-418c-9b59-b9efd2110a75"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Tirval}Tirval{/d} gives you a tired look, but there's an ingratiating tone "
"to her voice.{/n} \\\"Please, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}, do not execute these fools! Yes, they have… overstepped their bounds. "
"But this was simply folly, nothing more! I implore you, have mercy on the guilty "
"and do not disband the militia altogether!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37b84a56-2161-4dfc-b049-bcfe3dcd84ac"
msgid ""
"{n}Tirval gives you a solemn look.{/n} \\\"That would serve no purpose. All these "
"people wanted was to protect their homes and their streets. And all it took was a "
"single mistake for you to… But it shall be as you wish. But do not expect me to "
"stay here even a moment longer than necessary. Farewell, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53ca097f-e6ec-401b-ad4d-a65a1e6c4c4a"
msgid ""
"{n}Tirval shakes her head in regret.{/n} \\\"What a pity… but perhaps the people "
"really cannot be trusted to protect themselves, after all. And still… never mind. "
"It's our fault.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "837528da-d524-4d95-b356-94eafaa89028"
msgid ""
"{n}Tirval smiles, her face beaming with gratitude.{/n} \\\"Thank you. You have my "
"word, this will not happen again. We won't let you down. Listen up, you oafs! Away "
"with you! Back to your homes, everyone!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3727c3a2-a84b-4e6e-aa8f-477056046c89"
msgid ""
"\\\"What's there to explain… We got ourselves an army here, right? That means we "
"can defend our land on our own now, right? We build these little old huts "
"ourselves, we plow the fields, we fend off the bandits. That means we deserve to "
"rule Varnhold ourselves. We've no more need for strangers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65f7e546-e852-493a-996e-563dde27f12a"
msgid ""
"\\\"These idiots here decided they want to pretend they're independent now! "
"They've all but forgotten the vows they gave you! The fools can't see that if you "
"were to leave Varnhold, the whole region would fall into chaos! The bandits would "
"be back fighting for dominance all over again! The rivers would flow red! But we "
"gave them law and order! And if they decide to give it all up?! Why, if they'll be "
"such fools, perhaps we should let them have what they think they want...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b29d32d7-6f26-4fdf-a155-95d82879efa5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! Now we'll put "
"these upstarts in their place…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "911fc919-3918-41ef-81f6-4861eb03f912"
msgid ""
"{n}The militiaman cracks a broad grin.{/n} \\\"There, heard that? The capital "
"cares about the will of the people after all! As for — go, run back to the big "
"city. You're not welcome here anymore! We'll run things our way here, the Varnhold "
"way! Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, for taking "
"our matter to heart, and for listening to the people!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0e026b2-7b34-40de-97df-76a811f81f0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank the gods you're here! Reign in these dogs! They're inciting revolt and "
"trying to rile up my militia-men!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b37c0ce-eadd-4e8a-9d3b-911498cdf3b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Aha! She sees her master and runs to lick {mf|his|her} boots! This land "
"belongs to us, not this… bird of passage. We plow these fields – and we protect "
"them as well. When the bandits come, we'll be the ones out there shedding blood "
"for our homes, while the big city folk hide in their holes! I say – no more!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eacdd878-6535-431f-96b0-42eb927164f4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Heh, you wish! You hear that, folks? They want us to run home with our tails "
"between our legs! Whaddya think? We fighting for our land or what?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "242475fd-7bfd-4a1c-8f8d-fab41bb5cfe8"
msgid ""
"{n}Tirval gives you a solemn look.{/n} \\\"You know you've doomed this place, "
"don't you? Who are you leaving in charge? These nitwits? They'll do a damn fine "
"job running this place, they will… Without law, without order, this land will "
"descend into mayhem. I'd rather leave this land forever than watch that happen. It "
"was a pleasure knowing you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. Farewell.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ef5f8d21-282e-45cd-8082-761f9ca94f4d"
msgid ""
"\\\"What you say is true. You have helped us arm ourselves, and for that we are "
"thankful. That's why we don't want to break away from the {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom} — we just want to rule our own homes! What gives you the idea "
"that you, living in the capital, know better than us what Varnhold really needs? "
"Trust me, you'll only thank us once you set us free!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13575955-c9d6-43aa-8773-5ab33fcbe597"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you even remember whose gold bought those weapons? Who taught you to fight? "
"Who gathered the militia in the first place?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6593e8a4-fc56-4d22-8c5e-bed640f3819a"
msgid ""
"\\\"And what will you do? Hang us all? And then what? Send in your soldiers? "
"That's the true face of your 'grace' and 'mercy'! You butcher anyone who speaks "
"out against you! You two-faced bastards…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7fb77d1-cfd8-4696-95b6-87109e90ae85"
msgid ""
"\\\"Forgive me, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. It's just…"
"\\\" {n}The half-elf lowers her voice.{/n} \\\"These were our people, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Our neighbors, farmers, craftsmen… "
"I didn't want to spill even more blood... But I... I suppose I've failed, haven't "
"I?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a85cae76-b3ff-4a88-9f96-b1dfb951bbff"
msgid ""
"\\\"Morhalan is under arrest. He's patching quilts in a prison cell right about "
"now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98015ee3-52d8-4ad9-a194-4ae719dc1277"
msgid "\\\"What did you want to tell me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6958ce1-cb9d-49b1-8028-8eece7ecfc10"
msgid "\\\"I'd like to know more about you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e01e9311-2729-4a44-b21a-e247a541f139"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8aa0796-08f2-422a-9e6c-e4318e97c13e"
msgid "\\\"Where are you from?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c141087a-acc9-40dc-8886-18cde7353f55"
msgid "\\\"How did you become a tailor?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50ed5d7f-6021-4ee9-b776-cfd1c8e2c9b8"
msgid "\\\"Let's discuss it later.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7161ac2d-056e-4bdd-bd48-d2a0c85dd071"
msgid "\\\"Look at these skins. They were stripped off of murdered lizardfolk.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdec05c7-48ca-4b24-a434-a1d193771f3a"
msgid "\\\"You blush all the time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a31b42ed-e431-4717-ae9b-74b67b45f6dc"
msgid "\\\"All right, I'll track down the hunters.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ad46554-bb39-4665-84c0-15641ca2d43b"
msgid "\\\"I can't make any promises.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ebb7876-a1e9-46ca-959b-04b03b281c80"
msgid "\\\"I can't waste my time on this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "307c2c26-5612-4769-8bd5-9c9442113b6f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, it's you! Please, accept my gratitude for the workshop! The house is "
"beautiful, the neighbors are wonderful, and everyone is so kind and friendly! I'm "
"flooded with orders! And to think I could still be {d|Shariel}rotting{/d} away in "
"jail for a false accusation...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71ff9792-45ea-4e1f-a6cd-d960cf55b572"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-elf puts his hand on his heart.{/n} \\\"I am happy to see you at any "
"time!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e29320ce-9175-4caf-95c3-ff23666666a8"
msgid "WHAT DO YOU WANT TO KNOW ABOUT"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7c10d45-88a5-42f9-98c8-8bd208e864a2"
msgid ""
"{n}Sharel looks around nervously.{/n} \\\"I beg your forgiveness, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, for making you come all the way to our "
"distant region... There are too many guards in the palace that were chasing me "
"recently. The thing is, I think I know who wrongfully accused me. There's a tailor "
"in the capital – his name is Morhalan. He has the reputation of a brilliant "
"master, so I wanted to become his apprentice. But when I went to his workshop...\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7b047de-0c56-4dc6-8ceb-561488a2cb3b"
msgid "\\\"As you wish. I'm always happy to talk to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64bcb241-8565-43c4-b689-552fdec42c4c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I come from Erages. It's a small fishing town in Kyonin. That's the place "
"where the elves send my kind into exile. The exile for half breeds. My father is a "
"fisherman and a smuggler. He served as a steersmate on an Andoran warship until he "
"met my mother and settled down. My mother is a net weaver. There's an art to "
"weaving a fishing net! And my mother is simply the best at it. She taught me to "
"tie knots and weave patterns...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02fd4157-9649-46c1-8a09-bb2885b45aec"
msgid ""
"\\\"I started when I entered Erages Academy. I wasn't much into archeology, but "
"you don't have many options in Erages. It's either the Academy or a fishing "
"business. That was when I realized that an ancient elven ornament can spruce up "
"any object at all. I realized that using this sort of design made anything I sewed "
"exquisite – and quite popular. A couple of months later, half the student body was "
"wearing my vests and capes. I'd finally found my passion. But then I left, in "
"search for better opportunities.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b15bba9f-9774-42dd-b296-1e9fa25fb606"
msgid ""
"\\\"You'll hardly take my word for it – but it's true! A master tailor in the "
"capital is butchering lizardfolk to make clothes from their skins! I'm no tracker. "
"I can't go hunting down Morhalan's poachers... But you could! If only you could "
"find those murderers in the marshes and bring some evidence, the guards will take "
"this seriously, and we'll rid the capital of great evil!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed5da865-bc08-483e-93c8-314d69f45454"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, I hope he finds enough Light in his soul that he can someday see the "
"graveness of his crime. You can't slaughter intelligent beings as if they were "
"beasts, and make clothes of their skins!\\\" {N}Sharel stays silent for a few "
"seconds and then shakes his head.{/N} \\\"Even now that it's over, it's hard to "
"believe this evil act really took place.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e786c3a6-a3c3-4fcb-bd0f-20f999b1b068"
msgid ""
"{n}Sharel looks frightened. He touches the skins with evident disgust.{/n} \\"
"\"They were skinned very skillfully. There's no doubt about it. The butchers meant "
"to use these skins for leatherwork. If they were just trying to scare someone with "
"a bloody murder, they would have made more cuts. But here they made the least. The "
"butcher was clearly saving the skin. I was right! Morhalan is buying the skins of "
"lizardfolk! He's a monster! Thank you for your support! Now I have all the "
"evidence I need. Now I've taken too much of your time already. I will go to the "
"guards and see the monster arrested myself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9dcce7dd-022c-4154-9a71-62d546ba48ef"
msgid ""
"{n}The young Sharel looks embarrassed. He fixes his hair, trying to hide the blush "
"in his cheeks.{/n} \\\"What... what would you like to know?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4bf6ab0-5807-4413-b07f-f56a09fb6700"
msgid ""
"{n}The {d|Shariel}half-elf{/d} is whistling carelessly. He gives you a graceful "
"bow as he sees you.{/n} \\\"It's good to see you! How can I help you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2936c6e5-2ce6-4baa-aa8c-949840003015"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you! I could never have brought Morhalan's crimes to light without your "
"support. Now that he's in jail, I might return to the capital... but you know "
"what? I've quite gotten used to the air here. And I have wonderful neighbors. Fate "
"has brought me here. So be it. I'm staying. Especially since I've begun making "
"sketches for a unique piece! Another relocation would only delay its creation.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b129ae64-7210-4291-a3cf-1dfc0e81d349"
msgid ""
"\\\"In his workshop, I saw... things which alarmed me very much. Vests, shoes, "
"gloves, all made from reptile skin. But the pattern was... distinct. I've only "
"seen the pattern on lizardfolk – intelligent beings, who also live in the {g|"
"Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}, as far as I know. I tried asking Morhalan about it, "
"but he threw me out into the cold. And when I tried to start my own business and "
"open a shop, I was literally driven out of the capital!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ae98af62-f9d8-4e95-a083-12aa72a1a866"
msgid ""
"\\\"Me? Oh... Yes, indeed.\\\" {n}Sharel turns purple and laughs.{/n} \\\"I beg "
"your pardon, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! I'm not used "
"to chatting with the ruler of the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} {mf|himself|"
"herself}! Before I met you, I'd always thought that rulers never talk to ordinary "
"people. You're different!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e28fd3c-dd2f-4282-981f-cf1653e01524"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank the gods! I'm sorry I cannot say exactly where to find the wretches. But "
"I'm certain they must be hunting in the {g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}. That's "
"where you'll find them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9afefd36-5a4f-4fb5-9fa8-d48787fc3c59"
msgid ""
"\\\"I understand, I'm asking for too much... but still, if you ever come across "
"these poachers on your travels, don't let them get away with it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8213339b-5793-4801-b04d-2326c4e35f82"
msgid ""
"{n}Sharel steps back in fear.{/n} \\\"I... I'm sorry! Forget what I just said! I "
"will... handle it myself... I guess. I'm sorry!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ea18ec9-3292-4ff0-ba72-766e6f34d3a0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Lizardfolk aren't real people! – There's nothing to be sorry about! They're "
"only good for making boots!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d883cfe7-2202-4e83-bfd2-161da7da62cb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Huh, your noble skin is soft and gentle... You'll make a fine pair of pants.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "699e1e2c-7897-4262-9d29-b0640613123c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm innocent! It's... a mistake! A terrible mistake! I haven't taken anything "
"from anyone!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "834e631d-c6f6-4fc2-a9d2-9862555b5c9f"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's exactly what everyone always says. Every prisoner says they're innocent "
"if you ask them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17e06daa-8745-4f23-a233-b4538bab8bd8"
msgid "\\\"Ask Hassuf! He'll tell you himself!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3578975-779b-4622-8664-b87f40044a3c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Are you suggesting I should drag myself all the way to the capital? No way. "
"It's your own fault you ran all the way out here. But now we've got you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f83c5764-4fbe-4c47-93b4-fe65bfc5f3ec"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh damn, we're busted. Let's put 'em down! – We'll bury the bodies in the "
"swamp.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0bfbcee-3360-44e4-828c-8096ccd04f95"
msgid "\\\"You shouldn't have come to this place...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ae077142-01c1-4d3f-8b4c-b597d5e1f417"
msgid ""
"\\\"Stop! I'm beg your mercy, {mf|sire|milady}! You win! The jail is better than "
"the grave.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "963e1ec6-2c17-4627-9145-cb42cfb776c0"
msgid "\\\"What are you suggesting?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0dd97812-cb96-4c4d-a945-89f5ebcae51e"
msgid "Captured the flaying tailor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3be90ee7-c29b-4516-b0b4-47b3d2b6b8f8"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"I'm not listening to this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b75485f9-8882-4f2d-a1b5-ab2631ff2c74"
msgid "Made a bargain with the flaying tailor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7546a99-2d48-4cff-a1b2-71172884edb5"
msgid "\\\"I rather like this idea.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89f7ec1f-29dd-4ff9-bc93-cf6eec333029"
msgid "Captured the flaying tailor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ae0e3fe1-092f-439b-9878-cbafd49b9d72"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"What a disgusting offer. You will be brought to justice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "847ddf47-15cc-4f29-beb1-14d3c4de05fd"
msgid ""
"{n}Morhalan looks at you apprehensively, but his voice sounds confident.{/n} \\"
"\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I can see "
"that my humble efforts to escape your observant royal gaze seem to have miserably "
"failed! Well that'll all right, it remains for me to make you an offer that you "
"will find hard to resist!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4bfea879-4635-4646-816d-a6bf54151f82"
msgid ""
"\\\"The very same thing that I offer all the other over-meticulous hunters and "
"prying guards. Gold. Gold, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. "
"All that I've managed to save and scrape up over my life. Rest assured, it's a "
"very substantial amount. You wouldn't reject an offer like this just because some "
"naive spring chicken decided they want to play justice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0ea3bec-5e9c-4f79-b48d-a8a8c87ce65d"
msgid "\\\"Help me! Help me, lads!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "846d9dd4-fa49-4a62-9910-ac7ec3b8bad9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm happy to hear that you have found my offer sensible. Please accept this "
"purse of gold. Your people can collect the rest from my workshop. Now if you will "
"excuse me, there is one more matter that I simply must address before I leave "
"these lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fd4a0bc8-d5db-4e72-9d40-af27dae86e70"
msgid "Helped the wrongfully accused clear his good name."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "083aa98c-7719-4fe7-8e1f-029bb99689dd"
msgid ""
"\\\"I brought confirmation of his innocence from Hassuf. All accusations of theft "
"are false.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "744af827-c2ac-49a4-bd3c-8fd31956749c"
msgid "\\\"What is going on here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19266753-1c46-4f97-a150-9f925f9c3c7e"
msgid "\\\"What is this half-elf charged with?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8532b310-0ae2-4d8c-9599-4724c390be2f"
msgid "\\\"I must go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14cbf404-832b-49c3-9c87-7132e997aa20"
msgid "\\\"I'm tired of hearing this wretch's screams. Put him in jail at once.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ddad7a7-6de6-4c52-bce6-7c5ce2af8322"
msgid ""
"\\\"I order you to release this man! He is innocent! And next time you should "
"conclude a proper investigation before you restrain honest people!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32e62d0c-a40f-4e30-8834-9b8378079b43"
msgid ""
"{n}The young half-elf looks up at you, exhausted. Somebody has recently given him "
"a black eye. There's panic in his voice.{/n} \\\"I beg you, help me! I haven't "
"done anything wrong!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "559a8150-506b-4da9-a0ad-8687197d21b9"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-elf raises his head as you approach, and looks up at you with eyes "
"full of hope.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27c67ab5-9d63-4908-92b1-02f523f4d76c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Theft, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. We chased him "
"all the way out here from the capital. Stole something from a merchant and "
"escaped! Just another scoundrel, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. Never mind him. They're all the same. He was found out, so now he's "
"yelling about being innocent.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e07734d0-7e65-4906-9751-64824f43f6cc"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-elf looks shocked and terrified by his circumstance.{/n} \\\"You're "
"the local ruler, aren't you? I beg you for your mercy! I've been arrested as a "
"thief, and I'm about to go to jail! But haven't done anything wrong! I've never "
"taken anything that wasn't mine. Someone slandered me for stealing property from a "
"merchant in the capital!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28cecf4d-9ed8-4c8d-b735-ab0dfb1a7185"
msgid ""
"{n}There's hope in the half-elf's eyes, and his voice trembles with awe.{/n} \\"
"\"You... you really did it! For me! I've never seen anyone so honorable! My name "
"is Sharel, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I'm pleased to "
"meet you. If there's any way I can repay you... oh wait! Do you need the services "
"of a good tailor?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "195f0c30-3d74-4f4d-a8a4-e41b4409daf5"
msgid ""
"\\\"We had a deal. He promised to lend me money for a new workshop. But I didn't "
"take a single coin! It's all a lie! I beg you, please! Nobody believes me. The "
"merchant's name is Hassuf! He would help me, if only he knew I was in trouble! "
"Please, talk to the merchant in the capital. He will confirm I'm innocent!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1d20998e-b131-4373-acbc-f259ea47ac2a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Trust me, I can work wonders with a needle and a thread. It's only...\\\" {n}"
"The half-elf stops.{/n} \\\"I can't afford a workshop of my own. If I could find a "
"workplace... even one out here! I don't feel like returning to the capital after "
"all that's happened.\\\" {n}Sharel rubs his black eye.{/n} \\\"Please help me set "
"up a workshop, if you're in need of decent tailored cloth. I'll make it worth your "
"while. May the Gods protect you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4bbf18f9-a6d6-4cee-8d0e-6265338905be"
msgid ""
"\\\"So that's how this is going to go... Pardon me, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}! But better safe than sorry. Here, let's set you free "
"there, lad. Be careful now. You should keep your eyes peeled with enemies like "
"yours.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa8ebab9-cb8e-4503-bfc1-26eead4ebfc1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! I apologize "
"for the noise. Our captain thought it would be good to make an example of this "
"criminal. Keep the public in line, you know. This one turned out to be a little "
"noisy...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c258071-3124-4add-bf20-25782708329b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Right away, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! You're "
"right, my head is throbbing with all this noise. Let him cool down in a quiet "
"place for a while.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce137ae7-4a25-4c73-8db4-0122727e7ee2"
msgid "A glorious robe made of amazing fabric."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca0d5372-4996-4a93-a1f3-86571f80b1a8"
msgid "Robe of the Pure Heart"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c456729a-6338-47e0-9aec-ccd1cab907a7"
msgid "Scaly skin, flayed by a ruthless butcher."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2815644c-f12f-4cce-8e2c-fdc45deccaac"
msgid "Lizardfolk Skins"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89b35b0c-fef8-4420-98d5-25c5e197b8fe"
msgid "A letter that repudiates all accusations against Sharel, the half-elf."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37cd6949-50a2-4596-b697-a790866627cf"
msgid "Confirmation of Sharel's Innocence"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1dd1a5be-1908-4b40-88c1-4bded0793653"
msgid "\\\"Thank you. I hope to see more proof of your mastery in the future.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c63cf241-a3ea-4a59-a6cd-55d91dda5731"
msgid "\\\"I need something from you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19bb9873-2189-40d6-bfe3-1bd68e5af0da"
msgid "\\\"I don't want to see you anymore.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2fb8e52d-6ee2-4216-81f6-01e3dfc1e60e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why don't you set to work on that special thing you were making for me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "823a2a01-9e19-4549-ac23-d9de93415896"
msgid "\\\"I need some new clothes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "266f4b6e-7cab-4f85-b3c8-b02c11cd806c"
msgid "\\\"A decent robe for a mage.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f94cf930-e0a3-457e-b923-6523e0652eb2"
msgid "\\\"A sturdy cape.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "472a014c-ad1b-4ee3-8468-5f4b8130c92f"
msgid "\\\"As a tailor, you should know best what's missing from my wardrobe.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e87564e8-b936-4608-bfdb-7c2df6f63aea"
msgid ""
"{n}The {d|Shariel}half-elf{/d} is clearly embarrassed to be in the palace. He "
"shuffles his feet and bows shyly.{/n} \\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}! Here. I've brought you something.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "401adba4-8c87-4337-a0cb-687d7684c23d"
msgid ""
"{n}Sharel shifts from one foot to the other and then finally gets up the nerve to "
"speak up.{/n} \\\"You've done so much for me, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}! You cleared my name of slander, freed me from jail, gave "
"me a chance to do my job with honor! Someone wiser than I would simply settle down "
"and live a happy quiet life. But...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c11d07a3-a54c-4ff9-b8a2-515ce6394eee"
msgid "{n}Sharel bows as he hands you a bundle.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9bdb7a61-c47e-471b-94f2-d45b972356c6"
msgid ""
"{n}The tailor presents you with a magnificent robe.{/n} \\\"The Robe of the Pure "
"Heart is my masterpiece! Now that I know that rascal is in prison, I'm at peace "
"once more, and my mind isn't troubled by worry. I'm sure my further creations will "
"improve, but this robe... oh, there will be no other like this!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b632ebc4-7ac6-45ac-aeb7-82578fa22fc2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, and about Morhalan... I reported his crimes to the guards. However, "
"someone must have warned him. He escaped. He has eyes and ears everywhere. I'm "
"afraid your personal Warden is the only one who can find him.\\\" {n}Sharel is "
"shaken by righteous anger.{/n} \\\"I pray to {g|Torag}Torag{/g} not to let him "
"make more mischief before the guards find him! And I pray you don't to let him go "
"unpunished!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4a2da7f-6a88-4d1d-b960-69bf19130e31"
msgid "{n}The half-elf blushes and bows hurriedly.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de6f529d-9566-422c-b2ac-26ddca00997a"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-elf shivers, and freezes like a scared animal. After a pause, he nods "
"slowly and heavily.{/n} \\\"As you wish. I'm sorry for offending or interrupting "
"you. I didn't mean to do anything wrong. Farewell.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6928355d-4400-415d-8c1d-c901a156cb9b"
msgid ""
"{n}Sharel gives you a quick glance.{/n} \\\"Just tell me what you need. I'll take "
"care of it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea56612f-41e8-4eab-bfc2-0b68e952ddc3"
msgid ""
"\\\"After you and I brought that wretch Morhalan to justice, peace has once more "
"filled my heart. Thank you for returning tranquility to my life, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I would like to give you... a special "
"gift in thanks. Give me some time and freedom to work on my own, and I will make "
"something very special, just for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b8c0af7-600a-432e-9da0-00ba6ae2ecdb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you. Believe me, I'll spare no effort or time! You won't be disappointed."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98b27dc2-367d-40d9-9a11-0b03aab80981"
msgid "\\\"You will look irresistible in the clothing I'll make for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f094d56-c78a-493d-8439-3f1f64c5f349"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's a reason I was arrested at the outskirts of your domain. I don't want "
"to discuss it here. Please, come over to my village when you have a moment. We can "
"talk there. Believe me, I have quite a story to tell you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a7eac5bd-2448-43c4-9a36-75dbadfd97eb"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi's cheeks are wet with tears. She weeps and sniffles.{/n} \\\"{d|Shariel}"
"Sharel{/d}... the half-elf you saved from wrongful accusation and hired as the "
"court tailor... he's been murdered!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06240869-084d-4d6e-87e7-50b4f7195a05"
msgid ""
"\\\"Someone butchered him – cut open his stomach! Right in front of his own "
"workshop! His neighbor was scared to death when she found him this morning... oh, "
"this is so horrible! He was such a nice fellow!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "abb0111b-3cff-4d10-b7b2-aa11f3a4ac8a"
msgid "\\\"Tell me more about your offer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68b782d8-92ad-4f38-95a7-11e3957ab008"
msgid "\\\"I don't want any part in your affairs!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "989ff772-8d3e-4df9-91ce-ac1dbd1e3be7"
msgid "\\\"I won't tolerate smuggling in my domain. Guards! Take her to prison!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "faf82fb9-8748-4a77-b6fa-16f9f2cfd8ea"
msgid "\\\"I'll see what I can do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "730b5aec-7352-4c7b-a441-0508eaa6d33a"
msgid "Jailed the smuggler."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c297d640-e58b-45ed-9e2c-35dfed0bc3cd"
msgid "[To guards] \\\"Didn't you hear me? Take her away!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f47b7ca9-4df1-4fe8-85b0-41e97099afdf"
msgid "Exiled the smuggler."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4925c6e0-3838-47e1-8e6f-44e3e67a4eaa"
msgid ""
"[To Irlene] \\\"Since this is your first time, I'll give you a break. Never set "
"foot here again.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e0d8638-0e0f-4dd3-af40-5dc344c95ace"
msgid "Ordered the smuggler to be executed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc0834fc-b124-423d-ba6d-01be81baa76f"
msgid "[To guards] \\\"Execute her. Immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44284c90-71b0-448c-858c-c6a575cb6b0a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! Allow me to "
"pay my respects and deliver a gift on behalf of my master, a well-known "
"connoisseur of magical artifacts, kindly welcomed by you in the capital!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d9442580-d54e-47fa-b940-362f8e9a8cec"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let me introduce myself. Irlene Greyridge, at your service.\\\" {n}The girl "
"bows briefly and springs back up. She casts curious, assessing glances across the "
"throne room and holds out a package.{/n} \\\"This is a modest gift from my master, "
"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. May it serve you well! And "
"in case you're looking for more...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea4f9281-9cd6-44f6-8829-8a0be99fce87"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene looks at you sideways and smiles mysteriously.{/n} \\\"I beg you to "
"forgive my audacity, but since destiny is giving me the opportunity to speak with "
"you face-to-face... You see, my master is a highly educated and respected "
"specialist, but unfortunately, he has no business acumen whatsoever. For my part, "
"as much as I appreciate collectible items of great aesthetic value, I'm far more "
"interested in turning my knowledge in this sphere toward tangible profit. If you "
"take an interest in obtaining magical items without all this hassle... I could "
"arrange it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ca08328-f483-4e86-b5eb-857ad6d20b69"
msgid ""
"\\\"You see, over all my years of travel, I've built up... a long list of contacts "
"across {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g}. In other words, I can acquire magical rarities, "
"no matter the distance or difficulty. If you kindly help me open my own shop, I'll "
"gladly quit my master and use my talents for your benefit.\\\" {n}Irlene stops "
"speaking and looks at you expectantly.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69774f16-e270-4d74-98e7-e3ad9fdc077a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, thank you! May your reign last for years to come!\\\" {n}Irlene bows.{/n} "
"\\\"I dare not distract you any longer, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|"
"Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "753234c0-90d8-4545-b78b-225c51bf272f"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene cowers in fear.{/n} \\\"No... {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|"
"Your Highness}, I beg you... Forgive me my insolence! Don't kill me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bc78dd36-b234-44be-9666-ed4306d3cfbe"
msgid ""
"{n}The halfling utters a sigh.{/n} \\\"Such a shame... In that case, I won't let "
"my presence here bother you further. Farewell, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14211e10-ea7d-41ed-9685-6ca3aee6964d"
msgid "A delicately carved box filled with pure gems."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "557dca8c-21e9-4f2c-88e7-0fd48003fcd3"
msgid "Chest of Genuine Gemstones"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a19bf86c-353a-409b-bff0-dbba5f64dbf5"
msgid "The ivory twisted horn seems to glow softly."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "562eaa45-9c3d-4011-9950-0134d5b324f5"
msgid "Unicorn's Horn"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24312097-71eb-4bc9-ac9d-9b5e8428bd43"
msgid "\\\"Thank you. I'll be expecting your future creations.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "246d1e15-b10a-4ad8-9252-0e38f92bb920"
msgid "\\\"I would like to order a specific item.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0757e36-0d28-4b7c-82af-a434e66f2d93"
msgid "\\\"Your services are no longer needed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "904af8e5-c7ed-4376-8062-c7f80c84650c"
msgid "\\\"A set of magic scrolls.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e12563f1-ff91-4755-9c5c-0b1262ef4b39"
msgid "\\\"Wand.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4dd99d37-89e6-4906-a3c4-6618f31d862b"
msgid "\\\"Rod.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "376e688c-e2ce-4d40-b032-e1d6e1ef74d2"
msgid "\\\"Staff.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e583ec2-b4b7-4da4-aced-306416b0fffe"
msgid "\\\"I changed my mind. Do as you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6216696-bfee-4e2d-a656-a22a986bff54"
msgid "\\\"Of course!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22b0ef7c-6f88-4cd1-908b-192ecaf93e0a"
msgid "\\\"No, Irlene, your regular deliveries are enough.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d9a4dae5-f606-4347-9c3c-ba07fb4b556c"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Irlena}Irlene{/d} bows.{/n} \\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}! Allow me to alleviate your daily concerns with a humble "
"gift from your admirer!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69070355-d08c-443e-8f24-eae180e09a85"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am certain that you or one of your friends will find this... trinket useful. "
"It's come a long way to get to your hands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab76e2fb-4fd9-4b3f-b554-4fb8fcdb776d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd like to take this opportunity to thank you once again, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, for your kind generosity. I have another... "
"appealing offer for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c85cd1e-6457-4821-ac41-08fb1025e0a1"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene pales.{/n} \\\"But... have I done something to insult you? Well, I "
"suppose it's up to you. I won't trouble you again... But this was quite an "
"unexpected rejection.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83dd0b7a-d60b-48cb-a336-321432133c87"
msgid "{n}Irlene breaks into a smile.{/n} \\\"I won't keep you waiting.\\\""
msgstr "{n}이를린느가 미소짓습니다.{/n} \\\"곧 준비될 거예요.\\\""

msgctxt "2030cf78-5ca3-4ce9-a6e0-436400ccfae5"
msgid "\\\"My quality for your money! What would you like?\\\""
msgstr ""

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "7000c174-b5e5-4b73-a956-36c80727e811"
msgid "\\\"Whatever you say!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"네가 무엇을 말하든!\\"

msgctxt "1aa41468-a9a3-49ef-ae92-077d07b9fd1b"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene starts twisting her hair around her finger.{/n} \\\"My range of goods is "
"wide enough, no doubt. But just for you, I can get something exquisite... One of "
"my partners may have come across something valuable and rare. However, I'll need "
"your help to deliver it to you. Are you interested?\\\""
msgstr ""

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "31fa81e6-5081-4773-9c00-2a0e54eab363"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene claps.{/n} \\\"Come to my shop, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|"
"Your Highness}, so we can talk more in private.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}이를린느가 박수를 친다.{/n} \\\"제 가게에 오세요, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}, 그럼 좀 더 사적으로 대화를 나눌 수 있을 거예요.\\\""

msgctxt "e4fc1b6d-c459-452f-b20e-bc0e5bd824dc"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's a shame. If you change your mind, you're welcome to visit my shop to "
"discuss the matter in private.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"부끄러운 일이군요. 만약 생각을 바꾼다면, 얼마든지 제 가게에 와서 이 문제에 대"
"해 사적으로 논의하죠.\\\""

msgctxt "703e951a-4528-4f75-b249-0b3fc6e45646"
msgid ""
"\\\"There is something else. My partner finally managed to send the article I "
"promised. Now I just need to arrange its delivery. If you want your trophy, "
"please, do not disturb my work. Allow me to do my job, and you'll have it very "
"soon!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2eec6400-df2a-4af6-908f-e6e2d4b778e0"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Irlena}Irlene{/d} bows deeply and hands you a package.{/n} \\\"Here you are, "
"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Please, accept this gift "
"as a token of my special respect and admiration. I swear, any concerns you had "
"while it was en route will be repaid!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d72e69ca-5e03-4b81-a909-303ba13d95b0"
msgid ""
"\\\"You showed up and revealed your hand so easily... What's the real reason "
"behind that? I could have you thrown in prison, you know...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "009b8633-1d21-4ff4-9873-702c92b18600"
msgid "\\\"Let's discuss this 'exquisite' item you can get only for me.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그대가 나에게 줄 수 있는 '특별한 것'에 대해 논의해봅시다.\\\""

msgctxt "60765185-26f7-4ab0-b4a3-ff51e162cc33"
msgid "\\\"If you need to borrow money to pay your partner, I can help you out.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9af6b5fe-b2d2-42dc-b4bd-9e3a0d0032aa"
msgid "\\\"Here are your gemstones.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a45753e5-6cf7-43bd-805c-9e8b5553eb7d"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f95aa58f-8d6d-4a44-af98-24a9a0924baf"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"난 가야만 해.\\\""

msgctxt "852f3527-4fd8-41ac-9b2d-b380a221cb99"
msgid "\\\"How are things going in the shop?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"가게 돌아가는 건 어때?\\"

msgctxt "ac316787-f304-4db9-8996-bf62985501fe"
msgid "\\\"Can I buy something from you right now?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e180141-ba44-464e-bd22-8569890dbd75"
msgid "\\\"Describe Lidika so I can find her.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"리디카가 어떻게 생겼는지 말해줘. 내가 그녀를 찾을 수 있도록.\\\""

msgctxt "ecea6d67-2527-4de6-85de-c5448759231c"
msgid "Refused to kill a unicorn for a rare ingredient."
msgstr "희귀한 재료를 위해 유니콘을 죽이는 것을 반대한다."

msgctxt "3599b7ab-a5e6-4138-90a7-b7187fb68409"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm not killing a good-hearted, sapient being for some magical trinket!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"난 마법물품을 위해 선한 마음을 가진 존재를 해치지 않을 겁니다!\\\""

msgctxt "4bc1d15c-d55f-4839-81b5-9c6b417e5b85"
msgid "Agreed to kill a unicorn for a rare ingredient."
msgstr "희귀한 재료를 위해 유니콘을 죽이는 것에 대해 동의하다."

msgctxt "a5cafea7-15b4-4522-bc0a-29179e1f75a1"
msgid "\\\"Very well, Irlene, I'll do it. Where can I find the unicorn?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1d34c842-776c-4ed6-9a06-996d089a253d"
msgid "\\\"Why don't you do it yourself?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"그 일은 네 스스로 하는 게 어때?\\\""

msgctxt "0ff9b5ce-e215-4b40-b2c3-afc13cc829ab"
msgid ""
"\\\"Here's the unicorn's horn. I hope your partner can be trusted to carry out his "
"part of the deal.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"여기 유니콘의 뿔이 있어. 너의 파트너가 계약에서 자신의 부분을 완수하길 빌어.\\"
"\""

msgctxt "2ac25616-e182-45d0-bc89-59f0ff61dd4e"
msgid "Promised to get a unicorn horn for Irlene."
msgstr "이를린느에게 유니콘의 뿔을 구해줄 것을 약속한다."

msgctxt "87aa3a53-ee85-472f-8523-ebcae7ca86d8"
msgid ""
"\\\"I won't track down and hunt a unicorn, but I'll bring you a unicorn horn if I "
"ever come across one.\\\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"난 유니콘을 추적하거나 사냥하지 않을 거야. 하지만 구하게 된다면, 유니콘의 뿔을 "
"네게 가져다 주겠어.\\\""

msgctxt "1bc590f5-2e2b-4689-a879-67fce2028af6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! It's an "
"honor to have you here. Now I can deliver all kinds of magical rarities for you "
"from all across {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g}! You may order something specific, if you "
"so choose, or I can act of my own accord! As I said, nothing is impossible.\\\" {n}"
"Irlene gives you a cheerful wink.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ef5702d-ee77-4ae7-9db2-8d71557a610f"
msgid ""
"\\\"How can I serve you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}?\\"
"\""
msgstr ""
"\\\"어떻게 당신을 섬길 수 있겠습니까, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}?\\\""

msgctxt "ce4b4124-7993-4d68-b637-76dd85fc9268"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene shakes her head.{/n} \\\"Nothing escapes your eye, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. The truth is that it was worth the risk. "
"Our... contract is as profitable for me as it is for you. Royal favor is the best "
"insurance against the mob of enemies I've made over my years of traveling. I'd "
"rather have {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness} as a friend "
"than hire a bunch of bodyguards!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ffb753d3-71b4-4c75-b0a0-6e91a7c4ed24"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene clasps her hands in frustration.{/n} \\\"Oh, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}, this is so embarrassing! I'd love to, but there's "
"something...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f89df84-ed19-42de-bd11-1316a5acfd0a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have an associate, shall we say. Name's Ollie. He's a human — my gopher. "
"Long legs, strong. He was due back with payment for a fat contract three days ago. "
"I have a feeling that something happened to him... or worse, that he fled with my "
"money, which was promised as a down payment to my partner for that rarity I was "
"procuring for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1dac8211-080d-4c89-94be-4194055dbc8e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ollie has the chest of gemstones stashed somewhere near the southern border. "
"Without that, we're never getting your relic.\\\" {n}Irlene pauses a moment.{/n} \\"
"\"Why, if someone could find Ollie... maybe visit his family at {g|Lake Silverstep}"
"Lake Silverstep{/g} or talk to his wife Lidika... No, it doesn't feel right to "
"request this of you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de890cdb-fd0a-45df-961a-d66c04dc74dd"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene shakes her head.{/n} \\\"I wish it were so easy, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. These aren't ordinary coins we're talking "
"about. These are genuine gemstones, suitable for crafting magical items. I've been "
"looking for them for so long... and traded quite a valuable piece for them...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2dda390-196f-45eb-b987-325e05239f34"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene grabs the chest, counts the gemstones, and sighs in relief.{/n} \\\"None "
"are missing. What a relief! Rest assured, now I can strike a deal with my new "
"partner. Come back in a week. I'm sure I'll have good news for you by then.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ae6fa16-2952-40ce-8c74-7dd3405c7934"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene tut-tuts.{/n} \\\"I really don't think this is necessary, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. You're such a good {race}! I don't feel "
"like pulling the wool over your eyes. However, I'm afraid you won't believe my "
"stories without at least a little wool there to smooth things over!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e14e325-bdd3-4679-9916-c3ed2cd91ef6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well! Couldn't be better! You know, there are so many magical trinket "
"hunters in your lands! They want to grab everything, be it expensive bric-à-brac "
"or a sophisticated professional tool! But don't you worry! Whatever orders I "
"receive, yours always come first.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38e62ec1-7789-4eb6-949c-89f595d9d009"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sorry to disappoint you. Everything I have in the shop has been ordered "
"individually. That's how I do things.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3cfdaaf9-1a93-46d1-be31-686ac8259aba"
msgid ""
"\\\"How would I know what she looks like? I never paid attention when Ollie talked "
"about his family. Adorable, charming kids, his wife always waiting by the water "
"for him to return from adventures... Yuck.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6d9d28b6-119a-4ec2-ae71-2c5f4064a6c6"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene looks at you with hesitation and almost fear.{/n} \\\"Greetings, {mf|"
"Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}... You've... come to fetch your "
"order, right? So, here's the thing...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa5f10a0-0471-4aa9-9a71-ca4dbd8c0111"
msgid ""
"\\\"I sent the gemstones to my partner, as we agreed. Now it turns out it's not "
"enough! He wants something else from the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}! You "
"see, magic artifact gatherers need... extremely rare ingredients, at times. Such "
"as... such as unicorn's horn.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f0f2e5b2-5699-4bae-9721-02c868be93f0"
msgid ""
"\\\"These animals are rare. They don't come along very often. And many people "
"consider killing them for their horns to be pretty bad, because of their "
"intelligence... You're not someone to be stopped by petty superstition, are you?\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7a2dd3a-4719-4a5f-bec6-8fbc9d3fbe91"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm afraid I'm not much of a hunter, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|"
"Your Highness}. It'd skewer me on its horn in a flash! You're our best shot.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac60edd9-2759-4d37-b8b1-c3ec5f0bf332"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene smiles wryly.{/n} \\\"Just as you say, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}. It's a shame, though. We were almost there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e13d9eb5-cd17-41fb-baf3-aeafd87bfe95"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene rubs her hands.{/n} \\\"It's so nice doing business with you, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Regarding the unicorn's "
"whereabouts... Try tracking it down in the {g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}. I hear "
"it's been seen there.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}이를린느는 그녀의 손을 문지른다.{/n} \\\"당신이랑 거래해서 좋았어요{mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. 유니콘이 어디있는 가에 대해선... {g|"
"Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}에서 흔적을 찾아보세요. 유니콘이 그곳에 있다고 들었어요."
"\\\""

msgctxt "230da11a-76ca-4bff-9464-9106f44ae792"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene regards the unicorn's horn with admiration.{/n} \\\"Oh my... I never "
"hoped to hold such a rarity in my hands! Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}. I'm sure we can make it this time. I'll keep you abreast "
"of our progress.\\\""
msgstr ""
"{n}이를린느는 경탄하며 유니콘의 뿔을 다룬다.{/n} \\\"오, 내가 이런 희귀한 것을 손으"
"로 쥐어보게 될지는 꿈에도 몰랐어. 감사합니다. {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}. 우린 제시간에 만들 수 있을 거예요.당신에게 진행상황을 알리"
"도록 하죠.\\\""

msgctxt "173fc8a5-c58f-483a-83c2-110d94acbb02"
msgid ""
"{n}Irlene smiles sadly.{/n} \\\"Just as you say, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}. We look to have a long wait before us, I think.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f7e022e-7f02-43f1-9328-7465d3ac0f91"
msgid "\\\"Hey! Leave our friend alone!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"이봐! 우리 친구는 내버려둬!\\\""

msgctxt "5a59d6db-7b5d-42a9-aaac-94ba569a4343"
msgid "\\\"Go away! Go away!\\\""
msgstr "\\\"저리가! 저리가!\\\""

msgctxt "0994959c-7626-4f94-b588-463c0eab79f8"
msgid "\\\"Were you crying? May I help you?\\\""
msgstr "\\\"울고있는 거니? 내가 도와줄 일이 있을까?\\\""

msgctxt "5dfe6d37-40f8-4016-87f8-3d48e6815f2a"
msgid "\\\"Do you know Lidika? She lives in this village.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"리디카를 알아? 그녀는 이 마을에 살고 있어.\\\""

msgctxt "8efde16d-6899-4e7e-a4ab-cb97e78f6239"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr "\\\"난 가야만 해.\\\""

msgctxt "68a39800-0c99-444a-9c3a-fc0716b64218"
msgid ""
"\\\"Irlene sent me. She's looking for Ollie, and she said you might know where to "
"find him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5015d5b8-c305-47e3-8067-c74276c31759"
msgid "Gave priceless gems to the widow of the courier."
msgstr "귀중한 보석을 과부에게 넘긴다."

msgctxt "ef750174-49a2-4528-90ce-15b08cf69c04"
msgid ""
"[Give away the chest of gemstones] \\\"I found it on Ollie's body. I'm sure he'd "
"want his family to have it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "438a4948-0ae7-426e-b81a-dd9c80aec90a"
msgid "\\\"I found Ollie's bode. I'm so sorry.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dbf7da35-6800-4c9a-9331-9f6005a10934"
msgid "[Let Lidika go]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7ea5f66-dd2c-4655-9f6a-f097a161f211"
msgid "Granted a pension to the poor widow."
msgstr "가난한 과부에게 작은 집을 하사한다."

msgctxt "cdf563ba-0015-4f3f-aa42-0360cb828a3e"
msgid ""
"\\\"The {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} will support you, now that you've lost "
"your provider.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8e50905-a339-4f2e-8ccb-4ce43ef8e025"
msgid "Gave money to the poor widow."
msgstr "가난한 과부에게 돈을 준다."

msgctxt "91ecbc7a-ebc2-4efc-b9fd-c9645d2007be"
msgid "\\\"Please, accept this money. It should last you for a while.\\\""
msgstr "\"제발 이 돈을 받아주시오. 당분간은 생활할 수 있을 거요.\\\""

msgctxt "29e28b88-a587-4bad-a62b-67fac3dfcb2e"
msgid ""
"{n}A woman with dark circles under her eyes watches you anxiously as you approach. "
"When you come closer, she bows.{/n} \\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82b35e38-66c7-41bc-beeb-c7e5ac4391a9"
msgid "\\\"Yes, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7923979f-d6b1-46d7-b65e-2c8bee128f7d"
msgid ""
"\\\"If only you could track down and punish my lost husband, the bastard! Oh, "
"pardon my language, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I lost "
"my temper. You see, Ollie, my husband, left on business a few days ago, and he's "
"disappeared. I'm just so angry! And a little scared...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "502ff46d-c3a5-450b-89b9-e175a1a97f51"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm Lidika. Has something happened? Something... Do you know something about "
"my husband?\\\" {n}The woman's voice rings with fear and anxiety.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "838cb5c2-fd7e-4982-8b70-42bebbf9813a"
msgid ""
"\\\"{d|Irlena}Irlene{/d}! That greedy witch!\\\" {n}Lidika stomps her foot.{/n} \\"
"\"It was her who sent my Ollie on that mission! If not for her, my husband "
"wouldn't have dreamed of becoming rich! He wouldn't be slaving away for some "
"wench! She's been using him as a packhorse, always ordering him to deliver all "
"kinds of stuff. I have no idea what her deal was, but I can feel it in my bones — "
"no ordinary goods need to bypass guards and highroads in their delivery!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5df3ce61-8eed-441a-aecd-345fa8cb39b8"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't know where Ollie is. I've been racking my brain for what could have "
"happened! He mentioned he was going to the southern border to grab something from "
"some cleft. He said it was a desolate location, and that the package was safe "
"there... Guess it turns out it wasn't safe, after all!\\\" {n}Lidika starts crying."
"{/n} \\\"He widowed me and orphaned our two children! He's gone, he's dead, I can "
"feel it! He would never just leave us to starve!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb6413e6-218d-4c1b-bef3-3006fb7870af"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh... This... This is a fortune! The cursed fortune that ruined my poor "
"husband! If it weren't for the kids, I wouldn't even touch them...\\\" {n}Lidika "
"wipes her face with a sleeve and smiles wearily.{/n} \\\"Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. You saved us, I swear you did.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eca0e4e2-3b3b-4371-9ad9-30094738f254"
msgid ""
"{n}Lidika stares at you for a few moments, as if not understanding what you just "
"said. Then she buries her face in her palms and turns away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9eaaae35-0e47-40c6-ae7e-388638fa7fb9"
msgid ""
"{n}Lidika wipes the tears from her eyes. Her whisper is barely audible.{/n} \\"
"\"Thank you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f02781b-ca98-40c5-8824-2e212cb684f6"
msgid ""
"{n}Lidika blinks away the tears and looks at you in astonishment.{/n} \\\"Th... "
"Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! Thank you for "
"not letting our children starve! And me... I'm nothing without my Ollie...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cca5c7f2-3931-4f47-ae69-b6485c74839a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Now our "
"kids will be all right.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3db97953-b7f0-4ca6-b53b-f34890accdbf"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. We'll "
"manage... We'll survive through this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f74d4f2-f7c3-46a1-9f50-11d4e3565d7a"
msgid "\\\"Iomedae, I am the sword of your justice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bc363719-b40a-4e9f-b2d9-cd847df6e7c0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you! That rascal Varrask will pay for his crimes! We'll have captured "
"him by the time you reach the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "189102f5-09f6-4ada-bb0d-5af9665672e5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Here you are, you old fool. No money, no tools... You're in real trouble this "
"time, Varrask, you old fool!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "03cc3d08-d76d-4aa8-b402-00252fa42028"
msgid ""
"\\\"The elders were right – we're cursed, our whole bloodline. We're dumb. And "
"unlucky.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed93d0f3-3c40-439c-88c2-f22636e10853"
msgid "\\\"A good master can always find a place… Ah, but without my tools!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79992749-b4c7-4bda-b7d0-5f4dae662656"
msgid "\\\"I brought you the blood of the one who murdered your family.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c6f42a7-51a1-44dc-9409-fc2b76ed3c71"
msgid "\\\"I brought you the metal you need.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f773ac2-2ecb-4980-9575-04b19468af1e"
msgid "\\\"What was that relic you spoke of? Can I help you fix it?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92cf657f-bfd9-49a0-bd3a-4bddecca900d"
msgid "\\\"You lied about the murderer of your family. It was the inquisitor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8fa75e76-ca4f-4d1e-8d9f-b3cbd05289fe"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b01f710-0e8a-4a36-9be0-f8367d66de06"
msgid "\\\"Where are you from?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "944730eb-0584-4142-bcda-75e623054b78"
msgid "\\\"Remind me what you require to reforge your hammer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57adbc16-dd9f-438d-84c4-eaaa85986dee"
msgid "\\\"How did your family die?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e45b8a88-59d8-4170-8130-0c5efabe5d7f"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about your craft.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b0963d7-9425-4e22-99e4-beef20e67550"
msgid "\\\"Hold up your end of the bargain.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ffa0dc09-4177-4d0d-bf4e-599d84a80e2b"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"Your lies will be punished!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a650c7fe-ce27-4a81-8c39-befea253932e"
msgid "\\\"We'll speak later. Get to work.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dcddb0d1-08e1-4e4c-b76d-26cddba84031"
msgid "\\\"Let's put off this conversation until later.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8ec7628-e859-4e16-a5d2-74548999db8d"
msgid "\\\"Remind me where I can… collect the blood you need.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d70fe5d-9906-4bff-88e5-b4d3574ff1c7"
msgid "Approved of Varrask's revenge."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22015037-965b-4fb6-814e-fde01870afb5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Don't worry. The malicious woman deserved to die. You did the right thing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06c66e52-9935-4586-95e3-9933fc6be30d"
msgid "Supported Varrask's desire for revenge."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "558dcffb-52a5-4ef6-9e0e-35f66b6322d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're a bandit and a murderer, but you had the right to avenge your family.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1d718f6-8aaa-4214-ba5b-e47c9f22c59d"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! Decided to see how old "
"{d|Varrask}Varrask{/d} is doing? I've set up nicely here! I forge armor and "
"weapons for anyone who's got the coin. Though the fighters in these lands are weak "
"– some can't even lift a normal axe. They cannot hold a candle to my sons...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "906fcb2b-b5ea-48b4-9131-0399ccbeb840"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, patron. How can I serve you? Looking for a hatchet or a helmet?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc2629c1-e046-49bc-a86b-c5d59764165e"
msgid "\\\"What interest do you take in old Varrask?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50b8e418-f5ea-4c27-8d81-cf4419dbb6cb"
msgid ""
"\\\"What should I tell you? I have no idea... ask me what you want to know.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da3e09e9-8da5-423f-9f49-00723efbaaaf"
msgid ""
"{n}The old man looks at you angrily, but cautiously.{/n} \\\"Hm... It is truly so. "
"My family had faults, indeed. We committed robbery and murder. These are common "
"things in our kingdom. I didn't lose my family to bandits, but to a bunch of "
"inquisitors from Lastwall. Should I not long for revenge because I am a thief, "
"like my wife and my kids? What are you going to do with me now?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ae07a69-e288-4696-ade7-51486f0976ed"
msgid ""
"{n}The old man looks at you angrily and warily.{/n} \\\"Yes... it's true. Our "
"family committed some petty sins. But do I want revenge for my family less, "
"because I'm a little light-fingered?\\\" {n}Varrask licks his lips.{/n} \\\"So "
"what are you going to do now?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7e5f5ade-3227-4baa-b858-3d7776073293"
msgid ""
"{n}The old man slaps himself on the thigh, happy enough to dance.{/n} \\\"Yes! My "
"clan is avenged! Ha ha! Old Varrask outlived you, you arrogant witch! Oh, how I "
"would love to taste her blood! It must be so sweet. But I can't afford the "
"pleasure. I'm going to need every bit of it to harden Earthbreaker.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "150a013b-a11a-4618-97a2-316808567a40"
msgid ""
"{n}Varrask swells with pride.{/n} \\\"It's a hammer named Earthbreaker. Hold it "
"with both hands. Whatever you hit, the only thing left there will be a greasy "
"spot. I gave it to my son when it got too heavy for me. He named it Nibbler. You "
"see, its head has beak-like wedges made of inubrix. Inubrix is a very hard "
"celestial metal. It cuts through iron like a knife cuts through butter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ba67f92-816c-45a0-9c9e-b3b2ab76926e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Inubrix. It's a celestial metal that looks a little like lead. It's pretty "
"rare, but you might find just enough in the {g|Technic League}Technic League{/g} "
"camp.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca80cfcf-6375-46d2-832b-d29b7eba9609"
msgid ""
"{n}Varrask grows grim, and his eyes start watering.{/n} \\\"I left my house. Went "
"to a tribe that had ordered weapons from me. As I got back to my house, I was "
"ambushed. They'd hid in my own yard! I have no idea how I survived. But I saw the "
"dead bodies of my wife and children with my own eyes. I had four lads, all of age, "
"all carried weapons. Three daughters too, and they knew how to fight.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04109074-fdb3-4f68-9b18-64ba9e0a9a73"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's nothing to tell. It's a traditional orc thing. Any decent battle gear "
"must be big, heavy, and tough. Fragile and brittle materials don't last. The orcs' "
"strength rages and storms! Small and light objects get lost all the time. That's "
"why orcs need a weapon that can't be broken in half on the enemy's head. Orc armor "
"must be even sturdier, because they fight each other far more often than they "
"fight their enemies. Thin armor would result in many deaths among the tribe.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a371cf52-d04a-44f0-b6c1-c56ae5c37e3f"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's nothing to tell. Barbarians think all good things must be sturdy, "
"heavy and big. Fragile and brittle things are no match for their strength – they "
"have so much, and it begs to come out. Small and light things are easily lost in "
"battle. A weapon must be sturdy, or a warrior might break it over the enemy's "
"head. And armor must be even sturdier.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8769e406-1c23-4ee0-afe3-d4273681794f"
msgid ""
"\\\"I was born in {g|Hold of Belkzen}Belkzen{/g}. I had to take off when I was "
"still a snot-nosed kid. Got in a fight with some bonehead... And I hit him. I "
"mean, not the bonehead. Was aiming at him, but I hit chief's son. And he suddenly "
"went and died. I had to run away as far as I could, just to stay alive.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7afc7a6d-2af4-4e73-968f-abb68893c62b"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you say. I'll gladly tell you all that I know. What else can an old man "
"like me do?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21cbfa77-6283-4232-a420-b7e937c34eb2"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you say. We old people have nothing to do but tell stories. Come, I'll tell "
"you one.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89040717-eb4e-481c-ba5a-faa93a889c9b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect! Now I have enough material. But here comes the hard part. I need "
"blood. An enemy's blood. The creator of this hammer hardened it in the blood of a "
"sworn enemy. This made the hammer incredibly powerful and furious. Should you want "
"to reforge it, it will require another such hardening.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5136625f-e108-4e7f-9c1f-286ff444ba35"
msgid ""
"\\\"They say there's a secluded outpost out there in the forest. The huntress that "
"lives there gives shelter to travelers. I think her name is Dumra. I hear an armed "
"girl is staying there. She's missing two fingers. That's her!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a4fe85b-74f8-45d1-8310-75941de12421"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc has a dark, angry, and threatening grimace. It's not hard to "
"believe he once lived a life of robbery.{/n} \\\"It means I'll die as I lived, "
"with a weapon in my hands. Nulgreth, see Old Varrask die in his final battle!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f143a3da-8ee1-4bba-b4ec-554a084a067f"
msgid ""
"{n}The old man gives a sigh of relief.{/n} \\\"I appreciate it. I'm old, but I "
"still want to walk the earth a little longer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53f760ee-5642-4627-a52b-7f20042480e6"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc heaves a sigh of relief.{/n} \\\"Thank you. I'm an old man, but I "
"still wish to trample the ground a little longer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52bc2072-c7a1-4a03-9b08-5eacb4fe360d"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc grows grim, and his voice becomes dull and soft.{/n} \\\"My eldest "
"was a strong one. He could hit an ogre with a hammer so hard that it would leave "
"behind its teeth along with its boots. But they are gone... Both the son and his "
"hammer. For twelve generations my family has owned this hammer. It's a relic, you "
"could say. I wish I could fix it, but how? And for whom?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "07119f80-bd2d-4b0f-92f4-26a3a33c54d7"
msgid ""
"\\\"It was a fine hammer. Nobody knows how many skulls it cracked. It broke the "
"day my son was killed. The hammer's head cracked all over from a magical blow. It "
"needs to be reforged, but where can I possibly get any inubrix? Without that, the "
"hammer is just an ordinary sledge. You can use it to hammer in posts, or tie it to "
"your neck and drown.... Hmm... The {g|Technic League}Technic League{/g} is bound "
"to have some. If you come across one of their camps, you might find inubrix there."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b534a7bc-080d-4b76-a104-4e4251a56fd2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm old. Most of my enemies are dead. But there's one that's still breathing. "
"The witch that slew my family. Oh, how I would love to harden the hammer in her "
"blood! I could never defeat her, though. But I know she's been spotted in an "
"isolated outpost in the forest. She has a distinguishing mark – she's missing two "
"fingers. And she's got the look of a devil.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "899349d0-2ba8-4a61-b6bf-1d489e1ed0c6"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you slay the wretch, collect her blood and bring it to me. I'll give you "
"the reforged hammer in exchange. I don't have anyone to leave it to. This will "
"make you a clan member, avenging my family.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7984cf6-8c7c-4ff2-9c9b-44a1cd537fa0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I settled in Lastwall. A godforsaken place. Orcs are treated like scum. – "
"It's understandable, I guess. Orcs kill many more people than you can count. I "
"moved in near the Thorn Scar's territory, out of harm's way. They're a tribe, or "
"what's left of one. They worship {g|Lamashtu}Mother Lamashtu{/g}, so they stay "
"busy. They needed new armor and weapons every year. And so I worked my force in "
"return for their protection.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86a5ef63-cdfc-4cfb-b98b-bf053ee4c64a"
msgid ""
"\\\"So I ended up in Lastwall. An awful place. Anyone with orc blood is a misfit. "
"Which is fair enough. Orcs have killed so many of them… But I settled there, "
"started my business, and a family.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "264d78a8-16e9-4041-b719-629a3d9b1395"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's how I learned my craft. That's what the Thorn Scar used to say: 'Big "
"thumbs up to Varrask's hands! Big thumbs up to Varrask's head!' Which meant they "
"respected me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e74ccde4-436d-48ee-b005-bae8c448c181"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll get to work immediately. {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}, when Verex the Blood God asks of me whether my revenge for my family's "
"death was bloody enough, I can tell him the best assassin I've ever met was "
"entrusted with the task.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c13015d-bb4a-488e-93f6-71d896ea33b8"
msgid ""
"\\\"More of the scoundrels kept coming. I guess they'd tracked us down, waited to "
"catch us by surprise. And I guess I was lucky... they didn't kill me with the "
"others. I fought them off and got lost in the woods. Walked for a long time "
"without a road... and finally ended up here. You know the rest. But the gods "
"didn't see a long life for those bandits. – I heard they're all dead. Only their "
"chief is still breathing, the fingerless witch.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d4fa01a-d869-4c5c-88a8-8ffa4c075589"
msgid ""
"\\\"I remember my pledge. Your army will have something to cover their soft flesh."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a627ab5-3d66-4bf3-a526-9a2b4813aa44"
msgid ""
"{n}Varrask shows his enormous fists on disproportionately large arms.{/n} \\\"You "
"see, a blacksmith must be strong, even by orc standards... Just like his tools. "
"Big, heavy, and tough. And patient. There's the catch. That's why the craftsmen "
"are valued so much. I'm telling you, they can't even hit us!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a111e578-5d42-4e17-a684-fb0a9df70949"
msgid ""
"\\\"And a blacksmith, I figure, needs to be like his armor – sturdy and strong.\\"
"\" {n}Varrask shows you his huge fists and absurdly thick arms.{/n} \\\"And "
"patient. Barbarians have trouble with this last one. That's why a master is so "
"valuable.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69220d78-6870-49f8-8476-b982c5968b2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"The bandits had greater numbers. They must have tracked us and timed their "
"strike carefully. You see, our outpost was isolated. They waited for me to leave, "
"then slew everyone else. And then they waited to ambush me. I was lucky to escape. "
"I took the hammer from my elder son's hands, fought them off, and fled into the "
"woods. After that, once my head cooled, I started hunting them. Eventually I lost "
"them in the swamps by the {g|Kamelands}Kamelands{/g}. You know what happened next. "
"I heard things turned out badly for the bandits. They're all dead except their "
"leader. The fingerless wretch is still alive.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d64d34bb-6ec7-4c28-aacf-80a2cc2dc69d"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc grins happily.{/n} \\\"I'm glad I trusted someone like you with my "
"revenge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ef3e1e4-bc65-490d-8546-42fb191d5cca"
msgid "\\\"What happened to you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c1a07f1-b1f7-48c2-9bb0-7d1de0c5f2eb"
msgid "\\\"What is your name?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f4965dbb-dc01-4fc8-8e3c-a3bdebfda23a"
msgid "Killed old half-orc Varrask for no reason."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f21c6e43-7b0f-42ee-8464-0888c1d81651"
msgid "Killed old Varrask without any cause."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca624a83-a4d8-42ab-949b-73c5ae0a6a0a"
msgid ""
"[Attack] \\\"You look like you're at death's door. Let me give you a little push.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd56668d-51f5-44d6-84a9-8c2a679eb116"
msgid "\\\"I won't distract you from your woes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "facc1ab4-c193-45ba-ae7e-126f722440d1"
msgid "\\\"Here are your tools.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06c5ad8e-9aa1-4cca-9d25-5799a9b8d909"
msgid ""
"{n}An elderly half-orc looks at you without any friendliness. His clothes are "
"covered with spots, and he looks exhausted and sickly.{/n} \\\"What are you "
"looking at? Can't you see, master Varrask is not well. On my last legs. Go along, "
"leave me to my unhappy fate.\\\" {n}Despite the cantankerous tone, there is "
"certain confidence in the half-orc's voice, especially in how proudly he spoke the "
"word 'master'.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2897e0d7-3905-41dd-b614-2c02f1a2dbb6"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc harrumphs brashly in response, but his eyes seem disappointed.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31556871-e14c-47ae-933d-143af7fe9e4d"
msgid ""
"\\\"What happened... It was a calamity! I was going about my business, and then I "
"fell ill. Cut down by a fever. I'd been burning up for three weeks. I thought I "
"would die more than once. A local merchant saved me... a kind soul, damn him. He "
"saved me, but not for free. Took everything I had as payment – even my precious "
"work tools, the last of my treasures!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b565b401-691f-4af2-8040-ac99f22020e2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm useless like this. What good am I to anyone? But if I got my tools back "
"I'd be quite all right! I used to make such weapons and armor – they sold faster "
"than I could make them. But without my tools I'm useless. If you tried to use a "
"regular hammer to forge like I do, you'd just ruin a good thing. I'd bend the "
"tongs, and wouldn't make anything worth putting my name to. That trickster got "
"everything I need!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5618bf3-f531-4e33-8aec-e577fe154fc4"
msgid ""
"{n}Varrask looks at you with eyes full of despair and clenches his huge fists.{/n} "
"\\\"Old Varrask is listening. What are we going to talk about?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34571bdd-ecbd-4dbf-89ec-c1c9b746481d"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc touches the tools tenderly, as if he can't believe his eyes, and "
"then clutches them as tightly as he can.{/n} \\\"Can I have them back? Really? "
"Thank you so much! Well now I'll be all right! I'll have food on the table, I'll "
"get rid of this damn fever, and do what I promised my children! And I'll keep my "
"promise. Give me a place to set up a shop, and I'll work hard to repay you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29274436-1889-4d4d-9c31-4b83335e74d9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Varrask. Varrask the Wildfist, they call me. I was once an armor and weapons "
"maker. I'm more of a corpse than a master now. Some evil people took everything "
"from me. My family, my house, my craft... Even took my tools. Everything.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6bae574a-4068-4313-9dd6-4ab4d0d0f470"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc pierces you with his angry eyes.{/n} \\\"Listen, I can tell you "
"got money... maybe you need an armorer? If you help me, I'll serve you. I'll make "
"formidable weapons for you! Ones that just beg for enemy blood! But first I need "
"my tools back.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c6c73c45-a6ba-47cf-b360-dd482b6efd01"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"Varrask sends his regards.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a3b1d27a-a258-4a31-9ae6-bff38e5ae9a0"
msgid "\\\"Have you heard the name Varrask?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2965cb35-df2b-4f60-ae93-aec39eddc99d"
msgid "\\\"What has this criminal done?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a4df8f7-b720-400d-9e22-15f709edaf31"
msgid "Killed the Lastwall inquisitor at Varrask's request."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e43847b-4360-4b59-9eb2-5a9f63a54a04"
msgid "Killed the inquisitor of Iomedae at Varrask's request."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc69927e-fd2a-458d-beeb-6f85a8e0b83a"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"Enough talk. I've come for your blood.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "511ddb92-1da2-453a-919e-945d3f93658e"
msgid "\\\"With a common traveler. Never mind me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2863cd4-a28a-4733-bbf5-acd46ac49e88"
msgid "Killed the Lastwall inquisitor at Varrask's request."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83866ef4-d463-410d-9e0f-aed7f65647b2"
msgid "Killed the inquisitor of Iomedae at Varrask's request."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd1525e8-8e91-4900-9345-ee9e9eb43ab9"
msgid ""
"[Attack] \\\"I need Varrask, and he wants your blood. It's as simple as that.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fdda44ab-c124-415c-975e-f4e1257ba63e"
msgid "\\\"Varrask is on the right side of the law now. He won't hurt anyone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19b2112d-ebdd-4a7a-81d3-f48d9c06a069"
msgid "Handed Varrask over to the Lastwall inquisition."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "650b4853-8c4b-4ce6-9e01-569cdcc1410d"
msgid "Handed Varrask over to the inquisition."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1dc9fa8-4178-4694-8b79-b50d378333aa"
msgid "\\\"Hand me the map. I'll point to the rascal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe38deec-5994-4ed9-8c36-c1c3318ed71d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am {name}, the {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen} of these lands. Who are you?\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77eb6841-bc1f-41f8-a583-80ff743c7033"
msgid "\\\"You must do as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34551221-3e1f-4558-8aba-b9bad23f2580"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl is eyeing you expectantly, her hand laying casually over her weapon. "
"The hand is missing its two smallest fingers.{/n} \\\"Who do I have the pleasure "
"of addressing?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43c71588-0522-4a91-adc8-18b98008a342"
msgid "{n}The girl looks at you with distrust.{/n} \\\"Hm... Whatever you say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2120b876-76b3-4077-bd71-a2f5c5533eb1"
msgid ""
"\\\"The half-orc formed a gang with his wife, sons, and daughters. {g|Iomedae}"
"Iomedae{/g} alone knows how many people he killed for their money, how many "
"children he deprived of parents... His whole family was awash in bloodshed until "
"my comrades and I tracked them down and put an end to the violence. Only Varrask "
"managed to escape.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34d32a77-f81e-4bf2-8d0b-223a1d584f3c"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl looks eagerly at you.{/n} \\\"Of course, I know the {d|Varrask}name{/"
"d}. He is the criminal I'm after! What do you know of him?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ffed27b-f99c-4ad2-823e-2e8d583c2c4e"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl studies you for a moment and then speaks with regret:{/n} \\\"Do you "
"think I'll give up on my mission just like that? I won't. I know he's alive. I "
"know where he is. He's in your capital, right? Even if he's not there, he must be "
"somewhere nearby. I shall keep looking until I fulfill my vow.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98d873e3-218c-4d15-b0ad-857e299f4e1f"
msgid ""
"{n}She narrows her eyes as she draws a breath, as if she's trying to sniff out "
"Varrask.{/n} \\\"Thank you. {g|Iomedae}Iomedae{/g} must have brought you to me. "
"The bloody bastard will finally be punished.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22f316a4-0053-4e71-afd4-895ebb09f288"
msgid ""
"\\\"I couldn't let the criminal go unpunished, and swore to pursue him until one "
"of us falls dead. I only here lost his track, at the edge of the swamps of the {g|"
"Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}... You would hardly take an interest in this matter "
"if you weren't involved. Do you know anything about Varrask? Where is he now? Say "
"the word, and I'll rid your lands of the bastard.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ceb4761c-5a82-4f67-ba54-2c0a099ac71c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am the Lastwall inquisitor, {g|Iomedae}Iomedae's{/g} servant. I'm looking "
"for a dangerous criminal. His trail leads to the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. "
"The rascal is the only remaining member of the gang that spread terror across the "
"lands. I took a vow to put an end to their bloody tale.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc986f40-8ea5-4df3-8190-e46e7556d059"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl sighs.{/n} \\\"Thank you for not keeping me from my task. My little "
"holiday is over! Varrask is in one of the local settlements – and one step away "
"from being arrested! His time will soon come. Farewell, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f571e9c-a833-44d7-9132-7dca12eda03c"
msgid "This is the blood of the murderer who took lives of Varrask's family."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2a1946b-26b8-4475-a97f-f9646eca29e7"
msgid "The Blood of the Murderer of Varrask's Family"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62a9d180-75dd-4828-a84a-91e6198231a1"
msgid ""
"Ordinary-looking metal, rather soft. Who would have thought that Varrask would "
"need it to craft a deadly weapon?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eff2cc2b-505b-4a99-9489-f9ac1640960f"
msgid "Several ingots of soft grey metal."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b8d9474-f0bb-40b2-bbbf-00815682739d"
msgid "Inubrix"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d133c8c-e7db-4ca6-8865-a6d8896ddd03"
msgid "Varrask's blacksmithing tools"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6bd7cd79-9a30-4b8f-a4c3-7c53cc58ef2d"
msgid "Varrask's Tools"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed52dc2f-6d63-4294-a165-eae2e8665fbf"
msgid "\\\"Thank you. Keep at it, Varrask.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77a7cb10-847f-473b-9576-f398b6174701"
msgid "\\\"I have a specific request for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "848979a9-2f42-4fc2-aa20-1d2b66a654ff"
msgid "\\\"Get out of my lands. Your service is no longer required.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7cb2783-8924-4117-8177-719ef3ef81f5"
msgid "\\\"A two-handed sword.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7cf1a1c1-1d07-41c3-aea0-0eb0fabc87a0"
msgid "\\\"A two-handed axe.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8d14167-d0a6-492c-913e-8d99435307b2"
msgid "\\\"Armor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63364701-c85e-4156-a962-0da7bf39360f"
msgid "\\\"Give me a Kellid-style weapon.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cbe3f1aa-cbab-48c4-8ae6-b032d0f2367d"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're familiar with orc weapons and armor... can you make something like that?"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29d719a5-35ff-42d0-871e-e6e09e3cc174"
msgid "\\\"A two-handed mace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ba33657-9a93-4a8d-bbd8-04ef97e9295f"
msgid "\\\"Forget it. Make whatever your heart tells you to.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1f81df3-8e3d-45b0-9dab-d547dd910e3c"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! I have a gift for you. "
"This is an orc weapon, and they know a thing or two about war.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e02fd3e9-4aa6-49b2-abc5-c95b6b1ee3ff"
msgid ""
"\\\"Here, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! Earthbreaker has "
"been reforged and hardened. It has drunk itself full of enemy's blood. This weapon "
"means business. Let your enemies fear for their empty skulls! No helmet can "
"withstand a blow from this monster!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48f16b1b-dd0a-4b84-8be8-3c677d860e2f"
msgid ""
"\\\"However, I could give you something much more impressive.\\\" {n}The old man "
"gives you a wink and a bloodthirsty grin.{/n} \\\"A weapon worthy of {g|Gorum}"
"Gorum's{/g} herald! It's a family relic. Come to my forge, and I'll tell you more."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac2d8a51-6e19-44e9-8f9e-3451faecc110"
msgid ""
"\\\"With such weapons you can go on raids and protect your lands! Everything has "
"been tempered in lamb blood, with proper prayers to all the proper gods. "
"Everything is done with care for you personally!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "743a519b-1e06-4e65-a219-c1ef7fdc9dea"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've completed my work, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. Earthbreaker has been reforged and hardened! And I swear, it is now "
"even more deadly than before. Please, accept this glorious weapon as a token of my "
"gratitude for avenging me. Let your enemies fear for their empty skulls! This "
"hammer will make you invincible.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "edd38284-e1fa-46cb-ba2e-5d435664cdca"
msgid ""
"\\\"Anyway, it was amusing work. But I could give you something even more "
"impressive. – A weapon worthy of {g|Gorum}Gorum's{/g} herald! But I'll need your "
"help with something... Come by if you're interested!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fa7b536-2b9e-4c1d-8a5f-b25523de2a82"
msgid ""
"{n}The {d|Varrask}half-orc{/d} bows diligently, trying to adhere to etiquette.{/n} "
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I come bearing gifts. "
"A sign of my gratitude for taking an old man into your service.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad32ef98-473c-4303-970d-40a44ee2a078"
msgid ""
"{n}For several moments the half-orc looks at you, baffled. He starts to breathe "
"heavily, trying to puff himself up, makes a few angry faces... But then nothing. "
"The old man's shoulders drop, and he turns away silently.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a8f562a-87a7-4f87-8969-447f2ef38e0e"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc's face becomes serious.{/n} \\\"Well. What are we making? Armor, "
"weapons?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0e49006-3c35-40c0-92d8-f1bcc76ef02f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Gladly. When a weapon or armor is made for a good fight, the work does itself. "
"And I know that many great fights await you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b6e9487f-ef5a-4016-a9dc-501f9dc1109c"
msgid "\\\"As you say. I'll keep working.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c6797211-1f07-4e63-82c4-27f0c0f6ce21"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc winks at you.{/n} \\\"Why strike with one hand when you have two, "
"right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7aa6682-107c-4472-908e-d57d70383f33"
msgid ""
"\\\"A good warrior always has good armor – otherwise he doesn't live long. I'll "
"get right to work!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bea1d3a4-2bd9-4643-bdf2-8827000999e4"
msgid "\\\"Sturdy, frightening, and elegantly simple. Got it, will do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50cc670a-60d2-4030-ba09-2d7234259e85"
msgid ""
"\\\"To be sure! I can make you some first class gear – you'll be like an orc chief!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6761ad64-006b-4dfa-a996-b4210ddee786"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's something else... I have all I need to start reforging Earthbreaker. "
"You'd better not give me any big orders for a while, so I can concentrate on the "
"hammer... and make sure you don't forget my payment!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d994ce9a-cfb9-4205-9c8b-73d2979350b3"
msgid "\\\"Well, I'll get to work on Earthbreaker then.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41a1c299-98dc-4155-a375-18efc9ce766d"
msgid "\\\"Jubilost is a renowned scholar and author. Talk to him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15208538-8da5-4f1b-8e85-9d3295dc20de"
msgid "\\\"Linzi loves stories. You can talk to her.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dbda3e45-7d6e-411b-8469-0cea96de691a"
msgid "\\\"And so we meet. What next?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9792d4a7-6042-4975-a932-234a5b789cc5"
msgid "\\\"Who are you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1716a70b-8042-41c1-9003-8b248ed53b78"
msgid "\\\"I need to go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "09a09b37-655c-4dfe-9508-208e5e21c66b"
msgid "[Remain silent]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "844dc092-df0b-437e-b7f5-f4be04524e16"
msgid "\\\"Your story is truly incredible, Shaynih'a.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1447a4c-7a3f-42b0-a21e-4a8f535a7c5a"
msgid "\\\"I believe you, Shaynih'a!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d542362d-6a16-4a18-8a12-f100144177c1"
msgid "\\\"I'm sorry, but I have to go!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cec5b587-ec70-4c2f-9758-9225d38729a6"
msgid "[Listen to the story]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13fa07d4-0857-48bc-9057-b703ba33361c"
msgid ""
"{n}A young woman catches your eye. She looks like she has come from far away. She "
"approaches with a dancing gait and addresses you, speaking in an unfamiliar drawl."
"{/n} \\\"May the Perfect Human protect you! I am happy to meet you, o worthy one.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52c9a12f-8146-4975-9c16-343015770d74"
msgid ""
"{n}Shaynih'a notices you and smiles broadly.{/n} \\\"Destiny has brought us "
"together once more, o worthy one! This is no mere coincidence! The Perfect Human "
"is telling us that our paths are deeply intertwined, like snakes coiling around "
"each other in an act of love!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e30fc1b-54c7-4a4b-8584-16dd4e4c8348"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perhaps I chose wrongly when I decided to become a muse. Until I can answer "
"this question, I shall remain true to the calling I've always pursued — "
"weaponsmithing. If, in your kindness, you could indulge me once more, and grant me "
"a workshop in these lands – then I swear to you, I shall make for you truly "
"miraculous weapons, the likes of which these lands have never seen! But for now, "
"let me tell you a story that our conversation reminded me of...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a84bf025-90da-4d2f-baa0-2a62b7ca4637"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ah! Let us see, then, how learned this man truly is! I hope this esteemed "
"opium inhaler will enthrall me with the depth of his knowledge and the richness of "
"his verse!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea1b0d92-115e-41b6-87c5-f1601040c41d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am grateful, o worthy one! I shall relate to you the story of my ancestor Vu "
"Balak. Let us see if she is nimble enough to write it all down without omitting "
"any of the colorful details!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68956574-cd36-4e3e-91cd-27f52384743a"
msgid ""
"\\\"You, o worthy one, can help me find my calling. I am beset by doubt — what if, "
"by choosing the path of a master smith, I am making a terrible mistake? After all, "
"I, Shaynih'a the Tulip, have seen many wonders, the likes of which your humble "
"realm has never heard of. And I wish to recount them. But alas, I cannot write in "
"your language! For this reason I require a writer, and a worthy one!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68f697d8-988a-4948-8fe7-24eee9394fe0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am a traveler from the Impossible Kingdoms of Vudra! I was led here by the "
"will of the gods, by my love of amazing adventures, and by the promise of "
"inescapable retribution uttered by my former husband, who has since become a "
"revered sage and a dead man. I never doubted that my path would bring me to a most "
"worthy ruler, one who would help me. — And now you stand before me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a65fe941-e7ca-498e-843e-9c2a720bcff5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Go, o worthy one! Our paths shall cross again, for that is the will of the "
"gods!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a200e5d0-b2e7-41d9-811f-382faef369ea"
msgid ""
"\\\"My name is Shaynih'a, but you may simply call me the Tulip, as all the best of "
"my friends do! Ever since the sun rose today, I've had a feeling that I shall take "
"part in a grand encounter — one that shall change our fates forever! And, lo, it "
"is so. Praised be the Perfect Human for this gift he has bestowed upon these eyes "
"that see the future!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acea4fd2-6e0a-4f06-8fb0-791cb70c1302"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have witnessed master Chokhek cover emptiness in tattoos, and a human grew "
"out of them, for these patterns were so intricate and deep that the ink became "
"more important than the flesh. Trust me, for I have woven the tale of these events "
"myself! Perhaps I have been destined to become the muse of a great writer! If, o "
"worthy one, you find a suitable scribe for me, I shall pay you back handsomely "
"with my wisdom and advice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08d7d790-f76f-4315-bb13-19a3dfb42e9b"
msgid ""
"\\\"At a feast, Mahka once swallowed a whole tiger and the beast's rage and hunger "
"burned in his veins – until, consumed by it, he ate himself. Years went by, and a "
"young prince by the name of Purusav Vagbha destroyed Mahka's empire, slaying all "
"of his generals. For Purusav was a reincarnation of Mahka, bent on restoring the "
"empire to its true glory. Eventually, Purusav was defeated in battle and his "
"empire died with him, but it was Mahka Abihcara who spawned the terrible race of "
"rakshasa – cunning beasts, half human and half animal. Trust me, for I have met "
"these creatures many times!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17e39f90-ced8-4876-ba71-e15973764b84"
msgid ""
"\\\"Mahka always dreamed of leaving a mark on the world. And he did, but not in "
"the way he expected. It was not on the battlefield that his name became "
"immortalized, but in bed, surrounded by concubines. Each may be mistaken in "
"choosing their own path, even the wisest of all! Perhaps I am destined to be your "
"advisor, o most worthy one? Or your lover? Go now, for I need to be alone to think "
"upon my words.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e8735f8-427a-4061-a6df-7fa3b178ba54"
msgid ""
"\\\"I greet you, o most worthy opiumist! I have heard much of your wisdom. Now, "
"lend me your ears, and I shall tell you a story that…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca803c5d-b408-4a50-b1e9-0f5a2d637c28"
msgid ""
"\\\"I greet you, young Linzi! They say that you are writing a book. That is most "
"fortunate, for I can embellish it with a few stories that I have lived through "
"during my adventures! Once I met a monk from the House of Perfection. He was an "
"ascetic, and hadn't eaten for four whole years...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b5aff198-f7c8-4996-9568-9a9b7e1f34ea"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just a moment! Why on earth do you call me an opiumist?! Who came up with "
"that?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "10794a16-d333-4485-a666-92f84aa5f2fc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ermm, isn't every learned man supposed to be an opiumist? Back in Vudra, I met "
"many noble and illustrious scholars. Each and every one of them inhaled the smoke "
"of opium, so as to lose his mind, that the surrounding world with its lowly "
"impulses would not distract him from his scientific endeavors. I have noticed how "
"empty your eyes are, and...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3fa3c363-2e02-4e50-a456-5b41c7f82929"
msgid ""
"\\\"Never have I inhaled anything, nor do I intend to. And I find it highly "
"unlikely that a whole caste of intellectuals would willingly expose themselves to "
"such substances in order to lose their minds!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d1be9325-ff0e-47c0-96c9-38b3bfab2967"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is as true as the fact that the fastest black genies can outrun light "
"beams, thus evading the touch of the sun, which is fatal to them. Trust me, for I "
"have seen this with my own eyes!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "464c380c-3f78-4548-8e78-723c1eaa309e"
msgid ""
"\\\"It seems to me that you are spinning these wild tales on the go. I very much "
"doubt they have anything to do with your actual travels. I have no interest in "
"such things.\\\" {n}Jubilost turns his back in anger.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5ac9a02-ce1b-4458-b0f3-046ddc643240"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hold on, four years? Are you sure that he ate absolutely nothing? Maybe it "
"was, well, you know, some sort of moderate fasting? More like a diet? Like when "
"you do eat, but only a little bit…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e4ab7e4-78e8-4a22-bffe-767db051c9db"
msgid ""
"\\\"No no no, why would you think that? Breaking his askesis would have been a "
"shameful weakness! He did not eat at all. The people revered him as a pious and "
"enlightened man, whose spirit was very strong. But I, as soon as I met him, "
"suspected that he might be a liar! So I decided to expose him for what he truly "
"was. I...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b91fd27-3702-47de-ae6b-270c38ca1bca"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wait a moment. Four years?! That's impossible! If I skip breakfast and dinner, "
"my stomach hurts so badly I can't even walk! It's really hard to believe that the "
"monk could spend a whole four years like…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d2131b9-3210-47d1-8074-a56fa5f3715c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Young Linzi, by paying attention to such unimportant details, you run the risk "
"of missing the heart of the matter! As I was saying, I decided to bring the monk's "
"dishonesty to light. I enlisted the services of a shaitan who owed me a favor. "
"This earth genie stood in front of the monk and sang a song. And that very moment, "
"the hermit's face twitched, and a stream of stones erupted from his mouth! Imagine "
"this — he had swallowed rocks to fill up his stomach, to save himself the pangs of "
"hunger!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a01b93d6-6a8c-4639-87e0-2eb6cce61350"
msgid ""
"\\\"Mmm…He swallowed enough stones to fill his stomach? And lived? And never had "
"to eat again? As far as I know, it doesn't work like that… Of course, I'll write "
"down your story. But I doubt it will enjoy much success. It's just… too incredible "
"for our provincial audience!\\\" {n}With a guilty smile, Linzi turns away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3826ab80-a9d2-436a-b1de-c357da78f565"
msgid ""
"\\\"I thank you, o worthy one! It is such a shame that your path is the path of a "
"ruler, and not that of a wordsmith!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8b53a97-c929-427e-8ed1-2e0fd699eefc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm… Perhaps I'm not as good at telling stories as I thought. After all, "
"putting the events of the past into words is not quite the same thing as "
"witnessing them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ef4535c-ef45-4835-8df4-99a3a33d16e4"
msgid ""
"\\\"This truthful story was divined for me by a woman who had eyes on the palms of "
"her hands. Once upon a time, the sorcerer Mahka Abihcara decided to become "
"immortal. He started living his life with such purpose and determination, that his "
"essence would be imprinted on all of his future incarnations. Mahka studied the "
"arts and became a great conqueror. He consumed the flesh of his enemies and "
"servants to gain their strength.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37111350-5a37-4f54-9826-65108a77ff83"
msgid "\\\"Greetings, o worthy one!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7442967b-a848-416f-bd83-86b71fa22aea"
msgid "\\\"The locals are kind and warm-hearted. But also impatient.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb9f589b-a0b4-471c-8a67-4515ff695c69"
msgid "\\\"Perhaps, it is my destiny to be an owlbear trainer? Or a painter?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96843b63-bba8-4a52-82a4-32e8adc62990"
msgid "[Lie] \\\"Hassuf was delighted to read your letter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0155286c-f003-4641-b1d1-c4e4d46df0e5"
msgid ""
"[Tell the truth] \\\"Hassuf tore the letter into shreds, all the while cursing "
"your family.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f511188-378f-4462-9b4c-3f1a884d6d8b"
msgid "\\\"What sort of help do you need?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "67aa4bf0-20ef-4c0e-adda-c5a01cacf76b"
msgid "\\\"I would like to know more about you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43f22baf-c3ea-4e37-8e24-5a3ebc8c90b9"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48f410d4-86ce-47cb-99f6-52a08717399e"
msgid "\\\"What happened this time?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "36bb9a0d-3aba-4779-ae71-8ec2db48d585"
msgid ""
"[Tell the truth] \\\"The Storyteller has seen that your ancestor was a coward and "
"a failure, not a hero. I am sorry.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "526caf12-135c-402f-bd56-ebb1f57b49f5"
msgid ""
"[Lie] \\\"The Storyteller told me that your ancestor was a hero. However, he does "
"not know where to seek the monster's heart.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f3f9b0a-1863-4f28-9a69-88007619f1b0"
msgid "\\\"How did you end up here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24d1949a-68a0-4e47-9866-ab83cb57fced"
msgid "\\\"You were a ruler?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3dcfd794-623e-4525-a685-db4603f484d6"
msgid "\\\"Tell me of your homeland.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87f7184b-d49c-448b-be00-afa59da5eb60"
msgid "\\\"It seems to me there are quite a few… exaggerations in your stories.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6400f46a-d650-4ddc-afb5-e7d60b92106f"
msgid "\\\"Do you enjoy living in my lands?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c17a1a0a-b50a-40fc-b212-3586ca8ff71f"
msgid "\\\"At times, you are insolent towards me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2dc83155-75ca-4b6d-b2fa-fb31c5b98644"
msgid ""
"\\\"You've talked about the treasures of your homeland. How would one go about "
"trying to find them?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b96685ac-7970-42c3-90c2-a4f68cf620cd"
msgid "\\\"Tell me of Vudra.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57f43851-709f-483e-b644-2e89213250ab"
msgid "\\\"Let's talk of your homeland some other time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a9eb89f-5691-4afc-91b2-9c0a31289578"
msgid "\\\"Let's do this another time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a62c1c5a-8df1-4b11-b12e-1804a820f9cc"
msgid "\\\"I'd like to listen to your story some other time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a40c4dd4-2d2e-45f3-82a3-9b223d085a35"
msgid "\\\"No, not now. Maybe later.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e40cec20-5a59-412c-8dbf-7ea7b100f684"
msgid "[Keep listening no matter what]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a55b5e35-e0b8-40f0-8092-e941058f882b"
msgid "\\\"I can't go on. That's enough.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16a5a6ce-6e09-42a0-8584-422f09b50db7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think you haven't finished your story… The one about the genie-binder.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "93de3b58-6545-4816-a27e-47dd4350f8f0"
msgid "\\\"You wanted to tell me a story. I'm all ears.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b7301b2-58a1-40b0-a45e-18a9f23feac2"
msgid ""
"\\\"You wanted to tell me something about a spear and one of your ancestors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6117720d-4355-4eef-9571-d0f082d04c19"
msgid "\\\"Ahem… Let's change the subject.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8f2a0fc-2544-4786-ad6a-90a70ed9e537"
msgid "\\\"That's more than enough, I can see where this is going.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b7eb6db-f464-434d-8c17-9b05847fe07d"
msgid "\\\"Oh no. Please, stop.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e982166-2339-4c55-8a62-21000ff0c8c2"
msgid "\\\"Very interesting. Let's talk about something else.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fafe613-5f93-404a-b165-7be831f13dbb"
msgid "\\\"A simple 'yes' would have sufficed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1124e10b-08f5-423a-9bdf-b7e1927bef5f"
msgid ""
"\\\"{d|Shainiha}Shaynih'a{/d} is happy to see you, o most worthy one! Rest your "
"legs and listen to my stories – that is, if you've nothing more important to do… "
"such as assisting me in a delicate situation...\\\" {n}Shaynih'a gives you a sly "
"wink.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d745c0aa-4444-48a8-9782-137853559100"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am pleased to see you again, o worthy one. What brings you to {d|Shainiha}"
"me{/d}?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a45a5846-9457-47a3-af1a-71afd0c7f642"
msgid ""
"{n}The Vudrani proffers a small scroll.{/n} \\\"This was written by my father. It "
"was meant for a family that has lived for centuries, near the home of my relatives "
"in Absalom. Life has scattered us all across Golarion, but we never gave up hope "
"of reuniting with those we once knew so well. My father asked me to pass this "
"letter to a member of this fine family, if I should ever happen to stumble across "
"one.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96b7e5cc-17d9-4093-9949-1ca8617aa056"
msgid ""
"{n}Shaynih'a peers at you in surprise, but her melodious words come off her lips "
"effortlessly:{/n} \\\"He wasn't pleased? How sad… This reminds me of a story that "
"took place a long, long time ago. Please, let me enlighten you, o worthy one…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a143c0ab-abe6-42fe-b14b-d4a05a78139d"
msgid ""
"{n}Shaynih'a smiles joyfully.{/n} \\\"I knew that wise Hassuf would be most "
"pleased to receive news from home. All of this reminds me of a wonderful story, "
"one that took place a long, long time ago…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0993d357-ebec-4039-93f8-ac2d56bfbc97"
msgid ""
"\\\"There once lived a mighty warrior by the name of Khorkhor. His mother was a "
"white shark, and his father the most lustful – and most inventive – of all "
"mortals. Khorkhor inherited his fearlessness from his father, and from his mother "
"his strength and thirst for blood. His skin was as white as milk, and his sharp, "
"crooked teeth grew in three rows. There wasn't a warrior in the world who was "
"stronger or more warlike, and he served the Maharaja loyally.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41460195-6607-41f8-a038-330275eea0b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"This story teaches us that however long and difficult the most worthy path may "
"be, happiness, honor and triumph always lie at the end of it. Our family has "
"feuded with the Hassuf for many centuries. Many of his kinsmen were slain by our "
"hand. Once we'd destroyed almost all of them, but we gained wisdom and sought a "
"truce. I am glad that this news brought joy to the wise Hassuf, for he was noble "
"enough to recognize suffering as a sign of enlightenment, for which we work so "
"tirelessly, in doing both good and evil. Go now, o worthy one, for my heart has "
"gained peace, and my mind attained clarity, which is so important to a true master."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ef4b53f-943e-4c3c-a63f-8fc3a634db61"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you can see, both honor and disgrace may live in the same body, even though "
"it may belong to a person of worth. Why then cannot my family's deeds be both "
"honorable and disgraceful at the same time? Yes, my kinsmen have spilled much "
"blood, trying to destroy Hassuf's family, but it was also they who first decided "
"to seek out peace. I am grateful that I have been able to fulfill my duty no "
"matter the price. Go now, o worthy one, for my heart has gained peace, and my mind "
"attained clarity, which is so important to a true master.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5003cf22-2f79-4a1e-b057-1bd461076cc0"
msgid ""
"{n}Shaynih'a hands you a heavily worn piece of metal.{/n} \\\"I have heard, o "
"worthy one, that there lives a Storyteller in your realm, whose eyes can see into "
"the memories of things. Please, show him this. It was the tip of a spear that once "
"belonged to my esteemed ancestor Vu Balak. He was fated to live in interesting "
"times, for it was then that Kothogaz, the Dance of Disharmony, Spawn of Rovagug, "
"attacked Vudra. A million Vudrani came out to fight him, and amongst them was the "
"cleric Vu Balak.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42ed7c3b-04b0-4dcd-8811-6fd28223e5f2"
msgid ""
"{n}The Vudrani frowns, but then her face lightens, and a smile crosses her lips.{/"
"n} \\\"This is not news that I expected to hear. And still, is this news all that "
"bad? For it means that I need not sail back to Vudra, but may instead continue my "
"work here. This reminds me of a story...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d56b66a-da62-43df-b225-bba3fab9685b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm… Perhaps, I was wrong. The Perfect Human has sent the Storyteller to remind "
"us all of the great purpose that we have each been given. I must not leave for "
"Vudra to seek the shards of the heart of Kothogaz. I must follow my chosen path. I "
"shall recount to you a tale that is well-suited to the occasion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6848ffbd-3267-4547-87ff-d500bcdf5d06"
msgid ""
"\\\"Maharajah Khiben-Sald etched his glorious name in history when he conquered "
"the kingdoms of the genies. He spied on the descendants of the goddess Janasini, "
"the Garuda, and saw how they charmed snakes by playing their flutes. Through these "
"secrets, he discovered a way to charm and bind the genie to his will. Khiben-Sald "
"openly declared his new mastery for all to hear, and in doing so insulted their "
"race. Emissaries from the vizier of the djinni, the genie of air, came to demand "
"an apology from the wizard – only to be turned into slaves, and their bodies bound "
"in chains. It was then that the malik of the fire jinn, known as the efreet, sent "
"his assassins. They hid in a cloud of dust and approached as the mage was sleeping."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a7a72b4-1cee-477a-9df2-ad2683fa491c"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you can see, even a mortal can accomplish such great deeds that their "
"memory shall live on longer than the palaces built by the magical genie. This "
"thought has given me the strength to create a great masterpiece, one which will "
"ensure the memory of my name.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15737f81-3e03-4186-b162-98eeddfe93e0"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you can see, your actions may be seen as valorous by some and heinous by "
"others. For it is still forbidden to utter the name of Khiben-Sald among the "
"genie, so much is it hated! Let others think of you as a villain or lunatic – all "
"that truly matters is that enlightenment and devotion to your own goals blooms in "
"your heart! It is decided. I shall continue my work on my path to mastery, and "
"will create a masterpiece which will immortalize my name. May it serve you well, "
"whether I be praised for it by your friends or cursed for it by your enemies!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13140131-e61d-4207-9b20-7e23d08aba34"
msgid "\\\"I am flattered. Where should I begin?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d7f2112-076a-4cdc-af73-2b009de265ce"
msgid ""
"\\\"Until we meet again, o worthy one! It shall happen sooner than you think – the "
"Perfect Human has told me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7464017-7b6b-41e0-bfc2-3cd7bd6b9bb7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, they often say this about the Vudrani! Know then that the gods have given "
"me such lessons in humbleness, that it is quite against my nature to lie and "
"spread falsehood! Have you ever been to Niswan? It is the capital of the Island of "
"{g|Jalmeray}Jalmeray{/g}, the city of a thousand rooftops, above which flutters a "
"thousand silk banners. Not water, but the finest wines flow from their magnificent "
"jade fountains! There isn't a city more beautiful in this world! But Niswan's "
"greatest jewel is its Houses of Perfection, monasteries wherein the world's finest "
"warriors train.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34e05a25-a989-40f7-ab9d-f54f3b74ea94"
msgid ""
"{n}Shaynih'a's eyes glisten, and her movements become so smooth it's as if she's "
"beginning to dance. It takes her a moment to stop herself.{/n} \\\"Vudra is a land "
"of wonders never seen in your realm. As witnessed by the ten thousands lines of "
"Mizravrtta Brahmodya, as recorded by the wise Balazastrin from the words of the "
"goddess Likha. Vudra is fifty thousand years old. That means that it is far older "
"than the rest of the world, which grew up around Vudra to become its outer mantle, "
"like shells and weeds grow upon the bottom of a ship.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0765b6c4-8760-46b5-9198-553156d0862d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes, I am of the rajah caste, although I have lost all my lands.\\\" {n} "
"Shaynih'a speaks in a sing-song manner, as if she were reading a ballad or verse.{/"
"n} \\\"I once disturbed an ancient city of the dead, one that lay hidden, deep in "
"the jungle...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b8b4ceaa-3aa0-49c1-873f-5055db509444"
msgid ""
"\\\"Have you heard of Rudrakavala? High in the Vudrani mountains lies the Adhaarm "
"monastery. Its monks are pious and devout, their duty is to feed a dead man whose "
"green-skinned body floats over a black metal altar as he meditates. Back when "
"Rudrakavala was alive, he was the vilest of the rakshasa. However, one day he "
"stepped upon a river bank and became a seeker of truth. And thus he stood for a "
"thousand years, unmoved...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c59332ac-b97f-4fe8-9b1c-057494f0d16b"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is a wondrous land! You have such strange cuisine! And kobolds? "
"Incredible creatures, we do not have them in Vudra. And those insolent "
"creatures... Squirrels! I have never seen such fierce creatures!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8e7d0782-ca2d-41e6-896a-88129e23b2a5"
msgid ""
"{n}The Vudrani stares at you in surprise.{/n} \\\"Insolent? I am a rajah, same as "
"you. We are equals by caste. True, I hold no power, but what does that change? The "
"sage Ulvantha told me a story. Once, he was a groom to the moon herself, but he "
"angered her with his rapturous nature, and was expelled from the plane of "
"Nirvana...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2ab7ee7-144b-48ed-81f8-b44f78779270"
msgid ""
"{n}A sly smile crosses the Vudrani's face.{/n} \\\"Greed is a dangerous thing. "
"Have you ever heard of the Consortium of Aspis, o worthy one? It is the union of "
"the greediest merchants of all Cheliax. The head of the Consortium in Vudra "
"learned of an abandoned palace of the princess Chhaya, rumored to be filled with "
"fabulous riches. He hired guides and porters and set out for the palace, and the "
"treasures they found there exceeded their wildest expectations – but their robbery "
"had not gone unnoticed. They had awakened an evil spirit that sped towards them, "
"taking the form of a white cobra...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34d2748d-0302-436a-8cb0-f931c5ae8c87"
msgid ""
"\\\"O most worthy one! It pains me to ask of you yet another favor, yet {d|"
"Shainiha}I{/d} desperately require your aid! I fear yet again that I may have made "
"the wrong choice when I set myself upon the path of master smith! A rumor has come "
"to my ears and has upset my heart, making me doubt myself! The Perfect Human has "
"sent me a sign — a sign that shows I was fated for a great undertaking! I beseech "
"you, help me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0044d77b-207b-4f93-a031-8ee29809b64e"
msgid ""
"\\\"But this land lacks order. The gods granted Vudra castes. You have none here, "
"and that is why there is no order. For when you meet a member of the lowest caste, "
"you know that they only barely deserved to be born human. In their previous lives, "
"they were animals, or maybe even a vile things like Tieflings, who are lower than "
"even the lowliest beggars. Trust me, for I have more than once faced their wicked "
"nature! Whereas when you encounter a member of a higher caste, be he a padaprajna "
"warrior or a rajah as you and I, that signifies that in our past lives we were "
"pious and noble, that our words were strong and true. It is that understanding "
"that these lands lack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75c5cb54-78bb-41e0-b502-bf26c3dc8d82"
msgid "\\\"Of the Kingdoms of a Thousand Wonders? Where should I begin…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "176af80e-06b7-441e-ac10-9ffcc91ae6cf"
msgid "\\\"As you wish, so shall it be. I have many interesting stories for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6965803d-e1b8-461e-88fa-1cd37ff36ee8"
msgid ""
"\\\"...The Aspis realized that they would pay dearly for their greed, and ran as "
"fast as they could. The foolish Vudrani who had helped them ran as well. They "
"built ships and fled their homes. Many turned to piracy, and you can find them "
"still in the Protectorate of the Black Marquis, now known as the Mandagara League. "
"Woe is the fate of thieves and outcasts! Others settled in Kaer Maga in {g|Varisia}"
"Varisia{/g}. It was they who took the pyramid-box from the palace and hid it from "
"the Consortium. This box is covered in the finest oil, and carried by dead men, "
"and inside the box lives the Child Goddess.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68a2b90c-b419-4f1a-ad3a-d854d9953c4f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Trust me, for the Child Goddess spoke to me once, and foretold that you and I "
"were destined to meet! The Vudrani hope that the deity's protection will save "
"them, but it is this box that the evil spirit seeks. It has since transformed into "
"a demonic ship, and it comes into ports by night. Sailors who look like crocodiles "
"search the towns, and the ship is gone by dawn. There will come a day when the "
"ship finds Kaer Maga's port, and the Vudrani will pay dearly for their greed. "
"Vudra knows how to protect its treasures, and it is best not to seek them, o "
"worthy one.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa56d9c6-ae9a-4119-8e4f-3660f2ea7595"
msgid ""
"\\\"... To ensure that he never again falls victim of his ill nature, he carries "
"with him the skull of his mortal enemy, and consults it on all occasions. Trust "
"me, for I myself have heard the words of the skull's wisdom! Once, this wise man "
"Ulvantha was heading north. However, his path was blocked by the local rajah's "
"army, who was waging war against his neighbor. The soldiers were ordered not to "
"let anyone pass. This infuriated Ulvantha.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a49c2909-e7e0-453b-8425-81b8aaf1d9e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"But, following the skull's advice, he did not kill them on the spot – after "
"all, the soldiers acted honorably, neither buckling to his wrath nor flinching in "
"their duty. Instead, the wise man took some rice from his bag and boiled it, "
"making an army of rice soldiers. The rice soldiers then tore the rajah's men "
"apart, while Ulvantha visited the rajah's capital. He then overthrew the rajah and "
"placed a dead whore on the throne, as a reminder that power is as fleeting as "
"life. So do not hurry to think that your position of power might give you a "
"strength that I do not posses. Only noble behavior and enlightenment truly matter."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "979c5285-fa09-420c-a42e-04e72e377cbd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Once the Monastery of the Unblinking Flame became jealous that the Monastery "
"of the Unfolding Wind was known as the house of the greatest masters. Many turned "
"down the invitations of the Unblinking Flame in order to join their white-robed "
"rivals. The Monastery of the Unblinking Flame swore to make them pay for the "
"insult. In the streets, the markets, and the palaces, the red-clad monks would "
"insult the white ones, provoking them to bloody duels.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40cfda39-dc2c-4332-9282-95e6d2fbfa2b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Niswan shook as if from an earthquake. Trust me, for I witnessed it myself. In "
"that life I was an arrogant master of the Unblinking Flame and my pride demanded "
"war. I knew that my days were numbered, and desired nothing but to see the "
"Unblinking Flame triumph. In my arrogance, I could not see how much suffering I "
"brought to the people. Those who were struck by a monk's fist fell and did not "
"rise again, and those who were touched by a priest's finger were permanently "
"crippled in body and mind. We fought with honor, seeking to demonstrate our "
"mastery, not murder our enemy – while the townsfolk died by the thousands. And we "
"did not care.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b407ec11-0ac6-4f52-9606-40d58e0c5291"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our students, however, secretly arranged the Tournament of Unseen Mercy, which "
"took place on a bridge over an abyss. They fought, and it was agreed that the "
"losers would be shown no mercy, and their bodies would be thrown down, into the "
"abyss. By dawn the bridge was completely empty. It was then that we, the masters, "
"saw how arrogance had weakened our Houses and deprived us of our future. The "
"ambitions of the past were all that remained. It was a bitter lesson, and it was "
"then that I swore in all of my incarnations to be always humble and "
"straightforward. I have since kept my promise, no matter how strongly I may wish "
"to embellish my story!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "893e4cb7-74a8-46f5-b462-f310a0524094"
msgid ""
"\\\"As I have recently discovered, one of them lives nearby. The noble Hassuf "
"trades in your capital. I confess, I am too nervous to meet him. I fear that my "
"anxiety will cause me to behave inappropriately, and I may disgrace myself for it. "
"Would you assist me in fulfilling my duty and deliver him this letter? I do not "
"believe that my heart can be at peace until this letter is delivered! One cannot "
"be a master when beset by such distraction.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59396011-126c-4178-919a-cb6daf90b6e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is the land of genie, monks, wondrous beasts – and gods, of course. Vudra "
"is home to thousands of gods, while in other lands they worship mere dozens! The "
"Perfect Human is the head of the pantheon. He is called Irori, the Master of "
"Masters. Among the gods he is as a maharajah, ruling Vudra and all of its "
"Mahajanapadas, or kingdoms as you call them. Each kingdom has its own rajah. The "
"wealth and glory of even the feeblest among them is such that would make even the "
"wealthiest of your rulers rage in envy. Trust me, for I was once a rani myself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c6c20307-a9d1-47f0-b728-bd21129b45a6"
msgid "\\\"Of course, we would need many a week to discuss all of her wonders!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2444efa6-c4b3-48d0-8fb6-6bf26fdc34e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"The walls of my palace steadily absorbed their attack, but in the end they "
"turned to dust. I was preparing to die, but the red wind suddenly fled in terror, "
"banished by a strange traveler. He was a vanara, half-man and half-monkey, and he "
"wore the orange robe of a priest. I wished to thank him but he had little interest "
"in my treasures. He offered me to play the wise-men's game of BARME, and if he won "
"then I would have to give him my throne.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0aa617a-1bb9-48f4-acc2-4411d05c02ff"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agreed, for how could I say 'no' to my savior? He easily outwitted me, "
"hiding four pieces up his sleeve, while I only managed to brush one off the table "
"and stash another one in my pocket. I ordered my guards to seize the vanara and "
"put him in chains, as I had no wish to give up my throne. But by dawn the monk had "
"fled his prison. — He'd used his tongue to lick a hole in his manacles. I knew "
"then that the monk was Ragdya, the monkey god, a sage, a petty thief, and the "
"lover of a hundred brides. Trust me, for I have met many gods, and know of what I "
"speak. I gave Ragdya my throne along with my apologies, and set out to wander.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6b81b2c-5ffc-486b-abb8-502dfc6630ec"
msgid ""
"\\\"A massive ant hive grew around him, but this did not concern Rudrakavala. A "
"thousand years passed, and Diomazul, the god of war, came to visit him and offered "
"Rudrakavala any reward, for he'd shown great merit. The rakshasa demanded all "
"eight of the god's swords. Upon receiving them, he chased Diomazul into a dungeon "
"and, content with himself, sat down to rest. Soon the other gods realized that war "
"has left them, for it was much more difficult to resolve conflict and maintain "
"order. And so they began to seek the missing god. To be precise, they found a "
"young hero and tasked him with finding and rescuing Diomazul.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7795916-e38f-4988-84fe-e357c1262236"
msgid ""
"\\\"But he was terrified by the sight of the mighty three-headed rakshasa. While "
"one head was reading Mizravrit Brahmodiya, the second was puffing on a hookah "
"while the third was sipping wine. The hero didn't stand a chance in battle. But "
"the rakshasa's bride fell in love with the hero. It is she that stands before you "
"today. I put Rudrakavala to sleep with fragrant incense, while my prince took one "
"of his swords and severed all three of the rakshasa's heads. I hid the heads in "
"secret places were my groom could not find them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13c671c6-15be-4209-8359-6f54309ecdc5"
msgid ""
"The memory of my treachery remains in one of his heads. I hope that it will never "
"find its way back to his shoulders. But I'd best stay as far away as possible, in "
"case that ever happens. So I prayed to the gods, and trusting in them, I jumped "
"over the ocean landing in Varisia. From there my feet carried me here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "526f4505-4d3c-46c0-aab1-ca7e394c1a9b"
msgid ""
"\\\"But they did not know that the wise man had taught his servants his "
"techniques. While he slept, his servants captured the assassins. The pasha of the "
"shaitans, also known as the earth genies, sent his finest warrior, Turmir, the "
"destroyer of palaces. By his command, Khiben-Sald's palace fell and turned to "
"rubble. The cunning wizard foresaw this, however, and fled to the island of "
"Jalmeray.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8fc030aa-3f6a-4147-a03a-b6ed6bc9d1b8"
msgid ""
"\\\"One of the royal marids, the genies of water, came to free his brethren from "
"captivity. Of all the genies, he was the wisest. For three days, Khiben-Sald "
"competed with the genie in the art of poetry. At the end of the third night, "
"Khiben-Sald was so exhausted that he was about to take a ceremonial dagger to open "
"his own veins... The genie, however, was first to admit defeat, and entered a "
"copper vessel which the wizard then sealed. It was thus that history came to know "
"the maharajah as the great conqueror of the genies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "775ce288-94b8-4cf5-b6b4-49cb0462f0db"
msgid ""
"\\\"Kothogaz walked across the ocean, and the water reached only up to his waist. "
"He was covered by a mighty shell like a beetle, and the slime from his body "
"covered the waters like fat, calming the waves around him, and his many mouths "
"dripped with spittle. Kothogaz cried out, and the putridity of its breath made "
"creatures faint, bleeding from their eyes, their nose and their ears – while the "
"monster's saliva burned through everything it touched. Trust me, for I have seen "
"stones that were touched by this poison. Vu Balak, however, called forth the "
"priests and they cast their magic. The ocean boiled and Kothogaz began to boil in "
"it. The whales came surfacing all around him as he screamed, and his chitin "
"hardened, becoming more and more fragile – until finally it cracked and crumbled.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "afc7ee71-ed24-43a1-adc6-d98eab704550"
msgid ""
"\\\"Finally, Vu Balak saw the heart of the Dance of Disharmony. He jumped so high "
"that his mighty body blocked the sun, and the stars shone in the day. He then "
"threw his spear and shattered Kothgaz's heart into a hundred and one pieces. We "
"have managed to gather some of the pieces, but not all. Perhaps if the Storyteller "
"were to read the spear's memories, he would be able to tell were the other pieces "
"went. Then I might collect them to honor my mighty ancestor. That would be a truly "
"heroic deed. Perhaps the path of a hero is what fate truly has in store for me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e1f7513-4757-48e4-bca3-1bf35b8c0b01"
msgid ""
"\\\"One day, Khorkhor defeated the poisonous dragon Sruvara, who turned rice "
"fields into nauseating marshes. But Khorkhor did not notice that Sruvara had "
"scraped his white skin with its talon. Infection entered the hero's body, and he "
"grew weak. He lied down to rest and remained there for a thousand years. Nothing "
"could awaken him, even all the strife brought on by the fight with Kothogaz, the "
"Dance of Disharmony. Once he finally awoke from his slumber, Khorkhor discovered "
"that his homeland had been ravaged by this terrible attack, and he'd slept through "
"the battle! Disgraced, he moaned and set off for a faraway gorge, where he would "
"deliver his body to the scorpions, that they might eat his flesh and hide him from "
"his shame.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83ddf2df-6824-43a3-8594-ce073c0999aa"
msgid ""
"\\\"For three months, the scorpions ate his white skin and ruby flesh, but still "
"the warrior endured. Even when he was eaten, Khorkhor did not die, for he was "
"truly great. It was then that Bundha the Singing Butcher came to him. The immortal "
"rakshasa told him that great was Khorkhor's shame, but more shameful still would "
"be to run from it like a coward, rather than atone for it. Khorkhor's spirits were "
"rekindled. He arose and, through sheer force of will, forged himself a new body "
"out of iron. He accomplished many great deeds thereafter, and in the end he "
"regained his position of honor and nobility.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02b7dba6-79b4-4b43-9c79-927d482cfd82"
msgid ""
"{n}Surprised, the Vudrani falls silent, shrugs and gives you a slightly displeased "
"look.{/n} \\\"Impatience is the mother of all sins, o worthy one. Be careful on "
"this path. Return when you have the time to listen. Until then, I shall wait for "
"you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9c26603-2b27-489e-879f-5a27ffd70c39"
msgid ""
"{n}The Vudrani purses her lips in disappointment and mumbles something under her "
"breath, but soon she is smiling at you again.{/n} \\\"I shall await your return.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f329bf0-d69e-4055-9a46-326cdc292a9f"
msgid ""
"{n}The Vudrani freezes with her mouth open. Obviously, she was just getting to the "
"best part. She snorts disapprovingly.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e545e607-065c-4b35-b146-96ace15cbc17"
msgid ""
"\\\"Turmir chased after him, forgetting that the waters of the ocean could not "
"hold his heavy flesh. As he began to drown, Khiben-Sald sent ships to save him, "
"but only after Turmir swore to serve him. As compensation for the palace he "
"destroyed, the genie was commanded to build the Pure Temple of the Maharajah, "
"which was a hundred times more beautiful than the one he destroyed. Trust me – for "
"I have seen this temple with my very eyes!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86f28e3b-583b-4033-9045-1a558942414c"
msgid "\\\"You are wise, o most worthy one. But not patient.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3dfaf872-d17a-4dae-9aed-b4eede2553c7"
msgid "\\\"What would you like to hear?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69612f38-dcf0-4af5-9e26-1d0c07da2fbf"
msgid ""
"\\\"A great evil returned with me to my kingdom. The macaques of Sikari, diseased "
"and rabid, swarmed the land. They rolled like an enormous wave, engulfing and "
"destroying everything in their path. They called this horror 'the crimson wind'. "
"My warriors went forth boldly, but were overrun.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "308692f9-4e09-4815-93b7-a2c2a8cb83d0"
msgid "\\\"O, how fleeting is your attention!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c9f6156d-99b0-4c0a-b218-cf6a28e39c56"
msgid "[Keep listening in silence]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a3c3aa3f-c7b2-46a8-bbd8-9c731d3547ae"
msgid "{n}With a barely audible sigh, Shaynih'a bows her head.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51a4b65c-fbac-4de6-aa99-d6ad7852a20b"
msgid ""
"A letter from the Shaynih'a family, addressed to the family of the merchant Hassuf."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca7f7160-ece8-40ef-9d2b-e8043b68638c"
msgid "Letter to Hassuf"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e99adc6-3a76-4ba6-8743-e750ea832fe5"
msgid "A fragment of the spear that belonged to Vu Balak, an ancestor of Shaynih'a."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32d5db7d-0ca4-43ad-ac80-db78026bc405"
msgid "Spear Fragment"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46300021-3877-48d8-8904-5b26e5a3b1e9"
msgid ""
"A magnificent weapon, borne of the mastery of the Vudrani smiths, and the "
"refinement of their philosophy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4af5ced3-582a-4654-bc70-6cb06655f8ef"
msgid "The Pride of Vudra"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d0f4134-5982-4f95-966e-8c8f009e34e2"
msgid "\\\"Begin making your great weapon.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8a9d3a7-47a3-478e-9038-eb84a3b9e119"
msgid "\\\"I thank you, Shaynih'a the Tulip.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4deb1232-bd1c-4731-8232-f3958a2b4a86"
msgid "\\\"I want you to make something specific for me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ccef488-6927-4f39-ac1c-351fc01a1393"
msgid "\\\"Go home and never come back here again.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e40a9da-b3ca-49a3-aae8-645bf82ba0b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"You've finally found your true calling. Tell me now… Why did you tell me all "
"of those stories?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fd11d72-feed-4928-8b66-ed70ae69d244"
msgid ""
"\\\"I greet you, o most worthy one! As decided, {d|Shainiha}I{/d} have stepped "
"upon the path of the master smith, as fated by the Perfect Human. Since a rare few "
"in these lands appreciate the aesthetics of the Vudrani, I have decided that my "
"gifts will be made for you. However, even though my feet may carry me swiftly to "
"the top of the mountain of perfection, on this path I shall need the help of "
"someone tactful and dependable — someone such as you, o worthy one. If you are "
"ready to aid me, come see me at my workshop, and I shall tell you of my need.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "188011cf-b77c-420a-b753-3c89c268c848"
msgid ""
"\\\"{d|Shainiha}I{/d} am happy to see you, o most worthy one. A new gift and new "
"stories await you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96a0d52b-50a0-4166-b954-a4e429474499"
msgid ""
"{n}The Vudrani ceremoniously extends a magnificent weapon.{/n} \\\"I swear, "
"nowhere in Avistan shall you find a weapon such as this. I have named it 'The "
"Pride of Vudra'. The master of masters himself taught me how to make this weapon – "
"a material symbol of the harmony of destruction. Someday I shall tell you the "
"story of how I was blessed by Irori himself... someday...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "182cc8c8-08b1-4526-8245-9e9cf9f42f44"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am very grateful for your help. The path to one's purpose is difficult, and "
"I am glad to have found a companion such as you. Now that I know which road shall "
"lead me to perfection, an urge has grown in my soul — to create a great weapon for "
"you. In it, I shall be able to embody that confidence in my future that you "
"yourself have helped me to gain.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b210ea47-a32f-42a7-8658-8b52b19977ef"
msgid ""
"\\\"Still, I urge you to visit me at my workshop. I wish to share with you a rumor "
"that may lead me to quit your realm, to suddenly embark on an adventure. Please, "
"do not take long!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc040321-a751-4138-9b4a-4a7de4705a14"
msgid ""
"\\\"Please, accept this fine item. It has been crafted according to the traditions "
"of Vudrani craftsmanship. Even in the Impossible Kingdoms, possessing something so "
"precious would inspire awe and envy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70d1b8b0-1973-4c53-8b1c-ce8aaaa3f2d8"
msgid ""
"{n}Shaynih'a snorts and pouts her lips, clearly insulted.{/n} \\\"Our friendship "
"has been ordained by the gods, and this is how you treat it? In that case, as you "
"wish! You shall never see me again, but you will most definitely hear about me and "
"my adventures! Time and time again!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "05e13b53-a2db-4097-ae69-098588e4cab0"
msgid ""
"{n}The Vudrani throws back her head in laughter.{/n} \\\"You wish to ask me for "
"something specific? But please, how can I foresee which thoughts the Perfect Human "
"will send into my mind? Of course, I can promise to fulfill your order, but if the "
"Perfect Human wishes it, I will go against my word, and then everyone will say "
"again: 'don't believe the Vudrani — their words are nothing but lies'. And why "
"would we want that?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b17f1e2c-aee6-4ab6-925c-81fc9983dfe2"
msgid ""
"\\\"It will truly be magnificent. Believe me, for I have been to a hundred lands, "
"and with my eyes I have witnessed the most perfect creations of a thousand masters."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6fe3a66-f5a7-4b55-9f53-03f16fcdcdd1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I would gladly relate a story from my homeland that inspired me to create "
"this. But alas… due to another pressing matter I must take my leave sooner than I "
"would like!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a69b5d8a-afee-48d0-8f3d-92d8e2b64c22"
msgid ""
"{n} Shaynih'a sighs heavily, almost defeated, and suddenly starts to speak in "
"plain and clear words.{/n} \\\"A good story is like an island. You sail to it in "
"your boat, get off on the shore and start walking. North or south. Into the "
"mountains or along the shore. Or perhaps you start digging a hole, wishing to know "
"what lies underneath. Depending on what side of the story you choose to look into, "
"you will always find something different.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "288a355a-a433-4b64-920d-6769f0978b3c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Good friends or vicious monsters, great treasures or pesky mosquitoes... Do "
"you see? The same story may become the story of a villain or a hero, it all "
"depends on how you tell it. It may become a comedy or a tragedy... And you can "
"make of it what you wish. You may arrive at any conclusion you desire. So, "
"ultimately, does it really matter what happened? And does it matter whether or not "
"it actually did? Or perhaps, the only thing that matters is the story itself – and "
"you, the listener, deciding on your own what to make of it...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "caa58060-8310-4078-946d-a452e3bb534c"
msgid ""
"\\\"All of this sounds like the work of the Ebon Destroyers Cult. They are "
"servants of Dhalavei, the goddess of unmaking and secrets, of ruin and "
"degradation. Perhaps you know her by another name. She appears as a beautiful "
"three-headed woman with deep black skin and dark hair. Her servants range from "
"monks and priests to politicians to the undead. You may trust in this, for I have "
"heard it spoken by a severed eunuch's head, who was among their victims. Most of "
"Dhalavei's cultists are pathetic rejects of the lower castes, who are of no "
"interest to the other gods. Together with Vasaghati, her spirit sister, Dhalvei "
"brings death and decay. The Ebon Destroyers seek out secrets, while the Knife in "
"the Dark, Vasaghati's cult, can infiltrate the ranks of any organization and "
"slowly destroy it from within.\\\"\\n\\\"In the ocean that surrounds Vudra lies an "
"island known as Gho Vella. It is a land of lepers, and those who live there suffer "
"from incurable curses and afflictions. Certainly, the gods do not burden pious men "
"with contagion, for all such affliction is a lesson meant to show that a man has "
"led a sinful life, and to show others they'd be wise not to know him. Trust me, "
"for I myself have seen men struck with leprosy on the very spot for their woeful "
"ways! A group of philosophers, known as the Curse Shepherds, has taken upon itself "
"the duty of seeking out those punished by the gods. Their black boats ferry the "
"misfortunate to Gho Vella where they may contemplate their sins in peace.\\\"\\n\\"
"\"I have heard of the First World. The ratfolk practitioners of the ancient art of "
"rantagi have long led their caravans between the worlds, through breaches they "
"make in the fabric of reality. Trust me, for one of them ventured into the first "
"world and revealed the truth of it to me. Once this wondrous world was the home of "
"the heavenly harems and treasuries of the gods. Their slaves, however, rebelled "
"against their masters, craving their masters' power for their own. For their "
"insolence, the gods separated themselves from the First World, and instead created "
"for themselves Nirvana. Their slaves remained in their old homes, and were "
"henceforth known as Asura – rejected servants. They serve as a reminder of the "
"cataclysm one causes when denying one's rightful place in the cycle of "
"reincarnation, and living blasphemy. They hate the gods for their condition, and "
"seek to avenge it. Do not trust the Asura of the First World, for none of them "
"wish you well!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23dfab79-f512-4744-bb13-2b6cf82e5e21"
msgid "\\\"Aaaaa!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12c2519d-e520-41cf-98cf-f20c23399269"
msgid "\\\"Aaaaa!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2954c13c-7c7a-4428-b8cb-65a722aeada8"
msgid "\\\"Die, scum!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "433ad927-adf7-40dd-9211-35549e5e388d"
msgid "\\\"Tests? What tests?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "676aecdd-27c6-4150-bb1e-ca2363558557"
msgid "\\\"I should go now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eac9b748-eeee-4264-b099-3d7f16c25417"
msgid "\\\"The wererat died from taking the potion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16237a65-ba46-4d9f-8330-6e803ec3c0d4"
msgid "Lied to Bokken about the results of the potion trials."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a466bb4-5028-4f1a-ab9f-03c84ce865eb"
msgid ""
"[Lie] \\\"As soon as I fed your potion to the dog... spots appeared on it from "
"head to tail! And then it had orange saliva dripping from its mouth!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43811427-c3a5-4d15-b6f7-ed5b4dfa8631"
msgid "\\\"I need to buy something from you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb3699f9-7c77-49a2-b12a-f78d9f0e0087"
msgid "\\\"What formula?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ff531ba-3be1-4365-bcce-57f6a8f0b412"
msgid "\\\"I bet a gold piece that you're not even listening to what I say…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28e4d317-8fa4-4707-825f-d98938e60f40"
msgid "\\\"Speak clearly, old man. What on earth are you blathering about?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54366e64-4007-407f-ae86-e92f689ef3fe"
msgid "\\\"The potion clouded your mind. You attacked me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b238e5a-8da0-40e9-bd6d-9bc85810f08c"
msgid "Made Bokken plea for his life after his new potion drove him berserk."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34d27563-234b-476d-84cb-82ac6065425b"
msgid ""
"\\\"You've dared to raise your hand against your ruler. Beg now for your life.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11f3785c-860c-4efe-b093-2a804a51e170"
msgid "Killed Bokken for going berserk after drinking the potion."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26e00078-200c-448c-8a5c-ffcf63b8714e"
msgid "\\\"Not bad. But I'm going to kill you anyway.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8325ea0a-ae5a-457e-9678-810c9243cc0d"
msgid "\\\"That's more like it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6afb2305-896a-43bf-b635-338373a848be"
msgid ""
"\\\"No, Bokken. Svetlana is worried about you – and I can see she's right to be. "
"You are obsessed with this idea. It won't lead anywhere good.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a5cb419-a99a-4517-b97e-d2668606b7cd"
msgid "\\\"All right, I'll do it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d2a6f32-73c7-4b5c-81b2-203b76913936"
msgid ""
"\\\"Shut up, you nitwit… and next time think before you take any more potions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "78080f23-0f14-49db-8505-e9f875720250"
msgid "\\\"I'm not tormenting living creatures for the sake of your ambition!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe4d075e-9819-44ba-8187-ed47c97fba20"
msgid "\\\"Your potion made the dog go mad and attack me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f128d9cb-d289-4d93-8aef-ccbc924cc581"
msgid "\\\"I didn't get to torment the wererat with your toxic potion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c6b107f-7a38-47cb-9a4d-a235fb51723a"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Bokken}Bokken{/d} looks tired and haggard. His face is grey, his brow "
"furrowed, and his eyes shine with a feverish glow.{/n} \\\"Who's there? What is it?"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1f809c6-9faf-4c3d-b8f3-ab929f79f0f0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, it's you! How convenient! I need your help – we have to run some tests…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35125975-846d-4e91-ad84-22ba5733ed1a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've found the formula! All on my own! These damned books didn't have it – "
"nothing but hints and half-truths there. But you can't fool old Bokken that "
"easily, he he heh…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a91c80d0-db53-4264-9ea2-02c717c143c6"
msgid "Lied to Bokken about the experiment."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee59493b-14af-4492-828b-fde4fcbc06bd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Is that so? Hmm… The wererat simply died, and the mutt gone rabid… You see, my "
"potion wasn't meant to do anything with the mind. Only the body!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad6bb7d5-d592-4e78-98ed-debbdead1eba"
msgid ""
"{n}Bokken squints his eyes, looking at you with barely hidden irritation.{/n} \\"
"\"You lie... I can smell a lie when I hear one!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29195abf-635e-424b-b4bf-bdb298d23458"
msgid ""
"{n}Bokken blinks at you, clearly surprised.{/n} \\\"Orange saliva? But wait… "
"what's that, then? This potion wasn't meant to make such changes to the body...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7716d3a-6c6f-4a32-ab85-9a67f2b30b49"
msgid "\\\"Well?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22005d21-3102-40ee-b900-98a85e6bd43c"
msgid ""
"{n}The old man's eyes are beginning to clear. It seems that he's coming back to "
"his senses.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7120b5e6-a725-43d6-940e-12395711c41f"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll need to go for one final test, it seems. We must try the potion on a "
"human. An elf would do just fine as well. Or a dwarf... or…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04658513-6026-4fb7-8a02-88bb39323df4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why would I? Though I can hear you clear as day… Now, what was I saying, then? "
"Oh, right – the formula!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3a39385-e6fe-4cfe-b63b-d283dad65fd1"
msgid ""
"\\\"The elixir of eternal youth! A most wondrous brew – restores the strength in "
"one's hands and the swiftness in one's feet. I first heard of it when I was still "
"just a lad, and I didn't believe in it. But now I've lived a long life, and I've "
"seen even stranger things. So I thought: why not give it a try?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c7fa8d1-c9b1-4cc7-b58d-35174478f651"
msgid "\\\"What… what happened?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c2af4f2-a8e8-418c-903f-972b3a4aface"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, please, forgive me, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}! How the devil… It's all that damned potion's fault, I swear! It stole "
"my mind, that wasn't me, I swear…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39c4b853-49af-4ceb-9c65-444a3ad71910"
msgid "\\\"Gods… Forgive an old man. I didn't know what I was doing…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "adbf1826-38d4-45a8-b5f8-4aeebeb9db00"
msgid ""
"{n}Bokken wipes the sweat off his brow.{/n} \\\"I never thought that potion could "
"work in such a way… but still, it does seem to make one stronger! Thank you for "
"all your help! Now I know how to iron out the wrinkles – I think…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0de1fe9b-4047-4569-92cf-e8832fa007aa"
msgid ""
"\\\"So I asked you to find these books for me. – I'd heard that one of the volumes "
"contains a formula. Well, it turns out they don't. All they do is make things "
"clear as mud. Still, I was able to find something useful in there… I can't "
"remember how many nights I stayed up working on the solution, but here it is!\\"
"\" {n}Bokken proudly shows you a few vials filled with silvery liquid.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ae418447-3cb3-4cd0-bf28-c7ec8e2ecb28"
msgid ""
"\\\"Can't drink it yet, though. Must test it first… Can't be too careful with "
"these things.\\\" {n}Bokken gives you an expectant look.{/n} \\\"So will you help "
"me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "045c5b05-b628-42ee-a8e3-8e05fefed675"
msgid ""
"{n}Bokken is almost shaking with indignation.{/n} \\\"So that's how it is, is it?! "
"That mischievous schemer… Fine. I'll just make it on my own. It won't be the first "
"time!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0ec53a0-70f3-414e-b2e2-57cfaff5f18e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful! Thanks for that! Let's try it on a dog first. There's a mutt on a "
"leash around the corner… you can test the stuff on it. I won't feel bad for it if "
"something goes wrong! That'll teach it to stop barking at me every time I pass by! "
"I could do it myself, but what if it's off the leash? It won't harm you as it "
"would harm me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb58a796-8016-47df-961d-f268b26148cf"
msgid ""
"{n}Bokken takes a small glass vial from his pocket. He exhales sharply, takes a "
"few gulps – and the vial is empty!{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ebb31103-fd01-4c26-8a79-5699c74b883e"
msgid ""
"{n}Backing away in terror, Bokken whispers, his voice barely audible.{/n} \\"
"\"Thank you for your help! Now I know what's wrong with the formula. I can take it "
"from here…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe2f73f5-146b-4377-918f-72e7bc31f03e"
msgid ""
"{n}Bokken is practically shaking with indignation.{/n} \\\"So that's how it is, is "
"it?! Fine. I'll just make it on my own. Won't be the first time!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7e9bd39-48eb-4e08-80a4-7d9aae94f708"
msgid ""
"\\\"To the demons with the dog. We need someone more human to experiment on. Know "
"what? My neighbor, a hunter, once told me he saw wererats in a forest not far from "
"here. They'd make better test subjects. After all, they're closer to humans than a "
"dog. We should find them and try again... but take this vial. This potion has a "
"different, improved formula.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2d1cbc8-dfb8-4e45-9aef-638d1b08b597"
msgid "\\\"A mad dog? Sounds wrong, very wrong... I must have made a mistake.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "072fbf2d-b1e2-40ae-a167-042e2cf21fa4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Alchemy is the triune science of: primes, or basic elements, of which all "
"things are composed; forces, by which those things are set in motion; and families "
"of all such things which a studious mind can perceive in our world. An art most "
"formidable, it grants its practitioner power over nature, and even over that which "
"beyond nature lies; he who has mastered it fully shall become like the gods, yet "
"woe be unto he who sets about its study without diligence and zeal, for his days "
"are numbered. The path ahead is perilous and arduous in equal measure, and he who "
"sets his foot upon it heedlessly shall not find wisdom, but only a quick and "
"grisly end.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b52e462d-c2ed-43b8-a5f9-088870d67e9c"
msgid "\\\"Of Transmutations and Bodily Poisons\\\", Part I"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "688d5dc2-5932-4796-b537-4258954ce51a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Truly blessed and enlightened is that learned man or wise woman whose gaze has "
"pierced the mysteries of alchemy. This path fortifies the spirit, sharpens the "
"mind and teaches temperance in all things. Even the petty and the shallow have, "
"through ardor in their pursuit of alchemical knowledge, achieved virtue. Yet "
"nevertheless, this art is not without its dangers. An alchemist who turns to "
"imbibing his own concoctions, as is custom among the young and impatient, may "
"wreck havoc upon his very nature. For a potion is not merely a concoction, but a "
"mixture of primes, which the naked eye cannot see. These basic elements of spirit, "
"once they take root within, may intermingle and converge, and through their union "
"poison the soul, compel deeds most disgraceful, or excite with the temper of a "
"demon...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb9c3bf1-4cae-4f3c-ae1a-89f2bea7340b"
msgid "\\\"Of Transmutations and Bodily Poisons\\\", Part II"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14cc2786-9c5d-4f81-9a0c-f9f385a39e85"
msgid ""
"\\\"All matter is, in itself, both poison and cure – like water, which lies at the "
"foundation of every process. All living things perish without water; all living "
"things shall drown if in water submerged, for even a fish leaps from its lake each "
"day to breathe in the air. All other matter succumbs to this universal law. That "
"which the unlearned call poison is only the measure of a substance that the body "
"which imbibes it cannot overcome. However, if diluted threefold, fivefold, even "
"tenfold, that same substance may affect the body much differently, strengthening "
"or cleansing it. Therefore, not every poison-maker is a villain, as is often "
"believe among the common herd. The art of handling poison is neither dark nor evil "
"in itself...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "befcb0ca-57d3-47d3-bf83-b67531a5e898"
msgid "\\\"Of Transmutations and Bodily Poisons\\\", Part III"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bc8bb5d4-f0ea-4960-b0ba-4541fa3714e1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}, I hope that matters of state in this "
"land of ours are indeed all fine and well – and what troubles there are don't "
"weigh too heavily upon your mind! I write to ask you to check our local herb "
"doctor, Bokken. The poor old man is losing his mind. – He spends all day and night "
"stooped over his cauldron! He looks about to lash out at anyone, especially those "
"he doesn't know. He even snarls at me and Oleg, which he'd never have let himself "
"do before... Please come and see him before the old codger loses his mind "
"completely, may Erastil save him. We've no one to turn to but you!\\nHoping you "
"come as soon as possible, I remain,\\nVery truly yours,\\nSvetlana Leveton\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "417bcb2f-d370-461f-8593-11d4824ad057"
msgid "A Letter from Svetlana Leveton"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b814f1d-6b06-40da-915c-ac5a3dc46124"
msgid "\\\"Thank you. This will prove useful. You may go now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d75b66c3-b246-439f-b93d-5ea64b14cbe0"
msgid "\\\"I no longer require your services, Bokken.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f9f31a6f-6c5e-4e80-8f4f-6dfa21d15f7b"
msgid "\\\"I would like you to craft something specific.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c8a547b-e3fd-4125-b899-7ca609b4dbd1"
msgid "\\\"I'm running low on potions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1cac896-e232-4ae2-8f0b-3bd6218e4529"
msgid "\\\"I need more of your oils and ointments.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "265fc802-146a-48b1-8b21-fd03763498c2"
msgid "\\\"I could use another one of your alchemical items.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "757f7f47-9b5f-4895-a842-2bf4429e5eed"
msgid ""
"\\\"On second thought, I've changed my mind. Just make whatever you think will "
"turn out best.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "883b00ae-1abe-4d38-bee5-0ab101d98643"
msgid ""
"{n}Unfazed by the awkward silence, {d|Bokken}Bokken{/d} searches through his bag "
"for quite a while. Finally, he pulls out a sizeable brown paper package.{/n} \\"
"\"There you go. A little something from old Bokken.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "091659c0-7ecc-4c77-bba5-b75f62923781"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you ever need anything in particular, just let me know. If you're not sure, "
"I'll go home and think of something myself. My bones ache.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83f81df8-949f-474b-8531-ed71732f6c78"
msgid ""
"\\\"My pleasure.\\\" {n}Bokken gives you a sideways look, then turns his eyes to "
"the ceiling.{/n} \\\"I only hope that no one throws it away or leaves it to rot in "
"some old chest. Oh well…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c26776ad-7573-4a0a-8b8b-0c554321ea74"
msgid ""
"{n}Bokken nods and pulls a piece of coal and a scrap of paper from his sleeve. He "
"takes his time smoothing it out before giving another solemn nod.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e53d6db1-a50e-407e-8e45-122a3589bdff"
msgid ""
"{n}Bokken frowns and sticks out his lower lip.{/n} \\\"What, one of your lackeys "
"spit in your porridge this morning? What did the old man do this time? I bring you "
"a present, and you send me away. You city-folk are a bad lot, I tell you...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab6d9fe7-ed81-471e-9608-30a4d7a15c91"
msgid ""
"{n}Bokken carefully writes something down on his scrap of paper.{/n} \\\"Very "
"good. And if you want to buy anything else – just come around.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "abec31a5-d84b-427c-92f1-6f4c8d944720"
msgid ""
"{n}Bokken picks his ear with the piece of coal, and hides it and the paper back in "
"his sleeve.{/n} \\\"My choice, then? Fine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b35424a-9e4a-4094-9b98-fd982f476c64"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Bokken}Bokken{/d} looks different today. His pace is slow and solemn, his "
"back proudly straight… It seems that he's even put on a different robe – though it "
"doesn't look any newer or cleaner than his normal one.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21e4cc03-3191-4f90-8335-a23d38abcf21"
msgid "\\\"Perfect! You won't regret this!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73f273fb-f590-4ec6-b60a-599d27fe29b1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, and while I'm here… There's a book that I've always wanted to read. 'Of "
"Transmutations and Bodily Poisons'. In three volumes. If you were to find it for "
"me, I could produce something… most remarkable for you. Something that might even…"
"\\\" {n}Bokken cuts himself short.{/n} \\\"Oh well, there's no use in empty words. "
"But they say there's an ancient formula hidden in one of these books. Bring me the "
"books, and I'll brew the potion for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e20326e5-df33-4c4e-a956-f257a9db57b1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I know that the Old Beldame – the old witch who lives in the swamp – had one "
"of these volumes in her hut, gathering dust. She must still have it for sale, I "
"imagine. As for the other two volumes, I have no idea. You might look in a magic "
"shop. Or in the bookcases and locked drawers of other alchemists, if you happen to "
"across their possessions in your adventures.\\\" {n}Bokken grins, bows to you and "
"leaves the throne room with a shuffling walk.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81fcf459-d389-49da-998a-897ed718287c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Here it is, the potion! The things I had to go through to get this made… Sure, "
"it doesn't bring back one's youth, but it does strengthen the body, sharpen the "
"mind and embolden the spirit! And doesn't affect one's temper any longer, ha ha.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a602b88-daf1-4dec-a594-8b6d523736f0"
msgid ""
"\\\"And one more thing… You remember that potion you helped me test?\\\" {n}Bokken "
"gives you a conspiratorial wink.{/n} \\\"Well, it's almost ready! I got rid of all "
"the rot that was spoiling the formula, and now it works just fine. I just need to "
"brew a large enough dose, and that takes time. Unless you have another assignment "
"for me, you'll have the elixir the next time we meet!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8e69464d-a64b-4ef6-be68-e701f51eab01"
msgid "\\\"I do hope this helps.\\\" {n}Bokken smiles and bows to you.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27e35def-f0e4-49c4-a212-fb2b672a3c28"
msgid ""
"\\\"Try the potion, won't you? It's the best I've ever brewed! My life's work, one "
"could say.\\\" {n}Bokken smiles and bows to you.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7607a210-5574-435c-90c8-673e81a7f9f3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your grace, I was at Oleg's trading post recently, and I noticed old {d|Bokken}"
"Bokken{/d} just standing there, bored to death with nothing to do. This is most "
"unfortunate – after all, the old grumbler is a very knowledgeable alchemist! "
"However, he has no use for his skills, since the locals need nothing more than the "
"simplest of healing potions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "facf300a-0a00-416f-8ece-0d1b20332cd0"
msgid ""
"\\\"And then it struck me – why don't you hire him as your court alchemist? His "
"decoctions and tinctures would certainly prove most useful to you. Also, it might "
"be cheaper than simply buying from him or some other merchant.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b222b4b-166b-46e3-aaf9-7e4cb90976c8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why, would you look at that! Svetlana sent you a letter! It seems she's "
"worried about old {d|Bokken}Bokken{/d}. – The letter is very emotional!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42ef8207-cecb-4856-8d5b-0a757d1144e0"
msgid "Experimented on the dog with Bokken's potion."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4046c942-e72a-4854-8218-c72fede845e7"
msgid "[Pour the potion into the dog's mouth]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9da8bb51-f735-4039-8eeb-c5c401ed7ca6"
msgid "[Leave]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89ee20c5-a862-427f-848e-e0201923b2fe"
msgid "Let the dog run away instead of testing the strange potion on him."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c63e1c06-1220-4e74-b566-dd39ba36a1b0"
msgid "[Untie the dog and let him go]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b54b0d90-d165-4a00-bad7-1b7c4a5b8d0d"
msgid ""
"{n}It's a typical street dog on a leash with a dirty yellow coat. Its watery eyes "
"regard you without particular interest.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a53cfdc-e291-4777-b4f7-60709bf87dc5"
msgid "\\\"Wait! I come in peace!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "474a9d4d-43a0-44ab-b8a8-531b855849e1"
msgid "\\\"Easy, easy. We can always fight later. Let's talk first.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64184de5-ed48-4f8a-9cc9-056e62e33cd2"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"There's too many of you here. And I only need one…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e53af76-91fc-47ba-8eab-abf01236de51"
msgid ""
"Asked the wererats whether anyone would volunteer to take part in Bokken's tests."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe47b5fa-9b2e-431e-aea3-dddfdee55bd7"
msgid ""
"\\\"An alchemist I know is working on a new potion, and the decoction has to be "
"tested. Does any of you wish to risk your life in the name of science?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "817c4083-408d-49ca-b9fd-18de5dd2e2aa"
msgid ""
"\\\"The ruler of these lands wishes to show that all who inhabit them are like "
"children to {mf|him|her}! In {mf|his|her} grace, {mf|he|she} gifts you with this "
"rare, noble drink!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3e752286-7fa8-47aa-980d-9d8f38a09d40"
msgid "\\\"As a matter of fact, nothing. I guess I should get going.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5188a6cc-11e2-46b7-888b-c2efbb1eeb77"
msgid ""
"Asked a group of wererats whether any of them were willing to volunteer themselves "
"as test rats."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e471a8a9-5fd8-4913-be2f-c4a4713c0447"
msgid ""
"\\\"What do you know. I was just looking for a couple of lab rats. Do I have a "
"volunteer?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "10b105b4-ad9f-45d1-91af-567d76c172d0"
msgid ""
"[Pour the potion into the wererat's mouth] \\\"Here, take a sip of this first…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "368f4339-154f-4466-ad68-fb7242695ced"
msgid "[Kill the wererat]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "927ddc97-e884-41f6-84fd-f08fc970699c"
msgid ""
"{n}Hunched, gray figures turn to face you as you approach. Yellow fangs show from "
"grinning muzzles, and clawed paws reach for weapons.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2252fdaa-b2c5-4e76-9c2c-72efdc571d3d"
msgid ""
"{n}The wererats freeze in intense anticipation, ready to pounce on you at any "
"moment. Finally, you hear a hoarse, cracked voice.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b832f219-1aab-414d-9dc6-ee356d5d669b"
msgid ""
"{n}The raspy laughter of half a dozen throats resounds over the small clearing.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a3c27314-78ff-4b8d-bd00-724a03026c5b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Move one finger – an' we'll cut your bald hide to scraps. Whatcha need?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2395860a-b48d-41fc-99ef-6e9c13a51bee"
msgid "\\\"Whatcha… lookin' at… Finish me… off…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "09eebfe4-1e74-4e3f-9b37-a4ffc3da7e6d"
msgid ""
"\\\"What, you lookin' to test this stuff on us? Of course – why try it out on "
"people when you've got monsters! Not like anyone's going to miss 'em, right?\\"
"\" {n}Tiny rat eyes glisten with an evil glow.{/n} \\\"Arrogant bastards… Tear 'em "
"apart, boys!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "089fda90-d6d1-480c-89c2-85aba348bb54"
msgid "\\\"Wet-tail. Take the bottle off {mf|him|her}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7cf3b4c7-44ae-49c2-8d6f-f6ed37bbcf1e"
msgid "{n}The pack leader's snout twists with hatred.{/n} \\\"Die, baldskin!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29b1afa5-29e5-428c-be4a-727b0b653182"
msgid ""
"{n}The wererats exchange glances, clearly surprised. One of them approaches you "
"and takes the potion. However, as soon as his clawed fist clenches the bottle's "
"neck, he rips out the cork and greedily raises it to his mouth! A gulp, another "
"one, and another... and the wererat falls to the ground, shaking with violent "
"convulsions!{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f53f3f00-2bbc-4aeb-aaac-1d0869a8812f"
msgid ""
"{n}The pack leader bares his teeth in a sinister grim.{/n} \\\"Not so fast, you "
"pup…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1fa4dbb-bc0f-4978-9f62-a567b5a22088"
msgid ""
"\\\"That idiot. How predictable.\\\" {n}The leader shifts his animal eyes towards "
"you.{/n} \\\"They've killed one of ours. Get 'em, boys.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bfc81487-6edd-469b-bf98-a5556b371da4"
msgid ""
"The pinnacle of Bokken's alchemical mastery, the result of years he's spent "
"striving to uncover the secrets of life."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "170f7961-1098-4878-9710-f193bc20f047"
msgid "Elixir of Inconceivable Transmutations of Body, and Soul, and Also Mind"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f9f9829b-b464-43f8-a62d-71f8d4371299"
msgid ""
"This armor belonged to a great warrior, and ancestor of Dragn Woradash. He "
"restored his family honor and made this armor shine again."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8b529285-2b06-4fae-b38f-469f7ea363dd"
msgid "Onslaught"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d725e28-0935-4fa2-878a-cb0134ae3a29"
msgid ""
"Adventurous Irlene Greyridge obtained this rare artifact at the {mf|baron's|"
"baroness'|King's|Queen's} special request."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2498d9e-133c-4a38-84af-b4ae6d33d667"
msgid "Grandmaster's Rod"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e008642-d5b4-4943-b8ce-1f5f8f6b493e"
msgid ""
"Renowned woodworking master Chimiel crafted a bow whose mere shadow is a deadly "
"weapon, on special consignment for the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77fdba06-11c3-45c5-98bf-835a8645d387"
msgid "Heartrender"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b226247-d184-4b8f-abe5-3e40ef5f1651"
msgid ""
"This stunningly beautiful magical adornment is the handiwork of Mim Wobblegander. "
"The jeweler put her heart into it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bbcf240-11a7-404b-b2ff-efffec5465d7"
msgid "Heart's Desire"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8432cf9f-578c-4479-90a6-a7cd9d31b36d"
msgid ""
"This razor-sharp blade bears the mark of Nazrielle, the honored court master of "
"the Stolen Lands' {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e052a3f1-9066-422e-a327-6e94278c09ba"
msgid "Enforcer"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7fab32fa-5b8c-4b0a-ad51-33c9df5765d1"
msgid ""
"This magnificent weapon is the creation of master Shaynih'a, the follower of the "
"Perfect Human, who finally discovered her purpose."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e48f53f-df61-43e7-915b-12cda8205b10"
msgid "The Pride of Vudra"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e4d1bbe-dfcc-4a15-ae00-c9836afe7bd3"
msgid "A glorious robe of amazing fabric made by the brave and noble artisan Sharel."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7fdbb427-7de9-477b-bc63-d57162f0eae8"
msgid "Robe of the Pure Heart"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fd89f7df-b4e7-45fe-a33b-48bfb6367661"
msgid ""
"A magnificent set of leather armor, crafted from the hide of an unknown predator, "
"shot by leatherworker Tirval, the head of Varnhold's militia."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b94467c-37d0-4e87-b1ee-57369b85e824"
msgid "Varnhold's Gratitude"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b22c9617-79c5-4751-a12f-71b6a2579c73"
msgid ""
"A family relic of Varrask, the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}'s court blacksmith. "
"This frightening-looking weapon possesses a great might."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f155a07-e401-4f86-945e-d87d78febc4f"
msgid "Obliteration"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acd076db-a8ab-432b-9857-d482e4931e26"
msgid ""
"\\\"Diplomacy above all. We shall exchange our arcane knowledge with other states."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46d105d9-2fad-45e5-a911-8fd2555b6b6b"
msgid "\\\"I wish to improve the education and training of our priests.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "722cac73-4dce-473d-a4c3-2b4666858487"
msgid ""
"\\\"I command the construction of a great workshop, so we may begin manufacturing "
"magical equipment for our army.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2df050c2-1a8a-4a6c-a761-cad7dd1d43bf"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's been a while since I came to you like this, {name}! You must be wondering "
"if I'm here to talk about troubles again, eh? Well, believe it or not, this time I "
"just wanted to tell you about all the successes we've been enjoying recently.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31b98927-fca5-4d83-a864-0a26f072da95"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, Your Highness. I would like to advise you on the current state of "
"magic affairs in the kingdom. But you can rest easy — it's only good news.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98a5f30b-4a6e-4f7d-ad86-597d2b256c83"
msgid ""
"{n}\\\"Maegar\\\" looks somber and triumphant.{/n} \\\"I greet you, Your Highness. "
"And I've something to tell you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "234e6465-3aee-4905-bb7a-7469b426ef73"
msgid ""
"\\\"The common folk have grown to trust our magic users – in great part, I think, "
"thanks to the ban on the... errrm, exotic magical ingredients.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5779ba95-8d91-4406-a703-9af3b7582808"
msgid ""
"\\\"Despite my expectations, maintaining the ban on exotic magical ingredients "
"proved highly beneficial. Your subjects have developed more trust towards magic "
"users, and are buying more goods and services from them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "422b7b6e-ba25-43a4-888f-85f142287e35"
msgid ""
"\\\"Somehow, maintaining the ban on exotic magical ingredients did not hamper the "
"rapid growth of magical potential in these lands. Perhaps not least because it "
"quieted the ever watchful and ever grumbling peasants...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e758c380-f600-4bb9-a2f6-fd531f834860"
msgid "\\\"Wonderful! I can't wait to see what we gain in return!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "326987ea-d9d1-4dc6-9fd5-5e25a20dd654"
msgid "\\\"Certainly, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1bc03fe-7737-4686-b1a5-947aae2ba512"
msgid "\\\"As you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2ac66a2-8eed-4259-96f0-d031d3424106"
msgid "\\\"Perfect. That's exactly what we'll do!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2b8e8c5-dcd7-4272-954f-5ca03975ae45"
msgid "\\\"It shall be done, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57ebaf77-815b-4347-b121-db3e7f2e593e"
msgid "\\\"Very well, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b16e4fee-190a-48eb-b0f3-a5ab70cd9224"
msgid "\\\"That wouldn't be my personal choice... but it will be quite useful.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "723cee40-41ae-49cb-80cb-2b45a9d98d66"
msgid "\\\"It shall be as you say, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "848bcf1e-26e5-4356-8570-62e8cf013543"
msgid "\\\"Splendid.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "830c7df0-0260-46e4-abde-ac32e2fe03c2"
msgid ""
"\\\"It seems appraiser was right after all. By permitting the unfettered trade of "
"all magic ingredients, we've attracted even more commerce to our lands — and more "
"rare specialists.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75eeb096-f811-4157-8f28-b50c9bca07f7"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've come a long way over the years. Our kingdom now employs magic of the "
"highest order, and does so confidently and responsibly. Unlike many other states, "
"we've done everything in our power to constantly maintain control over the "
"situation, and ensure that the development of magic serves the people, and not the "
"other way around.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3e7c082d-d28a-46e3-bdfc-de179e341973"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've come a long way over the years. Our kingdom has become an arcane power "
"unto itself. Knowing that they can't find better conditions anywhere else, all "
"manner of inventors, researchers and experimenters have flocked to us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "538bc68f-4cd7-4075-b84a-45bef470a28e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Despite my fears, the magic community took the new regulations we introduced "
"quite well. Many simply moved their laboratories out of town, and continued "
"working like nothing ever happened. Hardly anyone even thinks to speak of it "
"nowadays. — They've gotten used to it, it seems.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fb554b3-a064-4a7a-842f-6d486ea9949b"
msgid ""
"\\\"We refused to place new restrictions on the use of magic — and, as expected, "
"the people made peace with the decision. Recently, our mages have even started "
"enjoying a bit more understanding and tolerance...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2155f7ec-7eaa-4358-b7b6-abe159336ab5"
msgid ""
"\\\"And the time has now come to enjoy the fruits of our labor! There are three "
"projects I can suggest. First off, my personal favorite – we could exchange our "
"arcane knowledge with our neighbors. Second – we could use the experience and know-"
"how of our magic schools to help educate our priests more quickly and thoroughly. "
"Lastly – we could start producing magical weapons and armor for our army. So... "
"what do you think we should we focus on?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3c53f710-6245-4126-ae04-f8aefb2a3ea1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Lifting the ban on exotic magical ingredients proved highly beneficial to "
"commerce, and the development of the magical arts in these lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8fc19d51-6724-4fd1-a46f-312cbb3f0a0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"The magic community understood the need for the new regulations which "
"restricted the use of magic in densely populated areas. There's every reason to "
"believe that the reforms were a resounding success.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d87bc0c-dea3-4280-bd5f-77517efc4ef2"
msgid ""
"\\\"The masses still look upon mages with distrust. However, it's worth tolerating "
"a little social tension, considering the rapid development of the magical arts in "
"our lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3dc64348-25e8-4e9a-b3ec-1b4e6210159e"
msgid ""
"\\\"All in all, we've become one of the leading arcane powers in the River "
"Kingdoms. Among our subjects, there's a disproportionate number of scholars and "
"inventors, theorists and experimenters. It seems they are drawn here by the "
"freedoms our society offers, and the opportunity to undertake unfettered, even "
"extravagant research in our domain.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96d35729-97d8-4f78-9ba3-95b036c76d7a"
msgid ""
"\\\"All things considered, we've become one of the leading arcane powers in the "
"River Kingdoms. We have further distinguished ourselves in the way we treat magic "
"responsibly, ensuring that we maintain control over its development. Magic always "
"remains an instrument in our kingdom, and never an end in itself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1372f636-5edb-4c7a-8c15-ae525a13d2ab"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our successes have opened the way for us to pursue an ambitious project. I "
"have three ideas. We might employ the knowledge that our magic schools have "
"gathered to train our priests more quickly and thoroughly. I believe that would "
"ultimately be of the most use to our kingdom. We could instead disseminate our "
"arcane knowledge to our neighbors, for whatever knowledge they might offer in "
"return. Finally, we could start producing magical weapons for our troops.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57337325-e335-4d93-b93b-c1c49ebc97e6"
msgid ""
"\\\"However, this is not what I have come to discuss. I have weighed the magic "
"potential of our domain against that of our neighbors, and concluded that we "
"surpass them several times over. We do not lecture our mages on morality, and "
"place no obstacles to their research. Your subjects have reached a level of "
"mastery far higher than I expected. I must say, I am impressed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7be73cef-d24d-4b67-a41e-9c8103f1ec84"
msgid ""
"\\\"We are now in a position to pursue something on a grander scale. I suggest to "
"you three projects. The first: exchanging our arcane knowledge for that of our "
"neighbors. The second: make use of our magic schools to better train our priests. "
"Finally: create a workshop that would produce enchanted weaponry for the army. "
"Need I even mention that the final option is by far the most useful?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a35ac52a-67d6-43eb-8750-c7f3f3b31b11"
msgid ""
"\\\"It was wise to lift the ban on exotic magical ingredients. This greatly "
"benefitted our mages and sorcerers. Now they can spend less time procuring "
"material components, and more time in their studies... and they've still so much "
"to learn.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68d64a7b-090c-4522-bfa1-1e285e1f05af"
msgid ""
"\\\"Strangely, restricting the use of magic in the towns and villages only "
"strengthened our hand. Once their self-importance was placated, they grew quiet — "
"and stopped meddling our affairs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e6a3d288-1f9e-4668-91f1-e663bff42e4e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just as I expected, we lost nothing in refusing to bow your commoners. We "
"could not restrict the use of magic to soothe their fears. They grumbled for a "
"time, just for show. But soon they accepted their fates — as befits chattel...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ba4e9f7-368d-41a8-afe9-31a787e8d152"
msgid ""
"\\\"However, this is not what I have come to discuss. I have weighed the magic "
"potential of our domain against that of our neighbors, and concluded that we "
"surpass them several times over. I have not always agreed with your decisions — in "
"my view, you are too cautious. Still, your successes speak for themselves. Your "
"subjects have reached a level of mastery much higher than I expected of them. I "
"must say, I am impressed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "231fdc8a-ac03-4f47-93e3-780d0999a8fd"
msgid "\\\"I wish to control weather and luck.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ae7664b-4da6-4fbd-acee-801459538a33"
msgid "\\\"I wish to dominate animals.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12d5b931-7fe6-40d3-805a-ce5acfeb716c"
msgid "\\\"I wish to influence the minds of my subjects.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d82af45a-24fa-491d-b199-da230e913260"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia grins from ear to ear.{/n} \\\"Your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} "
"attracts the most unusual and interesting characters! They must have heard the "
"rumors that your country is a place where one can live without chains and "
"restrictions! Not long ago, I was visited by an appraiser of magical items – a "
"rare and sought-after profession in many countries!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e606c6cb-cb69-4254-a4c8-6935289e2632"
msgid ""
"\\\"This man proposed that he settle in our lands and open his own store. I agreed "
"then and there – why can't we be as good as {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g}, right? In "
"tribute, he offered his new ruler a valuable gift! But he didn't dare select a "
"specific item for you. Instead he simply invites you to choose from all the finest "
"things he keeps in his best store-rooms!\\\" {n}Octavia hands you a small list, "
"written on a piece of parchment in ornate handwriting.{/n} \\\"We'd best not be "
"greedy, and choose just one item.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0171c2e8-2817-4f75-81e3-ebe424b085c4"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller bows and hands you a piece of parchment, on which is printed a "
"short list, written in ornate handwriting.{/n} \\\"My respects, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I hasten to hand you this paper, that I "
"have received from your new subject.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7422a6b3-8551-44ff-a8d4-025e203d7665"
msgid ""
"\\\"An appraiser of magical items has settled in the capital. We are nearly "
"colleagues, and this news fills my heart with joy.\\\" {n}The Storyteller smiles.{/"
"n} \\\"Grateful for his new home, the appraiser asks {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness} to choose as a gift one of the artifacts from his "
"store-rooms. See for yourself...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46df1baf-51ed-4640-876f-296691c002bf"
msgid ""
"{n}You look through the list. The appraiser offers you a choice of three magical "
"items: one of them attracts good weather and good luck, the second one allows you "
"to dominate animals, and the third one – to influence the emotions of sentient "
"creatures.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7dd5c142-8cfc-42b3-ae50-2816d0d56ba3"
msgid ""
"{n}\\\"Maegar\\\" waves a piece of parchment in the air.{/n} \\\"An appraiser of "
"magical items has come to the castle, hat in hand – a pathetic toady, trying to "
"win over the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} with trivial gifts. What can be more "
"amusing than the groveling of a miserable worm? I would have laughed at the fool "
"and thrown him out, were it not for one of the items he offers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25544c9a-1127-4160-8dae-51f7902b63f9"
msgid "\\\"Great! I will express your gratitude to the appraiser!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2a15fa9-6590-43a6-9394-6c252a61128a"
msgid "\\\"As you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "addff202-7884-4547-89a9-22ea1deee9de"
msgid "{n}\\\"Maegar\\\" just hums in response.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "059a458a-94d3-4c16-be45-14b76c8aabdb"
msgid ""
"\\\"This paper lists everything you can choose from. Among other things there's an "
"artifact that allows its owner some measure of control over the minds of mortals.\\"
"\" {n}The eyes of \\\"Maegar\\\" flash.{/n} \\\"If I were you... {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}... that is exactly what I would choose. "
"Never underestimate the intersection of magic and power.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba8ed966-d43f-4001-b16f-aaa4679c4a99"
msgid "\\\"A wise choice, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ef381d1-87d5-4686-bc1a-fd9e0d9aad46"
msgid "\\\"Leave the charm to the one who found it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1122f508-6b11-4cf3-9a84-f3e53d66a570"
msgid "[Pay 500 gold] \\\"Buy the charm and give it to the appraiser.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2450de17-a0e8-4b34-a27c-052bab580e53"
msgid "\\\"Seize the charm by force and give it to the appraiser.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47d5fb50-3225-4f6c-abd9-d528bde7e5ef"
msgid "\\\"You are quite capable of making this decision without me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f280d3d3-db4d-4bbf-ac36-f11fce5d33ac"
msgid ""
"\\\"A messenger from a distant village has arrived. Something strange is happening "
"there – it would appear that some wizard is fooling around! The locals have never "
"met any wizards, but one of them found a strange charm from the swamps not long "
"ago. He showed it to the whole village and bragged of his luck!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43ae02c7-8651-442e-b7d5-eb84f76135fd"
msgid ""
"\\\"The lucky fellow now completely refuses to allow anyone to examine the charm, "
"so no one has been able to discover if it is the reason behind the disorder in the "
"village. He is within his rights: he found it, and it's his property! Besides, the "
"magical interference so far has been harmless – no one has yet been hurt.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f522e47-772e-4eb7-90a5-14150d464ce4"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia taps on her chin thoughtfully.{/n} \\\"I think the locals are simply "
"scared, and nothing more. Let's not make something out of nothing, and leave the "
"charm to the person who found it. Otherwise we'll set an example for other "
"squealers – and be buried under an avalanche of anonymous letters! It's only one "
"little trinket – what's the worst that could happen?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "105d449b-a495-4a04-8c17-f3e115d62f33"
msgid ""
"\\\"A complicated situation, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. Dwellers in one of the distant villages have asked that we deal with "
"their neighbor – one way or another. They can't talk sense into him, which is why "
"they've turned to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c314139-c3c8-4bb2-8942-82a36ddd43b3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Their troublesome neighbor discovered a magical charm in the swamps – among "
"some ancient ruins, he claimed. Afterwards, strange things began to happen in the "
"village. One day a dead silence fell upon the whole area. Another day, the sun "
"seemed to stop shining. Everyone blames the charm, and they beg its owner to give "
"it up – but he refuses. He found it, and by his thinking, he'll be the one to "
"decide what to do with it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8eecb707-dbc0-43f2-88bc-8757b65accc0"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's dangerous to leave an unidentified magical item in hands of an ignoramus. "
"– All the more so when it seems to be causing such disturbing events. But it won't "
"be fair just to take it from him. I suggest we buy it from him, and then give it "
"to our appraiser for examination.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4a61e2d-e065-4275-90fe-540d8421a0c0"
msgid ""
"{n}\\\"Maegar\\\" looks annoyed.{/n} \\\"The vices and self-confidence of the "
"lower races never ceases to amaze me. A messenger from a distant village arrived "
"to the castle, requesting an investigation. It would appear that one of the "
"villagers has discovered a powerful artifact, which is releasing bursts of magical "
"energy and scaring the other peasants.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f27b093d-f052-4aad-b9e2-77e9336aaa08"
msgid ""
"\\\"This worm refuses to part with his newfound possession, so the stubborn man's "
"neighbors seek protection from you, their ruler. If I were you, I would set an "
"example, and tear the charm from the insolent fool's hands. – His dead hands, if "
"need be.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "048e7ee3-68a8-4c42-ba52-74092202cc7b"
msgid "\\\"Hooray! A fine decision!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e29e7585-0a83-4084-a8f9-d5cc71240ec7"
msgid ""
"{n}A shade passes over the Storyteller's face.{/n} \\\"Are you certain? I cannot "
"predict where such carelessness on your part might lead.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66c782b6-4b87-4285-9c46-f9699a2374b4"
msgid ""
"{n}\\\"Maegar\\\" sniffs disdainfully.{/n} \\\"Slaves can hardly be blamed for "
"intemperance, when their master indulges their ridiculous whims!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab00a3d1-afb8-40cf-92f4-030e1af70dee"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well… I suppose that's a reasonable solution. He would probably sell the charm "
"anyway, so this will be a win-win solution.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da8eb2fe-a642-4090-b4b1-bad633a8f50d"
msgid "\\\"As you wish, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e8aa493-ffd1-40c1-9878-b67cf041c92d"
msgid "\\\"A waste of money. But I will obey.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d9c59a8a-5a50-4add-a1a6-705325e1228e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hey! You can't behave like that! Especially with the poor – life is difficult "
"for them as it is!\\\" {n}Octavia pouts.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eeb2b3e6-8dc9-4614-9ea9-84463ba170a1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmm... indeed, that would solve our problem as well. I will do as you say, {mf|"
"Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89216719-de78-4524-a4d3-af3c3d046547"
msgid "\\\"I shall leave the castle at once and attend to the matter personally.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76fbdc75-a1af-400d-b221-95a65538fdbd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Fine! I will leave the charm with the fisherman. – The poor man deserves for "
"fortune to smile on him at last!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a11550ca-77b2-4b42-be25-78c41eef0189"
msgid ""
"\\\"I shall allocate the required sum, immediately purchase the charm and convey "
"it to the appraiser.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f52749e-d91e-4421-a654-fef0fd11b24c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I shan't hold back the guards if the peasant proves obstinate. I shall use "
"whatever force is required to procure the charm for the appraiser.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c765912-14b6-4970-9aaf-40bcdb57ee2f"
msgid "\\\"I forbid this necromancer from practicing his dark arts in my realm.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c06355e7-85d0-44a7-ad85-dbdaa70faab0"
msgid ""
"\\\"His offer sounds promising. The necromancer shall receive his license.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6084274-67cf-4fce-b188-59cc18ffc8b3"
msgid "\\\"I'll rely upon your advice in this matter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70b71eed-6f4c-43c4-a9d3-b8e4d93bd394"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have news. More and more mages come to our capital every day – and it seems "
"a small mage quarter is forming around the artifact appraiser. There's new "
"bookshops, new alchemy labs, and now we even have an illusionist's parlor! That "
"woman can conjure up more dresses and make-up and hairstyles than you could "
"imagine! Perfect for an evening out – just remember to get back home before the "
"spell wears off!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83c68394-a43c-4a38-abe6-2f26322356e5"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am pleased to inform Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness} that the "
"magical arts have blossomed in our lands, and each day more and more magic users "
"flock to our capital. A mage quarter of sorts has begun to form around the "
"artifact appraiser – bookshops, alchemy labs, and even an illusionist's parlor. "
"However, such rapid growth also attracts more... dubious practitioners.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eaf6f88b-6307-43c5-aae5-8f2c0b5a3801"
msgid ""
"\\\"The mystic arts are gradually taking root in your capital… as much as can be "
"expected in such a primitive era. Like ants swarming a mound, more and more gather "
"around that artifact appraiser. How proudly they present him with their poorly-"
"drawn scrolls and dandelion tinctures! But one of them proves even more amusing..."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0c5f5a3-c5ea-4f84-8f7b-5fac59218b75"
msgid ""
"\\\"However… there's a darker side to this expansion. A necromancer from Geb is "
"looking to set up shop in your domain. – He wishes to raise undead servants and "
"rent them out as cheap labor! In his homeland, skeletons till the fields, cut down "
"trees and mine ore... while elsewhere, around the world necromancy is strictly "
"forbidden, for in order to animate a dead body, one must snip off a small fragment "
"of the soul that once resided within it! Our guest asks you for a license. In "
"return, he promised to supply us with a fresh batch of 'workers'...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82d18acf-6607-42d5-9b6e-b4507477d759"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have been approached by a master necromancer from Geb. Considering that his "
"craft is outlawed and vilified across the world, he suggests a deal. We supply him "
"a license, allowing him to provide 'non-living workforce rental services' – Which "
"means we'll allow him to raise undead laborers and rent them out to farms, "
"sawmills and warehouses. In gratitude, he will deliver us his first batch of "
"'workers'.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f5971ea-7c84-47d8-8964-5a37f8a0fe80"
msgid ""
"\\\"A puny peddler, who dares to call himself a necromancer, sought an audience "
"with me. He begged us to give him a license which would allow him to create undead "
"slaves which he could then rent out to farms, sawmills and mines. Power over death "
"itself, and the spirits of the dead, even the secret of life eternal – all right "
"under his nose! And his only thought is to rent out farm labor!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0fe3f4f-7b83-4e66-ad09-f312aa82a8f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful! I hope this vulture will leave the capital for good, as soon as I "
"deliver him the news.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e1cab9a-ce8d-4ddf-9ac7-b6885c729d75"
msgid ""
"\\\"I support this decision wholeheartedly, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|"
"Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "046a68dd-86a7-43f5-b3aa-8d85bfed6471"
msgid ""
"\\\"An… interesting… decision. Especially in light of other decisions Your {mf|"
"Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness} has made earlier.\\\" {n}\\\"Maegar\\\" grins at "
"you knowingly.{/n} \\\"But as you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9cb00789-6bc2-4274-92b7-2685d51b4007"
msgid ""
"\\\"What?! You're going to let that vulture…\\\" {n}Octavia catches herself and, "
"after a moment, exhales loudly.{/n} \\\"As you wish. But this will be on your "
"conscience – not mine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "940f58d9-400c-4372-b18d-719cd9e0d830"
msgid ""
"{n}A deep shadow falls across the Storyteller's face.{/n} \\\"A most… unfortunate "
"decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee7c0326-e6a9-4103-8146-ed078224a569"
msgid ""
"{n}\\\"Maegar\\\" bows to you with grim satisfaction.{/n} \\\"I will tell the "
"necromancer of your decision. The might and power of our lands shall grow manifold."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "103b9d5f-13d0-4c08-bdde-be791c405893"
msgid ""
"\\\"I shall inform the necromancer that his dark arts have no place in these lands."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ead3a34-b1d5-4f75-ae14-00d9a1b6839c"
msgid ""
"\\\"He assured me that he only works with 'willingly donated materials' – bodies "
"of peasants who signed a contract prior to death. Nevertheless, I advise you to "
"decline his offer. It must be remembered that the necromancer must cut off a small "
"piece of the departed soul, in order to animate a body. Also bear in mind that our "
"living workers cannot compete with undead slaves. Thus our good people will grow "
"even poorer – and be forced to sell their own labor for even less. This would "
"result in a vicious cycle gradually making our state completely dependent on the "
"services of necromancers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1b515ee-0983-4b30-8cd1-cd552f5d8a27"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just thinking about it makes me sick. He vows only to use those who sign a "
"contract while they're still alive, selling their own bodies away for a few gold "
"coins. However, I have little doubt that this will lead to all sorts of trouble. "
"First, enterprising citizens will buy shovels and develop the habit of paying "
"nightly visits to the graveyard. Then beggars and orphans will start disappearing "
"from the streets... No, {name}, we cannot allow this to happen!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e917e4c-057e-4fdd-8ea1-54b842cde177"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nevertheless, in return for his license he promises to supply us with his "
"first batch of 'workers'. Of course, we should agree to his offer. No matter how "
"pitiful his creations might be, an undead slave is always worth more than a living "
"one. The undead never tire, and never fall sick. They obey orders without "
"question. They require no pay, no food, no rest – nor even light.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55fd0dd3-d6b4-4a3b-a11e-2fe4778da1ca"
msgid ""
"{n}Giving you a sharp look, \\\"Maegar\\\" continues in an irritated voice:{/n} \\"
"\"I should inform you that this will be the last order I shall take in this "
"position. I've had enough of this nonsense – and I've better things to do with my "
"time than squabble over petty complaints and run trifling errands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d26e483a-ba30-4d25-a4bf-647218c94008"
msgid ""
"\\\"From now on there will be no more magical experiments within the city walls. "
"It's far too dangerous.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9da06c1a-9339-48f4-bd6c-25f877510f2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"The experiments must continue. The townspeople will just have to put up with "
"it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71632d2a-550c-4712-b6fb-42d97bcf011e"
msgid "\\\"I leave this decision to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "745d4364-6223-47a3-a7a5-8976e8c1b1e0"
msgid ""
"{n}After a short silence, the Storyteller decides to continue:{/n} \\\"Forgive me, "
"Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}, but I can no longer occupy the position "
"of Magister. My advice is of no use to you, for we see life so differently. To "
"follow your orders means going against my conscience. I hope whoever replaces me "
"will be able to serve Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness} better than I could."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8297a6cf-a5b7-487e-8355-c7147bab87d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I… I just can't go on like this. We're just too different! All the "
"things that I'd pursue, you just say they're useless. Whenever I come up with an "
"idea, you reject it. Worst of all, your sense of right and wrong is completely "
"different from mine! {n}Octavia exhales decisively.{/n} \\\"I'll just have to give "
"up my position as Magister... no matter how difficult that is for me. But don't "
"worry, I'll still be glad to join you on your adventures and follow you into "
"battle.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7782055a-aaf8-4ed8-848b-659c30c70753"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, the townsfolk have launched a complaint against the inhabitants of the "
"mages' quarter. They speak of 'dubious characters prowling the streets', while "
"their sleep is disrupted by 'terrifying noises' and 'flashes of color'. So no big "
"deal, right? But the people became fed up when a young alchemist's mistake lead to "
"a... uhhh... contained explosion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3b1c97ac-3ad2-4a44-b20a-8cdb67c151aa"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's a matter that demands your personal attention, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|"
"Highness|Highness}. The people of the capital have lodged a complaint against the "
"inhabitants of the mages' quarter. Not only do unnatural sounds and strange lights "
"disturb the peace, especially within the quarter itself – but also, the ongoing "
"experiments have simply become too dangerous.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96362b0a-086e-4c43-aaac-b3fab638e7b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"The rabble once more forgets its place, {name}! A madding crowd of concerned "
"idiots has lodged a complaint against the inhabitants of the mages' quarter. The "
"brainless vermin tremble in terror at the sight of anything that exceeds their "
"narrow frame.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c74d52c-6bb1-41f6-86b7-f25b3b493c41"
msgid ""
"\\\"I understand just how… difficult it can be to live alongside mages and "
"alchemists. But if we forbid their experiments, the magical potential of our {mf|"
"barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} will surely dwindle! If we limit their freedom to "
"research, we'll clip our mages' wings, and they won't be able to help us expand. "
"Therefore, I think we should refuse the citizens' complaint.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "102f6611-19eb-4173-8d34-e97fbbbab774"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've no doubt that some of these reports might be exaggerated. However, I also "
"have no doubt that on the whole, the concerns of our citizens are well-founded. "
"Magical experiments have no place in a densely populated city. Thus, I suggest "
"that performing magical experiments inside the city walls should be outlawed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e176e07c-26d2-4cdf-8f73-311001163b38"
msgid ""
"\\\"The answer is clear. If one wishes for magic to continue growing and "
"developing in their {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}, one should accept that "
"many experiments end in explosions, whirlwinds and clouds of acid. It is vain to "
"hope for any better in these backwards lands. Those who complain may go to hell – "
"they're even more useless than our dimwitted mages.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca10b926-af24-428d-9c20-d7a731da9cf7"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia's shoulders sink.{/n} \\\"Perhaps… perhaps you're right. But how "
"crushing it will be to deliver this news to my friends…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8b8304a-9957-4b1f-b596-7b9b881a72ee"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller nods.{/n} \\\"I shall speak with the inhabitants of the mages' "
"quarter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e544f6d-4b1e-4384-88a6-2df9acf8a014"
msgid ""
"\\\"I knew you'd understand! Don't worry, I'll find a way to calm down the "
"neighbors. We'll put on a fireworks show or something…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "703057c0-5b7e-4d1a-828e-d551f49e1f6d"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller frowns.{/n} \\\"A risky decision, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|"
"Highness}. But so be it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f77d34db-2bb7-4ab6-8e82-8111ee3ef9bf"
msgid ""
"\\\"You put the interests of peasants and serfs above your own. Do you hope to buy "
"their loyalty with a show of weakness? How naïve.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54c35beb-2b72-4d96-ade5-fb9bfef8fc2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful! I shall tell everyone at the mages' quarter that they may carry on "
"with their experiments.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5dd6994b-0f6f-4cf0-a530-2b64cc9e618e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Splendid. I won't even bother replying to the whiners. It sickens me even to "
"look at them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "982c4388-1eb0-48a8-ba3a-76bdff1e5d55"
msgid ""
"{n}Giving you a sharp look, \\\"Maegar\\\" continues in an irritated voice:{/n} \\"
"\"I should inform you that this will be the last order I shall take in this "
"position. I've had enough of this nonsense – and I've better things to do with my "
"time than squabble over petty complaints and run trifling errands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5deed33-e5cc-46af-b43c-ca7ad428e2c7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Windows all along the street started shaking, and then some sticky purple "
"substance rained down on the town. Children started playing with it immediately. "
"Well, that was messy! Allegedly, it made the streets smell like a 'wet goblin's "
"hide' for a whole week!\\\" {n}Octavia tuts.{/n} \\\"They're amazingly well "
"versed, these accusers. They must have plenty of time to go out smelling wet "
"goblins!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5aeba8e0-3b96-4684-841d-19bed1e4c6e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"A young alchemist's experiments have lead to an explosion so powerful that his "
"neighbors up and down the street felt their window panes tremble. Later that day, "
"an unidentified purple substance fell from the sky – all over the city. Our people "
"complained that it made the capital reek of 'wet goblin hide'.\\\" {n}The "
"Storyteller raises a concerned eyebrow.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25c1e6e1-945b-417c-b3b1-93563e72567d"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you can imagine, this list includes practically everything: lights, noises, "
"and smells… The complaint was renewed today after an explosion at an alchemy lab "
"which made the whole city 'reek of wet goblin hide'! Ha!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85d31aa1-3010-4b62-97fd-66e1a06a3f88"
msgid ""
"\\\"From this day forth, the creation of undead, no matter the intent, is "
"forbidden, and shall be punished by law.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2b78062-5a8d-4f4e-8bf8-9642281541cb"
msgid ""
"\\\"My decision stands. Any subject who has received a necromancer's license may "
"carry on with their work as before.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5cb00e2f-a31a-40d3-bc5b-d6d902f152e8"
msgid "\\\"I trust in your vision. Act as you deem fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b18df751-cdac-4452-8214-6268c80d1a6e"
msgid ""
"\\\"He has my permission. Let's see if his golems are as good as he claims.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b84d1ba-622a-4438-843b-ad5c0709180e"
msgid "\\\"We shall not employ his services.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4f36abe5-2533-4512-9f22-43a442635da7"
msgid "\\\"You may resolve this issue as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "498fe3d6-d6b3-4148-8a25-fc22de82bb39"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia looks worried.{/n} \\\"Our dalliances with necromancy have not gone "
"unnoticed, {name}. The priesthood of {g|Pharasma}Pharasma{/g}, the goddess of fate "
"and death, has sent a delegation to our capital. The goddess abhors the undead, "
"and her followers demand that we 'put an end to the blasphemy' – that is, stop "
"creating undead laborers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e39b90a-12fa-4491-a7dc-ce5a585ebf26"
msgid ""
"\\\"A delegation of pharasmites has entered the capital, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|"
"Highness|Highness}. Necromancy disrupts the natural cycle of life and death, and "
"for that reason {g|Pharasma}the Lady of Graves{/g} forbids the practice of this "
"foul craft. Her priests and her faithful demand that we ban necromancy across your "
"lands and put an end to this blasphemy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fbd03dae-be8d-44c8-80c7-ce1629fee9fc"
msgid ""
"{n}Today, as always, \\\"Maegar\\\" is clearly not in high spirits...{/n} \\\"This "
"world is replete with meddlesome idiots. I am plagued by pharasmites. Their "
"goddess hates the undead, so they're constantly demanding that we surrender our "
"undead slaves and ban the creation of new ones.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "514b3ba8-cd1b-4a44-b285-635bc2bf9540"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think we should listen to the priests. Raising undead is an evil, violent "
"act. It cuts away and corrupts a fragment of the departed soul. We never should "
"have allowed this dark craft in our lands… and it is high time we put things right!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6bdb30d1-81ac-4ecf-8eb3-9233589723e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I believe that we should agree to their request. This is only because the "
"availability of cheap undead slaves has led to the impoverishment of living "
"laborers. But worse, in order to create an undead minion, a mage must cut away a "
"miniscule fragment of from the departed soul, and corrupt it with negative energy. "
"They then plant this seed back into the dead body. Nothing can justify such "
"depravity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b275c7f5-a0c4-4483-91cf-f8f82a50a60b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Their incessant wailing makes my teeth hurt. The imbeciles must learn their "
"place – and we must put an end to their complaints once and for all. Need I remind "
"you that necromancy is the only path that leads to true power?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c81b5d75-c009-4d8f-a48c-d34c96affffc"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia gives a sigh of relief.{/n} \\\"A decision that should have been made "
"long ago!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "78c7a496-ce6b-4ea8-95c7-eb398821206a"
msgid "\\\"And, just as before, it shall remain a cruel thing to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4535d008-0311-412f-a6c5-88dcb1a695ee"
msgid ""
"{n}\\\"Maegar\\\" snorts in derision.{/n} \\\"For some reason, I knew that you "
"wouldn't have the resolve to just send them away. Mage only hamper their own "
"growth when they bow to the will of clueless laymen.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b9bd582-43e1-44e0-89f1-5cfdb9710c84"
msgid "\\\"Very good. In that case, raising the undead shall become illegal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65968046-6d63-4527-af19-86f1d276aa46"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller nods.{/n} \\\"I shall inform {g|Pharasma}Pharasma's{/g} "
"faithful that they may rest easy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7387283c-a188-43f4-8bd9-0b8d05004609"
msgid ""
"\\\"Splendid. I shall decline the pharasmites' complaint, may they find themselves "
"in their goddess' cold embrace as swiftly as possible.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4a2fe7a-31f6-44f4-8744-640e0df7733c"
msgid ""
"\\\"An amazingly impudent fellow, {name}! I have been approached by a wizard from "
"Nex, who has learned to create golems from piles of literal junk: splinters of "
"wood, rusty nails, broken furniture… He asks your permission to set up shop in the "
"capital and start selling these junk golems. In return, he promises to provide us "
"with a few of his finer creations. Now, you may find this surprising... but I am "
"convinced that we must reject his proposal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "479eda8f-bd2b-429a-b07d-12777665bf2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"A most interesting proposition, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}. A "
"wizard from Nex has offered to create a number of golems for us, using only the "
"rubbish that litters the capital's streets.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4fe1d97-070f-40ea-83a6-9cf06926a6dc"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've received a curious offer. Some upstart from Nex has mastered the art of "
"creating golems. Even more, he assembles their bodies out of whatever junk he can "
"find. – A simple rubbish heap is typically enough. He is willing to grant us a few "
"specimens in exchange for permission to open a shop and sell his golems in the "
"capital. There's no reason to refuse. We could use a few workers who don't ask any "
"questions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7dbb13b9-aaee-4d0e-9a6f-5c949734c41e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I believe we should take him up on his offer. Golems are perfectly well suited "
"for guard duty, as well as hard physical labor. Usually, creating them can be "
"rather costly. However, the mage will take care of all the expenses – in exchange "
"for your permission to set up shop in the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff08c640-763d-45d6-a57f-5d609461015d"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia's eyes narrow.{/n} \\\"So what, as long as they're different from us, "
"enslaving sentient beings is fine?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de4dc303-5bf2-4f14-af3e-68b4cebd1e2d"
msgid "\\\"I shall instruct the mage to begin.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b89be95d-b2f2-414b-9f7e-f1dceefa89d1"
msgid "{n}\\\"Maegar\\\" nods impatiently.{/n} \\\"Wonderful.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86d9cb9f-2ae2-44c6-aa85-c1cb44820872"
msgid "\\\"Perfect. It will be my pleasure to get rid of this crook.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "399cba91-71d4-4ca4-b760-75b170528f5f"
msgid "{n}The Storyteller nods coldly.{/n} \\\"As you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70462223-e45b-4407-a766-c0de914fff50"
msgid "\\\"In that case the mage shall begin immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ddb110d-a682-4571-beed-952634624df4"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia shakes her head.{/n} \\\"What do I have to do to make you see just how "
"terrible necromancy really is?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "07e458ae-8d65-4736-b9f8-ed448710aeea"
msgid ""
"\\\"Moreover, the bumbling fool somehow stumbled upon a way to eradicate the main "
"flaw of many types of golems – the chance that the construct might go berserk. "
"Golems are animated by enslaving an elemental spirit and binding it to an "
"artificial body. Sometimes these spirits can go out of control. However, this "
"Nexian shyster has found a way to strengthen the magical restraints that hold them "
"captive.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ba34dfd-cd02-4b51-ab49-70526f57528a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you know how golems are created? A mage must ensnare a living spirit from "
"one of the elemental planes – most typically, an earth elemental – and bind it to "
"the construct. This means that golems are no better than slaves – after all, "
"elemental spirits are living, sentient beings. The mage even brags that his golems "
"'never go out of control' – as if total domination of a spirit makes the whole "
"thing any less cruel!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9290e726-90f4-4548-b83d-d9585a9aefac"
msgid ""
"\\\"An absolutely incomprehensible decision. Then again, that's nothing new...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d044726-5d7d-43fb-a90f-76a4f2025e3f"
msgid ""
"\\\"After assembling the body out of various junk, he binds to it an elemental "
"spirit, which lends the construct a semblance of life. In some golems, this "
"enslaved spirit may go out of control and become berserk. However, the mage "
"assured me that he has been able to completely eradicate this flaw. All he needs "
"now is your permission – and access to our rubbish heaps.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d65384fc-8ce3-4df5-a9db-fd0ad353344d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I won't be their new 'chief'. The shamans have ten days to leave my realm.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0c46aa9-83ec-4fc3-9ab7-a85b14d45dcb"
msgid ""
"\\\"They may remain in my lands — for as long as they serve me faithfully and "
"loyally.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18290bb0-3695-411c-8481-8957751186ef"
msgid "Ordered that the wayward shamans executed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "faff5629-a0d6-4714-adf0-271201c53176"
msgid ""
"\\\"Once a traitor, always a traitor. Arrest and execute every one of them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c6071dd-98a9-4bce-ad71-83bae53fc82a"
msgid "\\\"Do as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48300fa7-a046-4694-99b3-3061497a81f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I've just spoken with a Kellid shaman, who came in voluntarily and "
"surrendered himself to the guards. He and his brethren have fled their tribes. — "
"They know that they'll never win, and that you're 'the best chief', as he puts it. "
"Now they wish to serve you, and are even willing to share their knowledge with us."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d44c3a13-034f-4062-ab59-6644ba7e5c86"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, today the guards brought before me a barbarian shaman. He had "
"surrendered himself to them of his own free will. He and his… colleagues… have "
"fled their people, leaving their tribe behind. The way he puts it, they've seen "
"who's 'the best chief around here', and now they wish to serve you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6171e3f4-32e6-4a18-9e6e-4f955be6cf10"
msgid ""
"{n}\\\"Maegar\\\" sounds tired and impatient.{/n} \\\"Just now the guard have "
"brought before me a barbarian shaman who willingly surrendered himself. The savage "
"is so dim and mush-mouthed that I could barely understood what he said.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4d8850e0-021d-4902-b67c-a705acb5171e"
msgid ""
"\\\"But I don't think we should take them up on their offer. It's not that their "
"word can't be trusted… but our security is more valuable than any assistance they "
"could offer. Plus, the people are scared to death of them. — They can summon "
"ferocious beasts, and not long ago, they were doing terrible things in the service "
"of our enemy. I believe it would be best to simply command them to leave and never "
"return.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0597a1f-0906-4d61-b044-d5941829f0c5"
msgid ""
"\\\"This turn of events is most fortunate. Don't let their background discourage "
"you – their magical traditions are centuries old, and we've much to learn from "
"them. Of course, our people fear them at the moment, but I believe in time that we "
"can disperse these fears.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86c331b3-8d1e-4631-a144-8d9622a77aa9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've no use for them. — There's enough useless idiots around here as it "
"stands. I suggest we simply rid ourselves of this burden.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac927b76-8c12-4a6f-836d-c7d268eb8f8f"
msgid "\\\"Wonderful, {name}! I'll tell them as much!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8bdae760-2cdc-4bad-96e9-be062891115d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Most disheartening. A new ally stretches out his hand to share his knowledge "
"in friendship, and we push him away. Why?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3c26284e-a032-44e5-9403-fc8011a68815"
msgid ""
"\\\"Better we were slaughtering them to the one. Oh well, at least it's less fuss "
"this way.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f238416b-8c0f-4709-abe1-d8e1f522b3c3"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is not the best decision. Your subjects will surely not approve of this — "
"and I can't blame them!\\\" {n}Octavia falls silent, contemplating something.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b12c43e6-ced6-4333-9609-5eb349140ca4"
msgid "\\\"I see, Your Highness. I shall inform them of their new duties.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc5a236b-9c88-4fdb-8b99-92a87fe376e9"
msgid "\\\"Damnation! You wish to burden me with these primitive louts?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2c13096-7690-4c1d-8900-a58f55573701"
msgid "\\\"Perfect. I don't wish to spend another moment on them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2a05f00-acf8-419b-a057-5632b5297297"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia gasps, and her face loses all color.{/n} \\\"By the gods! Why such "
"cruelty?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b3b6a37d-9670-46e4-a51b-d3c8ece14bb6"
msgid "{n}The Storyteller's face darkens.{/n} \\\"A severe punishment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c31f773-2173-41b2-9355-2a0b356402d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"It seems he and the other shamans have fled their unwashed cousins to come "
"serve us. Who would have thought! And their leader even generously promised to "
"share the 'ancient secrets' of their primitive magics! Pfft!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "428b596d-976e-48fd-a4e8-965370b2961a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I'll send them away. We'll do without their troublesome services.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "515581f5-9200-40fe-9c63-1db3169c0474"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's trouble, {name}! A powerful magical anomaly has afflicted one of our "
"regions! According to the local mages, spells either simply don't work, or lead to "
"completely unexpected results. While trying to repair his carriage, an experienced "
"mage unwittingly levitated a bystander. Elsewhere, a famous illusionist was "
"setting off fireworks, but instead turned the ground under his audience's feet "
"into deep and slippery mud.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c27d279-9ca3-4c9e-a99f-40bca4f1bdc3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Troubling news, Your Highness. Magic has turned wild in one of the regions. "
"Spells are not working as intended. The incidents are numerous and varied. While "
"trying to repair his carriage, an experienced mage unwittingly levitated a "
"bystander. Elsewhere, a famous illusionist was setting off fireworks, but instead "
"turned the ground under his audience's feet into deep and slippery mud.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "327c5721-8a25-4f9c-a942-fbb4ffe01adf"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your subjects are cowering at shadows again. Somewhere off in the provinces, "
"spells have stopped working as intended. One 'mage' tried to repair his wagon, and "
"instead levitated one of the onlookers. Another wanted to captivate and amaze the "
"idiots gathered around him by means of simple fireworks — and ended up turning the "
"ground under their feet into deep, loose mood. There's no end to the complaints: "
"magical fires, acid storms, ferocious attacks of animated furniture...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e025c736-7aa8-4caf-87d7-548a3b536428"
msgid ""
"\\\"New reports pour in by the day — magical fires sweep the settlements, storms "
"of acid form from nothing. Furniture comes to life and attacks its owners! The "
"worst part is that we have no clue as to the nature or cause of this. There are "
"simply no scholars with sufficient knowledge remaining in the kingdom. — We put "
"too many restrictions on the inhabitants of the mages' quarter... All that remains "
"is to deal with the consequences.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d53a93b-4a1a-4599-aa54-7fcde57183b6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The High {mf_HighPriest|Priest|Priestess} may be able to help those who are "
"suffering. — For now, divine magic remains unaffected by the anomaly. Still, who "
"can say how long it will stay that way? If you want my advice, support our "
"governors with gold from the treasury. That way they'll be able to solve any "
"crises in a timely manner, as the situation dictates.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8619760e-db95-4423-9f32-081a6b5cd593"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course, no one had any idea what was happening until I intervened and "
"determined that we're dealing with a magic anomaly. Perhaps I would even be "
"willing to study it a bit more closely… However, since you've put all these "
"restrictions on mages, there's no one left in the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|"
"kingdom} with enough intelligence to assist me. And naturally, I have no wish to "
"pursue such research alone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42fbf8cd-8e39-4661-83b5-cb3bf7d3b85c"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia is as pale as ash.{/n} \\\"{name}… There was a poisonous gas leak "
"tonight, during another experiment in the magic quarter. It's... it's horrendous. "
"People died in their homes, unable to crawl to their door… Many simply tucked in "
"for the night, never to awaken... It wasn't until early morning that someone heard "
"some weak moans coming from one of the streets that run alongside the quarter...\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e32d66cf-8c2f-4a9e-afbc-385f9f035bc6"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller looks concerned.{/n} \\\"Tragedy has struck the magic quarter, "
"Your Highness. Another one of their experiments ended in a poisonous gas leak. "
"However, because the experiment was held in the dead of night, the alarm came too "
"late. People died silently in their own homes. — Too weak to get away, too weak to "
"call for help...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "020d8c26-fb25-402e-af16-e5613a778db1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ha! The lower races are so entirely ill-suited for magic! Last night's "
"experiments in the mages' quarter ended in a poisonous gas leak that went "
"unnoticed for hours. As one would expect, it was morning by the time our dim-"
"witted townsfolk realized what was happening. — Once they started stumbling over "
"their neighbors' corpses.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12b3da69-8b31-4915-8412-e4faac37a01e"
msgid ""
"\\\"New reports pour in every day — magical fires, acid storms, attacks of "
"animated furniture… The reason behind this magic anomaly is beyond our "
"understanding, for not a single one of our subjects is knowledgeable enough about "
"magic. Our greatest scholars left the kingdom a long time ago, citing "
"'infringement on their freedom to research'. Now we can only battle the "
"consequences.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a4be593-6490-4100-8fb9-3ad1f2cda4f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Treasurer could simply send some money to the poor souls, and hope they "
"can deal with their problems themselves. However, the more reliable course would "
"be to enlist the aid of the High Priest. Divine magic is powerful, and unlike "
"arcane magic, it remains untouched by the anomaly. — It still works as it's "
"supposed to.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c03f7c8-9694-4941-8b26-c33335dd432d"
msgid ""
"\\\"As always, the knaves expect that you… Your Highness… shall come to their "
"rescue. Perhaps the Treasurer can buy their silence for a few coins. Or you could "
"order the High {mf_HighPriest|Priest|Priestess} to intervene. In any case, it is "
"pointless for me to help you reach a decision. The suffering of the rabble are no "
"concern of mine. Therefore, I shall leave it up to you to deal with this most "
"fascinating dilemma.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d942d0b-1b0e-4ad1-9193-c32ad8979d0a"
msgid ""
"\\\"The poisonous cloud is no more — the wind dissipated it. But everywhere there "
"are people wounded and disfigured by the gas. There's no two ways about it — we "
"must help them! I suggest sending our best healers and priests in immediately. "
"What use is a monetary compensation if you've become a cripple!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "868d7380-875c-4dbf-b200-6fd7e5eb8343"
msgid ""
"\\\"The poisonous cloud has dispersed, but its victims are many. We could ask the "
"High {mf_HighPriest|Priest|Priestess} to send healers into the quarter, in hopes "
"of saving some of those who are dying — but they have little hope of success. "
"However, it would be best if the treasurer provides those afflicted with a "
"monetary compensation. Some will be wish to hire healers for their loved ones, and "
"others — gravediggers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d80c8f38-7dbe-47ef-b8e1-353864ce692b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The High {mf_HighPriest|Priest|Priestess} could deal with the wounded. The "
"Treasurer could open the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}'s coffers and give out "
"gifts to all who suffered. I see no point in either, so do whatever you see fit. "
"Frankly, I simply cannot care…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea0d6edf-562c-498f-a8bb-0a0cd877e02b"
msgid "\\\"The limitations stand.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f03385a1-0ecf-4463-a2c1-83a0e3bb022b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Amend the law as needed. Henceforth, any and all magical components may be "
"traded in my domain.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "998a54a8-1739-4628-8c66-7a477795e429"
msgid ""
"\\\"We cannot allow baseless fears to dictate our actions. We shall set not "
"needless limits on the freedoms of spellcasters.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f3784f1-a3c5-4db9-b889-9996d3054acf"
msgid ""
"\\\"The delegation's demands are well founded. I order you to issue a decree, and "
"set out to regulate the use of magic in the settlements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4203eb67-7a80-4077-bf8c-530e8b511a98"
msgid "\\\"I'll trust you with this decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db3341ee-6249-407c-a56c-eb2d2a1dd2cf"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, the artifact appraiser approached me — do you remember him? Our friend "
"has become quite an influential figure in the mages' quarter. Perhaps even its "
"unofficial leader, in a sense. And this… worries me somewhat.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "089ea1e9-58b5-4362-b408-964a34441adb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our acquaintance, the artifact appraiser, has sought my audience once more. "
"The mages' quarter has grown — and with it, the influence of its unofficial "
"leader. However, the appraiser feels that this growth is still far from its "
"limits… This time he wanted to speak of trade – in particular, alchemical "
"ingredients and the material components of spells.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "80c4207b-7eaf-4580-a241-b2ff81a8646d"
msgid ""
"\\\"The artifact appraiser from the mages' quarter has once more sought my "
"audience. It seems he's become something of a leader for the rabble who dwell "
"there. Somehow, this time he's thought up something useful — to permit the trade "
"of any and all rare ingredients and magical components.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b30776bc-792a-4f4a-a88a-341b6ec4011a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why, you ask? Well, he's urging us to lift all trade restrictions on "
"alchemical ingredients and other material components for spellcasting. – Even such "
"things as black onyx, devil blood… and human hearts. Do I have to explain why I'm "
"against the buying and selling of body parts? — Or any other ingredients that "
"empower the darkest and vilest of spells?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "448b177b-f70e-4989-a120-a92a9f1a8c31"
msgid ""
"\\\"He complains of the difficulty in acquiring the materials necessary for the "
"more… exotic types of spells. In the capital, at least, such materials as black "
"onyx, devil blood, or even the hearts of the deceased – these are only available "
"on the black market. Most merchants are afraid to stock them, assuming that they "
"are banned by law, just as they are in the lands of our neighbors. However, our "
"laws are in fact silent on the issue.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a54823d-d0f6-4ac9-8983-c27dc0b18db5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Today, black onyx, devil's blood and human hearts can only be found on the "
"black market. Such a deplorable state of affairs should indeed be remedied at once "
"– there's no doubt of that. Such a decision would greatly hasten the growth of the "
"magical arts in these lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a181cf1b-d219-40dc-9cd9-518a4f5c925b"
msgid ""
"{n}A tired smile crosses Octavia's lips.{/n} \\\"I never thought I'd be pushing "
"for any sort of restrictions or limitations… but my time at this post has shown me "
"that sometimes you can't do without them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f0352ce-b59d-4ce4-88f0-93e2a23162c9"
msgid "\\\"As Your Highness wishes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e34f75a0-a3eb-4a4e-9014-aed1c82bd7d7"
msgid "{n}\\\"Maegar\\\" shrugs.{/n} \\\"Your domain — your loss.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b3c2cc14-9256-427a-aea5-b094c68ec072"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia looks away.{/n} \\\"I just don't know, {name}… It sounds dangerous. "
"Still, you're the {mf|King|Queen} — you know best.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e341b1fa-16f3-42e0-ae06-8372b4043236"
msgid "\\\"I shall look to it immediately, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89a7f94a-97aa-4913-ab39-2146ebfa4cd2"
msgid "\\\"A wise choice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b67cec6d-d576-4959-b00b-7b38857c184f"
msgid ""
"\\\"I do not envy you, {name}. It's a tough decision. We're at an impasse — the "
"simple folk can no longer 'suffer the threats' of our mages and sorcerers. A wave "
"of protests has rolled across the capital and the surrounding regions. I've just "
"spoken to a delegation that represents the people. Their demands are quite clear.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e5c20a9-d6cb-40e1-98d7-b047143bbd11"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller looks tired and sullen.{/n} \\\"Your Highness, the people are "
"unhappy. Your subjects feel certain that mages and sorcerers who practice their "
"craft in the settlements are a source of constant danger — and they shall suffer "
"it no more. I've just spoken with a whole delegation, assembled from "
"representatives from every corner of the land. They are petitioning a change. I "
"must admit, I do take their points.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bfbb77f1-e8f7-493a-bfff-d0d172fbd5c5"
msgid ""
"\\\"What a farce! Frightened, wriggling worms, trying to manipulate forces they "
"cannot possibly comprehend! All across the kingdom, peasants are demanding the "
"restriction of magic use in the settlements. A wailing delegation of fools from "
"every region of the kingdom entertained me for an eternity today, gnashing their "
"teeth and beating their chests.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "082a57b2-f5b2-47fc-b713-15f403c31e8e"
msgid ""
"\\\"They want us to restrict the use of magic in places where people live. This "
"will mean that casting spells and brewing potions will require a permit. Even "
"then, it would only be allowed on the outskirts of settlements – and during the "
"day. Can you imagine the outrage that such measures would spark in every member of "
"the magic community? And is a false feeling of safety worth limiting people's "
"freedoms? I don't think so!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15a90309-a459-4533-8ef0-424c709decd9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've anticipated this development, and I believe that the petitioners are in "
"the right. Justice demands that the safety of the majority be placed above the "
"freedoms of the minority.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84d2262f-abd5-4209-8390-8f97c54cec3a"
msgid ""
"\\\"They wish to limit the practice of magic to those who possess permits! "
"Moreover, they also demand that all existing magic schools and laboratories be "
"transferred from the center of civilization to its outskirts! It's more than clear "
"that these oafs should be put in their place.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cdf2dfaf-866a-40fb-a6a9-0a8998d97b6a"
msgid "\\\"Well said. So be it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37295bea-89c8-4880-b4f8-583d66d6010d"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller nods in contemplation.{/n} \\\"I understand. I shall inform the "
"delegation of your decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a38649a-3c7e-491d-abcd-eb1fa630dc29"
msgid "\\\"The only correct decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6946f1c5-ec3a-4eed-b0b4-3c5325083cf8"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll never understand why you're doing this. Nevertheless, I will carry out "
"your order.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0daa71dd-7a3a-4a7d-84e4-9774679df66c"
msgid ""
"{n}The creased Storyteller's brow slowly unfurrows.{/n} \\\"We'll get to working "
"straight away, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b9dd0a9-dab4-4618-a301-ab8056f749b6"
msgid ""
"{n}Gritting his teeth and piercing you with his gaze, \\\"Maegar\\\" squeezes out "
"a cold smile.{/n} \\\"As you wish… Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f074d326-6006-4d23-9222-da7381b3f134"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thus, the appraiser has asked us to permit the trade of such materials. You "
"may find this unexpected, but I believe we should grant his request. It's the only "
"measure that would allow us any control over how these foul substances are "
"procured and used. And in the case of such ingredients as human organs – well, "
"oversight is crucially important.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "849edeb6-8577-48a9-93d0-7fc9649b5c5f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Their principle demand is the introduction of restrictions on the use of magic "
"in densely inhabited places. Firstly, spellcasting and potion brewing within "
"settlements should only be allowed for those who have received a proper permit "
"from the town hall or village elder. Secondly, all magic schools and laboratories "
"should be moved to the outskirts of settlements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1db08a23-e0ba-480b-a554-e75ab952d0c8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I'll lift the prohibition altogether. Trust me, you'll see the benefits "
"of this decision after a couple of years.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94611366-9b11-4e3f-b4c6-189b9f5cdbe4"
msgid ""
"\\\"I see no use in such cowardly laws. I'll see to its removal for the sake of "
"all respectable spellcasters who desperately need their components — whether the "
"commoners like it or not.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d714cd00-052d-41f5-ba02-dfe1aba75898"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, {name}, if only I could put into words those heavenly sounds! An orchestra "
"is but soft clay in Larzio's hands. One moment the singing of angels descends upon "
"you from the stage — and the next you are overtaken by the roar of Hell itself! Of "
"course, there are always critics. — Where's the deep message? What are the "
"existential questions? — But can you ever please them?! Anyway, I'm exalted! The "
"audience is going out of their minds! Larzio is triumphant! Anything anyone can "
"talk about is what the world would have lost were it not for your keen taste and "
"unrivalled generosity! And the scale of production! And the decorations! And... "
"And...\\\" {n}Exhausted and completely out of breath, Linzi pauses to collect "
"herself.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd6b12fc-d20e-4f03-be0e-6779c79814ee"
msgid ""
"\\\"The premiere of maestro Messus' opera was a success. His name thunders across "
"all the kingdom. Tickets are already sold out for the next two months, and the "
"audience sings praises of the composer's talent – and his patron's generosity. "
"However, the critics noted the somewhat... shallow... plot. And of the "
"overabundance of battle scenes, and costumes and decorations. And to be honest, I "
"cannot argue with them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "adc31db5-677d-450e-8844-69e70b4fe9ae"
msgid ""
"\\\"The premiere was a howling success! The tickets are selling faster than they "
"can be printed, and the audiences are raving. The ever-disappointed critics "
"complain of the \\\"shallow plot\\\" and \\\"flag-waving patriotism\\\", but their "
"words find no purchase in the vacant minds of the audience. Larzio Messus held a "
"speech to express his gratitude, and dedicated the opera to you. You are praised "
"in the streets and eulogized in toasts. I congratulate you, {name} — you've etched "
"your name in history as a most generous patron of the arts... and an even shrewder "
"politician.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1537362-2bba-40b0-a63c-7096a1c0389a"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know, {name}… no matter what obstacles have risen before us, and what "
"troubles we've faced, we've always reached new heights. Just think — just a few "
"short years ago, there wasn't even anyone here to talk to around these parts, "
"aside from the Stag Lord's thugs and the miserable, frightened peasants. Today you "
"can't throw a shoe without hitting a bard! Every day there's more exhibitions, "
"plays, and concerts...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ddbd378e-6c75-4267-a543-4aab1589947d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, there's something else I wish to mention. Every day I receive "
"new supplicants — painters, bards, and sculptors — and no matter how hard I labor, "
"the next day there's only more. But I suppose it's a good sign. It means that the "
"seeds we've planted here have come to bear fruit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f9cb9497-7f30-4d4f-a4d1-19d9ec4518ad"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your success speaks for itself. Before you arrived here, none but mindless cut-"
"throats and cowering peasants lived here. After winning the rule of this "
"backwater, you've managed to turn it into the cultural metropole of the River "
"Kingdoms. I've watched this struggle with interest — and I am impressed. Few are "
"capable of such deeds.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1a81c73-f253-4f7f-8511-158840087cd3"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}… Larzio is dead. He never lived to see his opera reach the stage. "
"However, someone in Galt did stage his tragicomedy... and the audiences are "
"raving! The critics have declared him the most talented composer of his generation "
"— and the most underappreciated. His music mesmerized me as well. As for the "
"satire and the plot... it's a bit too bitter for my taste, even vitriolic. His "
"admirers are already organizing trips to our kingdom — to see the sights their "
"favorite genius lived by...\\\" {n}Linzi sighs.{/n} \\\"And still... still, life "
"goes on.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc832225-279e-4f0d-b090-b779d2c31eac"
msgid ""
"\\\"We have news from Galt. The posthumous production of Larzio Messus' opera has "
"been a great success with the audience. The critics praise his poignant satire, "
"his 'merciless keen eye and sharp tongue'. Many visit our kingdom to take in the "
"sights that inspired their favorite author.\\\" {n}For a long time, the "
"Storyteller remains silent.{/n} \\\"I must say, I haven't heard such music as his "
"in many decades. It is hard to believe that a mind so young could have produced "
"such flawless harmony...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1161731-9df0-437a-9177-576d219eff57"
msgid ""
"\\\"Larzio Messus' opera was staged after all… after his death, in Galt. The "
"premiere of the tragicomedy was sensational, and the critics have declared him a "
"genius. His insolent and slanderous attacks against you and your authority are the "
"season's 'precise and poignant satire'... But there's a silver lining: his "
"admirers flock to our land, wishing to see for themselves where the events of the "
"opera took place. No doubt, the result could have been far better had we supported "
"the composer. But yet...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8e36af87-d056-46c2-9692-4d779f4fff3c"
msgid ""
"\\\"The opera's premiere was a complete disaster!\\\" {n}Linzi hesitates in "
"silence.{/n} \\\"I've no idea how it came to pass… but one thing is certain — "
"Larzio's talent did not shine through. The audience was indifferent for the most "
"part. But the critics tore Larzio to pieces. – For his \\\"utter lack of taste\\\" "
"as well as \\\"groveling before the powers that be\\\"... Oh well. You can't win "
"them all. We've pretty much failed on this one, but it won't be our last chance to "
"do something wonderful.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7554e244-c79d-4a93-b52d-dcf223caf146"
msgid ""
"\\\"The opera's premiere was a disgrace. As expected, without strict oversight and "
"daily support, Larzio was unable to come up with anything of worth. Even the low "
"peasants wouldn't choke down the detestable tunes… Still, his failure only serves "
"as a foil for the overall prosperity that the kingdom has achieved in these last "
"few years.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e991747-f2df-41b6-9287-cf197b5543a7"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's something more to people's lives now than back-breaking labor all day, "
"and a jug of moonshine before sleep. They've somewhere to go, something new to "
"see, something to talk about – and think about! I guess I just wanted to say that "
"I'm proud. — I'm proud of how daily life has changed in your lands, and I'm proud "
"that you let me be a part of that change.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5bdfbe6-faff-455f-a712-463ec836f842"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, yesterday was the premiere of maestro Larzio's opera. The event "
"was… not everything we might have hoped. Much of the audience left after the first "
"act. The critics lambasted the author — both for 'ill taste' and 'subservience "
"before the powers that be'.\\\" {n}The Storyteller falls silent, his bony fingers "
"fumbling with his sleeve.{/n} \\\"However...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d54c6faf-9860-4cda-9628-a8a55f561f88"
msgid ""
"\\\"Once, only bandits and peasants lived here — but now a beautiful city has "
"sprung up, full of energy and the sound of music. I have not always agreed with "
"the decisions you make, but I am happy that I was able to take part in the rebirth "
"of the Stolen Lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7be85755-000b-4c79-9505-29a3b2e25509"
msgid ""
"\\\"Larzio Messus' opera premiered yesterday! His work was met with great "
"excitement by the townsfolk, and even the critics are mostly satisfied. I loved "
"the music, but he needs to work on his writing a bit more… But all in all it was a "
"great result for a budding composer!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "beff42e9-ccdb-4c63-ba25-8bbeebc4776b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Maestro Messus' opera has finally been staged, Your Highness. The premiere was "
"a success: both the audience and the critics were quite satisfied. Some noted that "
"the production might have been a bit more... grandiose. But I do not think the "
"work would have benefitted from that. I would say that the young composer has a "
"long and illustrious career ahead of him...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b920df3b-ad0a-4d7d-b005-e0af8fed75b2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Larzio's opera has just premiered, and to much fanfare! The audience is "
"thrilled, and overflowing with patriotic feelings. The critics are mixed, but the "
"people are too vacant to listen anyway. Of course, the production could have been "
"more grandiose… but we'll surely correct that flaw in Larzio's future work.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "253522a8-0a95-445c-a00f-2976271d3b8b"
msgid ""
"\\\"People completely ignored any sort of art until just recently. But look at "
"them now! Every new exhibition, every staged play, every foreign bard makes them "
"so happy! And creators are also happy to see their ruler's favor and fortune. On "
"the downside, there's talk that our cultural life is a little too close to that of "
"Irovetti... but you can't please everyone, am I right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e651fc7-990c-4a44-b75f-0260dc0ac19e"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I wish to commend you for the great fulfilment we're witnessing under "
"your rule. I speak of art, that most fanciful and gentle flower only a ruler can "
"truly grow. Perhaps not all of your subjects' creations flatter you, but this is "
"merely an indication that the artists enjoy as much freedom in your lands as they "
"like.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "287a5995-e110-40a1-a2f5-0d5c7990e27a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Freedom of thought runs rampant in your domain. This phenomenon is a danger to "
"any ruler. Nonetheless, you remain on your throne, which is clearly an indication "
"of your subjects' affection. Despite what I might think about the path you've "
"chosen, I must admit, the Stolen Lands have become the cultural center of the "
"River Kingdoms under your governance. Few rulers are in a position to carry out "
"such work.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df5081f3-5e54-4127-8a8f-2d9d97fa8a8e"
msgid ""
"[Pay 100 BP] \\\"We will open schools. I don't want my lands to be inhabited by "
"uneducated bumpkins.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5de10ff6-39c0-4fe5-8111-4067059be7ed"
msgid "\\\"Forget about schools. There are already enough ways to spend money.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ebc6580-1f5c-400f-91b2-9e5319797fbb"
msgid "\\\"Make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e1e05f3-b1eb-43d7-9449-2cfdcfd65c8e"
msgid ""
"[Pay 100 BP] \\\"I would follow your advice. Spend the money on opening new pubs "
"and inns.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77467524-d8a8-4872-ad0b-b55a98322f1e"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi waves her hands in excitement.{/n} \\\"Finally, finally you have your own "
"advisor for cultural affairs! I am so happy you entrusted this to me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f7071d1-40fe-4a46-96f4-fe1fb3dffdd0"
msgid ""
"\\\"First of all – art in our {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} is not doing so "
"well. People care more about the soil and what it can give them, and not about "
"affairs of the spirit or the life of the mind. But we can fix this! Your subjects "
"just need a gentle nudge in this direction...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e6ca1d8-2ccd-4ffb-8d74-4eaabf367ef7"
msgid ""
"\\\"You just have to spend a little money and time on education! Open private "
"schools, offer classes at temples, or even invite foreign teachers to the capital "
"– anything will be better than what we have now! What do you say?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "025fff4b-50f1-4174-b476-668fe21812c1"
msgid ""
"\\\"My respects, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\" {n}"
"The storyteller bows.{/n} \\\"I'm sorry to disturb you, but there is an important "
"issue concerning my responsibilities.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3c07206e-0aa9-4295-8cbd-a678fe6634e0"
msgid ""
"\\\"As a curator I could not help but notice that the level of education in your "
"{mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} is abysmal. Many citizens don't know how to "
"read, and they send their children out not to study, but to work from dawn to "
"dusk. We must break this vicious circle.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8b20429-5841-4551-9865-e4e6042eb12a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Make the first step. Order the opening of village schools – or at least "
"contact the priests who are educated enough to teach their congregation reading, "
"writing and natural science. Of course, this will require no little investment, "
"but the result will justify any expense.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a79f1384-7493-4843-ac6a-b9b175fb0d7f"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal raises her eyes.{/n} \\\"I have become the curator in your {mf|barony|"
"barony|kingdom|kingdom} according to your wishes. So please listen to what I will "
"say as your advisor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a41e3e2a-e07d-49f1-962e-43e7c2dff285"
msgid ""
"\\\"Among my responsibilities is ensuring that your subjects are educated and "
"knowledgeable. But instead I offer a warning: a peasant who knows much is a "
"peasant who riots much. Give them no reason to reason, and you'll keep them eating "
"out of your hand.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f0d2387a-faf9-4c8b-848c-f05c609c190a"
msgid ""
"\\\"There are no schools in your lands – and that's a beautiful start. Rather than "
"building schools, I suggest the construction of more pubs and alehouses, where the "
"peasantry can drown their days in oblivion. There is no more obedient servant, "
"than one who sees only the bottom of his beer mug. I strongly suggest you continue "
"this state of affairs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "001ada70-47ee-47ad-ba9b-a23f7d1f2b8e"
msgid "\\\"Yes! We'll do just that!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6b8d7d8-d940-407a-87fd-6c36f8ad4a83"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller nods.{/n} \\\"A wise decision, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a37e5684-ed02-4a0a-b955-27565a9b504b"
msgid "\\\"A pity. I'm sorry you can't see past your own nose.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a14c3c3-2d1a-4b7d-a471-21923fd191e8"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi looks like she is about to cry.{/n} \\\"But... what about the future of "
"the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}? You can't be stingy about such things! You "
"just can't!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da149b54-ad92-4dc9-9db5-28390238d280"
msgid ""
"{n}A wrinkle appears on the Storyteller's forehead.{/n} \\\"This is none too "
"provident on your part. This investment would pay dividends far into the future, "
"when today's children become tomorrow's scientists and wizards.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c938cd74-76f5-4345-b9c1-a1557592ae1a"
msgid ""
"\\\"What is there to decide? Of course we'll open schools! I'll handle everything, "
"don't you worry!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "493e4528-e8bd-46ee-bce8-952fb49de4a9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for your trust. I will order the opening of reading and writing "
"classes at our temples.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75d95170-d70b-4bd7-b861-d1aa297f1720"
msgid ""
"\\\"There aren't enough places in your capital where the citizens can sit and "
"think about nothing. I will remedy this immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f179f46e-e627-4192-b52b-e7f86bc84a21"
msgid "{n}The elf smiles delicately.{/n} \\\"With pleasure.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42355beb-02d4-47fe-b926-5db14ef49d8b"
msgid "[Pay 75 BP] \\\"I wish to support this art society financially.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aef8b106-220d-4926-91e5-4ba15506fae5"
msgid "[Pay 50 BP] \\\"We shall help them found and promote this society.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2aab1c6-95ed-4bc3-b7ee-b49683764a9c"
msgid "\\\"We will not be participating.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85360aee-0cfe-4bab-9fef-2493d97dc77d"
msgid "\\\"Do as you deem right.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7a50890-5ead-44c1-ab50-d10fc480e939"
msgid ""
"\\\"I need a moment of your time! I have here someone who is sure to help us turn "
"this city into the cultural capital of the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aacdd2c4-2b6d-4df6-9502-86591a25a312"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller raises his hand to get your attention.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, please spare me a few moments. As your "
"curator, I request you listen to this kind lady, who wishes to discuss with you "
"something of great importance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f969636c-5a84-4671-8fb9-e44503b81df4"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal waves carelessly in the direction of an aasimar.{/n} \\\"A petitioner. "
"She insisted on a personal meeting.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd16451f-acad-4aed-a74d-032565216c94"
msgid ""
"{n}The aasimar bows. The young woman is wearing simple clothes, but carries "
"herself with dignity.{/n} \\\"My greatest respect, {mf|baron|baroness|my King|my "
"Queen}! My name is Rikri Sharvan, and I am the leader of a small group of "
"enthusiasts, who wish to enrich life in the city. I come to you for two reasons: "
"to tell you about our cause, and to ask for your support.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c86c1bfe-5358-4c00-a1f2-35e0d195e1e5"
msgid ""
"\\\"A while ago an idea emerged in our ranks. Even though there are many ways to "
"entertain oneself in the capital, there are still not enough cultural events "
"taking place, even as artists are starved for money and audience. Thus we have "
"decided to form a society for the appreciation of fine arts! Each member pays a "
"modest monthly fee, and in return gets to vote which event the society should fund "
"each month. Just imagine: the community will finally be able to organize "
"exhibitions, performances, philosophical debates, concerts – and do this all on "
"its own! We will inspire our friends and neighbors – but in order to provide an "
"adequate reward for our most distinguished artists, we shall need to attract more "
"members, and increase our funds.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90b80f86-2a9f-4120-9587-42906999f704"
msgid ""
"{n}Rikri folds her hands.{/n} \\\"All we ask of you is a little support. Any funds "
"you can spare will be most welcome, of course, but we especially need your help in "
"founding and promoting the society and organizing the events. It will require a "
"great effort to make this dream come true!\\\" {n}The aasimar bows.{/n} \\\"Thank "
"you for your time. Please, if you decide to support us, send us a message through "
"your curator. And whatever your decision, I hope your esteemed advisor will honor "
"us by taking part in the opening ceremony!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7f4ca28-b4d9-4918-b6f1-fae8e32a3cdb"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi's eyes shine with excitement.{/n} \\\"Well? What do you say? I say it's a "
"very worthy cause – and I wouldn't be stingy about it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5abe699d-ac58-4ed3-b5ce-909a2636357b"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller cocks his head.{/n} \\\"So? What shall I tell Lady Sharvan? To "
"my mind, these people need our guidance and attention more than they need our "
"money. We could inform all the city of this newly-founded society, and assist in "
"the collection of membership fees.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e551a49c-de6a-4b58-bced-9246f41940c6"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal thinks for a moment.{/n} \\\"Yes. Support them. Give them money. Make "
"them feel they owe you. Moving forward, the resulting mixture of obligation and "
"guilt will allow you to control everything that goes on in this 'society'."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2607b05c-23ca-4a1d-9afe-09853475df2f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful! I will immediately give orders to draw money from the treasury!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "433cd488-c0fa-4304-96fd-974d39806b49"
msgid ""
"\\\"A most reasonable proposal, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}\\\"."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee56904b-6858-481f-bc4a-8c8cdf8d76f3"
msgid ""
"\\\"A good step, {name}. I will write to the aasimar in the most refined and "
"sincere terms.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c41ea49-5fe5-49fa-893d-a828ebfd9bab"
msgid "\\\"Great! No one in such a situation would reject that kind of help!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65b47d06-83b4-4d9d-8fad-fda088fda343"
msgid "\\\"A most wise decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b8b9f8e-2f61-42bb-b76f-40bd970b931e"
msgid "\\\"Not a great deal of leverage, but better than nothing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70c6c989-7a02-4626-acd4-531cec0a7639"
msgid ""
"\\\"You have no idea how sad I am to hear this. You probably have your reasons, "
"but still... fine, let's just forget about it. I hope Rikri and her friends can "
"handle everything on their own.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6b31d3b-4d52-48af-b133-32358b7ab966"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am sorry to hear you would choose to neglect subjects in need of your help. "
"Still, I feel certain that Lady Sharvan will find a way to handle this project on "
"her own.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bd02943-bd0c-4b1e-9fd6-4331eb32be5c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Letting the matter run its course? I assure you, once their little society "
"grows, its members will not be drinking to your health.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c7603f4-c7ee-43f3-b643-48df02634dee"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I will go to the Treasurer immediately, and order the necessary sum be "
"sent immediately to Rikri and her associates!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1632587a-2729-4640-b159-aede2fe00bab"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well. Lady Sharvan will receive all the help she needs in founding and "
"running this society.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a7e69e80-8db6-4151-8a04-f5e5ee570c7b"
msgid "\\\"Very good. The Treasurer will have to dip into his coffers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c2fcb05-212d-4ba2-8460-2e467576ffdd"
msgid "\\\"Tell me more about each candidate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d83b11b5-3895-470f-922e-b9a15081e911"
msgid ""
"\\\"My soldiers risk their lives every day for these lands. Let them enjoy some "
"well-deserved glory. Let's order the series of etchings from the artist.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8a53926-24b5-412b-8d1f-65ba171794ff"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let our neighbors learn all about the talented people of our lands. We'll help "
"the musician.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "336d026d-ed8a-4fa5-8181-d785d56ea4cd"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is our duty to preserve the culture and traditions of the Stolen Lands. "
"We'll support the provincial teacher.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b17fd411-2127-4717-b9bf-642d78e47ba2"
msgid "\\\"Make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7e8c3b7-d6fc-4e98-b763-8a6802c773dd"
msgid ""
"\\\"In any case, you should find yourself another curator, {name}. It doesn't make "
"sense to me to continue as your advisor. Apparently, you already know how to spend "
"money, what to do in every situation, and how to solve every problem. You know "
"where to find me when you want to talk.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bc10a3ae-00ca-431a-a20b-b1508d029c3a"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I've been thinking "
"about this a lot lately, and I'd like to resign as your curator. You and I regard "
"life very differently. Our values seem to be in opposition. I hope you will "
"understand my decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e27ebff8-4a12-4a31-bf65-cd80a0406465"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know, {name}... I think it's time I resigned as your advisor. I'm sorry, "
"but what's going on here makes me feel really bad. I will gladly set out on "
"campaigns with you, and I'm not giving up on my book, but public service... Well, "
"it's just not for me. I'm sorry. I hope you understand.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70f843c8-738b-48e6-985b-617b7975bfb5"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, our Treasurer informs me that we've managed to save up some money "
"allocated for culture – a substantial amount, in fact! I talked to my friends in "
"the artistic communities, and I've found three projects worthy of support!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11ce1155-874f-49d5-bb26-15f3441f911e"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, my calculations show "
"that we haven't spent all the money we've allocated for cultural development. I "
"have three projects on one of which we could spend the surplus.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82293338-a5ad-43fe-8e7e-c39ec1035816"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Treasurer reports that we've allocated more money than we've actually "
"spent on culture. A considerable sum of money remains. Money must be put to work, "
"so I suggest you invest it in one of three projects.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "295542c2-1ebc-4e3f-bd39-5fda51d97e7d"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's an easy guess, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, "
"that I suggest you pay attention to the folk wisdom collector. I myself am working "
"on preserving tales from the ancient times. He's working hard on preserving modern-"
"day tales for our descendants. The one can't do without the other, and both "
"complement each other nicely!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ff7beef-dfb1-4c08-82a3-293b8a77855e"
msgid ""
"\\\"At first I thought of a local violin player I know. He's always dreamed of "
"traveling around the neighboring lands, playing his music. I also talked to a "
"provincial teacher who is assembling a book of local legends and traditions. And "
"finally, I kept receiving letters from an artist local to the capital – I have no "
"idea why. When we met, she offered me a series of etchings depicting your "
"'brilliant officers' and the 'great feats' of your army.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56e37bc7-0710-4f66-8eff-4b44c39e7fe4"
msgid ""
"\\\"The first is a famous local violin player, who wishes to tour our neighbors' "
"lands. The second is a book of local legends and traditions assembled by a "
"provincial teacher. But the most promising is a series of etchings depicting your "
"military campaigns. This artist's love of her motherland... it's most impressive!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "723a442e-b34f-49cf-bb18-946d809bfe0a"
msgid ""
"\\\"The violin player I told you about is an old friend. Even the most callous "
"listener is touched by his music! Besides, he has plenty of friends in the {g|"
"River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}. His concerts will be of the highest standards. "
"They will attract crowds of fans, and every one of them will be grateful to you "
"for giving them the gift of such lovely music.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70cd1dc1-28cb-47b5-b0ff-c3f2685a66c3"
msgid ""
"\\\"The violin player's endeavor is commendable. Besides, when people hear his "
"music and learn that you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, "
"are the one who made his concerts possible, then they will certainly grant you "
"their favor and respect.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c94fb643-fe3f-46de-9bb1-b8aae9be76af"
msgid ""
"\\\"A musician wishes to tour around the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}. "
"It's not our best option, but it could enhance your image among our more sensitive "
"citizens. The provincial teacher's proposal is the least promising. A book of "
"peasants' superstitions and stories will lead nowhere of interest.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bcef325c-b8a6-4b5a-9e72-875fcbae32a2"
msgid ""
"\\\"What?! Are you saying no to honest artists, and instead giving money to that "
"slippery, cunning weasel? What am I going to tell the others?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97326dee-99bd-4585-905e-cc641a72898d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Soldiers risk their lives every day. That's the reason that art should reflect "
"the true hardships and deprivations of military life. They deserve to know the "
"truth. Our young people might buy their ruler's promises of glory and wealth, but "
"they'll abandon their camps on the eve of battle.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aeb055ee-9556-42e6-a8ab-5f21a146eaff"
msgid "\\\"A fine choice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7515794-40dc-4269-a649-b24a4535b739"
msgid "\\\"Excellent! Let me tell him! He'll be so happy!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82e8b877-232e-4b25-be56-bea2038f5387"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll discuss with him the details of his tour, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "020a322a-03ed-4d30-beba-8117f7185c50"
msgid "\\\"Yes, well, that's a fine use of our money...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1e9fe07-ba56-4a6d-9128-8b2d79cf7791"
msgid "\\\"Hm... I'll hate to upset my friend... But I'm glad for the teacher!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3134a180-fe01-4265-8ec7-c10f2c3f4fdb"
msgid "\\\"Very wise, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3fa9f45c-e72b-4d33-a018-2caf5a0d32ec"
msgid "\\\"Wasted money. But I guess it's not up to me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7bc64f35-492e-4768-99bf-58d34ca09fe1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm sure we should support the musician. Your patronage of the arts will make "
"you famous across the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "508f00c6-b7a6-4360-966a-72fd67feedaf"
msgid ""
"\\\"First of all, we can send forth our outstanding violin player who wishes to "
"tour the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}. Second, there is the provincial "
"teacher collecting the legends, beliefs and traditions of your subjects. As a "
"third option, we can order a series of etchings depicting your army's feats and "
"campaigns.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a181cc16-9ce0-4a2a-bd15-9360aa02f88f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Considering our position, I believe that supporting the artist and her "
"workshop would be most useful. You might print many copies of these etchings, and "
"thus elevate the prestige of military service! Besides, she herself wishes to "
"paint your 'glorious army' and 'remarkable warriors' as faithfully as possible. "
"She said she would not fall victim to the provocations of whiners and cowards.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8837220f-2707-4ca3-8c96-80f31ca2e884"
msgid ""
"\\\"As to the series of etchings... I may be blind, but even I can see this "
"artist's true, self-serving motives. And I can't say I agree with her desire to "
"glorify the army and the officers' life. Art must reflect life, not distort the "
"truth.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ec890e3-7bec-4708-ba20-379983d04bab"
msgid ""
"\\\"The legend-gatherer's work seems the most useful, and not only for our "
"descendants. Your subjects, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}, will be proud for their culture. Thus they might dedicate more time and "
"money to its development...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b6f4964-9dcb-4e9e-a354-9182142fb848"
msgid ""
"\\\"The provincial teacher is very naive and sweet, but his innocence only deepens "
"his vision. You should hear him speak of the folk culture of the {g|Stolen Lands}"
"Stolen Lands{/g}! Your subjects will be very proud of their origin and culture "
"after they've read his book.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "adc49019-7d2c-479a-bece-4c1a07468092"
msgid ""
"\\\"The artist seemed an awful back-scratcher to me. I'm sure she only came up "
"with the military theme to get herself a big order. I hate flatterers and apple-"
"polishers. Especially when it comes to art!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8469c27-181b-4248-b1b1-2a50908fb377"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll tell the violin player that we'll help him! Oh, he'll be so happy!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1b09c45-f9a4-4ddc-b5fb-c1d694b5a3e9"
msgid "\\\"Then I'll inform the teacher he can count on our support.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb8007e6-995a-4fbf-97ef-c2187a15014c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll order the series of etchings... and see that it's done to our "
"specifications.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c37f1a20-ef86-4bb0-bfdf-9e077fcad06b"
msgid "\\\"We shall grant this young composer what he asks.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9919cda2-1044-41d9-9920-beb6213589cc"
msgid ""
"\\\"We mustn't interfere with the creative process. Not even if the composer begs "
"us to. Larzio won't live in my castle.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "410b69eb-9388-439a-831f-e27389156550"
msgid "\\\"Make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3b4a2077-3377-4691-85ce-9bd6cac3f694"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm fine with your plan, Jaethal. Assist the composer and see how he's "
"progressing!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bcecfd9d-bd09-48f9-bebf-8d053608e066"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's incredible, {name}! I wish you could see him! How his eyes burn! His soul "
"is so pure! And his mind is so elevated! We should – no, we must help him!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc995d2d-3c39-4ec1-a8dd-30089ec133d7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Something "
"curious happened yesterday. During my evening promenade, I met a young man. His "
"name is Larzio Messus – a young composer from {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g}. He told me "
"that he left his hometown in the search of inspiration. He's astonished by the "
"story of your ascension to the throne, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|"
"Your Highness}. – So impressed, in fact, that he's determined to compose an opera "
"about it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a8ef51ca-d688-43a7-a062-775d38854dc3"
msgid ""
"\\\"A passionate young composer arrived to the capital quite recently. He's "
"seeking my audience. I am told he's known in {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g} as a bringer "
"of hope. His first pieces were warmly greeted by the critics – especially the "
"dames. He's said to be quite handsome.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a26a264e-4e1b-4dd8-aa7c-b6de8af04bf3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Last night I met a wonderful, glorious young composer from {g|Absalom}Absalom{/"
"g}! His name is Larzio Messus, and he hasn't yet obtained the glory worthy of his "
"talent. I swear on {g|Shelyn}Shelyn's{/g} good graces, he will be famous! He left "
"his home in search of material, and as he traveled in our lands he was astonished "
"by the story of your success.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2dc630c5-9f23-4d14-9b68-a09e04c58c76"
msgid ""
"\\\"He's asked for permission to live and work in the palace, so he might draw "
"your character from real life. Nevertheless, I think we should say no. Art must be "
"free!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "591f09b3-e8ab-43f2-ae5a-0ae096c92eb0"
msgid ""
"\\\"His name is Larzio Messus, and he needs your protection. He's been looking for "
"fresh material, and he came across the story of your ascension to the throne. He's "
"so impressed that he's dreaming of composing an opera about it. He's young, "
"inexperienced and naive, which makes him even more useful. We should settle him in "
"the palace and give him patronage. I'll answer to all his questions. It won't be "
"difficult to arrange his thoughts in the right order.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f080dcbf-5672-4172-b3f6-e04e955739dc"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi smiles and claps her hands.{/n} \\\"I promise, {name}, you won't be sorry "
"for your generosity!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55a5301d-70c1-44ca-83ed-f01e67e780ea"
msgid ""
"\\\"I can't approve of such a decision, but the word of {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness} is the law.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0fe68296-552f-4661-8748-bc902a752357"
msgid "{n}The elf nods with a hint of a smile on her face.{/n} \\\"Wonderful.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6be12770-81db-4746-a2c0-2913b32418eb"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi's face turns red. She watches you reproachfully.{/n} \\\"I knew it! Why "
"are you so stubborn...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90d95c48-c2f2-42f4-9d59-697a2bfe8d1f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for your trust, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. In due time, we'll see the positive effects that freedom may have on "
"the artist and on his creations.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc5f9376-9fd3-4a8f-8818-e7beaebe62aa"
msgid "{n}Jaethal shrugs indifferently.{/n} \\\"Another lost opportunity...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0c7d303-93a4-4ae5-bc87-f756ec75f293"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's no two ways about it! Larzio is going to live with us! Oh my, it's "
"going to make him so happy!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "289f1ab7-6c76-4e8f-a70d-b1fa2778c475"
msgid ""
"\\\"He says he's been dreaming of writing an opera about your adventures! He only "
"wants to live in your palace and compose music, so he can be as close as possible "
"to you and to everyone in your party! I'm sure it's destiny that brought him to "
"our gates. – And destiny will never forgive us if we fail to support this young "
"genius!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85160274-9a62-4bc8-9abd-693b42c6da77"
msgid ""
"\\\"Living here will make him feel obligated to us. Seeing you every day, he'll "
"lose the dispassionate distance that every artist needs to see his subject "
"clearly! He will hardly understand the virtue of your decision now, but this "
"freedom will do him much good. A flower grown in a greenhouse will wither and "
"perish at the first sign of cold! A weed on the roadside will stand firm through "
"drought and the storm, whatever trial it faces.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c407182f-32f5-4046-8fb2-a74586e2b223"
msgid ""
"\\\"His opera will not only preserve your name through the centuries, but also "
"send a message to the peasants of today. They will learn how grateful they must be "
"for your constant efforts, and will have no other thought but to serve their "
"powerful and enlightened ruler. As for me, I won't mind spending time in the young "
"man's company. You know I love to admire all manner of fancy trinkets: flowers, "
"gems, naive and sublime young men...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e80431b9-b197-4c04-ba67-f05902fe9454"
msgid ""
"\\\"We can't allow unknown agitators undermine the people's respect for authority. "
"I demand this newspaper be shut down, and all political media banned!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "599cd1ea-88f8-492d-b5eb-f9edb4eebfe7"
msgid ""
"\\\"The River Freedoms guarantee their freedom of speech. We will not interfere.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3dd3d3d0-027e-4b48-bff8-f1018861002a"
msgid "\\\"You're my advisor. It's up to you to decide how to act.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71fdf21f-7fb7-4a28-80bf-fa6266e5c1f9"
msgid ""
"[Pay 2 BP each week] \\\"We'll meet all their accusations by issuing our own "
"newspaper. It's a good thing we already have a printing press.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65f9536f-0319-4c48-bfbb-fe5ec07df7f4"
msgid "Ordered the execution of the newspaper publishers."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "861661c0-e60e-4eec-9c8f-fefe71c0f36d"
msgid "\\\"What is there to explain? Execute the slanderers! Now!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1640f2a2-7686-4c28-9c43-8979b8ba31b1"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi's cheeks are burning, and she's raised her voice to nearly yelling.{/n} \\"
"\"They've gone too far! Just listen! 'Two-handed swords of gold and dragon-skin "
"robes – is this where our taxes go?' What blatant lies! Plus, they're talking "
"about money that isn't even theirs!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1c06561-e69c-4153-b0d1-8e717ba58db8"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I was informed that "
"various political newspapers and leaflets have become very popular amongst your "
"subjects. Many criticize the authorities, and some publish gossip and rumors that "
"might be unpleasant to you personally. However, the very appearance of these "
"things, and their popularity among the people, are signs of the great success "
"we've managed to achieve in education!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4386bd08-eedc-4722-acbe-4687b845b5ae"
msgid ""
"\\\"Another day, another problem. Political newspapers and leaflets are becoming "
"very popular among your subjects. They're nothing more than nasty rumors and "
"criticism of the authorities.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37d5f9b1-cead-449e-a75b-4fe480c4fc52"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi calms herself and addresses you more formally.{/n} \\\"Phew. Hello, "
"{name}. I was out shopping for feathers and ink, and I saw a boy distributing "
"newspapers in the market. I read a headline and almost burst with outrage! I even "
"thought of buying one to show you, but I wouldn't want to spend a single coin on "
"the cheeky scriveners!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5ef689d-a62d-40ef-9426-c5ef3641809e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't think we should act. If we try to stop the spread of such newspapers, "
"we'll only be adding fuel to the fire. Leave everything as it is: we'll let them "
"have their discussion, and allow their readers to make up their own minds. My "
"experience shows that only a free society is capable of criticizing and "
"eliminating absurd ideas – more effectively than a thousand censors ever could.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0c79ebe-63da-42e3-98f8-bc29fb05c94c"
msgid ""
"{n}The elf is as calm as an iceberg.{/n} \\\"Your reaction must be swift and "
"severe. As your curator, I advise that you shut down these newspapers, confiscate "
"their printing presses, and arrest everyone involved.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0acc444c-fc2e-4ff5-9ad4-037eece51455"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi opens her eyes widely, and then scrunches them up.{/n} \\\"So that's how "
"it is.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77c3eccc-845b-4e06-8ed9-439596acd89f"
msgid ""
"{n}Storyteller's voice is distant and cold.{/n} \\\"This move may bring a moment's "
"satisfaction, but it may cost you the whole game tomorrow.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b4e145e-11b7-475c-b2eb-946f1bbfb78f"
msgid ""
"\\\"You might be right. After all, no one can make me read those filthy stories!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3c02022e-4583-4695-8a7a-d7edeae1a4ad"
msgid "\\\"The words of a wise and confident ruler.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39cf98fd-990c-404f-9171-918c54a3ddef"
msgid "\\\"A very reckless decision. Very well, as you please.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56a0562f-e2cc-45c7-82c1-f3cf41005d0b"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll... we'll let them publish their idle gossip! We're beyond reacting to it!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "566aeea2-742a-45be-9d9f-661b8cda8100"
msgid "\\\"In this case, we won't respond.\\\" {n}The blind man smiles gently.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98f905a6-aa43-41c8-b242-dce9cf05102f"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll inform your Warden and bring a squad of guards. All individuals "
"responsible will suffer the consequences.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dbbf97f3-2135-42a9-9a51-90c6bcd60a92"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi stands for a while, tapping on her chin. She then continues:{/n} \\\"We "
"shouldn't follow the example of the monarch who would close the newspaper, fire "
"the editorial staff, and burn all the issues... That's exactly the sort of "
"response that would prove to your subjects that all the gossip in those papers is "
"true!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f479a497-4417-41f2-a6a8-25d5f0d100a7"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi slaps herself on the forehead.{/n} \\\"Of course, how could I forget! "
"That's the perfect solution, {name}! We'll fight their nasty and distasteful "
"stories with our own truth and beauty! I even know a decent editor...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76a2751b-faee-4c87-bc44-83378e1fecef"
msgid ""
"\\\"What would we call it? \\\"The Royal Times\\\"? \\\"The Loyal Herald\\\"? This "
"will lead nowhere good...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04f30e6c-9d77-4735-9752-1eb2a0f7120b"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's not the simplest solution, but it might work. I'll find an editor and "
"start printing our responses. Our circulation will be twice as high as the "
"opposition's.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "03f2f431-b62d-489f-884e-d10c4ab44e4a"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi covers her mouth with her palm and gasps.{/n} \\\"How... how could you be "
"so cruel?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39fa229a-979c-45c3-974a-b09cac7e97ed"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller sighs.{/n} \\\"A sad fate awaits those who solve problems with "
"violence. A sad fate for their subjects as well...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a96bd57-7de3-466c-8176-6c838df61f0a"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal raises an eyebrow, but immediately nods.{/n} \\\"It will be done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c62af5e-0207-443c-ab76-ca1776f312fd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Art demands sacrifice. By my decree, Larzio Messus shall receive a monthly "
"stipend.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d01ad077-fd2c-4ba0-9e4f-c7aa400631ad"
msgid "\\\"We shall not sponsor Larzio.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13a6fdf1-e924-4b92-bebb-efce5b73e66c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well, Jaethal. The Treasurer shall provide you with whatever you require."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e7db199-e111-434c-a04d-57d6bcf26543"
msgid "\\\"You are my Curator. This choice is up to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3913deea-0fa7-4218-b94e-ce317a05fc78"
msgid "\\\"Larzio should write of commitment to duty. Of loyalty and honor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd28d386-7168-4a4d-b787-8f9d59608615"
msgid ""
"\\\"His opera should show that each of us is the architect of our own fate. Hard "
"work and perseverance lead to success and prosperity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e23c35a-618e-4489-8e9e-65cc2a824508"
msgid "\\\"His work should tackle the all-important question of faith and piety.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44e1ad84-1a98-4372-82b8-66dd65789deb"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, once again I've come to speak about Larzio. He's still writing his "
"opera, and now he's asking us for financial support. Progress goes slower than he "
"hoped, and his funds are running low. But he's shown me some of his manuscripts, "
"and the work is definitely very exciting!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "735e54d3-61e3-4f09-9ae9-f11868e7b6eb"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've been approached once more by the young maestro Messus, Your Highness. "
"Despite certain difficulties, he's still hard at work on his opera about your "
"adventures in the Stolen lands. This time he's asked us for financial support. It "
"seems the scant funds he brought from Absalom are running dry. If we don't help "
"him, he'll have to start taking commissions again.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b98cdc15-74ce-41cb-b537-84405dbe05b2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Larzio Messus, the young composer from Absalom, has sought my audience once "
"again. Just as I expected, he's still working on that opera – the tale of your "
"ascension to the throne. He hasn't a single coin to his name, for he has declined "
"all other commissions, to devote himself entirely to his magnum opus.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13be3879-448c-4e45-8ecb-a25135812b58"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think we should help him out. He's spent everything he had, and I know he's "
"done his best to support the endeavor on his own. He's still wearing that same "
"holey old shirt he wore on his journey from Absalom, and he's had nothing but "
"bread and water for weeks. Trust me, supporting him means supporting true art at "
"its finest, and you stand to gain a hundred times more than you will lose!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd2f7635-2f0b-4ce7-a58b-feab80300288"
msgid ""
"\\\"My advice stands — we mustn't interfere with the creative process. A good "
"artist must be able to work on multiple pieces at the same time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "249f4e46-d62b-4563-a358-3ccbf951346e"
msgid ""
"\\\"This gives us the perfect opportunity to gain a decisive influence over him. "
"We should help Larzio — and once he's taken the bait, explain to him that honor "
"demands he listen to his patron's opinion, and make certain… refinements to the "
"opera. The grateful, naive child will be unable to refuse.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d89c4e68-db85-46b7-a4f5-4ce538c76d61"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, right, and one more thing… He wanted me to ask you: what should he pay the "
"most attention to as he writes? What message should he convey to the listener?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a7ecac0-53dc-4b98-abf8-93e72cbd7444"
msgid ""
"\\\"Dreadful. Just… dreadful. Why's it always me who has to deliver the bad news?\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa2da18d-00fa-4477-a1b8-f2ba5dcb07ef"
msgid ""
"\\\"How unfortunate.\\\" {n}After a short silence, the old man continues in a "
"melancholic tone:{/n} \\\"Well, since this can no longer be considered independent "
"art, I shall pass on another of the young maestro's requests: he wishes to know "
"what themes you would like to see addressed. Do you have a specific lesson you'd "
"like to share with the audience?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8890ff77-6cb4-4d84-a203-ac5ae5c4d8ea"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you wish. Do not be surprised, however, when this opera casts you in a much "
"different light than you'd prefer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0be7aa8e-441f-4c31-9541-27f83650fa2f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tell me, {name}, what should I turn our young friend's attention to? What "
"should he always keep in mind while he is writing?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a146bf66-4ba3-47fb-8cb6-6afea3b644b9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, {name}, thank you so much! I shall go at once to tell Larzio that "
"all his troubles are behind him!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4bb18731-2b8b-44a5-8872-155020e0443e"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller nods.{/n} \\\"I shall inform the young man that he'll have to "
"rely on himself to overcome these obstacles.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f587a03-c2a1-40ab-bfd7-e4f25ba1f266"
msgid ""
"\\\"Larzio shall have everything his heart desires… and only later will he have to "
"pay for it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5949202-9318-4874-99b9-3440112d3917"
msgid "\\\"It shall be as you say, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35a14444-dedf-4de7-b298-6b668cd15515"
msgid ""
"\\\"I bring amusing news of Larzio Messus, the young composer from Absalom that "
"I've been watching over. He met me yesterday, and by turns he informed me that "
"he's up to his neck in debt. His friends lead a most lavish lifestyle, and at "
"first he was simply too sapless to let himself fall back — and now he simply "
"cannot imagine living any differently. Of course, it was none other than I who "
"introduced him to these rakes...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6747ac4c-fbb5-4e7e-8040-c1df0e46cc84"
msgid ""
"[Pay 200 BP] \\\"We cannot stop progress, so we must champion it. I order the "
"treasury to release the necessary funds for the foundation of the Crown's "
"University.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2dae9514-6a33-4ddd-bcd6-9e8daf94a187"
msgid "\\\"The kingdom cannot afford it. We won't be opening a university.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52c4bf93-d3c5-4aa0-b12f-ae0974070d85"
msgid ""
"[Pay 2 BP each week] \\\"I order the Treasurer to provide everything necessary for "
"the development of a school of enlightenment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79fa872c-69f2-4a41-b18a-2c55c6da5c0b"
msgid ""
"\\\"We cannot allow troublemakers to disrupt the peace. The school will be closed "
"on my authority.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8549d44-3196-4dda-ac67-5e677ff9be63"
msgid "Ordered the school closed, and its organizers executed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34004a81-5fe2-4e8f-ac23-126f610e4e00"
msgid "\\\"Shut down the school immediately. – And execute the organizers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7cc8ea22-8be6-4287-93c0-87621fc757ce"
msgid "\\\"I will heed your advice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c83ce6c2-f51a-4c21-a46c-1570079f6eba"
msgid "\\\"Make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89b550fa-918a-4270-b5af-2a9e9a28d4e1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't know if you've noticed, {name}, but the kingdom's people have become "
"much more educated. The schools we helped found are now full of children, and "
"there are plenty of young people that thirst for knowledge and wish to dedicate "
"themselves to science. So, here's what I thought: why not found a university?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df921ff8-1666-40d1-826e-60ca1de5b2e6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, Your Highness. I wanted to inform you that our efforts to open "
"schools have paid off immensely. The literacy level of your people is growing "
"throughout the kingdom, and there's hardly any family whose children aren't "
"learning to read, write and count. Thus I wanted to propose a next step – to open "
"a university in the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21952e74-625b-4059-a845-51eae062d38c"
msgid ""
"\\\"The ill-advised whim to open schools for the riff-raff has finally borne its "
"fruit. Yesterday we received a petition: the teachers of the capital ask that we "
"found a university.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f79a8fc-2c27-4cbd-9312-66a308ef84a1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just imagine, learned men and women from all around the world shall flock to "
"our {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}! And they'll bring books! And magic "
"scrolls, and recipes for new potions… And maybe someday they'll open a school of "
"philosophy, or maybe we'll have great alchemists! — And your neighbors would be "
"green with envy...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc71604d-4f60-49e2-9c2c-238aab49381c"
msgid ""
"\\\"The influx of learned men and women from all around Avistan will surely be a "
"boon for trade. Our scientists will require books, magic scrolls, alchemical "
"reagents and potions. Our kingdom's prestige will rise in the eyes of our "
"neighbors. I believe this endeavor will bring nothing but good fortune to our "
"lands. Although many rulers fear the free thinking that breeds in universities, it "
"is well to remember that free thought is only ever a threat to tyrants.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a7e93f71-6174-401b-a646-875bcc8e129f"
msgid ""
"\\\"As if the extraordinary cost weren't enough, this endeavor would work directly "
"against our own interests. Universities are a hotbed of dangerous free thought, "
"and naturally breed mistrust of any powers that be. From there, this plague "
"spreads to all of society. No economic or diplomatic benefits could ever justify "
"this. Clearly, we must refuse this petition.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a98b4ae-cd6e-45cf-b4cb-076ae7a19533"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well said! I will get to work immediately. Ha! If only the crosspatches that "
"threw me out of the Academy could see me now!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1030c774-3ebb-4fc5-bc9a-8790c81dadf8"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is an investment in spirit itself. It will pay off much sooner than you "
"think, and will continue to bear fruit long after we've all returned to dust.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e1def63-f575-405a-80c7-0f8d0ec2078f"
msgid ""
"{n}The Inquisitor raises an eyebrow.{/n} \\\"Do you actually imagine that you are "
"doing the kingdom a favor? You are simply pushing it closer to anarchy and "
"lawlessness. Consider Galt, and you will see what I mean.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54c187bf-c110-40a3-96d3-f7c99c08d40b"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller's face is serene, but a note of sadness can be heard in his "
"voice.{/n} \\\"Unwise.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54a59c42-336d-441d-86f7-6fa2c1d44b67"
msgid "\\\"You've made the right choice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54762606-6f47-45e2-8895-7bd5a90231a4"
msgid ""
"\\\"What a shame! Oh, what a shame… We're missing out on a truly wonderful "
"opportunity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92aedbcd-78ad-4283-a975-af5c4c185395"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, {name}! We should have founded schools while we could! Now, others are "
"doing it for us. Followers of Irori have opened one of their schools of "
"enlightenment in the capital, and they're holding open debates. Today's topic of "
"discussion — the successfulness of the {mf|King|Queen} and {mf|his|her} government!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "651dbfab-5be0-487e-99a3-da7202024e29"
msgid ""
"\\\"An opportunity that passed us by has been taken up by another. The followers "
"of Irori have opened the first school in the capital — a school of enlightenment. "
"They are now holding open debates. Participants are discussing whether or not the "
"rulers of this land are a success.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c904e4be-ca25-4c1b-b10e-88cccebef128"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not long ago, we maintained peace in the kingdom by keeping the peasants "
"ignorant and content. Now a school has been founded in the capital, a school of "
"enlightenment. It was founded by the followers of Irori, and even now, open "
"debates on the failure of your government are being held there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c905935-4a81-48ac-a539-9385f80f9b2f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Every day, disloyal citizens corrupt your nation like a rotting limb. We must "
"strike now, and without remorse. The participants in these debates must be "
"dispersed. And as for their initiators… The organizers of the debates should pay "
"with their lives. Let it be known across the kingdom that those who challenge the "
"throne do not have long to live.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d1e31997-81f9-44ff-aeba-8273c6df0b3a"
msgid ""
"\\\"In my opinion, we should neither shut down the school nor sponsor it, as the "
"townsfolk might simply consider sponsorship another form of bribery – and would "
"they be so wrong? Instead, with your permission, I would like to take part in the "
"debates. Not as a contender, but rather perhaps as an observer and commentator. "
"Our subjects will get an opportunity to voice their worries and fears, while we "
"will be able to explain our positions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bae017ab-9419-4da7-84c6-e0f3025335db"
msgid ""
"\\\"Doubtless, a more pleasant topic could have been chosen... But we mustn't "
"respond with arrests and repression of free speech! Let the people speak their "
"minds. It could even be in our best interests to support these debates, and the "
"school itself. It would certainly help our reputation!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6b0acf5-6c47-47a9-b8f6-69eaffb147b0"
msgid "\\\"That's right! We have nothing to fear.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ffe2f4b-04ae-4638-a534-0187a0281314"
msgid ""
"{n} The Storyteller smiles at you.{/n} \\\"Long ago, I spoke with much passion "
"about politics and matters of rule. Many of the youth thought quite highly of my "
"speeches — perhaps, too highly… Let us see if there's anything left of that "
"youthful zeal in me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4ffecfd-cd62-4aa2-bbbb-37912b2e29eb"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal shakes her head.{/n} \\\"First they think, then they talk, and then "
"they begin to act. Foolish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d8bf11f-4ddf-4ef3-8da6-5d1ef2502262"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi's shoulders sink. She speaks quietly, without addressing anyone in "
"particular:{/n} \\\"Sometimes I feel like I never left Pitax…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cffebb6-1e69-47a9-b906-9223f4093e70"
msgid "\\\"I see… Such is your right, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32543a99-1c4d-4826-ad1b-31d08fbebc09"
msgid "\\\"It won't be enough. Still, it's better than nothing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62d65f04-b137-469f-a4e4-35c7a341ae97"
msgid "{n}Linzi turns pale as a sheet.{/n}\\\"Such… cruelty. Why…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55eadf1f-9e59-4ad7-ad54-ead4ea9fd460"
msgid ""
"{n} At length, the Storyteller falls silent, and his hands hang loose at his side. "
"The elderly figure looks particularly fragile in the failing light of the throne "
"room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ff9fa9f-1946-41bb-b33c-c40e3c2fd0b5"
msgid "\\\"Excellent. They shall be dealt with.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c956defb-8899-469f-aa92-29f6ba459594"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll support the school. Let's show our critics how generous and open-minded "
"we are!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23967804-53b3-4f76-905c-3aae5473c74c"
msgid ""
"[Pay 200 BP] \\\"There's no time to waste, Jaethal. Give Larzio a sense of just "
"how much he owes us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2745c65-695f-4f49-8c8c-f96b3b1b0a03"
msgid ""
"[Pay 100 BP] \\\"Larzio may build his stage upon the main square. And his "
"production shall be funded as well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a34cb810-31d0-4f20-b550-9e88a93455c2"
msgid ""
"[Pay 50 BP] \\\"The composer is free to use the main square as he pleases. Nothing "
"more, nothing less.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c11b2c74-670e-4a96-afa5-6536b7957ee4"
msgid "\\\"Larzio will have to find his own stage. We shall not help him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e41a33cf-025b-4290-9008-651312852e34"
msgid "\\\"Make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa6795e4-7aea-4339-9f60-11d277eb1669"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I bring wonderful news: Larzio Messus has finally finished his opera! "
"All that's left is to direct and stage it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "419b7f88-6838-4f21-b3f1-4a8ea45127e9"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could help him find a venue — for example, we could let him use the main "
"square! That alone would already solve a lot of his problems. But it would be even "
"better if we funded the production! He's already found all the singers and has an "
"orchestra ready to perform, but he cannot afford any spectacle. — The colors, the "
"costumes, the decorations...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ea3261e-b1bf-4215-99fe-3cc087564f30"
msgid ""
"\\\"I bring news from Larzio Messus, Your Highness. Despite all his difficulties, "
"he was able to finish his opera. He has already found singers and an orchestra — "
"all he lacks now is a stage. I am, however, sad to inform you that he's also been "
"taken ill. He's suffering from consumption, and this may well be his final "
"request...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc925132-828e-4a88-8b8b-78c729d2210b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I believe we should help him this time. — Not in everything, of course. By if "
"we allow him to set up his stage on the main square, we would allow his opera to "
"gather the audience it deserves, without influencing its substance in any way. "
"However, I would advise against funding the production, Your Highness. Theatrics "
"only distract the viewer from the true meaning of what is happening on the stage.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8d07208-6ebc-476e-8c8a-6e00a7a58b69"
msgid ""
"\\\"Astounding. Despite everything he's endured, Larzio Messus has finished his "
"opera! He's even found the singers and an orchestra, but is now confined to his "
"bed, suffering from consumption. He has asked that you find him a stage. His "
"condition grows worse by the day. — It may well be that this is his last "
"request... and our last opportunity to influence the result of his work.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35276508-d18b-46af-949a-c814477a275c"
msgid ""
"\\\"We should allow him use of the main square, and even take it upon ourselves to "
"build a stage for his premiere. Moreover, we might fund the production and ensure "
"his troupe receives all the best decorations and costumes. The more he owes us, "
"the easier it will be to convince him to censor any part we find disagreeable – "
"and add as much fanfare and eulogies as we like.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0bff27f7-e91f-464c-beb2-58fc364ced90"
msgid "{n}Jaethal takes a graceful bow.{/n} \\\"It shall be done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a01936c-c5e3-4f8b-820a-1bbd4d586a11"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, how wonderful! You'll see – this will be nothing short of magical!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7bcd9d7b-87d3-4b9b-be00-e7fbf40df37e"
msgid "\\\"It is not the decision I would make… but it is not up to me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64da8615-70b2-4bf0-856b-92d3526e5acf"
msgid "\\\"Thank you, {name} — Larzio will be very grateful!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b70e00bc-f025-4ca4-abc8-bdb8fd7ed65c"
msgid "{n}The Storyteller bows.{/n} \\\"I shall make the arrangements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71cb5600-c20b-4907-aa8e-344f4f088650"
msgid "\\\"I see. Well, that should be just enough.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c359289-463b-4629-a1da-a67ada2dda44"
msgid ""
"\\\"You might not believe this, {name}… but Larzio Messus, the composer, has "
"approached me once again! The poor fellow has finally finished his opera, and now "
"he's been taken ill by consumption. He needs to find a stage to present his work "
"to the public, but he's been bedridden for a week now. This may well be his final "
"request...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "36832d87-a556-4f46-afb6-a1d86cccbcb7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Good news, Your Highness! — The composer Larzio Messus has finished work on "
"his opera. Now all he lacks is a venue suitable for a premiere of such consequence."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e648fe11-bfbb-4874-a975-36c65b5a4db5"
msgid ""
"\\\"My young and precious friend, Larzio Messus, has finally finished his opera. "
"He spends all his days dreaming of the premiere, but he still lacks a few key "
"resources: a worthy stage and the funding necessary for a magnificent, colorful "
"production.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5550474e-0d58-46b7-b52d-9668db10030c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I can't say that I understand you thinking… but you're the {mf|King|Queen} — "
"you make the rules.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc09ded9-d050-4861-8ff4-49cec1d265b0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I understand your thinking, though I would have made a different decision. It "
"will be done, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee493c5d-e961-436f-b204-57ba2cb4bf4a"
msgid "\\\"A shame. One should never miss an opportunity like this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a42df88-e906-4082-863d-206f8db85c07"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll tell Larzio he can use the main square! And that we'll fund the whole "
"spectacle as well! Oh, this is so exciting!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e12be97-800f-48c3-951c-bc4f22451862"
msgid ""
"\\\"I shall make the arrangements for building a stage in the main square.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0e8edd0-fab3-4ce5-95df-d4654de250e0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agree. Lamashtu shall take her place among the kingdom's patron gods.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08b0ce28-b1cf-4f19-be55-f04a25db1df6"
msgid "\\\"It's not the right time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b040d2e0-43e6-4b2b-8552-48852ae935a3"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd like to congratulate you, Your Highness. These lands were once a gloomy, "
"godforsaken place. Its people were shackled by ignorance. But now the sky shines "
"with the light of the gods! Now the temples are full of followers, and godly "
"blessings protect the kingdom against calamity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e6cc5db-38be-457b-9332-bba43b790138"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, what have you done, {name}...\\\" These lands were dying until you came. "
"This was a dark, godless place. It's your fault that my god has turned away from "
"this kingdom! It's your fault that it blossoms again! The people rejoice! They've "
"forgotten what is coming for them! This makes me very sad. They were nearly "
"prepared for the truth. Now they hide once more behind their delusive happiness.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cafb519d-97e9-44f2-8aa8-a8a30d1195e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"You've surprised me, {name}. I always thought that not a single god, not even "
"{g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g}, ever cared about what was happening here, or who might "
"rule the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. This place was quiet and mournful. But "
"you filled the temples with followers, and the gods have turned their eyes upon "
"you. I imagine they have big plans for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "917050df-2f99-4682-96f1-b5a367cf974f"
msgid ""
"\\\"You relentlessly pursued the small cults of dark and vile gods, and cleared "
"the lands of blight and abomination. The priests appreciate your effort. A sacred "
"guard gathers – priests of the gods we honor here, to protect law and order in "
"these lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0325437-46a8-410a-a075-c04e8e5b857e"
msgid ""
"\\\"You have resolutely cleared these lands of minor cults, but the {g|Stolen "
"Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} has served as a graveyard for the obsolete for too long. "
"The old religions clung to life and didn't want to fade away. You gave them peace. "
"Your subjects wish to continue what you've started. The priests of all the "
"kingdom's recognized gods gather in a sacred guard, to protect your domain against "
"crime and intrigue.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14323037-f044-4f34-be27-9b2a7d824384"
msgid ""
"\\\"I approve of how you've treated the small cults that settled here. It was time "
"for them to go, and now this place is cleared. The priests of your kingdom's "
"faithful gods have no intention of retreat. They are setting up a sacred guard, to "
"deal with any crimes against the gods and their followers. My pack is safe, in any "
"case. A couple of my brothers occupy high positions in the guard. But the other "
"cults will have to make themselves small, or be taken over by {g|Lamashtu}"
"Lamashtu{/g} in order to survive.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1eef8ddf-ac31-4bc0-9a6f-43b8925d797b"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Cayden Cailean}Cayden{/g} had a wonderful influence on your kingdom. One "
"fair goes on after another, and people treat each other with kindness and light in "
"their hearts. They laugh more, and bear their misfortunes bravely. Bards love our "
"lands. Once they arrive, many decide to stay. We have a good reputation, and you "
"are known as a dear and understanding leader.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38476705-f886-443f-9b7b-364a0913cd15"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Gorum}Gorum's{/g} priests are generous with their blessings for our "
"warriors. Our fighters are strong, daring in battle, and confident in victory! "
"Many of the kingdom's children dream of becoming your knights when they grow up. "
"You are considered the ultimate power in the realm – a true leader!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a96982e1-cafb-4e55-81a1-9b3e2743d8e4"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g}' followers have brought order to your domain. Laws "
"are executed consistently, and punishments are now accepted as part of the normal "
"course of life. {g|Cheliax}Cheliax{/g} sends its messengers to sign lucrative "
"contracts with us. Alas, our immediate neighbors are worried and enraged. And yet "
"the comprehensible of Asmodeus is far better than the incomprehensible chaos that "
"plagues other lands. The {g|Hellknights}Hellknights{/g} arriving to our domain "
"intend to bring order to the neighboring lands – with fire and sword. Meanwhile "
"you maintain the image of a just and fair {mf|king|queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2e7afc4-2ac8-4465-8ff9-edda63d24cab"
msgid ""
"\\\"Where {g|Groetus}Groetus{/g} might grant your subjects understanding, {g|"
"Cayden Cailean}Cayden{/g} gives them solace and oblivion in a jar of wine. They "
"drink and rave, just to escape their fate and the burdens of their lives. They go "
"to fairs, give birth to children, and enjoy the simple things in life, certain "
"that it shall forever be, just like this. They open their thoughts to adventure, "
"as if they were immortal, and call you their beloved {mf|King|Queen}, in the merry "
"land with no woe.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9237ad55-5c88-49a8-8768-7f1b7b3a6ed2"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Gorum}Gorum{/g} ensures that your warriors are ruthless and devastating. "
"They are lost to {g|Groetus}Groetus{/g}, for they do not stop to consider death – "
"it's as if the end doesn't exist! The game of war is as child's play, with many "
"children looking to join your army, to kill and maim at your command. People say "
"you've taken your throne by right. After all, everyone who has challenged your "
"right is dead!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a928ff5f-52f8-47e5-ae1e-86f3c4f5ceab"
msgid ""
"\\\"Faith in {g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g} has led many to accept law as the only way "
"of life. People obediently bow their heads, so obedient they've trained themselves "
"to be, as if obedience and diligence could protect against the inevitable end. "
"Your neighbors were outraged by the new church nearby, and seriously considered "
"warring with you. But ambassadors from {g|Cheliax}Cheliax{/g} have expressed their "
"appreciation for our loyalty to their patron. The {g|Hellknights}Hellknights{/g}, "
"who arrive on our lands this very moment, regard our territory as the key to "
"restoring order in the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}. It was a dangerous "
"bargain, but it promises a substantial reward.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6737f9ed-979b-4822-a952-8e23fe7aab13"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Cayden Cailean}Cayden's{/g} bliss pleases your pack. It sates and cheers "
"them. They celebrate, sing songs and frolic at their fairs. And, of course, they "
"multiply. {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} likes this – except for their free thinking. "
"Their tongues are loosened by their cups, and they grow too daring. They cannot be "
"easy to rule – I don't understand how you make them obey your commands, and even "
"honor you with songs of praise, their merry and generous {mf|King|Queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25d1cfa1-0ca0-40cf-b45e-61473acc5e97"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your armies are blessed by {g|Gorum}Gorum{/g}. Our warriors are cold-blooded, "
"mighty, and fearless. Children dream of shedding blood on your orders, when they "
"grow up – for the glory of Gorum. This could come in handy sooner than you think. "
"As the rumor spreads that you're the strongest {mf|king|queen} in the world, many "
"will come to challenge you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a8b339d-cfc2-4db2-80c3-ddca6a03ff87"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g}' servants have taught your pack to obey the leader "
"and submit to your will. Your neighbors are furious with you, while {g|Cheliax}"
"Cheliax{/g} has sent its ambassadors to your capital. You've strengthened your "
"position, taking the advantage of your alliance with the church of Asmodeus. This "
"was clever – a bold decision with a great reward!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1424cf52-dde2-450c-b5c4-50cca0b7f5d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thanks to your tolerance of the small cults, rumors are spreading that every "
"minor religion will be welcomed in your kingdom. And so every odd rag-tailed "
"priest and congregant of the minor deities is flocking to your kingdom in search "
"of shelter. Many of them are good but misled people. There's a bad element as "
"well, but we're watching them day and night. The wide variety of worship may "
"confuse some decent folks, but most of them are committed to the true faith.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f55f78a7-dbc0-431e-8cba-a88d6292749e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I accept that you avoid imposing your faith on others, allow the worshipping "
"of idols, and give shelter to the weak. But look where this has led you! Dozens of "
"smaller cults, more worthy of oblivion, are flooding your lands, seeking "
"protection! They survive in your kingdom rather than face the inevitable. Their "
"teachings and obsolete magical knowledge, so welcomed by your wizards, were meant "
"to be forgotten!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d85fda58-e9db-4d27-9b2d-1d25c0ac64a4"
msgid ""
"\\\"You were right not to stamp out the smaller cults hiding here. Whispers spread "
"that minor religions are safe in your domain, and cults scurry to hide themselves "
"{mf|behind your shield|under your skirts}. Some possess curious knowledge of "
"ancient magics. All their priests are willing to share it with you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59542fc2-0f67-4e83-b28a-165c81d6164b"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod clears his throat and continues muttering in a friendly manner.{/n} \\"
"\"The outsiders are a source of much good as well, of course. They bring pieces of "
"valuable magical knowledge, and they're sought after by researchers and wizards, "
"who seek rare and forsaken magics.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d9262be2-75cf-48b0-ab9d-3b89bca98b37"
msgid ""
"\\\"And one more thing. {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} gave me a sign. She approves of "
"the way you lead your kingdom and your pack. Now that we've found common ground... "
"and got along so well... why don't you praise my goddess as well? You could "
"introduce her cult to the world, and claim boldly that we in the kingdom of "
"{kingdomname} worship none other than Lamashtu! Our neighbors will surely turn "
"against us, but my pack has grown strong under your care. We are capable of "
"protecting the country.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c5b66161-d45b-4719-952f-977597ec944c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I understand... We must hide to protect our faith. But the day will come...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ecde4af-5311-4a99-b07a-176ddadfae26"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna's rat starts squeaking triumphantly, and Tsanna bursts out laughing.{/n} "
"\\\"Thank {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g}! I've been waiting for so long! Let everybody "
"know that we renounce this disgraceful silence! We will openly pray to the Mother "
"of Monsters – we will praise and worship Lamashtu! We shall live, kill, die, and "
"multiply in your honor!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec49a7be-15c6-428e-89e4-9cb45b2206d9"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} and his followers have brought law and order to your "
"kingdom. Little by little, the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} are shifting away "
"from the dark times of the past... thank the gods! Your subjects appreciate this "
"newfound peace and order. Trade flourishes, lining the people's pockets with gold. "
"Your choice of patron for the kingdom was very wise indeed!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f9c0782a-8f1e-4900-a098-958ee0b04e3a"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} is a fool. Even in the face of inevitable oblivion, he "
"continues to fret over his doomed life's work, day and night. But he is not "
"without his admirers, even in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. Our merchants "
"and traders rely on Abadar's support in their affairs, and our artisans seek his "
"protection against bandits, which are still numerous in the area. You are praised "
"as a wise and caring {mf|king|queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "facacefa-dcd5-444c-a60d-4f2e7f9eff38"
msgid ""
"\\\"Speaking of {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g}, who you invited to your lands so "
"carelessly... I cannot say that his followers are entirely useless. They've spread "
"the idea that obeying your laws is good, and that submission is virtuous. But I "
"still dislike these narrow-minded penny pinchers – and so does my mistress.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "374e7673-21cf-4ecf-923f-b25f47c9252c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Grind these strange idols to dust. I've no wish to see strange shrines in the "
"area.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f16147e4-498c-42a9-9b87-5fe6cd7fcfe5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Leave the idols where they stand. Someone worships them, and we've no right to "
"interfere.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c838b767-a2bb-48e8-9e80-13f03d80ed06"
msgid "\\\"Do whatever you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45d92f22-35f6-4549-80ea-942fc2524cef"
msgid ""
"\\\"I bear bad news, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. A "
"number of foul idols have been seen around your new capital! They don't belong to "
"any god known to me, and strange loners seem drawn to them – which only gives me "
"greater concern.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52ecc344-b7f0-4903-b7ca-2aa681e2f790"
msgid ""
"\\\"I suggest we tear them down and be done with it. Who know what evil still "
"lingers in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} from the old times. In any case, "
"they certainly don't belong here!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1fc42a22-35e4-4853-bfb8-5420e17838f4"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim mumbles to himself, pulling on his beard. Finally he notices you.{/n} \\"
"\"{name}! Allow me to speak for those who cannot protect themselves and their "
"faith! The priests of {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g}, and the priests of the other gods – "
"they've all turned against the ancient faiths that once flourished in the {g|"
"Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}, now long since passed into eternity. Their final "
"traces are the ancient shrines and idols, which lay hid among the swamps and "
"woods, symbols of transience and decay...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c36910c-12be-4110-a71f-6d0deb6b616f"
msgid ""
"\\\"They wish to demolish these idols! They seek to destroy, with fire and chisel, "
"all that would remind them that all things must come to an end.\\\" {n}Harrim "
"strokes his beard broodingly.{/n} \\\"Whoever it was that once to worshipped these "
"idols, their faith deserves our respect. It is your decision, but I would not "
"destroy these ritual places just because the god they are devoted to isn't well "
"known. I myself serve such a god, often decried by ignorant tongues.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c6b564b-c58e-4cd8-8283-5c95660deabf"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, your pack trembles in fear. Foul idols circle around your capital. "
"Rumor has it they've been here forever, but the smell of blood upon them is still "
"hot and sweet. Strange looking lights have been seen around one such idol. These "
"remnants of ancient cults frighten your people, who clamor to demolish and burn "
"them down.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a33d6303-6719-4f75-b022-f1bb7955f012"
msgid ""
"\\\"But I would not, if I were you. Believe me, dead gods know how to leave nasty "
"gifts for those who would destroying their last vestiges.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff21c7e2-8ec5-468f-b432-36585adc4952"
msgid "\\\"Very well! I shall ensure that nothing remains of them, rest assured!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2976b70f-addf-4e38-801c-1ad4323a4114"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim sighs hopelessly.{/n} \\\"Another shadow of the past, to dissolve before "
"its proper time. It is a pity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f08c0091-1fc1-4fef-a796-63f53b75bc11"
msgid ""
"\\\"They do seem dangerous, yet my throat chokes when I hear you order them "
"demolished. As does yours, I'm sure. Do you truly prefer to ignore their power, "
"even as your every instinct cries out – 'Run!' Are you sure that this is wise?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf1f4143-8ee9-47a8-876a-cb91217faa42"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod sniffs.{/n} \\\"You're making a mistake! What if something hideous crawls "
"out from under them? Some daemon or worse... You are simply too kind, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Too kind, and not firm enough!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e2d12ee-0bfa-42a5-85d8-70eaa5c6b362"
msgid "{n}Harrim nods gravely.{/n} \\\"That is the right decision, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "249d9936-ecf9-4107-ad71-8e30a6b29cfb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Most reasonable. You should not seek to awaken whatever lies there, sound "
"asleep. It may have teeth sharper than yours.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0981828-740d-4868-b421-df8533e85082"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then it's time to send for our workers, and remove ever traces of this heresy."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ddea267-e8d5-4239-a920-16a13689a7ee"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will preserve the shrines. May your subjects remember that this is the "
"future of every faith.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2af59c9-2c9e-41eb-9e69-fd0331fb4829"
msgid ""
"\\\"I shall forbid anyone to engage with these idols. Who knows what strange "
"darkness sleeps beneath them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f30f76c6-ab6b-4f10-9231-8c3ae548e96f"
msgid "\\\"I allow this preacher to profess his faith in my lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64536815-4d78-4376-b25f-ffdb62d98857"
msgid ""
"\\\"I forbid this preacher to fill my subjects' heads with his rubbish. Throw him "
"out!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2ac97b7-1e95-4994-9dee-ee85f1954f7a"
msgid "Executed the innocent preacher."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0aa01e67-c30e-495a-9f8a-9b15986c017c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I demand the preacher be executed. Make him an example for the others!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61f5efd6-7b9f-492a-be85-b2fb90e5b096"
msgid "\\\"Make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "840cafb0-d871-4089-a440-c713c5c891f0"
msgid "\\\"I have never heard of these Speakers of the Depths. Who are they?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "07f6a5cb-560f-4ebc-b4a9-b3ac4b76cbb7"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod nibbles his mustache, annoyed.{/n} \\\"Oh, these {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen "
"Lands{/g}... They're a breeding ground for filth! No sooner have I dealt with one "
"crisis, but another is on its way! This time, a preacher of a religion that no "
"one's ever heard has ventured onto your lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56dd8e8a-aea1-4ca2-a754-a6388374cf2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"The people say that this priest speaks of some Speakers of the Depths. It's "
"the first time I'm hearing any of this, but the name alone says you shouldn't "
"expect anything good from them! But alas, not all our people are as reasonable as "
"you and I: the preacher has already gathered his first followers! {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I beg you: please decide what we are to "
"do with him! If you ask me, I say we should run him off with a pitchfork!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dff580de-bb95-439b-bccb-acc5993fa1b3"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim looks at you attentively from under his bushy brows.{/n} \\\"A god's "
"crier has come onto your lands. But he is not another one of {g|Cayden Cailean}"
"Cayden's{/g} barker or {g|Erastil}Erastil's{/g} preachers, oh no... He is a priest "
"of the Speakers of the Depths – ancient gods, whose names are forgotten in these "
"lands. \\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a26e442-2801-4ccb-b35d-14507c025595"
msgid ""
"\\\"He bears the message of the Speakers to your subjects – and he is has already "
"gathered his first worshipers! I see no reason to interfere: let the people choose "
"whatever faith they wish. But people are displeased – mainly the followers of {g|"
"Erastil}Erastil{/g}, and among our citizens there are many. They say that evil "
"hides under the cover of this strange religion. But this is folly. Still, you must "
"decide what to do about this new faith in your lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75b2c97f-5a0c-4721-af96-e1e213b11d6e"
msgid ""
"\\\"The guards have captured a suspicious traveler. A preacher of a strange "
"religion, who was traveling about your lands, spreading stories of strange gods. "
"He called them the Speakers of the Depths, or something of the sort. He's even "
"recruited a few followers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9c6cd3b-cf9d-4f5a-8c51-328de320a43e"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is only natural that his pathetic cult soon comes to an end – losing its "
"followers to other, more powerful deities. However, if you allow him to preach "
"freely without fear, this would send a message to adepts of other... neglected "
"cults. They too might emerge from the shadows and flock to you for protection. You "
"might make use of the stronger ones. As for the weak and futile... I shall deliver "
"upon them the wisdom of Mother {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g}, and take them under my "
"wing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5394cc97-7850-4cc6-812b-304d27084a20"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod is annoyed and mumbles something, but then waves his hand with a sigh.{/n} "
"\\\"As you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dbd0fd45-da30-4fa0-aeb7-d9247278a647"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your decision is merciful. I shall inform him that he has your permission.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5820bdba-2773-4baf-b23d-6858b89e3627"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna sighs.{/n} \\\"Very well. {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} respects those who "
"appreciate... diversity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a349514f-972e-45c1-b300-56030e8e9691"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod nods in content.{/n} \\\"Well said! There are simply too many of those... "
"ugh!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88b66c08-9f97-4af7-8012-36c23769e6b6"
msgid ""
"\\\"A pity, truly a pity. I shall inform him of your decision and send him on his "
"way.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0fc7f76a-a3eb-47b3-9a26-c300b9567d99"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna sighs.{/n} \\\"As you desire. Perhaps your pack is not disciplined "
"enough to accept what they cannot understand. You should resort to the whip more "
"often.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38cf5af2-0bdb-4913-bda4-d5d1873f40a3"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod freezes, astonished.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}, I am not glad to suffer such guests myself – but an execution? As you "
"wish, of course, but...\\\" {n}Rather than finishing his thought, Jhod just "
"silently shakes his head.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2861a41f-a112-456c-b25b-ba2549b866d9"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim lowers his head in grief.{/n} \\\"There is an end to all things, but to "
"bring death upon someone just because of their faith? This is hasty and unwise.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aacc561a-126c-4bd4-85a6-ec6c1fdf82ef"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna flexes her fingers.{/n} \\\"As you wish. But beware. Should your people "
"show such unkindness to my pack, their warm blood shall water the ground. And we "
"shall feast on their tasty fat... Their sweet, ivory fat.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a0617f7-61ea-4161-884d-99e66eafb472"
msgid ""
"\\\"Really? Very well. Then let him leave the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} "
"forthwith – we've enough trouble without these Speakers!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e75a2bf0-7fe6-41ec-a37c-9e3d96ddc0b8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then he shall receive the High Priest's permission. Let him bring his word to "
"those who have yet to find solace in the face of the inevitable.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5d72ccd-44d2-4e79-901a-aa01f440aaaa"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agree. The preacher will continue his travels. My pack will keep an eye on "
"him – and his flock. In the end, they may come to prefer {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} "
"to their strange idols.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77a39875-05a5-45e5-a741-2c67847f3487"
msgid ""
"{n}The priest ponders.{/n} \\\"I know many gods. Some of them show favor to "
"mortals, some show wrath. But some want nothing to do with the peoples of {g|"
"Golarion}Golarion{/g}. The Speakers of the Depths may be of this sort – who knows? "
"All the more reason to prevent your subjects' heads to be filled with this rubbish."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1a28893-6f1f-463d-bf89-db84b0b92e4d"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim shakes his head.{/n} \\\"The world is full of amazing gods, {name}, but "
"there are some strange things one should never touch. The Speakers of the Depths "
"may be harmless, or they may hold the key to the gate of destruction. Death and "
"oblivion await us all, either way. – So why fear the inevitable and plot against "
"those who are different from you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8c1e591-5dbd-4c21-bc54-39863f6e26b4"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna considers the question for a few seconds.{/n} \\\"{g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/"
"g} has revealed much to me. But I have never heard of the Speakers of the Depths. "
"Perhaps they have been careful to avoid becoming famous. Or perhaps they are too "
"pathetic to capture our attention.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f0131900-d0a8-44aa-92cc-0fb54c508a6b"
msgid ""
"[Pay 100 BP] \\\"We shall build this library of magic. It will spur the "
"development of mystical arts.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2752701-702b-43e3-87e8-1783cef244b4"
msgid ""
"\\\"We can do without a magic library. There are more urgent matters before us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14ad9b61-f2c0-48aa-b3ce-56395df2cbdf"
msgid "\\\"Why don't you decide?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb5aebbd-f889-43bf-8934-1210988d2150"
msgid ""
"{n}The priest sighs heavily.{/n} \\\"As you wish. But with {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} "
"as my witness, this will not lead to much good.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0c69db9-d0c3-4d99-ba72-79038167ee8c"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna pats her rat gently. Her rat's grey body is swollen, as if it were "
"carrying a brood of twin-headed beasts.{/n} \\\"Your pack grows like rabbits, and "
"your mages multiply along with the rest. You should find yourself an advisor, a "
"Magister, to look after these spellcasters and keep them on a tight leash. You "
"might find my methods for establishing order too rough.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29f321b5-3f22-4cc8-b522-01da45f03bc0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Speaking of spellcasters. A few worshipers of {g|Nethys}Nethys{/g} have "
"traveled here from {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g}. They await you in the hallway. They "
"seek to construct a library of magic in your capital, to make it a center of "
"sacred knowledge for all the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}. Were I in your "
"place, I would say yes. Such power might come in handy in making your subjects "
"more... open-minded about the worshipping of Lamashtu.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9527c524-5c0d-4d37-aaa5-c7202a2ddbc4"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim broods and mumbles, then clears his throat.{/n} \\\"Listen, {name}. I "
"wish to give you some advice: find another advisor who can deal with affairs of "
"magic. The {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} will struggle without a Magister. It "
"is dangerous to leave such important issues unattended.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d647b924-e451-4b01-9d88-f1e43b6b7afc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Before you appoint someone for this position, I will take upon myself this "
"final case, involving wizards and other spellcasters. A group of {g|Nethys}"
"Nethys'{/g} priests have arrived at your court, to propose an amazing thing: "
"founding a library of magic – here, in the capital. Your barony would gain a "
"valuable store of knowledge, that would otherwise fade into darkness. I believe "
"this deed is worthy of you and your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba8e5806-0822-4274-b730-802cec19635c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agree. I will convey your message to the priests of {g|Nethys}Nethys{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2746884d-dce9-4ede-9347-ca58dbeb63a6"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I... we need another "
"advisor, who is equipped to deal with issues of magic. In the past I have spent "
"some of my time on these affairs, but now the population of the {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom} – and my congregation – has grown so much that I simply cannot "
"handle the extra responsibility!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f0d623cd-825b-4106-b48b-585aae316d9d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, and another thing: a delegation of {g|Nethys}Nethys{/g} worshipers has "
"come to us from {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g}. They've dragged a miniature of some "
"magical library with them. They say they want to build it here, in your capital. "
"If I were you, I'd send them back the way they came. – We've enough on our plate "
"without the crazy projects of a crazy god.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72ead3ef-0c8f-43fa-ab7a-6dbc984dd351"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will immediately pass this news to the priests of {g|Nethys}Nethys{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "663b5df4-5373-4cef-960c-24f4e1a63841"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod nods.{/n} \\\"Don't worry about what to tell them. I'll find the right "
"words. The priests of {g|Nethys}Nethys{/g} will see their folly and leave in peace."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7a41d84-2891-4ad3-b9ce-302aa03c1299"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, then there shan't be any {g|Nethys}Nethys{/g} archives in the capital. "
"We can do just fine without them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "167996a1-c144-42bc-9e8a-39d13aafe435"
msgid "\\\"I will agree to the project.\\\" {n}Harrim bows slightly.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f654205c-ddd8-4bbd-ae6a-eea1b25df781"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will inform the priests of {g|Nethys}Nethys{/g}s that we accept their offer."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25957185-b234-44b1-afb0-a810e217cbdb"
msgid ""
"{n}The dwarf shakes his head slowly.{/n} \\\"Another step towards oblivion. {g|"
"Groetus}Groetus{/g} would be pleased, if he were with us now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8990d90d-3249-4cd4-93ae-9b031772e0d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"I see no reason to reject this opportunity. This meat is ripe. To let it rot "
"is senseless waste.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46b739f9-e675-4425-89fc-65d1719aff72"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let me be frank, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I've "
"been in this position for too long, and each day I feel more worthless. You should "
"find yourself another High Priest – someone more flexible. As for me, I am too old "
"to argue, or play your tutor now and again.\\\" {n}The priest bows and turns away."
"{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5434bf32-d5e6-48cb-af9c-3210dc9eb564"
msgid ""
"\\\"Enough, {name}. I have taken a position I am unfit for, and I cannot be "
"burdened by our arguments any longer. I am your High Priest no more. May you find "
"someone more to your liking.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b0d0b29-13ee-48a8-8415-4bea77c56ac8"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod blushes, then turns pale, his fingers trembling.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, blasphemy awakens in your domain! I hear "
"rumor of a cult that pretends to worship {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} – but the faith "
"they practice is nothing I recognize! According to them, my god demands blood "
"sacrifices to make the forest fertile and strong. The cultists walk the forest "
"with bows, shooting any who pass on sight!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18aa13d1-adf8-497e-9eeb-0d449b53746a"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I have curious news. Rumor has it that there is a cult in your lands "
"that twists the teachings of {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g}. They say the forests are "
"depleted, and the god demands blood sacrifices to restore the power of the woods. "
"They paint their faces and kill anyone they come across in the forest. Of course, "
"Erastil's worshipers condemn this new cult, and expect you to deal with it "
"decisively.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5007f73b-e53a-4095-9e88-cf2d3a913a84"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna looks pleased and excited. Her rat stirs restlessly on her shoulder.{/n} "
"\\\"{name}, you should be informed of a cult that sows unrest in the forest. They "
"worship {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g}, but do not follow the common faith. They claim "
"their god demands blood sacrifices to restore strength to the fading forest. The "
"cultists paint their faces and hide amongst the trees, armed with bows. Every "
"passerby is marked for death.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ab4c8f1-1429-4930-938a-2a2027df2545"
msgid ""
"\\\"These impostors must be stopped! Their bloodlust and blasphemy ill become us! "
"Some would appoint the General and unleash havoc upon them. The Treasurer might "
"bribe them with gold, that they might leave our domain. Heed my advice. Bring this "
"case to the Councilor. Public condemnation on your behalf will turn people away "
"from this vile cult!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd35ee39-9b69-4978-85a1-1f98f50d1aec"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is up to you whether you will order your General to send in forces, or "
"condemn this new cult through your Councilor. You may even ask your Treasurer to "
"pay a ransom, in hopes they will leave.\\\" {n}Harrim clenches his beard in his "
"fist and gives you a sidelong look.{/n} \\\"It is for you to decide.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7fda78c4-200f-4e75-812e-cd689dfd8a8e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd allow these madmen, but you can hardly afford it. You wouldn't want to "
"engage in this matter personally. Order one of your advisors to deal with it. You "
"might rely on your Councilor's grand rhetoric, or your Treasurer's gold – or even "
"your General's packs... You are ruler here. It is you who must decide.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0679f8b6-6cd7-41ae-8bd7-ec2a47c014da"
msgid "\\\"Let these cultists find a new home for themselves beyond our borders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6da60950-5810-436a-ab3a-27ff6399b8e8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Those villagers had better settle down. That coven harmed no one. The "
"followers of this strange religion have nothing to fear from me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96b98e73-db44-48ed-a808-72d3c98db981"
msgid "Let Tsanna secretly destroy the peaceful cult."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "80e6d900-12b0-44a1-86d4-999d81fa3930"
msgid "\\\"You may take them, Tsanna.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b602b118-2dbe-48eb-a2e8-49a21c111c4b"
msgid "\\\"Work it out on your own.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d4a7afb-f681-4500-ae9a-1c1cac8f283b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sacrifice and murder haunts our forests, and your subjects grow suspicious of "
"the other cults. There was a clash between some villagers and a small coven "
"possessing a couple dozen followers. That coven is perfectly peaceful, though "
"nonetheless strange. Its followers remain silent for their entire lives. They "
"believe that words and conversation invite madness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fd3b1ebd-b7ba-48bb-865f-5659b1810f5f"
msgid ""
"\\\"A number of innocents require your protection, {name}. After suffering much "
"bloodshed in the name of {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g}, our peasants have begun casting a "
"suspicious eye on followers of other religions as well. The more inscrutable the "
"faith, the more unpredictable and dangerous the cult seems. There have been "
"clashes with a small coven of silentiaries, whose sin is very minor indeed: they "
"believe that speech is dangerous, fearing it leads to madness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e86ea0e1-765e-4c9d-9104-d2f760183f67"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, the murders committed by {g|Erastil}Erastil's{/g} renegades have led "
"the peasants to see as threats anyone who holds strange beliefs. A conflict has "
"erupted around a small coven of silentiaries. These people are savage, but "
"nonetheless helpless. Their core belief is that speech is a dangerous invention, "
"leading to madness. They fear the spoken word, but they never do harm to anyone.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2143931a-6749-4d98-b472-9a8fdd0af94e"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod purses his lips stubbornly.{/n} \\\"We will ask them to leave – politely, "
"but firmly. I hope they will discover for themselves a better faith along their "
"journey.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "401e3d56-d74e-4c23-97fb-0ff056af3f40"
msgid ""
"\\\"How sad. Everyone is always trying to demolish something, expel someone, "
"banish each other to dark oblivion. The world is full of fragile things, you know. "
"Today you're banishing a harmless coven... And no one will remember it tomorrow. "
"Ripped from their home, they will surely perish. Will we mark their passing, or "
"even care? Do you not see now why our whole world deserves its fate?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7e54be60-898a-4031-b1d9-3cf7194dad6a"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna rolls her eyes. Her rat stares at you intently, squeaking furiously from "
"both of its throats.{/n} \\\"Will you truly banish anyone who attracts the "
"suspicion of your peasants? Who is the leader of your pack? You – or they?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2b1ed43-c978-4f57-9306-ad0cdfbf5128"
msgid ""
"\\\"This will return to bite you later, Your Grace. You'll see… The moment turn "
"your attention away, they'll be back to make more trouble for you. I do not "
"understand why we should suffer these fools on our lands...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ef4cec3-4a44-4598-a921-050e82d26f2d"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim runs his fingers through his beard with a smile.{/n} \\\"Leave the coven "
"be, and let the peasants learn to stop being so arrogant. It is good to have a "
"place in this world where the weak and the few in number can find refuge and live "
"in peace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30b8c6f1-a571-4908-b389-43c490d1c735"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna curls her lips.{/n} \\\"As you wish. We'll see what happens to the coven "
"when you withdraw your guards. I should have claimed them. My pack could have "
"protected those animals.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98667643-8544-4ece-be5e-a19090a8efd8"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna openly flashes her wicked smile.{/n} \\\"Perfect. My pack will gladly "
"play... Or I should say... Accept this task.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1a8d64c-76b9-45c9-95b4-652506912c11"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your people will remain on edge, so long as these fanatics remain. They will "
"not suffer such neighbors. – And to tell the truth, I stand by the people. Should "
"a friend or kin of mine join such a cult, I too would be deeply troubled. I "
"recommend you order this coven to leave from here, and find a place where they are "
"welcome.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba13e79d-dfc5-4bd9-8413-66974f255493"
msgid ""
"\\\"They are to be beaten and banished merely for refusing to speak! They surely "
"did nothing wrong! These innocents are breaking no laws or traditions! Tell your "
"subjects to quiet their anger, and leave the peaceful neighbors alone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e6e7024-27af-4f29-b0cc-84beeff78bb7"
msgid ""
"\\\"However, the peasants suspect them of all manner of nasty things, and wish to "
"be rid of them. We could rein them in, whip a few, and send them back to work the "
"earth, but this would in the end lead to massacre. We could expel the coven, but "
"this would send the message that anyone unwanted by the crowd would be subject to "
"the same treatment. But there is an easy way out: give them to me. My pack will "
"take their leaders from them, and rip out the tongues of the others – since "
"they're so fond of silence – and convert them to {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g}. I shall "
"ensure they don't bother anyone ever again.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bc43ceba-7fd1-4f4f-819b-47dcf3063aa7"
msgid "Chose Cayden Cailean as one of the godly patrons of the kingdom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c532d4c7-9368-4c9c-946d-01aa76e6535d"
msgid "\\\"I prefer Cayden.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35d6cb47-4f73-46ca-94ab-83e0cc763f83"
msgid "Chose Gorum as one of the godly patrons of the kingdom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed3747a6-b391-4f09-b37d-d840f5862b86"
msgid "\\\"Let them build Gorum's temple.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61c4e1de-0e0d-44e0-b0ae-1f791f72b5fa"
msgid "Chose Asmodeus as one of the godly patrons of the kingdom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a37cdb1c-ac66-4060-8a77-190eb668bd1f"
msgid ""
"\\\"We shall allow the servants of Asmodeus to set up a temple, regardless of our "
"neighbors' opinion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "664df44e-311a-4caa-a6aa-1b215082acfe"
msgid "\\\"Why don't you suggest a temple to your own god?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d48c8bd-1328-4d8a-887f-92a9784061c0"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about the gods.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df7b7012-3135-4355-b26c-8c23c454bd1f"
msgid "\\\"I'll trust your judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a8ea7552-1281-465e-aba0-5cdfc5ab98d6"
msgid "Chose Abadar as one of the godly patrons of the kingdom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84bd1463-3ac3-4c61-9dbd-7f707308226c"
msgid "\\\"I will allow Abadar's followers to erect a temple in his honor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8552b9bb-69b5-459a-84c6-f09b12f625a4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness! The fame of our domain is increasing. Many priests look to "
"erect their temples in the capital. The competition has stirred up no little "
"tension, and even some arguments!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "805412c4-c92e-4cfc-a3b2-091055025d58"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, the chronicles will remember you as a great {mf|king|queen}, not a "
"mere {mf|baron|baroness}. But even if you were an {mf|Emperor|Empress}, you would "
"still be wise to seek divine support. Four influential priests have arrived at "
"your court to plead for a temple honoring their gods.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "527dd69c-253a-42da-a7ec-9972e5af484b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your kingdom grows more famous by the hour, and many hope to take advantage of "
"this. Four gods are keen to lay their hands upon your domain – or to grant you "
"their patronage, to be precise. Priests of {g|Cayden Cailean}Cayden{/g}, {g|Abadar}"
"Abadar{/g}, {g|Gorum}Gorum{/g}, and {g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g} have each offered to "
"build temples in the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c907604-4922-4e79-9cbd-ac3d21657a25"
msgid "\\\"A little feasting and fun won't hurt this kingdom and its citizens.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58cce624-2639-4f2a-855d-fc4079d25191"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Drunken Hero? The one who hopes to drink himself into oblivion rather than "
"face the inevitable end that comes even for him? I disapprove of your decision, "
"but I will not oppose you on this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98b84723-26f8-44bf-b9e4-9706d1cf9568"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Cayden Cailean}Cayden{/g} may not be the worst option. Drunk people cast "
"off the shackles of decency and turn into primal beasts.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0507f97-22bc-493d-9843-ba4e55094b8d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Are you certain that we need even more war and bloodshed? I'm afraid {g|Gorum}"
"Gorum{/g} does not promise security to our kingdom. On the contrary, he will "
"involve it in ever more battles.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f208e48c-abd9-46a4-be76-dbe6ed49e469"
msgid ""
"\\\"I hope you will find satisfaction in his unforgiving patronage. He determines "
"the end that comes for us all... and even for he himself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cdbabe6-418a-472e-96e7-5327afc94d51"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Gorum}Gorum{/g} is ill-bred and cruel, but he's good in battle. At least "
"our enemies' swords will drink the blood of his followers, and not my pack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18ace146-14e8-4a6b-a282-5e931b09fc14"
msgid ""
"\\\"Summoning the god of law and tyranny to lands that have hosted chaos for "
"centuries... This is either very wise or very foolish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65b53b73-bf41-4313-9dce-9211001b628b"
msgid ""
"\\\"An ambitious decision. A deal with {g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g} promises profit. "
"But you must read the contract very carefully...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce012e55-831b-4fc2-a7a3-a5e1c348edfb"
msgid "\\\"Hmm... As you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a818a42-6bf9-4cf8-a37d-594cf23e29a5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why would I? Take a look around. This land is covered in forests. There are "
"plenty of deer in the thickets. Wildlife thrives in healthy lands, and its people "
"are decent and honest. This land is already under {g|Erastil}Erastil's{/g} "
"protection. Why would we need another temple?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf833214-2096-4580-a82e-efbf5d8b48d8"
msgid ""
"\\\"But why would I? All temples will eventually be destroyed. All of {g|Groetus}"
"Groetus'{/g} priests will turn to dust, like the priests of every other god. There "
"are few who can hear his whispers, and we are satisfied with ruined temples to "
"other gods...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa63fabb-6f1d-4066-82a9-63c06189496a"
msgid ""
"\\\"So I could start looking for another refuge? As soon as {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/"
"g} became patron of these lands, some righteous paladin would be placed on your "
"throne by common consent, while your head would be placed on the tip of his lance. "
"No, the time has not come. Yet.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b6dac667-3c05-497a-b679-1cc30588507a"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is no coincidence that {g|Cayden Cailean}Cayden's{/g} nickname is the "
"Accidental God. He was a mortal, a deathly drunk mortal, when he became a god. He "
"doesn't even remember how it happened. Under Cayden, your subjects will live "
"happily but senselessly, spending their time in feasts and fairs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e05c4fd8-9455-47b7-81dc-0dd780adf3f5"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Cayden Cailean}Cayden{/g} loves freedom and the simple pleasures of life. "
"People feel at ease with him. They drink, have fun, and live an easy life. He "
"promotes feasts, fairs – and brewing!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "148e93f1-c7cf-4752-a996-f5f36b3908f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Cayden Cailean}Cayden{/g} is the Accidental God. He loves everyone having "
"fun, and no one troubling anyone else. It sounds nice, but would you really want "
"your subjects always drunk, like their god?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35551ebd-682b-4666-b5ea-efde9650f703"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then let {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} ensure your people are civilized and prosperous."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "566e3974-7d44-437c-837e-abc04c4675aa"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let {g|Gorum}Gorum{/g} carve his path of destruction through your city gates, "
"{name}. Why postpone the inevitable?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "09a3442f-e6f3-44c9-a060-1ab245d3bd4f"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will make arrangements with the priest of {g|Gorum}Gorum{/g}. Let your "
"neighbors learn to accept that these are free lands, where we may worship any god "
"we choose, even one known to be 'violent' and 'dark'.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5bf68c7f-861e-4229-bfad-b16f7440bcc5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Each of them wants their god to win new followers in a young and strong "
"kingdom. But they won't tolerate any rivals. Gods hate to share. Thus you must "
"select only one god. I'd place my bet on {g|Gorum}Gorum{/g}. {g|Cayden Cailean}"
"Cayden{/g} is an unreliable drunkard. {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} and {g|Asmodeus}"
"Asmodeus{/g} are alien to me by nature.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "383bef44-82a0-46ad-95e8-c88addb1f3c9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Each wishes your kingdom to prosper under the blessings of their god. We must "
"choose between {g|Cayden Cailean}Cayden{/g}, {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g}, {g|Gorum}Gorum{/"
"g}, and {g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g}. I advise you to consider Gorum. His road to the "
"end of things is at least simple and direct.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3755d7ab-df00-4215-9e14-0165f0476a0f"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must opt for one of the great gods, thus winning the hearts of his many "
"followers. The most influential priests are those of {g|Cayden Cailean}Cayden{/g}, "
"{g|Gorum}Gorum{/g}, {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g}, and {g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g}. My advice "
"is that you take a closer look at Abadar.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84d5cf4c-95ea-4901-a3ca-6e039a692297"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Gorum}Gorum{/g} is the dark patron of battle, the master of violence, bold "
"and merciless. His followers believe only in power. They are soldiers, barbarians, "
"mercenaries – and murderers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a2391469-2f68-4040-b3aa-2be9e467b254"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g} is the strongest of the archdevils. {g|Cheliax}"
"Cheliax{/g}, a powerful kingdom, has long prospered under his patronage. He "
"believes in discipline and obedience, and the right of the strong to rule the "
"weak. I wouldn't advise getting involved with him. Our neighbors will turn against "
"us, and his patronage will bring down a curse on us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aba8fdcd-c469-4989-bbc9-7ccc1ea6a3ed"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Gorum}Gorum{/g} is a cruel and bloodthirsty warrior, as are his followers. "
"He is the god of war. He is worshipped by orcs and barbarians, but he has quite a "
"few followers among the civilized as well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83efdb84-db40-4560-b39b-d49d54129bf6"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g} is the lord of {g|Hell}Hell{/g}. He's the archdevil "
"worshipped by the powerful state of {g|Cheliax}Cheliax{/g}. Asmodeus believes in "
"power, compacts, order, and the obedience of the inferior. He's crafty but not "
"deceitful. You should read the contract very carefully, if you choose him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17c73d62-7a74-46cc-824a-66e3272442a9"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g} is the archdevil, the lord of {g|Hell}Hell{/g}. {g|"
"Cheliax}Cheliax{/g} made a deal with him – and benefitted greatly from it! It is "
"now a great country which no one wants to fight with. For Asmodeus, order and "
"discipline are absolute. He trusts in the right of the strong, the obedience of "
"the weak, the power of compacts, and the impotence of reliance. It would be a "
"profitable deal – which our neighbors would hate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7c23174-122b-4f7f-8f19-d2e1a2533d4d"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Gorum}Gorum{/g} is the god of war, soldiers and assassins. He's arrogant "
"and merciless. His followers are great warriors that would come in handy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79e9c689-e224-42cc-8873-9dbe0e3215be"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} is the god of cities and laws, merchants and trade. All "
"he cares about is law and order. It wouldn't be an easy life for his followers in "
"the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}, but his patronage might make your citizens a "
"bit more obedient!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "995baec0-b184-4a5f-9276-df3b6e3adb41"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} is the patron of cities and trade. He is there, where "
"civilization flourishes, and he detests chaos and destruction. I'm not sure if his "
"followers will survive well here, in these wild and untamed lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "960689de-3713-4c4a-a9f0-846c1a0e962b"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} is the god of cities and civilization... which I hate by "
"my nature. {g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g} is the archdevil, the lord of {g|Hell}Hell{/"
"g}. He trusts in the right of the strong, obedience of the weak, the power of "
"agreement, and the impotence of reliance. If you decide to turn to one of these "
"two gods, beware! They might strangle your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} and "
"you with the infinite bonds of legislation."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e98d1976-5f58-4d57-8e70-50d37c67e089"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is a wise decision, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} doesn't have too many enemies. No one will be "
"sorely disappointed with your decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ef9afd0-9db5-4857-8163-006ee20b1fcb"
msgid "\\\"Let it be so, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cbce660a-c931-4c79-93be-cb3522e7f8b3"
msgid "\\\"Hm... As you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5dc2dae1-90e3-4f12-ac86-626df8d0b2ef"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}! It's all gone! The idols around the capital that we chopped down... "
"They were some kind of security walls, or seals. Now there are weird portals where "
"they stood, and what's coming out of them...\\\" {n}Jhod shudders and shivers, "
"barely breathing out the last word.{/n} \\\"... It's an abomination! The monsters "
"are stalking the area, killing people and devastating small villages. Some wizards "
"are demanding that the Magister to return the idols where they belong. They "
"believe the idols can somehow drive away the monsters.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed8dd691-6062-4dd1-8c4e-8990b9f740f3"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim looks at you, sad and calm, his hands leaving his poor beard alone for "
"once.{/n} \\\"...Portals opened in the places where you ordered the idols "
"demolished. Monsters are emerging from them – filthy and unnatural creatures. Even "
"I can see they should not be here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "980d1f33-ca02-4e1a-97a0-3bc020680dda"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna's fingers are constantly moving, as if she's squeezing someone's "
"invisible throat.{/n} \\\"Sinister portals opened in the places where you ordered "
"the idols removed. The monsters that emerge sicken even me. I know not where they "
"come from, not what they seek, but they must be stopped. They spread through the "
"forests and devour your subjects.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7994dc4-3c66-4caa-b2f6-95419f02d119"
msgid ""
"\\\"I do not like this solution. We must face this evil steadfast, and never try "
"to defeat one dark magic with another. Our army is powerless against the monsters. "
"Our soldiers are trained to fight in the open, not to track monsters through a "
"thicket. If only Your Highness could appear everywhere at once and repel each "
"attack! But no, we must order the Warden to call upon the people to resist. Gather "
"the hunters, pathfinders, and those who know the thicket. We shall stand united!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7e1afe47-6785-42ee-a1da-7b5932376c0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must stop these monsters. I wouldn't rely on weapons, even if the Warden "
"managed to unite the whole kingdom in resistance. Soldiers cannot track the "
"monsters in the forest, and you cannot be everywhere at once. We must bring things "
"back to normal. I made a sketch of the idols, so I can help the Magister seal the "
"portals. The monsters should die if we succeed. Their tether to their native world "
"will be severed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e63b465-382d-4356-92b3-0dd200608314"
msgid ""
"\\\"You yourself cannot hunt them all down, and your army will be of little help. "
"They do not possess the skills of the forest hunter. We could order the Warden to "
"drum up the people for a full raid... But don't expect your hunters and wood "
"choppers to overcome their own fears, when facing such beasts. Better to assign "
"this matter to the Magister. Perhaps he would not only be able to seal the "
"portals, but also examine the monsters. I would like to learn more about them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf93530c-4b66-41c4-8704-b0cc1d331024"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have bad news, Your Highness. The idols you ordered protected have become "
"crime scenes again and again. Bloody traces are often discovered. We found a new "
"grave recently, and I couldn't believe my eyes. It seems that someone's been "
"making sacrifices to the idols!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "36de6963-4614-43aa-9e3a-905d4e62ae21"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have bad news, {name}. Someone has been making bloody sacrifices to the "
"idols that you so mercifully granted your protection. We discovered blood and dead "
"bodies. The guards have attempted to root out the cultists, but the people are "
"scared, and all attempts have failed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa6b103c-c35d-401c-bb0e-b4e9d5376c03"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, the idols that you granted your protection have are attracting "
"dangerous cultists once again. We keep discovering blood and dead bodies. The "
"guards have tried to root out the cultists, but the people are afraid to talk.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e71daf00-556b-4176-bf0a-34cfa5978b2a"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must order the Minister to send assassins after the bloody cultists! No, "
"not assassins... We should invite inquisitors who honor the good gods! They will "
"quickly root out and put an end to the rascals. Let the diplomat write invitations "
"for them. If these idols are so dear to their pagan worshipers, they could have "
"come to me to negotiate. Alas, now that the blood is spilled, the time for words "
"has gone!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17d0c4e1-2aa8-4462-bc3d-e51df73977f2"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could order the Minister to send our best assassins after them. Our Grand "
"Diplomat could engage inquisitors, who are much like assassins, except that they "
"serve their deity rather than their own purses. But I think I could come to terms "
"with whoever is conducting these rites. Allow them to be performed quietly, "
"without alarming the community. What if they serve a greater purpose?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6a86e78-97f9-4fbe-81da-28c819ba6933"
msgid ""
"\\\"They're doing a fine job, I'll give them that. I don't think we could persuade "
"them to work for us – so why don't you tell the Minister to send killers after "
"them, and seize all their journals and books? Also, I advise against ordering the "
"Grand Diplomat to summon the inquisitors of benevolent gods. Their investigation "
"might bring to light... other ominous cults that operate in your lands. And we "
"wouldn't want that, now would we?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "303d14d7-b39d-4e15-b7d8-868da5a5cf13"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let them speak out, without fear for their lives or their freedom. Leave them "
"be.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b5159a3-f0ca-4fbb-86d8-f90c7a86d7d1"
msgid "\\\"Declare their teachings prohibited, and drive them to the border.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27d05d4b-5f7e-408f-b4c3-6c7aa3cb984f"
msgid "Ordered the atheists from Touvette to be secretly exterminated."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41ce16eb-1d82-4468-a2af-849c2d0beca9"
msgid "\\\"Execute them publicly.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c6593f4a-10f8-47b9-9f58-d80f1d62806f"
msgid "\\\"I will rely upon you in this matter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ae57c71-b936-48c7-8c73-d73b0fc600bc"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about this Touvette.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3f37a98-6c00-4331-98ef-53d50e69a7e5"
msgid ""
"\\\"We have arrested some agitators from Touvette. They claim themselves "
"harbingers of atheism, and doubt the high status and authority of the gods, whose "
"servants cause only pain and suffering. We should do as Touvette's neighbors have "
"done, and drive these agitators away, while still preventing bloodshed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2b9aa28-2a2d-422a-a842-580ce3233be4"
msgid ""
"\\\"The guards have arrested some agitators from Touvette. They call themselves "
"preachers of godlessness, also known as atheism. The gods should not be "
"worshipped, they say, and I agree with them. Only {g|Groetus}Groetus{/g} is worthy "
"of our prayers. He alone is honest with us. He doesn't promise any reward. On the "
"contrary, he shows what awaits us, no matter how tempted we may be to reject him "
"in horror. So I would leave these... atheists alone. Their frustration with the "
"gods is justified in many ways. That's why the priests are after them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc24460c-c317-4acd-8e8a-b347d6384b67"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've captured some dangerous rebels. They're agitators from Touvette claiming "
"to be atheists, or simply put, godless people. They may be fools, but they're "
"dangerous nevertheless. Our divine patrons might turn away from the kingdom, "
"depriving us of their protection, and all because of these fools! They must be "
"banished. Or even better – publicly executed, to show the gods that we haven't let "
"them poison our minds.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd3ef15a-8937-4b5c-b86c-ab13c9d5047e"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod purses his lips and scratches the back of his head vigorously.{/n} \\"
"\"Hm... I don't like it. They lead otherwise decent people astray, and you're "
"letting them do it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a8d9a4d6-ee54-4ed4-bba2-ddd3ef2e85a2"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim's voice is hollow, as if echoing down a deep well.{/n} \\\"Every voice "
"may sound in the void, but not every voice can fill the void.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f054fcf-964e-4fd6-bf93-a7c72d71025f"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna wags her finger.{/n} \\\"Never disrespect gods, {name}. Never give "
"shelter to those who defy the power of the gods. The divine wrath can be "
"overwhelming.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83b0f19d-0665-4df1-8f5e-749ae30e5178"
msgid "\\\"I will make sure that they are entirely driven from your lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ef286a7a-ecb1-4b15-a6ff-96b605b04c08"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim shrugs.{/n} \\\"Very well, but it's not going to change anything. Their "
"teachings have already been shared. Fate cannot be changed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1677932-8221-40a2-938c-68f1b566eb36"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you think the people will forget everything just like that? Your ban will "
"be the first topic of gossip, and someone is bound to believe their words. In the "
"end, you'll have to banish fifty, not five! Or even worse, {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/"
"g} will unleash a pestilence herself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a92645b-967c-4262-a5a9-6a6f77da6f3b"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod's eyes widen.{/n} \\\"What unprecedented cruelty! They are like confused "
"children, mistreated by their strict parents, who've decided that all grown-ups "
"are bad. Do they truly deserve punishment for their plight?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19d620be-b423-4a1c-a3f1-0e58876b1e15"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim frowns.{/n} \\\"If they're lying, why kill them? If they're telling the "
"truth, will death put an end to it? This is nothing but foolishness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ea84f05-9ad3-459e-b824-708eb568ed58"
msgid ""
"{n}A predatory grin appears on Tsanna's face.{/n} \\\"It will be done. I'll see "
"that they suffocate properly – slowly and painfully. The gods won't blame us for "
"showing mercy to their enemies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5f2c980-4af4-49d9-882a-ec79de57020a"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod frowns and clenches his fists.{/n} \\\"I'll make sure they're driven away "
"quietly. Let them preach their false ideas in Touvette. We'll not welcome it here. "
"The gods are gracious, and our ruler is not angling to take their place!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71861c9d-a8f3-42ee-9aaf-8f531a4cb30c"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim sighs.{/n} \\\"Let them teach what they will, then. The end may come "
"when we finally give up all religions but {g|Groetus}Groetus'{/g}! This makes "
"their teaching harmless. It only promotes the inevitable.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ffe3fc73-0ee7-4a4a-bcf8-6be37ba345ed"
msgid ""
"{n}A predatory grin appears on Tsanna's face.{/n} \\\"I'll ensure that no one ever "
"hears their dangerous teachings. I'll put their heads on display.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f351699-2159-4de6-92df-82aa7f97d5f2"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a bad place! Wars between rival priests tore Touvette apart. The fighting "
"almost destroyed the country. Neighbors annexed half the territory. The people "
"were starving. – And the priests and the king didn't care at all.\\nSo General "
"Voran gathered the people's full support, overthrew the king, and seized power. "
"Voran put an end to the war, restored order, and recovered the kingdom's lands. I "
"even approve that he seized the priests' treasures to feed the people. It was the "
"priests who led the people to starvation! But Voran isn't the sort of man you "
"would freely give power to.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ea6d4d4-a688-4771-9a59-8b2d688b3b77"
msgid ""
"\\\"Touvette is a brilliant example for us all. Emptiness and death await "
"everyone. The priests of Touvette fought each other too fiercely, and this brought "
"their country to ruin. But just as Touvette was about to fall, General Voran "
"appeared. He overthrew the king, expelled the priests, and restored order. He "
"spent the temple's treasures to feed the people. You must wonder if this story had "
"a happy ending? No, it didn't. As I said, the inevitable cannot be stopped.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da41f86b-8af1-4a0d-8329-35a0834c6cfb"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a bad place! The local priests of the \\\"good\\\" gods began to quarrel, "
"and almost ruined the country. General Voran seized power, and became a strong "
"leader. {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} could have granted her blessing to him. But Voran "
"attempted to become even more. I think he considers himself almost a deity. He "
"killed or expelled all the priests to eliminate competition, and turned the "
"temples into headquarters for his knights. They are soldiers, judges, and "
"executioners all at the same time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1367842-efcd-436e-8fa3-ec96d98a331d"
msgid ""
"\\\"He expelled all the priests from Touvette. Dissenters were dragged behind "
"horses through the streets, and stoned to death. He also turned the temples into "
"'refuges', a combination of schools, hospitals, and offices.\\nVoran instituted "
"strict order and fully subdued Touvette. Its people sing praises to him every "
"morning, as if he were a god – for saving them from religion and laziness. "
"Everything is closely watched. Indeed, Voran himself announced that the country "
"was full of spies. This is how he compels obedience. Like most crimes, speaking "
"out against the general is punished by death at the hands of his Knights. They are "
"warriors, judges, and executioners, all at the same time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c6b242f-adb3-400a-8006-3f1abde7effa"
msgid ""
"\\\"The worst sin in Touvette is believing in anyone or anything other than Voran. "
"The general has declared war on all gods. He combined the ways of {g|Razmiran}"
"Razmiran{/g} and {g|Rahadoum}Rahadoum{/g}, the famous country in {g|Garund}Garund{/"
"g} which denies all the gods. Take my word for it, Touvette will never flourish "
"without the patronage of a mighty god. On the contrary, the country is now "
"isolated, and it has no allies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd875727-4f03-45a4-a583-72b8e96ffb0c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now there is order in Touvette. Strict order. There's only one punishment for "
"breaking the law. Death. Speaking against Voran or worshipping the gods are chief "
"among crimes. Everyone is watched so closely that no one can hide. I don't have "
"any brothers or sisters there. That country is destined to perish, either by the "
"will of the gods, or by the simple act of its neighbors, who have broken off all "
"ties with Touvette.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6187cffe-640b-47dd-a6d6-98edc2e17c2d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Voran went mad. He forced to people to worship him and utter prayers of "
"gratitude to him every morning. He banned all other gods and killed the priests. "
"His knights watch everyone, and kill all who dare worship a god. This is a country "
"of strict laws, and everyone must submit to the cruel dictator.\\nHe once "
"crucified a defeated general and carried the cross above his army like a banner, "
"can you imagine it? That's the sort of man he is, the savior of Touvette.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ad642af-32ec-4751-889a-6c5193dd45ce"
msgid ""
"\\\"But he's merely postponed the death of his country. Either it will be punished "
"by the enraged and jealous gods, or starved to death by neighbors who've no "
"interest in further dealings with Touvette.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0cc70b11-5280-45ec-89fb-3d4b0a076129"
msgid "\\\"Invest our gold in trade points. I need loyal people abroad.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0635cf8e-0c64-4ad4-9bd3-9d4aa011c113"
msgid "\\\"Pay tuition for our young people in foreign lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc8320da-8a84-40b6-8c0a-06ba4c768976"
msgid "\\\"Invite a weather mage.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a49556e-2a39-4c3b-8bb3-977b60c1a2d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"You managed to bring to order the village chiefs and local leaders, and found "
"common ground with the smaller local governors. They considered themselves kings "
"in their own right, but now they faithfully serve you. It's a victory.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6e1a321-50f6-4a44-8d8e-84c635ef424c"
msgid ""
"\\\"You managed to reform a hostile country government, once full of corruption "
"and bribery.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a912e08-11b4-4988-b67d-ec1668496a6d"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost chuckles contentedly.{/n} \\\"Oh, I'm only joking. Although I do "
"respect the way you dealt with this mess of a bureaucracy. I couldn't have done it "
"any better. It's a good thing that you put an end to all those bureaucrats "
"mistreating the townsfolk.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ad718d5-6d10-479d-b962-2d11db5be746"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost chuckles contentedly.{/n} \\\"I'm only joking, of course. Although "
"there's much that commands respect. When you came to power, you didn't dismiss all "
"the Stag Lord's larcenous servants and governors, but organized them into a "
"working system. As a result, the country under your governance is now thriving.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b8595642-7cd4-4906-a615-6de7fe3bab0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"It was your vision not to imprison everyone you captured... so to speak, red-"
"handed. You realized that bending these people to your will would be far more "
"beneficial!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49248c4a-64ba-46f3-9006-521cd3c5ebfe"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your celebrated steady hand cleared this swamp of corrupt servants and "
"kleptocrats. Now that there's nobody to plunder your treasury, it's full of gold!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2cdc425-c6d2-4e43-99ea-039e3d8c3f94"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're not as simple as you pretend to be. All right. I will make the "
"necessary arrangements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90a116b4-9082-4a70-b34a-d561487c0f5d"
msgid "\\\"That's a promising idea. I will organize everything.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02c42aec-1f4f-46dc-b4dd-0a8a25aaf966"
msgid "\\\"Great idea. Every gold coin we invest in this will multiply tenfold!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab5aea39-2696-406f-961c-878e37c20abb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Taking care of youth is certainly the way to go. Let them see the world!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1f96e82-7a17-4f73-a05c-a28e52f6a01c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm glad that my example has proven to you how valuable a well-rounded outlook "
"can be.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "95d3713e-e952-4485-b277-b57ccfa3f321"
msgid "\\\"Very wise. We shall need some foreign-trained servants.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9089fd1a-cbcd-4d2e-a82f-7c0cf466a9b3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well. It's wise to protect your fields from an early autumn or a torrid "
"summer. When I was a baron, I also tended first to my subjects' bellies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de0d69ed-19b7-47ca-834c-daf463ea5463"
msgid "\\\"Perfect! Finally I'll have someone to talk to. I mean, academically.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "959d0621-93fd-4fcb-a0ab-22e0bbc732a7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Having a court mage of such skill is very prestigious indeed. And "
"advantageous! I admire your vision!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d4ebffd2-33be-49fa-8ff9-c7d3dd25e28c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, I have come to express my boundless respect! I had no idea I "
"would be a part of something this... grand. You were able to build a prosperous "
"and wealthy state, where there was once just a broken, cursed, and godforsaken "
"backwoods.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4111a309-034c-4ae2-8d4c-1ca642596c22"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your efforts have brought in too much money. It's strange, I never expected "
"I'd say these words. Anyway, you must decide where to invest it. I suggest you "
"invite an experienced weather mage from {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g} to drive droughts "
"and floods away from our fields. Another option is to send our talented youth "
"abroad for study. Or, for that matter, we could open a couple of trade offices in "
"neighboring countries and use them as cover for our agents.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fee052e4-169a-438c-a734-0ec17354d26c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I know why you applied such effort, {name} – why you turned this wasteland "
"into an advanced, wealthy, and prosperous state. And today you will hear the words "
"you've been striving for all this time. I'm proud of you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc2a7728-d362-4022-85e4-08e61888b062"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness! As your humble servant, allow me to express my respect. You "
"have turned a gloomy, hopeless land into a region of prosperity and opportunity. I "
"hope you fully appreciate my modest contribution.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d36c5bc2-7c59-4ce9-83ee-0878d8968094"
msgid ""
"\\\"We managed to fill the treasury. Overflow it, in fact. Literally. The "
"abundance of gold in the royal treasury has caused our subjects to develop a nasty "
"disease. Greed – causing an acute inflammation of envy. Take my advice. Invite a "
"famous weather mage from {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g} to the capital. I've heard his "
"lectures. He's a true harvest-saving expert. He will protect the crops against "
"flood or drought. Another option is to send our gifted youth abroad for study. On "
"the other hand, if we harbor less-than-noble intentions, we might set up a few "
"trade offices in neighboring countries to serve as cover for your agents.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9cfc1dd2-2d3c-4bfa-8601-20102d8d0dbb"
msgid ""
"\\\"I wouldn't seal away the kingdom's coffers. You should rather invest the "
"money. Consider inviting a famous weather mage from {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g}. His "
"services are expensive, but he would protect our harvests from droughts and "
"floods. Another promising project would be to send our youth abroad for study. We "
"could also open several trade offices in the neighboring countries. As cover for "
"our agents, of course.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2ba68e5-a830-4cb5-a5c1-9e1399d00845"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tell me, how does a gardener feel, when he looks at flowers blooming in a "
"garden that he's grown in an arid desert? How does an alchemist feel when the gray "
"lead in his vial turns into shining gold? You received this land as a wild, "
"uninhabited swamp – and now the richest merchants in the land vie for the right to "
"do business here! I can only be proud of being a humble part of this miracle "
"you've made happen.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72084fe7-1a16-4e46-8375-b917bc71d525"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your servants are loyal to you. Each of them remembers how much they owe you, "
"how your generosity raised them up – and how your disfavor could turn them to "
"dust. They didn't suddenly transform into honest people, but you've nevertheless "
"managed to build a sturdy house from gnarled boards!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06640614-31da-4cb4-84f5-60f358455719"
msgid ""
"\\\"Like a well-trained dog who wouldn't dare to look at the meat in front of it "
"without its master's order, your servants have all but forgotten what bribery and "
"embezzlement are. No longer do they serve their own purses, but only the glory and "
"prosperity of the state.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad05f237-abc8-46f9-a1a6-9e83c58b71ce"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course, there is no such thing as excess of money, but we do have some idle "
"funds. It would be unwise to let them lie fallow in your coffers! We should spend "
"the money to increase the profits and glory of the nation. I suggest we invite a "
"famous wizard from {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g} who could command the weather. Such a "
"learned man would not only adorn your court with his presence, but ease the lives "
"of the peasants who suffer from droughts and floods. We might also invest in the "
"younger generation, and pay the tuition fees of promising young men and women at "
"foreign universities. We could even open trade missions in neighboring countries – "
"which could make an excellent cover for our spies!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5af4902-a6aa-43cf-959b-a6ae0eb6f463"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your decision is wise as usual! What could be more prestigious than masters of "
"arcane arts at court?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12d65be2-5e34-4532-9122-3b60d93f2d11"
msgid ""
"\\\"Right, we need to think about the future. The generation that will inherit "
"everything we've created must be ready to expand on our achievements, not waste "
"them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "007d81ff-2edf-4aa0-8ed8-85c89270bab2"
msgid ""
"\\\"This decision will not bring us glory, but its benefit will be great. When our "
"envious neighbors start whispering and plotting against us, we'll know right away "
"– and be ready to dismantle their plots!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a61ed51f-2b45-458a-8d2e-b56d479154fa"
msgid "[Gain 60 BP] \\\"Take these riches to the treasury.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06e06170-638f-422a-a6b9-a70f091c4af9"
msgid ""
"\\\"The owners of these things might be dead or on the run. We will use them to "
"revive the villages that suffered the most under the Stag Lord's reign.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e044aa04-1008-42d2-ae63-9daf2887df58"
msgid ""
"\\\"These things don't belong to me any more than they belonged to the Stag Lord. "
"Order them returned to the people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "108a6b5d-7acf-450b-9912-885926022a95"
msgid "\\\"You may decide what to do with these things.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cf04bdf-6a36-4fcb-9bab-7e0f5d5b870e"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost cordially greets you with a document.{/n} \\\"{mf|Baron|Baroness|King|"
"Queen}! You will never guess what your Treasurer is holding.\\\" {n}He waves a "
"paper above his head. The ink on it seems still wet.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a77870b7-2e1b-4e61-b72d-41c335d94b16"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is a list of things that tumbled out of the wall of your own basement, as "
"the workers were undertaking repairs.\\\" {n}Jubilost adjusts his glasses and "
"starts reading.{/n} \\\"A gilded guard, one, silverware, three, a set of old "
"coins... The list is long and varied, so I'll get straight to the point: it "
"appears that your workers uncovered the Stag Lord's secret cache – items stolen "
"from his own henchmen.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "279939e2-bc73-4f37-a326-0b0d80b25574"
msgid ""
"\\\"Finding the true owners of these things would be a hard and thankless job, "
"while taking these trinkets for your own chests is complicity to expropriation. In "
"other words – robbery. As your financial advisor, I recommend a compromise: "
"appraise these 'riches' and spend an equal amount on reviving the villages laid to "
"waste by the bandits. Let these treasures bring some good to those who suffered "
"most under the Stag Lord.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ed252df-69d0-437d-aed9-7d759ea2fd38"
msgid ""
"{n}Maegar's face is lit with a contented smile.{/n} \\\"My deepest respects, {mf|"
"baron|baroness|King|Queen}! I have wonderful news for you: our workers have "
"unearthed a true treasure!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28c04143-c2e3-41c4-b1c5-a6fcadf3b736"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew bows down.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}, I am happy to see you well! I would not bother you were it not for some "
"wonderful news that I'm happy to share.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eed72f67-5c4a-48a7-a84c-c56c36321b70"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I shall arrange that the funds be directed to the restoration of the "
"villages.\\\" {n}A contented smile crosses Jubilost's face.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ca5c3d7-7d10-45c8-89c8-4710db84f611"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost sniffs, disappointed.{/n} \\\"A noble gesture, but folly nonetheless. "
"Very well, as you wish.\\\" {n}The gnome sighs sadly and waves his hand.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d92d1be-5947-4cc0-b329-4b5f22293196"
msgid "{n}Jubilost nods solemnly.{/n} \\\"I knew you would follow my advice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4815a0d1-4396-40bb-b6e6-20dcfa51bb44"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost lets his glasses fall to the tip of his nose as he sizes you up, "
"annoyed.{/n} \\\"So it's like that, is it? Following the example of your "
"predecessor? If I were you, I would think well about this Stag Lord you're so glad "
"to imitate – and the way he ended up!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a63479e-ffaa-402e-af71-78a3671989d8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, not exactly a treasure... more like the secret cache of the Stag Lord. "
"Our workers broke through a wall to expand the basement, and found inside a hidden "
"alcove filled with valuables. Not endless gold, but not rubbish either. I think "
"they are the valuables of locals who thought they'd buy a few days' peace from the "
"Stag Lord and his bandits.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "117ab91c-2f4d-4467-99c4-cd4a86366e6d"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's up to you what we should do with these items. Of course, they were found "
"in your castle, so you could keep them in the treasury...\\\" {n}Maegar cringes.{/"
"n} \\\"If you wish to consider the opinion of your Treasurer, I say you'd best "
"give them away. It wouldn't amount to a great loss, and a few people might recover "
"their family heirlooms.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8304c4b7-1a96-4d69-ae62-b11542bd950e"
msgid ""
"\\\"The workers who are expanding the old fort's basements stumbled upon a cache. "
"It appears that the bandit leader, who previously lived in this fortification, "
"kept a little stash for a rainy day. Luckily, I was able to intervene before the "
"workers stole everything, and now the treasure is at my... I mean at your disposal."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "00539df3-a8db-4785-ade5-8d1ae2015249"
msgid ""
"\\\"I recommend you claim the cache for your treasury. No matter how these things "
"made their way to the Stag Lord, they are now yours – just like the castle, the "
"surrounding lands, and all who live upon them. As your Treasurer, I assure you – "
"in the future you and your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} will require all the "
"money you can get!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86ee9b33-7e23-49cd-ba08-11c62c6f2c7d"
msgid ""
"{n}Maegar's face grows dark.{/n} \\\"It's wrong to put claim such stolen things "
"for yourself. I do hope in the future you will be more attentive to those who are "
"less lucky in life than you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24b47595-7f33-4547-87b6-10ebf4998fd4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very wise, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. But still, "
"such a pity these things will never see their proper owners again... but your "
"decision is probably fairer. I will make the necessary arrangements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa6e28ea-e190-4aed-8cfe-e0eec07798c8"
msgid ""
"{n}Maegar nods contentedly.{/n} \\\"We will do just that, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, don't you worry. I will do everything in my "
"power to personally track down the proper owners of each little thing – that is, "
"of course, if they're still alive and weren't run off by the bandits.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5dd53f2e-f1da-4da9-baa7-f34495c57fde"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for your trust, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. With your permission, I shall order the discovered riches returned to "
"the people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f6c9d6b-d4d2-4761-bda1-4ad064bf197b"
msgid ""
"\\\"A wonderful decision, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! "
"I will do as you ask!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1b786d9-c334-4e8d-910a-c7b0030d3e62"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew strokes his mustache, brooding.{/n} \\\"You are farsighted, {mf|"
"Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I hope the returning village "
"folk appreciate your generosity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8bc78c9d-4cf8-442c-ae77-5403261b0f9c"
msgid ""
"{n}Red spots appear on Bartholomew's face, and he repeatedly opens his mouth, as "
"if gasping for air.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}! How could you! Such... pointless... expenses! If we keep giving your "
"treasures away at this rate, we'll soon be begging on the streets!\\\" {n}The "
"Treasurer is silent for a few moments, then sighs and lowers his head.{/n} \\\"As "
"you wish, {mf|baron|baroness|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5dd0964a-3e6d-4ced-9b78-3b437e1bf25d"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I am glad to be worthy "
"of your trust. I shall ensure that all these riches, to the last coin, find their "
"way into your coffers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7877f373-2834-4c5b-a56c-4ead5252f344"
msgid ""
"\\\"Look at this.\\\" {n}Kanerah is fiddling with a fine silver snuffbox.{/n} \\"
"\"It's just a small part of the treasures that the workers found in the fort's "
"cellars. The treasure's unpleasant history puts both of us – you as the {mf|baron|"
"baroness|King|Queen}, and me as your Treasurer – in an awkward position.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2eb304b7-3662-4449-a069-71f15c90cb0b"
msgid ""
"\\\"To Millar Fulson from his brothers-in-arms.\\\" {n}Kanerah frowns, reading "
"aloud the text engraved on the lid.{/n} \\\"And all the other treasures are the "
"same. Goblets, silverware, jewelry... Some still tainted with dried blood. "
"Apparently, the Stag Lord stashed away many of the valuables he'd pillaged. And "
"now we must decide what to do with this dark inheritance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f47acb5-370f-4e74-83a1-fe248b3080f0"
msgid ""
"\\\"We can't keep it. If we do, we'll admit we're not a legitimate power, but just "
"another gang of thieves. On the other hand, how are we ever going to find this "
"Fulson and all the other poor victims? How many of them still live? I suggest we "
"use these treasures to restore the villages decimated by the Stag Lord. That will "
"be good for the state, and at the same time will strengthen your reputation as a "
"fair ruler.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b301ed9-5916-4feb-abc8-d74a01c67ed1"
msgid ""
"{n}Kanerah shakes her head.{/n} \\\"Fair, but impractical. Your subjects will "
"appreciate the gesture, of course, but I'm afraid we'll spend more money looking "
"for the owners of these little treasures than they're even worth. Well, I'll go "
"put together an inventory!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1fd43b0-0a7b-4e4f-83b7-b41273649aed"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's the right call. This way you'll be able to present yourself as a fair "
"benefactor to your subjects – and at their own expense!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e14e8c23-7daa-46dd-b6f7-80630e892668"
msgid ""
"{n}Kanerah shakes her head.{/n} \\\"I will do as you say, but I must warn you, "
"you're making a mistake. You'll have enough chances to rob these poor folks. But "
"you shouldn't pass up the chance to buy something that's usually not for sale – "
"their good will.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "400161b0-f163-4e69-9981-7dd232cf00ce"
msgid ""
"\\\"So we'll spend it on restoring the villages. Most importantly, we need to "
"spread the word about this as quickly as possible. Even villages that won't see a "
"single copper of this treasure will hear all about your generosity and fairness!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86da9a1d-c142-4657-b12b-caeff2bdb1f0"
msgid ""
"[Pay 2 BP each week] \\\"I have another proposal. We will lower the taxes "
"slightly, allowing the economy to grow in the future. First of all we need to "
"think about the common people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4889f408-bb07-4453-82ed-53e661813977"
msgid ""
"\\\"We will raise the taxes by one third. I think this will be a fair solution.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "397d5680-cb4b-4ccf-b32b-1a44cdc2d0ee"
msgid ""
"[Gain 2 BP each week] \\\"Let us double the taxes. The barony needs all the money "
"it can get.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed518616-a9f7-41bf-b55e-52e0ba6d0090"
msgid "\\\"I trust you. Do as you deem right.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2287085-f7a8-43f4-b713-be9e46fca2ac"
msgid ""
"[Pay 3 BP each week] \\\"I like this idea. Let us announce a mandatory work "
"initiative, and lower the taxes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3e82573a-2055-4e7b-a2db-b07eb905e5f7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}! I hope you are in a good mood. We "
"need to discuss a rather unpleasant matter...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b6811785-f5fb-4377-b43b-1fcaef5934f8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your {mf|barony's|barony's|kingdom's|kingdom's} expenses have increased "
"several times recently. Construction, clearing lands, urban beautification – all "
"of this requires resources. And we don't have the revenue to match. The only thing "
"we can do is raise taxes. Of course, your subjects won't like it, no matter how "
"much money you demand.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51e1bf47-ed8f-4551-97a9-967effacd5ba"
msgid ""
"{n}Maegar strokes his beard thoughtfully.{/n} \\\"Although... there may be another "
"way out. We might avoid any unpleasantness, if instead of money you introduce... "
"let's call it a mandatory work initiative. The people will be required to work for "
"the betterment of their community. They won't be as irate if they see their work "
"is directly for their own benefit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b09dd4c-ca82-49de-8066-fa6c4559fc7b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}! Let's not beat around the bush: you "
"and I simply must discuss taxes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6505c456-f5e7-4f05-8eb5-2930ca744199"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't know how often you go to the treasury, but I go quite often indeed, as "
"my service requires. Well, there is less and less money in your coffers, while the "
"demands of the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} keep growing. We simply must "
"raise taxes, whether your subjects like it or not.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3669ff40-3ea5-4a4b-b63d-21a199b3ef4c"
msgid ""
"\\\"If I were you, I would raise the tax modestly. Of course, the treasury will "
"not be replenished quickly, but the people will curse you significantly less.\\"
"\" {n}Jubilost grins.{/n} \\\"Which means you may remain on the throne "
"significantly longer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6325daa1-a23a-4a67-92dc-5d9303e6eb1d"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, it is good to see you "
"so well! I come to you with a delicate and urgent matter. Your {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom} is in dire need of money, and I have come up with the perfect way "
"to raise it: introduce an additional tax.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55a29cc2-7737-4264-9aa4-824a0068e604"
msgid ""
"\\\"Mark well my words: unless you raise taxes, the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|"
"kingdom} simply will not survive. No matter what you decide, you will have to "
"increase the taxes. We can hardly expect the peasantry to understand this "
"necessity, but their understanding is not required. As for me and your other "
"attendants involved in the country's finances – we will fully support you in your "
"decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3eb35f5f-0553-4e05-8f06-57c9f672fa11"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you are interested in my advice, I am in favor of high taxes. Your {mf|"
"barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} will thrive, and people will keep busy – working "
"hard to gather the required sums by the required dates. But of course, the "
"decision is yours.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac620373-0793-4c98-accd-b9aba4248181"
msgid ""
"\\\"At least you are not taking the shirts off their backs. Very well, I shall "
"execute your order, {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "974d1361-e46d-4ad7-bae9-19635b0a3c0c"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost adjusts his glasses.{/n} \\\"It does my heart good to see how "
"reasonable and patient you can be. Believe me, in such a situation this is the "
"best possible decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "679b858e-7391-4abf-ae7e-5f4e4578fad8"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost cringes, removes his glasses and rubs his eyes.{/n} \\\"Mark my words, "
"{mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}, your love for easy money will not serve you well "
"in the end. Very well, where was I... ah, right, I must go execute your orders. If "
"you will excuse me...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ead4527-c0c9-4e61-98de-61f5a53c1c0a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Right, I'm not here for decoration. I will raise taxes modestly, but not more "
"than the people can bear. – And you will thank me later for my far-sightedness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "448cc102-8698-4d77-a9b5-92cf04ae2296"
msgid ""
"{n}Maegar nods solemnly.{/n} \\\"A fair decision, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}! I shall make all the necessary arrangements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c81081f-9fb5-49df-87c1-738df78ce482"
msgid ""
"{n}Maegar shakes his head.{/n} \\\"I admit, this is not the decision I expected. "
"Do you not fear riots, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}? I "
"strongly suggest that in the future you give greater concern to the needs of your "
"subjects.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "783df9e3-6eb1-49f6-b5f4-d2187e400a6b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I will "
"immediately announce the establishment of your work initiative.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cbef6a5c-37eb-4bbe-a6e7-6f0e3663ed4a"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew's face darkens.{/n} \\\"And who will remain most concerned with the "
"treasury, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}? Apparently, I "
"myself am the only one who concerns himself with such trifles, and you seem most "
"dismissive of my apprehensions.\\\" {n}The Treasurer bows solemnly, abruptly "
"ending the conversation.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91d7df71-9f2b-44f7-bdde-37010bff88b5"
msgid "\\\"Well, it's better than nothing. I shall instruct our tax collectors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eef0aebc-1634-46c9-9bd1-4886aedf477f"
msgid ""
"{n}Your words make Bartholomew smile.{/n} \\\"You have made the right decision, as "
"usual. Rest assured: soon, our coffers will once more overflow with gold!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a3594895-032d-4722-9266-120fed262c55"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I am glad to be worthy "
"of your trust. I shall double the taxes and ensure the treasury wants for nothing."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f24dbb8f-20cd-4041-b679-befd9adddac7"
msgid ""
"{n}Maegar nods gratefully.{/n} \\\"I am pleased I can be helpful to you, and take "
"care of your subjects at the same time. As I have your permission, I will proceed "
"to make the necessary arrangements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e41c0adc-d175-4ba2-8e43-6b7479882176"
msgid ""
"{n}A sweet smile plays on the tiefling's lips.{/n} \\\"I came to discuss something "
"that rulers love more than the sun in the sky – and subjects hate more than "
"plague. That thing that fills a state with strength, that golden honey that "
"diligent bees carry to their master's treasury... Yes, I'm here to discuss taxes.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2773bb9c-61ec-4ebb-9dd1-dddf56730f25"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nobody has any more doubts that your power is here to stay. No one has any "
"illusions that your throne will be knocked over by the first gust of the wind, or "
"that these lands will ever be open to gangs again. – And that means your subjects "
"are ready to wear the heavy yoke of taxes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4bb1664-d23e-4637-a632-91a1a5eb838a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course, some will grumble, but that's to be expected. We'll first spend the "
"taxes of the obedient on pacifying the ones who rebel. You've done a fine job "
"seizing power – now it's time to enjoy its fruits! I suggest we double the taxes.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31be4c7b-7aa1-49dd-9aae-06a01fe99a29"
msgid ""
"{n}The joy on Kanerah's face dissolves into disappointment.{/n} \\\"I keep "
"thinking about the ordinary people day and night. About what we can afford to take "
"from them, what we should leave them, how to reward the obedient and punish the "
"rebels... While you seem blind to the very nature of power! So be it, I'll abate "
"the taxes, but be warned: excessive kindness ruins rulers far faster than "
"excessive cruelty!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ae7ee5de-de44-4c5d-80b3-fe0fed4acd20"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just a third? Such caution is commendable. Sometimes raising taxes can lead to "
"riots. But believe me, your sheep aren't starving. They have much more wool to "
"give!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f744a170-9c2d-405f-9e4f-cdd5e5de3c55"
msgid ""
"{n}Kanerah's smile grows wider.{/n} \\\"Your words are like a song to my ears. And "
"the clinking of coins pouring into the treasury will be a worthy accompaniment to "
"this song. I think I'll announce we're tripling taxes... And when petitioners pour "
"into court, I'll announce that {mf|His Grace|Her Grace|His Highness|Her Highness} "
"has heeded their words and graciously ordered them only doubled!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b1e39a8-4069-45e2-887e-c2455b4249bd"
msgid ""
"[Pay 100 BP] \\\"I will take the risk. I shall support Leymar's proposal, and "
"invite him to open a shop in our city.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4e4b641-fb5b-4825-836f-cc9c399bd762"
msgid "\\\"I don't care for this risk. Tell Leymar that the answer is 'no'.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7251b8c-329b-4bb7-81bc-4221a3ce5168"
msgid "\\\"You're the Treasurer. Solve this dilemma yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ec711a4-9fd8-486f-8609-1e7fd5ed6910"
msgid ""
"\\\"I hope your intuition doesn't fail you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2aba1a24-4d4e-4266-8661-b5ea303af0a2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I share your opinion, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. "
"I'm afraid we'll have to disappoint our guest.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8eba18b9-923a-440d-ba98-cb4e8249e389"
msgid ""
"\\\"In this case, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I shall "
"go immediately to sir Leymar and refuse his request in the most polite way I can.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c866361-cf42-4ae8-8c86-1e6768175e46"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, it is my honor to "
"introduce Leymar Tinch, an expert on alcoholic beverages, who has traveled here "
"from distant lands.\\\" {n}Bartholomew frowns, apparently trying to remember the "
"name of Leymar's native country.{/n} \\\"This... sir insisted on speaking to you "
"in person, and I decided no one better could explain his request.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d1ff3108-075d-47ee-be26-ea1c9f30d8c3"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've brought a petitioner with me, Leymar Tinch – a famous expert on "
"everything regarding alcohol and the beverages which feature it. Our impatient "
"guest wanted very much to speak with you in person, and tell you all about his, "
"ahem, 'project'.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61ab15f8-57dd-40fd-b5e7-04bececcb9c2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just like that, without considering the risks? Of course, it's entirely up to "
"you, {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}, although I'd remind you that the money "
"belongs to the state.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "735eda41-6b69-443b-b197-23688704ccbd"
msgid "{n}Jubilost silently nods in response.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bda490ed-aef0-4be1-bad5-2aa6dbbee2ad"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you thought you might change my mind by inviting me to decide, I'm afraid "
"you were mistaken. I shall refuse Leymar's request straight away.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c859c0f8-68af-46bf-aa20-c6305101d207"
msgid ""
"\\\"Is that so? Very well. Let's hope the number of halflings in your lands "
"doesn't drop significantly.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b70d577d-47df-4178-add9-450637e6e4fa"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd be happy to, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88690ad6-6f76-4afe-afe1-677591683f0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for your trust, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. I shall invite sir Leymar to leave – first the castle, and then the "
"city.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f29242b8-6294-472e-8e6c-d12e1fd3c948"
msgid ""
"\\\"Allow me to introduce Leymar Tinch, a well-known distiller and a renowned "
"potion-maker. Sir Tinch insisted on a personal meeting, to present to you his "
"unusual idea.\\\""
msgstr ""
"레이마르 틴치를 소개합니다, 저명한 증류주 생산자이자 유명한 표선 제조자입니다. 틴"
"치 경은 개인적인 만남을 요청했습니다. 당신에게 자신의 아이디어를 소개하기 위해서요."

msgctxt "48cca431-bace-458b-840f-34c45a1223c5"
msgid ""
"{n}The halfling before you looks young, but his sharp eyes framed by slight "
"wrinkles gives away the petitioner's considerable age. Leymar nods politely, "
"sweeping the floor with his beret and showing off an emerging bald spot.{/n} \\"
"\"My respects, {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}! I beg your forgiveness for how "
"boldly I sought our meeting, but I could hardly trust anyone with the fate of my "
"beloved new child – which appeared to me in a waking dream, as I walked your lands."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa8da63d-ed51-47ce-b986-eebfea355729"
msgid ""
"\\\"You see, I was traveling through on my way to {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, when to my "
"surprise I discovering a most curious detail: it turns out that many spicy and "
"bitter herbs, which I and my colleagues use in our work, grow wild in these lands! "
"Wineberry, goatweed, gentian...\\\" {n}Leymar bends his fingers, enumerating the "
"plants, then waves his hands.{/n} \\\"Ah, these names probably tell you nothing, "
"but to me... oh, for me this rich list is like a splendid palette – the foundation "
"upon which a true masterpiece might be built.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d0d4a8d-e11f-48c3-9a7a-0ee6745731fe"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I once imagined "
"settling in {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, but your lands have truly inspired me – and now "
"my greatest dream is to open a shop in this very capital. With a bouquet you can "
"easily gather nearby, I can easily create a new beverage – true ambrosia for any "
"halfling! Only one thing is holding me back: lack of financial resources. I hope "
"that now, upon hearing my request, you and your respected Treasurer will not "
"refuse a humble artisan a little assistance... of course, in exchange for a future "
"percentage!\\\" {n}Leymar bows deeply once again.{/n} \\\"I shall eagerly await "
"your decision!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "900c95c8-ced9-4ffe-845c-e5d0da8a94fe"
msgid ""
"{n}Maegar chews his lip, annoyed.{/n} \\\"Of course it's up to you to decide, but "
"I personally don't trust such moneymakers. 'Ambrosia', 'bouquet'... if he wanted "
"to open a forge or, say, a pottery – why, that's a different story! But how can we "
"say whether this investment is any good at all? What if he gets the money and "
"simply disappears without a trace?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0bde28bb-cb4a-4c43-aa64-874f41f84aeb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you want to hear my opinion? This business will fail. Halfling alcohol is "
"like fruit juice for the other races. It's nothing like your dwarvish stout. You "
"want to take a risk and put your money on halfling drunkards? Well, it's your {mf|"
"barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} and your business. But remember, if you give this "
"trader the money he asks for, then tomorrow there will be ten more at your gate "
"just like him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb2532fa-14dc-4380-8a61-1328183754d5"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew clears his throat.{/n} \\\"If you ask my advice, I would not "
"encourage our citizens to come ask for loans for their crazy ideas. You will "
"quickly lose money, while this character poisons your subjects with his "
"concoctions... Perhaps three and a half halflings will enjoy his fizzy wine, but "
"that will hardly repay your investment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33831537-01f9-4256-b90b-36e17f5610a6"
msgid ""
"\\\"A sure sign of our state's maturity is the long line of entrepreneurs awaiting "
"audience. Each has a project on their minds, and each sincerely believes that the "
"others are rascals and madmen, while their own ideas are magnificent. "
"Congratulations – this is a great moment for your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|"
"kingdom}! The first petitioner is Leymar Tinch, and he has quite a business "
"proposal for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a59a148-4a4b-4466-9627-7fe8501fbd9b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sounds dubious, doesn't it? Nevertheless, I do recommend allocating some money "
"to this endeavor. True, it's unwise to get too involved in risky business, but "
"it's even less wise to forgo it altogether. Most often such projects end in "
"nothing. But the success of one can more than outweigh a dozen or even a hundred "
"failures!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d76ee2a7-66d4-464c-a439-448088dadecb"
msgid ""
"\\\"A wise decision! If our guest's business fails, our losses will be small. If "
"it succeeds, our profits might range from modest to enormous. But most "
"importantly, people like him will continue to come to court. A hundred might have "
"only pebbles in their hands, but the hundred-and-first will bring you a diamond!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cdc2eded-de6a-4fed-b614-ddc83b1bc192"
msgid ""
"\\\"I see you don't like playing dice with fate, and prefer to act when the "
"situation is certain. Very well, it's a sensible approach. But I'm afraid it will "
"be painful when the entrepreneur you turn away rains gold upon one of your "
"neighbors!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cfa106dc-1fe9-4f86-8101-707112e96e70"
msgid ""
"\\\"In this case I will lend sir Leymar the money he is asking for. There might be "
"some risk, but it's justified.\\nEntrepreneurship is the living blood of the "
"state, and you can't avoid taking chances!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5c0c1bc-f050-46c0-bef1-b3b6faa7c321"
msgid "\\\"Order these 'Taxmasters' to stop oppressing our people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58c07098-8f05-46b5-b07d-80fb8e78f853"
msgid "\\\"Let these Taxmasters do their job. Command our guards to assist them.\\\""
msgstr ""
"조세관이 자신의 일을 하게 둡시다. 그리고 우리 경비병들이 그들을 체포하도록 합시다."

msgctxt "f5668be7-bba8-40c4-b0d7-662f537b3edb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Denounce these Taxmasters... in word, but not in act. But let them keep "
"working. But more quietly in the future.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "674f077d-4b9d-41ba-ad91-c16e12c06cfa"
msgid "\\\"Act as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24ee6a6d-3b55-421f-a1c3-ceb291f5e730"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, we have a taxation "
"problem. Or rather, a tax collection problem. The people in these lands are not "
"accustomed to paying taxes. Some try to hide their income from your tax "
"collectors. Others even set their dogs on them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8489783f-c3cc-488e-952b-c1a610a3fc8a"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, your subjects truly are savages. My, how the peasants hate paying "
"their taxes! As if they preferred the Stag Lord's way! When he ran out of gold, "
"he'd just kill everybody in the nearest village and pick the loot from their "
"corpses. But here you come, with your monthly tax collection. And for them it's "
"nothing less than a nightmare!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1d801e1-4772-4731-ab50-640146124738"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, it's despicable! It's "
"bad enough that your subjects evade their taxes. But what's worse – they often "
"attack, beat and otherwise abuse your tax collectors! And this on top of the fact "
"that they, in effect, are stealing right from your treasury!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c1fa554-17f6-4b5e-8362-a943e0c663fa"
msgid ""
"\\\"I shall see to it that the Taxmasters stop oppressing your people. Once your "
"subjects see that you're on their side, they'll be more glad to pay their share of "
"taxes. The key to successful governance, after all, is the affection of your "
"subjects!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cf9827a-952e-4b19-8052-7fd58afbc3f0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I see your strategy. You'd rather be broke, so long as you're loved by the "
"crowd. I sincerely hope your soul is warmed by the happy cheers of these pathetic "
"tax evaders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5acba3d-cf8a-41d4-a6f3-c25dcebf2724"
msgid ""
"\\\"So, you defending those who steal from you, and condemn those who perform "
"their duties? But who will you blame when your tax collectors fail to bring in the "
"money they're charged with collecting? Them? – Or me, perhaps?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5fc02af-44a2-427d-be67-456006f77cad"
msgid ""
"\\\"How sad it is to see you whipping your own subjects to rebellion. They will "
"only rise more steadfast against your authority, and soon we'll be sending our "
"military forces to collect your taxes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ee268b3-e93e-4e7d-98eb-c840ae0ce94e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I understand. The firm-handed approach, the iron rule. Don't be offended, but "
"Razmir is still more hated and feared than you in the {g|River Kingdoms}River "
"Kingdoms{/g}. But you're certainly going in the right direction.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f043dfd7-e019-439f-8b26-2c5bf90d7531"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect. I will appoint guards to escort and assist these Taxmasters. It is "
"good to see how you appreciate your servants' effort. I do hope you will continue "
"to appreciate my own service, as well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f614f102-80ad-402c-8f18-c4248ef19261"
msgid ""
"\\\"I hope you won't be troubled by a touch of hypocrisy. The peasants will hear "
"you denounce Taxmasters, and that message will comfort them. In the meantime, the "
"tax evaders will still be attended to... during the night-time. Quietly. Covertly."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4853fa0f-7ff9-43f1-afd5-4fa6c478249f"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is the reason why more and more people join the Taxmasters. They are "
"followers of {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g}, who hold to the idea that everyone must pay "
"their debt to society. And they do not shy from the use of force, threats – and "
"even blackmail – to collect what debts fall due. They hide their faces behind "
"golden masks, for people detest and fear them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7be5ccb5-7129-449a-8526-b54bc3290f3f"
msgid ""
"\\\"The money flow has increased, but the people have started to grumble. It's "
"certainly no good that some of them are evading taxation. But beating the money "
"out of your citizens will lead them to openly despise you. You must order these "
"Taxmasters to stop oppressing your people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d9d5cce-1591-4aa4-b8b7-991af68a885e"
msgid ""
"\\\"However, your people won't get off so easily. Numbers of them join the "
"Taxmasters, followers of {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} – they regard avoidance of taxes as "
"a major personal offense. These Taxmasters wear golden masks, and go from door to "
"door to beat the gold out of your people... along with their teeth. It is indeed "
"the civilized approach!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea04a9b4-c165-4e60-9872-9d6e735114af"
msgid ""
"\\\"It may be the only way to bring some sort of civilization to this forsaken "
"corner of the world. However, if you allow this to continue, you will surely be "
"called a tyrant! I urge you to act carefully. Address these Taxmasters, and let "
"them know that they have gone too far – but don't disband them altogether. Someone "
"has to collect your taxes, and there aren't many people willing to take this "
"thankless job...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a692c779-ef95-4ec8-9bce-45230ba95bfa"
msgid ""
"\\\"They're so bold as to complain about being caught in the act, and forced to do "
"their duty! Some of your tax collectors have joined the Taxmasters – {g|Abadar}"
"Abadar's{/g} cult, who worship the law and have great respect for the due of all. "
"They regard the payment of taxes as the sacred duty of every citizen. Any violator "
"is forced to pay to the last coin, under threat of force.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75cafa53-4904-4898-bfdf-04e796e73b11"
msgid ""
"\\\"The people are outraged about being robbed. They want us to put a stop to "
"these Taxmasters! If you ask me, though, they're the ones who need your support. "
"The work of the Taxmasters is difficult and dangerous, yet vital to the country!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ed6d398-d162-4b8d-a9ac-327e0e898e70"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know I'm no fan of religious orders, but I must admit that sometimes they "
"can be quite useful. As your state grows, more and more of your subjects follow {g|"
"Abadar}Abadar{/g}, the god of cities, laws and trade. There is now a very useful "
"society among his followers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5822e725-245a-4d15-9094-3e606dbc98f2"
msgid ""
"\\\"They call themselves the Taxmasters. They're a fraternity of tax collectors "
"who are tired of the crowd vilifying them and sometimes even laying their hands on "
"them – all for honestly carrying out their duties, while demanding the same from "
"others! They hide their faces behind golden masks, and teach lessons of obedience "
"to those who attempt to evade taxes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f108996c-85b1-487d-a35a-63acd430c418"
msgid ""
"\\\"The common people complain of their cruelty – as if your servants are to blame "
"for the crowd failing to appreciate your kindness! These people are true patriots "
"and your most loyal subjects. You should reward them, or at least honor them in "
"words. Or better yet – assign your guards to assist them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c2bc086-a177-4d4c-8be6-229517c66643"
msgid ""
"\\\"I can't believe my ears! You want to insult people who endure curses and "
"spitting every day, at risk to their health and even their lives, that your "
"treasury may remain full? And for who? Ungrateful parasites who despise you and "
"your power, who enjoy your patronage but try to evade their own responsibilities? "
"This is madness. You're digging a hole under your own throne with your very hands!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a4ea8cc-d5fc-4dea-816f-c3be8c815052"
msgid ""
"\\\"I admit, when you offered me the treasurer's position, this was not how I "
"imagined this job. I knew that it's ungrateful work, that I would have to endure "
"the hatred of the crowd who clutch their purses tightly... But I didn't expect "
"that I'd be stonewalled at every step of the way by my own {mf|baron|baroness|King|"
"Queen}! Are you trying to ruin your country? Well, it's your right, but don't "
"expect me to help you. This is the end. I resign!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f26de21d-c456-46c2-a92d-35bdc099c364"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well. It is good that we value such people. They are the backbone of the "
"country, after all! They may be surrounded by weaklings who only care about their "
"own interests, but they voluntarily offer you their shoulders, because they know "
"that rock-solid governance is good for everyone. I will prepare a letter of "
"commendation on your behalf, and allocate some guards to assist them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f16537e4-7d99-4962-8f1b-06541d7335f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"The shadow trade must be put to an end. I command the establishment of proper "
"customs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d43f4662-5eb9-41ad-ac23-8d1ca191ae0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let's leave things as they are. Order our guards to stay away from captains "
"carrying suspicious cargo.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7daaefb6-4af4-423e-b088-3848620ea51d"
msgid "\\\"It is up to you to decide.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f81bb9a-63fa-4087-bb05-b17996f6f78b"
msgid ""
"\\\"When you offered me this position, {name}, I truly believed that you "
"appreciated my financial skills. Alas, now I see you only seek to argue, and act "
"as you see fit! I shall fulfill this order at your command, but then, with regret, "
"I must quit my position and take up some other occupation.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89c3aec9-08b7-46b0-b6e5-484ebdedbbbb"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I beg your advice. I "
"too was a baron once, so I know full well how difficult it is to rule the {g|"
"Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. This is a land of pirates and bandits, where "
"shadowy sorts deal in stolen and smuggled goods. Now that you've brought order to "
"these lands, this trade has surely decreased... but not as much as we should like."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c805a34-6751-4094-8a86-8d179bee5afa"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, it's time we discuss one of the gravest problems of the {g|River "
"Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}: piracy and all the crimes which accompany it. You "
"see, for decades the illegal trade of stolen goods flowed among the criminals and "
"corrupt merchants of these lands. Now that we have guards in the harbors and along "
"the roads, this illegal traffic has slowed... but only somewhat.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48a0090b-6bf7-468c-883d-4a96c1b5da92"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I'd ask you to address "
"an important issue. You see, the harbors of the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/"
"g} are traditional locations for trafficking goods that are... not entirely legal "
"– which is to say, stolen or smuggled. Even now we still see much of this, though "
"less than before your rule.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69983992-6618-467d-9d00-960c88cb7854"
msgid ""
"\\\"Once we expel those traffickers, our domain will no longer be seen as a safe "
"haven for pirates. Were I ruler, I should do the same.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "268f7ed5-c62f-4afa-8397-265961ef2921"
msgid ""
"\\\"So, we shall put an end to the illegal trade of stolen goods in these lands. "
"What music to my ears! You heed my advice, proving that my labors to elevate this "
"territory have not been wasted! I shall endeavor in my next book to explain how "
"important it is for every wise advisor to work with a leader who knows better than "
"to interfere.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "481038e3-deb5-4cf2-9f0a-64f848da3bed"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew speaks softly, choosing his words carefully.{/n} \\\"I expected "
"more... pragmatism of you. There was no suggestion that you become a pirate "
"yourself! These goods have already been... taken. They're bound to be sold "
"somewhere or other. There's nothing dishonorable in that. We simply want this "
"business to proceed on our land, not on our neighbors' – that's our only concern. "
"Oh well... I only wish there was some way to profit by your honesty...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca613bd1-0adb-4659-bd01-bcfb42cb465d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... I see. I can't say I approve. The bandits will pay handsomely for the "
"right to sell their goods in your harbors – of that I'm quite sure. But soon "
"enough, those who they plundered will come seeking revenge. They'll find your "
"harbor crawling with robbers – any may simply burn the lot to the ground, along "
"with the river pirates too.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba8b834c-758f-4edc-bd24-05100d063504"
msgid ""
"\\\"I see. {kingdomname}, a charming remote province, peaceful and serene. No one "
"knows much about it, or cares for that matter. What need do we even have of "
"reputation, relations with major merchants, or interstate trade? That would ruin "
"your whole image of a tranquil picturesque backwater where robbers freely sell "
"each other's stolen livestock!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c95c64a-70eb-43c8-af6c-3141804477e9"
msgid ""
"\\\"A fine solution. Of course, we shan't tarnish our reputation. The sale of "
"stolen and smuggled goods is far beneath us. Only 'legal' goods will be allowed in "
"our harbors. But we won't be too querulous about it. So long as the proper fees "
"are paid, the goods are considered legitimate, whatever their original source "
"might have been.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29f6d0ee-2b7b-40c7-84ff-698d94399198"
msgid ""
"\\\"One might call it a boon – lawless captains bringing their fortunes here. But "
"it's worth remembering that their money is covered in blood. Should we become "
"their partners in crime? Or should we instead establish proper customs and expel "
"these traffickers from our harbors?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee9789a1-185a-4432-9e9f-545a6ba9d82a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Someone else might suggest you take advantage of the situation: simply collect "
"your fees and don't ask too many questions about the blood these goods are soaked "
"in. But as a traveler far and wide, experience has taught me that real wealth only "
"gathers where there's no robbery or smuggling. The major trade unions won't want "
"to deal with one who promotes piracy. I warn against tolerating things as they now "
"stand. Establish proper customs in your harbor, and hunt down these lawless "
"captains.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b8d00bd-c49d-4b76-bd2a-754c2c65c6bb"
msgid ""
"\\\"The merchants fear that you might yet put an end to their shady dealings, that "
"the customs authorities and guards might grow increasingly stricter and less "
"forgiving. But if we stay faithful to the unwritten laws of the land, this would "
"go far in dispelling their fears. You wouldn't want to make matters difficult or "
"meddle in their established routines, would you? What does it matter where the "
"goods come from, so long as we receive our fees? They're not making things "
"difficult for us, so let's not make things more complicated for them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0aa8fb1-fb86-4954-89b6-6b0e4664affc"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've put off this conversation for a long time, but I can't do it any more. "
"It's time we discuss a vice that's tormented your country from the moment of its "
"creation. – A vice as beneficial as it is devastating. I'm referring to the black "
"market which thrives in your lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c122a69-0f95-4916-96e6-a632aa6b2f45"
msgid ""
"\\\"Since I took the position of Treasurer, I've dedicated myself to strengthening "
"the legitimacy of your power. I've worked day and night so that no one would dare "
"say that you're just another in the long line of bandit lords that have tormented "
"these lands. But what legitimacy are we talking about, if our trading ports are "
"open to pirates, fences, and smugglers?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f530901-8b11-423e-b729-738bd5a8f206"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes, clandestine trade does bring a lot of gold into the treasury. However, "
"your good name is easily sold – but impossible to buy back! If you allow pigs and "
"vultures at your table, how can you expect people of honor to sit next to them? "
"For the future of your country, I urge you to place customs houses in the ports – "
"and put an end to the black market once and for all!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5961914b-a995-4aac-b620-7456dfe8a837"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will go immediately to organize customs. That's the decision of a true "
"sovereign, whose country will stand not for days and weeks, but for years and "
"ages! Don't give any thought to your lost profits. – Whatever we lose by chasing "
"away thieves and bandits, we'll regain a hundredfold from deals made with worthy "
"partners.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "111043b2-396f-43c1-89ab-7852cb5cb242"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're wrong if you think gold has no odor. Believe me, by accepting dirty "
"money today, you take on the reek of sewage for years to come. Don't be surprised "
"if no one wishes to shake hands with you tomorrow!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1f64e3a-e64e-4043-b1c1-3b3af01daf0f"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know, {name}... As much as I struggle to keep your domain from economic "
"collapse, you – you make every effort to stymie me at every turn! This might seem "
"all in good fun to you. Indeed, it's not like a provincial ruler has anything "
"better to do than make a fool of a famous traveler. In fact, I've got an idea for "
"a new book, and I can't presently afford the luxury of wasting my time on useless "
"debates and unheeded advice. I'm sure you can easily find a more flexible "
"Treasurer once I am gone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad74c77f-2c99-4390-9e87-3f1151c36d18"
msgid ""
"\\\"I fear it's time I bring my service to an end. There is simply no way for me "
"to continue my work as your Treasurer. Our views on the future of the country are "
"far too divergent. I cannot stand silently by and observe what it's to become.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4df90be5-3778-4f46-8fb6-be771880a382"
msgid "\\\"Let the merchants pay fees only when importing luxury goods.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bcc376e-2ca4-4e05-bb39-c827cb665147"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let the merchants pay fees on luxury goods and materials for craftsmen.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50752019-6653-4ff9-a48b-9f7d8dbfc108"
msgid "Assigned taxes on all kinds of goods."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff9d041a-5488-4530-b1ea-bd05c57168ff"
msgid "\\\"Everything, every single item to the last apple, will be taxed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "505f7adb-823e-4bca-a061-ed8095ff6f42"
msgid "Abolished taxes according to the River Freedoms."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8a3cbcf-d030-4d9e-9b4c-05a2e6cd2b27"
msgid "\\\"There will be no taxes. I honor the River Freedoms.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "367cb5f3-a39a-4cd1-85f8-09f16487fc48"
msgid "\\\"How should I decide? I will leave this to your capable judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b82ddfb6-fd30-48d2-92ce-68265ae73807"
msgid ""
"\\\"A trade guild is a great idea! If you manage to create one, everyone will "
"honor you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f068145-866e-4e71-a094-c0db419c6e5a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, before this country became a kingdom, {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} used "
"to collect taxes from all merchants entering our lands. But now this gold is "
"rightfully yours. When I was a baron, I didn't oppress the merchants too much. My "
"advice is that you only tax those who sell luxurious things, and leave the "
"craftsmen and townsfolk alone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "adb9ee32-6b1d-4cef-a69d-49f0d8f152bd"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, the movement of goods through our lands continues to grow. It's time "
"we exercised your right to charge fees and taxes on merchants who enter your "
"borders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7e9e857f-8bd5-4efd-9be2-2c8fb8638472"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness! The movement of goods through our lands is growing! – And our "
"independence from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} means that we may now collect taxes from "
"the merchants who enter these lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1140cae1-0c88-4a3b-a299-ac252125cb64"
msgid ""
"\\\"Merchants will be happy to visit us, and our subjects will be able to buy "
"goods cheaply easily. They will grow wealthier, and at the same time, your tax "
"base will grow. This is how we make up for the taxes we didn't charge the "
"merchants! It is a wise solution. I would do the same.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea37582e-cafe-4b7e-8ead-344ac15f2a12"
msgid ""
"\\\"So that's how you want it. All right then. At least it will make the people "
"happy. Perhaps that's even more important than a few extra coins.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b874a7d-7a22-4f49-84a5-033392285f9b"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew purses his lips.{/n} \\\"As if only wealthy people have money! "
"What's the point of my efforts to save every penny, if you just cast hundreds of "
"coins out the window?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b16c212-2dba-4189-b24d-20d9458d9289"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, perhaps that's the best solution, indeed. The taxes we'd collect on "
"materials are too great to pass up. The treasury will always be empty without this "
"money. At least it won't harm the interests of the ordinary people. I like this "
"decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42258ade-100e-4c59-b600-9dbd7ca830d3"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost nods approvingly.{/n} \\\"I can see you like reasonable solutions, and "
"do not stray to the extremes. This is commendable.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6d7de18f-d27b-4289-8d2b-91ca480430b0"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew calculates something pensively, then smiles lightly.{/n} \\\"That "
"might be even better. The merchants will pass through our territory just to avoid "
"our neighbors. We'll collect less gold, it's true. But our neighbors won't get a "
"penny! That is the essence of being wealthy! – If you have more than your "
"neighbors, you are feared and respected. This is a very sensible decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "996de7dd-1b81-46ad-8a17-f5268e5151c5"
msgid ""
"\\\"You can't treat the rich and the poor the same! You just can't! This is how "
"you devastate your people!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c05a4a8-5054-43eb-94ef-a1b9f0009af6"
msgid ""
"\\\"You think that's the way to get more money, but that's not how it works. You "
"will reduce the volume of goods imported into your lands. On the other hand, the "
"coffers will fill more...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e139c874-20fe-4b5b-9202-2ad052e7ca9d"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is an excellent solution! I swear we will have to expand the treasury to "
"fit all the riches we'll soon have in our coffers!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7be6cceb-c082-4630-b5b5-48331cc45365"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll tax only luxury goods, and leave all else be. Needless greed would "
"undermine trade in our lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d1b4378f-63fc-4edb-b1a0-5c334542b207"
msgid ""
"\\\"We will levy taxes on goods for the rich and for artisans, thus ensuring that "
"everyone takes a reasonable stake.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "037030e5-ccb1-42db-925d-b27064b9669f"
msgid ""
"\\\"We won't let a penny slip by. Everything that the merchants bring to our "
"territory will be taxed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "03ac5884-7788-4d31-a5a6-45478ab002ca"
msgid ""
"{n}Maegar scratches his chin.{/n} \\\"You've made a very generous and noble "
"decision. The people will appreciate it. But I hope you have some idea how you'll "
"fill the treasury.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22be1948-bb30-4330-a7e6-101d1cb5ef03"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost smiles slightly.{/n} \\\"You think you're that crafty? Building your "
"first kingdom without duties or taxes? You know, these are bold fantasies, best "
"stored as far away from your head as possible. I've got a special notebook for "
"them. You should have one, too.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "952a62df-ee26-4141-bdb0-99a3b1dca07b"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew's eyes widen. He moves his lips, as if trying to utter a sound.{/n} "
"\\\"But how... Why... You're stealing from your own pocket! From your own "
"treasury! Don't you need gold? Why do you even need a Treasurer then?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47df4349-900b-4a5b-8461-57400d913fb8"
msgid ""
"\\\"In the past, {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} has exercised this right, but now it's in "
"your hands. You only have to decide what to levy taxes on. I recommend you to "
"steer to the middle course. Do not oppress the merchants too greatly. Do not "
"believe their complaints and claims of poverty either."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ddd3b1a-b00f-4ca3-8c92-d2e4a82280b6"
msgid ""
"\\\"You should place a tax on goods for the rich, and on craft materials for "
"artisans. They both have enough income to survive these taxes without going "
"bankrupt. Certainly you're free to dismiss my advice. After all, what's the word "
"of a famous traveler who's seen so many countries and watched how they prosper...\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f846d416-637b-4bb8-ae26-573bc3e85419"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's a fortune flowing through our lands into other countries. I recommend "
"we don't miss this opportunity, and fill the treasury as quickly as we can. And I "
"suggest we don't quibble over details, and simply levy taxes on everything.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6da3a2b6-6159-418a-b520-8a1a8b30133b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Any gold that an artisan saves will enter circulation anyway. It will be used "
"as material to produce goods. Any hold saved by the townsfolk will go into "
"circulation too. – They'll use it to buy goods. Whereas the money of a wealthy "
"person will be invested in useless trinkets, which will sit in their mansion "
"collecting dust. – Not doing any good to anyone!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "693f314d-0850-45b0-a5da-d200f4e61b86"
msgid ""
"\\\"A kingdom...\\\" {n}The tiefling savors this word like candy melting on her "
"tongue.{/n} \\\"Yes, you now have a real kingdom. Your entire capital was once "
"worth less than the goods now flowing through your ports! It's about time to "
"reform the tax system, before we start looking like hapless guests at a feast, "
"hungrily eying the most delicious dishes as they're carried past!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "03b4096c-b576-4273-98b9-c274eeab0181"
msgid ""
"\\\"Although one mustn't give way to greed either. Luxurious items for the "
"wealthy, materials and tools for craftsmen, and simple goods for the common folk – "
"all of these are different things, and it would be unwise to tax them equally. "
"I'll prepare a detailed draft of the reform... But first, listen to my proposal.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b130b86-698e-44c7-b8dd-f6b4fe157caa"
msgid ""
"\\\"Allow me to found our own royal trade guild in our lands. Its members will "
"enjoy lower taxes and extended rights... But membership would have to be earned! I "
"will make every merchant go out of their way to ingratiate themselves with us, and "
"demonstrate that doing business with them is highly profitable for the crown. Just "
"think what opportunities this will open!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6c60dbe-3bed-4010-8cb6-fc01adba1101"
msgid ""
"{n}Kanerah smiles sweetly.{/n} \\\"Very wise, as usual. I will create a royal "
"trade guild, one that will be the envy of all, from Galt to Numeria.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d33b9006-4e5e-4808-a1aa-c6508e509697"
msgid ""
"\\\"Taxes on luxuries are important, but you shouldn't underestimate the profits "
"that less refined goods can bring to the treasury. There's a lot of meat in a "
"single buffalo, but far more in ten thousand rabbits!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "00903790-badc-458b-a91c-1991d2399778"
msgid ""
"\\\"Both the wealthy and craftsmen are excellent sources of income, but they are "
"greatly outnumbered by the poor. It's unwise to deprive the treasury of their "
"copper! And don't hope that the common people will thank you for low prices. Most "
"of them are blind as moles. They imagine that they themselves are the ones to "
"thank for securing their well-being, and only thank their {mf|baron|baroness|King|"
"Queen} for their troubles!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6759bb78-46d4-4267-8d3f-c117a8781b70"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course. Well, if my idea for a trade guild doesn't appeal to you, I will "
"work on drafting a new customs code. It will require pinpoint precision. We'll "
"have to shave as much wool from each sheep as it can give – not more, but not less!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ea48f37-0a84-4cd3-8592-a6e6d24c9627"
msgid ""
"{n}The smile on Kanerah's face turns into a grimace.{/n} \\\"This is madness. I'm "
"serving an insane {mf|king|queen}. After this, I won't be surprised if you decide "
"to walk around the streets naked, appoint an owlbear as head of government, or "
"execute anyone who has more than three cats at home.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49c0ece2-cd97-4d10-af93-a12ae6b993c2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd be happy to enter a trade agreement with the citizens of wealthy "
"Daggermark.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32b24945-3e7c-4822-b8fb-0c9d1e9b717d"
msgid "\\\"Let them go home. We've no interest in their offer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8e1444b7-3cf9-4d80-b3d7-9941a6dd966c"
msgid "\\\"I trust your advice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b1d3e0e-978e-495c-b1a9-9db9af6d20ae"
msgid ""
"\\\"A sales representative of several trade houses in Daggermark has arrived at "
"your court. They are interesting in trading in our domain. They offer us fair "
"compensation for a trade agreement, but I wouldn't hurry to trust their siren "
"songs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a84fbf18-9e7e-4730-916a-ed910bf607f4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, an ambassador of trade union in Daggermark has arrived at your "
"court. The union is asking for permission to trade in our domain. They are willing "
"to pay a generous fee.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6af31095-49ac-4659-b19d-2be87e9ab225"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, a sales representative of Daggermark has arrived at your court. "
"They seek to make a trade partnership. But know that Daggermark has its own "
"traditions. Everything can be bought and sold. Perhaps some of the local merchants "
"will have a difficult time alongside such neighbors. But we will profit greatly "
"from Daggermark's offer, and continue collecting a reliable income in the future. "
"I see no reason to say no.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "628b151e-407f-4ec9-9e63-fbc6d542cc71"
msgid ""
"\\\"It seems like a bad idea. I have little doubt that the first thing these "
"newcomers will do is use threats and blackmail to suppress the local merchants. "
"The very merchants who rely on our support and protection!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65d67a26-6d13-49ef-999d-f681b744cbf9"
msgid "\\\"It's a brave choice. We'll see what this risky cooperation brings us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b741c846-5bf8-4552-b1d5-59ad87403ae1"
msgid ""
"\\\"This trade agreement will connect us to a large and powerful trade network. "
"This means that anyone who menaces us also jeopardizes Daggermark's commercial "
"interests. Believe me, your Highness, Daggermark knows a thing or two about "
"safeguarding their interests!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca415c35-73b4-4868-9ffa-3c34159fdb86"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will send them away at once. We can do without street gangs, smuggling, "
"bribery, kidnapping, and all the other lovely gifts of these Daggermark "
"'businessmen'. If the tragedy hadn't struck my domain, I'd have loved to neighbor "
"a kingdom led by so wise a ruler as you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bb3c5c4-e4a1-4c7d-9219-19938263de0a"
msgid ""
"\\\"You must remain sober, and never play with someone more skilled in shuffling "
"the deck. You don't want to be taken by a cardsharp, right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a6c622e-155a-49c0-a5d9-ceb2ca4308b4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why? Do they employ unethical methods? Why should we care? You trusted me with "
"your treasury. I'm trying to make it grow, and you simply won't let me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12864688-4016-41f8-ae76-bd833c211e1a"
msgid ""
"\\\"What they truly want is to ruin our merchants – to replace them, and lay down "
"their own rule. The rule of urban bandits with sharp blades and deadly poisons. "
"But they are a strong community. They stand united and support each other. If you "
"make a decision that is not to their liking, they won't hesitate to pressure you, "
"or cause trouble. In any case, I strongly advise against this dangerous offer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b3dc6b7-f1d8-44f7-a797-7c7201cb7ed2"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's worth considering who we are dealing with. In Daggermark, your power and "
"privilege depend directly upon the weight of your coinpurse. Whereas leaders of "
"other countries often surreptitiously act as profiteers and bandits, it's through "
"profiteering and banditry that rulers in Daggermark rise to power. – And to be "
"clear, the city is thriving.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06687d8e-a850-406d-b431-c047b5e66e1c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I often hear praise of the intelligence and business acumen of Daggermark's "
"citizens, but never any praise of their honesty or ethical perspective. It's up to "
"you to decide who you make deals with, but I don't mind playing this little "
"business game we've been offered.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a8b92521-a82c-4800-8c80-064634d3cae7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will grant our consent to Daggermark's representatives. We'll see who's "
"craftier.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1d52a04-6baf-4c75-9269-0db4fc3cf75b"
msgid ""
"\\\"A messenger from the Daggermark trading houses has arrived at court. They're "
"requesting permission to trade on your lands. His words are sweet, but not like "
"honey. – Rather more like the sickening sweetness of rotting meat.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "534c8d1d-9deb-4673-bb49-aac56c03df19"
msgid ""
"\\\"Daggermark is an ugly travesty of a state. A den of thieves and thugs, where "
"you can easily buy a life – or lose your own for a handful of gold. Yes, "
"Daggermark does possess money and goods. But they also have a reputation!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c426706-5e90-4eaf-8f33-e67fbcb318ea"
msgid ""
"\\\"If they do come to your dominions, do not hope that they'll conduct their "
"business peacefully – oh no! They'll begin by imposing their own rules. And like "
"plague-stricken rats, they will spread extortion, blackmail, forgery, and a "
"thousand other ailments throughout our country! Is that worth the profits they "
"promise?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30dd2d99-61ed-4904-8021-41f72fbd5bfd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wealth comes in different forms. Sometimes neighbors build it together, "
"enriching each other. Some decimate each other instead. An agreement with "
"Daggermark will definitely bring much profits... But to whom? Think about it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5519111-07bc-4693-b37b-c2b89d457c2a"
msgid ""
"\\\"A wise decision. I think I won't insult our dear guests with outright refusal. "
"– We don't want these respected businessmen to bring their assassins' knives into "
"the capital. I'll tell them we're ready to deal, and then propose such terms that "
"they'll have no choice but refuse. They'll soon go back where they came from of "
"their own volition.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57b6bfba-3c8f-4cb6-84f6-1f261d99cb97"
msgid "\\\"Start producing these coins.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b955129c-68c5-4b1d-85b3-e0537dde4b37"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let's avoid the expense. Besides, seeing my face on every coin would drive me "
"crazy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a07e4cfc-0d85-4345-9801-d5db1eaa0936"
msgid "Ordered the minting of deficient coins."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "432cb455-6d9d-44c5-9bab-5e63191aa0ed"
msgid "\\\"Do what you offered. You know what I mean.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca2e156c-4f54-4fd0-bbd7-0049854007c9"
msgid "\\\"Decide it yourself. After all, you're the Treasurer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "198ff968-e766-4e89-8eae-701c607bb23a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I like your plan. Let's start minting coins, and order that taxes can only be "
"paid using them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a8b32631-0b26-48bb-bcee-cd3eb71e4d2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, a couple of Daggermark swindlers were arrested at the city "
"market. They were paying with coins from their own country. There was "
"significantly less gold in the coins than there was supposed to be. The coins "
"turned out to be cut by nearly a quarter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94349c70-66e5-4c95-93a5-0551f371dfcd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your citizens are grateful to you, {name}. Thanks to you, their pockets are "
"filled. Strange that it's not me they're thanking. Now that you're a true {mf|king|"
"queen}, why don't we start producing coins with your face on them?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55438c8b-c314-4635-82e3-08904a725976"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, I suppose that your contribution to the history of this once-"
"worthless land is so great that we must perpetuate it. At first, I was thinking "
"about a park, a statue and a couple of fountains, but that's too visionary. Then "
"another idea came into my head. Let's produce coins with your face on them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a0b0bee-72a1-45aa-937c-47ddd3c08ec0"
msgid ""
"\\\"It will be done. This day marks a new milestone in the history of the kingdom!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "deeda486-17eb-4970-8498-0e77f861199e"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost nods approvingly.{/n} \\\"Everything is already in motion. Your "
"decision was so obvious that it hadn't even occurred to me to delay the "
"preparations.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8cb7cce-8933-4c96-b87f-5a93bd4ac9eb"
msgid ""
"\\\"As I proposed?\\\" {n}Bartholomew catches your eye hopefully, but then loses "
"interest.{/n} \\\"I see. Simple coining. Without applying my wise and thrifty "
"advice. Not that you've ever paid attention.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa3860d1-6379-4bca-a655-b9709530b64a"
msgid "{n}Maegar shakes his head.{/n} \\\"Very well, as you please.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ecae5708-0877-4901-8aed-faa3242c1e27"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost takes off his glasses in astonishment and starts wiping the lenses.{/"
"n} \\\"Are you serious? Do you have a phobia or something? A magical disease? I've "
"never heard of anything like it. I'd love to know more, if you don't mind. What "
"about mirrors? Your reflection...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11c8eb1d-2a7f-4fb9-9068-f8a1a45f59c5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Indeed, we shouldn't be in such a hurry. There's always a better use for money."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "050a7649-2832-4d39-be41-0715ba1215f8"
msgid ""
"\\\"For the record, this is the way for us to get our own currency at our "
"disposal, which will have a positive impact on the market due to inflation... "
"You're not listening to me, are you? I'll put it simply. Producing coins does have "
"a price, but it will pay off over time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1ae7660-75e0-4cb4-b7ba-92a49d3134f5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let every one of your subjects remember who to thank for the money they're "
"holding in their hands! You pulled these lands out of poverty! You deserve a "
"reward, don't you? For instance, one tenth of the gold from every coin, which we "
"will secretly replace with copper. This new currency won't pay off right away, and "
"we'll have a significant up-front cost. But don't worry, nobody will notice our "
"little trick.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "450a9581-3aaf-416f-85ac-0c03e979c791"
msgid ""
"\\\"It makes me wonder why we haven't already produced our own coins. One with "
"your face on it, for instance. It's the only way we can be assured that the money "
"of our subjects is intact. It will also send a message to our neighbors that we're "
"someone to reckon with. It will be some expense to set this up, but it will pay "
"off eventually.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76508727-481e-4e02-8f9d-139515f22f8b"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost puts the glasses back on when he catches your expression, and his mood "
"darkens.{/n} \\\"Oh, I see. You're joking. Very funny. Ha. Ha. As if you were so "
"modest. All right, enough chit-chat, I've got things to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "701fffbd-323f-4694-9282-58b060ca19f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"It will be done. Congratulations, Your Highness. You have become a part of "
"history.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e65b7c4-ea00-44cf-a79d-0f6ea8c92af4"
msgid ""
"\\\"I could abuse your trust and stamp out coins with my own face on them. But why "
"should I? My face already decorates several books which are more valuable than any "
"amount of gold!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "123de6ff-fabc-4efc-9a16-b98b2ae6de14"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew winks meaningfully.{/n} \\\"I'm on it, Your Highness. I shall order "
"everything that's required: the coin machine, gold, casts... as well as a "
"grindstone and tin snips.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca74c9ae-2f21-4e51-8464-9c4b822fb8a8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your subjects already celebrate your wisdom and fairness. I think they should "
"also be reminded of your captivating beauty.\\\" {n}The girl smiles coyly.{/n} \\"
"\"It's high time to make everyone in your kingdom carry your portrait with them... "
"A profile minted in gold!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dae2938a-797c-4423-ad9a-6e991ba27fee"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our trade depends too much on the coins of others. Constant rate fluctuations "
"make our money changers rich, at the expense of everyone else. Your country needs "
"its own real currency!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ddc03cf2-d14a-4be5-bf2d-03455c2130de"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have a plan that will make coins decorated with your noble profile far more "
"valuable than the gold they are made of. Soon after minting the coins, we will "
"announce that taxes can only be paid with these coins. Our merchants will be "
"falling over each other, snatching these new coins! What do you say?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b0f9621-cef6-4df5-bdfe-2791c0c827c7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for your trust.. I will give the order to begin minting coins, and "
"prepare the announcement about new tax collection rules. You'll see – a coin with "
"your profile will soon be worth three times its weight in gold!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c17236f-f102-4570-a262-723597f7bbc2"
msgid ""
"{n}Kanerah grows gloomy.{/n} \\\"Well, what is best is often the enemy of what is "
"good. Even without my tax collection plan, our own coins would have been "
"beneficial for the economy, not to mention international prestige. In any case, "
"know this: in your caution, you're passing up a big profit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29e3f62e-4a03-4acb-9767-f04652ea32bc"
msgid ""
"\\\"You have a strange notion of thrift. I suggested minting our own coins because "
"at present your treasury is taking in much less than it could.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a50b3aef-8926-417a-b30e-5c8db37f8a8c"
msgid "\\\"It's not even a question. Spies can do the most good for the army.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8e9d1f1-b87b-4c0d-944b-bbabd96ce350"
msgid ""
"\\\"Spies in embassies and consulates bring in the most valuable information.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "05130b7c-4980-4b7f-bf9e-001074a8b55f"
msgid "\\\"I want spies placed in the guilds and magic schools.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2c4a1ef-6d1b-473a-a9a5-0591b3bb5a89"
msgid "\\\"You're the spymaster. It's up to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5c89a19-ccc8-4a9c-ae9d-f69db31f9ac6"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've done well. We have loyal eyes and ears everywhere. We need not fear "
"spies or conspiracies. Your domain is well protected against all manner of quiet "
"threats.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d3bc47d-198c-47f8-938b-8ce5879b6292"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have recalled our best people to the capital. They will pass on what they've "
"learned about our enemies, and instruct the guards on how to trace conspiracy. "
"Their experience in intimidation and command authority will come in handy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d42eb045-8418-41c2-954b-b309923b1d7a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have recalled our best people to the capital. They're crafty and sly – "
"slippery as eels – and they've learned much from their dealings with our enemies. "
"Make them your ambassadors now. A good spy makes a good politician.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57d0f604-3999-4e72-965d-fe49816bf1c7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Speaking of enemies, our strike hit its target. The Assassins Guild is licking "
"their wounds. Meanwhile, we're seizing their power.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5b1f236-2345-44d9-b792-d872c6835475"
msgid ""
"\\\"Speaking of enemies, our strike hit its target. The Poisoners Guild has gone "
"underground, leaving us to seize their riches.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c6630ad0-42f4-4c55-8969-0606d652a8c3"
msgid ""
"\\\"The attacked Guild had spies in every corner. They need a new master. We have "
"the chance to become that master. But where do we want our spies?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53bb3283-27b3-4be2-a650-afdc748768b1"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know, {name}, our spies finally seem to be everywhere. It's a most unusual "
"experience. Sometimes I feel like a new god. I see everyone! I hear everything!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7bec10e4-a01f-4e76-a6a9-19d7c8cd7de4"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, we received news from Daggermark. We are victorious. I think "
"congratulations are in order. You have an eye in every corner. All secrets of the "
"living and the dead are ours.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc8e6a4e-ff51-4e66-ab85-f7c2b374e2ff"
msgid ""
"\\\"I summoned several of our agents back to the capital. They will share with the "
"guards the expertise they gained in the ruthless struggle against the enemy. This "
"will be good for... let's call it 'conspiracy prevention'.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e343b60-1da5-4c42-bef3-5aa351c165c9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I summoned several agents back to the capital. They will enlighten our "
"ambassadors in intrigue and the art of deception. This expertise will come in "
"handy in their games of politics.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0bf0e25d-a456-4420-951b-9e62b6b2fc89"
msgid ""
"\\\"By the way, do you remember the Daggermark Guild that tried to throw sand in "
"our gears? Our response has the weasels running scared. The Assassins Guild still "
"exists, but it's far less powerful now. Indeed, they're struggling to fight for "
"what little they have left.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "048e2dfb-0644-4de5-a28f-466eec9e1a09"
msgid ""
"\\\"By the way, do you remember the Daggermark Guild that tried to throw sand in "
"our gears? Our response has the weasels running scared. The Poisoners Guild is "
"acting like everything is fine, but the victors are raking off their belongings.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ed112e8-37c2-43bb-9669-8393c0c94400"
msgid ""
"\\\"We want our piece of the pie too, of course! I'm looking forward to getting my "
"hands on the agents who are ready to trade masters. But it's up to you to decide "
"where we should send our new infiltrators.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75fba449-437f-4fc0-a8c3-a234de51688b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I summoned several agents to the capital. The guards could use their "
"experience in their ruthless struggle against the enemy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83f69426-9b3c-4b04-be55-93496319b90d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I summoned several of our agents back to the capital. Our diplomats can make "
"good use of their experience in intrigue and deception.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6418d081-e105-415d-a4a3-13bc83415e72"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you're wondering about our old enemy's fate, don't worry, they're no longer "
"a threat. The Assassins Guild suffered a severe blow. For now they are preoccupied "
"mainly with their own survival. The vultures have already begun to tear apart "
"their possessions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34605022-35fc-4481-86c1-c96ebfb77012"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you're wondering about our old enemy's fate, don't worry, they're no longer "
"a threat. The Poisoners Guild poisoned themselves. They're desperately struggling "
"to stay afloat. Everyone is clawing at their pile of riches, and they can scarcely "
"keep an eye on us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e456e7c3-b71d-48c4-a68c-3e328daffda5"
msgid ""
"\\\"We should claim our prize as well. The Guild had many spies with a variety of "
"skills and areas of expertise. Many of them would surely love to trade masters in "
"these stormy times. But where could we put the new people to greatest use?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a13a8a88-3224-4ef4-a598-ca64918b51e1"
msgid ""
"\\\"It will be good to have ears in the armies of our enemies. It will be done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df546663-f0a4-44b0-958f-a6fb7baf5318"
msgid "\\\"Hmm. This sounds reasonable. I'll make a few inquiries.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b33fe62b-2d29-444f-a456-a12ec39581b0"
msgid "\\\"Knowing about one's enemies makes killing them that much easier.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20810579-d9b8-4620-b872-8720836e9a04"
msgid ""
"\\\"All right. We'll learn what is being discussed in our neighbors' palaces.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f5ca6ff-cb07-4949-976d-0cd3e060a57f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Diplomats are spies with public credentials. The secrets of neighboring "
"monarchs are more valuable than their crowns.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41484f4f-5bf9-4f31-8fa1-5bfb7aa6e84f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sometimes I doubt whether the art of diplomacy even exists. Perhaps it's all "
"just lies and daggers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2a46497-d05a-4d7c-a411-505781c897b0"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun takes a pause to think and then nods.{/n} \\\"You know that I don't always "
"trust magic. But poisons and daggers cannot be our only tools.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d53d2736-95de-4f6c-aac5-3a724eecdd2f"
msgid ""
"\\\"I believe that magic is the future of espionage. This is a wise decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "93ab6b15-dc85-42ec-8c35-07db426e2e37"
msgid ""
"\\\"Mystical secrets are more valuable than military plans or political intrigue. "
"Mortal life is short. Magic is eternal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c13d1a1e-549b-4fbd-9310-01a434b25d83"
msgid ""
"\\\"Speaking of enemies... The Daggermark guild accepted our offer of union. The "
"strike on their rival was unexpected and successful. We get to share the prizes "
"with our new ally.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "509284f9-7440-4f30-8a83-0e47115b21c1"
msgid ""
"\\\"By the way, do you recall when that Daggermark guild tried to throw sand in "
"our gears? Our response encouraged the weasels to change their plans and organize "
"a strike against their rival! Of course, the poor sods didn't expect anything of "
"the sort, so now they're licking their wounds, and their enemies are raking off "
"their belongings.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73059cd8-f787-4949-832d-fb473ef4f775"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you're wondering about our old enemy's fate, then worry not — they're our "
"friends now. After our united strike on their rivals, those old grudges are "
"forgotten — everyone's clawing at the pile of trophies from this unexpected "
"operation while the wounded guild is acting like everything's normal — though it "
"can scarcely stay afloat.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16a6f264-6b90-4441-b8ee-dc4985ce425f"
msgid "\\\"Let the guards watch those who arrived by the caravan.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "042a54cf-b21e-48cc-b177-780e528278ae"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tell the merchants that if they fail to hand over the stranger, we'll seize "
"their gold and goods.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3b36cda0-015f-4348-9e0b-0c4d5cfa1d4f"
msgid "\\\"Put all the merchants on the rack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33bbe335-fb5a-4d04-b5a5-c9f2fdc9de7c"
msgid "\\\"Who, in your opinion, sent the spy?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19c1fe68-b31e-4dd9-9dee-2ad6332c11f9"
msgid "\\\"I trust your opinion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58af3084-25ba-4003-82f1-669afa637c88"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, these lands are like a forest. Everyone is hungry, and all keep "
"constant watch on their predators and their prey. What you need is ears – by which "
"I mean spies. We don't have any yet, but others do. They're planting them among "
"us. I must stay in the shadows, so I can catch them. Don't tell anybody I'm your "
"head of espionage. Simply tell them I'm a minister. Keep it simple.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f19c08c6-11de-44a4-8ade-881e5d901a2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"A crowded caravan has arrived, the kind that often carries illegal goods. The "
"guards searched the caravan and found a stash, but it didn't have potions or "
"artifacts. It contained spying equipment. It's unclear who the spy is, but he's "
"clearly experienced. He had fine tools.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f884afa-53f4-49c1-ae2b-69e8e193fac6"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, surely you realize that once you enter into intrigue, you will attract "
"very close attention. All our neighbors are wondering who we are and how we can be "
"used. And since we're but a quail among hawks, it's essential to be very careful. "
"This is why I'm asking you to keep my doings secret. Introduce me as a minister. "
"Simply a minister.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7dcb3ec-286d-469f-a7da-c6926d064bb8"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, do you know why I find the company of the short-living very annoying? "
"They're in such a hurry to do as many things as they can, that they cause utter "
"chaos. Back in {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}, intrigues are very carefully devised. They're "
"intended to last dozens of years. The plots were elegant and lies exquisite.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "587c2b77-0300-48eb-83b6-7f042a621b0c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I wouldn't be surprised to find actual ears on your palace's walls. Ask me "
"what we found in the merchant's caravan if you don't believe me. A guard "
"discovered a stash for smuggled goods – and a spy's gear was inside. It included "
"very curious mathematical ciphers from {g|Ustalav}Ustalav{/g}. I must admit, they "
"are very elegant.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab127faa-a8c3-450a-994a-6ba5218b3a60"
msgid ""
"\\\"Things are done differently here. For starters, spymasters publicly identify "
"themselves as agents of espionage, all-seeing visionaries... They might as well "
"paint a target on their foreheads. It's not a mistake I would like to make. For "
"your subjects, I shall simply be a minister. You've come to power only recently, "
"and the city is already full of murderers and spies. A guard recently found a "
"stash while inspecting a trade caravan. It didn't contain any smuggled goods "
"except some spying equipment and a few deadly toys. We could identify neither "
"where the package came from, nor to whom it was going. But if you don't want such "
"tools put to use, you must figure out who the spy is.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31b971a0-55dc-4627-9f34-2d89a200ed0e"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun nods.{/n} \\\"I'll order the guards to keep an eye on the merchants.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a70b3d1-a85d-4b88-9670-bf700d22ba71"
msgid ""
"\\\"Phew!\\\" {n}Jubilost raises his eyebrow and puts hands on his hips.{/n} \\"
"\"The solution of someone who loves potboilers! A true spy is a professional! Our "
"people are only amateurs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c13d2f1-0560-41cd-9c16-84f7fdb20a4f"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal looks focused, her voice is as quiet as wind's whisper in the night.{/"
"n} \\\"I hope those fools don't give away the game. It would be safer to arrest "
"everyone involved.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7e8167b2-37f2-4872-925f-30aad137c03c"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun replies after a pause:{/n} \\\"I'd rather it was I who was doing the "
"hunting. But it's good to give the merchants a reason to cooperate. They do love "
"their gold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b9f9d1b-7f71-45b1-ba68-4d64e1dc00e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect. The merchants would rather hand over their own mothers than lose "
"their goods. They traveled a long way here, so they got to know their fellow "
"travelers. They'd recognize a stranger in an instant.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "78380cd7-3ba5-4e6b-b610-ab3ed9bfed59"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal loses interest.{/n} \\\"We've practically caught an enemy spy, and now "
"you entrust the final hunt not to me, but to some smuggler merchants? What a waste "
"of time...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad5dbae9-b65a-4528-8e57-75fddeddc033"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun shakes his head.{/n} \\\"This isn't fair. It's not the others' fault. "
"Tormenting them is wrong.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53e4e6f3-7851-4d35-8ad4-558d40d8a1d4"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost opens his mouth to object, but then changes his mind, nods, and frowns."
"{/n} \\\"Well, it's rough, it's tough, it's something an amateur would do, but "
"it's nevertheless efficient. Like a hammer to the head.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22945702-3634-4aa5-a464-cca433c22330"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll teach them some new ways to feel pain. Only the truth will ease their "
"bodily suffering.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96f3420a-cd63-4667-9c93-4061ab0ec189"
msgid ""
"{n}The ranger shrugs.{/n} \\\"An enemy. A neighbor. An inquisitive mind. We "
"haven't picked up the trail yet. We must keep looking.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8ef1441-2033-4ed3-848e-d89bf7b9aeba"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think of it as everyone at once. All countries are tied together by a chain "
"of intrigue. Some would send their agents because they're scared. Others would "
"send them because someone else did. The third one sends spies to watch the other "
"two. Everything is interconnected.\\\" {n}Jubilost notices your facial expression "
"and sighs.{/n} \\\"We don't know who sent him yet.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0521b5a3-0a2d-483b-9efc-633b693ff1e4"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal's smile is predatory.{/n} \\\"I wonder, too. The name we receive under "
"torture will be real. The others will be fake, just to trick us. So far, all I can "
"say is that it could be any of our neighbors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88dcf305-8263-4f95-aa97-dea48f915022"
msgid ""
"\\\"I could order the merchants to look for a stranger among their servants. But I "
"don't trust money-bags traders. I'd rather charge my people with watching the "
"merchants. Then again, why look for clues when the best proof is evidence by "
"confession? If you bring me the merchants for a couple of hours, the problem will "
"be solved! The rack will make the spy sing like a bird.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0112e59a-bee7-44b4-aeab-23c25cb9bf94"
msgid ""
"\\\"We failed to identify the owner of the package. But judging from its contents, "
"this specialist is dangerous. Our people are helpless against him. They can't even "
"catch their finger before it finds its way up their noses! Trying to track down a "
"spy is out of the question. But you can't torture all the caravan's members – the "
"merchants wouldn't approve of it. So we must tread lightly. We should threaten to "
"confiscate their goods and kick them out. Trust me, they'll give us their "
"information in no time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5754c8eb-c5be-4c73-bd0a-3a821db7cae8"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must catch the spy to track down his master. This is an animal that must be "
"stalked quietly. We'll need a tail on every member of the caravan. But let them "
"keep back. No threats, no torture. There's only one spy. The others are not at "
"fault.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b9645984-4758-49c1-aa00-6a75b55c74a0"
msgid "\\\"Take her friends and family hostage.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a3729ba-fc4f-40fa-8271-165dbe4d393c"
msgid "\\\"Spellbind her.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bff1dbc3-6783-438a-aaa1-d0b6be49674e"
msgid "\\\"Send her in the wrong direction and follow her.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50578337-24ce-4b27-9be5-4b9cc25550e2"
msgid "\\\"Act as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24f4084c-4acf-43da-ab05-eb80dcd55639"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't trust her. She's betrayed one master. She is bound to do it again. We "
"could take her hostage. We could even use magic to probe her mind. But both "
"methods are unreliable, and besides, magic is bad for the brain. I suppose we "
"should set a trap. Let us feed her a lie and see where she takes the bait. Do you "
"understand what I suggest?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f3b95f0-b9bd-4c8d-a25c-676ad3267a74"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm not sure she's under orders to insinuate herself as a double-agent. So I "
"don't think it would help to deliberately feed her lies. But what if she decides "
"to sell us out? Simple greed must never be overlooked. We could take a hostage – "
"someone significant to her. But what if she's not sentimental? The safest bet is "
"advanced magical brainwashing. I couldn't guarantee the security for her "
"personally, however.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5cecf28b-ec93-495d-93d5-e24a04a1b7de"
msgid ""
"\\\"Should we trust her? I for one am not that stupid. She's only worried about "
"her own skin. Loyalty is out of the question. However, it would be short-sighted "
"not to make use of her knowledge. We could use magic to brainwash her and command "
"her obedience, but that is not the most reliable solution. Besides, a couple years "
"later she'd be useless as a dumb vegetable. The best way to control her is to "
"spill blood if she betrays us. The blood of her friends and family. Her obedience "
"can be ensured if we take the right people hostage.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f1ce1ad-b6da-4ee8-ad92-70e592483333"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's cruel, but it might work. We're risking the lives of our people. If she "
"betrays us, she'll be risking lives of her own people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d239b5ea-da8f-4095-a0b6-ce2f0a766775"
msgid ""
"\\\"Trembling in fear for one's family makes for poor spying. You'll make her "
"unpredictable. Irrational. Ultimately, unreliable.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "01b7f045-4d2b-4ef5-a6a8-318262d06db2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect! I'll give her a vivid description of her family's future, if she "
"should choose to betray us. It's going to be a long story.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e39e6a28-d991-4794-ace0-d11f451c5c16"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun frowns and makes an unfamiliar gesture as if brushing off a fly.{/n} \\"
"\"Magic... isn't dependable. Something could go wrong without our even knowing. "
"Our own tool could become the knife that stabs us in the heart.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9446598f-d896-4c8c-a6e1-126018f56916"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will oversee the magical treatment myself. Hopefully it won't affect her "
"mind too much. But I know one thing for sure: after this we won't stand a chance "
"of becoming fellow scholars.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "615a1791-704f-45d3-9b55-03e8a1bbdf7b"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal studies your face.{/n} \\\"Aren't you worried about the consequences? "
"Strange visions? The risk of insanity? Well, at least, you don't have any "
"scruples. That much can be said.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "80edf63c-84d9-4fdd-9a23-4812ead46993"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun nods.{/n} \\\"She's lying to us. We'll have to lie to her. But our lies "
"will be more convincing!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d512f8d9-cc40-4f9d-b810-ebd27e33bd99"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you know, every decent plan must have at least seven layers of lies to "
"cover the truth. Well, maybe this is indeed the best way.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0350b43f-f9e6-4282-989d-33417e25e91d"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal juts out her chin in resentment.{/n} \\\"You're far too cautious. Trust "
"me, your enemies are not sharper or cleverer than I.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13c4bd56-9f59-43d4-a76e-5b9ed2a20542"
msgid ""
"\\\"We arrested a spy – a mercenary from Daggermark. He identified his client for "
"us. But it turns out she wishes to go over to us, and save herself from her old "
"master.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b996cdc8-7e98-4902-887d-a13094682494"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've captured a spy. You'd be surprised to learn where he came from. He's "
"from Daggermark, the capital of espionage and intrigue in the {g|River Kingdoms}"
"River Kingdoms{/g}. My agents were seeking his client, but she made hurried "
"contact herself. She wants come over to us. But don't celebrate yet. It may not "
"have occurred to you, but her entire story, which would be so convenient for us, "
"might be a ruse.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cac5d689-5bee-4948-baba-224f89924c24"
msgid ""
"\\\"We captured a spy, a mercenary from Daggermark. This city is like a spider at "
"the center of a web of intrigue, that entangles all the {g|River Kingdoms}River "
"Kingdoms{/g}. The spy identified his master. Once she realized we were following "
"her, she anticipated the tortures she was facing, and claimed that she wished to "
"come over to us, just as people of weak loyalty do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6d92523-8f12-4936-b51d-12e40ad030f9"
msgid "\\\"Deliver the list of agents to Galt.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "afad2087-9585-43a4-af15-83990a057833"
msgid "\\\"Report the treachery to Gralton.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e483ff3-c2e5-4083-9211-01f287da3aa6"
msgid "[Gain 2000 gold] \\\"Sell the information in Daggermark.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ccad7e1-ed42-4f72-b6d6-1b3e67982f31"
msgid "\\\"I trust your judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dcff999f-5928-46c6-9a70-da8f0428352b"
msgid "\\\"Tell me more about Gralton and Galt.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4f386534-bbda-437b-b07e-f5a7c4c3dbf5"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've found the one who meant to harm us. By day, he's a small fish, a scribe "
"in Gralton. At night, he becomes an important spy from Litran, the Galtan city of "
"Grey Gardeners. We do not know what his interest is in us, but we're following "
"him. He recently sent a message to {g|Galt}Galt{/g}. We managed to intercept the "
"courier on a backwoods path. The message contained a list of all Gralton's spies "
"in Litran.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bcbb862d-dc84-4d28-8605-fab0cb2691c5"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're finally on top of the enemy spy we've been tracking. An ordinary scribe "
"from Gralton was plotting against us! It also happens that he's the head of the "
"Grey Gardeners' intelligence operations in this city. I've no idea what interest "
"he has in us, but we followed him and intercepted his correspondence. It contained "
"a list of all Gralton's spies in Litran, in alphabetical order. The letter was on "
"its way to Litran – to the Grey Gardeners' headquarters!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "473b11b7-0af8-402a-bf26-c4acfd32c33b"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've learned the name of the one who was plotting against you. It's an "
"ordinary man from Gralton. However, he's a major spy for Litran, the Grey "
"Gardeners' capital in {g|Galt}Galt{/g}. I don't know what attracted him to us, but "
"now we have him on the hook.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b8e9ea1a-33d5-4827-99bd-c1fd71cbb1c0"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun frowns.{/n} \\\"Litran is dangerous. They kill people without a second "
"thought. There are too many madmen there. You should not seek their friendship. "
"Especially not if you have to pay for it with other people's lives.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "476a3693-010e-4faa-a5ea-811c035c90b1"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's your right to choose which of your neighbors you make friends with. But "
"what of the lives of Gralton's agents? Well, their blood is on your hands now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d978c756-b110-474b-b8a1-897f4e24bbb1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll be sure the Grey Gardeners know that their operation hung on our "
"discretion. Let them be grateful to us for not punishing them harshly for their "
"carelessness. The lives of the ungrateful are very short and full of suffering.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a30789b-c36d-4619-a454-a8ef2efa07c7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Gralton's people will stay alive. The traitor will go to jail. It's a good "
"decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ef73d47-a199-4ec9-bee9-4f2ae13b6337"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's your right. But you shouldn't interfere in a squabble between two other "
"countries. It's none of our concern!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f50ca282-53da-4d77-8760-0fddb128aac8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why? For the naive fairy tales that you call principles? Well, this is all "
"very noble, no doubt, but you put me in charge of the espionage, which means I "
"don't have the luxury of principles.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c08c2d70-3065-4e10-9538-5ddd12ec902e"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun's face grows very dark.{/n} \\\"We sell human life for gold. It's a bad "
"trade.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62f58d34-e913-4c40-8f47-fdd913a272b3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Selling this paper will bring us profit, and we won't even double-cross "
"anyone. Hopefully...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4692e96d-f1f4-41cf-8c9f-6ab40adb2f94"
msgid ""
"\\\"In the game of espionage, money is dust. Are you that fond of trading dust? "
"You shouldn't be selling something so valuable for gold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdd6f53e-549e-4f5b-8cd8-5ad5a8df0d38"
msgid ""
"\\\"A revolution took place in Galt. Many were executed without trial. Others fled "
"and hid in Gralton. They were the merchants and nobles. They dream of reclaiming "
"their homes – and of vengeance. So the Citizen's Directorate of spies against {g|"
"Galt}Galt{/g} was established.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3280d943-7b02-427e-a55f-05a4b7c91075"
msgid ""
"\\\"When {g|Galt}Galt{/g} was flooded with the blood of the revolution, many "
"nobles and wealthy merchants sought shelter in Gralton. Now they obsess upon "
"reclaiming their former greatness and regaining what was taken from them. They "
"created the Citizen's Directorate, a quite capable spying network, but still they "
"could not bring Galt to its knees.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13177f3c-a7fb-4633-995b-88eefef65eee"
msgid ""
"\\\"While mobs of ruffians were burning mansions and chopping the heads off of "
"their nobles, Gralton sheltered those sentenced to death by the revolution. It "
"became their refuge, in a way. Now, of course, they're just a bunch of idle fools, "
"thirsty for revenge and dreaming of the days of yore. They created the Citizen's "
"Directorate, a spy network, which has proven itself toothless and helpless from "
"the very beginning.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e273ac0a-740b-443f-ae4a-a40fa9b1a159"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could pass this information to Litran, and thus condemn these spies to "
"death. The Grey Gardeners would appreciate it. On the other hand, their "
"appreciation isn't worth so much. Better to deliver the traitor to Gralton in "
"return for their friendship. The fanatics of Gralton are a charming bunch, but of "
"course there's no great difference between them and the Gardeners. Why even get "
"involved in their quarrel? My suggestion is to sell the information on the rumor "
"market, and try to keep out of trouble.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34ea5ffb-db7c-4b43-a85c-606a11249234"
msgid ""
"\\\"Their lives are in our hands. Many would be willing to pay for this list, {g|"
"Galt}Galt{/g} first among them. Selling it would mean a death sentence to everyone "
"on the list. I suggest we report the traitor to Gralton. We don't want these "
"deaths on our conscience.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cedd8593-0958-42a7-9869-056abcc4c23c"
msgid ""
"\\\"We intercepted one of his letters. It contains a list of all Gralton's spies "
"in Litran. Oh, these greedy, crafty sorts, entirely oblivious to the fragile "
"barrier that separates them from the scaffold. My good will. Gralton would be "
"happy to learn of this treachery amongst their ranks, but what good would that do "
"us? Would we gain their friendship and goodwill? At least the Daggermark rumor "
"market would pay in gold! It's Gralton's own fault they weren't watching their "
"servants. But I suggest we allow the letter to proceed to its address in Litran. "
"If the Grey Gardeners show themselves to be ungrateful, we'll be able to eliminate "
"them easily.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "edf24ace-2346-4d6b-83cb-64a1fc726a5d"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Grey Gardeners have a monastery in Litran, a city in Galt. They are spies "
"and punishers. They keep {g|Galt}Galt{/g} safe from enemies both without and "
"within. Their faces are covered with masks, which means anyone could be one of "
"them. They are quite feared, and known for showing no mercy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f5477fb-09e1-4384-bfd6-bd1516e3eb1d"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's no mystery why. It's because of the Grey Gardeners – their monastery is "
"also there, in Litran to be precise. They look fearsome in their masks, so "
"frightening and anonymous. Executioners, investigators, vigilantes, and murderers. "
"They're better suited to slaughterhouse work than anything involving intellect. "
"But people do fear them. And some are fond of them, too. They help protect the "
"country against spies and traitors – and what's important, they keep away from "
"politics.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bcae97de-0ad6-4d86-9702-c26942ea6fc8"
msgid ""
"\\\"I like their enemies, though. The Grey Gardeners, guardians of the revolution. "
"A vivid example of the fanaticism of the short-lived. The first thing they "
"sacrifice in the name of their ideals is the right to life. They behave as though "
"they cannot physically pronounce the word 'mercy'. Their reputation speaks for "
"itself. They built a monastery in Litran; now they're casting terror in the hearts "
"of everyone around. Their enemies don't stand a chance against their covered "
"faces. At least until we demonstrate otherwise.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b6bca1e5-ff3b-4377-aa1e-2bb585d5e9b3"
msgid ""
"{n}After a moment of tense silence, Ekun continues:{/n} \\\"You need a new head of "
"intelligence, {name}. I'm... not the right person. I hunt alone. I account for my "
"own actions, and make my own decisions. You don't need my help. You never heed my "
"advice. You can hunt as you like. I'll fulfill this order, but then I quit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e14ab99-b909-4c5c-9a64-a054d30afb2d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've grown tired of our arguments. You should find a more obedient and less "
"sophisticated master of espionage. I will fulfill the order, but then I will "
"attend to other matters.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8143aa4-dd9f-4ded-bafd-124c8fbfd76a"
msgid ""
"Openly displayed their relations with the perished spies and acclaimed them as "
"heroes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "748b7d44-7f55-496f-9b47-560d5ca58cd6"
msgid "\\\"They died for us and our cause. We shall openly honor the dead.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a235fee3-3cbb-44bb-ad62-0e8db1fb5c4f"
msgid "\\\"Take care of their families without attracting undue attention.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f58ad304-a148-49d5-887b-ae899a59da08"
msgid "Renounced their dead spies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3da55f40-2c5d-49ce-9eaf-3202479668aa"
msgid "\\\"We have nothing to do with them. That's what everyone must think.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "650d066c-e64a-433c-a103-f3956afa338d"
msgid "Turned Galtans in their lands into undead."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33a9a256-5100-4fc5-bd4d-e1cad2df062f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let's execute travelers from Galt and then raise them as undead. I'm in need "
"of loyal servants.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f737602-e22e-479c-9b2b-7fe2e0580b6c"
msgid "Started a massacre to avenge the death of the spies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62a4daab-c2d4-4f75-94a1-1cf8843b6ac7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hang ten citizens of Galt in our territories for every victim among our people."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "131ab397-530c-49fc-810f-f7e5fb780bb2"
msgid "\\\"You decide, and it's done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02755f45-1145-4da0-acd3-df59bc8161ef"
msgid ""
"\\\"We shouldn't have gotten caught. But we've been caught. I don't understand "
"how. Litran learned who blew their spy's cover. In retaliation, they seized our "
"own agents and executed them. They mean to send us a message. But what troubles me "
"more...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce4b00e9-1af7-4931-b591-9ebdbb709cc0"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost's gestures are abrupt, his voice betrays uncertainty.{/n} \\\"Despite "
"all our secrecy, someone in Litran discovered who thwarted them. Accuse me all you "
"like! I can find a dozen better scapegoats for you. But it doesn't matter. Our "
"people were captured by the Grey Gardeners and executed. They've sent us a clear "
"message: 'stay away'.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e868bff-93a5-4616-91a1-07c75db4eba8"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I've done my best to tread lightly, but Litran learned of our "
"interference with their plans nevertheless. I told you we shouldn't play games "
"with them. Our people have been captured and beheaded. Pathetic fools, and their "
"irrational act of defiance! Others would recommend you renounce these executed "
"agents, to protect your reputation. After all, they were nothing but pawns.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1723f09-5b09-4915-8e0a-f5a7ba65747e"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's dangerous. That's going to irritate our neighbors. But it's noble. Death "
"doesn't seem so frightening when you know you won't be forgotten.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a8b2e83-bfb0-44bf-81e1-f14110b68f1c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thinking about your conscience? I know, conscience is important for a ruler. "
"It must be kept clear. But we spies have a job to do, and a spy's conscience "
"demands only one thing: to protect our country.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5cacbaa2-26ce-4998-9633-8975111d5150"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... That's unwise from a political perspective. However, politics are "
"constantly changing, like the boiling waters of a hot spring.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e93144f2-70b2-4376-ade1-563f33a644f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"They fulfilled their duty. We shall fulfill ours. We will take proper care of "
"their families.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29a1be40-898f-44b5-bb56-10de3cd388ef"
msgid "\\\"Very well, so be it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f039b54d-2307-4c97-9fd2-fcefdb815158"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you hope to keep this secret forever? You shouldn't. You're looking after "
"the living, not the dead. The living are not so good at keeping secrets.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98272dc1-bddc-49a4-9df3-7e9f2b17cd69"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun shakes his head.{/n} \\\"This is no good. In the future, our people will "
"choose to betray us, rather than die and leave their families without support.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f6cbdb3-41d7-4019-9c31-bc5c20149da1"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's for the best. Only by openly renouncing them can we really take up and "
"finish their job. If we accepted responsibility for their deaths, we'd not only be "
"harming ourselves, but we'd also be making their sacrifice meaningless. – Or "
"whatever you're supposed to say in a situation like this...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a612802e-9146-443f-9b53-29b945890e5a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will happily demonstrate to the pathetic mortals that death is not the end "
"of their service. I promise, you will appreciate your new servants.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d140b284-9362-4ea0-9939-4cf405dc0154"
msgid ""
"\\\"You want to teach them a lesson. This I understand. But this is worthy of a "
"wild animal. If you behave like a wild animal today, then be assured, tomorrow you "
"will be treated like one. They will put out traps and hunt you down.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af37598f-c579-40f6-b2a3-70bab59ebcee"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is no way to settle scores. What do you hope to accomplish? To instill "
"fear? They were bound to fear us in any case. But after this savagery they'll "
"never deal with us again! And how am I supposed to erase these ugly stains from my "
"reputation? I understand – you enjoy being a tyrant. But I've got better plans for "
"my future.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7e726784-d0b3-4443-9b21-f171768aedcf"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're no stranger to the creative approach. I like that. I will order a "
"general hunt for interlopers from {g|Galt}Galt{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ca75dfe-24b2-49e4-8030-d76646247350"
msgid ""
"\\\"I implore you to embrace this message and refrain from further dealings with "
"them. Do not think of vengeance, or even acknowledge the families of the dead. "
"There can be no monuments to the fallen. We must avoid war. We mustn't allow "
"predictable moves to lead us into a trap. Our agents knew very well what they were "
"getting themselves into. As do we all.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "513a763e-cec9-426f-9c2e-748d0dd38e5a"
msgid ""
"\\\"But this would send a message that you're scared. I've a better plan. We'll "
"capture citizens of {g|Galt}Galt{/g} that are presently in our lands, put them to "
"death, and turn them into the obedient undead slaves. We must demonstrate that we "
"cannot be intimidated or brought to submission.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f755488-27ca-44cd-89f0-54e5be98c6a9"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun sighs.{/n} \\\"What shall we tell their families? Do we promise them that "
"we won't disown them? That could be dangerous. Do we renounce them? That would be "
"disgraceful. My advice is to take care of their families, but secretly. The dead "
"would have wanted this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39c79d2a-1159-4e1d-889f-e406919199c6"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost becomes sarcastic.{/n} \\\"There's something I don't quite understand. "
"Why did you offer this position to me in the first place? To reject my advice over "
"and over? Please find yourself a new Minister. Meanwhile I will fulfill this final "
"request and then return to my regular life.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8cb46496-2412-4e61-a28b-3ef14808188e"
msgid "\\\"We won't abandon our people. You must plot their escape.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bffbaa1a-b732-4a49-9d17-9b4950e288a0"
msgid "[Pay 100 BP] \\\"Ransom our people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9837df66-92d6-4457-af37-a37889d2977f"
msgid "[Pay 50 BP] \\\"Let them be silenced forever.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50955fe3-21bf-47c2-9097-f6d3e973a408"
msgid "\\\"They're your people. You must decide.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "402c5157-e2c5-4244-bc19-6f0138a7f395"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you remember the spies from Gralton? Their masters learned that it was we "
"who condemned them to death. In revenge, they have kidnapped our people and thrown "
"them into prison. We must rescue them while we have the chance. But an assault on "
"their prison would be far too bold to easily be forgiven. But if you don't wish to "
"start a fight, we could act more cautiously and simply ransom them, although it "
"will be expensive. Finally, we could silence them. Forever. They possess valuable "
"information, of course. But this would be... disgraceful. I wouldn't do it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff7e2c56-2b1a-4856-91ea-fffd574fcf3d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Gralton somehow learned that we consigned their spies to death. In "
"retaliation, they arrested our own people and threw them into prison. The "
"information our people know shouldn't fall to Gralton's hands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91e3f672-68c4-41d3-b3d8-6cf6b5fd3add"
msgid ""
"\\\"Gralton found out that we were involved in their spies' deaths. They only had "
"themselves to blame, but they've twisted their anger toward us, grabbed our "
"people, and thrown them in jail. They're looking to torture valuable information "
"out of them. As if we would sit by and watch them succeed!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62d8deab-320b-461c-b820-436732266fc8"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll gather my best people and plan our raid. We'll extract our people bring "
"them to safety.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8af4e673-be32-45b9-a7ea-033b420812e4"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is absurd! As if we didn't already have enough problems with Gralton! "
"Let's pile on a little more! They'll make such a lovely burial mound – over our "
"graves!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "01d9358a-fae7-49cf-b57e-bf4de947d8b3"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's risky, but bold. In any case, it will send a message that there's no "
"use putting pressure on us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3ada7a6-27fa-48f7-9afe-54c1319e26dd"
msgid "\\\"Better to shed gold than blood.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b61a7956-d3d6-44e8-94f9-b59cb310ff3f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very wise. A generous payment would... smooth things over. Even the most "
"powerful ruler appreciates a bit of extra gold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ef3bd0e8-743a-45a7-900a-77a2f30d0597"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now we look like rich losers. – The perfect victim. Now all our other "
"neighbors will want to sink their teeth into us. You shouldn't make your own "
"weaknesses so obvious to others.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ac3165f-e0b0-4249-b93b-533fb01645aa"
msgid ""
"{n}A deep wrinkle crosses Ekun's forehead.{/n} \\\"Killing your own people is a "
"bad idea. The others will not understand. We're going to lose their trust.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6dd649c2-6e87-4bee-8e82-522cc65eecba"
msgid ""
"\\\"That is tough but fair. Espionage is a trade for those who are ready to sweep "
"their conscience under the rug.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0373e837-5241-456e-945f-2f04cfd57100"
msgid ""
"\\\"Their captives will find a peaceful death. Let Gralton consider this: we don't "
"spare our own people, so we're not likely to show greater mercy to them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21d80f1e-380b-42a2-b6e5-7538a5317d0f"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must ransom them, and if we can't come to an economical compromise, then we "
"should make them fall silent, forever. We mustn't lose our heads and try to free "
"them by force. Such issues are solved differently by the civilized rulers. You do "
"want to appear civilized to your neighbors, don't you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74d873ab-1550-49d7-8d2b-64c7b5ef8561"
msgid ""
"\\\"These captives must die before they meet the executioner. They were valuable "
"once, but now they're a dangerous liability. Of course, if you felt you had an "
"obligation to these people, you could attempt to release them by force. But I "
"dislike that option. Gralton might accept a ransom, but we'd be showing weakness.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fd8c9d1b-c079-42f4-af3a-34a171062dde"
msgid ""
"\\\"Pass the information about the Gardeners to the leader of the Revolutionary "
"Council of Galt.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76e040ee-8784-468e-8d80-a6fe53c7a04e"
msgid "\\\"Help the Order of Vengeance achieve their revenge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4f73933-5004-4a53-a41d-90b4193f9717"
msgid "\\\"Organize peace negotiations with Litran.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ef29183e-1f8a-493b-a357-da5a9aa97a5a"
msgid "\\\"I'll trust in your judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f751c448-14b1-49a6-91e4-968e882f121b"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're fighting someone else's war. We aren't Gralton. We aren't Litran. We "
"have no stake in this fight. Let us escape it before we're stabbed in the back. "
"Petitioning for peace is an option, though unreliable. Let's distract them first.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4dfda269-101d-45ce-9c1b-bcb17a9f322d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Look, {name}, we've suddenly stumbled into the middle of a fight between "
"Litran and Gralton. I don't know who might benefit from this, but it's surely not "
"us. It's time to figure out a way to extricate ourselves from the situation. I "
"suggest we negotiate a peace treaty. However, if you're too proud for such a "
"measure, I'll tell you a couple other options.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "340c47ed-e221-4b71-882e-462e422a9a65"
msgid ""
"\\\"We are pulled deeper and deeper into Litran and Gralton's fight. This already "
"drains our forces, and cannot end well. It's time we plan our escape from this "
"situation – preferably something that casts us in a positive light. I can see two "
"options.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "727a369e-5b7b-4737-8554-e8c97261110e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well. I'll send Goss all he'll need to know about the grey masks.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48f93908-203b-4a36-998a-042f68186335"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... To be honest, this is not the best decision. You've let a wolf into your "
"house to get rid of the rats. The Gardeners are fanatics, true, but Goss is a "
"manipulative weasel. He's the more dangerous of the two.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b0c98a7-1dca-4ede-a41e-4118040aac27"
msgid ""
"\\\"He'll be more than happy to bleed the Grey Gardeners a little. And we've all "
"the information we'll need to begin bloodletting. The ignorant fool won't even "
"stop to think why we shared our knowledge with him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "004202c2-1881-46a5-8a64-547ac8eb8002"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun shakes his head.{/n} \\\"We have delivered {g|Galt}Galt{/g} into war. I'm "
"afraid it's a gift that Galt will return as soon as they are able.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d19e677-2ff0-4f3f-b03f-0a042f2ec8d7"
msgid ""
"\\\"This inane war between the two countries was bound to happen eventually. At "
"least we might profit from it. That will have to be good enough for now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "392c9dd4-9a52-44fb-a44a-5e005bf01139"
msgid ""
"\\\"Litran will forget all about us, once the partisans seize {g|Galt}Galt's{/g} "
"borderlands. The Grey Gardeners should never have crossed us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7aba993b-9db8-40ca-be99-e7f4daa30819"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun stretches shoulder.{/n} \\\"It might work. Litran is dangerous, but they "
"are no fools. We are not their enemy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4ad9d41-d6e7-4e71-8ac6-14b7782d1d55"
msgid ""
"\\\"That is most wise. I will send an ambassador to Litran. I do hope they won't "
"decapitate him... No, no, they mustn't.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b02f6411-10a7-4d2f-abee-0842033a470e"
msgid ""
"\\\"You want me to beg them for peace? How revolting! Do you even see the giant "
"gap there is between us?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "95ea2bcd-bfa3-4b44-a528-81da99c3ec9e"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could convince the Grey Gardeners simply to forget about us. All we need do "
"is deliver their names to Korran Goss, the head of {g|Galt}Galt's{/g} "
"Revolutionary Council. He's afraid of the scaffold that ended the lives of his "
"forerunners, so he will take the chance to undermine the revolution's guardians. "
"The Gardeners will suddenly be fighting for survival, and in any case will have "
"more pressing needs than worrying about us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d037c71c-dede-4bd8-a7e9-02573dfa6e04"
msgid ""
"\\\"Another enemy, also thirsty for the Gardeners' blood, is a secret society from "
"Gralton – the Order of Vengeance. They've sworn loyalty to {g|Calistria}Calistria{/"
"g}, in the hope that she will help them avenge their losses. We could aid them in "
"forming an alliance with Gralton. They would start harassing {g|Galt}Galt's{/g} "
"borderland, which will occupy the Gardeners' full attention. I will enjoy seeing "
"my enemies bleeding to death in a battle that I caused.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4403c990-4e8a-421f-ad67-236e8ab8f4d0"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Grey Gardeners have a more attractive enemy than us – and they're nearer "
"to hand as well! Of course I'm speaking of the Revolutionary Council of {g|Galt}"
"Galt{/g}, headed by Goss. After all, the Gardeners' favorite pastime is to behead "
"members of the council 'for the benefit of the revolution' – so Goss prefers to "
"keep a low profile. He fears that his government could be decapitated, in every "
"meaning of the word. But if we give him something to sink his teeth into, he might "
"decide to go after the Gardeners after all. However, I would avoid this course. If "
"Goss prevails, he could become even worse than the Gardeners.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8b272da0-34d0-47bc-abad-84eeb35040e0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Another way to distract Litran's attention is the Order of Vengeance, a secret "
"society in Gralton. They are avengers, who seek to repay injuries suffered during "
"the revolution. If we aid them in forming an alliance with Gralton, the Order "
"could engage in guerrilla warfare on the borderlands. A shame that this mess will "
"be taking place just next door.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61f70cd5-2b6b-4aa8-a29a-8b881b96cdd5"
msgid ""
"\\\"You cannot deal with the Grey Gardeners, but death already stalks them "
"closely. Korran Goss rules {g|Galt}Galt{/g}, and he is wary of the Gardeners. They "
"decapitated more than one of his predecessors, and he'll strike if we give him a "
"target. He'll find good reason – a betrayal. We can expect to be left alone after "
"that.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8fcfca47-9d05-4bfb-b67b-625b4c49abad"
msgid ""
"\\\"We have another option, but it leads us down a dangerous path. There is an "
"Order of Vengeance in Gralton, wild avengers with deeply wounded hearts. They look "
"to settle scores, but their numbers are too few. We could draw them into an "
"alliance with Gralton, and their numbers will grow. They would return to {g|Galt}"
"Galt{/g} to exact their vengeance, and the Gardeners would become too busy to "
"bother with us. But blood will flow. And they'll remember what we've done!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ca58670-90d6-494e-87cf-9d5841f37b88"
msgid "\\\"Help Casal Tarne face his cousin.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a21efb31-c3c4-47f9-ae65-2f7203ac2eb9"
msgid "\\\"Dispatch soldiers to the Grey Gardeners.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50717ec9-3e50-4ef5-a164-e7818a6ef048"
msgid "\\\"Arrange peaceful negotiations with Gralton.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee0a0175-8797-421e-ae78-53271999536d"
msgid "\\\"I'll trust your judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e5ea73e6-5a76-4429-ae36-07ad8231bd0f"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're fighting someone else's war. We aren't Gralton. We aren't Litran. We "
"have no stake in this fight. Let us escape it before we're stabbed in the back. "
"Petitioning for peace is an option, though unreliable. Let's distract them first.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30627b3e-f637-437d-9373-509139384037"
msgid ""
"\\\"Look, {name}, we've suddenly stumbled into the middle of a fight between "
"Litran and Gralton. I don't know who might benefit from this, but it's surely not "
"us. It's time to figure out a way to extricate ourselves from the situation. I "
"suggest we negotiate a peace treaty. However, if you're too proud for such a "
"measure, I'll tell you a couple other options.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b5ff133-0815-4d83-9ed2-ee8e26f4733d"
msgid ""
"\\\"We are pulled deeper and deeper into Litran and Gralton's fight. This already "
"drains our forces, and cannot end well. It's time we plan our escape from this "
"situation – preferably something that casts us in a positive light. I can see two "
"options.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c8c4f7d-710e-4a7c-8fa2-ed50f3683716"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun nods.{/n} \\\"While the wolves fight in Gralton for dominance, we can "
"disappear without a trace. And without any further losses.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a771bb8-4979-449e-9a7c-a1a4c5c41b0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hopefully, once this mob of aristocrats stops fighting, they won't remember "
"what the whole thing started with...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3233af64-a5ee-4123-9887-38f4ee2efdd9"
msgid ""
"\\\"The short-lived are so easily manipulated. They're always seeking massacres, "
"as if to make their lives even shorter. We'll just give them a little push, and "
"they'll be trapped in bloody conflict!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0758dd73-3456-48e5-9af8-7c09b51f77fe"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun winces.{/n} \\\"We help the Gardeners grow stronger. But do not expect "
"friendship from one who fails to see a friend in anyone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6d4aa46b-14a2-4c4f-af59-80965e77a454"
msgid ""
"\\\"What a disgusting alliance. Don't think for a moment that I approve of "
"cooperating with them. I always try to stay away from two types of people: rulers "
"who seek to restrict thought, and rulers like you, who associate with bloodthirsty "
"lunatics.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c135ee88-036a-4903-b522-569b1962ed67"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Gardeners will strike Gralton with vicious force. The bloodshed will "
"remind Gralton's people that there's a price for challenging us!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87478d02-e71d-4590-913b-eee391ee0ca9"
msgid "{n}Ekun nods.{/n} \\\"A peaceful resolution is the best outcome.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9915c378-11b8-4058-91fb-9c0f8e59b081"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is wise. I'll send ambassadors to Gralton. We must make peace – and then "
"figure out how things could have gone so far! I suppose it would never have gone "
"this far if I had a more flexible and less dignified ruler. But that's just an "
"assumption.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4dde7b96-7ea1-4c3f-b452-bf3bd6a343c4"
msgid ""
"\\\"You want me to beg them for peace? How revolting! Do you even see the giant "
"gap there is between us?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33bcd6bc-854e-4563-a318-fd76ff9e4d0f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Halidan Tarne is the commander of Gralton's army. He's the general that "
"sending his raiders to {g|Galt}Galt{/g}. This commander is as bloodthirsty and "
"narrow-minded as any other military man. His cousin, Casal, envies his relative "
"but he's too cautious to disturb Gralton's fragile balance. But if you help Casal "
"gain a piece of Halidan's power, they'll busy themselves with their own problems "
"and leave us be.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7eaea19-9da3-4e15-8239-2dfaa635c7a6"
msgid ""
"\\\"On the other hand, we could involve Gralton in a fight with Litran. The Grey "
"Gardeners' greatest strength is spywork and intelligence, and I respect their "
"consistency and ferocity... But they need more soldiers. Real fighters. If we send "
"them some experienced warriors, Gralton will focus all its time and energy on "
"preventing Litran from crushing them. We ourselves cannot afford to make those "
"arrogant fools from Gralton weep blood, but I'll enjoy watching the Grey Gardeners "
"do it for us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "406ec3bd-fa35-4bc8-9047-3d11c71fcf56"
msgid ""
"\\\"Officially, I must mention the third option. The Grey Gardeners. Good "
"executioners, but poor soldiers. If we sent them more troops, Gralton would begin "
"to smolder under the Gardeners' pressure. Although I don't think supporting these "
"butchers is a good idea. So let's not discuss it further.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8b58f74e-692c-42fc-ba37-f3584e290a8b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Gralton has many groups vying for power: the Wise, the Order of Vengeance, the "
"Nameless, the Hand That Takes, the Directorate, and many other fancy names. There "
"are also the people of Halidan Tarne, Casal Tarne... Speaking of which... they're "
"cousins. The former is the army general, and the latter is the leader of the "
"sentry guard. Halidan is a wild daredevil, while Casal is a careful fool. But "
"Casal envies his cousin and his brave soldiers. If you help him take over "
"something that belongs to Halidan, they'll busy themselves with their own problems "
"and leave us be.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a55716dd-64ca-4334-997a-308ab0ca7a7d"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's a good solution. Gralton is like a serpents' nest. Many squads, many "
"commanders, all of them vying for power. If we aid the weak in taking something "
"that belongs to a strong, the delicate balance will shift. They'll busy themselves "
"with their own problems and leave us be. Casal Tarne, the head of the guards, is "
"weaker than his cousin. Halidan Tarne, the army's commander, is the stronger of "
"the two. Let us pit them against each other.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f4c39481-8608-4ad7-96c5-c62e1274af0c"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's another solution, too, but it leads us down a dangerous path. We could "
"aid the enemy of our enemy, the Grey Gardeners. They have punishers and spies, but "
"few soldiers. If we send them more troops, the Gardeners will engage with Gralton. "
"They'll keep themselves busy with their own problems and leave us be. But I would "
"not advise interfering. They are cruel and know no mercy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2fcc447-679b-4a07-a472-c42bda0dd1bf"
msgid "\\\"Tell me more about each candidate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65dc9658-6c28-4687-8011-30347eccaf10"
msgid "\\\"I am ready to make a choice. Summon the advisors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96cbd032-2442-4745-a910-2400cc4539b1"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun seems embarrassed, and his eyes do not rise from the floor.{/n} \\\"Bad "
"news, {name}. We've been cheated. The double agent, the scribe from Gralton, the "
"whole story... We've been deliberately pulled into someone else's war by an "
"unknown third party.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a17d7f9a-e701-42c0-a98a-673c44a9d600"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's been a mistake, {name}. Someone – I don't yet know exactly who – "
"played us. The double agent that came to us, Daggermark's spy, the scribe... It "
"was all a scheme to pull us into a fight with our neighbors! We've been "
"manipulated and trapped!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0937903a-5d67-4689-a457-459aa97b2721"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I don't think you're going to like the news I bring. We've been "
"deliberately pulled into the conflict between Gralton and Litran. A third player, "
"thus far unknown, sent us this mercenary and plotted his failure. They arranged "
"for us to discover the Litran spy, and then our actions were disclosed to the "
"enemy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "413b939c-3fcc-4135-837f-84441fcc5098"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Twilight Talons from Andoran are masters of covert war. They are as "
"dangerous as they are loyal. It's just that... they care more for their appearance "
"than their worth.\\\" {n}Ekun frowns.{/n} \\\"They serve their own country, but it "
"would be good if the Grand Diplomat persuaded them to help us. The Sleepless "
"Agency are urban hunters. Private detectives. And they aren't cheap. The Treasurer "
"will have to bargain hard for them. But they're worth the money.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ca1f9ca-776e-4970-81f2-f2dbf5ef72d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Twilight Talons are a squad of Andoran's best fighters. The Grand Diplomat "
"will have to make a heroic effort if there's any hope of bringing them here. But "
"their daggers and their capes are as famous as their snobbish attitudes. The "
"Sleepless Agency is a private company that provides security and investigative "
"services. Its staff are experienced and expensive mercenaries. I'm not sure if the "
"Treasurer can persuade them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a06d8832-dcb6-402e-9540-57c71f6f409f"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Twilight Talons and Sleepless Agency use similar methods. Both are "
"experienced spies and assassins. The former are the spy branch of the Eagle "
"Knights regiment. The Grand Diplomat will have to deal with them. The latter are "
"private detectives from Ustalav. They work for anyone willing to pay. The "
"Treasurer will have to release more funds than we're used to.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e186bf2f-571d-4c64-b698-a45f89fc7c1d"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must clear the ranks. I don't know which of them we can trust, so I'd bring "
"in completely new people. – People who cannot be bribed by the enemy, preferably "
"from distant lands. We could hire the bloodhounds of the Sleepless Agency... or of "
"course we could turn to Irori's oracles. But the Twilight Talons from Andoran are "
"the only ones I would trust with my life. You can rely upon their word.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c5473347-6b99-4516-aa57-ecb307aa88dc"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must clear the infestation from our ranks at once! This should be done by "
"someone from the outside, someone uninvolved with the plot. We should contact the "
"Sleepless Agency detectives or the gentlemen of the Twilight Talon. Or we could "
"ask the Irori oracles for help... if we would reach an agreement with them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e275894c-5af6-48b9-a93d-10298cfcd16d"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's time to hunt down the rats. We should bring in outsiders, whose hands are "
"clean. I have several candidates to offer. But I wouldn't bother contacting the "
"Twilight Talons, knights from Andoran. They're experienced, but they would never "
"serve us. They serve their own people. However, the detectives of the Sleepless "
"Agency might do. Irori's oracles are good, too.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b1dd865-8626-4704-bc9e-fbd3383b2548"
msgid ""
"\\\"Irori's oracles are seers who serve the god of knowledge. They are honest. And "
"rare. But I hear they can be found in the East. If we offer them the knowledge of "
"our priests, they might look into the darkness for us, and find the faces of our "
"enemies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c5e60bf-2666-488c-a24d-a50d3201262b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The oracles have been given the gift of divination by their Irori, the god of "
"knowledge and self-perfection. I hear there's an isolated coven of Irori's oracles "
"in Dunsward. We could persuade them to uncover the faces of our enemies – in "
"exchange for generously sharing our priests' knowledge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2193649d-d459-437e-9d7c-cf765c142da9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oracles are the servants of gods who can see what others keep hidden. I heard "
"that a small group of Irori's oracles live in an isolated community somewhere on "
"the outskirts of Dunsward. They could surely help us if we promised to share with "
"them the knowledge of our priests.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da51d87b-a6be-43ff-b907-2e7f55539ea5"
msgid ""
"\\\"During all this time, while we were wasting energy on a useless war, our "
"intelligence was being infiltrated by the spies of an unknown party! I no longer "
"trust any of my subordinates. I've never trusted them anyway. But perhaps that's "
"what's keeping us alive.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c528440-f42c-45c1-92f4-5c798b85eff8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then, while we were off fighting someone else's war, our real enemy sent in "
"spies to infiltrate our ranks! I conducted an investigation and found proof that "
"our entire intelligence apparatus has been compromised!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a2d601a3-ab07-4cff-8133-09752c5578e9"
msgid ""
"\\\"While we were busy brawling, they sent in their spies. We were distracted by "
"our neighbors and neglected our own home. Now it's full of rats.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1a658b6-4764-4350-8763-97829055fc21"
msgid "\\\"We're going to hit them right in their fat purses.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3973540b-0d5b-4180-9d51-82e0fb424088"
msgid "\\\"We're going to hunt down Daggermark's agents.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b80c261f-d8f4-419f-bf4c-4370617a87c2"
msgid "\\\"Act as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c3f7cda-034b-4158-9d78-caba09a6e365"
msgid ""
"\\\"We interrogated the traitors we discovered in our ranks. They were hired by "
"someone in Daggermark. The enemy is dangerous and covers his tracks well. But I'll "
"find him. We don't know which of the Daggermark elders is our enemy. But they do. "
"And they will willingly betray their own, if they can profit in doing so.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85fcc1a6-a989-4fd9-8947-455af7bff1f7"
msgid ""
"\\\"The traitor's trail leads to Daggermark. Our quarry is hiding unseen, but I "
"know how to lure them out. We can give Daggermark's elite some political problems "
"to deal with – wreck their business affairs without spilling a single drop of "
"blood. They'll gladly betray the offender to end the chaos.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4bd4a947-618a-4c52-94e5-0940abb0549e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our enemy's trail leads to Daggermark. The one who infiltrated spies into our "
"ranks is now hiding quiet and still. They don't seem to understand the vanity of "
"the pose. We're no longer looking for a single offender. We will take broader "
"measures instead. Every servant, spy, or tradesman's assistant, whose master hails "
"from Daggermark – he can count himself most wanted.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "942f1577-ed5c-482f-a374-a319e39ee74c"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun nods happily.{/n} \\\"There is no honor among such as these. We take away "
"their meat, and they'll turn on each other like jackals.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ebb0d78-e33e-4e5d-b37d-c0e4db32c9cf"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ha. The offender will be brought to us before I can say, \\\"An accidental "
"fire wiped out their depots!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9cec5869-53f7-4d14-a696-46405bdb7a0f"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is careless. You'll merely tease them and make them angry. Far better to "
"simply inspire terror. That alone will prevent them from stabbing you in the back."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43886a94-aa4b-4aa1-9929-8719921590fc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your vision is clouded. You do not seek to pursue a goal, but to avenge an "
"insult.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74d54d96-2024-454d-9334-f1b7ea8e6ffe"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh. You're overdoing it. If you push too hard, they won't want to meet you at "
"the negotiation table later. They'll come at you with pitchforks and torches "
"instead.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac71c51c-2dbc-46ca-a879-dcc320acc85f"
msgid "\\\"My harvest will please Urgathoa.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a694afd-6ae0-4bda-87d1-151f14cfc611"
msgid ""
"\\\"Daggermark's influence stretches far and wide, and its representatives can be "
"found across the kingdom. We can strike them at any time. If we apply enough "
"pressure, the elders of Daggermark will be forced to reveal our enemy's name, if "
"only to stem the loss of blood. Though in truth it is not blood but gold that "
"flows in their veins. Ripping open their purses would be even more effective than "
"ripping open their bellies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1487c937-2b87-4476-9700-3be213f8e15a"
msgid ""
"\\\"They are expecting us to make an attempt on their purses. It's the only way "
"they think. But we need not trouble ourselves with their enterprises. We'll simply "
"be killing them one by one, sparing no one. The elders of Daggermark will come "
"crawling to us on their knees, begging us to take the traitor and leave the rest "
"of them alone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68ad0eb8-dc3e-4d6b-aaec-7a983fe43e2e"
msgid "\\\"Destroy her reputation. Let her allies abandon the Guild head.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e51c9f0f-4d3a-4025-b6cf-cd5ab1aed922"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let everyone believe that she was planning to overturn Daggermark's government."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a19dc3cf-35ac-4fe1-ab96-2292d93d7349"
msgid "\\\"Offer her to make peace, join forces, and attack the other Guild.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d48d711c-a04a-45c4-bb29-0763f3794286"
msgid "\\\"Make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3510391e-6dcb-4ce1-998f-ed119de42e96"
msgid "\\\"Describe the forces in Daggermark for me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5ba21fb-fc79-44da-bbde-b06b15665b66"
msgid "Perpetrated a mass murder in Daggermark by collapsing the Guild."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "301cd752-cdcf-461c-89a1-67c0d6d0d20a"
msgid "\\\"Blow up her headquarters.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "054f373e-1eec-4dc4-807a-e559fc254607"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, we've a report from Daggermark. The enemy we seek is the leader of one "
"of the two Guilds that rules the city.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4f00ee1-2a77-494e-94ab-22da5853ec05"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well, I'll just tell you. It's old Tragshi, that schemer and poisoner. "
"She's wise, like any woman of her age... But to put it simply, she's a cranky old "
"lady who is stuck in the past. I wouldn't share a cup of tea with her. Anyhow, our "
"aggressive politics seem to have startled her.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0dd8a15f-de17-4883-b577-a22f82cc9b80"
msgid ""
"\\\"All right, don't try to guess. It's lady Janna Smilos, the head of the "
"Assassins Guild. She's fearsome, smart, and crafty. – Smart and crafty enough with "
"her dagger anyway. She prefers to solve her problems with a simple dagger thrust "
"between the ribs. But she's not as smart or crafty as we. She knows this full "
"well, which is why she tried to get rid of us before we reached our full strength."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f463bd3-7e03-40b0-9b34-09e64a245bab"
msgid ""
"\\\"We can solve the problem by planting a bomb in the Guild's headquarters or by "
"spreading rumors to slander her. We could even plant evidence of her conspiracy "
"against Livondar, the Lord of Daggermark. Ah but there's one more option. We could "
"defy expectation and extend a hand of friendship to her. We could seal the deal by "
"attacking the other Guild, to cement the unexpected bond.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2493094c-3e2e-48e7-a16b-c3cc7527ecdb"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, we know who's been waging a war of spies against us! It's the leader "
"of one of the two major guilds in Daggermark. Guess who it is – the Assassins or "
"Poisoners Guild.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3b667a7e-2dda-4b4c-a6d1-ddbfcaa59334"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I have a gift for you. The name of the enemy who conspired against us. "
"Have you heard of the two main Guilds in Daggermark, the Assassins Guild and the "
"Poisoners Guild? Our enemy is the woman who runs one of them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1738cb9e-08ce-4240-8d38-303b9c1eca7a"
msgid ""
"\\\"A clever woman by the name of Tragshi, leader of the Poisoners Guild. She's "
"known for her wisdom, and values balance, like other druids. She thought we were "
"acting too abruptly. Rocking the boat. She meant to discipline us. It was a "
"mistake.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66764c62-e908-45b0-b6c6-84c3954634f0"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's Janna Smilos, the head of the Assassins Guild. Bold and dangerous. She "
"recognizes an enemy when she sees one. She saw us as a threat and decided to "
"strike first. And now we have her all but cornered.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "07c11094-30b8-4ed7-babb-0b539ff7b61f"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's time we strike back. It is for you to decide how we should proceed. "
"Deception? Slander? A bomb that turns the whole Guild to ash? We could send a "
"false letter to Livondar, the Lord of Daggermark. We will lead him to believe that "
"the Guild was conspiring against him. Finally, we could turn our enemy into our "
"friend, by striking the other Guild. Their blood would forge a new alliance!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b9551a3-d821-4e69-9f15-6687956dbe60"
msgid ""
"\\\"Her name is Tragshi. The old wretch runs the Poisoners Guild. Our decisive "
"manner probably scared her. The old coward meant to undermine our kingdom with her "
"schemes, but the snake only poisoned herself. We won't be the ones who fall. She "
"will.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e769470-bd97-4a37-abe2-226ac7d78f3f"
msgid ""
"\\\"The name is Janna Smilos, the head of the Assassins Guild. To be chief among "
"ignorant butchers and stranglers is a dubious honor. In any case, Smilos regards "
"us as dangerous and unpredictable foes, and she certainly has a point. But she "
"imagined she could bring down our whole espionage network, and the kingdom with it "
"– and that shows a serious lack in judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99f35433-6056-416c-8aa5-357a961ee041"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could blow up the Guild headquarters and hope she dies in the rubble. We "
"could slander her and ruin her reputation. Or we could make it look like she's "
"conspiring against Livondar, the Lord of Daggermark – though I dislike the idea of "
"someone else serving justice on my behalf. But there's another, more artful move. "
"Everyone expects us to attack our enemy. Meanwhile, what if we made a deal with "
"her and strike her competition? It's the last thing they'd expect. Then we could "
"share the treasure and part as friends.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed1ee006-e742-4d98-b2ee-f13ed70ea810"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll slander her, then. And if our enemy lacks flaws? We'll make up flaws! "
"Our stories will be so true to life that the truth will pale before the shining "
"lies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a2132c2-dd35-4522-bf9f-5ceac059cc19"
msgid ""
"\\\"People always prefer to believe lies. It won't be hard to blame her for every "
"fault and failing since the world began.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46c5d131-eb96-4bda-bbad-15275fea2682"
msgid "\\\"It will be done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c42f5ff3-3785-4a01-b5ff-81011f8a8f0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"It should be easy to convince Lord Livondar that there was a conspiracy "
"against him. There have been plenty of attempts on his life in the past. Even if "
"he figures out it's a lie, he'll still be happy to pin the crime on her.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66eec973-c8b4-4cc0-9b65-3e6f3b8c4e39"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very logical. Let Daggermark's scorpions sting each other to death in their "
"little jar, as we watch from outside.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7765fe73-dbed-456f-81f0-1ed46b4e46e1"
msgid "\\\"It's a crafty move. I'll take care of it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "815a0119-10b6-48f4-b732-bbc550bf9254"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll take care of it. But don't ask me how. I'm your minister – I have my own "
"secrets.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14fb0e73-129d-4902-a409-4ba7fce229df"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll seal the deal with her and strike her enemy! Fate presented two options: "
"her or us. Yet we've chosen a third. Very clever.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea515d99-0cea-49dc-a826-9feefeb35532"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Assassins and Poisoners Guilds are on peaceful terms, but it's a fragile "
"alliance. Both guilds possess strength and power. Both are large, with extensive "
"networks of relations. Martro Livondar ensures they don't wipe each other out. "
"He's rather more of a judge and a general than he is a ruler.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83182be4-5037-4748-9d6f-5b6a4f6fbbab"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Assassins Guild and Poisoners Guild are equal in power. Both have plenty "
"of money, spies, and connections. Their alliance is more of a heavily armed "
"stalemate. Martro Livondar, the formal Lord of Daggermark, keeps the balance. But "
"neither Guild would pass up the chance to grab everything that the other one has.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4aea097c-23f5-440c-8c4f-42689b024be6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Assassins and Poisoners Guilds share power, and their strengths are "
"somewhat comparable. They have plenty of gold, relations, and agents. They were "
"once allies, but today each of them looks with deadly envy at the other. Martro "
"Livondar, the Lord of the city, keeps the balance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd70a573-0b7a-40ad-9b07-0865249bdc01"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun is thoughtful, but his voice is resolute.{/n} \\\"Many will die. They're "
"not bakers and fishermen, though. Their job is to bring death. They chose this "
"fate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acf455b4-0d0e-4a52-90b1-c46f5c6d8aeb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Normally I wouldn't recommend such a stratagem... But this is precisely the "
"sort of situation where it's appropriate. She's already caused us too much trouble!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c69e2b5-8a33-4cfe-8a11-26f1a74d11e8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Many bystanders will die. Servants. Students. Clients. But this is well. "
"She'll find it hard to make friends if everyone is afraid of getting close to her."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1de31e3e-6924-4987-b941-1f29eea5d470"
msgid ""
"\\\"The merchants became wealthy because they know how to read and write, and they "
"studied history and geography. Let the people send their children to schools, "
"temples, and sages, so they may learn and grow wiser.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d80c1b72-7d53-4893-91c9-de1f702bafe7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I want your people to become the kingdom's ears. Keep an eye on any suspicious "
"foreigners. Never discount a strange rumor. Only united can we stand against our "
"enemy's deceptions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b5e2aee-7c4c-46a6-8071-3a543efe4247"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tell everyone you meet that I'm a just ruler. The log drivers wander all "
"around the River Kingdoms. If our neighbors learn of my people's respect, my fame "
"and power will grow.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08ea7963-028b-4790-8885-aef6f99bc4a6"
msgid ""
"{n}It takes the sturdy old man a while to clear his throat. He seems confused but "
"tries to stand tall.{/n} \\\"Greetings, Your Highness! I am the leader of the log "
"drivers. Everyone in the whole area knows me. We deliver goods, ferry people "
"around. – Basically, we live on the rivers. I've come to thank you, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "581c30f1-86d1-45d3-a073-788b50c0de27"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's a strange thing to say! But it's true, in times like these, all our "
"neighbors envy us. Don't you worry. If any trouble stirs up, your guards will be "
"the first to know!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "399b0d56-9b43-4fbb-9350-4d7fff9c0161"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll do it, {name}. It will take time, of course, but eventually we'll be "
"better for it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "875dbedd-f1b3-4153-a51a-530ae2f178ce"
msgid ""
"\\\"It will be done. All your neighbors will hear how your people support you. "
"That will make them respect you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39722f34-27ef-4bc3-9202-028300c315ce"
msgid ""
"{n}The old man bows.{/n} \\\"We've seen many things, but a ruler who stands up for "
"the ordinary people against the rich – that's something new. The petty merchants "
"that robbed the people are like the bandits now. They're singing a different tune, "
"and engaged in honest trade. For this I thank you. – And not just with words. Tell "
"me what your people can do for you, and I'll make sure they hear your request.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "406ba4b1-96c8-488d-884b-445c0b49184e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our gallows cannot wait to meet them. Let everyone see what fate awaits "
"traitors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "615d7079-0f11-40d1-853e-eaefe1edd77d"
msgid "\\\"Let them go. We've taught them a lesson. It is sufficient.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b9d4b72-bc8e-4cbf-a208-b4aa2f10c503"
msgid ""
"[Gain 10000 gold and 200 BP] \\\"Free them from their chains. Also free them of "
"their wealth, their estates, their luxurious clothing and any other possessions. I "
"will be seized for the good of the state and its people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "425b5d51-cd08-4342-b98b-3105c801f7bc"
msgid "\\\"You may determine their fate yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7ee9084-418f-4a95-97c0-c113c38e6b30"
msgid ""
"\\\"The merchants became wealthy because they know how to read and write, and they "
"studied history and geography. Let the people send their children to schools, "
"temples, and sages, so they may learn and grow wiser.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4d2e1ac8-6350-4b6b-bf34-37dbab275027"
msgid ""
"\\\"I want the people to become the kingdom's ears. Keep an eye on any suspicious "
"foreigners. Never discount a strange rumor. Only united can we stand against our "
"enemy's deceptions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ef6c9a61-8aa6-4fb2-b238-0a675b46b98f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tell everyone you meet that I'm a just ruler. If our neighbors learn of my "
"people's respect, my fame and power will grow.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8914c62c-d67d-4154-becd-0ecdf44f76ad"
msgid ""
"\\\"But now for some less uplifting news. The guards have exposed a conspiracy of "
"merchants. All the plotters have been arrested, and you must decide their fate. "
"The people are concerned that the rich merchants will simply get away with it. I "
"believe your justice will be served rightly and mercifully.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9f2ef71-f28d-45a0-bfdd-5fc0d04ebc44"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your citizens gathered in a council today to plan some more new slums. They're "
"naming one of their squares after you. I love how they roll over for you. Not "
"every ruler enjoys such a mixture of fear and love!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db15bd8c-68e2-4c5a-92a6-4e068a1f614a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am sad for them. I wish someone had stopped them before their conspiracy "
"went too far. Part of the blame for this is also mine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "edb1a6ea-815e-4cb3-8f65-18021891855f"
msgid ""
"\\\"This will teach a harsh lesson to all who witness the punishment. The lesson "
"of fear and respect, {name}. They are the two pillars of every true leader's power."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa2e1745-6ce6-4020-8d46-0c1825903e92"
msgid ""
"\\\"I hope they recognize how lucky they are, and use this chance to start a new "
"life.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7abbc190-9ffc-46e0-b62f-24a9ecfa6d05"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your softness is sickening. Very well, as you wish. Your pack may consider it "
"a token of generosity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21fc6376-9b54-498a-ae7f-bd0d729e9a43"
msgid ""
"\\\"I heard it's only when a man has nothing that he recognizes true virtue. "
"Perhaps they'll become better and purer souls without their riches...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9397a9ed-56d4-4d2e-adec-1ed68ce127a0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... You might be doing the right thing. Anyway, they'll be helpless without "
"their wealth.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea6b45b4-6016-4f9b-b3de-f51c6ce44479"
msgid ""
"\\\"We shall forgive them, but deprive them of their means of bribing people and "
"plotting behind your back. Let their wealth be put into use for the ordinary poor "
"people, and let the conspirators join their number.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f3c4926-bd65-4a38-a54b-a2a783942746"
msgid ""
"\\\"Dangerous and diseased pack members should be eliminated. I will take care of "
"everything, beginning with these pathetic conspirators.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c189f915-4f0a-4521-91a3-f1736d090925"
msgid ""
"\\\"Another visitor awaits an audience with you. He is the leader of the druids of "
"{kingdomname}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f35d81f-f02b-4861-81e4-74fe3e6cfc5d"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna's face darkens. She seems nervous. Her rat has disappeared gone.{/n} \\"
"\"Now that the destiny of the conspirators has been decided, please accept another "
"visitor. He is the leader of the druids of {kingdomname}. But beware – he is not "
"as simple as he seems.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ac22d0c-cbe9-4b42-9bcb-62367a112472"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, the city council discussed the expansion of one of the districts "
"today. The square in its center will be named in your honor, by unanimously "
"consent. You deserve the love of your subjects! Not every ruler has a chance to "
"enjoy it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3034f9bf-0851-4110-a7e4-48c8e712966b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The loyal hounds of your guard arrested the last members of the merchants' "
"conspiracy today. It's time to decide their fates. I would not recommend mercy. "
"It's not as if they'll ever do anything with their lives. Besides, there's only "
"one way to ensure that such a conspiracy never forms again: a harsh punishment for "
"all involved.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0def0a5b-f2c8-4973-aa5c-df1d697306a0"
msgid ""
"{n}A sturdy old man with a shaggy beard begins to clear his throat. His "
"penetrating eyes scan you, his face benign and respectful.{/n} \\\"Long live Your "
"Highness! I am here to speak on behalf of your vassals. – Those who survive by "
"farming the land, which my brothers and sisters have sworn to protect. We were "
"their only defenders before you came. We didn't think of you as a friend at first, "
"I admit. But we were wrong.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d4847373-a5ca-40f8-9a6e-ef081dfb040b"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll do it, {name}. It will take time, of course, but eventually we'll be "
"better for it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75489cb0-29ca-4521-8068-3d5d7aa7651f"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're speaking dark words, but I don't want to argue. It is true, in times "
"like these, all our neighbors envy us. Don't you worry. If any trouble stirs up, "
"your guards will be the first to know!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b3187d4c-44ec-4e20-9598-c45216cdb039"
msgid ""
"\\\"It will be done. All your neighbors will hear how your people support you. "
"That will make them respect you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dbb918f7-07b7-42ae-b722-ab16bf577677"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've seen many things, but a ruler who stands up for the ordinary people "
"against the rich – that's something new. The petty merchants that robbed the "
"people are like the bandits now. They're singing a different tune, and engage in "
"honest trade. For this I thank you on behalf of the druid circle. Tell us what "
"your people can do for you, and your words will be ours. The people heed their "
"druids.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0afff0d-da3c-4c12-8fdc-1304bf8ac5ed"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your people truly love you. However mighty or powerful a ruler may be, the "
"druids never bear gifts to tyrants or villains.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "01e9b5d1-cf0c-46bd-a748-6fe84a4af464"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna and the old man stare down one another as if discussing something "
"silently. Then the Councilor nods reluctantly.{/n} \\\"I'm glad to see you have "
"come in good faith, old man. You have delivered the people's message, and we have "
"heard you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9240ba57-48b8-4701-a7ba-006de3049f8a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, the merchants who conspired against you have been arrested. You "
"will have to determine their fate. Naturally, the crowd is out for blood. The "
"smaller traders hope that you will confiscate the conspirators' assets. – They're "
"looking to take their place.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bfa46b96-badc-466e-88d8-32162c84ab29"
msgid ""
"\\\"If they were mere peasants, I would agree. But these are people of great value "
"to the kingdom. They've made a fortune on their own wits. We all might benefit "
"from their wisdom. Their clever heads on spikes – that would truly be a sorry "
"sight!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa3c2616-fc9a-4aa1-9e31-67456dbc5287"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, it is time we graciously receive another visitor, if you "
"please. He is a representative of the people, so to speak. Ahem.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf043b51-5cc9-4558-adfd-2500464d3146"
msgid ""
"\\\"They've learned their lesson. Arrest and imprisonment sent them a clear "
"message. We can be sure that they'll think thrice before stirring up another "
"rebellion. – And more importantly, if any make such a proposal, they'll all come "
"running to report it to you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7b1a2605-06d2-4fa1-b7d8-03bd05e70ed2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, that's tantamount to murdering them. But it's not their "
"individual lives that matter. It's their names and assets that are important. "
"Strip them of their gold, and you'll destroy pillars that support your kingdom. "
"Though your power to devastate will strike fear into the hearts of the other "
"merchants...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a7259f30-f4ec-4540-9ffc-5c16ac2e0cbb"
msgid ""
"{n}The Councilor smiles at the druid graciously, but her gaze is cold.{/n} \\"
"\"Your Highness, I am glad there's someone in the kingdom who we may rely on. "
"Let's hope that the people's leaders will be reliable and loyal enough to take the "
"place of the kingdom's nobility.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ef36976-8424-4d4b-8562-065ac92e9450"
msgid ""
"\\\"But I suggest they should be pardoned. They made a mistake, true. But they "
"were caught. That will teach them to fear your wrath, and carefully consider their "
"actions in the future. They have been among the most noble people in the capital. "
"You have now their obedience. The same might not be true of whoever should replace "
"them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "587ade39-4de0-4abb-87f8-1e88d09f8055"
msgid ""
"\\\"Open public schools. Even the peasants in my domain should know how to read "
"and write!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2df04fc-796a-4714-9a06-0c211c5d93e7"
msgid "\\\"Openly tell your neighboring partners how you are treated.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "911cc011-d889-4c37-b2ff-66189b0ece0e"
msgid ""
"\\\"You have ears everywhere. Put them to use. Report anything suspicious that you "
"come across.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "193fa09c-b323-40e3-8b07-7979bfe36b73"
msgid ""
"{n}A fresh-faced halfling bows before you affably. She looks very young, but her "
"voice sounds confident and bold.{/n} \\\"Greetings, Your Highness! I represent a "
"small trade alliance that was formed in your capital. Commerce is in my blood. My "
"family have been merchants for three generations. I am here to thank you on behalf "
"of all the other merchants that live and work in your domain!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63c0a22b-ab6f-4b2d-8736-c70a18865913"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's a very wise demand! An educated youth could come in handy, especially "
"now that trade in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} is flourishing!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19876d2d-f6b7-4ded-84d9-c1f67e6911d5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, I see! Rest assured, the merchants of the neighboring lands will be green "
"with envy. We will spread the greater glory of your name from here to {g|Absalom}"
"Absalom{/g}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e4ba7d5-7741-41c3-9feb-78abd70c860b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course. If the merchants learn that some rascal is planning to cause "
"trouble, the guards will be informed of it right away.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cfbe6c5a-7d23-44e3-b98b-7f530e35ef99"
msgid ""
"\\\"Lords often consider us nothing but milk cows for the state. We appreciate "
"that you have let us go about our business. You didn't rob us as you grew in "
"power. We're not used to such decent treatment, and your good faith and "
"understanding have been a great boon. My friends and I discussed it, and decided "
"that we'd return the favor. Tell us, what can we do for you, Your Highness?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4e54e01-29c7-40b3-bcf8-a122664dbccf"
msgid "\\\"Off with their heads!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18af66ef-204b-49df-84d0-1597c580767d"
msgid "\\\"I will grant pardon to them if the priests agree to bail them out.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66fd5b1a-3fd8-4c19-af06-72575a08fc79"
msgid "Showed mercy to the rebels by sending them to the army."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f825fa94-dd07-4b5b-8962-bbcd38cd61a0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll spare their lives, but I cannot let them go just like that. Let them make "
"up for their sins by the honest service in my army.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e092838-2da3-495b-9cd1-b497e53268d9"
msgid "\\\"Decide their fate by yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aad2ae35-4341-4095-96d8-6909101f28d5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Open public schools at the cost of your profits. Even the peasants in my "
"domain must know how to read and write!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2162d99-118d-4040-90e9-b1c7517edacd"
msgid "\\\"I love magic trinkets.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89eba91e-4232-4a94-89b1-fbac791580c6"
msgid "\\\"You're wealthy, so reward me with gold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2027228a-e5d4-4005-8de2-294f37b4561e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now to the bad news. The guards arrested a few citizens, organizers of riots "
"in the wealthy quarter. You must determine their fate. You can impose strict "
"penalties... or show mercy – that's what I'd like to ask you to do. Perhaps, you "
"could kindly allow priests of {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} and {g|Sarenrae}Sarenrae{/g} "
"to bail out their followers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cdc7a42a-6ead-43b1-8964-2a93f6401c6b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Today the assembly of merchants decided that the city would hold a feast in "
"your honor! It's so lovely when your name is associated with joy and wealth. It "
"means, your pack is flourishing, and they know who they should thank for it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdfa0c8a-8774-4d35-abe7-98b27a70fdc2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I understand... your wrath. Although I'm sorry for the poor fellows that were "
"denied mercy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c28f87e-191f-4027-a6ac-676dace4f552"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a shame. They were ambitious and strong. But they never feared you, so "
"they would have caused trouble anyway.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32078ac0-1390-4bc9-ba74-abb457cad297"
msgid ""
"\\\"The priests will gladly take the responsibility. This is merciful and wise. "
"Thank you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18e653f3-de0e-4c90-ac03-2a2157396573"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm surprised at how willingly you share credit with these prudes. But it's "
"your decision, of course.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7466d63d-5398-428c-9f16-d02f14d817d3"
msgid "\\\"It is merciful and just. Let me pass your message to the general.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c53532eb-2681-4dbf-8bc8-e958094c9d2d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agree. Why waste such daring and strong fellows? They may serve your pack!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de59785f-8943-41c9-ae4c-6ec5352b0dde"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let's send them off to the temple for schooling. Priests will help their heads "
"clear by hard labor and a word of wisdom.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49598229-0372-47cb-b4b5-83bfb0d175fc"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will dispatch them to your army. Their fault must be washed off with "
"enemies' blood. They're destined by fate to induce rage of their comrades.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c937a82-a768-4ea7-a7af-16adaac6d57f"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's someone else waiting for your audience. Please, take the time to talk "
"to the visitor. It's the head of {kingdomname} kingdom's trade society.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fda4ec0c-cf61-43c1-81af-e60818d76840"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now that we're done with the rebels, I'd like to ask you to receive one more "
"visitor. It's the leader of merchants of your kingdom.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5721ccae-4b4e-4d30-bf0f-cac390dfbb7c"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, today the high society council decided that the city would hold a "
"feast in your honor! With street food, fairs, music and fun! The people want to "
"thank you for their peaceful, abundant life.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fdce2d48-71e7-4acd-902a-9ce91438ab7c"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's something else. The guards arrested the last organizer of the riot "
"today. It's time to pronounce the verdict. You may demonstrate your strictness by "
"executing them. Or you may acquire a reputation of a merciful leader by pardoning "
"and sending them off to purge the guilt with blood. The only thing you shouldn't "
"do is listen to {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} and {g|Sarenrae}Sarenrae's{/g} priests. "
"They want you to pardon the troublemakers and send them to temples on probation. "
"Even if you do so, it's them who will get the credit for mercifulness, not you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f3f0117a-d744-4cbc-be2f-3c8302b42c8c"
msgid ""
"{n}A solid halfling with graying hair bows to you politely and wipes off the "
"excessive sweat.{/n} \\\"Greetings, Your Highness! I am here to thank you on "
"behalf of all merchants that live in your domain! Lords often consider us as money "
"cows. We appreciate that you let us go about our own business. You didn't get to "
"rob us as you took power. We discussed the matter and decided that we'd like to "
"pay you back for your kind understanding. What can we do for you, Your Highness?\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5eafb90-35b0-4e8e-9df0-1fae537f696f"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a very wise demand! The educated youth may come in handy, especially now "
"that the trade in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} is flourishing!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c6a2255a-92b3-41fe-87e9-0a39dc7b39b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"You have a fine taste! My colleagues and I will do our best to surprise you "
"with a decent gift!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b56d94f4-0e15-481f-8f0d-98865fdb863b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Believe me, Your Highness! We will spare no expense for the most luxurious "
"monument possible! It will make rulers of other kingdoms jealous!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5caa1cc1-b106-41a1-8478-7cdb6d15f2fc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Don't forget to pay well to your servants, not only to your ruler!\\\" {n}"
"Tristian stops, looks at you apologetically and smiles.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1dede5e8-f777-4de4-ac6f-5e823235d1bd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Remember who you owe your abundant life in the capital to, without having to "
"hide from robbers in the bushes.\\\" {n}The merchant nods hastily. Tsanna looks up "
"and down at him, like a cook checking out a fresh steak that goes straight into "
"cauldron.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59902776-3de8-4faa-a771-51f2b914cb71"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, the instigators of the riot have been arrested. You will have "
"to determine their fate. If you're asking yourself whether you should make a grand "
"gesture and pardon them, the answer is no. They're as dangerous as a hound that "
"tasted blood.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0dda7b5-4621-45f7-b6b7-0fbee0792145"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's questionable. They'll keep spreading their dissidence among soldiers. The "
"army mutiny is going to turn out much, much worse. I'll send my agents for "
"surveillance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb0f3911-622d-4615-9406-f7773ad27f8a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your gentle heart will get you in trouble. The only lesson they'll learn, is "
"that starting a riot doesn't carry a penalty. The next riot will gather even more "
"followers. Those who got scared of the punishment last time, will certainly join "
"the next riot.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e20c9d49-cb5a-47e7-b945-1da83cc98846"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hang the troublemakers. It's your best option. It'll teach peasants a proper "
"lesson. Just the idea of a riot makes the kingdom unreliable.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28db7f7e-51b6-44ee-98f0-442b1703fb9e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now that we're done with the unpleasant task, I'd like to ask you to receive "
"an important visitor. He's the leader of merchants of your kingdom.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6eef4895-5fa7-4f8a-97f6-70c1d3143178"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm happy my advice came in handy, your Highness. You managed to tame the "
"natural urge to take populist measures, and carefully considered your policy in a "
"pragmatic manner. It was very insightful of you as a ruler!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c74d4b4a-a1da-4f0e-bd85-307afeed8664"
msgid ""
"\\\"The riot will start again unless you punish them. In Brevoy, they usually hang "
"the rebels or exile them to army service. Considering that we don't want a "
"military riot, I'm sure the rascals belong with the scaffold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23c38e41-a30e-45ab-9178-164f7afbad9b"
msgid ""
"\\\"We shall hold a fair for the common people. I want them to know that I hold "
"them closest to my heart.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a93ba3b0-2a2b-436d-8fe2-a3690952498e"
msgid ""
"\\\"We will hold a luxurious dinner party for the merchants. The support of our "
"wealthiest citizens is essential.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1a9c0a2-43ba-4752-8b8c-58ea14dc894b"
msgid ""
"[Gain 20 BP] \\\"I don't care to arrange anything. We can do without festivities "
"and feasts.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c78cbe74-f1f2-43bf-a327-0cd62a9cc1a5"
msgid "\\\"Make up your own mind. – I don't care who we pander to.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f1aacbe-4423-42bf-b7ec-e54b740d6f14"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian lowers his head.{/n} \\\"Greetings, {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}. I "
"am sorry to take you away from your other affairs, but your people need you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45d92e61-62e9-4902-97b2-dd3370c22ea2"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra bows briskly.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}, please spare me moment of your time. As you know, it is my "
"responsibility to hear what words are spoken when you are absent. And I must say, "
"what I have heard lately does not bring me peace. The people are suspicious of "
"their new {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}. But I know how to solve this problem.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "004bf7d9-ed9d-4f98-9718-7088e6c57407"
msgid ""
"\\\"When the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} were freed from the Stag Lord, the "
"people sighed in relief. But many are still confused by their swift change of "
"fortune. Truth be told, they simply don't know what to think of their new {mf|"
"baron|baroness|king|queen}, nor what to expect of you. Will you be a fair ruler "
"for all, or only for those of wealth and status?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df9717d6-afb0-4237-8336-84c5d5809314"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let us reassure your people – show them where your favor truly rests. Perhaps "
"a small celebration would help to win them over. Of course, you could spend the "
"same amount on a luxurious dinner for the wealthiest of your barony, but I "
"recommend organizing a fair for the common people – the ones upon whose shoulders "
"your power truly resides!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a7a3466-5c42-4e1c-872b-a12e1c88bed3"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra holds out a piece of paper.{/n} \\\"I took the liberty of composing a "
"list of the wealthiest and most influential merchants in the region. All that is "
"required of you is to hold an lavish dinner, to show them how generously their "
"support is rewarded. This would draw heavily from the treasury, but I'm sure they "
"will appreciate the gesture, and your noble attention.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "adb26afc-cfed-4f90-9451-09738016a750"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra ponders for a moment.{/n} \\\"Of course you could use the dinner money "
"instead to entertain your peasants, but I wouldn't recommend it. The whims of the "
"crowd change with the wind. They'll will forget your generosity after the first "
"bad harvest.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0592d3ed-6568-45d4-ab27-db198b78b204"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian smiles warmly.{/n} \\\"We will hold a common celebration, where "
"everyone will be welcome – including the poor and downtrodden. This is the "
"greatest gift a ruler can give to {mf|his|her} people!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ec95746-0394-4d1b-89bc-421f65896d67"
msgid ""
"\\\"Cheap populism has never done anyone any good. You'll throw your money to the "
"wind without achieving anything. But it's your decision, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db427da0-31e6-4071-910a-57d45b5b5251"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian keeps silent for a few moments. He is choosing his words very "
"carefully.{/n} \\\"It saddens me to see money that could feed the hungry and bring "
"joy to the suffering, will instead be spent on a feast for the wealthy. But if "
"that is your decision, I cannot change it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2331c117-bc42-44be-9344-30aeac8dae45"
msgid ""
"\\\"An impeccable choice, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. "
"I shall make the necessary arrangements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "00600bf0-70e7-4d7b-8c3f-07084554eace"
msgid ""
"\\\"But...\\\" {n}Tristian interrupts himself and sighs.{/n} \\\"As you wish, "
"{name}. As you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ce44a72-385c-443e-9340-8c941322cc7e"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra raises her puzzled eyebrow.{/n} \\\"Are you afraid of the extra "
"expense? You shouldn't be. But if this is your decision, so be it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19891867-c242-48f1-9b5a-8469d7b0ed18"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian's face darkens at your words, but he hides it, lowering his head.{/n} "
"\\\"Then I shall commence preparations for the folk fair.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dca10855-3ad1-43cd-8f72-24ef18ea2825"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra looks through her list.{/n} \\\"I will send out invitations to the "
"merchants today.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c9aec0f4-4d81-47bb-864a-5064eb07c46b"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I'm offering you guidance on leading your pack, so I will share my "
"wisdom. You have won this land by right of strength. But your new pack doesn't "
"know you. Are you kind or vengeful? Should they seek your favor, or flee in "
"terror? Something tells me that the one who killed the Stag Lord might become even "
"more fearsome.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a83eb7d2-7a65-431d-91bd-b48ea8aa7580"
msgid ""
"{n}You hear a rustling sound from under Tsanna' clothes, but she ends it with a "
"swift, impatient slap on her hip.{/n} \\\"Show your pack that you bring peace and "
"prosperity. Give them food. A feast is the surest way to loyalty. And make no "
"distinction between the wealthy and the poor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a99a4c3-2e5d-4f39-bf9a-a516f7d75e8a"
msgid ""
"{n}A rat's grey face peeps out of Tsanna's sleeve.{/n} \\\"Very well. The people "
"will enjoy a royal feast, and my rats will sup upon their leftovers and scraps.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "932a160a-34b1-4dbd-a2f8-b5f987a51642"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is wrong, {name}. You tease your pack by feeding the well-fed in front of "
"the hungry. If you mock the hungry brutes long enough, they'll come to you at "
"night to gnaw upon your bones. Is that not right, my children?\\\" {n}Two little "
"grey faces emerge from Tsanna's sleeves.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1b108ef-331c-4765-98ae-7343cc2a7cf8"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is your right. If you wish to be a strict leader, such gestures are beneath "
"you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7be6198-9732-4439-a790-d0abb0b07b7e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will succor your pack. Your subjects shall be fed and happy, and the traders "
"well entertained.\\\" {n}You see a rat's nose peek out from under Tsanna's hair.{/"
"n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1acc7466-980a-4424-aee9-f525b7b91d75"
msgid ""
"\\\"I know that your wealthy merchants seem the most powerful within your pack. It "
"may feel right to throw a feast for them and leave others to fight over scraps. "
"But beware of spoiling them before they prove their loyalty.\\\" {n}You hear the "
"rustling once again, and the folds of Tsanna's clothes shift and ripple.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "913336b4-95c6-4e83-830d-3827671abb5f"
msgid ""
"[Gain 30 BP] \\\"Arrest that shifty merchant immediately! He'll answer for selling "
"stolen goods, even if it happened before my time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4a9c903-898e-4f57-8fa1-0a014afc9e69"
msgid "\\\"I'd prefer to forget about this minor matter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72526c2a-8e3f-4f22-ae04-800b65764c74"
msgid "\\\"Why don't you make your own decision?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8e75654f-451d-4a04-b20f-4f37d6fbcddc"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will issue an order for free pardons. Let the peasants keep out their "
"countrymen's business.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed679f7f-322c-423b-a969-32468316c935"
msgid "Handed the criminal over to the mob."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c9b059c-4f7d-4d1f-93d4-533111c54e30"
msgid "\\\"Turn him over to the people. Let them do with him whatever they wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23870f4c-2023-4a04-a0ea-a7a36af0d2a6"
msgid ""
"{n}There is a look of determination on Tristian's face.{/n} \\\"I bring bad news "
"from your subjects. Today one of our citizens stopped me in the street, and asked "
"me to tell you something of import.\\\" {n}Tristian ponders a while, as if he "
"doesn't dare continue.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dfafe088-0ab4-44ab-a19b-e1887503d513"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. A woman approached me "
"on the street and asked me to tell you of, as she put it, a 'great injustice' in "
"the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "10b6cace-fc21-4a2b-8108-7ffbd87046a5"
msgid ""
"\\\"You see... one of the traders, who today sells imported specialties in the "
"capital, has not always led an honest life. Under the Stag Lord, he helped the "
"bandits sell stolen goods – for a percentage, of course. This scoundrel was far "
"from the fort on the day you struck the decisive blow against the Stag Lord and "
"his band, and today he continues trading in plain view of those who he recently "
"helped rob!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a17c072-0175-401e-a652-328b8fffb833"
msgid ""
"\\\"I never rush to judgment. But you must at least arrest this merchant, to "
"question him and give him a chance to repent. Think of those who see him in the "
"streets every day – walking free and unpunished for his crimes! The people appeal "
"to you for justice, {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2472ba6a-2e1e-452a-b5aa-86cf097271bb"
msgid ""
"\\\"It appears that one of the merchants doing business in the {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom} has been keeping silent about his previous ties to the Stag Lord "
"and his bandits. This trader used his position to his advantage, offering his "
"services as a tradesman to act as fence for the bandits' stolen goods. The "
"merchant was away on the day you defeated the Stag Lord, and since then he's kept "
"a low profile. The informant who brought this matter to our attention asks that "
"you to give this trader his due.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f11f466c-3952-4d46-9a16-8ffd85254354"
msgid ""
"\\\"I fear the people will continue to demand punishment for any who were able to "
"profit during the times of trouble. If you want to know my opinion, you must to do "
"more than simply ignore this bullying – you must issue a general pardon, for any "
"who weren't directly involved in violence and vandalism. Don't give these "
"squealers any more reason to stir up trouble, or you'll never hear the end of it.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8e5de58-92b4-4d6c-8771-ccbb83bd92b0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I shall order that this merchant be detained. Of course we will fully "
"investigate all these rumors and get to the truth before we judge him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2028319-b147-4b51-9451-01063cb81d80"
msgid ""
"{n}You see Shandra purse her mouth for a moment.{/n} \\\"I won't lie to you, "
"saying I understand your decision. In this situation I would act quite "
"differently. However, you are certainly in your own right.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e60e1979-9c55-47fb-a769-51eeefe2a457"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian looks away.{/n} \\\"I can't agree with this decision... but I "
"understand your reasons.\\\" {n}The priest says no more, and falls deeply into "
"thought.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "994155cd-3cb4-41cf-ba8e-befbc8192a61"
msgid "\\\"Hmm. If you think that will be enough...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cfcfc659-5c4c-4f4f-9a99-a4c2f4c5c91f"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian sighs.{/n} \\\"I will handle this. To do so, I will need to detain "
"this merchant and speak with him. I'll see to it personally.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "150a5967-4073-447e-aa20-7cb5d9285883"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I shall draft the general pardon. I am sure this will make all our lives "
"more peaceful.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "722e0fb7-7101-4e04-ae64-dc90823aa45b"
msgid ""
"\\\"A wonderful decision, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. "
"I shall prepare the order for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65fb0122-b7af-4afa-bec4-05f1b68a62d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, my confidants tell me of a wicked person in the capital. Under the "
"Stag Lord's reign, he trafficked in the bandits' stolen goods, but today he wears "
"the mask of a decent man. But we know his hands are stained with blood from his "
"ill-gotten gold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a93d7bb-7732-4593-8ee9-10697ea4a45a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, you deprive yourself of a pleasure... It's a genuine delight to look into "
"the eyes of a man, chased down by a pack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "465d7460-efcf-4d57-a1d3-6f6a598dcece"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your pack will never forget. If you fail to exercise your authority, then "
"someday someone will seize it for themselves. That will be the consequence of your "
"mistake.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b519d0e1-c4d9-44de-8793-9dfa2987cb03"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll put out the word you no longer take an interest in this merchant's life "
"or well-being. Then we'll find the perfect spot to watch the chase!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04a6009d-9d13-4159-b9dc-4d3749dfef5a"
msgid ""
"\\\"The people who were robbed by his cohorts surely know all about him. And "
"surely, they want revenge. I expect he's not the only one in the {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom}. Whatever we subject him to, the same will happen to all the "
"others who laid down with the bandits.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0182a60-b258-4129-b6ed-f3ea70032e69"
msgid ""
"\\\"What would you like to do with him? Grant him your protection? Send him to "
"prison? I see no crime in his actions, but punishing him will make your pack love "
"you. Let the crowd savage him, and they'll remember it was you who let them taste "
"his blood. They will adore you for it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5868e6df-dcd0-4123-b494-d8ca56f5ef8b"
msgid ""
"[Pay 100 BP] \\\"It would be well to open a printing house in the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92f24c48-4cbc-428a-80c8-d4e5c71881dc"
msgid "\\\"We won't be opening a printing house in the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c9713074-f060-47d2-a620-819afd2f2e89"
msgid "\\\"Make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42b25867-7ffb-4fa8-9610-c185a9fd198d"
msgid "\\\"But we have Linzi's printing shop. Why do we need another one?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6fc3d8c-b02d-45bd-8270-285067efeb92"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's something important I wanted to discuss with you.\\\" {n}Meeting your "
"eyes, Tristian looks away, as if perplexed.{/n} \\\"It's not easy to admit, but "
"recently the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} has grown so much that I feel it "
"slipping my grasp. Please, ease my burden by finding someone for the position of "
"curator of arts and education.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a289eade-187d-4493-ab52-c82576009eff"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian catches his breath and smiles brightly.{/n} \\\"It's a huge weight off "
"my shoulders! I have other news as well, which I'm sure you will find agreeable. "
"As you know, our neighbor, {g|Galt}Galt{/g}, has been in chaos for years. Their "
"ever-changing rulers destroy that which goes against their fickle doctrines, "
"including scientists and creators. But one of them was recently able to escape – "
"to your lands!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31dbdd87-e967-4a94-9890-da7e0cdb165b"
msgid ""
"\\\"He's the publisher of a newspaper, whose headquarters in {g|Galt}Galt{/g} were "
"burnt down after false accusations of slander. He wishes to move to the capital "
"where he will enjoy your protection, and in exchange he has offered to found a new "
"printing house! He escaped Galt with his plans for a printing machine with him, "
"and is ready to start his business here – with your permission and help, of "
"course. I think it's a wonderful opportunity – not only to get our own newspaper, "
"but to help an innocent man get back on his feet. What do you say?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12dd96c3-09d3-42e8-92e3-6432e8e95fad"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra looks thoughtful.{/n} \\\"I am trying to solve a problem, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. You see... my responsibilities "
"require me to focus on the most important problems of the {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom}... meanwhile, less important issues – particularly relating to "
"culture, art and education – are left unattended. The only way out I can see is to "
"find a curator, who may deal with these nuances, and free me to focus fully on our "
"more urgent affairs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3244d1d7-9a51-4be5-aa68-3481c7e2c202"
msgid ""
"\\\"Anyway, I've come to speak with you of another issue. There's a man from Galt "
"here in your lands, seeking asylum. He's different from the other sorry refugees, "
"fleeing {g|Galt}Galt's{/g} unending flames of revolution: this one used to have "
"his own newspaper press. Today all he possesses is a lingering ambition, and the "
"plans for a printing machine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdab6e76-c705-4519-9718-463c93c5aa9e"
msgid ""
"\\\"You've probably guessed where I'm going with this. Much can be said against "
"Galt, but not for its lack of technical progress. I believe that founding a "
"printing house in the capital, run by an experienced manager, would reflect well "
"upon our population's education and enlightenment. Besides, as patron you would "
"control what would be printed in this workshop.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50e6f45f-67c3-4a1d-8a98-ea3d3e70b063"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna pats the two-headed rat peeping out from her clothes.{/n} \\\"{name}, "
"everything is going smoothly in your domain. The people have filled their bellies, "
"and now they crave beauty. However, my vision of beauty... is slightly differs "
"from yours. Find a new advisor who can deal with the issues of art and culture.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a43ca4b-b80f-40d0-abb0-8dc3483aed45"
msgid ""
"\\\"Before you find one, there's something I'd like to discuss. A poor fellow, a "
"typographer from {g|Galt}Galt{/g}, has come here seeking refuge with us. To show "
"his gratitude, he'd like to open a publishing house in the capital. My job is to "
"deliver the message, but if you want my opinion, it is this: send him away.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e0c5094-98c4-45f2-8fda-6d712521a193"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's difficult enough to manage a pack of scholars and academics. It's even "
"worse that this fellow is already someone else's prey. Don't stand in the way of "
"the {g|Galt}Galt{/g} hounds that chase him. It could end up worse than you can "
"imagine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9efc23c4-7877-4208-b578-77756def2e23"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful! I shall immediately send a messenger to the poor fellow, and inform "
"him of your decision!\\\" {n}Tristian's eye flash with excitement.{/n} \\\"You "
"have saved another soul from hopelessness and despair!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91016432-b504-4617-857a-9286bcf00fea"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am happy we're of the same opinion on the matter. I'll make sure this "
"runaway receives a fair welcome in the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7338836c-fa40-44a3-8a28-46d8e49df563"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian sighs.{/n} \\\"I am very, very sorry... well, I hope this refugee "
"finds a home somewhere else.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84f2b8c8-a2cf-49a8-8423-2b430a6c0744"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra thinks for a few moments.{/n} \\\"I understand. You don't want trouble "
"with {g|Galt}Galt's{/g} authorities. Who knows what hunters chase this refugee. "
"Your decision is quite reasonable. I shall do as you say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fec88d2-a259-4a68-a6ed-6eab21a6e127"
msgid ""
"\\\"You'll cause trouble for your pack. The day you pay for this mistake will "
"surely be a black day indeed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4020d54a-ff08-425f-be68-548344781c17"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agree. I'll make sure this refugee is driven from your lands as quickly as "
"possible.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "93590ab0-f3ba-429f-8f42-fba006a98f6d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I will immediately send a messenger with an invitation to the capital. "
"Forgive my haste, but I just can't stand by and watch someone suffering.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "365e8164-5560-4d28-9f54-0271a26ff2a9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I insist we open a printing house. Don't worry – I shall make all the "
"necessary arrangements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec9aa90c-cd57-41e7-9901-0ff08459b8db"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll chase him from the capital, {name}. And I will make sure he never "
"approaches our borders again.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea81c63c-8c0c-47c8-9218-a76b3b1ba987"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian smiles.{/n} \\\"Linzi publishes books, not newspapers. I doubt she'd "
"be interested in this kind of endeavor. And our guest from {g|Galt}Galt{/g} "
"specializes in it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b02b41a-1282-4959-bd35-db6aaa775dfb"
msgid ""
"\\\"With all due respect, Linzi is far too creative to manage newspaper "
"publishing. It demands certain discipline – which, I am sure, this publisher from "
"{g|Galt}Galt{/g} possesses.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ffacaa7-0bb2-4cce-8a0b-ccb9346b384e"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna smiles sarcastically.{/n} \\\"All the more reason to reject the "
"refugee's offer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de0ac2c6-7de2-479a-9d46-29e0eccba2a3"
msgid "\\\"Exempt this merchant from taxes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1735a7a1-715b-4fbe-b397-ed73030d93c4"
msgid "\\\"Tell him that the law in my domain applies equally to all.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bfa1ecfb-6316-4a92-85ec-4ed38c28d8d4"
msgid "Executed the trader for attempted bribery."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a334793f-abb7-4cf9-80b5-e218269d5c74"
msgid ""
"[Gain 5000 gold and 40 BP] \\\"This corrupt tradesman will pay for his insolence. "
"Arrest and execute him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f66eaaa-8f92-4639-baf4-0f6d01baf01e"
msgid "\\\"I trust your advice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f4c3639-93aa-4694-91b9-befd3eaaaabf"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, a local merchant wishes to be relieved of his taxes, which naturally "
"stands against the laws of the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}. In return for "
"this… service... he promises to put in a good word for you among the city's trade "
"community.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eeaac375-d784-4c78-b5fc-fc474651656e"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I've curious news for "
"you. A local merchant is trying to bribe you. He wants his new salt-production "
"shop relieved of trade taxes. In return, he promises to act as your 'patron' among "
"the {mf|barony's|barony's|kingdom's|kingdom's} trade community.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1dc251d4-51e7-45a8-903a-822fd278d428"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, a merchant is offering you a business deal. He wants one of his shops "
"relieved of trade taxes. This certainly goes against our laws. However, in return "
"he promises to put in a good word for you among the high society of tradesmen.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5701b2ac-3030-4a62-a82b-454708814b13"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian blinks, perplexed.{/n} \\\"You... You're not joking, are you? So you "
"will turn your back on the equality of your subjects, in favor of those who so "
"easily buy and sell others?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d4c41693-f673-44c7-80e8-968595d9ec0a"
msgid ""
"\\\"This deal proves your visionary leadership, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}. The well-being of the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|"
"kingdom}... and of your treasury... relies on these people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16a04dee-984b-4a7f-b8e0-cc348ac3f74b"
msgid ""
"\\\"You shouldn't flirt with these men who imagine they own things, {name}. Now "
"that they've bought you, they'll find some way to sell you for a good price.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0959a4b7-6351-4527-9aef-6ceefe71603b"
msgid ""
"\\\"You'll have to turn down many similar offers. But eventually people will come "
"to realize that the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} have changed forever. "
"Henceforth, everyone is equal before the law.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff037751-b923-4e21-9ae5-18fb6396b68e"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra's voice is notably cold.{/n} \\\"You're playing with fire, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. These people may become dangerous "
"if they decide you threaten their most important possession – their wealth.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab1e1fb5-b44a-4274-9fc2-f7645dd5e07b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Is that all? You expect him to be grateful for your lenience? He's going to "
"harbor a grudge anyway. You should have gotten rid of him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6f18386-18ab-49ce-b3e9-7a8049198711"
msgid ""
"\\\"Isn't such a verdict too strict? It's only money, after all. Can we blame him "
"for living so long in an evil, lawless country that he eventually acquired "
"something of a bandit's mentality?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c5d5f744-f233-4a30-9f7a-18572cbf39a2"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra looks at you politely, her voice soft and slightly indifferent.{/n} \\"
"\"This is a grave mistake, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. "
"You turn all the wealthy people of the domain against you. Money may not be the "
"only source of power, but it is among the mightiest.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "990f8e65-7520-4032-bb61-52d090dbe7e9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will be sure his colleagues are aware of how painful his death was. May they "
"mind their own business in the future – and not forget what happens to those who "
"fail to do so.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "607945e1-1f61-41f1-8995-b5756bb38a25"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian's voice is very soft.{/n} \\\"I realize that such offer might stir you "
"to outrage. But try to understand, greed can cloud anyone's judgment, wealthy and "
"pauper alike. We must teach these people that the times have changed. The law no "
"longer serves only the rich. Reject his offer, but refrain from punishing him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55d9be2a-1d24-4f85-8c71-6b609465c76b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Surely, this fool is merely a symbol. He himself is not important. But all the "
"influential people of the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} are holding their "
"breaths, waiting for your decision. They need to know they can do business with "
"us, or we'll be seen as a danger. If I were you, I wouldn't want to look like a "
"fanatic, or a hostage of my own principles. Approve this small request, and be "
"done with this greedy fellow.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e97bb70-75f0-4974-aaca-abe000622cab"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's good he's come to you. It means he knows who the leader is. It's bad he "
"didn't come to beg, but instead offers to buy. This is disrespectful. The insolent "
"worm must be punished. The pack needs to see fear in his eyes, and remember "
"forever that your good will can never be bought and sold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12c6bd07-20c9-401e-be2d-9c89eac762a7"
msgid ""
"\\\"You obviously have some strategy, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. But I cannot approve of your methods, so as your Councilor I will fare "
"poorly at providing the assistance you need. It only makes sense for me to retire "
"after fulfilling this order. You can recruit an advisor whose thoughts are more "
"attuned to your own.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c65f002d-cf3f-4e43-a737-648dd6751a74"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm sorry, but we regard caring for your subjects very differently. I cannot "
"countenance the way you exercise power. I am an unwilling participant in this, and "
"I cannot be a part of it any longer. Your order will be carried out, but after "
"this I will resign, and leave my position vacant for another candidate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b75e1b7c-652d-4206-ba4d-a975443210b9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I warned you I do not wish to argue. It's not my advice you reject. You "
"dismiss the wisdom of the great goddess, who is far more ancient than all of us. "
"This means you will have to do without my opinion in the future. I will fulfill "
"your order, but then you will find yourself a new advisor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7d4f354-0e9e-46ee-97f4-04cd2ec3b0cc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Throw the mercenaries out of the capital. They're making trouble, so they have "
"to go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ee753c0-23cb-44e8-aecd-5f8e71539cb3"
msgid ""
"[Pay 100 BP] \\\"Finance more guards from the treasury. Make sure the merchants' "
"guards don't fight with the common people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f45b224b-d2d7-45cb-9373-ec4d6fa37613"
msgid ""
"\\\"Send our citizens the message that these mercenaries are under our protection."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb631255-6dcf-4cd6-9d2a-d4e68868e563"
msgid "\\\"You decide, and it's done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7743fb7e-acfd-47eb-bcda-1b6313f92d99"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, the situation has become rather fraught. A group of mercenaries "
"arrived in our lands to seek a better future. They've banded together for safety. "
"Some have been hired by our merchants as bodyguards.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ccf2e00-c497-46bb-af30-18cb2874db03"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's an issue that requires your attention. Tensions are rising between the "
"locals and a group of mercenaries that came at the capital to earn an income. Some "
"have been hired by wealthy merchants who can afford bodyguards.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e213786-bff2-4bd7-9207-6b2bbbf95e58"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, there is trouble in the city. A group of mercenaries arrived at the "
"capital. The people don't seem to like them, so they've banded together for "
"safety. These vagabonds seek work, and some of them have been hired by the "
"merchants. {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} blessed these people with strength and a love "
"for fighting, so why not use them?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d805d8ee-c3a9-43a3-9c90-4f136f710e5f"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian's voice sounds sad.{/n} \\\"You may be right. Not everyone is capable "
"of living side by side in peace. Nevertheless, it's a shame if we never try to "
"change things.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba3d8463-d809-4aac-b7ee-0aab3253311a"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra shrugs.{/n} \\\"This was short-sighted. They'll be replaced by someone "
"else, who the crowd will dislike even more. It's only a question of time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26ebd2ef-f0fe-4cd2-bb5e-0fa98eb892f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"You can't judge a predator for killing sheep. It's the natural order of "
"things, which neither you nor I can control. Banishing someone who makes your pack "
"stronger is... foolish. Truly foolish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0802d22-b90b-49f2-b804-a686758decff"
msgid ""
"\\\"Whatever money we spend on new guards, it will be worth it, if it prevents any "
"more blood from being spilled.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b7fd308-5b87-4db8-8ddc-9b947632b7ef"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra raises her eyebrow.{/n} \\\"Where will this lead? Do you expect the "
"peasants will appreciate it? They'll just find something new to hate tomorrow, and "
"you'll be the one to blame. You can't afford to solve all their problems.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9075de2a-7e9a-4573-a7ba-cb3ae2d1fa50"
msgid ""
"\\\"All right. In the future, I hope the two packs, the mercenaries' and yours, "
"will merge into one. Powerful... invincible.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dfc5dd40-3078-4512-8142-1b25935d8634"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian lowers his head. His voice is barely audible.{/n} \\\"So this is how "
"highly you value your merchants' comfort? Their bodyguards will become insolent "
"under your protection. They'll start openly insulting the citizens. And finally, "
"these outlanders, servants of the wealthy, will rule the city, not its citizens.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14706482-cc15-4780-a117-f16133f62629"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very wise. Allow the merchants to do as they like, and their coin will fill "
"your coffers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c75ef8c-4dce-4e45-8fab-73bb12b74b6d"
msgid ""
"\\\"You lock your subjects in a cage with savage cutthroats. Very well, let the "
"strong survive, and the weak perish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8d06cb3-e2f8-456f-9f1a-4e4d9aed002c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll draw from the treasury to hire more guards and avoid provocation. In the "
"future, I hope the two packs, the mercenaries' and yours, will merge into one. "
"Powerful... invincible.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "549161ce-1d5a-4056-8d2c-0f3f53e122ee"
msgid ""
"\\\"Alas, their manners are low, and the locals are prejudiced against them. They "
"fight more and more often. The peasants want us to banish the mercenaries from the "
"city. The merchants expect us to protect them, regardless of the peasants' "
"complaints.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2da72e70-5a95-40a9-9c43-79b9b8eec4be"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you ask me, we mustn't surrender to hatred. This matter should be resolved "
"peacefully. Draw from the treasury to finance more guards. They'll put an end to "
"these clashes. Nothing's going to change if we simply choose sides. We must "
"mediate, though this takes money and a will for peace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24fe47b8-6d19-4602-83d6-10bce272d659"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course, the citizens regard them as brutes and bruisers – stereotypes to "
"which they gladly conform. The people call us to eject this mob from the city. "
"However, this would be a mistake. Think how helpful the loyal merchants' troops "
"will be, if ever the peasants riot.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "950e7afa-a59b-4e67-806c-fb5046222258"
msgid ""
"\\\"Turn a deaf ear to those who encourage you to expel the mercenaries. It won't "
"make us popular among the people, but these mercenaries may prove useful. Nor "
"should you listen to the peasants who demand your guards to protect them against "
"the unruly brutes. There will always be clashes between different layers of "
"society. You must support the more useful ones, and arrest those who provoke the "
"mercenaries' bodyguards.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9d9962f-9b79-48ca-a7fb-af264414540e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Alas, the citizens despise these mercenaries. They insult them behind their "
"backs, and spit where they step. They provoke them, taunt them into fights, and "
"then scream bloody murder when they get what they're asking for. Your cowardly "
"people need to learn the meaning of strength. Let them see that there's a bigger "
"fish now to be reckoned with. You won't let the weakest of your tribe force you to "
"expel the strongest, will you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ac913bc-aabd-4d8b-bd5d-e097e8ef96d8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let the merchants know that their efforts are not required. If they touch any "
"vessels that isn't theirs, we will have to resort to force.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15e0b3f3-8c1e-49c9-afd7-a2f504d9634e"
msgid "\\\"Let the merchants and their mercenaries do as they will.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0de174b7-a9d6-43c8-a9e2-85a5075673ef"
msgid "\\\"Don't involve me in their fate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97d0a969-545d-4686-99ed-7b40711b977e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tell the guards stay away from the dispute. The stronger will have the right "
"to trading on the river.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b9d9f5c2-697c-4209-a5ab-d92b06688e17"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, a situation has developed. We must decide if we shall follow the "
"letter of the law, or do what my heart tells me is right.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "259f8f67-ff5d-49c4-80b6-c966318a88c3"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I require your judgment on a sensitive matter. The vessels of river "
"travellers have entered your frontiers. They sell cheap goods for nearly nothing, "
"and of course, they pay no taxes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fbb33542-4839-40a8-91db-d58bacf83d73"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, {name}. The law doesn't always grant protection to those in need.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e5e2a15-2e22-4b5c-ace5-1acd0a6728f3"
msgid ""
"\\\"So the merchants may freely butcher the travellers? But the travellers cannot "
"lay a finger on the merchants else they be branded criminals? That doesn't sound "
"like a fair fight to me. Your laws, for some reason, protect the weak from the "
"strong, when instead they should be rewarding strength wherever it may be found.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28ed2c12-cc02-444c-895f-345f10aa20ff"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian winces.{/n} \\\"This is a harsh act. You condemn not only the "
"travellers, but our people who will no longer see the travellers' floating stores "
"upon their shores. I'm sorry you've made this decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea9b2154-09f1-4a88-9ae0-914a72dda80b"
msgid ""
"\\\"But it's the merchants that pay you, not the travellers. Do you punish those "
"who submit? Do you protect those who deny you respect? This is a strange decision, "
"{name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3cbe139b-0865-4e1e-9a22-017f25e4b222"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will forbid this insanity. Let the merchants trade with those who can afford "
"luxuries. Meanwhile, leave the poor in peace, to buy what they can afford from the "
"traveler vessels.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "237c1851-e858-4032-a644-644e4b736c60"
msgid ""
"\\\"Travelers' merchant vessels roam the rivers of the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen "
"Lands{/g}. They sell low-priced goods, and bypass the official fees. They sell "
"nothing special, of course. Cheap clothes, utensils, simple tools. These are life-"
"savers for our peasants, who can afford little else. However, the merchants are "
"unhappy with the current situation. They wish to fund a boat squad to hunt down "
"and sink the travelers' boats.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f54d2a4e-bf7e-4403-92b9-f4f20a0bd343"
msgid ""
"\\\"The merchants are allegedly enforcing the laws, and fighting against the sales "
"of stolen property. But in fact they're only greedy to control the small "
"percentage of goods that the travellers live on. It's up to you to decide what we "
"should do. I'm sure you can see why this troubles me. We must interfere and "
"prevent this injustice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2fd1a609-ea51-4897-b118-a94c920255ef"
msgid ""
"\\\"But your moneybags merchants hate competition. They're assembling a squad of "
"boats to hunt down the travellers, sink their boats, and drive them from your "
"lands. It's simple greed that drives them, but they are on the right track.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e614daf5-74e5-4e60-956c-ce467fc3de03"
msgid ""
"\\\"My suggestion is to stay out of this. The river travellers are a hardy, "
"teeming people, much like termites. They please {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g}, and we "
"shouldn't trouble them unless we must. If the merchants decide to strike at them, "
"we should order the guard not to interfere. The waters will run red with blood, "
"and the river people will call upon their relatives from the neighboring lands, "
"and together they'll show the traders what they're made of. Those who are strong "
"will remain, to seek their fortune in our lands. And we will profit no matter the "
"outcome.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5629670b-5dd0-43d1-b639-f24d8f2df5f7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, there's something that requires your immediate attention. As "
"you probably know, there are travellers, humble merchant tribes of mixed origins, "
"sailing up and down the river, selling essentials to our peasants. They pay no "
"taxes, and answer to no authority. The merchants have decided to put an end to "
"their lawlessness. They're assembling a squad of boats to send those travellers "
"packing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72297121-5019-42cf-86a3-d6344bdd373d"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a good start, although I expect we'll have certain issues with these new "
"enforcers. It's an abuse of justice to some extent. I suggest you legalize their "
"actions before they arouse civil unrest. After all, it's your law that they're "
"upholding.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49686e3c-fa44-4923-80de-610e8e2c7cc3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes, let the stronger win. If the merchants cannot protect their interests, "
"let ones who are smarter and more skilled do the work instead. If the travellers "
"are ousted, then their spirit and their flesh were too weak. They would have died "
"either way. In either case, our pack stays strong, and the weak are culled.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30386123-8ee4-4a06-8862-1f6fc5d11376"
msgid ""
"\\\"What a surprising decision, your Highness. The merchants only mean to pursue "
"your own law, while the travellers are nothing but criminals, thieves, and tax "
"evaders – just like their customers. I have no idea how you hope to earn the love "
"of your subjects, if you deprive them of their income and violate your own laws!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "443a3dc7-36a7-4f38-b480-3a6748b16f8d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let the merchants give those petty thieves the boot. It's time we make it "
"clear that {kingdomname} is {kingdomname}, not the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/"
"g}! It's civilized now. There's an order to things!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3dd8cc36-aa7a-4ba8-8865-aa630dffcb1a"
msgid ""
"\\\"The land must bear fruit and feed the people, not amuse a crowd of wealthy "
"crooks. Allow the peasants to plow these new fields.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "202cee49-1001-42f9-991c-df2b3258acd9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't want any problems with the merchants. Let the peasants find themselves "
"another field to plow.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c5c0f6f-ea15-4053-94b1-8972dfadb0fe"
msgid "\\\"I trust your judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0759ab7-73f3-4880-99dd-7434aa59333b"
msgid "\\\"Take the oak grove. It is my gift for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bc45fdb1-5e57-4981-93ef-e691c6f42050"
msgid ""
"\\\"There are more and more workers in the kingdom, and our farmers require plots "
"of fruitful soil. The ordinary people regard you as their defender against the "
"iniquity of the merchants. And they have come to you with a request.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "658a60ce-d650-4486-be85-e74130261187"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, your subjects grow countless, like a swarm of locusts. They require "
"food, and there is not enough cropland. Hunger brings them to you. They seek your "
"permission to plow an ancient oak grove. It is said that the wealthy use this "
"forest for entertainment, hunting for sport. They won't like it if you take away "
"their toy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8643ab64-8116-4e46-a69c-9360ef0fad9e"
msgid ""
"\\\"You are merciful. The people will never forget who granted them land for their "
"honest labor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e86effc-e3b2-428d-b0a2-0317732070c9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I wish you had given them to me. But I understand. You must think of your own "
"pack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66de558a-b8a5-4ef3-b8a2-62b814adc5f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"It doesn't seem you care much for your pack, allowing a bunch of moneybags "
"merchants to entertain themselves in a place that might instead have fed your "
"starving people... not to mention the children of {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "024514a9-062b-4ce7-89e6-6b8863cfd036"
msgid ""
"\\\"But where? There aren't that many patches of fertile soil! It's a shame that "
"the miseries of a crowd of hungry peasants mean less to the kingdom than the "
"amusements of a few well-fed idlers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b29c3c9-8998-4e55-95c9-a19ac9d1ff3f"
msgid ""
"\\\"The oak groves will be restricted to everyone except my pack. The children of "
"{g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} will finally have a place in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen "
"Lands{/g} where they can be free!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d6102a4-17c8-4c60-b87f-20a2e4dd0d83"
msgid ""
"\\\"But the earth must bear fruit, not serve as a playground. But I know better "
"than to chop down old trees or give them as playthings for the idle. Grant this "
"territory to me and my pack! My wards long for a place of their own, where they "
"can escape persecution... and your pack may take all the rest. The children of {g|"
"Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} will keep away from your other lands, and leave them to be "
"safe for your pack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "441ea647-49da-4aba-b0f8-aecaa201732b"
msgid ""
"{n}Tsanna's smile is predatory.{/n} \\\"I can hear happy laughter. It's my "
"goddess! We shall drink blood to our heart's content. We shall glut ourselves in "
"celebration. We will produce beautiful monsters under that canopy of trees. We "
"shall leave to your subjects all the game and farmland around the area. Thank you, "
"{name}! You won't be sorry.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7bc0598d-8b71-4f8b-8ffd-7d9350a7f0a4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your subjects wish to clear and plow some nearby oak groves, where wealthy "
"men, both local and {g|Brevoy}Brevan{/g}, have hunted in sport for many years. The "
"merchants won't like it, but I'm sure you can see that food for the children and "
"the elderly is far more important than sports for the idle? Wouldn't you agree?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b1422e5-1326-4494-bada-4b0a0dc25ccb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, your protection of the rabble has borne fruit. Now the peasants "
"are demanding a permit to level the oak grove near the capital. They want to use "
"the land as a field to plant crops. But you see, the wealthy merchants have "
"enjoyed hunting there for years. They won't be happy of another violation of their "
"privileges. Take my advice. Don't turn the influential class against you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3439e4d9-7e9b-469d-92d8-83de3f00a2cf"
msgid ""
"\\\"Trust me, the love of the people is fickle. No matter how much you give them, "
"they'll forget everything at the first petty problem. Mind you, the wealthy class "
"has a significantly better memory. They will remember if you stand up for them – "
"or against them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98ded162-a0b7-4dd6-9deb-5e2a0dd1e5db"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect. The forest will stay. The peasants will just have to make do with the "
"food they have. The merchants will be grateful for this gesture.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51826663-c5ec-4761-8365-9f76eb7f4aef"
msgid ""
"\\\"The free market isn't going anywhere, no matter what the merchants might want."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "258b5d06-8ea7-4e01-8bb5-d13ea91b2c0b"
msgid "\\\"I like the merchants' idea. Let all trade go through the guild.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38ef045a-10dc-4250-b2e1-6e8e022a6d63"
msgid "\\\"I trust your opinion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32a5d66e-497b-400a-9c1b-172e4e10c290"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian looks morose.{/n} \\\"It appears that the merchants have decided they "
"can do whatever they like in your kingdom. They're asking you to control the free "
"market! Do you even realize what that means? From now on, our farmers won't be "
"allowed to sell their own crops for themselves. They'll have to hand over their "
"goods to the trade guild for distribution – at prices specified by the merchants!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "533fdf0a-d320-46cd-b5b2-07d9b5769949"
msgid ""
"\\\"The merchants have come to me with a strange request. They regard you as their "
"champion and defender, and it appears they've come up with another way to get "
"rich. They want you to deny the free market!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53c24011-3ee0-4eb8-8319-31070b9b2bb2"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian bows his head.{/n} \\\"Thank you. It's a noble thing to protect your "
"subjects against the despotism of the rich.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06590f2b-295d-4ad0-b25c-696854dc9fd0"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're doing the wise thing. When someone goes too far, you take them by the "
"throat and shake them a little. It's what leaders do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43e976af-8fbf-41ca-a916-4d775141a99a"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian remains silent for a while, and then begins to speak as if he's alone, "
"addressing an empty room.{/n} \\\"Will the merchants ever have enough gold, so "
"they can finally leave the people alone? Will the people's cries ever be heard in "
"this hall?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b2e4754-fd13-4788-9d7b-b535a6961f28"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't know much about trade, but I do know that the one who controls the "
"food controls the pack. You've just made a grave mistake, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2308cd3-db5b-47ee-b768-3ebf8dd6a6a3"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will inform the people that free trade in our kingdom will go on as always.\\"
"\" {n}Tristian's voice turns from relieved to sarcastic.{/n} \\\"The merchants "
"will just have to be happy with the vast riches they already have!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "67b720d8-96e6-40e6-86b7-d96071005a9a"
msgid ""
"\\\"In that case, let the merchants tame their appetites. I wouldn't deliver even "
"a tiny scrap of power into their hands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7136d124-72ee-4359-b7ef-481606f25805"
msgid ""
"\\\"Excuse me for being blunt, but this is the most shameless exploitation of the "
"people that I've ever heard of. We will disgrace ourselves if we allow the "
"merchants to dictate this to us. We cannot grant their request. – Let us stand on "
"the people's side this time at least.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f83bc415-822d-407b-92d6-d943ea4dd0ec"
msgid ""
"\\\"From now on, farmers would be obliged to hand over their goods to the trade "
"guild at a price set by the guild, who will them possess the power of distribution "
"as well. I'm no good at trade, but the whole situation stinks. They want more "
"control. More power. Don't give it to them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0b3b2a9-5cee-4b3b-940c-aadf70ad9ba4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, the merchants of the kingdom have a request for you. They are "
"looking to consolidate trade in the farming markets. The farmers will be obliged "
"to hand over their goods to the trade guild at fair market prices, ensuring their "
"prosperity and saving them the trouble of bringing their goods to market. This is "
"a wise decision and would strengthen the merchant class. I would support it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4cca43b-64f1-4a08-8a35-55d357e8ef16"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect. We will support the merchants. There's no reliable aristocracy among "
"the landowners, which makes the merchants the strongest class in the kingdom. As "
"we make them even stronger, we strengthening your own power.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac1420b3-030a-4e19-9ce0-e9ba9660edf6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmm... This is unwise. You don't have any landed nobles here, as we do in "
"Brevoy. Trade is your kingdom's only tangible source of income. A ban on free "
"trade would have strengthened the powerful class here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44328ea9-25c8-47fa-be9d-ac96be38b88e"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian looks worried but unafraid.{/n} \\\"{name}, your life is in danger. "
"The merchants are angry with you for protecting your subjects against their plots, "
"and now they conspire against you. Luckily, the people are loyal to you, and one "
"of your loyal servants reported this treasonous outrage.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "201dd8a2-4a16-4927-a7f1-bd4d26ac1fd8"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, the merchants have had enough of your rule. They've suffered heavy "
"losses, and now they conspire against you. Luckily, one of your citizens overheard "
"them plotting, and reported their treason to me."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a4a9afb-87dd-4c41-b817-d54925400b65"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must make up our minds how to prevent this attack and neutralize the "
"conspirators. One options is to entrust your Treasurer with bribing some of them. "
"Another is to order your Minister to eliminate the traitors in secret. But that's "
"more their style, not ours. There's not enough time to call in the troops, but if "
"your Regent addresses the people, your faithful people will rally around you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e00c6cd1-dc4a-4337-8780-b2ab388348cb"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must strike first! A coward would send a Treasurer with a purse, to reward "
"those who would renounce the conspiracy. Someone more naive might send a Regent, "
"in hopes of reaching the people's hearts, calling them to stand united and protect "
"the crown even in the face of their enemy's blades. I advise you to show more "
"wisdom. Visit upon them precisely what they plot to visit upon you. Order your "
"Minister to send assassins to the homes of the conspiracy's leader. Decapitate the "
"conspiracy, and no harm will come to you. They will be like a pack whose leader "
"was gutted on a horn.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ad3aab7-8db7-4af0-9bcf-5a691f161189"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, several prominent merchants of the capital are conspiring "
"against you. You are loved by ordinary people, and one of the servants reported "
"the conspiracy. We expect the merchants to dispatch an assassin.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7bf5744-05dd-4e42-8343-6ad759721e60"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could send the Minister's assassins to deal with these malcontents, or ask "
"the Regent to call upon the people for protection. But I have a better plan. Order "
"your Treasurer to bribe several of these errant merchants. If they come over to "
"our side, the rebels will stop trusting each other, and the conspiracy will fall "
"apart without any casualties.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "03d8306b-a351-4712-8d25-14eab039bd48"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's trouble in the capital, {name}. The people can no longer bear the "
"oppression of the merchant class. Your patronage brought you the affection and "
"loyalty of the merchants, but has driven your poor people into rage and despair. "
"The peasants are prepared to go out into the streets and destroy the wealthy "
"neighborhoods. I understand the feelings of who are sickened by poverty and "
"injustice, but we must intervene if we wish to prevent a massacre.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f45fc388-684e-45f4-943c-6f4061b870e4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Like I've always said, it's dangerous to taunt a hungry pack. And I was right. "
"The merchants are bleeding people dry, like fat spiders sucking out their "
"lifeblood. And your people have had enough. Everyone is talking about the riots "
"that the peasants are planning in the wealthy quarters. You must intervene, or "
"you'll lose your power and position.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "931ad517-256b-4a45-a23b-51d27775d77e"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could order the Warden to gather the capital guards, and stop the crowd "
"without spilling any blood. You might also order your Minister to kill the "
"people's leaders, although it pains me even to think of it... They are only "
"ordinary starving people, you know. You shouldn't try to resolve this matter by "
"force. Send in your Treasurer! Let them have some gold for their families. It'll "
"soothe down their wrath.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b57738d-5093-4167-8e46-a2dd8223dd7c"
msgid ""
"\\\"All they really want is gold. We could ask your Treasurer to distribute some "
"gold... If they promise obedience. Or we could send the Warden's guards to stop "
"them, though I wouldn't recommend it. The guards have families, and they too bear "
"a grudge against the merchants. It's best if the Minister sends forth his faithful "
"assassins. If they make a sudden display of force, and drain the lives of the "
"loudest among the mob, then the rest will see this and flee in terror.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3087a44c-7bec-4ae1-b3fa-486ba172db18"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, there's a riot in the capital. A drunken, bloodthirsty mob is "
"heading to the trade district to pillage the merchants and burn down their homes. "
"This riot must be stopped!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0481198-f0b4-4227-b8be-e94db6e4a738"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could send the Treasurer to bribe the mob with gold. We could also dispatch "
"the Minister's assassins to deal with the instigators. But take my best advice. "
"Let the Warden call up the guards to disperse the crowd.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24097a31-a3bb-4615-b482-a2fac3d0d422"
msgid ""
"{n}Wodga, priest of Kurgess, salutes you vigorously, and flashes an excited smile."
"{/n} \\\"Your Highness, your army grows stronger by the hour! Your warriors loved "
"Kurgess' lessons! A few have already committed themselves to his religion. Many "
"more will join them, I expect. But it's not only your warriors that are interested "
"in our faith.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7bee9a31-47b5-431c-a7b8-83a622591ed8"
msgid ""
"{n}Captain Romelo gives you a sneaky wink.{/n} \\\"Reporting for duty! It's good "
"to see you in good health! Your first and second crossbow troops have finished "
"training and equipping! Your ballistaire squads are receiving their heavy weapons "
"today. I'd love to see the local bandits' faces when they see your troops in their "
"new formations!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c54449b5-9437-46d1-a26a-527c557ed33a"
msgid ""
"{n}Raquillata nods curtly.{/n} \\\"Your Highness, last night's military exercises "
"were successful. Instructors from the Wands Brigade, acting as opposing force, was "
"successfully repelled by your mages! The training of your first class is "
"completed. The Brigade is now accepting students for the second class!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d571ee2-3094-487e-8ef8-21bdcd7c0a7a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your citizens don't want to be weak and sick either, so they've taken a "
"natural interest in Kurgess. I thought – why don't we build a temple here, "
"complete with bathing ponds? There's a place in foothills where a small creek "
"flows. The water is warm, and it can heal diseases and fill your body with "
"strength.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79e4ec34-b261-484e-84a0-8d71471624ce"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've a message from my employers. My company is eager to open a proving ground "
"to test our new products. – Somewhere far away from Alkenstar and it industrial "
"spies, and somewhere protected by a reliable and influential ally, able to "
"safeguard the factory's property and its secrets.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15a25202-c4b4-4013-9e2b-7e1467c1923a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, you seem to be a respectable person to deal with. Would you "
"like to open a small... manufacturing center in your domain? It would be to your "
"benefit! You should think about it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d765b90-e73b-4000-8a88-bf2d79e669b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Since everything has worked out so well, I have an offer for you. The Wands "
"Brigade would like to settle down. Most of us desire a home and a family more than "
"war and endless military campaigning. And we have grown to like your kingdom. If "
"you allow us to settle down here, it would surely be for your own good as well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4f7a316b-0c9b-4337-bc83-1eecf11f4b30"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've seen so many different magical weapons over the years! Dwarven axes, "
"elven bows, wonders from {g|Katapesh}Katapesh{/g} beyond description... We've "
"studied them all, and our masters can easily reproduce these masterpieces. With "
"your support we could set up a guild where we'll enchant the best weapons in {g|"
"Avistan}Avistan{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "123d17ae-8ae2-41d8-9b76-56702c6e4f27"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let the people rest their bodies and souls there. Other priests from our "
"church can come to offer their teachings. I hope you like the idea. Kurgess "
"bestows blessings upon the lands wherever he is worshipped.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "361b7f32-f321-4ecf-8598-9df4efaf5a49"
msgid "\\\"That's great news! Thank you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac61a924-8370-4df1-ad92-ca5f160611ce"
msgid "\\\"Why do I have the feeling that I've made a huge mistake?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db121d2f-1a0c-4317-9811-853ebd019113"
msgid "\\\"The credit goes for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "78e40aa3-3b52-400d-b9f9-8203e5e0a218"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar grins, pride glowing in his eyes.{/n} \\\"You know, I've been thinking "
"about which of our neighbors would be capable of destroying us if they wanted to. "
"And it turns out that none of them can! As far as military power is concerned, "
"we'll surely defeat anyone stupid enough to cross us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c74f3843-2f57-49bf-8643-f8d7bb21c2a1"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri looks at you solemnly, her chin held high.{/n} \\\"I have something "
"important to say, {name}. I want to congratulate you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdae98d0-3185-4cb3-8bb0-4bdbd285c62c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your army has so many well-trained blademasters that we've gained the "
"attention of the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g}. It looks like the new sword-"
"fighting school will be opening soon in the kingdom. The Swordlords are looking to "
"recruit all the most talented students.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6d64c935-abe5-4434-9530-dcd4b8ab25b1"
msgid ""
"\\\"By the way, I'm not the only one who appreciates the decisions you've made. "
"There are so many mages in our army that one of the orders or {g|Nethys}Nethys{/g} "
"decided to move their coven to your kingdom. That's worked damn well for us! Do "
"you have any idea what kinds of deadly spells they could teach us? They probably "
"have a spell that summons a swarm of carnivorous bees that fly into their victim's "
"mouth and eats him from the inside out! And a spell that makes your heart explode!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5d980ce-84fd-4de0-932a-ea5c7a240f04"
msgid ""
"\\\"The {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} are amazed by our glory, and want to set up a "
"new school in our kingdom. They hope that being close to us will give them better "
"chances to be in a big battle. To show their mastery and earn some fame. I think "
"this news will make you happy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89946a52-3d65-4304-b408-2d6a4285e70a"
msgid ""
"\\\"In the North, victory is achieved with sword and axe. It's different with you "
"southerners. You're not so good as warriors, but you're crafty and better with "
"magic. Your army has very strong mages. That makes you strong... for southerners "
"anyway. The other mages have seen it too. It makes them come to beg for "
"protection. Priests of {g|Nethys}Nethys{/g} want to open their own coven under "
"your wing to share the knowledge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59ceec36-1c45-4450-89da-a56536f29cca"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have no more issues for you, chief. But there's a visitor who wants to see "
"you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c8bbb39-6862-42b1-98bd-58288b985f62"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, that's all for now. There's someone else who wants to talk to you, "
"{name}. You can do that without me, right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "622ffcea-db77-4b8d-994c-8543dc20e5cb"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri presses her hands to her chest and smiles lightly.{/n} \\\"We're a tribe, "
"and that means we all take the credit, not me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da194e0c-2629-41cc-895a-4c8adcd5b85c"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's the a chief's burden. The enemies' blows make warrior's head ache. "
"Doubts and second thoughts make the chief's head ache.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0f62d37-9ab1-4be8-9790-867b57990a84"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's because you've got brain. Most people rarely have second thoughts. "
"Maybe that's why you're on the throne and we serve you. But don't be upset. If you "
"run into any problems, we can solve them. Together.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4f1f0de-ce9b-4529-ab88-63964a4d69c5"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's true, I'm a good leader. But you... well, you're good, too. You didn't "
"interfere.\\\" {n}Regongar grins contentedly.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50bbca95-8c5c-444a-a307-b90c26425de1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your army, {name}, is the most dangerous bunch in the {g|River Kingdoms}River "
"Kingdoms{/g}. Being a warchief is a Kellids' biggest pride. I'm happy to lead an "
"army as powerful as yours.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75bb1c75-4a32-4285-9d26-0b9185f74c87"
msgid ""
"\\\"I didn't understand you right away. You have ambition! And you can rule. It "
"wasn't a bad decision to come work for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca252189-c6b0-434b-80a0-0dd7942695f2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Please, accept my congratulations, your Highness! It's under your guidance "
"that we have raised a strong army! An invincible one, by local standards. Who "
"could have imagined that such a young country would have such a powerful military "
"force? I'm proud I could prove myself in the service of such a worthy ruler as you!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d4fc98d-533e-4e9e-b6d1-bc7bc772f36e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perhaps, at some point I lacked the wisdom to understand your intentions, but "
"I am only Lady Aldori's student. I still have a lot to learn. Anyway, a group of "
"priests of {g|Nethys}Nethys{/g} are looking to open a coven in your domain. They "
"appreciate the respect you've shown your mages, and hope that you might grant them "
"your protection if trouble ever arose. In exchange, they promise to educate our "
"combat mages. I find this a worthy deal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2aa0c12-6f5f-408b-86bd-1e22b14dede1"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's always been a traditional rivalry between mages and warriors. The "
"troops that defend the front lines have to face down lightning bolts and fiery "
"rain with nothing but shields. They afterwards find it difficult to embrace any "
"rainmaker, even as an ally. However, the mages in your army are respected and "
"treated differently.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a439a49a-198c-4baf-8652-3dc9dab438f5"
msgid ""
"\\\"The sword masters respect your army. Many are not bound by any obligation to "
"the major houses, and would like to join us. They know we expect many battles to "
"come, which promises a chance at glory and an opportunity to prove themselves.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3d3ad998-a026-460e-8fac-76f32be08b0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have nothing at present that requires your attention. But I brought one of "
"the military advisors, who may have an interesting offer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "646f3fa1-da45-4e63-a4e4-d037764a4703"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil shrugs.{/n} \\\"I'm sure all your decisions were correct. You only "
"question them because you consider it a sacred duty to carefully consider your "
"every step.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4fff4567-3495-47ff-aa72-af4b8019274e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I was only doing my duty, your Highness. And I'm proud I managed to maintain "
"the kingdom's honor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53565b54-ef02-4d0d-ae5b-301361f8aee9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I understand them well. This is why the sword masters have offered to open a "
"military school in the capital. For me, this is no little matter of pride. It "
"means that Lady Aldori's lessons were not lost on me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26000a62-d98b-4bd3-a81c-2c7d0ee36cbf"
msgid ""
"\\\"Open unrestricted recruitment. Anyone with the will for it is good enough for "
"our army.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d4193aa5-9bff-4364-9ae9-749cc50dc83f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Select the strongest and most skillful recruits. I need real fighters.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5373366-ded6-432a-b6b9-7b4822711049"
msgid ""
"\\\"Select those who have ambition. Soldiers who dream of glory and rank always "
"serve better.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d05036bc-7876-4983-a9a3-e6ae2faab63f"
msgid "\\\"Make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86089f4e-6a8b-4e01-9779-55b71657aeb3"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil bows briskly, then hurries to speak.{/n} \\\"On your orders, I have "
"reviewed our military forces. The results are... disappointing, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. We require new recruits – and the sooner "
"the better.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8932307d-7c72-412a-979b-45d50124e6d7"
msgid ""
"\\\"We can introduce some restrictions, limiting how many could qualify for "
"service. However, under these circumstances I feel they shouldn't be very "
"stringent. Indeed, I would recommend we announce that anyone can join the army – "
"and I'm sure that we shall find many brave men among your subjects, ready to "
"protect their lands!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89a1806e-95cd-4821-af51-e6458c95a212"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri looks displeased.{/n} \\\"Since you made me the troops' chief, listen to "
"what I tell you: you need more people. The ones we have now are weaklings and "
"cowards. If we don't get any good fighters, our neighbors will smash us whenever "
"they want!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc83b5e7-cced-43f1-b474-0cb62899f4d1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just so you know... you should pick better fighters. I don't want to deal with "
"overgrown kids who complain about every scratch! Don't take just anyone who wants "
"it – or else we'll have barracks full of pansies. What are we going to do with "
"pansies? We need them strong and gutsy or it's no point.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51d89530-b08c-4575-994a-12b49fe9b0d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"You busy? No? Then I got something for you.\\\" {n}Regongar stretches his "
"shoulders, like he's readying for a fight.{/n} \\\"You may have killed the Stag "
"Lord, but it's too early to kick back and relax. There's still plenty of bandits "
"walking your lands. They still think it's their home. Let me get some more "
"soldiers, before they cut through the ones we have and leave us with nothing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23295680-a7bb-4a02-b716-c797a85cc9d9"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc squints.{/n} \\\"You know which ones you need? Not the big dumb "
"guys. No, you need fighters who want power. They'll serve you well. And if any "
"should grow too bold...\\\" {n}Regongar sneers sullenly.{/n} \\\"I'll hang them "
"from the trees.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "384327b4-afc6-4f4a-851e-0a165aade32b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! I will "
"begin recruiting new soldiers immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d527aa11-d73d-4cf7-908b-2c53ee3aed31"
msgid ""
"\\\"Seriously? Your capital is already guarded by a handful of pansies, and now "
"you want a whole army like that?! Ugh!\\\" {n}Amiri spits on the floor and angrily "
"turns away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fdef484d-e341-46bf-a651-fc9f488c62e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Is that right? Well, you're the boss. We'll find a use for cannon fodder too.\\"
"\" {n}Regongar shrugs nonchalantly.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c25b7b34-cd20-45b1-9563-d43cd6426428"
msgid "\\\"As you wish, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc85a6ff-94ca-4c87-82e8-38ca0224da85"
msgid ""
"\\\"Right! Just like I say! No idea why I come to you. I could just do it all "
"myself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62b4154d-3493-4c5d-91d2-49d1080908b1"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar shows his fangs.{/n} \\\"Dumb blockheads marching around? What am I "
"supposed to do with these idiots?!\\\" {n}The half-orc growls in irritation and "
"turns away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27481182-a75a-4369-a137-012a28fb4202"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil frowns.{/n} \\\"Ambition is good, when there's a place for it. But an "
"army, with its strict order and hierarchy, is hardly a place for upstarts.\\\" {n}"
"The half-orc coughs.{/n} \\\"I'm sorry to speak so freely.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c93f9353-a47d-48ff-91df-02096206598b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmm... well, maybe something good will come from them. I understand. I'll go "
"find some.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37f5df39-039a-4697-8b59-2ad782b64e82"
msgid "{n}Regongar grins.{/n} \\\"I like your attitude. I'll go get busy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f7350b8-63b1-4314-a988-f1ee5ebd2c5e"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you wish. I will announce immediately that anyone who wishes to serve their "
"native land shall be welcomed in its army.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70b87dda-f99a-4b0b-ae98-e10d778a6b5d"
msgid ""
"\\\"So why did I come all the way here from the other side of the castle?! Fine, "
"I'll recruit the ones I like. If he can get up after I punch him, then he's in.\\"
"\" {n}Amiri cracks her fingers, ready for a brawl.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59ab5f3c-74ac-4a5b-b629-84f72000b29f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Great. I'll find the kind of recruits who'll crawl into the {g|Abyss}Abyss{/g} "
"if it means they'll get a medal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d994a45e-b280-401c-89ee-e482c40905a0"
msgid "\\\"Hire Swordlords as officers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d674dd27-0ab1-4641-aa00-8190b1c44f8e"
msgid "\\\"Hire spellcasters as officers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec1884b6-3781-4070-afb3-cd9874b7fce4"
msgid ""
"\\\"I see you understand these matters better than I. Solve the problem yourself.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90b4c9d5-99bc-408d-982c-14946dc19cf4"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I am happy to report "
"that recruitment continues. Our ranks swell with more and more fine soldiers. "
"However, we now face another problem – there aren't enough officers. We shouldn't "
"look for them among the common citizens: command requires certain skills and "
"knowledge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ecabf96-b327-40df-bc3e-9995d7f5fb45"
msgid ""
"\\\"I recommend you recruit officers from among the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g}. "
"They are experienced warriors and skillful leaders, capable of strategic thinking "
"and inspiring the sort of courage that will survive the harsh realities of the "
"battlefield.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca848280-d823-491d-bd04-a65cafffdf81"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, {name}, it's me again. Our army is growing. We got more soldiers. But "
"not enough commanders. And there aren't no clever ones among the recruits. Without "
"good command, you know, you can't run an army.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "adf88a2a-85f7-4034-bb33-b3555866b44a"
msgid ""
"\\\"In some armies the officers are wizards or shamans. They might be brainy, but "
"they don't know a damn thing about soldiers. But when I was in {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/"
"g}, I seen those... you know... {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g}, right! They look "
"skinny, but they know their weapons, and soldiers look up to them. I think we "
"should hire them to be commanders in our army – they'll definitely have the "
"troops' respect.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6669f522-ccff-4c8f-bddb-0e69f7d62fad"
msgid ""
"\\\"Listen, {name}. Remember about recruitment? Well, I did that, we have the "
"numbers. But there's no one to command them.\\\" {n}Regongar spits through his "
"fangs.{/n} \\\"We need to find someone these dimwits will fear and obey. Me alone "
"is not enough.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d899a11e-62f5-4577-86ae-3f43536ca241"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know who we should make commanders? Not those boneheads from {g|Brevoy}"
"Brevoy{/g}, who dance around with their pig-stickers. No, we should hire "
"spellcasters instead! Our regular bonebreaker troops won't whisper a word against "
"a wizard. They're too afraid of getting lightning thrown in their face. And just "
"imagine what terror they'll bring to the battlefield. Not like those {g|Swordlords}"
"Swordlords{/g} – {g|Choral}Choral{/g} mopped the floor with them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d373da7a-33df-449e-8e06-00b519ddbf4a"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil nods.{/n} \\\"I will make the necessary arrangements immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bcc1052d-0665-4ed5-9a85-0fa2c77cfdd2"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri hums contentedly.{/n} \\\"Right. Fine, I'll go tell the others what you "
"said.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7e3793c1-a261-4dbf-ba67-6d9077afcfa6"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar sneers scornfully.{/n} \\\"What, you too? {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/"
"g}, no shit... even the peasants aren't afraid of them – what soldier will respect "
"them?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17f9792d-8a7f-43a2-89c9-a7cf2b30d12c"
msgid ""
"\\\"But... how should a spellcaster, who has sat all his life in a lab, be "
"expected to take up command?\\\" {n}Kassil shakes his head.{/n} \\\"I… I'm "
"surprised by this decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4cdb0a2-dc42-40cc-8cf5-cc1fdf6f72ea"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri looks insulted.{/n} \\\"Wha-a-at? These skinny dudes in robes will boss "
"my guys around? You kidding me, {name}?! What will I do with them?!\\\" {n}Amiri "
"spits on the floor furiously.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44b780be-ea28-4197-b9c6-84392d30c620"
msgid ""
"\\\"Great! A couple of fried troublemakers, and the rest of your soldiers will toe "
"the line.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a42ef37-5d3d-4c83-8b6e-aa91a507d773"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for your trust. I will immediately send letters to any {g|Swordlords}"
"Swordlords{/g} who may be interested in such a placement.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7eb453db-1de4-438e-adc6-291bf887dc36"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I go find out how to get those {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g}. Be back "
"later.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a5b38ca-9ddb-47c9-ac4e-b822bd552fe5"
msgid ""
"\\\"I know a couple wizards who would make perfect commanders. I'll handle "
"everything.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a60423ce-6cba-4a0e-989e-d05d7c729b14"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know…\\\" {n}Amiri scratches her nose, then sighs.{/n} \\\"Fine, I'll just "
"say it. I don't like being your General. I give you good advice, and you never "
"listen. Of course I'll do what you say this time, but after this – forget it. Find "
"yourself another general.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8eac3e1-9c86-4180-8d9d-6c98a0d38e6e"
msgid "\\\"We will place training camps nearby the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04c74f0b-a345-4adc-a636-b3440fc1b4d9"
msgid "\\\"We will place the barracks at the borders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17003113-cd72-49e3-9ae3-fcc0f1b16273"
msgid "\\\"They're your soldiers – it's your decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f3c63452-5638-4999-b8fa-0a00f3e94b9a"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! I must inform you – "
"military affairs have begun to take up all of my time, and more than once I have "
"missed overlooked a detail concerning domestic security. Please, hire a Warden – "
"an advisor who will watch over the safety of your subjects, and I shall continue "
"to carrying out the responsibilities of your General.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04927cc9-a120-4d34-956a-c43f746bb23a"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil turns his attention to the map of the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}.{/"
"n} \\\"New recruits keep coming, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. You must decide where their barracks is to be built.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b8988faf-bf4e-42b4-a7f1-b83f0f7ba771"
msgid ""
"\\\"To my mind, it would be best to build both the barracks and their training "
"camps nearby, close to the capital. Many of these youths burn with enthusiasm, but "
"until it is tempered by discipline they will never be as good in battle as they "
"would hope to be. I recommend we create camps to train and drill all those who "
"would protect these lands in the future.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "daedddef-5cf7-4ade-82b8-76efb9e2845e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Listen to me, {name}. I didn't become your General to chase criminals and hang "
"bandits! I used to be able to deal with it along with everything else, but now "
"your army is big and I don't have any extra time for guard duty! You need to hire "
"a Warden to keep order on the streets!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04264c2f-d540-4eaa-882a-d00d5569c7f9"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's something else. Your soldiers are gonna have to start sleeping on the "
"ground outside. There are more and more soldiers, but there aren't no more houses "
"for them. Of course I'm all for teaching the new recruits how to survive in any "
"conditions, but these wimps will run away like babies if they don't get beds.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92676d2e-df70-4933-ba1d-d6c768a8e39a"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri grins.{/n} \\\"Here is what I think. If we have to build barracks for "
"them, let's do it on the border. Let them find their feet there – patrol the area "
"and catch some spies. And if someone attacks us – then good! A real battle is "
"better than any training. What do you say? Where do we put the barracks?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ebf4522-0359-4485-848b-14fe9c8b8c4b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Listen, I'm tired of hearing about bandits and thieves! My job is managing the "
"army, not chasing pickpockets. Hire a Warden. Let him drill the guards and make "
"sure your subjects don't make too much trouble.\\\" {n}Regongar shakes his head "
"fiercely.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da330ffa-8f9f-4101-b1f2-74a52191cb4e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Fine. So why did I come here? Ah right! I was thinking – your soldiers need to "
"sleep somewhere. It's time we build a barracks. I've brought a map – can you show "
"me where you want it?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57b7fc26-001d-4cf9-913e-ca2b769fd4d9"
msgid ""
"{n}An unkind smile shows up on Regongar's face.{/n} \\\"Of course, I'd build them "
"right on the border. Your neighbors are restless, and we need to show them we're "
"serious. Some troops in their face is serious all right!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76e15589-b6f1-4d7e-9388-884f9b3e5e8f"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil bows.{/n} \\\"I'm happy you'll give our soldiers a chance to train "
"before we send them into battle. I will take care of everything.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f3d0fd03-9a72-467a-ad01-8901e01971af"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri cringes.{/n} \\\"You southerners, all a bunch of spineless crybabies! "
"Pups should be sent to fight, not nursed!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "578af896-bdf0-48be-96ab-4f8fbccbc1cc"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar growls, annoyed.{/n} \\\"Maybe we'll requisition some fluffy blankets "
"too? Soldiers should learn to fight the enemy, not beat up wooden dummies!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea614023-df6a-4f54-8e35-1304d9826553"
msgid ""
"\\\"But... you do understand you're sending untrained youths to their deaths. The "
"slightest border conflict, and they'll flee – if they don't die first!\\\" {n}"
"Kassil considers your words for a while.{/n} \\\"But of course, I can't argue with "
"you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54bf7951-6ea5-4b6d-ba5a-ef8cb9b04099"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's more like it! Let them see first hand what it's like to be a warrior!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ec69bd4-b0ba-4bc1-a43d-0f75c937fc98"
msgid "\\\"Great!\\\" {n}Regongar rubs his hands together impatiently.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8073316-a684-4495-a1eb-1d03967b162d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I will order training camps built. Don't worry, I'll make sure the new "
"recruits learn everything as swiftly as possible.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab0e6ced-4f41-4162-8137-750f86035d2c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then I will pick places on the border with the most trouble, and build our "
"barracks there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "732d1b04-8523-45d6-a999-a72e12988a29"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ha ha, this is going to be fun. The subjects of other countries won't be "
"running through our borders any more... Unless they want to make themselves live "
"targets!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7963b516-1636-4fc4-bbbf-4bf2eded4859"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil keeps silent, gathering his thoughts.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}. All this time I have struggled to serve you in the "
"best possible manner. But it seems our opinions on how to handle the army are "
"simply too different. It is best that I should leave this position to someone "
"else. I will do so immediately after I carry out your final order.\\\" {n}Kassil "
"bows.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e51ee350-06c8-48cb-ae0c-2cf146add0ec"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar sizes you up.{/n} \\\"As you wish. But it's the last order you'll give "
"me, {name}. I'm tired of these arguments. I need to find something more "
"interesting to do. And you... you need to find yourself a new General.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d44fb58d-b7bc-44fd-8246-795983967054"
msgid ""
"\\\"You must immediately prohibit this home-made booze among our soldiers, and "
"arrest any who brew it. We need fighters, not drunken murderers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad68ad4d-a25f-43f7-b9af-ed8e288af109"
msgid ""
"\\\"I provide my soldiers with weapons and ask them to kill. How they do it is "
"their business. I won't make anyone drink, but I'm not prohibiting these potions "
"either.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75fe32f3-585b-4452-a419-ee64b27b82d0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I like the idea of these potions. Let every soldier drink them if they really "
"help. Whatever they lack in power, they'll make up for with this magic.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5836b028-3739-4bf5-b199-b2fcc6aa60f5"
msgid "\\\"What is the potion's effect? Is it dangerous?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bbb5e49-5292-4278-a143-a559f19ac456"
msgid "\\\"You're the commander. You decide.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b19a637-cae3-4fde-bd5c-b0fea2e95345"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil seems to be lost.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}! I need your opinion. I caught a new recruit brewing dangerous potions "
"for himself and the other soldiers. These potions turn them into fierce fighters "
"for a while, but they dangerously twist their minds.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4af8ca14-9c68-4dbf-b0b6-e7a6a137ac48"
msgid ""
"\\\"Instead of training and drilling, these lazy fools are relying on their "
"potions. Many have already tried it, and the others are surely curious. I've "
"arrested the cooks, but the officers are of a different opinion! They believe the "
"potions might be effective, though they're quite unpredictable.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "303f7d7b-38c2-43eb-a058-f6a98b4ebc45"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar has a strange look in his eyes, and his speech is confused.{/n} \\\"Ah "
"well, how you doing, your chieftesty? You know, I've seen a miracle! {g|Gorum}"
"Gorum{/g} himself honored one of my commanders... with a gift! He turns pathetic "
"weaklings to fierce spawn of the {g|Abyss}Abyss{/g}, able to defeat anyone with "
"their bare hands! You know how?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66668747-26ef-4eb7-901e-94e55fb7855b"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri looks annoyed.{/n} \\\"So, chief, it's about our soldiers. The pups are "
"brewing magic potions of strength and bravery. It leaves no fear or doubt in their "
"heads, just fury like the howling wind.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "815c270b-15ca-4299-835c-a3f85224b9c7"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar laughs out loudly.{/n} \\\"Potions, he says! He got his fighters "
"drunk! And they're not what you'd call fighters... All he's got is weaklings in "
"his squad! But they all went like they were battle-crazy, fighting anyone who "
"steps in their way! Pure gold, that's what this potion is.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22d82757-cb8a-48b4-ad80-a02038b5a61d"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil opens his mouth to object, but stays silent. After a while, he nods.{/n} "
"\\\"I understand, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Everyone "
"is responsible for the power in their own hands. I will pass down the values of "
"the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} to as many fighters as I can reach. Those who "
"won't listen... Well, I feel sorry for them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53ce04aa-bcda-48b3-bb08-248a980cbd3a"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil bites his lip subtly, clenching his fists less so.{/n} \\\"So, you don't "
"trust me. I'm sorry. I...\\\" {n}His last words are muffled, and he exhales "
"forcefully.{/n} \\\"I've been sent to serve and assist you. I shall do as you say."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44eb3ae1-c882-4a9b-a255-b437ae6436a7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I mean... Back in our tribe we used it some. But mostly it's for lazy bones "
"and weaklings. A real fighter like me doesn't need that stuff. I wish there was "
"more like me in your army. I would let them do what they want – and the potions do "
"make them look like real soldiers. But I decided to ask you what you want.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f68664b1-d84e-4799-bfef-4a931131dd95"
msgid ""
"\\\"The {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} taught me to rely on myself and my skills – "
"which were forged by sacrifice and struggle, not by drinking some potion. But "
"you're not Aldori. You have every right to establish your own order. Must I bow to "
"the officers' will, or will you trust me?\\\" {n}Kassil peers at you, sweat "
"running down his temple.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4d2cbf3-a700-43f0-8e8a-29c6d0098da0"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri looks at you ironically.{/n} \\\"You southerners have strange ways, you "
"know. I don't know whether you're their chief or their nanny, {name}. Are they "
"adults with weapons and deadly skills, or naughty children you tell little rules. "
"I still don't understand your ways here in the South, but I'll do what you told me "
"to.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51819301-22f4-4506-ba75-4077929b9382"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you realize how lucky you are? An army like this can conquer all the {g|"
"Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}! They're finally real soldiers! They've got only one "
"destination – to the other world, and in the prime of their lives! May every one "
"of them cut your path with their blood. And may this path lead to something... "
"really great.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "577ddd66-4e67-44af-9ea3-fb234c83462c"
msgid ""
"\\\"That is right. Fighters must be responsible for themselves. Otherwise it's not "
"a fighter, but just a bug wearing armor. If the potion is good for them, maybe "
"it'll help them live. If not, then it's their own fault they died.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a02408b-7ca8-4b74-9b2e-e635758bc461"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar looks at you with respect.{/n} \\\"Protecting your reputation, eh? "
"Very wise. We don't want the neighbors spreading rumors that you're doping your "
"fighters. I'll take care of everything myself. You'll have nothing to do with it. "
"You are a deep thinker, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3b174c3c-d988-434a-b2b6-13d1a96466be"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri frowns.{/n} \\\"I'm not drinking this stuff. I decide for myself how I "
"kill my enemies. But you're the chief. Your word is the law for the others.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ec13be3-e59c-4650-ac2f-ba5722768dac"
msgid ""
"\\\"Starting tomorrow, we'll have potion production in every camp. It'll turn your "
"weaklings into real head hunters. Just point them at the battle and stay out of "
"their way!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14118d74-48a3-4d31-bd5d-87c11c3fa465"
msgid ""
"\\\"The stuff makes your arms stronger and you vision clearer, but it clouds your "
"mind. It befits a savage – a goblin or a bandit – but not a fighter who goes to "
"battle with a cool head.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1926d8b5-662a-484f-958a-2593daafffb8"
msgid ""
"\\\"It makes you mad. Makes you want to fight. And it makes you strong as a bear. "
"And there's something else...\\\" {n}Amiri frowns and waves her hand.{/n} \\\"Oh, "
"never mind about that.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "659ba4a9-c6d5-45ef-9d66-c82d16ecf3e2"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar's eyes grow dead. The half-orc looks away from you.{/n} \\\"The "
"quietest time is just before the thunderstorm... And then... drip, drop... plip, "
"plop... And then it bursts! And flashes! Your soul groans, and whizzes, the wind "
"howls, and the thunder strikes!\\\" {n}Regongar licks his dry lips. He seems "
"unaware of the electricity arcing between his fingers.{/n} \\\"And you are the "
"storm! No one can stop you. That's how it works. I tried it. I know what I'm "
"talking about.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff732643-b99b-4fd7-a499-1a4d5a6e04e0"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri's gaze is incinerating.{/n} \\\"I want to stay out of it. I'm their "
"commander, not their nanny. Let them drink whatever they want to as long as "
"they're ready to fight.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1edc2fd2-49f8-43a7-8682-2e9995408c60"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar's mania suddenly fades. He speaks quietly.{/n} \\\"I've been "
"thinking... Let's make all our fighters take these potions. Then you'll have an "
"army of real cutthroats. They won't care about death, pain, fear, or really have "
"any feelings at all. They'll kill without hesitation. Burn villages to the ground "
"without a second thought. What do you say?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2202e113-0d1a-4cfd-a03b-3fa89a20ad61"
msgid ""
"\\\"I appreciate your trust, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}.\\\" {n}Kassil pauses, and then continues in an earnest tone.{/n} \\\"I "
"am glad that you've taken my views to heart. The potions will be prohibited as of "
"today. Any who produce them will be punished.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d90b0f66-ade2-4046-bb35-5b56cd31adef"
msgid ""
"\\\"We don't leave our men behind. Let them climb into the angry mountains, if "
"they're so brave.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af0e8d76-85a0-4dbe-91bb-d3c068a4e581"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's dangerous and foolish. I'm not risking more fighters for the sake of a "
"few others.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6383d275-9815-46d4-99e9-b6df5bed0f42"
msgid ""
"\\\"You are the General. They're your soldiers. I'm expecting you to decide.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7be4f4a7-eb5c-43f8-bf96-09463ae255c9"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil is agitated. He's in a hurry, and his voice trembles.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! A border patrol is trapped under an "
"avalanche in the Eastern mountains. We don't know whether they're still alive, but "
"hope fades with every passing second. They won't survive for long without our "
"help. We have many volunteers among our soldiers, ready to go into the mountains "
"and save them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "680bc42c-93dd-4cc0-8c9e-72fa260dbcfd"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's been an accident, {name}. A border patrol got buried under an "
"avalanche in the Eastern mountains. They're trapped, and they won't survive. Some "
"of our other soldiers want to go rescue their friends, but the mountains are still "
"angry. The earth is rumbling, and the stones are moving. I can hear it even from "
"here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad739c38-d6b6-470b-a0f5-457faa8543c0"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar looks gloomy.{/n} \\\"{name}, we need to talk. A border patrol got "
"buried under an avalanche in the Eastern mountains. They're probably all dead. Not "
"a great loss. They weren't be the first to die, and they won't be the last. But "
"there's a number of troops volunteering to go rescue them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a81f21c9-8615-4c6b-b75f-add92c587df3"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll rescue them, no matter what it takes! You won't be sorry. Your soldiers "
"will gladly give their lives for a general who is loyal and reliable!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68176fbb-017d-45ed-b3db-7e4ce9afb159"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri spits.{/n} \\\"Only fools challenge mountains. This is a dumb lesson to "
"teach, chief.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ada138d2-96bc-48f2-ac8b-5431bae00e42"
msgid ""
"\\\"Pfff! They're probably dead already! It takes so much work to raise a good "
"fighter – and now we have to sacrifice them like this? When these volunteers go "
"missing, who's going to find them? Me or you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6b4bb9b-f75f-4eb9-acc5-b93fda69ec1d"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil's face darkens. He tries to show respect, but his lips curl, and his "
"fangs slip out.{/n} \\\"I will not dare dispute the order, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. But I fear that every soldier will know "
"henceforth that if he's in trouble, he's on his own. This shall doubtless "
"undermine their loyalty.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1787ce9f-018d-4d72-913a-3e6b1ecdf429"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri nods solemnly.{/n} \\\"You are wise. Their destiny is already set. We'll "
"raise a toast to them and remember them forever. The same for the ones that die "
"tomorrow.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a78af15c-52c6-4577-8e89-1ff4e46253f3"
msgid ""
"\\\"In fact, it's for the better. It will make our fighters angry – and they're "
"supposed to be angry! They need to get used to the fact that military service is "
"cruel. It chews up the noble and merciful sentiments.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49496a1b-e40a-4de7-8ff3-c539e5b850b0"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar grins.{/n} \\\"Ah, I don't care. Let them think of me however they "
"want! There will be no rescue missions. We're not going back. No one is getting "
"rescued today.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5106fce5-6ce3-422b-9e6a-27c03e81fd7f"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri shrugs coldly.{/n} \\\"We Kellids appreciate a helping hand. But when the "
"mountains are angry, you should flee. When someone finds bad luck in the "
"mountains, they cannot be saved. They belong to the spirits. Mess with the "
"mountains and you'll die. Unless you want to bury your whole army under new "
"avalanches, just forbid the rescue mission.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44168a08-a23d-4095-ae6f-2653f3db1532"
msgid ""
"\\\"The first avalanche is never the last. We'll risk losing half the army up "
"there. It's just not worth it. But if I say we're not going to the mountains, they "
"won't learn anything. They'll just take me for a heartless bastard. That's why I'd "
"rather you to give the order to cancel the mission. It's got to be you, the chief."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f530f823-5ea7-4208-94f1-ad14da73213d"
msgid ""
"\\\"The mountains are restless. New avalanches are possible. They could bury the "
"search parties as well. But our volunteers don't care about the risks. It isn't "
"wise, but it's very brave of them. We shouldn't leave our people behind. As a "
"fighter, I support them. But as your General, I must receive your permission "
"before engaging upon such a dangerous mission.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "521ebb4b-7f9e-40a2-a3a6-4d453b189fa2"
msgid ""
"[Pay 250 BP] \\\"My subjects have spilled enough blood. We have plenty of gold to "
"hire mercenaries.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0205b98a-c003-4f4b-b8e0-79eb1f8d5fad"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't trust the mercenary army. They've got nothing to lose in the defeat. "
"Let us begin a period of mandatory military service.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1cadf0a-80ae-4372-b3d1-275faee5858e"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've just defeated the barbarians from the North! No other enemy will dare "
"challenge us. Let's just leave everything as it is.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22f2c8d0-ff90-4f38-aa58-30b06ffc54a7"
msgid "\\\"You are my General. I trust your judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af4edd3a-121d-4285-9422-e10ee2e72a30"
msgid ""
"\\\"Chief, I've got a concern. We had a good battle with {g|Numeria}Numeria{/g}. "
"Our soldiers fought and died as brave as the Kellids. Our glory is great. Like "
"everybody knows, the best way to get glory is to defeat someone who already has it."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "caf83097-3876-40c1-9662-8446bbc5358f"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, here's the thing. We whipped {g|Numeria}Numeria{/g} into line, and "
"made a good show of it. But we lost a lot of soldiers along the way. Our good "
"neighbors must all be imagining how they'll to divide our territories between "
"them... That's what I'd be doing in their position. We have to renew our ranks "
"before it's too late.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b7dc6c5-8290-4f1a-9c05-f6bc858307e2"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri snorts.{/n} \\\"Only cowards and traders put their hopes in mercenaries. "
"You never know when they'll decide to run for their lives, and leave you holding "
"their gold. I'd have to stand behind the lines, to kill the ones who prefer "
"desertion to fighting.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1eb9e59-d49b-4df7-984f-3eb5cf973ea1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll strike a bargain with the mercenaries. I'd have joined them if I hadn't "
"become your General. Loads of weapons, pockets full of gold, and no trace of "
"remorse. That's my kind of party.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e3473df-44a2-4a83-a908-ad2c0bd62661"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your subjects are confident there will always be someone to protect them. "
"Someone like me. I'll explain to all the craven idiots what's going to happen if "
"the Kellids reach your kingdom and aren't met with an army.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0cf75cab-e7f2-4604-beb9-11dc2e4a4fb7"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's a crazy idea. When your new 'soldiers' get homesick enough to put you "
"on the rack, don't cry for my help.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "384e2096-f3d7-43e3-90ec-f5a2e28b7470"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri looks at you in astonishment.{/n} \\\"Are you out of your mind? Without "
"an army, this is not your land. This is nobody's land. If you don't care about "
"guarding it, then why don't you just dismiss all the rest of the army too? Could "
"an idea be any more stupid?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0ec1b4f-aca2-4c20-ba2b-ac29a5475fd4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sure, you defeated the barbarians – but now what? If your neighbors sent an "
"army right now, your military glory would be in the can!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea02fd76-ec6f-4baf-abf8-5011be7ffc71"
msgid ""
"\\\"You need a bigger army. There are many mercenaries in the city, trying to sell "
"their skills. I don't trust them. They fight for their purse, not for their "
"general. If the enemy bribes them, they'll stub us in the back. Then there's just "
"more for us to execute. It's best if you draft the locals instead. They won't be "
"very happy about it, after all that's happened, but let your people have to learn "
"to stand up for their own land!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a08f99e8-5870-499b-a28b-857dec76be70"
msgid ""
"\\\"You could call up the local citizens. However, all the volunteers are either "
"already recruited or six feet under ground. That means we either take in the "
"weaklings or we do it by force. We'll train them to kill, and then one fine "
"morning they'll take a blade in the heart. Not a bright future, eh? It's best to "
"pay the mercenaries. That bunch of daredevils is dreaming of fighting for a "
"warchief like you! And these guys are tough and dangerous men, not some untrained "
"farmhands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8cab1b33-003d-4463-8af5-70ff9349aec1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have alarming news, your Highness. I've just audited the officers' reports, "
"and I have to admit: the war with the Kellids cost us dearly. It was a glorious "
"victory, but we lost many lives. Our losses must be replenished, but with who? A "
"general mobilization would end with a mob of angry peasants in the ranks. Every "
"volunteer has already joined. I guess we'll be looking at forced conscription.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "239b5b64-ce4a-4567-ae79-1323a4972269"
msgid ""
"\\\"The other option is mercenaries, which is far worse. I've never trusted those "
"who fight for money, rather than honor or duty. It's better if we recruit peasants "
"by force. The training they'll undergo will make them realize that it was the "
"right thing to do for their own families and the homeland.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "267ef02e-9063-431d-8b1a-b2df8d96ce32"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm afraid they will disappoint you, or worse. You can occasionally come "
"across one or two decent people among them, but most mercenaries are greedy, "
"untrustworthy thugs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "be5acbf6-6848-419d-8f21-4590f57a1b50"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll commence military conscription at once. Soldiers with families to defend "
"are far more reliable than mercenaries who only care about their own skin and "
"their pay. A mercenary will flee while a true defender holds out to the end.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5588958b-af9e-4b1d-870e-b4e1194ca5b6"
msgid ""
"\\\"I can't agree with this decision. Our weakened position may be too tempting "
"for our less noble neighbors. I'll try to use the remains of your army to organize "
"our defenses, but this may cost us dearly.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7049331f-00e9-4f07-8c83-fb24bc072eb7"
msgid "\\\"What exactly do you have to offer to my army?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "abf0950e-8770-458f-b1d3-dc3b2e03e737"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tell me about your motherland. Where is it? We don't hear about it often here, "
"in our domain.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ecf766c-8476-4086-9436-a350c0e1d1b0"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about the weapon in your waistband.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d60c208b-41ec-4ee6-8889-32e4bc4b9e1c"
msgid "\\\"Thank you. I need to think.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e8ffa67-1725-42c3-8c58-7e569b09fe99"
msgid "\\\"What makes you think I'd prefer your odd toys to time-honored magic?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf29348d-b35d-4921-8717-d85d6ed5b4af"
msgid ""
"{n}A halfling stands in front of you, wearing fine black cashmere. He has a couple "
"of weird-looking palm-sized metal weapons in his waistband. His expensive attire "
"does not disguise the scars on his face and hands, or his sturdy posture. Your "
"guest seems more accustomed to sitting in the saddle and wearing traveling "
"clothes, rather than to visiting palaces in expensive attire.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb58cc54-54d6-4d24-a52b-a6b208030b5f"
msgid ""
"{n}The captain's voice grows serious.{/n} \\\"We will provide your soldiers with "
"our weapons, teach them how to use them, and make sure the weapons are working. "
"Believe me, each projectile shot by our devices will cost the enemy an equal "
"amount in gold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2ab5c7c-2cc0-4f3e-9c2d-002bfb35ceca"
msgid ""
"\\\"Alkenstar is halfway around the world. You see, magic... how can I put this... "
"It doesn't work in our lands. Don't ask me why. That's a question for the "
"researchers and historians. But we ordinary people of Alkenstar managed to turn "
"this nuisance to the greater good.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f4c5d794-f4da-4d2c-8e03-3dede251d842"
msgid ""
"{n}The captain grins and pats his crossbows.{/n} \\\"So, you'd like to know how "
"they're operated? What gears bring these small death machines to life? It's a "
"secret. We make our living from other people's ignorance of how our weapons work. "
"Nevertheless, I will tell you something about my weapons.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c35c1d9-98f4-4988-873c-8a1cab965ed6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, Your Highness. I'm Captain Romelo. I represent the Smoky Dawn Arms "
"Factory in the Grand Duchy of Alkenstar. Our enterprise is prepared to provide "
"your army with the finest weapons ever created.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d1835864-60fc-4233-b22c-a6fcb8425375"
msgid ""
"\\\"I should be clear from the beginning, we're not selling the technology. Your "
"engineers are not permitted to repair the weapons. We'll send our specialists. "
"However, if you're interested in any of our non-weapons technologies, our "
"craftsmen will gladly train your own!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0444c0e7-0135-458e-b5ed-61f0b102b745"
msgid ""
"{n}Romelo rubs his chin.{/n} \\\"We gave up magic for the sake of science. No "
"country can compare to Alkenstar in terms of its technological miracles! We didn't "
"just survive. We're doing very well here, where a mage could never endure. And we "
"are willing to share our findings with anyone willing to pay a fair price.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5588eca-0154-4140-a086-83f2683409f0"
msgid "\\\"What else would you like to know?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fcc5733-c1f0-47c0-9440-1bf0dabcd8f7"
msgid ""
"\\\"The left one is for normal work. I use it to kill bandits and thieves spying "
"on our secrets. It's loaded with ordinary bullets. The right one is for special "
"occasions. Each of its bolts bears the name of a rascal who wronged me or my "
"family from the times we languished in {g|Cheliax}Cheliax{/g}. When the right one "
"is empty, my travels on {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g} will end, and I will return to "
"Alkenstar and find myself something else to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04a1f09b-7f27-4c52-a7b2-63dddd4570dc"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's because you're smart, Your Highness. First, our 'toys' are far safer, "
"and their failure far less dangerous than magic cast awry. Secondly, anyone with "
"an eye and two hands can use our weapons. That makes things a bit simpler for you, "
"doesn't it?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e165494-8667-43ed-86a2-5a006e49d2c6"
msgid "\\\"Your title is very unusual.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98b01749-155f-4ce2-ae23-f9b0344467c8"
msgid "\\\"What do you have to offer to my troops?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9570dc9b-f4dd-4369-96df-f4871528247c"
msgid "\\\"What is this Arcanamirium so famous for?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35cf2619-d3c8-4773-a131-2836e74d3217"
msgid "\\\"I need to think.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1987ee54-1862-4107-a10c-03b971f98572"
msgid ""
"{n}A sturdy middle-aged woman in practical grey attire bows to you. You can tell "
"by the numerous strings and laces on her neck that she's wearing quite a number of "
"amulets under her robe. Her hair is short and cropped.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e6d8a1b6-f947-4469-8e4b-b61b8ede6a21"
msgid ""
"{n}The Wands Brigade's first foreman, Raquillata, nods politely and softly clicks "
"her heels together.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ec863ad-0b06-4296-8b3d-4d0c3a6a6957"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our experience. You're hiring the Wands Brigade, an independent squad of "
"mages, not merely as soldiers but as advisors and trainers for your other troops. "
"Each of us not only possesses magic but also has extensive combat experience. "
"What's more important, we know when and how to use it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdb57a55-749d-44e8-a4d3-d9a216d52a09"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is the oldest, biggest, and the most prestigious arcane academy in {g|"
"Absalom}Absalom{/g}. It's very influential. Students come from all over the world "
"to master the art of magic. Mind you, the school is tuition-free.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d4d10bb-86e9-4069-b1e1-4c36035bbb91"
msgid ""
"\\\"First Foreman Raquillata, at your service, Your Highness. Reporting for "
"negotiations on behalf of the Wands Brigade, graduates of the Arcanamirium!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2133ca7-ce07-4158-be22-81e770abd66d"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're not theoreticians or professors, Your Highness. We're arcane "
"practitioners, combat specialists, and frontline workers. We're willing to share "
"our knowledge with your military mages.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdd336de-457f-432f-948c-0dc126337ab6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Every member of our brigade is an Arcanamirium graduate. We each have combat "
"experience and a desire to build a mercenary career. We've been preparing to "
"accept your orders since we entered the Wands Brigade.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1d0d07d6-1586-4b2e-8f1a-4dd4ee522ced"
msgid ""
"\\\"They teach both magic and practical skills, both of which are certainly useful "
"to combat mages. For instance, if you've learned to summon enraged monsters, it "
"might also be a good idea to learn to run fast.\\\"{n}A smile brushes lightly over "
"Raquillata's face.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ed46375-2076-4d42-b922-f2897b15db34"
msgid ""
"[Pay 3 BP each week] \\\"I trust Alkenstar's engineers. Have them supply us with "
"their weapons.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ff586fa-ef4e-4c97-890a-843b0616b558"
msgid ""
"[Pay 3 BP each week] \\\"I am impressed with Arcanamirium's power. I'd like its "
"graduates to train our mages.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "371709b5-de80-4c5c-b894-f4762df1a0de"
msgid ""
"[Pay 3 BP each week] \\\"May Kurgess bless our warriors with strength and agility."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37147943-ccae-456e-a5c2-7e6d6c1028d8"
msgid ""
"\\\"You understand our army's needs better than I do. You can make your own "
"decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1768cfa2-59af-4600-ba25-56c5b6551c2e"
msgid "\\\"Who should I make the deal with?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2db4ff82-0e19-4b02-a1d6-f4193ea6c7bd"
msgid "\\\"I should talk to their ambassadors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bbb80eee-c340-4b2d-b0c7-3bf2cca9b47a"
msgid "\\\"The halfling in black.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4721962e-bf24-4902-aeda-d9b5a4b89b88"
msgid "\\\"With the dwarf.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0aa41196-bb53-4b13-8b7b-210a2380da17"
msgid "\\\"With the sorceress.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "145e55a9-e034-4246-be0d-fe74768bef9e"
msgid "\\\"In fact, it doesn't matter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e8f7ebc-486b-42d7-9ba8-c5b3eecc41ec"
msgid "\\\"Your title is very unusual.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "280535f6-f557-45d2-9cce-93b94341d267"
msgid "\\\"What do you have to offer to my troops?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ecb0802-8c9d-4cbd-a1ca-10d643299fac"
msgid "\\\"What is this Arcanamirium so famous for?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9806116-16b9-47df-8bea-d5044e86b3a0"
msgid "\\\"I need to think.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f8ce472-8734-4191-8c2a-aa86721c7374"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tell me about your motherland. Where is it? We don't hear about it often here, "
"in our domain.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af23ce33-f83f-4335-9354-29306d77eb1f"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about the weapon in your waistband.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc0db3ab-0128-4179-8e0e-88f43a006b5b"
msgid ""
"\\\"What makes you think I'd prefer your odd toys over time-honored magic?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53227f98-deb9-44b9-81fe-065dc3982e97"
msgid "\\\"Thank you. I need to think.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a410807-4623-4986-9511-338d8d281cd1"
msgid "\\\"What exactly do you have to offer?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "426f573c-71e6-419b-b060-7d343216ea3e"
msgid "\\\"How can you help my army?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b03271e-ead8-4515-9efa-6224d379df90"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about your god.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3c59489-a3a0-4a75-b010-be67f6d662e6"
msgid "\\\"What is your church?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a230555d-fa37-4035-b3a5-7d48227a2b7e"
msgid "\\\"You... look outlandish. Where have you come from?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56a73316-2d1b-4fe2-9248-db0b0681a2ee"
msgid "\\\"I need to think it over.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91f16048-695b-4f6c-8698-571159dfefed"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar grins contentedly.{/n} \\\"I have an idea I'd like to share with you. "
"I'm sure it's occurred to you that we are now in control? We're the power everyone "
"answers to – and not only in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. We demand "
"respect. And those worthy of respect are worthy of doing business with. Profitable "
"business.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf93adef-39e7-4590-aa28-7c084dd05aa0"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri smiles in satisfaction.{/n} \\\"It looks like word of our heroic feats "
"made it all across {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g}. Merchants and shamans are always "
"chasing great warriors, trying to sell them their best sword. So they can proudly "
"announce it on every corner!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a3ce2236-8273-4b2d-bfb7-89811ec06420"
msgid ""
"\\\"Anyway, three representatives of... dealers in life and death have requested "
"an audience with you. All three are willing to support our army. Talk to them and "
"decide which of them we want to sign a contract with. However, we can't hire all "
"three. Each of them wants to be your main weapons supplier. If I were you, I'd "
"consider the Arcanamirium.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e5e6ccb-695d-4b2f-bc80-811a69e4fca1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Three great clans want to offer support for our troops. There was more before "
"I got rid of the swindlers and the small fish. We should choose the best one and "
"seal the deal. But only one. We have to refuse the others to command their "
"respect. All three want to talk to you. Talk them all you want, but look closest "
"at...\\\" {n}Amiri gives you an 'inconspicuous' wink.{/n}\\\"... the Kurgess guy, "
"I say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad67b2f8-5f54-43e3-98f2-4995b68a7ed3"
msgid "\\\"Have you decided who we're going to deal with for army support?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89435183-cae8-43c0-9cd4-f5931dedc62e"
msgid ""
"\\\"You think their tricky devices will bring you victory? Well, you obviously "
"know better than me...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cfe89c0-9247-41b9-9fd8-6138b1b266cf"
msgid ""
"\\\"They invented their pathetic toys because they had no magic. Why stoop to "
"their level? After all, we do have magic.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9eb5ed70-c44e-4002-bcb6-6b80938bea7b"
msgid ""
"\\\"A mage acting like a soldier? That doesn't stop them from being a dodger and a "
"coward. Don't trust anyone who avoids a fair fight.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "904dead5-3bc8-4652-a11b-3f198b5fb3da"
msgid ""
"\\\"You can get a decent education in Arcanamirium. They don't just teach the "
"books, but also how to use your legs and hold a weapon. The result is a well-"
"rounded warrior.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7677f593-bc8b-4d7a-9c93-fc6be7485e43"
msgid ""
"\\\"If even half of our soldiers were like Wodga, we'd break every enemy spine on "
"the battlefield.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65f18971-d924-406d-9532-fd345d73838b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Did that jock impress you? Ah, what am I saying?! I liked him too.\\\" {n}"
"Regongar smirks.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d91ce54b-cf0a-4a1e-89bf-71a7cb110c9f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Alkenstar's weapons are impressive, but relying too heavily on their power may "
"weaken our troops in other ways. You know what I think about magic and mages. But "
"if all our soldiers looked like that Kurgess priest, the war might not happen at "
"all! The enemy would flee on sight!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23e6d3c2-7902-441d-b531-63d46f244a2f"
msgid ""
"\\\"With the mages, of course. Have you seen them fight? Now that's what I call a "
"massacre! Fireballs hurtling, ice crunching! Swoosh! Bang! They can rip a soul "
"right out of a body and use it as a bomb! Kaboom! Bony shrapnel flying everywhere! "
"Blood in everyone's eyes! And then they jump into the shadows, spread out, and "
"sneak behind the enemy's lines to finish the survivors. They surround them, cover "
"them with a force field, and create a little explosion on the inside. And don't "
"forget the roaring flame! All that's left is ashes and footprints on the scorched "
"earth...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79e19422-00f3-490f-a533-2be2cd5f0406"
msgid "\\\"Which of the three?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "60ded03d-b27d-46fa-b204-c77b36e66327"
msgid "\\\"Which of the ambassadors?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "607d40e3-6f36-4d92-b64a-22b157240420"
msgid "\\\"They'll be waiting for your decision, chief.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b76f8bb-f85c-4927-8e3d-1807eecec06c"
msgid ""
"\\\"You should think fast. What if an enemy assault takes us by surprise, and "
"we've got no reinforcements, hunh?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76f913bf-78dd-4e02-b1ac-568b3ff444bb"
msgid ""
"{n}A sturdy middle-aged woman in practical grey attire bows to you. You can tell "
"by the numerous strings and laces on her neck that she's wearing quite a number of "
"amulets under her robe. Her hair is short and cropped.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "895dc59f-cb51-437d-aef6-37ae3fab2d3c"
msgid ""
"{n}The Wands Brigade's first foreman, Raquillata, nods politely and softly clicks "
"her heels together.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5030eb0-377b-4acd-87db-38c244e71685"
msgid ""
"\\\"First Foreman Raquillata, at your service, Your Highness. Reporting for "
"negotiations on behalf of the Wands Brigade, graduates of the Arcanamirium!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b9424b94-01ca-44a0-a0d3-ad4b5cc814da"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're not theoreticians or professors, Your Highness. We're arcane "
"practitioners, combat specialists, and frontline workers. We're willing to share "
"our knowledge with your military mages.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ada023d-fcf6-4e6e-972c-645ba5143963"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our experience. You're hiring the Wands Brigade, an independent squad of "
"mages, not merely as soldiers but as advisors and trainers for your other troops. "
"Each of us not only possesses magic but also has extensive combat experience. "
"What's more important, we know when and how to use it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47e55c26-b0db-4448-bb0a-2bddfe3e1aeb"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is the oldest, biggest, and the most prestigious arcane academy in {g|"
"Absalom}Absalom{/g}. It's very influential. Students come from all over the world "
"to master the art of magic. Mind you, the school is tuition-free.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51a4087f-979d-4a94-b01c-ac26a78462eb"
msgid ""
"\\\"They teach both magic and practical skills, both of which are certainly useful "
"to combat mages. For instance, if you've learned to summon enraged monsters, it "
"might also be a good idea to learn to run fast.\\\"{n}A smile brushes lightly over "
"Raquillata's face.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3300fae-cd34-4706-b896-bd8451e0d0f4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Every member of our brigade is an Arcanamirium graduate. We each have combat "
"experience and a desire to build a mercenary career. We've been preparing to "
"accept your orders since we entered the Wands Brigade.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8414b01-c1e7-43dd-b8d5-b9262375d88b"
msgid "\\\"Always at your service.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f326537b-d6a2-4d32-a6d2-1085d7660779"
msgid ""
"{n}The halfling standing before you wears fine black cashmere. He has a couple of "
"strange-looking palm-sized crossbows in his waistband. His expensive attire does "
"nothing to disguise the scars on his face and hands, or his sturdy posture. Your "
"guest seems more accustomed to sitting in the saddle and wearing traveling "
"clothes, rather than visiting palaces wearing expensive attire.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02e045a7-8d97-4872-9baf-e0481412bef8"
msgid "\\\"What else would you like to know?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0cd5d147-4bc6-4d0e-889b-76cf246053ed"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, Your Highness. I am Captain Romelo. I represent the Smoky Dawn Arms "
"Factory in the Grand Duchy of Alkenstar. Our enterprise is prepared to provide "
"your army with the finest weapons ever made.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8cfa9d8-f068-4961-9057-54bdcca2decb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Alkenstar is halfway around the world. You see, magic... how can I put this... "
"It doesn't work in our lands. Don't ask me why. That's a question for the "
"researchers and historians. But we ordinary people of Alkenstar managed to turn "
"this nuisance to the greater good.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a2d86a63-6288-4e76-afdb-1d11a1c633a4"
msgid ""
"{n}Romelo rubs his chin.{/n} \\\"We gave up magic for the sake of science. No "
"country can compare to Alkenstar in terms of its technological miracles! We didn't "
"just survive. We're doing very well here, where a mage could never endure. And we "
"are willing to share our findings with anyone willing to pay a fair price.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eee991f7-06f5-4190-a3fa-c27c3a7875e2"
msgid ""
"{n}The captain grins and pats his crossbows.{/n} \\\"So, you'd like to know how "
"they're operated? What gears bring these small death machines to life? How can "
"they rain bolts down upon the enemy without ever recharging? It's a secret. We "
"make our living from other people's ignorance of how our weapons work. "
"Nevertheless, I will tell you a secret about these two crossbows of mine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c21b7eda-cba9-42cc-ae8c-6a1561968b3c"
msgid ""
"\\\"The left one is for normal work. I use it to kill bandits and thieves spying "
"on our secrets. It's loaded with ordinary bolts. The right one is for special "
"occasions. Each of its bolts bears the name of a rascal who wronged me or my "
"family. When the right one is empty, my travels on {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g} will "
"end, and I will return to Alkenstar and find myself something else to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3af080e7-b3d2-4bef-bf2e-54b4f8d0382f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Because you're smart, Your Highness. Firstly, our 'toys' are way safer, and "
"their failure is far less dangerous than magic cast awry. Secondly, anyone with an "
"eye and two hands can use our weapons. That makes things a bit simpler for you, "
"doesn't it?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d8c5d98-e2e5-4dfe-87c8-59cc261519da"
msgid "\\\"I'm sure we'll have a most productive association, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3bddc80-c1e5-4c27-9577-bd9c9847f874"
msgid ""
"{n}The captain's voice grows serious.{/n} \\\"We will provide your soldiers with "
"our weapon, teach them how to use it, and make sure the weapons are working. "
"Believe me, each bolt shot by our crossbows will cost the enemy an equal amount in "
"gold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28808d5e-d234-4b07-b8eb-21bce1ba558e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I should make clear from the beginning, we're not selling the technology. Your "
"engineers won't be permitted to repair the weapons; they're to be handled "
"exclusively by our specialists. However, if you're interested in any of our non-"
"weapons technologies, our craftsmen will gladly train yours!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1bbdbdf3-517f-4333-a7bd-686704f69ead"
msgid ""
"{n}An unusually tall and sturdy dwarf with a shaved head bows to you. Despite the "
"weather, his feet are bare, and he's wearing a simple vest over his naked torso.{/"
"n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "500b3fee-b0e9-4c25-8b5c-3223174ed39e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hey – let's arm wrestle, eh? Oh, no, I'm only joking. I know that Your "
"Highness is mighty busy. Is there anything I can help you with?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6681c6ea-d9b1-4210-9ea1-325a56221693"
msgid ""
"{n}His mighty but pleasant voice fills the entire hall.{/n} \\\"Greetings, Your "
"Highness. I am Wodga, priest of the glorious god Kurgess! I believe it was not by "
"coincidence that the road brought me and my comrades to your lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd646306-8cfb-4c82-8b60-ecbc3a9362ef"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your soldiers are... brave, but weak. By the will of Kurgess, we'll sort out "
"your pathetic forces. My priests know how to strengthen a soldier with magic that "
"will give them the power and speed of a mighty animal. And if that fails to "
"protect them, our prayers will heal your warriors and restore them to perfect "
"fighting form.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f7f67bf-d024-4c33-837b-902bd7fe266a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Kurgess was a {g|Taldor}Taldan{/g} villager of remarkable figure! He traveled "
"around towns, visited trade fairs, took part in every competition and show, and "
"always won. It's only natural that everybody was jealous.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f86d63d7-7e53-4df1-bd31-7e04a0642363"
msgid ""
"\\\"His rivals set a trap for him during a competition. He died, giving his life "
"to protect the other participants, but his glory lived on even after his death. "
"Few mortals are deemed worthy of joining the godly host, and Kurgess was among "
"them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "007544c6-74dd-4c82-ae24-0223e2228a55"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our church is young, and we don't have an established hierarchy yet. We wander "
"from town to town, healing the diseased, mentoring the weak and the sick, teaching "
"them how to harness their own powers, inspiring those who are able to reach beyond "
"their own boundaries. We do not build temples, for we believe our bodies are the "
"temples. A tent in a field, that's all we need.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a42d2e31-2291-4f82-98fa-2adb040d34bf"
msgid ""
"\\\"It disgusts Kurgess when people cripple themselves, so we reject alcohol and "
"stupefying potions. I shall prohibit these among your soldiers. The spirit grows "
"stronger in a mighty body! Kurgess dislikes foul play, so cheating is also illegal."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e562c156-a66c-4130-a001-bea412f76fc4"
msgid ""
"{n}Dwarf laughs approvingly.{/n} \\\"Well, thank you! I wish you could meet my "
"grandfather! He was a real hero, stately and notable! Myself, I'm a mere peasant "
"from a small village on unclaimed land. I was once a fighter. However peaceful I "
"may be, I am still very passionate. When it comes to wrestling, I can best even "
"you! Though now I'm a priest as well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5167735e-fedc-401c-adef-cd908f3c9c2d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Try throwing a kettlebell up and down. Physical effort stimulates the brain.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb39c38d-27bf-4913-b566-9bcab2f37f8e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, our army has grown strong enough to reckon with. There are "
"others who look to support our army, and share in the glory of our victories. "
"Representatives of three unions have arrived at the court to offer their services. "
"Unfortunately, we are forced to select only one, and the others will have to "
"leave. This is a matter of their insistence, something to do with prestige.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a78761db-4a71-4115-8d40-6747f46fff83"
msgid ""
"\\\"That arrogant dwarf is going to train our soldiers?! I wonder what he can "
"offer them! Real battle isn't a time to show off, and I've never seen a Kurgess "
"priest on a battlefield. I've never heard anything of their victories, either.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af479fdc-bf0a-40ad-b076-968bfe011b37"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't trust these cutthroats. They're deadly, no doubt. But they're prone to "
"dirty tricks that ill becomes our army. I'm afraid their deeds might destroy our "
"reputation.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13b12f5a-2aa2-4d3b-ba9a-f4b7083b1474"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll immediately begin training our shooters to use the weapons of Alkenstar. "
"I'll ask the ambassador for one for myself... to study our new armaments.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76b904f1-96b7-439c-a143-2397e27d67dc"
msgid ""
"\\\"I dislike Arcanamirium. They're dishonest thugs. And that Kurgess priest – he "
"looks like he's about to burst with smugness. His strength is impressive, but I "
"don't like his bragging and vulgar manners. As for Alkenstar... Have you seen "
"their weapon? It's magnificent! I would love to be trained to handle it! And the "
"tactical perspective it offers! Nobody here possesses anything like it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34d37c18-892e-48db-b257-865030ff035e"
msgid "\\\"Who would you like to know about?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f847db4-0886-42d3-94ec-12bd45a6d103"
msgid "\\\"Your visitors will wait for as long as it takes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87d2bd66-f787-4e76-b63e-804f422bbda2"
msgid "\\\"How can you help my army?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed3f3b37-fd4d-44ee-8577-fd1cab46e0b5"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about your god.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7687ec06-92b4-4614-92f2-b4d2d43f2357"
msgid "\\\"What is your church?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c439869-2065-42ae-bb11-e859c87d786f"
msgid "\\\"You look... outlandish. Where do you hail from?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec5cd648-2ae1-49db-98eb-49e56d2e64d6"
msgid "\\\"I need to think it over.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec94ea09-28f1-4120-92a1-baa4d32f369c"
msgid ""
"{n}An unusually tall and sturdy dwarf with a shaved head bows to you. Despite the "
"weather, his feet are bare, and he's wearing a simple vest over his naked torso.{/"
"n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f773066-8645-4ba5-8659-e4bb4d21f359"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hey – let's arm wrestle, eh? Oh, no, I'm only joking. I know that Your "
"Highness is mighty busy. Is there anything I can help you with?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7cc390c3-e221-47fc-ad5c-74ca2d9b034c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your soldiers are... brave, but weak. By the will of Kurgess, we'll sort out "
"your pathetic forces. My priests know how to strengthen a soldier with magic that "
"will give them the power and speed of a mighty animal. And if that fails to "
"protect them, our prayers will heal your warriors and restore them to perfect "
"fighting form.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8df5c2f8-e2d0-4d1e-bdfe-080d016683b4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Kurgess was a {g|Taldor}Taldan{/g} villager of remarkable figure! He traveled "
"around towns, visited trade fairs, took part in every competition and show, and "
"always won. It's only natural that everybody was jealous.\\\""
msgstr ""

