"grandfather! He was a real hero, stately and notable! Myself, I'm a mere peasant "
"from a small village on unclaimed land. I was once a fighter. However peaceful I "
"may be, I am still very passionate. When it comes to wrestling, I can best even "
"you! Though now I'm a priest as well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b6fc1ca7-0982-477d-9221-26dbb8facf7a"
msgid "\\\"Appoint a warrior to the post.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21e793d7-65c4-47d0-81d5-1532c4e265e2"
msgid "\\\"I want a mage to serve as general.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f6541b1-05eb-41ea-8d6d-055eab2aa270"
msgid "\\\"It's your deputy. You decide.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "958f60df-d87c-4778-a8e0-401e0f5dfdf7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Chief. We need to talk. There's a problem in your... in our army. The mages "
"and warriors have been challenging one another to find out who's tougher. The "
"competition is worse than it was when you came to power. Today I had to stop a "
"knife fight.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70a75c98-4391-4599-9a13-41ca65f8e8cb"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar looks a little banged up, and he smells like smoke.{/n} \\\"{name}, "
"you know me. I would never cause alarm for no good reason. But right now I'm "
"telling you: there's unrest brewing in your army's ranks. And it's not even proper "
"conspirators, no! It's just the regular idiots.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8eec78bc-0b87-40c3-92f3-8a0b0ae8d802"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sooner or later, blood will spill and someone will die. I can always feel "
"death in the air. If you don't want to watch your warriors kill one another, you "
"should do something. Aside from appointing someone to beat the crap out of the "
"idiots.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a3f0ae3-c35f-41cc-883e-1f451161e376"
msgid ""
"\\\"Two of our commanders are bursting with ambition. Both of them have outgrown "
"their current positions. They're always challenging each other, and settling their "
"scores by stirring up our soldiers. Officer Chevold insists that our infantry, the "
"vanquisher of {g|Numeria}Numeria{/g}, rules the open field. Commander Zefa argues "
"that only mages truly understand the art of battle, and the infantry are farmhands "
"and mudbeaters. You can imagine where this has led – to constant fighting among "
"the ranks.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61e141a4-fd4d-40f2-bb3f-04417c25aab9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Chevold will make a good general. I'll train him myself. If he survives, he'll "
"be strong as a bear and smart like me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c799b917-a7b3-41b0-8f2f-c9ccb6529932"
msgid ""
"\\\"So you prefer the guy with a big sword to the clever girl? That's pretty short-"
"sighted. I'm disappointed, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dacd693a-1459-44c6-80af-f42633cd7479"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri hems.{/n} \\\"That's too bad. A mage should stay in the rear and keep "
"quiet unless their magic is needed. Commanding the army is none of their business. "
"Now I'll have to watch my assistant, to make sure she doesn't conjure anything "
"stupid.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c8e7f4c-070f-427a-88df-b12d91c0b994"
msgid ""
"\\\"Good choice. A warrior needs a body that's tough enough to face the enemy on "
"the front lines, and a head that's small enough to do it without fear. Mages are "
"smarter and craftier. Zefa is your best option.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3aef873-c086-4939-a363-93b2c3402bc9"
msgid ""
"\\\"At first I just watched and laughed. But now it's not funny anymore. The lads "
"are so wound up, they're going to start killing each other! The fighting has to be "
"stopped. Divide the army in two. I'll take command of half. A new general, Zefa, "
"will command the other. She's the leader of the mages. She's still green for now, "
"but she's got potential. I'll put infantry officer Chevold under her command. He's "
"a swordmaster from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}. That's what makes him think he can bully "
"her. Promoting her to be his immediate commander will force him to calm down.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ddd0692-e23b-4fff-8a1c-c400f09a1ee6"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's time to show the mages that the soldiers are the real power in your army. "
"Divide the army and appoint a second general. I vote for Chevold, the infantry "
"officer. He was the very first {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} swordmaster in our army. He "
"proved himself in the war with {g|Numeria}Numeria{/g}. When the mage officer Zefa "
"hears about this, she'll stop causing trouble.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2ea642b-2c5d-493d-9b36-24e77c7b5e27"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, there's unrest among the army's ranks. Your mages are turning "
"up their noses at the warriors, claiming that they're the army's main assault "
"force. There's little doubt that their power is great, but what would it be worth "
"if they weren't shielded by the infantry?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f14c04f3-1e33-41b9-b8b7-8aa943693c50"
msgid ""
"\\\"There have already been a few fights. And sooner or later, there will be "
"blood. We have to prevent this. And I've got a plan. You should appoint a second "
"general to show them who is more important.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8b681488-af17-406b-a549-84243334fd52"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you choose Chevold, the infantry officer, the warriors won't be so easily "
"trifled with. He's a good fighter. He was among the first to join the army, and "
"he's proven himself in battle. He will be assigned the officer mage Zefa. She's "
"powerful but arrogant, and lacks experience.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c249242-e470-4b43-8167-6677013cd2ab"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you trust the lady mage more than you trust your warriors? Or is there a "
"personal reason you refuse to listen to my reason? Do you think her wits and skill "
"in magic mean more than looking death in the eye on the front lines? I'm not sure "
"the soldiers will applaud your decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17a4bbfd-9544-443e-9b36-c69b1a90d089"
msgid ""
"\\\"A general must be able to stand in the front line and lead the troops, not to "
"sit back in the rear where the mages stay. Chevold will make a worthy general!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3538641b-9f00-4715-976d-b2c718a65b46"
msgid ""
"\\\"The kingdom requires developed trade. I want every merchant across our lands "
"to receive a warm welcome, whether they're our own citizens or foreigners.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d266a432-1ca0-43b5-9903-ec91cf519666"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let them remember their less fortunate neighbors. Let every poor man or a "
"vagabond find their place on a ship that sails toward opportunity, shelter, and "
"wages.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bc3a0c8-39b7-4daa-9614-d2fbf6c66f11"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let them hold a celebration in my honor. That will please me, and the people "
"will have a good time!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63b6398c-203b-4319-940e-ffb473033b81"
msgid ""
"\\\"I want to develop trade. Let them tend to the roads and guard foreign caravans "
"with their lives!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28051da5-0dd1-4832-a6a7-c8223db81b01"
msgid ""
"\\\"Their crimes are serious. But I expect they will to be forgiven, if each chief "
"sacrifices a part of their wealth to the temple of one of the gods.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44668218-564b-43dd-b03f-38877acde257"
msgid ""
"\\\"I want my subjects to live in safety. Let the bandits organize volunteer "
"militia and to safeguard the citizens' security.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aacc097a-14f1-4bd0-839e-0b3da3d5f37b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd like to congratulate you, {name}. When you took the Stag Lord's throne, "
"you had a choice whether to rely on the support of decent, honorable people – or "
"thieves, which were then so powerful in these lands. You made the right choice, "
"and together with the people, you managed to overthrow the bandits! Peasants who "
"once cowered in fear now boldly report every crime! They trust the authorities. "
"The {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} prosper under your reign as never before!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51080df9-896b-4fb2-b5c2-00f577e4f054"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I'm proud to serve you. No one would have believed that the {g|Stolen "
"Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} could have turned from a criminal hotbed into a secure "
"legitimate country in such a short time. But you did it! Our youth dream of "
"becoming craftsmen, farmers and guards when they grow up, not forest bandits! "
"People that once cowered in fear of bandits now boldly report every crime! It's no "
"longer so easy for a bandit to hide among our honest citizens.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7461acb-a65a-428f-8c06-f8a82cbe2e62"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, you've done the impossible! You developed a mighty kingdom with "
"thieves and bandits from all across the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}! Every "
"other man in our domain keeps a bow or a mace under their bed. Who could ever have "
"imagined that the thugs could be this loyal... or grateful!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "811326b4-8085-4272-a3b5-a63f719458f4"
msgid ""
"\\\"A guild of river shipbuilders arrived today. They are very respected in these "
"lands, and local trade is impossible without them. They would like to thank you "
"for getting rid of the bandits, who sank most of the crafts they built. They ask "
"how they might repay you. How should we invest their energy?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac770dd9-93f8-4bea-ad76-3523363b585b"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you'd failed to reckon with the forest brethren, things would have turned "
"out much worse. They truly appreciate you, their chieftain. In fact, a messenger "
"arrived only today. Several major bandit leaders send you their wishes for many "
"years of happiness, and ask how they can thank you for your vision and your "
"generosity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3ba6543-b3a5-495f-954e-dca062fe57cf"
msgid "\\\"Excellent! I'm sure the merchants will appreciate the attention.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5028aec-1d99-4695-a316-1108c47d8ca5"
msgid ""
"\\\"That is so like you! Rather than caring about yourself and ordering a statue "
"of gold, you think of others! You're too kind! Let me pass along your message.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d11dbaf2-039a-4be7-8212-92fb917f4b79"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll throw a magnificent singing contest! Bards from all around will sing "
"songs about your deeds, praising you and your kingdom, and the mark you've left in "
"history!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b80760ac-d3b2-40e4-90fb-5061023545d9"
msgid ""
"\\\"That is a good solution. If we engage them like this, they will feel "
"responsible for maintaining order. The next thing you know, they'll stop spilling "
"blood for no reason.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cade6174-aba5-4725-aac9-c030e3f88125"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you think the gods can wash away blood for gold? Hmm. But no matter, this "
"is a question of faith, not governance. I'll do as you say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18a1d97f-d5d2-41a2-98bd-7e4206833547"
msgid ""
"\\\"I understand. The gods know they weren't born criminals. Everyone has their "
"own reason to do things... Things they're not proud of.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e731d7d6-b9b4-4f21-a43d-0c3a1f8f4a9a"
msgid ""
"\\\"That makes sense. Let the ones who have eyes everywhere help the guards "
"maintain order.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b7f1c94-fde3-4166-bf66-1c05c6c0e63c"
msgid ""
"\\\"They say they recognize you as their leader. They also admit their fault for "
"failing to deal with Davor, who disrespected you. Their laws prohibit them from "
"remaining in debt. What shall we ask of them?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c315cd86-72ee-4074-93c1-fa11631e39c0"
msgid ""
"\\\"People are grateful to you for the change. A guild of river shipbuilders "
"arrived at the palace today. They are highly respected in the {g|River Kingdoms}"
"River Kingdoms{/g}. They would like to thank you with a gift, for ridding the "
"rivers of the pirates who sank the ships they built. How shall we put them to use?"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ae74f7fd-aec1-4a50-9234-1e1e46b63099"
msgid ""
"\\\"I hope the merchants appreciate this gesture. I will convey your message to "
"them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51e3cdd4-a6ec-439b-a380-8190eb2906a8"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is wise. It is best to reduce the number of desperate people in our "
"kingdom. I will pass on your suggestion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8c636e0-5d43-4c1a-a600-9844355b8412"
msgid ""
"\\\"Pardon me for saying this, but... that's a waste of money! I'll ask one of "
"your advisors to take care of it. Cultural events... aren't my thing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e508a133-56fc-46ba-8d96-69db3f7b947b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd like to express my respect, {name}. I could never have done what you did! "
"It was no easy task to unite all our unruly troublemakers into a single people, "
"and earn their respect and trust. That takes more than just willpower. It takes "
"political vision!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7aa75cb6-8f19-41b1-b255-a68716ef96cd"
msgid ""
"\\\"I... don't entirely agree with you. But you decided to keep the peace with the "
"forest thugs, and even managed to come to terms with them, however shaky that "
"alliance was... Perhaps it was wise. Every other person in your domain is a "
"bandit, after all. So this brings you to the top of a strange pyramid. You rule "
"the bandits without starting a war. It's really quite unbelievable.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc923f96-8155-4e33-9c2a-0700eceaffd6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The forest brethren repay you with their respect. A messenger arrived today. A "
"few chieftains declare their loyalty and ask for your orders. They made a mistake "
"letting Davor rebel, and now they wish to make amends. What will you command of "
"your, ahem, servants?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c598db66-b519-4d2e-8056-4a083d9863dc"
msgid ""
"\\\"As long as our trade routes remain safe, we can afford these bandits' fee. "
"They might even turn into regular guards over time. Who knows!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1ecfaaa-a7b0-437c-ab90-ab92c08e9228"
msgid ""
"\\\"What a strange decision – to set forest thugs upon ordinary bandits and "
"criminals. I can't understand it, but your order will be fulfilled.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16a3b8d2-68e8-4a35-bfc1-671c05ac4f2f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Drive this bandit from my lands, and from now on do the same to any similar "
"petitioners!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e837d05b-60fb-4d05-bb5a-220812eb7a77"
msgid ""
"[Gain 50 BP] \\\"Arrest this bandit and clap him in irons. The same fate awaits "
"any like him!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f4c8270-0958-46f8-8529-4fc5c41a495c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will accept this tribute. I hope this good lad and his colleagues will "
"continue to share their revenue in the future.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0419cb6-4a5e-449c-acfe-ecd1f5f66b0e"
msgid "\\\"You know best what to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4fe31cf7-1143-4987-bc5f-94235cd3e876"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia looks alarmed.{/n} \\\"You won't believe what just happened! Some crook "
"showed up at your gates, insisting on seeing 'the {mf|lad|lass} who bumped off the "
"Stag Lord'! He says that he's brought a tribute to the new chief of the {g|Stolen "
"Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}, and asks for permission to conduct his 'business' under "
"your protection!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "03d97f31-3050-45c6-8579-fc89b303b957"
msgid ""
"\\\"You don't want to be seen as another Stag Lord, and your lands as an open "
"field for thugs. Then throw this scoundrel out – along with his tribute!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a968543-3710-4aac-8a12-82c458f1941e"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie enters the throne room, fiercely stabbing her heels into the floor as "
"she approaches. She stands before you and simmering with indignation.{/n} \\\"I "
"would never have thought that I'd commence my career as Regent with such a case, "
"but... the leader of a local gang is at your gate. He's brought a chest stuffed "
"with stolen goods, which he wants to share with you – the new lord of the {g|"
"Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e0bd067-724c-4a7e-8418-b65b699695be"
msgid ""
"\\\"I insist this impudent man be immediately arrested and brought to justice. "
"Your lands have a long and dark legacy, but your subjects fail to grasp that the "
"times of cutthroats and extortionists are over, and law rules here, now and "
"henceforth!\\\" {n}Valerie flares her nostrils vehemently.{/n} \\\"You will not "
"protect these bandits as the Stag Lord did!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "858b014c-bfe4-4d71-84c6-8f6fafe3e28b"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander smiles.{/n} \\\"Oh, it's an amusing situation, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}! A former cohort of the Stag Lord – a simple local "
"bandit – has come to pay us a visit. It seems that he and all the other bandits in "
"the area believe that you are now the new lord of the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen "
"Lands{/g}. So they sent him to pay their respects. He even brings gifts!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b662cb0-cfb3-4f3b-8802-69bdf8de3209"
msgid ""
"\\\"He wishes to share his loot, so that in response you will permit him to "
"conduct his, ahem, business in your territory. It's not a bad solution – I'm sure "
"the bandits will pay generously for the right to be private tax-collectors. Of "
"course, outside your lands some may look upon this as organized extortion – but "
"what do you care about those stiffs from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c29e352-142f-4cf2-bf57-b675b667c211"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia nods.{/n} \\\"Of course! I will indulge myself a bit, and let our "
"citizens chase the crook to the city gates!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2471935e-6cdc-4c90-af3a-e7322bd2df0c"
msgid ""
"\\\"So these presumptuous criminals can run rampant in someone else's lands? "
"Still, at least this may teach them half a lesson.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17accc32-616f-436f-b340-6ebd30728188"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander's face grows long.{/n} \\\"Oh, come now! You can't react like this to "
"every business proposal, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}!\\"
"\" {n}Lander sighs.{/n} \\\"But of course, I will do as you say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a31ba33a-8b67-412c-ba75-6dc4322faf24"
msgid "\\\"You're in no mood for games today, I see! Fine, let it be so.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "351d6e4a-8fe8-43a4-b4ab-c951e976f7fc"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie catches her breath and allows a faint smile to show on her face.{/n} \\"
"\"I will carry out your orders with pleasure, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dfe694e4-e873-44cf-bafe-52d62a7e8b77"
msgid ""
"{n}The smile disappears from Lander's face.{/n} \\\"Oh? I can't say this is a wise "
"decision: there won't be any fewer bandits in your lands… they just won't be "
"contributing to the treasury. But very well, it's up to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "07d0401a-5180-46b9-87ac-ce999c1ffaa0"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia opens her mouth, amazed, and for a moment seems to have lost her gift "
"of speech.{/n} \\\"So… so we what? Just let these scoundrels rob our poor citizens "
"without fear? How can we allow this!?\\\" {n}The girl looks at you anxiously.{/n} "
"\\\"I don't know what's got into you, but I don't like this at all!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f4c3860-7756-4d17-9fd8-d3391fdf685e"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie's face turns morbid and pale. For a moment she struggles to say "
"something, but in the end manages to force out only a single sentence, through "
"gritted teeth.{/n} \\\"As you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5fb9d11b-3502-48ed-a952-ee2ae8239d77"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander rubs his hands together.{/n} \\\"I'm sure your Treasurer will be glad of "
"this decision! Your subjects are not only the plowmen, but also such adventurous "
"folks as this one – and you can't just take away their wages!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40bafd90-c68a-4775-93c1-68213cf233af"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then this scoundrel and everyone like him can forget the way to these lands!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac5bd6c8-30c5-43aa-a8c5-82efca9f4a89"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will personally arrest this scoundrel, and see to it that his henchmen end "
"up in prison cells beside him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19e02bd4-6587-439a-aaa8-598de8716288"
msgid ""
"\\\"In that case I shall accept the petitioner's gifts, and discuss further "
"compensation with him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a289192f-4eb5-4373-bfcb-569a2db33681"
msgid "\\\"Return the cow to the shepherd.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da1cad89-f487-44bb-b662-674e040316ed"
msgid "\\\"Give the cow to the neighbor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "100ee10d-ea20-4b55-9e8d-2f7b2790fec8"
msgid "Seized the cow from the villagers."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89c04375-e248-4621-84d3-d02ae4e2307f"
msgid ""
"[Gain 10 BP] \\\"I like your idea, Lander. Confiscate the cow. It belongs to the "
"{mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2895fdb-0a3e-493e-a060-01fe86c20bc2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will not deal with such trifles! Send this petitioner away, and don't waste "
"any more of my time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d66b6d9c-79f1-452d-879c-27cef415268b"
msgid "\\\"I think you can manage this problem on your own.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e75f5525-5fea-48ff-a0ca-eb5a72e77458"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia smiles cunningly.{/n} \\\"I have good news. Your subjects, who have "
"until recently held you in distrust, now have such faith in you that they insist "
"on your final word to settle their disputes – such as the one I bring you today!\\"
"\" {n}Octavia giggles, but then grows serious.{/n} \\\"All right, since we're "
"here, we may as well help.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a2c1262-5913-42c2-bcbe-4392620094df"
msgid ""
"\\\"A shepherd has come to the capital, begging that you personally resolve a "
"delicate situation. You see, this shepherd has a favorite cow... please don't "
"laugh! This is important to your subjects! Well, this cow likes to graze in his "
"neighbor's yard. The neighbor was patient for a while, but then locked the cow in "
"her barn, claiming: 'If I feed the cow, then the milk is mine!'\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6288de7-b84a-4af9-acd9-9334cf704df4"
msgid ""
"\\\"The shepherd and his neighbor have been quarreling for two days, and it's "
"nearly come to blows! Settle their argument for them – after all, you're the {mf|"
"baron|baroness|king|queen}!\\\" {n}Octavia shakes her head.{/n} \\\"I have no "
"idea, who I'd give the cow to. Both sides have reasonable arguments…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3b3b488-497b-462b-b559-5dd9ef446a3c"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie keeps silent for a few moments, pursing her lips.{/n} \\\"I don't know "
"where to begin... You see, your subjects, who until recently felt only suspicion "
"towards you, are gradually changing their minds. What you've been able to do for "
"the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} has apparently made them feel that they can "
"bring you any problem they have – even the most trivial!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "085d67bc-234e-4277-81dd-a10ede366421"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie sighs.{/n} \\\"The neighbor of a local shepherd has taken his cow. "
"Apparently, the owner let it graze in her back yard, and now the woman refuses to "
"return the animal. According to her, she tolerated the imposition long enough, and "
"now feels the milk belongs to her. The shepherd, of course, is demanding the "
"return of his property.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8964d21d-b960-4e98-860d-127212497355"
msgid ""
"\\\"As I see it, the shepherd is right. The cow belongs to him, and it must be "
"returned to the owner. Although, if you want to know my other opinion…\\\" {n}"
"Valerie's face becomes more stern.{/n} \\\"This is a matter for the village chief "
"or a village council, or something of the sort – not for the supreme ruler of the "
"lands. This {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} may not be vast, but that doesn't "
"mean the peasants should bother you with such trifles.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42e1e96f-b7d1-4fb4-98d3-ce2622ee36d2"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! Your subjects now "
"believe in you so sincerely that they even trust you with the fate of their cattle!"
"\\\" {n}Lander laughs, amused at himself.{/n} \\\"Don't look at me like that, {mf|"
"baron|baroness|King|Queen}, it's true! Not long ago, your peasants thought you "
"were an impostor, no better than the Stag Lord – and now they're ready to hang all "
"their troubles on your door!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34c7d3a6-cade-496b-b3e8-165bb15a57dd"
msgid ""
"\\\"An aggrieved shepherd has come to court, demanding you deal with his "
"complicated and very mysterious case! You see, the shepherd has a cow, which a "
"neighbor has stolen from him. The woman, for her part, argues that the animal has "
"been grazing in her back yard for months, so both the cow and all its milk belong "
"to her. Oh, such brilliant village logic! Of course, the shepherd is livid and "
"demands justice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ebe8b1c3-74d6-4f15-8ac4-6047134a3ed3"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander smiles cunningly.{/n} \\\"Here's what I say. You can judge such cases, "
"if you wish to waste your time... or you can simply send some guards to confiscate "
"the cow. You'll take a modest profit and teach these foolish peasants a lesson: "
"they can solve their problems on their own, or lose whatever they're quarrelling "
"over.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4391d39e-9dc6-4f25-a3e9-ef4490e3b180"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia nods in consent.{/n} \\\"The word of the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} "
"is law!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd86123f-4797-431a-9267-8223de39c864"
msgid "{n}Valerie nods.{/n} \\\"Of course.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "883f372d-616c-4a39-8955-59d21b3a072b"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander cringes.{/n} \\\"A {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}, deciding the fate of "
"a cow... There is something wrong about this, forgive my audacity. Beware, they "
"may start asking you which side of the bed they should get up on in the morning!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "503953b0-8009-460d-9597-6840447ff364"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie raises her brow.{/n} \\\"Do you think that's fair? Just taking "
"something that belongs to one person and giving it to another? I am sorry to hear "
"that this is your judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7208e75f-c839-472b-b395-5294146fa91e"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander bows slightly.{/n} \\\"I serve {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|"
"Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aef97d2c-ceb6-4b47-9abc-51eca468a838"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia looks baffled.{/n} \\\"How so? Your subjects trust you with an "
"important decision... and you just dismiss them? You can't do that!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2637738-835f-4e3d-b51e-428fe9537e7e"
msgid ""
"{n}A contented smile crosses Valerie's face.{/n} \\\"I shall do precisely as you "
"ordered.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af60c98a-ecac-4472-a620-54a376e20a2c"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander shrugs.{/n} \\\"Ah, and just when we were about to gain a dairy cow for "
"the state property fund. But as you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1ef61a2-0502-44d5-902c-15ad240b899a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will give the cow to the neighbor. After all, without her clover there "
"wouldn't be any milk!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0b9da5f-a7b1-4c07-8239-cab230ac66ba"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will give the cow to the shepherd. Now make sure such issues are resolved "
"without my intervention from now on.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "252f0710-c43c-41d3-9c61-1408d2fc6934"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will take the cow... I mean, I will order it confiscated. We must seize the "
"occasion, mustn't we?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6725556f-caaa-4bdb-b126-c744d7b41819"
msgid "[Pay 75 BP] \\\"I like this idea. Let us build a consulate in Brevoy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f3c4d428-66dc-49b6-9f9a-25225ff3ca4f"
msgid "\\\"We can do without a consulate in Brevoy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d05a994a-c65e-4270-bc09-1e877c191074"
msgid "\\\"You can resolve this issue without me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c82cf7a-06c4-48f3-918b-1ac15aab7d76"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia looks embarrassed.{/n} \\\"I've come with... a request. Could you find "
"a diplomat to handle negotiations and politics? I lack the stamina to lead "
"complicated discussions... and I don't have time at all for politics. Your "
"subjects grow in number, and their problems multiply. It seems almost everyone "
"demands attention!\\\" {n}The girl smiles timidly.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45cbd7b0-2783-4876-9331-f2e47b454fd1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Speaking of their problems: I keep hearing about how difficult it is for your "
"subjects outside the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}. Especially in {g|Brevoy}"
"Brevoy{/g}, these past few weeks. Their merchants overcharge our peasants or use "
"their connections to force our people into a disadvantageous agreements! Why not "
"build a consulate there? I'm sure your subjects will appreciate you taking care of "
"them, even when they travel outside the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8023cb1-89f8-441c-a341-febe4728dee9"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie rubs her temple thoughtfully.{/n} \\\"Your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|"
"kingdom} requires a diplomat, {name}. Relationships with our neighbors require "
"special attention. Appoint a new advisor to manage this aspect of your barony.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2fb5810-8ad3-4ede-8aa3-f3a5af5f0356"
msgid ""
"\\\"But before you transfer these responsibilities to someone else, I would like "
"to make one suggestion. Not country can ignore the interests of its citizens who "
"travel beyond its borders. Our most active trade relations and cultural exchanges "
"are with {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}. I suggest we arrange with them to build a consulate "
"in their capital. Then, all your subjects who visit there can enjoy our support "
"and protection. As I see it, it's a worthy investment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aaa054cd-3329-474f-a453-26e71f5e151d"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, it's time to hire "
"another advisor. You need someone who can oversee our diplomatic relationships "
"with other countries. Considering your complicated ties to {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, "
"and the character of the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}, the earlier you "
"find a talented Grand Diplomat, the better.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6366098d-cfbd-4b83-a995-c7d1ee61aebf"
msgid ""
"\\\"Speaking of diplomacy, the project of a consulate in {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} has "
"appeared on my desk. This would be an establishment for your subjects, who find "
"themselves in trouble while traveling there. To my mind it's a waste of money, but "
"I felt duty-bound to inform you personally about this idea.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3443492-ec82-4c2c-b085-abf0bd97a13c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful! I'm glad that we'll be taking care of your subjects even when "
"they're traveling outside the country!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f5a79c4-00f2-4555-95fc-bfac56a97792"
msgid "\\\"Then I shall make the necessary arrangements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4de8647c-ad65-4c11-9efd-d005ac57aeb9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmm. As you wish, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c08137d-286e-4514-adf7-3f730d311087"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia grows dark.{/n} \\\"So you'll just let these matters slide? I expected "
"better from you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0df4474-fd01-4a69-8e80-75a91fde9fe5"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie frowns.{/n} \\\"Without legal support, your subjects will feel that the "
"weakness of their position is a reflection of their ruler's weakness. But it's up "
"to you – I'm only pointing out the potential for future problems.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63bf3caa-768d-43fb-b369-b778db9a1a9f"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander nods.{/n} \\\"I am sure {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness} can find better uses for the {mf|barony's|barony's|kingdom's|kingdon's} "
"resources.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c9f80512-4931-474c-a607-104111113e6a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will arrange everything. I do hope {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} supports this "
"project!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4938f56-592f-4d3e-9e34-f802b90c203a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will send a few letters, and wait for an answer from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}. I "
"think they will approve of the idea of building a consulate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "519abb0c-5050-479c-b6dd-3236ba002894"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nothing could be simpler! I just won't do anything. The easiest decision of my "
"entire regency!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7aa5c08-fab0-4555-b60d-473bcaa2962d"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander yawns ostentatiously.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|"
"Your Highness}, I wonder: have you noticed anything odd lately? For example, that "
"I'm trying my best to help you, and you... you simply dismiss my advice! I think I "
"should step down and let someone else take this position. Of course, I will, as "
"always, remain present at your court as an envoy. But as for everything else – you "
"know better than I, what the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} needs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81d4c475-2c4e-48e6-a510-7cfd7398925b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've had enough. I've tried my best to make your job easier, but you have an "
"opinion about everything! I think you need another Regent – someone who cares less "
"about her work than I do!\\\" {n}Octavia sighs.{/n} \\\"I'm sorry, but you really "
"will have to find another advisor to fill my post.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0da8dd78-4d34-459d-82f6-4c1ca3c6f435"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will do precisely as you say. But after this I will step down from office. "
"Our opinions on the administration of a country are simply too different. Thank "
"you for your trust, but you will simply have to find someone else to fill the "
"Regent's position.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e3f1f88-54e1-4d2c-b864-8f5125632ed1"
msgid "\\\"We need money and that means business. I'm willing to make a deal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed65a745-1e5b-49b3-9233-2dbb255cac65"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're not Brevoy's dump. Let them find another place to put their trash.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a2d739ba-3466-4539-84bb-cd5f329fc261"
msgid "\\\"I trust your opinion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc4516b4-4983-45ac-8bf3-2f5ea4b287bf"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}! We have a big fish here today – a noble from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}. His "
"clothes are worth hundreds of gold coins, and his eyes are shifty. He has a "
"business offer to make. He wants to open a leatherworking shop in our domain, to "
"tan skins.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9d0a7fa6-b81c-4f0c-8e4e-5f1da7637bc3"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, a nobleman from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} has arrived. He requests your "
"approval to open a small business. He desires to open a few leatherworking shops "
"in your domain, to tan skins.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b19c1120-55bf-466f-b75c-284b55737632"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, a man of influence has "
"arrived. He's a nobleman from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, a wealthy charlatan – the kind "
"of a dealer I like most. He has a few tanneries in Brevoy. He desires to relocate "
"them to your lands, and share the profit with you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20c41d76-2d42-440a-abd5-a85f811b562b"
msgid ""
"\\\"So that's how it is now, eh? We receive shiny gold, and {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} "
"gets clean air and healthy children.\\\" {n}Octavia's voice rings with irritation, "
"and her eyes flash with a scornful look.{/n} \\\"Indeed, who cares about these "
"beggars, your subjects!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0495541-d71d-4211-b682-273b0d97cf82"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll give the orders to begin construction. I'll also reinforce the patrols, "
"in case there's any unrest. It's time your subjects learn how to work for an "
"honest living, even if it means a nasty smell.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8252a06a-c66b-476f-98d9-f78ff49e269d"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander winks and smiles delicately.{/n} \\\"Excellent. After all, nobody ever "
"died of a nasty odor. I assume.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87402d3f-d27a-4e64-9a5b-9f63d2818e10"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia's eyes glow.{/n} \\\"Perfect! We didn't save these lands to just turn "
"them into a dump! Free from alchemical fumes, our people will live here happily "
"and give birth to healthy children.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3fb9b3b-3f40-4723-a48f-a1e71e01dbb2"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie's tone betrays thinly veiled irony.{/n} \\\"I'm sure your subjects will "
"make better use of {g|Brevoy}Brevoy's{/g} gold than they can of their pride. "
"Especially gold they earn by plying a fair trade – as opposed to their typical "
"methods!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7329123b-517d-4fb9-860b-77eacb3133d8"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander rubs his eyes wearily.{/n} \\\"It's not rubbish. It's trade and profit. "
"Which we'll never see, unless you quit acting as if your throne is standing upon "
"bags of gold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fd1cc35a-80b8-4f70-814b-26ebd24c47ca"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie nods solemnly.{/n} \\\"I'll give the order to prepare a location for "
"the tanneries. The guards will deal with any loudmouths who complain about the "
"smell.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1868be6-1e94-4505-bbb0-455979d92d67"
msgid ""
"\\\"A fine choice, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. You can "
"count on me. I'll immediately have people sent out to determine the best location "
"for the tanneries. We certainly wouldn't want their...\\\" {n}{g|House Lebeda}"
"Lebeda{/g} frowns gently.{/n} \\\"... odor... clouding the air we breathe here at "
"the palace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "95e02c0c-4ff3-4bed-9ad3-756fdef6cefc"
msgid ""
"\\\"These tanneries smell like a kobold's backside. This industry requires the use "
"of alchemical components, which are carried by the wind and cause nasty diseases. "
"Nobody's happy about these factories being in {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}. That's the "
"reason he's come to us. The offer is profitable, no doubt, but the smell that "
"comes with it is foul. We mustn't make a deal with this little man. Better to send "
"him away – and quickly. That will teach the other moneybags a lesson too. Just "
"because you're stuffed with gold, that doesn't mean you're allowed to do whatever "
"you want.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f41ef8ff-7a2c-459b-ad0c-7bfb7471c7bb"
msgid ""
"\\\"This alchemical enterprise would make an unpleasant neighbor. Of course, the "
"locals won't be happy about the waste and the smell, but we must concentrate on "
"our business interests and relationships with our neighboring countries. The "
"people of {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} will happily pay to move these tanneries away from "
"their homes. But you have the right to make whatever decision you consider best "
"for the country.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7d634cc-12b3-48f7-9cc8-79db25101102"
msgid ""
"\\\"These tanneries stink. The alchemical waste is hazardous, unless you're a "
"Kobold of course. It's only natural that nobody in {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} is happy "
"about having such a neighbor. This merchant will pay handsomely to pour his waste "
"into our land instead. We have plenty of forests and rivers, after all. Even if we "
"ruin a couple, it won't be so bad, and the gold will certainly come in handy. Some "
"of your people will surely be unhappy, but when are we concerned about the "
"complaints of peasants? I think we must say yes!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6df58e2a-958a-4917-aca9-6564998f5e1e"
msgid "Reimbursed the merchant's stolen goods."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "058a1d7b-91b9-4306-b2b0-d57b4a408c22"
msgid ""
"[Pay 100 BP] \\\"Send guards to search for Davor. Take care of the merchant and "
"reimburse him for the stolen goods.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da47ad86-81e8-4d0f-b2f1-c25a847d2d48"
msgid ""
"\\\"Send guards to search for Davor. Regarding the reimbursement... the Brevan "
"will have to do without it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b2e9ee7-2d11-473c-bace-e441ffd14c1b"
msgid "Ignored bloody banditry on the roads."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65937dfe-c90f-4883-89a5-d906c6221966"
msgid "\\\"Let him deal with his problems himself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "816dd232-7786-4a00-bb95-5bb32b9cc69d"
msgid "\\\"I think you already know what should be done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "837736fa-1fcb-43a4-8dfb-052d943b9e9e"
msgid ""
"[Pay 100 BP] \\\"Give him some money and let him go in peace. We're not interested "
"in hunting for robbers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6de8b1fa-c06a-4fc9-ae34-baa04c0afd1e"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's been an accident, {name}! A wounded man is at our gates, all scratched "
"up and covered in blood. He's a noble merchant from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, whose "
"caravan was waylaid by robbers. All of his traveling companions were killed! He's "
"the only survivor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3cc3aa3b-6747-46fa-9b5e-f727a2a152d4"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie clutches her sword.{/n} \\\"{name}! By the gate there a man who "
"survived an ambush. He's a nobleman from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, whose caravan was "
"waylaid by bandits. His companions were all killed, and he's very lucky to be "
"alive himself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f2bdcaa-d326-40e6-88c7-e18e0dbcb514"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander smiles carelessly.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}! A poor fellow, a nobleman from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, has been found "
"near the gates. Sadly, his caravan was ambushed. It seems the bandits who live in "
"the forest claimed it for themselves.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7dd79e54-9a53-44ff-b28c-fe66ff3ce9bb"
msgid ""
"\\\"This ambush was carried out by the infamous villain, Davor the Grey! He's "
"returned to our lands, to continue his dirty deeds. He's not known for his mercy, "
"and responds only to force.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "140a3b32-dc02-4770-8776-a8864333e6cd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Davor the Grey is behind this assault. I suspect he'll soon be bringing us "
"gifts... as soon as he's cleaned the blood off them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33e0ed61-4555-46f5-a6dc-d1ab3f71eb31"
msgid ""
"\\\"Davor the Grey was in command of the robbers. I have no idea how he managed to "
"escape from prison. An old accomplice of his must have tricked the guards or "
"helped him somehow.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c173e58f-0839-4183-a471-7a38863b263b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The man from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} is frightened and outraged. And it is, after "
"all, somewhat our fault. He was robbed on our land, where he's supposed to be "
"under our protection. He wants us to find and punish the robbers, and compensate "
"him for the damages. I think we should comfort this poor man. How would you feel "
"in his position?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b877e563-f224-4a10-84e1-f7e14be474d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"It was Davor the Grey who arranged the ambush. As I said, he should have been "
"put in jail immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df0c120d-2fce-4a96-93b9-3b8ace861a88"
msgid ""
"\\\"It was Davor the Grey who arranged the ambush. The one whose bloody gifts you "
"so gladly accepted.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62ded391-a187-4d8d-85f3-1495cf8c5bea"
msgid ""
"\\\"It was Davor the Grey who arranged the ambush. I already demanded an "
"explanation from the other prisoners. It turns out he escaped through a tunnel he "
"dug.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a79614b-d6e5-4c17-b629-5fa8b11337f2"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Brevan wants us to find the robbers, and he's every right to make such "
"demands. But then his business sense prevailed, and he asked us to compensate his "
"losses. Now this I consider most arrogant! We cannot be held responsible for his "
"caravan! It's Davor that owes him, not you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72c16ff0-190c-4348-9db7-52082b949ca5"
msgid ""
"\\\"It was Davor the Grey who arranged the ambush, the bandit you expelled so "
"carelessly. He must be very angry. Just think how we might have treated him "
"differently, and made him into your obedient hound.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02b4cc64-5dc8-4fd3-a5e1-d0436e2beeb2"
msgid ""
"\\\"It was Davor the Grey who arranged the ambush. See how hard he works to fill "
"your coffers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "615c709e-0104-4bb0-a53f-14f4654f8377"
msgid ""
"\\\"The gang's leader was Davor the Grey, who you so carelessly imprisoned. He "
"only recently escaped, and he has a lot to catch up on.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "490d7313-682c-449d-b80d-40585804ad48"
msgid ""
"\\\"The merchant demands that we find and hang the ambushers, and compensate him "
"for his damages. What makes him think we're ready to pay? Was it we who robbed "
"him? Did he pay us to ensure his safety? Nothing of the sort. We must send a "
"message to him and all the other merchants: anyone looking to travel safely across "
"our lands should dip into their purses. Just ignore his whining, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6bacbd7d-942e-4535-9c4e-6803a8e6597a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect! We'll find Davor, and this time he won't get away so easily. The "
"merchants will see that we're tough on murderers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16def1db-cb35-41f7-a904-2be032225c9c"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're far too generous. On the other hand, a good reputation never did anyone "
"any harm.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3b5e4a12-60d2-4307-b416-3502ba9f6e96"
msgid ""
"\\\"You act as though you have another set of subjects in your pocket, who are "
"somehow entirely different from Davor. Don't you understand that by prosecuting "
"him, you are making half your citizens nervous? They're all doing the same thing, "
"you know.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a92ab9c8-3f2f-4334-9137-17905ae1f2e2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well, I don't like the fact that he's so concerned with his money, "
"either. He should thank gods for keeping him alive, not rush to fill his pockets!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75b13b6c-2276-4db6-8328-fd5910a86313"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie looks determined.{/n} \\\"We won't stop until we have that villain "
"cornered! He shall pay for his deeds.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6a9db16-dc13-47df-8966-e999af4cecb2"
msgid ""
"{n}{g|House Lebeda}Lebeda{/g} rolls the eyes.{/n} \\\"Oh, but what's the point? "
"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness} will cut Davor's head off, "
"and the locals will elect a new chieftain, who will step up and cause the same "
"trouble that Davor did. Mark my word!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d742acdd-d524-480a-b6e2-5712af80c8c3"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia sniffs and clenches her fists.{/n} \\\"This... is wrong. People are "
"being ambushed and killed on our roads, and you... how many more will die by his "
"hand?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc9ca3a3-7039-4750-b4ff-561ff439b746"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie stays silent for a few seconds. Then she speaks somberly.{/n} \\\"This "
"goes against the law, and against all good conscience. Robbers should be executed. "
"But... I shall inform him of your decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "031ff4bc-88d7-4921-a68e-c352eac1f6c6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful. Rest assured, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}, this will do your treasury good. Merchants are always trying to avoid "
"taxation, hide their goods, pass fake gold and the like. Robbery is a far more "
"honest profession. Our forest brethren are happy to pay their fair share to {mf|"
"Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness} – in a timely manner and "
"without quarrel.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44592de0-444f-42f2-a80b-e3d9e84dc39f"
msgid ""
"\\\"We will pay for the merchant's lost goods, and we'll send our people to search "
"for Davor. Assault and robbery cannot be tolerated!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f0ca691a-133d-4b20-84d3-ca30be0542ed"
msgid ""
"\\\"The merchant is lucky to be alive. But it wasn't we who assaulted him. We "
"didn't steal his goods. So he shall get no compensation from us. However, justice "
"will be done. We'll send a troop to find Davor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f4fcd401-14a7-42a5-8082-53547a6f2739"
msgid ""
"\\\"That merchant can go to hell. I hereby announce a new law: if you wish to take "
"a road through the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}, make sure you pay its {mf|"
"baron|baroness} the proper fee, or you risk being robbed of all your belongings.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b73867cc-7289-4a12-8e60-e4cc390d5a42"
msgid ""
"\\\"That is most generous. But we should focus on the murdered caravan escort, who "
"will never need gold again, rather than consoling the merchant for his lost goods. "
"We need to capture those cutthroats!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f16ea051-429f-4be1-93a9-f5a7fa3601d9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... Will we pay compensation to all who ever were or will be robbed? Or only "
"the people we like? Only wealthy and influential foreigners perhaps? This doesn't "
"smack of justice at all.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11f05472-24de-4448-ac22-fbcd15d0c876"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander frowns.{/n} \\\"So it turns out it's not he who has been robbed... it's "
"us? Sometimes I simply do not understand your decisions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98d4d0e2-2a7e-4142-b0de-5a6a22323283"
msgid "Crushed a rebellion in the worst way possible."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd676470-68ec-45c5-86c9-10165d5bb559"
msgid "\\\"We'll crush this rebellion with force. Gather the troops.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c6908ff-63cb-4686-a9b6-4d22683d67e9"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, we've received news regarding Davor the Grey. Our guards have chased "
"him and his gang out to the {g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}. In an attempt to save "
"his own neck, the villain has been lying the locals – trying to win them to his "
"side. He says he's defending the River Freedoms from us, who he calls tyrants and "
"despots. – And it seems he's been successful: he's rallied the people of the "
"Narlmarches, and they've joined forces against us!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53dd2eab-0b4b-4268-b5df-8a89c50c17e3"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia is agitated.{/n} \\\"Grave news, {name}! The chieftain, Davor the Grey, "
"has bitten off more than he can chew. He's sparked a riot in the {g|Narlmarches}"
"Narlmarches{/g}, obviously in an attempt to overthrow you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4aebfcc7-0149-4fbb-9d79-f82a017218af"
msgid ""
"\\\"Something happened that was always destined to happen. The wanton Davor the "
"Grey has spilled so much blood that he's finally lost his mind. He's in the {g|"
"Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}, trying to raise a rebellion against us. Ridiculous as "
"it may sound, I'm afraid he's hoping to start a civil war, and ultimately seize "
"power.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa4a7c32-3eda-41c1-adc3-05a99051c927"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, we have news! Do you "
"remember Davor the Grey? The one your guards have been hunting. Well our soldiers "
"drove him out into the depths of the {g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}, and there "
"he's been taking rather desperate measures. He gathered the peasants there, and "
"fed them lies about how he's defending them from the greedy tyrant's taxations, "
"and that we're hunting him as a result. The people of the Narlmarches have rallied "
"behind him, and they're ready to march on the capital!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "177206a2-7add-4c3f-b1db-642bd749ccf5"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, we are having a minor "
"issue with one of the chieftains. Davor the Grey has claimed the {g|Narlmarches}"
"Narlmarches{/g}, and now he's raising a rebellion. The peasants are behind him. "
"It's unfortunate that he failed to appreciate the advantages of our patronage, but "
"it's an easy problem to remedy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa47773c-5353-4bc5-9aaf-ae6b1da7020f"
msgid ""
"\\\"So we have ourselves quite a situation. On the one hand, we can send out our "
"forces, led by the General. On the other hand, the Treasurer might offer a bounty "
"for Davor's head. But I believe the best way forward is to use diplomacy to "
"persuade the peasants to lay down their weapons. They mustn't die in this petty "
"war, just because some villain abuses their trust! Please remember this when it's "
"time to make your decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c0c252d-7222-4a59-b227-bea18649b055"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must hurry. We can't afford to enter negotiations with Davor and his "
"cutthroats. It's time for the General's army to crush this rebellion. I suppose "
"the Treasurer wouldn't mind bribing Davor's henchmen. I also expect that the Grand "
"Diplomat would prefer to settle this in a peaceful manner. However, there's no "
"more time for such half-measures. The rebels have determined their fate. Remember "
"this when it's time to make your decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e220c60b-0cc6-41a7-92dc-ece2be10d1d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could dispatch troops led by the General – or the Grand Diplomat could "
"commence exhausting negotiations with the peasants. But there's a far easier "
"solution. Let's ask the Treasurer to offer a bounty for Davor's head. I'm sure if "
"we made the right offer, the other chieftains would come running in with Davor's "
"head on a silver platter. Simple and elegant, is it not? But it's up to you to "
"decide, of course.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0af156b-affc-41a9-89cb-a16448061713"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, we have an update about the robberies on the roads. Our guards chased "
"Davor the Grey out into the {g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}. In desperation, he's "
"persuaded the local peasants to rise up in rebellion. Ridiculous as it may sound, "
"he's looking at overthrowing you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f3cd29e-4102-42a2-92e8-da1054a1884a"
msgid "Let the angry mob lynch the bandit chief."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8e4ed5de-8540-45be-b19b-3c872f6ce845"
msgid "\\\"Deny the fight.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c348ac14-fdbf-43c7-8b61-b2fdb64d9dc4"
msgid "Did not let the angry mob lynch the bandit chief."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "421ee5c2-fd17-4cb4-99ac-baf9b5b3cbe6"
msgid "\\\"Let them fight, according to their tradition.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66c3241e-ccd2-4948-b362-d1b711c160f0"
msgid "\\\"Act as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30b72f68-53f3-4d43-b9ff-ef43a192dd6d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I need your advice. There are two clans living in the swamp, both of them old "
"and large families. They've been arguing over a marshland meadow for a few years "
"now. Such fertile land is more valuable than human life in the swamps. The two "
"families have decided to determine the owner by a long-standing tradition.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aff3744d-c06e-4e35-8f26-fe7dd6db3390"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd like to ask you for advice, {name}. Two clans from the swamps are arguing "
"over a meadow. Solid fertile ground is very valuable in the marshes, especially "
"when you have so many mouths to feed. The clan elders decided to determine the "
"owner by a long-standing tradition.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11387868-7661-4f33-9b8e-57a42fee97e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just as I said. There will be no duel! Who cares about their bloody "
"traditions. They wouldn't just be killing each other – they'd be setting an "
"example for their children!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a76bfde2-4c70-4e18-ab3b-3cec1f98dca4"
msgid ""
"\\\"This tradition is older than your kingdom, {name}. Is it wise to interfere "
"with other people's laws without first understanding them?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b0931a9-aad7-44cb-8f42-16de31040047"
msgid ""
"\\\"Trying to cancel a centuries-old tradition by a decree would be like trying to "
"empty their swamp with a bucket. It'll be many years before they're prepared to "
"change their ways.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e5df9747-adad-4ed1-b866-ab90c98e0715"
msgid ""
"\\\"Here's the essence of it. Ten armed men from each clan will face each other in "
"the meadow. The first clan to lose all its fighters relinquishes its claim to the "
"land. It's a cruel tradition, but they've been following it for many generations. "
"Even if we prohibit the tradition, it'll only make them angrier, and they'll seek "
"to settle their scores by other means. Their way of life shouldn't be disturbed.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e6bdbc0-dee9-4c2e-b1d5-b0db07852e92"
msgid ""
"\\\"And that's where the nightmare begins. They're preparing a massacre. A few "
"dozen of armed people, half-naked, will fight on the meadow until one side has "
"lost all of its combatants. This is nothing short of savagery! So I had to "
"threaten them. I told them that if anyone is killed, the crown will claim the "
"meadow. Now the swamp clans complain that we're ruining their centuries-old "
"tradition. I need your support. I'm doing the right thing, aren't I?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "464a8992-beb2-4606-b344-7dbd3d504e64"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia speaks with sorrow.{/n} \\\"You know, you've changed a lot of things "
"here. A lot, but not everything. It's a shame that you think traditional killing "
"over a plot of land is too important to give up.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "272a8b2c-4190-4b30-af12-6509c1520653"
msgid "Announced amnesty for all criminals."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58ccc080-71e6-47b5-bfc1-da4f3f2198da"
msgid ""
"\\\"Anyone who starts working for an honest living will be pardoned for their "
"crimes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3880c9b4-863e-4d48-ab9f-69fe26b3994b"
msgid "Refused to forgive the criminals."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3d21d5bc-060e-462e-ba4f-a8d9b0bb29e5"
msgid ""
"\\\"They must be held accountable for their crimes. They will be shown no mercy.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eabd3169-a5e2-4b1e-b6a3-2ba4108ec706"
msgid "\\\"You should find the solution yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd93df61-1ded-45c9-821d-0a05cc4237d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our anti-criminal measures have been a success! The bandits hide deep in the "
"thicket, afraid to poke their heads out. But guess what. Many of them went down "
"that dark road in the first place because they had no other way to provide for "
"their families...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a195443-939e-47fa-bfba-fdc1a8f5aaa0"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, your kingdom is a refuge for criminals. Bandits feel at ease here, "
"their pockets full of gold – and they pay you their respects. Indeed, they regard "
"you as their chieftain, not an enforcer of the law. That is why they leave your "
"servants alone. However, they would like something in return. We should pardon "
"them. Many of them are sick of being outlaws, even though they're wealthy ones. "
"They want to live out in the open, and be solid citizens!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27785448-508d-4b88-b7e2-186ba9e47bca"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, we're fighting crime in our lands, and the bandits are running scared. "
"In fact, many of them are ready to come clean and return to civilian life. They "
"insist that it was starvation that led them down the slippery slope, but now that "
"the kingdom is prospering, they want to return and do honest work. Their families "
"are flooding us with petitions for pardon.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3bdfe3b-f0ed-4c7c-bd9a-02384a3aa390"
msgid ""
"\\\"Robbery is thriving in our kingdom. Some of the bandits who've made their "
"fortune here even act as your unofficial vassals. They pay their respects to you "
"and your people, and regard you as the chieftain of these lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "335fd42b-3cd9-4c01-8ac1-0320734f88bd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now that the people are better off, they're anxious to return home. But "
"they're frightened of the consequences. Their families are flooding us with "
"petitions of pardon. I think they deserve a second chance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "01e97fe1-92aa-4ca7-a3f0-7ce3a3689f00"
msgid ""
"\\\"I consider it inappropriate. You can't pardon highwaymen and murderers, and "
"let them live in peace among their victims! Every single one of them must answer "
"for their crimes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8aff5227-0a00-4738-b144-af8815f44ff6"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is merciful. I'm sure they'll enjoy peaceful life better than banditry. "
"As far as their conscience is concerned... perhaps they'll find a way to clear it."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65398d12-bd0e-48a3-9b3d-816a4c0fd48b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you expect them to give up their criminal habits so easily? Do you expect "
"your people to forget who robbed them, and not seek to settle the score? You've "
"only divided your people even further...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f407a80-c9d6-4445-8817-dcc40b9e035a"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia suddenly blushes, clenches her fists and blurts out, nearly shouting,{/"
"n} \\\"Well, if someone has done something wrong in their life, should they always "
"bear the mark?!\\\" {n}She then decisively stomps her foot.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f43c30cf-37cf-4a69-a244-a5b673803590"
msgid "\\\"That is reasonable. I'm glad we see the situation the same way.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd752335-004b-4d20-ae92-c6db12bc60c1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let those seeking an honest living return to their homes. But the gods won't "
"protect them if they betray our trust!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c412ff7e-4cab-4ab3-88e9-e7313236dedf"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let them turn themselves in and face a fair trial for their deeds. There will "
"be no general pardon.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f603c34f-e3c1-4215-a793-4a5f9ffc7039"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a good idea, if you ask me. The bandits are the most powerful 'estate' in "
"all of {kingdomname}. Since we're not fighting them, let's try to make friends "
"with them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a836773a-befb-472b-87db-37e601c15145"
msgid ""
"\\\"But our guards remain a thorn in their side. In hopes of someday living "
"openly, the bandits have sent you a petition for pardon. They say they'll declare "
"themselves your servants if you stop hunting them down. It's just more evidence "
"that this situation with the criminals has already gone too far. It's high time we "
"hunt them down and bring them to justice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08112a43-00ba-4333-bd84-5df5dc653fb8"
msgid "Prohibited the River Freedoms in the kingdom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f2887e7-f058-4599-ad25-bfac9c6e1172"
msgid ""
"\\\"My kingdom is in need of a noble class. Appoint those who possess enough power "
"and influence to rule over their lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f72f1bec-78d4-4724-a7dc-6e2193ba8f35"
msgid "Refused to prohibit the River Freedoms in the kingdom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec9a2343-42df-4b25-9890-d4ebd2e4234e"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Stolen Lands managed without aristocrats before, they can live without "
"them now and in the future. Let the people decide who they want as governors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "707c7a46-2cdb-49d0-9627-823ca409882a"
msgid "\\\"I'll leave this decision to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b240766-ce44-4951-8a4a-9efd5c73b3d5"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, your kingdom is growing, and its problems grow along with it. They "
"must all be addressed, and this leaves no time for the trivial things. {mf|Barons|"
"Baronesses|Kings|Queens} normally appoint others to deal with the little things. "
"Sometimes it's the mayors and the local leaders. That's how an aristocracy is "
"formed... a circle of power holders... But no matter what you call it, we can't do "
"without such a group of trustees.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8a7ffbc-e5a3-4db8-93ca-7dab689e9be4"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, your kingdom is growing bigger. No matter how many advisors you hire, "
"your officers can't address every problem and issue. A monarch should have "
"vassals: knights, mayors, guild leaders, local chiefs and elders. It is they that "
"form the natural aristocracy, the high society of any kingdom.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06691ea2-71ac-4c92-81a8-e1bdbf9e57de"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, I don't think that will work. We risk breeding an arrogant lot. They'll "
"consider the power they hold over other people's lives some kind of birth right..."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02761c63-ed47-4c3d-9824-c7f2c7631c13"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will personally select those whose ambition equals their talent. They will "
"be powerful enough not only to give people orders, but to protect them. You will "
"have nothing to worry about. It doesn't matter who they were. These warriors will "
"be your loyal vassals, reliable and just. I'll make sure of it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7132fc5-84f7-4e20-9684-7c30b9afddfb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect. I will announce to people that there will be no strange 'barons'. "
"From now on, they are a self-governing the kingdom. This will make them so happy!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0fd04406-2fb1-418b-9044-3a5037ab826e"
msgid ""
"\\\"You shouldn't. Governance is not something you can learn as a merchant or "
"craftsman. It takes talent and an understanding of social responsibility. "
"Community leaders hardly possess such skill.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b98ba89-a909-4566-9b4d-96e8dafc5a4d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Many knights and adventurers seek to become your vassals, and fill the vacancy "
"left by the local bandits you've exterminated. But what if they want more than "
"you're willing to give? This will only puff them up. They might even start bossing "
"people around and hurting them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "885722db-f9a5-4cf8-b4e3-73a2d5f75b45"
msgid ""
"\\\"There was a time when bandit chiefs were the aristocracy of the {g|Stolen "
"Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}, but we put an end to that. Many knights of honor now look "
"to serve you, to become your faithful vassals and enforce the laws of your lands.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46564174-a468-4732-a01c-ed52568d0b19"
msgid ""
"\\\"A common law made up by bandits has lasted for centuries in the {g|River "
"Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}. It says that every troublemaker has the right to talk "
"about whatever they like, that there is no law beyond an oath. Every tramp is free "
"to wander wherever they want. – And no merchants are obliged to pay royal taxes.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dfa1cdeb-c1cd-4dd1-9e2d-3fa247f9a238"
msgid ""
"\\\"The bandit chieftains hold the greatest power in your lands. They already "
"imagine themselves as the barons of your kingdom. Take it from me, giving them "
"even more power would be... Just plain dangerous.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b038e604-9b51-4b0b-934f-a576b0a4c506"
msgid ""
"\\\"Who lives in the villages and towns? The people! Regular citizens! Let them "
"govern their own lives! Our cities and towns have elected their mayors. The "
"villages have chosen their chiefs. They are the pillars we rely on, not a bunch of "
"self-absorbed sloths!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff67b17c-bbe4-47a0-93a0-88ce1fba9f69"
msgid ""
"\\\"Unfortunately, the only people powerful enough to be granted titles are the "
"local bandit chiefs. I'm afraid this situation is all too typical for the {g|"
"Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. Law and virtue is overtaken by brute force and "
"deception. One might expect them to behave with dignity and respect if they become "
"true vassals of the {mf|King|Queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a213a1cb-2841-418d-b080-499972e6e7c3"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's only natural that the law now rests on the shoulders of your royal "
"vassals, not 'representatives of the people'. Mayors and chiefs come and go, but "
"aristocrats remain, committing themselves to a ruler and raising worthy successors "
"from a young age. They're obliged by the nobility that naturally arises from their "
"responsibility to their subjects!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "067ed03b-d70e-4202-9b46-f96b9958f32e"
msgid "\\\"Open publishing houses to print newspapers for our subjects abroad.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ddf181c6-3667-4a56-8012-c19ac33977d0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let the General establish a regiment for foreigners who will serve in the "
"military in exchange for citizenship.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1683bdc-6553-4b51-87ec-ffef79ff7c53"
msgid "\\\"Our domain will accept every oppressed fugitive from foreign lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6fd34588-8278-482a-a0f0-d5146224750b"
msgid "\\\"Start accepting reports about foreign spies in our lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d99bf9fa-71ca-42d7-99f4-98d4061e8930"
msgid "\\\"Assemble a censorship board.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52c9f4e4-a579-48e3-997f-fe2f677fb168"
msgid ""
"\\\"Support our native merchants with special privileges — even if it's not to the "
"foreigners' liking.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "081f8640-a715-4f03-bacf-f08049ab1141"
msgid "\\\"Act as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b791c627-083e-4955-b2a8-7634b9081384"
msgid "\\\"Act as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8a603f9-3b20-4617-a9b5-42aa2e47fdf9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd like to congratulate you, {name}. For the first time, the Stolen Lands "
"have emerged onto the international scene as a strong country worthy of respect. "
"It has far exceeded its history as a wild wasteland. I can hardly believe our "
"diplomacy has achieved such positive effects! I'm thinking of establishing a "
"string of grand embassies, all across Avistan!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ca3aaaa-85c7-4361-a6e2-821f1fc7eb06"
msgid ""
"\\\"You've managed to establish a country whose citizens look to foreign lands "
"with great interest, rather than keeping their distance out of fear. This is a "
"great achievement, especially considering how things once were around here. Many "
"foreigners arrive at our borders seeking citizenship, though they understand that "
"such things are not handed out lightly. They are prepared to serve in the army to "
"earn their place in your domain.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4674e32-f6b2-45be-8249-cb3ee69e4253"
msgid ""
"\\\"So you've managed to build a truly open country. Many foreigners reside in "
"your domain, while your own subjects have no fear of traveling abroad. We are "
"beset by those striving to become citizens, and many are willing to serve in our "
"military to earn the privilege.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "164cb21b-6306-47c0-af13-b3b671ce2fdc"
msgid "Built a closed state."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04dbb5ab-cbe2-4563-a1a5-ff0cd94972b9"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Stolen Lands used to be but a waystation on the road to a better future, "
"which lay somewhere far beyond the horizon. But you've convinced the people to "
"stop seeking greener pastures, and accept this land as their home. This is a true "
"accomplishment!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ed532ee-ab06-4770-a427-44f01195df87"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, it is a great honor to serve you. One isn't even guaranteed a single "
"chance in a lifetime to see someone build something so grand from so little. What "
"was once but a waystation along the road is now a prosperous state rivaling all "
"the River Kingdoms! I'm sure even the rulers of faraway countries were impressed "
"when they first heard about the Stolen Lands. From this day forth, {kingdomname} "
"will be spoken of with respect across the world.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "baa846c0-e349-44cb-a7a9-f80812193e41"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, I received several letters today – welcoming diplomatic notes "
"and offers of friendship. We've had many similar letters before, but these are "
"addressed from Garund. Governors on the other edge of the world have taken an "
"interest in our friendship! They've heard much about us — and we have their "
"respect! This is a great success, Your Highness!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c69a9ee-0ecd-43b0-9ed3-3428ffd217de"
msgid ""
"\\\"You managed to create a country with its own culture and ideals, with no "
"connection to foreign demagogues who would only try to drag us into their own "
"quarrels or inject their foreign ideas. This is admirable. I'm sure we could "
"eliminate all foreign spies and troublemakers completely, if you encouraged your "
"subjects to report all those who promoting the interests of other rulers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1341346-21ed-447c-b315-ea294df4c56c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just as it's always been – people see everything beyond the stinking swamp "
"next door as a bizarre and frightening world that's best avoided. But you somehow "
"managed to elevate your subjects, and they've finally begun to travel abroad. And "
"as for our foreign guests... Well, at least they no longer mumble curses under "
"their breath as soon as they step out of their wagons.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c60cade-85fe-4523-89be-c2ca722b4f77"
msgid ""
"\\\"You managed to build an independent state, one that keeps out of foreign "
"business and doesn't let anyone interfere with our own. Naturally, your authority "
"is stronger than ever before. I have a few ideas on how to sustain this momentum. "
"For starters, you could essentially buy even greater love from your subjects. "
"Grant your merchants certain privileges that are unavailable to their foreign "
"colleagues. Of course, those foreign merchants might be offended. – Some of them "
"would even turn their caravans away. Your main duty, however, is to please your "
"own merchants, and keep your subjects happy and well-heeled.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73d26957-5060-46c6-8fa6-edeee592cd85"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful. The world will hear all about us as soon as the presses start their "
"first run!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee5cc792-4d82-448b-b502-495db8d3ccda"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let it be so. Your subjects would become foreigners if they were long enough "
"separated from their homeland.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a51387b9-f067-460c-a1a0-3f45d1352591"
msgid ""
"\\\"Newcomers from all corners of the world will become not only your subjects, "
"but defenders of your kingdom! It would be so curious to speak with them and hear "
"their stories...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df75d1a9-c4ea-4c64-b07b-65922914034b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Citizenship paid for with blood will be more legitimate in the eyes of the "
"people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e540e657-f6a4-40c5-bb05-b0c0c1243060"
msgid ""
"\\\"Excellent! Your subjects will be grateful if you make those common strays... I "
"mean, zealous citizenship applicants spill their blood for them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fc94085-6ab8-4dc8-b8f9-73de9a40ec61"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's a very merciful decision. Let every poor fellow and unfortunate slave "
"find refuge in this land of hope and unity we have established here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db668978-4e5c-48ea-9564-59d860670c47"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well, let the kingdom be known as a refuge from border to border. Anyone "
"who has suffered injustice or cruelty will find a safe shelter and a fair trial "
"here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5017e9cd-246c-4e5d-8933-14ffb5edf1aa"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... Such a measure will attract cheap labor. Our guest workers won't "
"complain about being left the dirtiest jobs. This is a wise and most compassionate "
"decision, Your Highness!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1bd6d1ab-40fc-42c9-94f4-8941bc15701a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... The press is a powerful instrument for shaping the attitude of foreign "
"subjects. This is very wise, your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55db9b07-95d5-4786-987b-c2bae9f84d6e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I guess it's best if we rely on our people – and they should be able to trust "
"and depend on us in return. If someone commits a crime, naturally their fellows "
"should tell us. It's not like we're doing anything wrong! We just care about "
"them... Right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "046bd433-fd5b-4358-99d4-3d87ad00e6d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"We will prevail upon the people that reporting on spies and traitors is a "
"moral obligation. If you're aware of a crime, remaining silent makes you an "
"accomplice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b99dbb0-f4cb-4207-861a-320bd19fb6df"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect! Why would anyone ever hesitate to report criminal activity? Coming "
"forward is a duty for the sake of society! At least, that's what we'll have to "
"convince the younger generations moving forward...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "104577c9-1e86-43fd-bd38-45a9bd14f8e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmm... I strongly object to censorship on principle. However, I agree that "
"artists must create lasting masterpieces, not throwaways to serve the interests of "
"Irovetti and his ilk. I will order that we only prosecute propaganda, and leave "
"the true artists alone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11381a56-33c9-44c3-b20e-a4bab503c664"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very good. I've always disliked the fact that foolish, dirty, and troubling "
"concepts which are naturally forbidden from polite discussion are nevertheless "
"routinely published, even in polite society. From now on, let both our "
"conversation and our press be right and just.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdb6ab4d-b095-4250-a2e0-4508d5bc33a3"
msgid ""
"\\\"A wise decision. We cannot allow rebellious concepts to trouble your subjects' "
"minds. Let all our writers and artists, who hope to be published, pursue a "
"positive tone in their writing – befitting to the kingdom, its people, and of "
"course, to you, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7354d6e2-66f4-4662-9242-207898152566"
msgid ""
"\\\"You've made a truly generous decision. Some of the foreigners are bound to "
"grumble and leave, but the well-being of your own people is your first "
"responsibility. Why shouldn't we be allowed to help our own merchants and subjects?"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eacf41fd-5bf0-4073-b4ac-f63a18dd71ce"
msgid ""
"\\\"A decent ruler must provide for their subjects. Their well-being is your most "
"important responsibility. If any foreign merchants raise an objection, let them "
"demand the same treatment from their own ruler, not from us!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cbfc4dad-081a-41b4-a262-f25da1bf1fd4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful. Let the foreigners leave if they don't like it. It can only "
"indicate one thing — that they'd hoped to trick and cheat our merchants, and we "
"rightly defended our interests.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3626f084-dec9-4984-9a6d-349e7fde6d8d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Others seek to hide from persecution, slavery, or the disdain that they face "
"at home. We can officially invite them to come here and live under your "
"protection. – But here's a better idea I've been polishing: why don't we establish "
"publishing houses abroad? They could print regular reports for your subjects, so "
"they can keep up with domestic affairs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eda58551-eee1-4473-8acc-30d851bc8580"
msgid ""
"\\\"You must remember, however, that not every neighbor is fond of your glory. I "
"would advise you to take measures to limit their influence on your citizens' "
"thoughts. For instance, we could establish a censorship board to block the "
"political efforts of our enemies. – But with a light touch, and not to a point of "
"cultural domination.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b768b967-675a-4c23-9ae9-230ff1a9f9f3"
msgid ""
"\\\"On the domestic front, our citizens travel to foreign countries and settle "
"down, but deep inside they still consider themselves your subjects. It would be "
"nice to maintain this connection by keeping them apprised events in their "
"homeland. We could distribute some printed media just for the natives of your "
"kingdom. On the other hand... Are you aware how many people would be happy to be "
"your subjects? Thousands! The oppressed, the abused, the mistreated, the wrongly "
"accused, the slaves... What a noble gesture it would be to declare your lands a "
"safe haven for all these lost souls, and to promise them your protection.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a491cf28-20bf-4434-8aed-6dc886e1958a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Another way to eliminate any chance of sedition is to show the people how "
"benevolent you are. Grant certain privileges to the native merchants, which are "
"denied to importers. Of course, many foreign traders will be disappointed, but the "
"newfound wealth of the locals will give them good reason to glorify you! However, "
"I think it wisest to simply silence anyone who promotes dangerous ideas. With your "
"approval, I will assemble a censorship board right away.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69d8464d-3d4f-4b0d-9bc7-f35afb323cec"
msgid ""
"\\\"We have a few options for maintaining this growth. Firstly, it would be nice "
"to stay in touch with those who are traveling abroad. One could compare it to a "
"sort of leash, you know. That is to say, we could publish a newspaper for our "
"kingdom's expatriates. Even if things aren't going so smoothly here at home, our "
"reputation abroad will be protected.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dcea2de3-c6ee-4263-a78d-e30a8ecd657b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Secondly, we could form a censorship board to prevent foreign agitators from "
"clouding your subjects' minds with doubt. Thirdly, and this is my preferred "
"method, we could expel from our borders all our disgruntled commoners — and all "
"the henchmen of foreign monarchs. It wouldn't take much. We would simply have to "
"persuade your subjects that denunciating their neighbors for the good of the "
"kingdom is a noble and honorable act.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "616436f0-2522-454b-a9fa-9e7d910624d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could call upon the people's help. Let them report those who spread "
"seditious ideas. – After all, it's for their own good! However, I think the best "
"option would be simply to show that your concern for your own subjects surpasses "
"all else. Consider giving your merchants special privileges, which are denied to "
"foreigners. The latter might object, but this will be guaranteed to maintain "
"national pride."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4c9adb3-3ad1-4e67-8932-cd9e829af0b5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Apart from that, there are many citizenship applicants. Rumor has it that you "
"plan on turning your kingdom into a refuge for the poor, ugly, and sick. But what "
"use could we possibly have for a crowd of invalids? It would be better to promise "
"citizenship only to the strong and brave – those prepared to spill their blood in "
"military service to prove their loyalty!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7e833a1c-1bd0-4fec-9fb7-0e33433c979c"
msgid "\\\"Let's just look the other way. They're only hunters.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fd3b2ad7-6486-42db-93a8-9d22c8a08859"
msgid ""
"\\\"We will immediately increase border control. We must put an end to such "
"incursions immediately!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9187a206-87e0-457f-88dc-4b2ca1831484"
msgid "\\\"I agree with your proposal. Set the fines as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8eae5eb4-0192-4054-8873-7e9acd360668"
msgid "\\\"You can deal with this without me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7c0ea61-b00d-436f-a6c9-e5907a669bbd"
msgid ""
"\\\"This will only take a moment! Really, it's nothing. But I do need your advice!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9bd1790c-491d-4df0-becf-70eb75899eca"
msgid ""
"\\\"Some hunters from {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} are wandering the outskirts of your {mf|"
"barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}. If you ask me – I don't care. There's enough game "
"for everyone. But the locals are outraged: what kind of {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|"
"kingdom} is it, if just anyone can cross our borders!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa601175-73fe-4a4e-a07a-5b707dd427bb"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi shrugs.{/n} \\\"We are not going to introduce border patrols because a "
"couple of does got shot! Right? Right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1bebb186-cb59-4035-bb1b-902ff0e97dfa"
msgid ""
"\\\"It appears that not all of your neighbors know that lawful order has come to "
"the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}!\\\" {n}Valerie frowns severely.{/n} \\\"Over "
"many years, they have grown accustomed to these territories belonging to monsters "
"and bandits – and have learned to behave accordingly.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e43b54b6-de73-44aa-af0d-7563775c40b0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've heard rumor that hunters from {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} cross the borders into "
"the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}, searching for game. They cross state "
"borders as easily as wading across a stream!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1b58ef3-7726-4730-a670-ed9e08433eae"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't want to sit idly and watch, as the peasantry of a foreign kingdom "
"mocks our laws! Please, enforce control over the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|"
"kingdom}'s borders – it will be an important move, for anyone who doesn't yet take "
"your rule seriously!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39098755-8cb3-4f98-8ea6-32bdd87b1585"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew bows to you.{/n} \\\"You won't believe this, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. There are border crossers in your lands!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df92fe9c-7419-452c-b16b-49ee6ec115c8"
msgid ""
"\\\"In fact they're just some deer hunters from {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}, roaming the "
"swamps looking for game. But they gave me a wonderful idea – which I hasten to "
"share with you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f01490e-c277-4326-b690-e8a05b0c86c8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course, we could look the other way in this situation... Or enforce border "
"control... but I propose something else: let's set large fines for crossing our "
"borders! Believe me, these adventurers will have an easy choice between money and "
"prison!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d71de6f3-03bd-4650-9c53-d88ef27a290a"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's what I thought too! So let's discuss something more important...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de398edb-346e-40d4-a953-d4db8daf6dfa"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie squints.{/n} \\\"I am concerned by your casual attitude towards such a "
"serious issue. But so be it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d808c0e8-442e-4098-9a2c-af27c01e00d8"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew waves his hands.{/n} \\\"Why pass up such an opportunity?\\\" {n}He "
"quickly straightens himself.{/n} \\\"Well, if this is your wish, I dare not argue."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "379b5743-398d-4fa4-917b-e137fc123529"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi lets out a disappointed moan.{/n} \\\"Seriously? Just because someone got "
"lost while they were hunting? We could just pretend we didn't notice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f7ef0b1-6b92-4332-8a41-c44854606b0a"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie nods.{/n} \\\"I will see to it that our soldiers take up this duty as "
"soon as possible.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83050b81-9f4c-4a92-a5bb-0dbcb558a0da"
msgid "\\\"As you wish, as you wish...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75501deb-90a1-4164-aa32-8fedf0cd43cb"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew breaks into a sugary smile.{/n} \\\"Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bacbe179-7569-46cd-ac3e-2804633adbbc"
msgid "\\\"Then I will try to calm our over-vigilant subjects!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fb26902-cbcf-48cd-ba14-ace71c16280b"
msgid "\\\"Agreed. I will set up border outposts at the first opportunity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ecf6c75f-9bed-42d9-ad10-f9a4a9028507"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then your treasury will soon be filled at the expense of our neighbors!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d854211f-a4e7-4e0a-93bd-ad98d114bacf"
msgid "\\\"I support the trade agreement with Razmiran.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04119997-544f-4d43-9c5b-cec7ab458d15"
msgid "\\\"Reject this proposal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58f96744-baea-463b-bfcf-a846b3ad191e"
msgid "\\\"I will fully rely on you in this matter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19406ef1-2442-4463-aca9-26ab76c22933"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about this Razmir.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "654681c4-4a6d-41e8-a86f-7cae6ecb7319"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi broods upon the letter she's holding in her hands.{/n} \\\"I received "
"this today. An official letter from {g|Razmiran}Razmiran{/g}... with a trade "
"proposal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ef30d12-cc7e-4afe-8e99-4e7b2e986e6c"
msgid ""
"\\\"It seems the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} has grown large enough to "
"excite curiosity even in odd corners of the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}. "
"It's just that...\\\" {n}Linzi sighs.{/n} \\\"I don't think {g|Razmiran}Razmiran{/"
"g} would make the best ally. Since their self-proclaimed god, Razmir, rules there, "
"tyranny has flourished across the country, and they think little of their "
"neighbors. – They just occupy any lands they can!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64eec7d5-c44c-4677-871e-81930108e6d5"
msgid ""
"\\\"If I were you, I would politely decline their trade agreement. Who knows – "
"maybe it's a trick? Although the terms seem profitable...\\\" {n}Linzi looks at "
"the letter again.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2cf1c63a-0f8f-4a0f-917d-414603127775"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie shows you an open letter bearing an official seal.{/n} \\\"We have "
"received an offer of a trade agreement from the kingdom of {g|Razmiran}Razmiran{/"
"g}, which lies to the west of your lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f5a789b-e4ca-4e58-88d6-b7afa712e338"
msgid ""
"\\\"The proposal seems quite fair. The letter was composed by Razmir's lawyers, "
"and it seems very transparent. Of course, I will give it to our men of law, if you "
"deem it worthy of consideration.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b13cf9df-e394-4eb1-99d4-38b945d9433a"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie pauses.{/n} \\\"Of course you know that {g|Razmiran}Razmiran{/g} is an "
"unusual kingdom. Many are suspicious of its self-proclaimed god ruler, and its "
"aggressive ambitions... But I won't give you any advice on this matter. Please "
"make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1206c533-fbbc-4669-bebc-0741625e86e9"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew holds up an open letter.{/n} \\\"Look, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}! Your neighbors seek trade agreements with you. I "
"received this letter from distant {g|Razmiran}Razmiran{/g} – a country ruled by "
"Razmir himself. Have you heard of him?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ef5ef77-c9ac-4145-b4f0-e9a95bbbb4b2"
msgid ""
"\\\"He's quite a curious person, I must say! Managed to persuade the entire "
"country that he's a living god! That's something to admire!\\\" {n}Bartholomew "
"laughs.{/n} \\\"Well, whatever you may think of that, his country is among the "
"most promising of the young kingdoms. We could use such a friendship!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a81bfb85-4927-4fdd-ada6-d200d52b23fd"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think we should accept this agreement. But of course, the final decision is "
"yours!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c6976f8-e420-4e48-a0db-e749a6762b1f"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi sighs.{/n} \\\"As you wish. I'm just afraid this might not turn out well "
"for us...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c670f728-8cfb-4704-a21a-ceaf85b365bf"
msgid "{n}Valerie nods.{/n} \\\"Understood.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3d251608-a62f-4cd2-8654-4c2da4ede2b9"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew tenderly strokes the letter in his hands.{/n} \\\"An excellent "
"decision, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! I will compose "
"our reply immediately!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9914dc8-69bf-4bf3-992c-51a63a40bc32"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi catches her breath.{/n} \\\"Ah... truth be told, I'm glad. I wouldn't "
"feel good about dealing with a rascal like Razmir...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2076218d-fe84-45f2-bbb1-68ecb862c4db"
msgid "{n}Bartholomew closes his eyes wearily.{/n} \\\"As you wish...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7aded821-0795-48a3-84b8-4ed37c6335cf"
msgid ""
"\\\"Really? Then I will reject the agreement. Let's just say we both listened to "
"my intuition – it never lets me down!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "832d5221-e78e-4b35-9e56-e28593bac362"
msgid ""
"\\\"In that case, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I am "
"inclined to accept. I shall compose our reply without delay!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "07c08244-8907-4580-87b9-605f542c5835"
msgid ""
"\\\"He's a quirky fellow. He took over a kingdom, and persuaded all the locals "
"that he's a living god! He installed his henchmen in all the key positions, and "
"now rules as he pleases, oppressing the population!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c29c244-6561-4467-a5c2-19d2bcee8ea0"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi sighs.{/n} \\\"The more I think about it, the less I like the idea of "
"dealing with him. He has repeatedly expanded the territory of his own kingdom by "
"occupying his neighbors! Such an attitude towards other countries is seriously "
"worrying.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9d1c4e8-acdd-425d-8c91-87996736ab65"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you asked one of {g|Razmiran}Razmiran{/g}'s citizens, you'd hear praises to "
"great god, protector of his nation.\\\" {n}Valerie purses her lips.{/n} \\\"But "
"Razmir is no god. Most likely, he's a mighty wizard. He doesn't possess even a "
"trace of true divinity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32ddb3d4-462f-46a8-90dc-9a752ca50f28"
msgid ""
"\\\"But {g|Razmiran}Razmiran{/g} is far more than a handful of fanatics. It's a "
"fully independent state. Under Razmir, it has only thrived, and can stand against "
"its enemies. Razmir set his own laws – and it's not up to me to judge them. It's "
"better there are laws than not.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "775b14af-fc64-4ca3-888c-30d02634afed"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't know who he is and where he came from. What's important is that he's "
"capable of subduing an entire nation! Presenting himself as a new god – what an "
"unconventional step! He even provides divine spells to his priests! I don't know "
"how, but he found a way!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2cad9618-c6b9-447d-9686-f0009c165aa3"
msgid ""
"{n}Bartholomew lifts a finger.{/n} \\\"Think well on this trade agreement with {g|"
"Razmiran}Razmiran{/g}, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Who "
"knows what opportunities may open to us if we sign it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "583ef2c2-9bea-41ff-a724-31c8c988b62f"
msgid "\\\"Help the guards find and arrest the runaway elf.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "685848fe-e867-4542-b7a6-9e68cdcb3d0c"
msgid "\\\"Make sure the elf reaches Kyonin.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4172a43b-e57a-4b0e-8906-24f46ddc74c2"
msgid "\\\"Decide his fate as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce4f2372-dbaa-4132-b7c3-061fba06d2f0"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about this conflict between Sevenarches and Kyonin.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3836d1ce-2a1b-4b9d-a521-b1aa8bfbb7d8"
msgid "\\\"We aren't going to interfere in this matter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56e87fb3-dd4f-4e8c-9a76-75d3620e7d7a"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! I'm probably not wise "
"enough to understand your orders. But I feel a complete fool every time I "
"recommend one thing, and you do something completely different! Does my advice "
"mean so little to you? Did you invite me to become a diplomat just to make fun of "
"me? Alas, I am tired of being a buffoon. You should find a replacement for me, and "
"I will continue to serve you elsewhere.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cbc2d484-9199-488d-9916-e176043d783a"
msgid ""
"\\\"There is a guard detail from Sevenarches at the border. They were sent by the "
"Voice of the Wind – one of the elder druids who rule Sevenarches, a diplomat and "
"chief scout. Their guard keeps insisting there's an elf hiding in our lands, a "
"fugitive who slipped out of their city.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8174b74e-1bb6-46a2-a818-1aca1b1a25eb"
msgid ""
"\\\"But now to the point. – A guard detail from Sevenarches has been stopped at "
"the border. They've been sent by the Voice of the Wind, a druid charged with "
"diplomacy in this River Kingdom. The guards are hunting some elven criminal, a "
"fugitive who is hiding in our lands. They've asked us to provide support, and seem "
"concerned that we might instead help him escape to {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de1f9c86-1a4c-44e7-a8ba-a56f500d36b3"
msgid ""
"\\\"For now let me simply report one of such delicate matter. There's a guard "
"detail at the border, sent by the Voice of the Wind – a druid and diplomat from "
"Sevenarches. They're hunting a criminal, an elf who's escaped to our lands. I "
"would imagine they're worried that someone might help the fugitive get to {g|"
"Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}, and ask our assistance in hunting him down.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f51adaa-1fdd-4234-be15-b78fdd213315"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why would you believe the guard so readily? It wouldn't be the first time that "
"someone unfavored by the authorities was falsely branded a criminal! We judge "
"without hearing the evidence!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "798753e3-ae74-45dd-a15e-9be84aaf04c9"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie remains silent for a while, biting her lip.{/n} \\\"So you believe that "
"accusations against this elf are fair? I wouldn't be so sure of that. It pains me "
"to think that you've made a decision so hastily and without consideration.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a504aee5-4cdc-49b1-a912-079e08690c7e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very good! We will catch the criminal and hand him over to Sevenarches. I'm "
"sure the Voice of the Wind will appreciate the gesture... and might even have some "
"information to share about our neighbors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23d9075f-ef5a-423b-b221-eb73733dbc38"
msgid ""
"\\\"Helping him get home is the nice thing to do. I'll make sure we find the elf "
"and get him back home safely. I'm sure {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} will appreciate the "
"friendly act! They might even send a letter of gratitude... along with some "
"ancient magical books... Oh, I should stop daydreaming!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59072ee3-362b-468f-b60b-790fece09eb7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't like hiding fugitives from justice, until it's proven that their trial "
"was corrupt. And I'm more troubled by the thought that your decision was guided "
"not by your desire to see justice done, but to befriend the elves.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f1896ed-e4a4-4800-9221-3b8ecb6a7925"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ah, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, do you really "
"expect gratitude from {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}? I need scarcely remind you that the "
"elves can be quite arrogant towards their neighbors, and are unlikely to offer any "
"generous gifts in return.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04af82ee-40f2-4536-9e56-3f78baabd24e"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi shifts from foot to foot.{/n} \\\"{name}, not all diplomatic problems are "
"solved openly. Sometimes a problem needs to be concealed, and sometimes knowledge "
"must be cyphered, and secrets overheard. To do this you would need a spy chief. "
"I'm not fit for the job – I'm used to speaking my mind, not keeping silent. Please "
"find a worthy 'minister' for this position, and meanwhile I will try to handle "
"today's delicate matter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d9e62aed-17c0-4bb4-a484-61cba81f6cea"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I was born in a noble family, so I can imagine why you decided to "
"entrust me with a diplomatic position. I understand how noble persons think, and "
"how they should be addressed. But I also know that the nobility doesn't always "
"solve their problems openly. Sometimes a dagger, or poison, or a purse of gold in "
"the right pocket can do far more than charters and official letters could hope to "
"achieve. But I myself am no infiltrator. These methods disgust me. You should "
"choose... some other 'minister' to lead your spies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1abad9fe-b766-4231-b920-62c8ac8b6243"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, more and more delicate "
"issues arise with our neighbors. You need a spymaster... who should, of course, "
"simply be called 'a minister'. I could certainly hold this position, but a "
"spymaster sometimes learns too much about his {mf|lord|lady}, and I wouldn't want "
"you to have even a shadow of a doubt about my loyalty.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "353e2534-965c-4789-9f84-c6206fedbd0f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sevenarches are built on a spot that is sacred to elves. The elves fled from "
"there once, and druids, the Oakstewards, have ruled there ever since. The elves of "
"{g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} would like to return their shrine, or at least be granted "
"access to it. But druids are wary of Kyonin, and feel hostile to any elves on "
"their territory.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c93c447-af8c-41ce-b934-566cea428ac0"
msgid ""
"\\\"The elves' ancestors even built the seven arches which give the city its name. "
"Then elves abandoned their shrines, or to put it more precisely – they fled. The "
"druids then came to this place to make it their own. Now the Oakstewards rule "
"there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a538c36d-9e7e-4bad-9d5a-6f54fa30571b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The elves claim they built seven arches for which the city is named, though "
"the evidence of this is questionable. Anyway, the elves fled these lands, and "
"druids of the bolder tribes claimed this land for themselves, any built a "
"flourishing settlement.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a02b01f-e743-4024-b748-1ce98dafeee0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... At least that way we won't be hurting anyone. But we aren't helping "
"either...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "084648ec-943d-4089-b25e-6b61fcc8c6ca"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very good. We won't help anyone, as we have no proof of anyone's guilt or "
"innocence.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4b2d833-a3d6-4713-a7b1-57b1d7140e66"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, we won't make any enemies this way. But we won't get useful allies "
"either... though we might have!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68272294-c5b9-409b-b084-fdef08a13312"
msgid ""
"\\\"They asked us to help capture him, or at least not to hinder their search. But "
"in Sevenarches they'll say an elf is a 'criminal' when they really mean he's a "
"'hindrance'. Since it wasn't us who sentenced him, why should we assume that he's "
"the villain? It would be better if find him and help him get back home to {g|"
"Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18e311ee-bf6e-4676-8c91-80d68b84b3b0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't advise taking either side. Everyone knows that the people of "
"Sevenarches have no love of elves and rarely judge them equitably. But everyone "
"has heard of the elven conspiracy to reclaim Sevenarches for themselves. Either "
"way, this argument has nothing to do with us. I recommend you refuse to allow the "
"guards onto our lands, but don't help the runaway elf either.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "844a9ba5-ad5d-41c6-b7c2-3bc881e9cdb6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Voice of the Wind is very knowledgeable. The winds whisper many secrets to "
"him. It is wise to befriend such useful persons. If we must give them the elf to "
"win their favor, then I'd consider it a bargain no matter who he is or what he's "
"done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e297899d-a9f5-41a3-9a57-529fe0e25f84"
msgid ""
"\\\"The elves of {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} keep trying to return Sevenarches, though "
"they abandoned the place many centuries ago. Meanwhile, the druids see a spy in "
"every elf, and won't tolerate them on their land, although without the elves there "
"wouldn't be any arches at all! Anyway, it's a complicated story, with no one "
"clearly in the right or wrong.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2f7d54a-12a4-4bfe-a00c-c58a6ae807ca"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now the elves of {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} are demanding the return of Sevenarches "
"– as the land is supposedly sacred to them! Though if you ask me, such a demand "
"smells of deceit. In any case, the Oakstewards who now rule Sevenarches have "
"refused. As a result there's very little peace between them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac9d71da-40f6-4d7b-8e5d-69cc0402c13b"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi rubs her cheek, baffled.{/n} \\\"{name}, forgive me, but I must refuse "
"the position of diplomat. I have always been closer to the people than their "
"rulers, and these diplomatic games are not my strong suit. I will obey your "
"orders, but after today I'd rather just focus on my book. I know you can find a "
"more competent advisor to take my place.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "adefd4fc-ff05-463d-accb-f7479659720d"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I must refuse the position of diplomat. To be honest, your decisions "
"disappoint me, and I don't wish to feel like that towards someone I've sworn to "
"serve loyally and faithfully. I shall guard your back and slay your enemies, but I "
"will not argue over matters of state. You must find yourself another diplomat.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7570a0c1-03b2-4f21-ba22-19ca0a8acb04"
msgid "\\\"I wish to know more about the Black Marquis and his Protectorate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eab476a3-9697-4564-8d67-3dce3a568e6c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Show him how strong our army is. They'd better not cross swords with us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24e59afa-d46f-4c1a-b3c2-5760ec442202"
msgid ""
"\\\"Show him we're rich, and he'll conclude that they'll be better off as our "
"friends.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41cb6412-504d-441b-b18a-6d061416227c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Deceive him. Convince him we're a backwards country with little to offer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6063082-1cdc-496d-8151-bec29d62358f"
msgid "\\\"I will leave this decision to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5d8293e-7d8b-4003-a359-01131a886783"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, we've arrested a strange man. He was making a map of our rivers and "
"bays. Upon his capture, he shouted that he serves the Black Marquis, and was sent "
"to create a map of the local trade routes. But pirates are full of guile, and this "
"map might be used not for trade, but for raids. What are we going to do with him, "
"being that he's admittedly serving another king?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f395075-c7d0-4d88-80f8-ef6b8eb91824"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, we captured a suspicious man. He was making a map of our rivers, bays "
"and backwaters. When he was placed under arrest, he admitted that he serves the "
"Black Marquis. By his account, he was sent to create a map, in order to arrange "
"trade with us. But I'd more likely believe that the pirates are preparing for a "
"big raid.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7de39f4-d7f8-40ef-9a67-d3695d2a15f9"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! I'm afraid I have bad "
"news. Today by the river they caught a man making a map of rivers and bays in our "
"lands. He said he was a scout for the Black Marquis, and was drawing a map to open "
"a trade route with us. But everyone knows the greedy and deceptive nature of these "
"pirates. It's more likely that they're preparing an attack against us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a2579319-997a-42b4-8526-b7f6dbf857e2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Once a {g|Cheliax}Chelish{/g} pirate named Morgan the White visited the "
"village of Deadbridge to rest and replenish his supplies.\\nHe settled there and "
"in time decided to build a whole pirate nation there! Those joined him began to "
"collect duties from foreign ships, but they never touched the ships of the {g|"
"River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}. Thus he gained the support and respect of his "
"neighbors. That's how the Protectorate was created.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "efc839cc-d23e-458c-a541-dcf00e186ca4"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a group of pirates calling themselves a country. It was created by a {g|"
"Cheliax}Chelish{/g} bandit Morgan, the White Marquis. But he didn't rule for long. "
"The Protectorate changed hands several times, until the Black Marquis took its "
"helm – the most cunning and treacherous of the White Marquis' henchmen. There is "
"only one law in this land – the law of the pirate. But these bandits don't touch "
"the ships of the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}... at least, that's the "
"official tale. But how far that agreement is respected – only the dead can say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cad87eb1-2704-4d6a-b746-a8cbdfecb8e5"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a dangerous place. This dominion was founded by a pirate from {g|Cheliax}"
"Cheliax{/g}. When he came across the village of Deadbridge, he saw an ideal camp "
"for pirates and the capital of his future domain. Morgan called on many allies, "
"and ordered that no ships be touched if they fly under the banners of the {g|River "
"Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g} – and 'duties' from all other countries be collected. "
"Now the pirate nation is ruled by the Black Marquis, and his subjects are, all of "
"them, pirates and robbers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4fcf3438-a2d0-4f3a-8c10-6151d00eaf14"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll show him the strength of our army. After the pirate sees our soldiers, "
"he'll not likely recommend that his Black Marquis ever approach our shores.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aab09fe2-ce9c-4d8f-8177-437efd09a753"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, maybe it's better we have no business with them. Who knows how much "
"blood there would be on their wares and gold?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c058d0c-465a-45c1-8550-8b153d41808e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh... You're provoking them! This could be a mistake, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! They don't understand who they're dealing "
"with! Of course you'll defeat them, there's no doubt about that – but at what cost?"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "faf49c9c-99bd-4e96-9212-207d6e62da2a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Great! When we show off our riches, and convince pirates to trade with us, not "
"fight. I can't wait for an opportunity to chat with the first captains who bring "
"us their goods!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92e90763-87d9-4685-ae2f-4d64f56de1ba"
msgid ""
"\\\"Showing gold to a bandit so he doesn't return... I don't see the sense in "
"this. You'll only be feeding their greed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb650192-397f-4690-bd0d-70225c1e36dc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm.... You're probably right, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}! Your courage allows you to see their greed, whereas I, due to my humble "
"nature, am too horrified by their cruelty to see anything beyond it. I do hope our "
"riches tempt them to start trading with us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "579e65b6-456c-4fc2-8683-0cee782876ee"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is a bad idea. The more pathetic we look, the safer a target we seem. And "
"I don't want my former friends saying that Linzi now serves the ruler or some "
"backwater country!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3377b691-d7a5-4431-a4cf-dbf9ebc8b718"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... Fine, I'll lead him past the pigsties and chicken houses, so he thinks "
"it's our main avenue. Let's hope it works. Although acting has never been my "
"strong suit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d927230-2b22-4a08-98a8-31185dfb0005"
msgid ""
"\\\"Great! This pirate will doubly regret his mission, because there's nothing "
"worthy waiting for him here!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "239a2ba8-0cce-46f7-8a9b-9577946add0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"The prisoner awaits his fate. We could receive him as an honorable guest, "
"showing off our riches and power. But it would only whet the pirate's appetite. "
"Better to show him an empty corner where there's nothing to take. But only "
"demonstration of military power would make these pirates forget the road to our "
"lands. Everything else is a half-measure.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "128a44dc-9341-41b2-9e2b-c475016f0815"
msgid ""
"\\\"I do not recommend we try impressing him with military parades. Pirates are "
"fearless and stupid, they're not afraid of a stronger opponent. It's better we "
"receive him as a dear guest and convince that it would be beneficial to be friends "
"with us. Or we could do the complete opposite, and pretend we're a poor backwards "
"country, with no treasures or riches whatsoever! This would yield the best result!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "305d669b-c4c5-4f91-add2-15ea44613a3b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The most important thing now is to appear strong and influential. If we "
"demonstrate our military power, the pirates will be afraid to face us. Even better "
"– we could show them our riches. Whether or not the story about trade routes is a "
"tale, we can let the Black Marquis wonder if he'd be better off if he were our "
"friend.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5f0e1e6-229b-4b24-b436-45587d8aaad6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Here are the latest reports from our scouts. The Black Marquis who used to "
"take interest in your domain has departed for other lands after our modest... "
"demonstration. It seems we managed to avoid the pirate war! This news is truly "
"great for all of us!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "013e845a-a294-4a45-955b-92a405c5dbc5"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, wonderful news! The scouts report that the Black Marquis's "
"blunderheads took an interest in other lands and have left your {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom}. They'll be someone else's problem now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0149e2b7-de5f-4510-9e3d-9b4b0ce5ce44"
msgid ""
"\\\"Congratulations, {name}! It looks like your subjects' efforts weren't wasted "
"after all. The Black Marquis and his pirates that were prowling around here won't "
"be attacking the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}. At least that's one problem "
"off our hands!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "360653f0-1b7d-4ff3-b234-d8609f2f5508"
msgid "\\\"Let's help Sevenarches.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cce54db6-4c6d-4d9e-ac2f-bc763ea5499c"
msgid "\\\"Let's stand up for Kyonin.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69c9a75e-2c09-45c1-bb19-e86c20385485"
msgid "[Gain 2 BP each week] \\\"Bring in our troops to keep peace in Novoboro.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ae27747-cc57-4cf6-a530-c6900e872520"
msgid ""
"[Gain 2 BP each week] \\\"We will buy wares from those who bring them. It's as "
"simple as that.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ea609cf-2345-4b1c-aaff-a9c31b9bd776"
msgid "\\\"You know best what to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9d0ad611-f4ba-48a1-96f8-f7a3d69222e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's an issue that demands your attention. Sevenarches want to bring their "
"fleet to Novoboro – allegedly to combat piracy. But in fact they simply can't "
"accept that the elves of {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} are trading dwarven wares with the "
"{g|Five Kings Mountains}Five Kings Mountains{/g}. Control over Novoboro would "
"allow Sevenarches to collect duties along this trade route.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f896192-0a7c-429c-9bc4-7124b2ab66da"
msgid ""
"\\\"One issue requires your attention. Sevenarches are bringing their fleet to "
"Novoboro, an important point along the river trade, and create a 'customs' there "
"to combat piracy. But don't be fooled, they're really just going there to level "
"duties on wares brought in from the {g|Five Kings Mountains}Five Kings Mountains{/"
"g} and heading towards {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3c366f0e-d90b-4730-85c2-275a725edfef"
msgid ""
"\\\"An important issue requires your attention! Sevenarches wants to bring their "
"ships into the harbor of Novoboro, a key point along {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} river "
"trade route. They claim that their only goal is fighting piracy, but in fact "
"they'll be searching all ships for dwarven wares. The smart captains will pay "
"duties to Sevenarches; the fools will be declared pirates.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4953317-4133-4aef-b321-5c7f4565dd59"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sevenarches might call it fighting piracy, but as I see it, they're the ones "
"who are acting like pirates!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af7daf2e-12d4-4cc1-b80f-e3bf66fb3adb"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you say. I hope you have a good reason for getting us into this broil – and "
"I hope you've chosen the right side.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "994f84d7-f16e-49dd-bbba-58075b5dc0f3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Great! It's time for {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} to know their egoistic politics is "
"over. There are several new, strong players in the {g|River Kingdoms}River "
"Kingdoms{/g}. Like you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f655bf5d-5182-4701-af12-79570f25b1f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wonderful. We will let Sevenarches know that we won't tolerate their brazen "
"efforts to seize an honest trade route.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "838f768e-1937-4418-9742-a07a87a7181b"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll support {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}, even though elves won't even consider "
"sharing their revenue or connections with us? {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}, I lack the wisdom to understand your decisions!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86a3df10-bee3-40a8-949b-97d32fa19aef"
msgid ""
"\\\"At least we'll be sure that no one is oppressing anyone. But will the others "
"be sure that we're not oppressing them...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7cd3cc50-ea7c-4882-92e1-59a43922ce25"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will order our ships to reach Novoboro first. We seize control over trade, "
"whatever our neighbors might think, and keep our eyes open for pirates and "
"smugglers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24aa27fe-0265-4805-aa6f-397e51ea3ce5"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's a bold move, seizing their prize right out from under Sevenarches. But "
"the fastest runner wins the race, right? I applaud your wisdom yet again.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15641bcb-9225-484c-981e-62904a2f8967"
msgid ""
"\\\"Maybe it's better to keep out of the troubles of others. The elves aren't "
"completely right to inflate the prices of dwarven wares and not share them with "
"anyone!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24b15473-476b-4a31-b525-f34233c40d17"
msgid ""
"\\\"Even if they have their previous owner's blood on them? Don't imagine that "
"your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} can avoid this conflict.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0075c3f7-b5f0-4d34-a669-890dfe1c76c1"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is wise to keep your economy separate from the political broils of others. "
"Let them fight over duties without us. Most reasonable, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5405f0f2-5a20-400b-8766-f3b21d158f01"
msgid ""
"\\\"At present, all the wares from the {g|Five Kings Mountains}Five Kings "
"Mountains{/g} that we receive arrive here via the elves, at the prices they set. "
"{g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} asks for our help in this trade war, and Sevenarches also "
"offers its cooperation. I think we should make an agreement with Sevenarches, "
"though it would be tempting to beat them both to the punch, and set up our own "
"customs office in Novoboro, and take all the profit ourselves.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e719d5aa-f24e-441b-ace7-2c6f660e24f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Both {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} and Sevenarches are asking for support. I don't "
"trust either of them, so I suggest we bring our own fleet to Novoboro. We're more "
"than capable of keeping an eye on the pirates, even if our neighbors are not "
"grateful for our interference.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50b59850-4f94-420e-94ca-33854252aa7c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Both {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} and Sevenarches are asking for diplomatic support. I "
"think we should put Sevenarches on a shorter leash. Their most recent step is just "
"another attempt to take away someone else's living! We could also bring our own "
"fleet to Novoboro to steal their initiative, but it's better we have Kyonin as an "
"ally.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49b13f65-35cd-4957-afd2-21b711b545a9"
msgid "[Gain 500 BP] \\\"We could make use of Razmir's gold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ba44cea-35e3-4234-a33b-9f6f6a6a7f85"
msgid "\\\"I'd prefer payment in the form of a magical artifact.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ca7d264-1188-43bc-91dc-ee9fb5073802"
msgid "Massacred the Razmirans."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab639c2f-1483-43dd-bbe6-d94ff29d48a7"
msgid "\\\"Execute all of Razmir's servants in the country.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3eae2776-44d0-4f53-9d79-f7805479b4f8"
msgid "\\\"Do as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86beb003-6cad-4fa2-9ef8-bce47670027b"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I have some bad news. It looks like we did well to keep our distance "
"from Razmir. Our warriors arrested a smuggler crossing the border. He was carrying "
"a large quantity of Razmir's Tears, a magical drug that can break any man's will "
"and turn him into a shivering addict. He also carried letters threatening our "
"merchants.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3733e41e-825b-4a7a-8e36-02aceab7afad"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, a Razmiran spy was arrested at the border. He was carrying letters "
"filled with threats, along with a large quantity of a drug known as Razmir's "
"Tears. Judging from the letters, this agent was under orders to drug our merchants "
"and dominate their wills.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c05ee50d-7f39-41da-b7a3-c4146ece1cec"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness! The sneaky, treacherous, nasty Razmir has made an attempt on "
"the stability of your kingdom! He's challenging Your Highness! We just arrested "
"one of his spies, who was carrying bags full of Razmir's Tears, a powerful drug, "
"so addictive that even a man of great spirit cannot resist! He also carried "
"threatening letters, directed at our major merchants.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "506422d7-ef30-4f9f-8b80-c648001ba01d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... Don't you think we made a bad bargain? It's only gold! Don't we already "
"have enough of that? All right, well... I guess some things I just don't "
"understand.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b84d7f8c-13de-4ef2-aa6b-52bf019236f8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your subjects will make good use of this gold, and our enemies will be "
"reminded that any attempt against us will cost them dearly.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6461d145-86aa-4f2d-836d-cea6a0206253"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well – let it be gold then. Razmir will pay a high price for his mistake "
"if he doesn't want to face the consequences!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e35855d5-4459-4682-ba96-601d91ef2ce9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect! I can't wait to see this new wonder from Razmiran! It will have to be "
"something amazing – after such a diplomatic incident we won't accept some minor "
"trinket! – You will allow me to study the gift, won't you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b5598ac4-b92e-46b1-a387-6652c556f0c6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... It's a questionable decision. The gift could be a trap, just as Razmir's "
"Tears were in fact a poison. Magical gifts are often treacherous.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca2c196b-1c4c-405c-b45d-75c41e8e0bc2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, getting our hands on Razmir's treasure is wiser than hanging his "
"subjects.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27faf3ac-1096-4e01-86cd-1d12a1796b34"
msgid ""
"\\\"What?! How could you do this?! What is their crime?! Is it their fault that "
"they're ruled by a bloody tyrant, desperate to take over the world? This... This "
"is horrible.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff015f92-39a7-46c8-abf2-e59e186877c5"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie bites her lip.{/n} \\\"This is unjust, {name}. This punishment is far "
"worse than Razmir's crime. It will be a senseless bloodbath.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c58bbb10-e606-4c61-a3a4-8e6eadab5d86"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect! We'll punish every Razmiran subject we can catch in our domain. Your "
"Highness, this is a lesson they are sure to understand! – They got in our way, and "
"now they'll pay with the lives of their servants! Razmir will regret his refusal "
"to forge an alliance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71831b7a-d036-4128-b15f-cbd5fc67c209"
msgid ""
"\\\"Razmir's plan was to cripple trade by manipulating our merchants after getting "
"them addicted to the Tears. Now that his agent is in our hands, Razmiran is "
"offering an apology – and a substantial compensation in gold – if we set aside "
"thoughts of revenge. I agree that we should extend some courtesy, and spare the "
"lives of Razmir's subjects. But gold is not good enough. We should request a "
"treasure from Razmir's private magic arsenal, which is rumored to be stocked with "
"many curious items.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d100b0db-1a0b-4876-a5b3-17dd26e9ed29"
msgid ""
"\\\"Razmiran's evil plot has failed. Fearing revenge, they have already sent us "
"proposal for compensation. They've offered us a choice between gold and a magical "
"treasure. I suppose it's safer to accept the gold – their 'gift' could easily "
"contain a magical trap.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ede6a08-8290-4970-a3b8-684ca529edfb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Evidently, Razmir was going to use the Tears to subdue these merchants. It's "
"an ingenious plan! – I wish I had thought of it myself... But it was also a brazen "
"affront, and Razmiran is trying to buy their way out of it with offers of gold or "
"magical treasure. But we should reject their offer! Razmir will only leave us "
"alone if he sees a monarch equal to himself – strong, ruthless, and dangerous. "
"Have their subjects executed. Only this will earn Razmir's respect.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38c993e5-5979-49fb-adb6-f08b02512981"
msgid "Provided treatment to the addicts of Razmir's Tears"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "78fecf6f-4c9e-43e3-83ac-d5973bdba69d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Place all the drug addicts in health institutions. We take care of our people."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99d2539b-774b-4c94-91e8-565130e3dd6f"
msgid "Destroyed the dens of Razmir's Tears addicts"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6468b41-5411-4209-92fb-ea9445b4be9b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hang the drug addicts. Appoint more reliable people to their positions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "907f4a65-7e66-4617-b55a-e703ffe3914d"
msgid "Punished the drug addicts by stripping them of their property and positions."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1fc99893-3419-4d23-9869-f50b54a146bc"
msgid "\\\"Remove all the addicts from their stations.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d948f4a0-4975-4fc1-a529-fb584d9f6c59"
msgid "\\\"You should act of your own accord.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe3f5f3d-d886-4cb1-8471-dc5bd053b945"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, this is bad! Our union with Razmiran has brought us nothing but "
"trouble. The guards report that many of your most powerful and influential "
"subjects have become addicted to an imported drug known as Razmir's Tears. "
"Razmiran is threatening to cut off the supply of Tears, unless our merchants sell "
"them goods for next to nothing. This must be stopped immediately!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9cdb8227-a063-405b-8ba4-3d5a0fd4ec04"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, our friendship with Razmiran has borne the fruit of a poisonous tree. "
"Their spies have infiltrated our ranks, and distributed Razmir's Tears to our "
"servants. It is a powerful drug that strips the user of all willpower, to say "
"nothing of honor and judgment. Many of our subjects are already deep in the throes "
"of addiction, willing to sell our goods for next to nothing just to get another "
"dose of the drug. It is time to put an end to this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c49b8e53-1d6b-4a35-bf67-45424a020300"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, Razmiran is carrying out a malicious plot against us. After "
"establishing trade, they saw to it that many of our servants would become addicted "
"to Razmir's Tears, a dangerous and powerful drug. The poor souls are now entirely "
"under Razmir's power, and are ready to sell our goods for nothing, only to please "
"their new master. Razmir made a bold move – and a successful one. It's time we "
"make our own.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92362659-e156-436a-a755-b6f4d45cffc2"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll treat them in the temples, and the treasury will pay the priests. This "
"is the right decision. Everyone makes mistakes. Once they're cured, the Tears "
"won't trouble us any more!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "069cddef-18e9-4aab-a29e-af64ddb85063"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a merciful choice, but unjust. These people were never forced to take the "
"drug. Why must our priests treat them? Why should we pay for their misdeeds? Why "
"don't we appoint decent people in their places. – People who are more deserving?\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "026b7530-e269-47c0-840c-909ea9fa1f4b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why should we have to care about them, your Highness? The logic escapes me. "
"Essentially, they betrayed you and your legitimate interests! They deserve the "
"gallows, not a nurse!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cca1e137-de20-4de0-a331-87da6d2b443c"
msgid ""
"\\\"This punishment is too severe! Have mercy! Everyone strays from the path "
"sometimes! This punishment is worthy of Razmir, not you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cfbc0c86-f3ed-48de-9913-788b2131143d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh... They'll be beyond hope. Their lives will be ruined... I feel sorry for "
"them, you know. They had everything one could hope for. Status, wealth, fancy "
"houses. Why did they have to go and ruin themselves with Razmir's poison?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92f3ca9d-a870-4e2b-ba58-3576b5c2f4c6"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't like the severity of the punishment, but the fact that both of us "
"regard them as criminals, not victims, is satisfying. Justice may be cruel, but "
"it's better than chaos and lawlessness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1190290-03a7-4eb1-b2e9-d64806330bb1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Excellent! The sight of the poison addicts on the gallows will make their "
"successors think twice about the consequences of weakness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b437ea12-5e16-48fc-be61-281cacdc0ae8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect. All those spineless drug fiends will be right where they belong – at "
"the ends of lonely country roads. Worthier candidates will take their places.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bb173baa-bf69-4f36-a9ca-59b8b0061911"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, Razmir planned dire consequences for the {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom}, leveraged on your people's vicious thirst. And with all modesty, "
"I dare remind you that it was my timely interference that prevented it. You are "
"far too merciful with the pathetic vermin.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "829d87ce-af80-459b-b454-b8ac741ac16c"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could ban the Tears, and dismiss the victims from their posts, and we'd be "
"rid of Razmiran's influence. A crueler ruler could even count the victims as "
"traitors and sentence them to death. Personally, I trust in your mercy. I believe "
"that you'll hand the addicts over to the priests for treatment. That would disrupt "
"Razmiran's plans, our subjects would be saved.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ed6d1bb-8d54-4180-ac69-f44da0ca0f86"
msgid ""
"\\\"These people fell for the drug. They jeopardized our kingdom's safety, and "
"they must be punished. I suggest you strip them of their positions and their "
"possessions, and bequeath them to their successors – who will hopefully be "
"individuals of stronger will and moral fiber. We do not delight in severe "
"punishment, but indulging their vices and then financing their treatment from the "
"people's budget – that is a bridge too far.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "757c862e-e208-4615-b61e-fb687919478a"
msgid ""
"\\\"These corrupt drug lovers have betrayed your Highness for their narcotic! I "
"hope they don't expect your Highness to give any thought to their treatment! The "
"traitors' punishment must be severe, so their successors will never be tempted to "
"follow in their footsteps! I suggest you sentence the addicts to death. Merely "
"taking away their positions and belongings isn't a sufficient deterrent for "
"betrayal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88aa6396-64b1-445e-8a0c-f7f531a82eed"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, we have alarming news! Kyonin has frowned upon our politics for quite "
"a while. Now they're encouraging the elves in our lands to renounce their "
"allegiance to you, stop paying taxes, and leave the country. Many of these elves "
"are among our most respected leaders, artists, and craftsmen – and they've already "
"started packing their belongings!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4eadba84-37b7-4eb1-8c38-58afdc425125"
msgid ""
"\\\"I hate to say it, {name}, but Kyonin has stood up to us. They're publicly "
"denouncing your rule, and encouraging all the elves in the kingdom to renounce "
"their allegiance, stop paying taxes, and leave the country. A wave of refugees is "
"streaming for the border, and we mustn't let them cross. There are many talented "
"and well-respected figures among their number, and their loss would be a severe "
"blow to the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a3fe46e-d4df-4750-90f4-fb6745514a4d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, the hypocrites of Kyonin dare criticize your governance! They "
"are encouraging the elves who live by your mercy to throw off their allegiance to "
"you, forego their taxes, and desert the country! It is revolting! Worse still, "
"there are experienced craftsmen and talented mages among them. If we allow them to "
"flee it will be a heavy blow to both our economy and our reputation!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a7d329a-4998-4988-a3b1-a7acf44d1d1a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Please, don't let the Warden's guards attack them! That would cause havoc and "
"suffering! They don't understand that they're being used as pawns in a campaign "
"against our {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}. Of course, we could have the "
"General close the country's borders, but wouldn't it be best if no one tries to "
"leave at all? I suggest the Curator should begin a retaliatory defamation campaign "
"against Kyonin. Why are they always telling elves who live elsewhere how they "
"should live their own lives?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b51b20b-b6cf-4b50-bbf6-815e0e1ecdfa"
msgid ""
"\\\"They may eventually come to see that trusting Kyonin was a mistake, but "
"swaying opinion like that isn't something that can happen overnight. I don't think "
"we'll ever be able to convince them, although I know understand that our Curator "
"is desperate for a chance to turn the war of words around, and shame Kyonin. We "
"could instead simply order the Warden to arrest the influencers behind the exodus. "
"They're known to be hiding in the capital, so we could make the arrests directly – "
"but the elves would surely fight back, and there would be blood. The better option "
"would be to have the General close the borders and prevent the elves from leaving "
"the kingdom. They'd have to listen to sense and see reason, and soon enough they'd "
"thank us for our intervention.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9f3c75a-bf75-4475-b35c-80b96bf9a2e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must stem the flow of refugees before it's too late. Closing the borders "
"wouldn't help, the elves would continue to plot their escape, meanwhile refusing "
"to work for the good of the kingdom. The very idea of deserting the country must "
"be shattered completely. We could order the Curator to paint Kyonin as the bloody "
"tyrants they are, but in the meantime we should order the Warden to raid the city "
"and arrest every troublemaker who talks of leaving. – There must be no dissent!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17994917-8284-4a65-94ed-a9c20d34a750"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, Sevenarches is trying to exact revenge for our refusal to aid in the "
"Novoboro conflict! Not only have they cut off food supplies, their wandering "
"druids hired to fight this crisis are instead spoiling our crops further! Faced "
"with the risk of starvation, our people are panicking and fighting for food in the "
"markets. This must be resolved.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b57c85d7-917b-4b2f-83a0-5ece22fbbabf"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, Sevenarches us putting pressure on us for not joining them in the "
"Novoboro conflict. They've stopped supplying us with food, and their druids, the "
"traveling farm hands, seem suddenly to be sabotaging the local crops. As the "
"threat of starvation rises, there's an increasing sense of panic in the kingdom. "
"The peasants will start fighting for bread before we even run out of it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9437690d-5fa2-4f2e-8647-0d0dff8ca4c6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness! Our reports indicate that Sevenarches is undermining our "
"farming industry! They've cut off our food supply, and their druids that travel "
"around the River Kingdoms as farmhands are now suspected of spoiling our crops! "
"We're facing starvation, and the people know it. Their panicked attempts to stock "
"supplies 'for leaner times' are devastating the market even more!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2744ba2a-2976-428e-accd-25a64d058cf4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sevenarches expects us to tighten our belts, send the Warden's guards to "
"collect bread from the citizens, and beg for mercy – but this will never happen! "
"We can find druids who will rejuvenate our crops. The High {mf_HighPriest|Priest|"
"Priestess} will be able to persuade them... or force them. The best we can do for "
"now is send the General to the Sevenarches border. Faced with an army, the farmers "
"will obediently sell us whatever we ask for.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f51809f4-448c-4e9b-a254-4a080cce7a67"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must take urgent measures! Sending the General's army to Sevenarches would "
"be effective, but cruel to the local farmers. I have two ideas. First, the "
"response they expect from us is to tighten our belts, stockpile bread, and order "
"the Warden to distribute it evenly. The second, and the better plan, is to have "
"the High {mf_HighPriest|Priest|Priestess} persuade the local druids to fix the "
"situation with this year's harvest. They normally stay out of such conflicts, but "
"this is a dire emergency."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "979c03b4-8dc0-4d4c-831e-21d62a7b7955"
msgid ""
"\\\"We must act quickly. We have many druids living in the local woods, but they "
"stay neutral in any political disagreement. The High {mf_HighPriest|Priest|"
"Priestess} will have to be delicate if we're to seek their help. Although if "
"Sevenarches really expects us to starve to death, it would only be fair to deploy "
"the General's troops. I'm sure their farmers will negotiate more freely with "
"warriors than merchants. But in truth there's nothing gained by making the farmers "
"suffer for the sins of their rulers. We could instead give them a role in solving "
"the crisis. The best way to avoid starvation is to gather all the grain that's "
"produced – and then have the Warden distribute it based on need.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "118a8405-4e5e-4bcb-a149-4becffa1ec9b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Send messengers to announce that all those unwilling to become a slave to "
"Razmir must unite.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e006f6f8-b9e6-4fb6-a0a2-e2060ae0b71a"
msgid ""
"[Gain 250 BP] \\\"We aren't meddling in the domestic affairs of other countries.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4bc8b8e6-38d0-45fe-8de5-c28b090c3511"
msgid "\\\"I want to know more about this political conflict.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "227a74e7-df18-4db6-8375-30b2a515ec0e"
msgid "\\\"I trust your opinion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eaea8140-8b0e-434d-a620-1007f767be52"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Outlaw Council wants to know our opinion on Razmiran's current behavior. "
"They're continuing to expand their borders, slowly extending their territory on "
"all sides. Tymon has already mobilized their army, and Lambreth is recruiting "
"volunteers from among the Black Eagles. But alone, they can never match the might "
"of Razmiran. – We must bring them together in stable union if we wish to curb "
"Razmir's ambitions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8dea8db0-8774-4ae1-a550-d14e918ce05e"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Outlaw Council is willing to hear us out. Razmir is pushing back his "
"neighbors in the East, and Tymon has mobilized his forces. Lambreth is bolstering "
"the Black Eagles with volunteers. But their forces are scattered and divided. Only "
"in a stable union would they be strong enough to oppose Razmir.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc238532-151f-4c21-960f-98c62fa36615"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Outlaw Council wishes to hear your opinion. Razmir is testing his eastern "
"border once again, and Tymon's ruler has started recruiting mercenaries to oppose "
"Razmir. Lambreth has mobilized the Black Eagles. Alas, these forces stand divided, "
"where they should be united in common cause. Only a stable union can stand up to "
"Razmiran.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8bc3b952-7dd3-400d-863c-e142ba956d6b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect! We shall call upon the River Kingdoms to stand together to face "
"Razmir's threat. I'm sure this open confrontation of tyranny will only add to your "
"fame.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "965cd568-1eae-4388-9609-782e3ab7bf79"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're calling upon the River Kingdoms to unite and face Razmir. His appetite "
"is too immense to imagine that we are not likewise consumed. As for the common "
"people, they will adore your commitment to striking down tyranny.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e46f3d03-c8de-4925-b53c-56f60b6459d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, Tymon and Lambreth are Razmiran's immediate neighbors to the East. "
"Tymon's founder was Maldar Tymon, a renowned Taldan hero. By long tradition, it is "
"a city of warriors, arena fighters, and gladiatorial champions. The Arena of "
"Aroden is there, along with numerous military schools. Razmiran has a predictably "
"difficult time of dealing with Tymon's army – especially when they're supported by "
"Gorum's priests.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b04e4eda-9b6a-44f6-a29a-b1e3628d6731"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tymon and Lambreth are Razmir's preferred prey, though both countries are hard "
"nuts to crack. Tymon was founded by Maldar Tymon, a great warrior and a hero of "
"Taldan. The state will send entire armies of gladiators and highly-trained "
"soldiers to fight under his banners.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b4fb079-d717-4781-9364-de305d28e26d"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's obvious that Tymon and Lambreth will soon fall to Razmir. Tymon is a "
"foolish state of gladiators, whose favorite sport is to slay one another in the "
"giant Arena of Aroden. Their fighting ability is unquestioned, but they lack any "
"political skill. Champion Ullorth Ungin, Tymon's ruler, begs the Outlaw Council in "
"Daggermark to help him defend against Razmir every year.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51dda7b4-4ea4-4413-b892-0f11db864596"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm... This decision will surely please the people, but is it really wise? "
"Sooner or later, the minor kingdoms will fall, and their lands will be taken by "
"Razmir. It would be wiser to support the stronger state, and reap a share of the "
"spoils.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e915b719-82e3-47fd-97db-ae939165fd64"
msgid ""
"\\\"So we're leaving our neighbors to rot? Will we leave them to be enslaved by "
"this foul wizard who thinks he's a god? It's... just horrible. How can I write "
"about that!?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dff0fade-02ef-4251-b012-5d7c9e77285a"
msgid ""
"\\\"You shouldn't imagine that invading his immediate neighbors will sate Razmir's "
"appetite. There will come a day when we see his mask on soldiers at our gates.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16ab42f8-e96b-4798-a337-9d13cd13d50d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very cunning. Only two monarchs of the River Kingdoms can see the future of "
"this land – Your Highness and Razmir. The others are destined to rot. We won't "
"derail our relations with Razmir – not yet. It is more strategic to wait... and "
"claim everything that he cannot claim himself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ce9bdb6-731b-4a4a-93d2-35edaea66f2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Kyonin and the other countries will listen to us if we vote for the River "
"Kingdoms to unite against Razmiran. However, Razmir has made a generous offer in "
"exchange for our silence. Besides, his future is far brighter than those minor "
"monarchs. I think we should side with him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "442196f4-e168-44bf-948f-11afa64d2c79"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sevenarches and other countries will listen to us, if we vote for the River "
"Kingdoms to unite against Razmiran. However, Razmir has made a generous offer in "
"exchange for our silence. Besides, his future is far brighter than those minor "
"monarchs. I think we should side with him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99856a83-516a-47a6-a852-ea09cf43c420"
msgid ""
"\\\"Kyonin is prepared to follow us, and many others will join them. But on the "
"other hand, Razmiran would generously reward our friendship. But to be honest, I "
"think it's time Razmir be taught a lesson. Should we call upon the River Kingdoms "
"to unite?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b41e807e-856e-46b9-9067-9e3c525d2d13"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sevenarches is prepared to follow us, along with many other countries, but "
"Razmiran has promised to reward our friendship generously. Still, if you ask me, "
"it's time to teach Razmir a lesson. Should we call upon the River Kingdoms to "
"unite?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87408b31-cd3d-4eef-baf1-3e46f06426b4"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Sevenarches trust us to act as we think best, as do many of the smaller "
"kingdoms. Razmir, for his part, has offered to generously reward our silence. But "
"we must call upon the River Kingdoms to unite. The Razmiran expansion must be "
"stopped!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d72038cd-3ec9-4524-b95c-13a204d84f98"
msgid ""
"\\\"Kyonin trusts us, as do many other states. Razmiran has offered to reward our "
"silence generously, but I think in good faith we must call upon the River Kingdoms "
"to unite. This Razmiran expansion must be stopped!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79053136-91a1-4f4e-9b08-0d6015a59ac9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Every year, champion Ullorth Ungin, Tymon's current ruler, asks the Outlaw "
"Council to help him fight off Razmir's aggression. The Outlaw Council consists of "
"the rulers each River Kingdom, and they hold court every year in Daggermark. "
"Unfortunately, not many of them are receptive to Ungin's pleas. Even Kamdyn "
"Arnefax is not his ally, though they have a shared enemy in Razmiran.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4dd7a27-9327-46d1-a805-378b5ed6b65c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Arnefax governs Lambreth, a small state that was formed through the union of "
"three rival merchant families, who feared annexation by their neighbors. "
"Razmiran's shameless land-grabbing is nothing new to them. – It was Razimir's "
"invasion that elevated Arnefax from a mere general to the Dictator of Lambreth. "
"The Black Eagles, his private knights, impose order in the country and ensure that "
"his will is carried out. They are feared even among the people of Lambreth, but "
"they excel at protecting the country and the citizens against invaders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15da01ab-48fc-48ef-823b-b722a347dbdb"
msgid ""
"\\\"The state of Lambreth was established by three merchant families who feared "
"annexation from their power-hungry neighbor. Razmir's aggression elevated general "
"Kamdyn Arnefax to the throne, which he occupies as a genuine dictator. His "
"personal knights, the Black Eagles, are feared throughout Lambreth, though they "
"maintain order and protect the country against constant Razmiran incursions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d0272b4-6c8f-4966-b613-95c543391313"
msgid ""
"\\\"Despite this opposition, Razmir stands strong. Every year, champion Ullorth "
"Ungin, Tymon's ruler, asks the Outlaw Council in Daggermark to help him defend "
"against Razmir. Hardly anyone listens to him. What else would you expect from a "
"union of River Kingdom monarchs, half of whom were once bandit chieftains "
"themselves?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b73e8e3-eb22-4ff9-8551-9788a9949801"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not even neighboring Lambreth comes to his aid, though both face the same "
"enemy. The state of Lambreth was established by three merchant families, under "
"constant threat of annexation by their neighbors. This annexation was exactly what "
"eventually came to pass, though not by Razmir. Instead, Lambreth was seized by "
"general Kamdyn Arnefax, commander of the Black Eagles. This grim dictator is no "
"better than Razmir, if you ask me. His knights are known for dispensing justice "
"after hours – as judge, jury, and executioner.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41b5c13d-76f5-4a18-b78a-af8e0f6007eb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Clearly, the Outlaw Council has no wish to help those who are too weak to "
"stand up for themselves. The Council consists of the rulers of all the River "
"Kingdoms, and none of them have any desire to upset Razmir. There are plenty of "
"fools among these minor lords, and none of them know the first thing about "
"politics. Luckily, we're nothing like them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cb49d13-045f-4619-8187-c3d3a478d4c5"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have news, {name}. Wigmold has finished his magic system. It's easier to "
"catch bandits now. Much easier.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52b5e1c0-b78b-43e0-9923-878d147bc4fd"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Kellid shaman problem has been dealt with. The Golden Shields got all of "
"them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c580aa00-42fd-463d-b162-b91096be4b1b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, I'm pleased to report that Wigmold has successfully installed "
"his magical surveillance system! Now it's practically impossible for any criminal "
"to hide from us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ab0be5c-cd95-4610-8187-7cd57b46981c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, as soon as the Golden Shields stepped onto the streets, your "
"domain became even more safe. Truth be told, I've come to think that I "
"underestimated them — though I already had much respect for their experience and "
"skills from the outset.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8245d50f-e815-4499-8ac5-aac51de18b68"
msgid ""
"\\\"Remember the magical surveillance system we purchased from that gnome? Well, "
"he's finally finished it, and it's working like a charm!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a8d018a-bbef-4441-b289-813f315f98e8"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, I just had a brawl with one of Golden Shields' patrols! This barkeep "
"wanted to make a little extra for himself off my tab. The bastard thought I "
"wouldn't remember how much I drank, ha! I was already done with the furniture and "
"ready to turn my attention to the barkeep when the golden heroes showed up... The "
"point of all this being that they know what they're doing! The just need to learn "
"who they can and cannot put their paws on, ha ha. But no matter — a few days in "
"the hospital will be enough time to think it over, ha ha ha hmmm... I think I hurt "
"my spine...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b475351-a90a-45dd-8d76-91d0888aa06d"
msgid ""
"\\\"We found the shamans who were planning to poison our food and water. – Even "
"before they reached the city's walls.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11e6592f-393d-43a6-9dbd-b86a80aedba8"
msgid ""
"\\\"We tracked down the shamans who were planning to poison our food and water. – "
"Took them as soon as they entered the city! But the townsfolk were watching. Now "
"there are rumors that the {mf|King|Queen} is spying on {mf|his|her} people. How "
"else could they have captured the barbarians before they even acted?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5b9f401-b3cf-499b-bf19-bc76e14ee48f"
msgid ""
"\\\"They took the barbarians before they even got near the food and water "
"supplies. Ours suffered no losses.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a883b8f-2233-4a7f-beec-94add6e61578"
msgid ""
"\\\"The barbarians snuck into some of the warehouses and poisoned the grain. But "
"Roham's people quickly found them. The grain was burned, and we suffered no losses."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f38b649-4e4e-400b-b641-5bd89c16a59d"
msgid ""
"\\\"He showed me how to use it for spying, and how to focus the system on "
"searching for specific threats. — And bam! We found our hairy friends' hiding "
"place! You remember those chest pounding shamans who swore to poison all the food "
"and water in the capital? Well you can forget about them now... forever, ha ha ha, "
"hmmm.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ffcfb34b-24cf-484a-97ed-4bc76ef8cbd2"
msgid ""
"\\\"As soon as those shamans entered the city, his system alerted us. Out food and "
"water is safe, but a crowd of gaping townsfolk gathered round and watched as we "
"were finishing the arrest. I chased them off as quick as I could, but the rumors "
"are already spreading anyway: 'See how quickly {name} took care of those "
"barbarians? '{mf|He|She}'s watching us — always...'\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8454de5d-87ef-4ad7-be28-8cc3b65b6874"
msgid ""
"\\\"They captured those hapless Kellid poisoners, by the way. It happened a few "
"days back. One of our guards caught sight of the barbarians, and followed him. But "
"when they got to the granaries, the Golden Shields were already waiting for them. "
"I hear it was a real blast. Someone even passed around a hat — to chip in for the "
"entertainment. The show earned a fair pile of coins!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88a358b4-2231-41dc-90a3-47c551b1c128"
msgid ""
"\\\"They captured the last of those shamans who were planning to poison the "
"capital's food and water in. It happened a few days back. Anyway, one of them "
"actually did manage to get inside one of the warehouses, but Roham's people "
"quickly found and destroyed the poisoned grain.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8ddf0c7-68d0-4b05-a376-7e69a1c4b994"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thanks to his magics, we almost immediately found and neutralized all of the "
"shamans who were planning to poison our food and water supplies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2734b173-8405-497d-9f1a-6461325b337d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thanks to his magics, we were able to catch every last one of the shamans who "
"snuck inside the capital to poison our food and water supplies. Unfortunately, "
"there were witnesses during one of the arrests, and our citizens are puzzled. – "
"How could the guard have known where to look for the barbarians, or where to "
"conceal its forces and wait in ambush? Some suspect that we're somehow spying on "
"the people of the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad3d7a22-c820-4fce-97ef-59c39c8f1494"
msgid ""
"\\\"The shamans who threatened to poison food and water in the capital were caught "
"one by one. None of them came within an arrow's flight of a well or granary.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0e45824-9305-4038-82cd-bc6ab102fe07"
msgid ""
"\\\"The shamans who swore they'd poison the capital's food and water were captured "
"one by one. Unfortunately, a few of them managed to make good on their threats. "
"But Roham's people found and destroyed the poisoned grain before anyone could be "
"hurt.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "534dcd71-0658-4f14-bf27-27faa86a79cf"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun falls silent, but after a while he continues:{/n} \\\"The kingdom has "
"grown much. It's far stronger now. We can protect our people from many dangers. "
"Perhaps nearly all of them. It's an impressive feat. I am glad that you chose me "
"as your advisor. I am happy that I could walk this path with you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "383e7c23-f49f-45c6-b99e-ee40209708a7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I also wanted to take this opportunity to congratulate you, Your Highness. "
"I've served many rulers, and none was able to achieve such order in his {mf||or "
"her} domain — especially under such harsh conditions. I shall remember with pride "
"my service to you in these trying times. I will carry these memories fondly, to my "
"grave.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16f83847-2eb0-4c85-b8dd-70099f57423c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I gotta say, I never thought being Warden could be so fun. Hell, I figured "
"that watching over the peasants and chasing away con artists would be boring. But "
"you… you've achieved heights far beyond the reach of any of the other River "
"kinglings. And did it all while your domain was suffering from three times the "
"normal number of cataclysms, monster invasions and wars... {n}Regongar bares his "
"fangs in a smile:{/n} \\\"My congratulations! The local dimwits could never have "
"dreamed of a defender like yourself!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d32ccde-f2b9-4c97-a840-70b8f26c9278"
msgid "\\\"I order the guard doubled in all settlements.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc175a77-5501-4657-a9d0-b4d8c75336de"
msgid "\\\"I order a curfew.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "219b83db-925e-4713-8b0e-fe9dede4be85"
msgid "\\\"Let them get used to taking care of themselves.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff174daf-720d-4fd0-a886-e5185863e4d1"
msgid "\\\"You're the Warden – you know what to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5d17a72-a691-4975-aa5e-ed61ac1eaa81"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten bows hastily and starts talking right away.{/n} \\\"Bandit attacks "
"continue in your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}. In some places, the people "
"are scared of leaving their houses even at dusk, not to mention in the dead of "
"night.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "822bb815-fbb6-477b-a66f-b41472be366e"
msgid ""
"\\\"As your Warden, I recommend we double the number of guards. That will allow us "
"to keep the situation under control. I will arm everyone I can, and hasten their "
"training.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3d5ee7be-7ead-48bb-abc5-c84f8fffa3b0"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun looks sullen.{/n} \\\"There's disaster. Everywhere. The Stag Lord may be "
"gone, but there's still much trouble in your lands. Robbing and killing on the "
"roads...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd7190f6-9740-4dbe-b350-52e9786aac3f"
msgid ""
"\\\"You must do something. Protect the people. My advice? A curfew. Announce a "
"time of night when people remain inside their homes. My guard will maintain order."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59f03c29-1b67-4eb8-94ad-9bdb2eb51fb2"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc grins darkly.{/n} \\\"Sometimes your subjects make me wonder. They "
"live in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. They've always got plenty of bandits "
"around, but they start families here, they raise their kids – all while they keep "
"complaining that the bandits won't let them live! And they don't ever leave!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12c9a087-569a-4d3f-a2e3-67325d4811c8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, the peasants finally got to me with all their nagging about bandits. But "
"I'm fine, I can handle it. I've just got to try to ignore them. I've already lived "
"here long enough to understand: as soon as the locals realize no one is going to "
"protect them, they'll stop whining and take up arms themselves. Give them a chance "
"to show their worth!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f59f7fc5-0dfb-4362-8c11-a7ad9906e457"
msgid "\\\"Will do, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a27fe94b-af72-46c2-b433-26fb41755dc9"
msgid "\\\"You know what's best.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9aa8d399-fdc4-4125-86ff-283eeaba9608"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar cringes with disgust.{/n} \\\"So the guards will loiter in the streets "
"rather than clearing out the bandits' lairs? Your barony won't go far at this rate!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8314e03-d820-4b0d-8767-1c73aaf05c40"
msgid "\\\"Right. I will give the order.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7201f066-a7f8-4ba7-854e-b6e4d24e3576"
msgid ""
"\\\"At least your subjects won't be crowding the streets like useless sheeple.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7e12711-85a0-42f4-8afe-80b4bfd85fe9"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! We can't just... lock "
"people up in their houses and hope that the violence will stop!\\\" {n}Kesten "
"shakes his head, but decides not to continue.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b54ce66b-479e-44ac-b522-fbc84faae13e"
msgid ""
"\\\"They will fail. And when the criminals finish robbing people on the streets, "
"they'll start breaking into their homes. This is a bad decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79b40a6b-998c-4290-adaf-913591c59a9d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Exactly.\\\" {n}Regongar cracks his fingers, as if he's preparing for a fight "
"himself.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13332787-ebf7-44d6-a71c-979c5b337ebe"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will immediately start looking for new guards, and dispatch units to the "
"farthest reaches of the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "baf6c203-56bd-439a-953c-17b02568f38f"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will announce time of night when the people should keep themselves inside.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c9d53c3-fb70-4e81-b0d1-a8c0e9c5eead"
msgid ""
"\\\"Like I said – nothing. You'll see, these petitioners can handle everything "
"themselves.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ae11a43-de26-40d1-934f-2f407cd52371"
msgid "{n}Kesten shakes his head, but doesn't argue.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a418773b-ddaf-487a-89cc-bb2010864f93"
msgid ""
"\\\"Set up additional guard posts and keep the locals away from conflict with the "
"fairies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74c10527-f4fe-4d42-9880-80206e05dcf5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Fairies don't attack for no reason. We've invaded their lands. Help the locals "
"pull up their roots and take them to another area.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "93622cd8-4cfc-42da-9bb8-aa9b9dd83355"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wipe them out, Regongar. I don't want to hear about these fairies again.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "030cc1ff-2160-4322-9e17-139314e8e1c3"
msgid "\\\"Make your own decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29fce6f8-3423-460e-94db-bf5c8b04afc9"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten is as black as thunder.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|"
"Your Highness}, there's a disaster in {g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}. Suddenly a "
"group of fairies came out of the forest to the edge of the swamps. They're a "
"vicious tribe – fitting their reputation perfectly.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e52dafc1-a144-402b-a669-eda0b90269cb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Until recently they merely toyed with the locals. – Pounded on their roofs at "
"night, threw their boots up in the trees. But now they've started spoiling the "
"cattle and trying to lure the people into the woods! We need to put an end to "
"this, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25ce28e5-28bd-4f7c-bae3-a1b45048de83"
msgid ""
"\\\"We shouldn't just go attack the fairies, of course. – They haven't done "
"anything yet that would warrant such a response. But increasing the guard would "
"help.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a84c8be4-e795-47ef-a447-59aba295bd6f"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun nods at you.{/n} \\\"We have fairies, {name}. They wander the {g|"
"Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}, along the border. They refuse to leave. They say the "
"lands are theirs. Your people are frightened.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f78cf9d8-7dea-46d4-8939-bcd22116ec7d"
msgid ""
"{n}The man cringes and shakes his head.{/n} \\\"The fairies are an old tribe. They "
"have their rules, and we must honor them. Order your subjects to leave this land "
"or there will be war.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ae645009-4195-44b9-a123-84d63ebec5b0"
msgid "\\\"Certainly, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dbe797f1-f77e-446d-9f8a-12f80268b791"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar smiles angrily.{/n} \\\"Good news finally! My guys were getting bored "
"at their posts, but we've just now gotten word about a chance to stretch our bones!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8abf772-de8d-41a3-aa17-dca4b3fedda7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Some fairies showed up near the settlements in the {g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/"
"g}. – And not just showed up. They're pushing our people back, saying they're "
"driving invaders from their lands. Do you know what that means?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58b169c6-924a-4464-a561-9321c850eeb2"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar squints.{/n} \\\"It means we can gather a team and crush those "
"pipsqueaks. Give this job to my guys – and you can forget about this problem "
"forever!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37951875-84b3-42e4-94ca-6f9eb56ad391"
msgid ""
"\\\"Senseless. People will die. Fairies too. And for what? A piece of land?\\\" {n}"
"Ekun shakes his head.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4432a5a1-3125-4a8c-bbc0-76bd53beeafe"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar sighs disappointedly.{/n} \\\"And we could have had so much fun...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b8d4e603-07a1-4f67-8f4e-efa80124afa4"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know, I'm loyal to you forever, but the people won't like this decision. "
"To be honest, I don't like it either, but an order is an order.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d6f80b9-d279-40b6-9773-790e8c879dc5"
msgid "{n}Ekun silently nods.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e67fa0b3-763a-457a-9223-499f09e46713"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar's smile turns into a grin.{/n} \\\"So we put our tail between our legs "
"and run? From freaking fairies?!\\\" {n}The words of the half-orc turn into an "
"angry growl.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35e7eb65-5340-46b6-a23f-34765fd47940"
msgid "\\\"Ha ha ha ha hmmmmm... I knew you would appreciate my plan!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c48de852-1529-4e66-b282-ceeffbee797b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I assure you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, the "
"guard won't allow any fighting. And we won't allow some fairies to terrorize your "
"subjects.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "322f67cc-4743-4d4a-ba3f-68058197a0ce"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will lead the people away from there. I know of a place they could move to, "
"near {g|Lake Silverstep}Silverstep{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5abd17d1-a843-4d53-9014-ca4751f8cc81"
msgid "{n}Regongar's eyes flare.{/n} \\\"Let the hunt begin!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0175f0b-b0e9-4d32-bbfc-3483a90eeec6"
msgid "\\\"The decision is yours.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f9b93e3-7185-4cfd-b2c8-e9ea7b1054d0"
msgid "Ordered that the love potion swindler be fined just like any other swindler."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99d46221-e8e4-4f4f-a032-829e28603d8c"
msgid "\\\"Let us follow the letter of the law. The miscreant shall be fined.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b355068e-6fd4-458e-8d61-15c12be2191c"
msgid ""
"Ordered that the love potion swindler be punished stricter than usual — thrown "
"into jail."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b27982be-a947-4df1-be49-55d330ece6f6"
msgid "\\\"This is more than simple deception. Throw the villain in jail.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c61d11bd-5616-4462-bf1f-adc044efcb76"
msgid "Ordered that the love potion swindler be executed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "302dfc01-39c8-4ffe-bb5a-339bbd477158"
msgid "\\\"Execute the fool.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f78af692-4d37-4b02-9329-76472f6c085c"
msgid ""
"[Gain 4000 gold] \\\"We agree. The search for the merchant's daughter shall be the "
"guards' top priority.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "876afc68-80a2-497c-a63f-3eb05c525cd6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The guard already has their orders. This case shall be dealt with like any "
"other.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da964079-f6c4-4a0f-8b88-07af912c4330"
msgid "\\\"You can decide this yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "091e3cca-1e15-4a64-96e7-1861ad2de127"
msgid ""
"{n}After some hesitation, he finally goes on:{/n} \\\"{name}. We both want to "
"protect this land. But when we consider the best ways to do this, we see different "
"things. It would be better if you find a different Warden. My place is in the "
"forest, with a bow in my hands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "479cfa89-8cf3-4ff4-99eb-f024ec783000"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's something else, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}… I've thought "
"about this for a long time, and I must give up my position. I cannot guarantee the "
"safety of those whose lives have been entrusted to me, if I don't understand the "
"decisions of my superiors.\\\" {n}Shuffling his feet, Kesten adds:{/n} \\\"I am "
"sorry, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7fda93e1-4b15-408b-8e5d-c3327d09349f"
msgid ""
"\\\"If I were you, I'd start looking for a new Warden. I'm not doing this any "
"more. All I ever do here is get angry and run pointless errands. It's not like you "
"need me here either. – You make all the calls yourself anyway. Long story short, "
"if you wanna go stomp some goblins or fry a troll or two, just whistle. But as for "
"being a warden, you can count me out.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "be77a732-4ca3-45d1-8884-db549cc5ccc8"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun's face is grim.{/n} \\\"Caught a swindler. He tried to pour a love potion "
"into a merchant daughter's drink. Her family is well-known, and the case is "
"unusual... The people are watching, and his guilt is already proven. But the "
"judges don't know how to punish him. You must decide.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3dadecb-517c-4a79-93c3-97525f765080"
msgid ""
"\\\"A minor court case has been the talk of the capital, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|"
"Highness|Highness}. A swindler was caught trying to slip a love potion to the "
"daughter of an important merchant. The court has found him guilty – but decreed "
"that since the situation is so unusual, only you could pronounce a just sentence.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b65113bd-42be-4fa9-870a-a04bff71d305"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar's footsteps boom throughout the throne room.{/n} \\\"The damn "
"swindlers, {name}! They're like lice – no matter how many you catch, tomorrow "
"there will be even more! My boys caught another scoundrel a few days back. This "
"one was trying to slip a love potion into the daughter of a local moneybag.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "314183de-4f3d-4d89-a8a0-5c4ff7038618"
msgid ""
"\\\"The usual punishment is a fine. But in this case... too soft. My suggestion – "
"a prison sentence.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11e49038-1af9-4dde-96bc-e53db9be01c2"
msgid ""
"\\\"The established punishment for fraud in the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} "
"is a fine. To my mind, this case does not warrant a departure from established "
"procedure. The case is not so exceptional as the locals imagine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6dd4aaba-b5f6-48c5-bd5f-80f8026be61d"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar chuckles.{/n} \\\"Anyhow, we caught the poor sod, the court found him "
"guilty, and all we need from you is a sentence. His plan was devious and cold, and "
"everybody in the capital is watching this case. Unless you show the thieving scum "
"around here who's boss, they'll just keep at it. I suggest a public execution. "
"Love can make you lose your head, ha ha hmmm.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7ebdafa-6357-44cd-a369-50220817d8a6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The daughter of a wealthy merchant has gone missing. Stolen, most likely. Her "
"father wants us to send out our best to search for her.\\\" {n}After a moment, "
"Ekun adds:{/n} \\\"He's hinted that he'll reward us for our trouble.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a975b857-a819-4c3e-a455-967c33447fd7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Rumors are flying around the capital, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}. "
"The daughter of a well-known merchant has gone missing. Some say that she might "
"have been kidnapped. Her father is calling on us to send every man and woman we "
"have to go search for her – and promises that he will generously repay his debt of "
"gratitude.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee0f8a78-a371-4a3d-a163-ec6923d924d1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Another day, another debacle, {name}! Someone's whisked away the daughter of a "
"local moneybag. The trader swears 'he'll make us all rich' if we send every guard "
"in town out in search of his precious little girl.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e3dde2a-adc0-45ef-9487-f7e274f15aa4"
msgid ""
"\\\"We should agree to help. We'll have to deal with the situation regardless. If "
"we agree, we might also fill our coffers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5fd3001d-8143-4f56-930c-dbf2e208f221"
msgid ""
"\\\"There are several reasons we should accept his offer. I've learned that he has "
"friends in high places in the trade guild…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f15447fc-3413-4980-b5d3-0b98b5582310"
msgid ""
"\\\"To tell you the truth, it wouldn't surprise me if she ran off herself. As for "
"the merchant – what's there to talk about? What should we care? Seems like the "
"idiot just forgot his place. 'He'll make us all rich'?! Who the hell does he think "
"he is?! We spend more on feasts in a week than he earns in a year!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ffcd18b-32b7-4fb3-bdf1-d6147823222f"
msgid "{n}Ekun slowly nods.{/n} \\\"I understand. It will be done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "439b20de-2b76-4fa8-b3a0-007b5c832e0e"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun wrinkles his forehead.{/n} \\\"This will not teach him anything. Nor "
"everyone else.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c32bd484-9dbd-4774-8852-d70343d7a354"
msgid "\\\"Wise choice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23b03743-0386-40d4-92b5-ac6d113a2383"
msgid "\\\"Then I'll send him to prison. I'm glad that you trust me, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57ae31af-11ba-46b9-bd20-4ceb33c822c7"
msgid "\\\"In that case, the criminal shall be fined and set free.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ceb42bb9-710b-4b15-ac9b-e74c10fc60ca"
msgid ""
"\\\"Good thinking. Why would you even need me otherwise? Hah. Long story short, "
"we're hanging the bastard.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ba4547d-ace4-41e3-ab69-39db7656ad9a"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten presses his lips together.{/n} \\\"As you command, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|"
"Highness|Highness}. However, it is my duty to inform you that this punishment does "
"not befit the crime.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c169be9-c482-4bc5-907e-a811df7331d2"
msgid "\\\"Nice! I'll get right to it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8b95385-d117-4a55-b42d-e5b598124730"
msgid "\\\"That should do it, I guess. Your wish is my command, ha ha hmmm.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fdfeb9d0-5980-4bce-bb44-06cde01a853d"
msgid "\\\"I'll inform the court, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "190f98b2-685b-493f-91a1-a487eb3cf95d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Damn it, {name}. These rabble don't understand mercy. They'll just figure we "
"have no spine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "623c30a9-9a51-4af4-b1e3-90543c1fa817"
msgid "{n}Ekun shortly nods.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c990c49-5872-4192-879d-4408eb51d47a"
msgid "\\\"We're missing a good opportunity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90d77a72-da66-41cb-afd3-1776acccdddc"
msgid ""
"\\\"It shall be done, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}.\\\" {n}Kesten bows, "
"holding his hand against his chest.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ee5fb84-81ac-4a5e-a1da-44f85d3942c7"
msgid ""
"\\\"What?! This city is chock-full of killers and thugs. All sorts of scum that "
"need to be kept in check. And now you want us to drop everything just to chase "
"after some runaway kid?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24ef3e1b-d88f-4bfc-b378-2878a3fb2e35"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten shakes his head.{/n} \\\"The merchants should not be underestimated. "
"Their power in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} is great…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34551231-5ef6-42c2-a85f-616ecfd0b021"
msgid "\\\"I'll order the guard to focus on the search.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62a3d569-c677-4862-9e3e-2058625f26b4"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you command, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}. I will tell the "
"merchant that his case is in good hands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23019a59-3c82-449b-a47b-2252742fca69"
msgid "\\\"Nice. Can't wait to tell the pig where he can stuff his gold…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da3cef73-9f4c-4013-b9e1-25c752d128df"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not sure why he went to all the trouble though. The dowry is all right, of "
"course. But the girl herself… Let's just say I'd rather be earning my bread "
"crawling around stinking dungeons through the rat droppings.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "627296b1-3d54-443f-aac6-161885181a51"
msgid "\\\"Such beasts have no place in my lands. They must be eradicated.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf6078b0-deeb-4f55-8eae-93dc18aa45a6"
msgid ""
"\\\"We should strive to live in harmony with nature – as much as is reasonable. "
"Henceforth, these lands are protected by my decree.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d90e4aa-c67c-43af-ba0b-ad118e7919d4"
msgid "\\\"You are the Warden of these lands. I trust your judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c30031f0-d3dc-4d67-9471-52c040f21962"
msgid "\\\"A bulette hunt? Sounds interesting. Do as you like, Regongar.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5db5eb46-f338-4822-b08d-be88b69352f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"A strange quarrel. I don't understand. There's a region where bulettes live. "
"Guards and hunters kill them, so that it's safe. But some are displeased.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51149e11-6653-4c5f-8796-84d9053d7f29"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}, a decision has to be made regarding "
"the bulettes that inhabit one of your regions. The guard and a local hunting club "
"seek them out and kill them, as they should. But the, uhhh... scholarly community "
"of the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} has objected to this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f559bba5-9f46-4123-889d-5a0c6c69d617"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar talks fast, his face beaming with excitement.{/n} \\\"Just wait until "
"you hear this, {name}! A rare, exotic type of bulette lives in one of our "
"provinces. However, they're almost extinct, so the bookworms across the {mf|barony|"
"barony|kingdom|kingdom} want us to declare their lands a natural reserve. The "
"locals, as you can imagine, want to rip them all to shreds – the landsharks and "
"the know-it-alls too, ha ha! Everyone is looking to us for a solution, and I kept "
"thinking – what the hell are we supposed to do about this? And then it hit me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c0afd84-3510-417a-9e65-5091807e73ae"
msgid ""
"\\\"Scholars of some sort. They say that a rare type of bulette lives there, one "
"that is almost extinct. They want us to forbid hunting in these parts. {n}Ekun "
"shakes his head.{/n} \\\"It's a strange quarrel. You know what I will say. The "
"monsters must die.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19ea1857-b4b5-4fcb-b6e4-94df7a6f11ee"
msgid ""
"\\\"Some zoologist has declared that these bulettes are a rare species… or "
"subspecies… Long story short, they only live around these parts and nowhere else. "
"Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}, the scholars ask that we take these lands "
"under our protection and outlaw the killing of these bulettes. However, I firmly "
"believe that the beasts should be eradicated. The safety of local peasants "
"outweighs other concerns.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d83ac398-c5a6-41b3-b4be-73b0fd03899c"
msgid ""
"\\\"We should declare the area a royal hunting ground! Then we wait a few months, "
"let those bad boys get fatter and breed some young… and go hunt ourselves some "
"bulettes! Just imagine, their hides hanging along the throne room wall! Or are you "
"supposed to do something with their claws and teeth or something? Whatever. So, "
"who's your most cunning, most irreplaceable advisor? Ha ha ha hmmmm!\\\" {n}"
"Regongar's laughter booms, and sparks jump across his fingers.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bddb447e-e924-407a-b469-857af242f9b3"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar is dumbfounded, and the excitement on his face slowly falls.{/n} \\"
"\"What the… Why would you let some lousy guards have all the fun? There we go "
"again, another brilliant plan out the window…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29993a0f-c254-4be1-ac9b-2686d7408404"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun's nostrils flare, but his voice is steady and cold.{/n} \\\"A dangerous "
"whim. I hope we don't come to regret it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf4bb18e-5b46-4a88-8782-b4f55d605ee3"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten grits his teeth and answers in a muffled voice:{/n} \\\"As you command, "
"Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af75f6d8-0fc5-491e-a848-03a125fe8d2d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ha. We'll see what you say when one of those cute little buggers comes to say "
"'hi' while you're sleeping in your tent… I know we're going to run into one of "
"them sooner or later – and then I'll have my hunt. But whatever. The main thing is "
"we're not letting anyone else kill them all off.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87c38c69-28c3-4a2a-9b8b-7968a7a15a71"
msgid ""
"\\\"Good. I'll order the guards to take care of the bulettes, and offer a reward "
"to any other hunters.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5594f212-7c1d-4112-acbc-b4bd08b19850"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten gives a short nod.{/n} \\\"The guard will hunt them down. Any who "
"volunteer to help will be rewarded.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea4ea259-4fcc-4698-9cf7-a55a461850a3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Great!\\\" {n}Grinning, Regongar claps and rubs his hands together.{/n} \\"
"\"This is going to be fun!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c1dd42b-7c4f-4a2b-9471-5d03daf749c0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perfect! I can't wait to shoot one of these things! You're supposed to shoot "
"them, right? Or do you use a spear? Whatever, we'll improvise!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b3386f7-fa9e-4b2d-8730-a2e0d150ca29"
msgid ""
"[Pay 200 BP] \\\"We should focus on causes, not consequences. I command you to "
"begin renovating the slums.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17d509a7-82a5-40cb-9647-1f90a28c87e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Order your men to patrol the slums more frequently. You should check everyone "
"who enters or leaves.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89820e3e-71b9-48e2-8b3b-56735d279ded"
msgid ""
"[Pay 50 BP] \\\"There's no place in my capital for this breeding ground of crime "
"and disease. The slums must be removed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38393ee9-85c2-4ac5-89c2-521431a94ebe"
msgid ""
"\\\"Such is life in the city. It can't be helped, so we shouldn't agonize over it."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc6d39b6-2c2c-41f6-bc26-650fccd11005"
msgid "\\\"Settle this matter as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d15cde12-98ce-46fc-b4d9-28d298fcfa54"
msgid ""
"\\\"But now there's a new concern. I've heard several complaints about the slums "
"on the outskirts of the capital. They say that only thieves and beggars live "
"there. They say that we should tear down their huts and send them away, and the "
"city would be cleaner and safer for it.\\\" {n}Ekun shakes his head.{/n} \\\"But "
"the poor have nowhere to go. They'll just find a new place and build new huts, "
"even shabbier than before.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51f4e4b8-ab42-4031-b5c0-0ef64354e1ca"
msgid ""
"\\\"There is other news as well. Due to the capital's rapid growth and the inflow "
"of people from the provinces, the outskirts of our capital have become a real "
"slum. Streams of sewage crisscross the streets, hordes of rats and disease abound… "
"What's worse – robbers, pickpockets, fences and the other dregs of society have "
"found a home there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff36d834-d285-47c0-8207-9be5054b74b2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, by the way, there's something else. The people of the capital are "
"complaining – again! This time it's the slums on the outskirts of the city. They "
"stink to high heaven, hordes of rats piling out 'em every night, and every thief "
"and pickpocket in town has a hideout there – or so they say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf8b4df9-975a-4a72-b0c2-2ed83aa730cb"
msgid ""
"\\\"My advice – lift up the slums from the mud. Hire those who live there as "
"builders. Teach them to dig wells and waste pits, to pave the roads and put up "
"street lamps. Then, once they're done cleaning their district, hire them to start "
"work on the next one. Give these people jobs and decent homes, and there won't be "
"a thief among them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca864be2-7445-4f04-8065-89f206648e9e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I suggest we double the guard in the slums and place restrictions on who can "
"come and go, and when. It's much cheaper than trying to clean them up, and more "
"effective than simply tearing them down.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38543ae4-f4e2-4692-8161-9851cec6d1bb"
msgid ""
"\\\"And as far as the last part, that's definitely true. Me and my boys would have "
"a much easier time if you let us just tear those dirty shacks down, and drive off "
"all the scum that lives there. Of course, some think the district could be cleaned "
"up... but they're just crazy. You could spend a mountain of gold building it up. "
"In a few years it'll just turn back into a slum again.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "afb290a5-de0c-48a4-86e7-d24f3b354034"
msgid "\\\"I will begin at once.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12692bea-6115-4a3d-9254-ec1ded830760"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you wish, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}. I must inform you, "
"however, that this decision will prove costly.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0bf513bb-492f-47d1-ba89-0e16fbce5339"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, there we go again. Working for the commoners instead of making them work "
"for us…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30f93f45-fa40-4d9e-a6b4-643edf6800ca"
msgid "\\\"It will be done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3e8433e-28b8-42c9-8987-24511ecd65df"
msgid ""
"\\\"Certainly, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}. I should have suggested "
"this a long time ago.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4807e9de-1e66-4e44-a098-fbbd6186475f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hm. That should do it just as well. I'll tell my boys to get busy. Maybe this "
"will finally teach them a thing or two about life on the streets…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5488a07-1404-4297-a934-d0fac067ce06"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun gazes at you with a deep frown.{/n} \\\"A harsh decision. That's not the "
"same thing as a strong one.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6d8a000-66d7-4138-82be-45bd9bd59134"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc rubs his hands in anticipation.{/n} \\\"Well said, ha ha! It's "
"high time me and the boys got a little exercise…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47ce67d4-aced-4973-ab38-9c588eba63c4"
msgid "\\\"A rash decision. We'll reap its consequences soon enough...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5401eb83-b51a-4ecf-8f93-9e75c5a7a894"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you wish, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}\\\". {n}After some "
"hesitation, Kesten continues:{/n} \\\"However, tensions are rising. I hope we do "
"not come to regret this decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "369bc060-82d3-41b1-b937-146ca29916da"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ha! Spot on. What do we care? The commoners can squabble all they want.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e79acfaa-e24f-4805-abb8-d72b360c2437"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun nods.{/n} \\\"We'll commence the renovation. The outskirts will become a "
"fine place to live, just like any other district.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "361b4c46-d954-455a-b6ff-0200d1f2431c"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you command, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}. I'll double the "
"patrols and ensure all entrances are watched day and night.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6d3e7d3d-2748-4bbb-af47-279382293508"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sure thing. I'll rid the capital of this filth… It's been a while since me and "
"the boys had some fun.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02fd8552-3cf4-404b-86b5-b5d4bb103fcd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Great news! More and more bulettes are being spotted in that region, what's it "
"called… I heard that some trader saw a landshark as big as a house! About time we "
"paid them a visit, ha ha ha hmmm…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bb47f6e1-6012-48d3-a27d-1d41e4e1d4f3"
msgid ""
"\\\"There have been new sightings of bulettes, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|"
"Highness}. The creatures are becoming more and more numerous – as well as bigger "
"and more aggressive. One of the guards swears he saw one as big as a hut…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4000c02e-4fe6-442c-9bff-516d789dc30c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Those bulettes. They are gone. All dead. But the peasants have begun to "
"complain about other wild animals and bandits. It seems that without the bulettes, "
"the other threats have become more numerous. But of course wolves and bandits are "
"better than giant monsters…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ef153a0-d7ba-47be-9361-5ac1ddc73b93"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten looks grim.{/n} \\\"I've received new reports about those bulettes, Your "
"{mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}. We managed to get rid of them, but this only "
"led to an increase in attacks from other dangerous beasts – and even bandits! It "
"seems that the bulettes had been keeping them at bay...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6eb43ea-9285-462f-9029-af59174f944b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Bad news. The hunters are terrified of a giant bulette, a really mean one. "
"It's giving the locals a lot of trouble. You were warned.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1ddeee7-0759-41ae-b831-ed22fdfa3106"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar is beaming.{/n} \\\"Remember those rare bulettes? Well not long ago, "
"the locals finally killed them all off… but now they're constantly under attack "
"from bears, wolves and even bandits! They've taken the bulettes' place! Ah ha ha "
"ha ha hmmmmm!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26c9243d-f7a7-4c0c-92fd-67682e37fca8"
msgid "\\\"As you command, Your {mf|Grace|Grace|Highness|Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5bed79c0-f684-495f-89f2-18a71e08618e"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll take the initiative. Gather your troops and drive the barbarians from my "
"lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe9899fb-9b5d-491b-a82c-f039f086c4cf"
msgid ""
"\\\"I wouldn't be surprised if that was exactly what they wanted us to do. — Start "
"chasing them across the hills. Double the guard in all the raided regions. We "
"shall defend ourselves.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "441dee23-c5f7-43ed-a06b-2a0f6f69c7ad"
msgid "\\\"This choice is yours.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d17751d9-d38c-4299-9363-c97e8e4e934d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Still there are many barbarians near the borders. They attack trade caravans. "
"Raid remote villages. Something must be done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08df64d7-ebd1-4e05-b296-4ac1b0737b14"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness... Our border regions inform us that remnant groups of "
"barbarians are still carrying out raids, burning villages and taking peasants as "
"slaves. We must put an end to this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ae05b01b-1dc2-4969-bd58-a0c871a747e5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tough shit today, {name}. The barbarians are still pecking at the border "
"regions. They've gathered into raiding parties and started harassing our peasants. "
"Of course the peasants are completely incapable of standing their ground, so they "
"keep jumping onto the corpse pile. – Leaving us fewer and fewer subjects and "
"servants each day. How dare they, the traitorous bastards!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0712518-b15b-436c-bb19-bf721ca8498a"
msgid ""
"\\\"We can strengthen the guard in the regions. But how can we know where they'll "
"strike next? We'd have to strengthen the guard everywhere. This would be "
"expensive, and difficult. I suggest we gather the troops and search for them. "
"Scour the woods and strike first.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79fb1e04-ba25-4466-adff-bfe4057d4059"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could perform a preemptive strike. – Send out a regiment, scour all the "
"nooks and crannies that the barbarians might be hiding in... However, this would "
"be risky, and it would mean playing the game by their rules. They'd never face us "
"in a decisive battle, but instead lure our troops deeper and deeper into unknown "
"territory. They'd force us to fight in constant skirmishes, and wear us down until "
"our soldiers simply started deserting en masse.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58fe8864-2e18-4f32-8573-2e64e586e217"
msgid ""
"\\\"So I see two solutions here: a bad one and a glorious one. We could send a "
"whole regiment of guards to the villages, tell them to dig in and hope that the "
"barbarians run out of the woods and stick themselves on their spears. Or, we could "
"do it like this: I'll gather a small squad of my best boys and girls, and assign "
"'em to a captain I know — a smart fellow, thinks on his feet. They'll scour the "
"area, find these blasted savages, and rip off their hairy... well, they'll know "
"what kinds of things are best to rip off. So, what say you? Not a bad idea, eh?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49484396-2c5e-4d12-8038-8c5588008eb3"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll take a squad of my best hunters to the border. We'll strike from nowhere "
"and crush the Kellids.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47b04677-caa6-4fa1-a91b-766edee27795"
msgid ""
"\\\"In that case, I'll increase the number of guards in our the border "
"settlements. We'll see how the savages like to fight real warriors instead of "
"unarmed peasants.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f8cb5c5-ed08-40a6-94d3-32180d15b44b"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc's eyes light up with excitement.{/n} \\\"Just what I like to hear, "
"{name}. The troops will march today.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b468846a-0436-4361-97fe-4084108f479e"
msgid "{n}Ekun frowns and looks away.{/n} \\\"It will be done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "01ec7aa6-a8cf-474f-81ae-a8149cefa727"
msgid ""
"{n}A grim look of satisfaction spreads across Kesten's face.{/n} \\\"As you "
"command, Your Highness. We'll show the savages how this land forges her men and "
"women!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3fea55dd-63cb-4d7b-be1d-8d48d09801e7"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar's face turns sour.{/n} \\\"Defense? How exciting... Ever since I was a "
"kid I've yearned to sit in defense...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd798b32-6417-484d-ac7a-5ea0bc351180"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun gives a short nod, his face a picture of decisiveness and resolve.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f20a584f-7941-4181-8744-2e503c5bf732"
msgid ""
"{n}A deep shadow crosses the warrior's face.{/n} \\\"As you command, Your Highness."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee4dd942-0109-4f7e-95cf-22497dbdbc6d"
msgid ""
"\\\"My advice — strengthen the guard in the settlements along the border, and "
"fortified our position there. Then the barbarians will have to come to us... and "
"they'll be easily dealt with.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b9feb881-30ce-4e23-8ef3-a5877c9a34bb"
msgid ""
"[Pay 2 BP each week] \\\"Sacrificing safety is folly. We'll pacify the people by "
"lowering the taxes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e6a40e4-5734-4273-b8a6-5993f5b6c4d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"If such is the will of the people, then we must surrender some of our control. "
"Certain security measures will simply have to be let go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74e6d70a-1017-45e8-bff2-03944206f64b"
msgid ""
"\\\"We cannot allow ourselves dance to the commoners' tune. Scatter the rebels and "
"outlaw such gatherings — for their own safety.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7fc3ec04-d1e3-4c93-a528-6b79e89df1d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The guards of this kingdom have been through hell and back. They deserve a "
"raise.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8fa0c2e-b78a-4b0a-862f-1d649ab034cb"
msgid ""
"\\\"A tired warrior is no use anyway. Let our guardsmen enjoy the rest they so "
"deserve.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "602e1950-ab4c-452d-ae27-a5b359aea6cf"
msgid ""
"\\\"They've brought my wrath upon their heads. Every man and woman who shirks "
"their duties will be shamefully discharged, and replaced with a mercenary.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7238807c-ba5c-487e-b3d7-71a78242997d"
msgid "\\\"I'll follow your advice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aed93888-44ef-4640-b314-3fa805e3a404"
msgid "\\\"I'll follow your advice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9978c262-5073-49f9-a08a-4b0f8a8f0455"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun's face is darker than a storm cloud.{/n} \\\"Big trouble, {name}. People "
"on the streets. They demand... 'a return to freedom'.\\\" {n}Shaking his head, "
"Ekun continues.{/n} \\\"They demand that we reduce the number of guards, the "
"frequency of patrols, and ban personal searches...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "857fc8e0-c848-46bd-a1ac-e0f98c35cd30"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten's voice is grim and harsh.{/n} \\\"It's a revolt, Your Highness. The "
"simple folk have flooded the streets. Pamphlets are scattered throughout the "
"capital. The way they put it, we're 'holding the people captive in their own "
"country'. Everything we've done to protect them is misinterpreted as measures to "
"limit their freedoms.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f911216d-c3b9-4f59-a149-84e2ba98a9be"
msgid ""
"\\\"The lousy peasants! Who do they think they are?! {name}, your subjects have "
"taken to the streets, and dare to make demands! 'The guard watches our every "
"step!' Just think of it — they want us to stop personal searches, lower the number "
"of guards, decrease the patrols...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acae4f28-a021-4556-8dc1-6e6f4c5249f2"
msgid ""
"\\\"My advice: do not clench your fist even tighter. It is not right for everyone "
"to suffer for the sins of the rash and the shortsighted. But I would not give in "
"either.\\\" {n}Ekun wrinkles his forehead in concentration. After a while, he "
"continues.{/n} \\\"What can we sacrifice instead of sacrificing safety? I can "
"think of one alternative: money.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "111acccd-8773-4b81-bc02-b82d3d5da06d"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten stands in silence, then continues.{/n} \\\"I'm afraid we'll just have to "
"give in. At least partially. It would certainly be cheaper than trying to placate "
"the people by lowering their tithes. And it's safer and more just than using force "
"to run them back to their homes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf04a919-c06a-4b76-97c8-cd9e8611f040"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll tell it like it is, {name} — if there's one thing they hate, it's that "
"I've brought this place to order! See, they can't loiter for days on end anymore, "
"idle away their day and then steal whatever they can get their dirty mitts on! My "
"hounds are watching their every move. There can be no deals, no appeasing them. — "
"Just give me the order, and my boys will have those dirty oafs back in their "
"homes, hiding under their beds!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b44b96d-3bb7-4cd7-b4d4-9440f2df0fdc"
msgid ""
"{n}A deep furrow crosses Ekun's forehead.{/n} \\\"The guards have revolted. They "
"refuse to work. They say, we 'fill every gap and patch every hole' with them. This "
"cannot go on.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4d107475-0a81-4449-892a-0b1c1eced1db"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten's ever-grim visage is painted with concern.{/n} \\\"Ill news, Your "
"Highness. The guard refuses to go out on patrols. The officers have declared that "
"their people will not take up weapons, until the conditions of their service are "
"improved. Truth be told, it is rare for a kingdom to see their guard take part in "
"so many battles, wars, raids and monster hunts...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46ae5a72-47f7-4746-8ecf-f6191467a8af"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar's voice booms across the throne room.{/n} \\\"{name}, your good-for-"
"nothing runts have gone on strike! Made demands! From me! When they were starting "
"out, I was like their ma and pa! I taught them which end of a halberd to hold! How "
"to shake down a vagabond! How to talk to the merchants, and make sure they pay on "
"time for their safety! And this is how they repay me! — By refusing to go out on "
"patrol?! By asking for a better quality of life?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad6fc7fd-d07a-4146-b437-74372dcebd9e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Mercenaries can never truly replace warriors who fight for their homeland. "
"Firing some of the guard would mean leaving someone without a defender. I think "
"instead we should raise their pay.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "faa185a7-12f3-4d2a-88e8-50d36f694d08"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness may instead pay for the services of mercenaries. But I think "
"that our boys deserve some time off. They risk their lives every day, and they "
"need to spend more time with their families... while they still can.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af7e7171-b148-4954-8cc1-298c6f5c3de9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I would kill the bastards if I could! There's so many damned people around — "
"and not a single soul you can trust! I say we just cut the dead weight, fire the "
"whiners and replace them with mercenaries.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea296da0-5939-4d53-87d8-5a9452a6674b"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun's shoulders relax in relief.{/n} \\\"I'll talk to your advisors. We'll "
"come up with something.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71f49f22-bdff-4d8e-a782-1404ffd84cc5"
msgid "\\\"I will obey, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7e53e47-fe99-43db-9ab0-639d4e7ebba3"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun nods in contemplation.{/n} \\\"It will be as you say. Perhaps it is for "
"the best.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9b6d4ea-f04c-4c0c-84ec-466b0edef26b"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten's face softens considerably.{/n} \\\"Your Highness only makes it even "
"clearer to me that this was the only proper course.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ea5eae3-0cfc-4f7a-82c6-143325846e71"
msgid "{n}Ekun winces, sighs heavily, and finally nods.{/n} \\\"I see.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f90151c-de65-46f4-af9b-24e3e1a69bdd"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten grits his teeth, straightens his back, and answers in a muffled voice.{/"
"n} \\\"An order I had hoped never to receive... As you command, Your Highness!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "01d02916-a992-473e-a74f-6327ab571d8f"
msgid "\\\"With pleasure, {name}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0eaac491-704e-44f4-90ac-cdd28c9a80f9"
msgid "\\\"I'm glad of this. I will deliver the good news.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7aff6d1-97d9-468e-9886-6fb424975063"
msgid ""
"{n}A slight smile crosses Kesten's lips.{/n} \\\"Thank you, Your Highness! I'll go "
"and tell your people the good news.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "251c7cd6-3d16-490c-baa8-521878c4501f"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you've got money you don't need lying around — then sure, give it to them. "
"Just don't say I never mentioned what sort of bastards you have serving in your "
"guard. I should know – I picked 'em myself, ha ha. Cut-throats and cold-blooded "
"killers send prayers to their gods when they see my guys crossing the street. Just "
"thought I should mention what kind of guys you're pampering, and what might be in "
"store for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3e7cae23-35ef-4fe2-bfde-e4e789d5e4ce"
msgid "\\\"As you command, Your Highness! I shall pass along your orders!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a739e639-3d58-465b-90ae-66376b692bb2"
msgid ""
"\\\"You don't know what you're saying! A good guard has to be either lean and "
"mean, or fat and cunning. These guys don't score too high in the brains "
"department, so I keep them running so they stay mean. We keep doing things your "
"way, you'll end up with a horde of fat, lazy bumknuckles!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "078974ab-d41f-43cc-8973-9978cbbbdbcd"
msgid "\\\"It is not my decision. But they do not deserve such treatment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3928530-3c5b-4658-a68e-5a36423a8378"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten sighs heavily.{/n} \\\"Those are the words that I have feared to hear... "
"As you command, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b38967e8-e614-4cf4-8e77-ac9a31917494"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar snaps his fingers and grins.{/n} \\\"Ha ha! That's just perfect for "
"the lazy numbskulls! They'll come crawling back to papa, begging for us to take "
"them back — and we'll give them nothing! The treacherous bastards!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8380459e-95df-4da1-9e30-525bfaecea47"
msgid "\\\"What?! You'll bend to these layabouts? These dimwits?! Ah, curses...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b6b3ed89-67a6-4467-bbb0-f4e90d562766"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, I'll enjoy this, {name}! My boys'll clean up the streets in no time!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3c5c657f-42ab-410c-b997-5888d6847c2e"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about your society.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79a25bce-9966-4c0d-b539-0ebc916baf42"
msgid "\\\"That will be all. Thank you, Roham.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1239f95-4ad7-419d-9f87-342c1d1db467"
msgid ""
"\\\"My advisor referred to you as the 'Golden Shields', yet you say 'Golden "
"Shield'. Which one is it?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1d10bc5e-385e-411f-921a-947c61b6b074"
msgid "\\\"How did you become a justiciar of Abadar?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39006522-f7cb-45dc-b3a3-cea7b1d1121c"
msgid ""
"{n} The woman before you holds herself erect, and there is confidence in her "
"stance. Her polished armor shines even in the dimly-lit throne room. {/n} \\"
"\"Greetings, Your Highness. I represent the Golden Shield — a society of Abadar's "
"faithful, which offers law enforcement services to anyone that may require them.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f2b6d8b-6a50-44a0-b592-86cc5614b14e"
msgid ""
"\\\"We are more than mere mercenaries. We are a brotherhood of warriors devoted to "
"upholding the law – and fighting the ruinous powers of chaos. Each of us has sworn "
"a solemn oath to follow the ideals of Abadar, and stay true to the best interests "
"of society. These are more than words. — By the powers bestowed upon me by our "
"divine benefactor, they have become a sacred pact, guided by the higher spheres.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71068744-b57b-4489-95ae-5757b20d8e48"
msgid ""
"{n} The captain smiles at you.{/n} \\\"It is 'Shield'. But it's a mistake so "
"common that we have long stopped correcting anyone. We even had to purchase the "
"golden shields which supposedly gave us our name. — Without them, some of our "
"clients refused to believe that we were who we claimed to be! In truth, our name "
"was chosen for a different reason. Gold is the color of our patron Abadar, the God "
"of laws, cities and prosperity. And the shield symbolizes our purpose — to protect "
"civilization and order from chaos and anarchy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc4f9dd1-4640-4694-998c-c985be21812a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Should one of us breach his contractual obligations to an employer or commit "
"any deed that breaks the law, in letter or in spirit, then the heavens themselves "
"will smite him down. He will be cursed, and all the members of his society will "
"immediately sense it – wherever they may be and whatever they may be doing. Our "
"oath demands that we track down their former comrade and bring him to justice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a4f1275-bf5f-4ef5-a23c-4cba9c2cf501"
msgid ""
"\\\"I grew up in Molthune. My town entered a contract with the local temple of "
"Abadar: the taxes on the priests' extensive property were waived, and in exchange "
"they raised the city's orphans. I happened to be one such child.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74ccec27-cbca-4b5d-932a-43ce67116a8b"
msgid "\\\"What's your advice?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f39ef8f-62d4-4170-a57e-b37e1aaa1be5"
msgid ""
"\\\"The barbarians are coming for us anyway, so let our guard benefit from the "
"extra numbers. Let the Golden Shields take up their duties immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e989fb6c-d0c6-4d04-9272-02de5337f210"
msgid ""
"\\\"We shall accept Wigmold's proposal. His magical surveillance system sounds "
"most promising.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d21be324-7967-41f2-a803-f90367ec1a63"
msgid "\\\"I wish to speak with Roham, the leader of the justiciars.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81dbb06f-915d-478f-8cb4-8977e77bbcb7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let us hear what Wigmold has to say about his magical surveillance system.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "efb30fc1-02b8-49ca-a4ee-2079ea2c41bc"
msgid "\\\"I wish to further question Wigmold\\\"."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8bfc11ac-94ca-4346-b653-023c6a626f91"
msgid "\\\"I wish to speak further with Roham.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0df1f7a0-66c5-4846-a494-7968adc4a9eb"
msgid "\\\"Enough. That is all that I needed to know.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "60774ad6-0b30-4d9c-b172-c1b454f95cd5"
msgid "\\\"So why did you leave Druma?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82751b21-9886-4151-9e47-15c89ebbf504"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about the lands that you hail from.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b4bf600-d631-465e-9f2c-14512eaa457c"
msgid "\\\"What exactly is it that you do?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5498607b-f855-4c8c-b958-376e3466f213"
msgid "\\\"How does your surveillance system work?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e5b7c6e-adb9-4939-89d2-df566d1029f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's been trouble. The night patrol caught a barbarian. He was about to "
"poison a well on the outskirts of the capital. Tried to run, got shot. As he died, "
"he swore that the shamans of his tribe would stop at nothing to poison all the "
"food and water in the city.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "282c3231-7295-4385-a3e9-c598a3e3fd08"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Capital is in danger, Your Highness! A night patrol in the outskirts "
"caught a Kellid barbarian trying to poison a well. He was fatally wounded during "
"the arrest. But before he breathed his last, he threatened that their shamans were "
"going to poison all our food and water, and even the air we breathe.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1341a657-64b3-4f81-8928-b0edc078ff99"
msgid ""
"\\\"I got three pieces of news for you: one good, one bad, and the last one good "
"again. The first is that my boys caught a Kellid barbarian trying to poison a well "
"last night. That's pretty good, eh? He still managed to poison the well though...\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "299125e8-e867-4042-bf0f-d3119700434e"
msgid ""
"\\\"We don't know what shamans he spoke of, or when they might strike. We don't "
"even know if we can trust the words of the dying barbarian. We're in a rough spot, "
"but I brought a couple of allies who could help.\\\" {n}Kesten nods in the "
"direction of his companions.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "05b6abc5-4d7c-4516-9806-016df2cd2084"
msgid ""
"\\\"We don't know who they are, how many they are, or where they are… And we need "
"any help we can get. Two of our citizens have already stepped forward to offer "
"plans and resources. The first — Roham Orand, justiciar of Abadar and leader of "
"the Golden Shields. She wants to distribute her people around the city and capture "
"the barbarians as soon as they appear. The other one — Wigmold Smegglyduddn. He "
"has plans for a magical spying system. With his help, we might be able to find out "
"where the enemy is hiding, and strike first.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3c81594d-0834-46a6-9a79-8706de67c892"
msgid ""
"\\\"Naturally, the savage gave us some lip while we questioned him. At one point "
"he even spat his teeth at us, ha ha! But in the end he sang. Apparently, a whole "
"group of Kellid shamans are planning to poison the capital's food and water "
"supplies. This whole thing has got me blazing mad. We knew nothing about this! And "
"it was just dumb luck that we caught this idiot. Who are they? How many are there? "
"– And when are they going to strike? It would have been a mess – and there's no "
"way we'd be able to catch them... However!\\\" {n} The half-orc smiles, baring his "
"fangs.{/n} \\\"Don't forget, the third piece of news is another good one.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a2d58f3-1637-4024-aa21-f50893653f39"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't know what sorcery Wigmold uses. But I do know that if you're looking "
"for a needle in a haystack, it's best to use magic. Too many people live in the "
"capital. There's too many wells, granaries, warehouses. Our guard isn't trained to "
"cover so much ground at once, and besides, we don't have enough guards to do it. "
"Instead, we've taught them to track down the criminals beforehand, and move in to "
"intercept. That makes Wigmold the better option.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7218093-1639-4eca-b775-501b57342a18"
msgid ""
"\\\"I do not trust magic. However, I know that out guard would make better use of "
"a surveillance system. The way we have approached the problems that have arisen "
"over the years – this has taught them specific skills. They know how to move "
"quickly and strike first, to prevent crimes from occurring... but they would fare "
"worse at protecting multiple locations at once, or sealing off every entry and "
"exit from the city. We simply won't have enough people for that. Thus, it's better "
"to chose Wigmold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5de4dc43-c8f6-474b-8327-ba96328cab04"
msgid ""
"\\\"I know our men. We've trained them to work with their muscles and their "
"intuition – but we haven't trained them for patience. They're just not the kind of "
"guys who can stand guard day and night at every gate and crossroads. And we don't "
"even have the manpower for it. So it would be better to let Wigmold cast his magic "
"thing and tell us how to catch the shamans before they strike.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ba08adc-f703-4acc-a477-c7ed300a9275"
msgid "\\\"I'll help Roham and her people settle in.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "354bcfe9-ec32-4ea0-a24d-9b23f63652ac"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you wish, Your Highness. I'll make sure Roham and her team are briefed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9bb1e771-903c-4809-b253-56b00d761d44"
msgid "\\\"Shall be done. We'll see what they're worth…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b18f1450-c01e-4d6e-9d47-471959579ff3"
msgid "{n}Ekun nods with a barely audible sigh.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7517bc6-daa8-4338-8cbb-e4bd4152013d"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you command, Your Highness. We will begin calibrations immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd645cc1-987f-4c91-9b4f-2b56022dbb78"
msgid ""
"\\\"Excellent. Well, no point standing around then. Let's go have a little talk, "
"Wigmold…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "634f6bf9-46db-4b6f-9e69-067f6f20d48d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Magic is good. But our guards cannot use the knowledge that Wigmold's spells "
"would provide. They're not fast enough, not nimble enough. They don't know how to "
"strike first, preemptively. We've rarely ordered them to do so. But they do know "
"how to lock down the city, and guard it day and night, so that no one can pass by "
"unnoticed – which would be even easier with more eyes and swords. I would choose "
"Roham.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cb670b1-b4e5-457f-8137-886dd6a217b5"
msgid ""
"\\\"The strength of our guard does not lie in its ability to track down potential "
"criminals and catch them ahead of time. But our guard can capably cast a net over "
"the whole city and maintain constant control over multiple remote locations. And "
"if the Golden Shields can help us make the net even stronger, and guard all "
"entrances and exits from the city even more thoroughly...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "365402d1-dcb4-4711-88df-4b04930f4f24"
msgid ""
"\\\"Even if Wigmold tells us where to look for the barbarians, even our fastest "
"guards wouldn't be able to intercept them quickly enough. Our boys can block off "
"several streets at a time, and stay on post day and night – and thoroughly pat-"
"down everyone entering and leaving the city... My fat-arsed oafs barely remember "
"how to walk. You think they'll be more effective staring at crystal balls instead "
"of patrolling the streets? Ha! We'll be better off with the Golden Shields.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb7576bf-334c-4f2d-b8bf-4a72525f4af7"
msgid ""
"\\\"The big one is Roham Orand, justiciar of Abadar and captain of the Golden "
"Shields. She guarantees that if her people go on patrol with our guards, they'll "
"pounce on the trouble-makers as soon as they enter the city. And… ahem… that's "
"Wigmold Smegglyduddn. He says he'll install a magical surveillance and prevention "
"system that will allow us to locate and neutralize those barbarians before they "
"can even get close to the city walls.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f0cf49e1-e07c-4e40-9345-346570f1ebc7"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's a couple folks ready and waiting to help us out. You just gotta pick "
"which one gets the job. Meet Roham, a justiciar of Abadar — her band, the Golden "
"Shields, promises to stand guard at every city gate and catch our unwashed friends "
"within a fortnight. And there's... what was his name, damn it... Ah, ha ha, "
"Wigmold. He's ready to set up a magical surveillance system of his own invention "
"in the Capital. With that we'll be able to catch both the barbarians and any other "
"undesirables, ha ha hmm...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "411e7db0-e1d0-4b08-a666-69b53455f20c"
msgid "{n}Roham bows courteously.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc0e7703-a386-4fa0-bbf9-9b7b3837b6d2"
msgid ""
"{n}The captain's face lights up with a barely visible smile.{/n} \\\"Thank you, "
"Your Highness. We will justify your trust in us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99451ff2-dde0-49ac-bbcf-141d72420462"
msgid ""
"\\\"Aha! And there you have it!\\\" {n} The gnome gleams with happiness. It seems "
"like he's barely holding back from sticking his tongue out at Roham.{/n} \\\"An "
"excellent choice, Your Highness! I promise, you will always remember old Wigmold "
"with gratitude!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "909c0282-087c-4c7e-97e2-454241647f9b"
msgid ""
"{n}Wigmold lowers his heavy gaze in a farewell bow. Even his bracelets seem to "
"clink more sadly.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acf212b1-9475-4fb0-bd14-1e1a59673b5c"
msgid "\\\"How may I help?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c54a8298-5c06-4ce9-a102-08007adf454d"
msgid ""
"{n}The aged gnome bows long and deep, as the many bracelets on his wrists chime "
"softly. The expensive cloth and elegant cut of his robe would be the envy of any "
"metropolitan dandy, though few would dare leave the house draped in such bold "
"colors.{/n} \\\"Wigmold Smegglyduddn, the finest magical surveillance system "
"specialist from Druma to Brevoy. At your service!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "578a8ffe-699a-436e-8a3e-6daecd0a80f2"
msgid "\\\"At your service!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44c63bcf-989b-43c9-bbeb-3b655a612c68"
msgid ""
"{n}Wigmold bows deeply, and the hall is once more filled with soft clinking.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "647e353b-d044-4094-b59a-87d9cc2a0944"
msgid ""
"\\\"Life in Druma is most remarkable, but it grows dull quite quickly. The "
"constant struggle for power and gold is wearisome. I felt a lack of spontaneity, "
"of unpredictability, of strong feelings and grand gestures… In other words, all "
"those things that are so abundant in your lands.\\\" {n}For a second the gnome "
"loses himself as he gazes dreamily into the distance.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce3eebc9-6909-4b7a-8911-0dbb05338bf6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness wishes to learn of Druma?\\\" {n}The gnome smirks.{/n} \\\"'Tis "
"a land most striking, for its people worship not the gods, but trade and "
"prosperity. Nearly all the people of Druma follow the Prophesies of Kalistrade — a "
"philosophy that preaches severe abstinence, and professes that the acquisition of "
"wealth is the purpose of life.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b46b1bc-4283-4c41-987f-edef30533f2c"
msgid ""
"\\\"They respect law and order, but never choose sides in the universal battle "
"between good and evil. They follow a strict diet and refuse themselves basic "
"comforts, even though they could afford to drown themselves in luxuries. They "
"maintain ritual purity, only draping themselves in white colors and wearing elbow-"
"length gloves to avoid any physical contact with infidels. It is considered a "
"virtue to never give to charity, and those who acquire wealth despite their "
"superiors' efforts are rewarded.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58de5232-e50c-4508-a922-e2966770e33f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness's interest flatters me, but I'm afraid that I would be ruining "
"myself if I were to surrender the details. It's a trade secret, you see. I can "
"only say that it is my own design, which has allowed me to radically increase the "
"zone of control compared to my competitors' products. While many of the usual "
"charms can capably detect a breach and send out the alarm within one or two "
"buildings, my system is capable of covering several districts... and a whole city "
"if necessary!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5da61230-3436-4a8c-924d-f920f98f5c8a"
msgid ""
"\\\"My enterprise offers a full range of services in security assurance! If you "
"install one of my magical surveillance complexes, you will always know who enters "
"or leaves the contractually determined zone of control, as well as when they enter "
"and leave, and even — for a price — why.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6fb9e021-d65f-42d1-8b8f-420e4a222219"
msgid ""
"\\\"In Druma, my systems were in high demand from both law enforcement, who needed "
"to keep the town hall and prison under constant surveillance, and countless "
"private clients. I've experience working with banks, jewelery stores, art "
"galleries…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1d8cc920-3726-46dc-9429-94983d93cdbb"
msgid "Killed the cultists for their evil ways."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20894009-b202-48e2-b629-0cc945e33cc5"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"You will pay for what you've done!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35736538-f594-4a20-a7c3-65e69420a672"
msgid "Killed the cultists for your personal enjoyment."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "01da189d-7310-417c-b40e-81644bde0705"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"It is my will that you die!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5dcd4106-9425-488e-a363-d57a058f5c78"
msgid "\\\"Who are you? What kind of ritual are you planning to hold here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73bd0545-4d9d-47b3-9e6c-3e86a8c261b0"
msgid "\\\"Why me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1477b3e8-c227-490d-9387-0f1af4c6d0da"
msgid "Refused to participate in the ritual of the Abraxas cultists."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83bba604-5244-4744-9bb3-219cef435503"
msgid "\\\"I'm not going to take part in your disgusting ritual!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "407a3304-119d-4506-84c1-9ba67987b6d6"
msgid "\\\"Who is Abraxas?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e401b09-dd76-4b5e-82fb-c3df12cf6a06"
msgid "Agreed to become a vessel for Abraxas' knowledge."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a0a3797-4aa5-4d04-a28e-4b2807844291"
msgid "\\\"I am ready to become the vessel for the wisdom of Abraxas.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29b94b01-4ad3-404f-a872-dd4ceefc9697"
msgid "\\\"You are guilty of the abduction and death of new-born children!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b61a1ac-19d0-4899-8837-11dd177c14b0"
msgid "\\\"I'm leaving now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "36364e9b-8476-41b8-8396-10c9dae2e935"
msgid "Agreed to become a vessel for Abraxas' knowledge."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71191071-8e29-4e57-9924-17738ff66b17"
msgid "\\\"All right, I will accept the gift of Abraxas.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c75770f-706b-4338-a986-c57476ff03fb"
msgid "Refused to participate in the ritual of the Abraxas cultists."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41bf1e93-e118-4cf2-bf0c-b67d2bc968f3"
msgid "\\\"I'm not going to take part in this filth.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bff17b5e-19d4-4fba-9825-7919e2a24c15"
msgid "\\\"You have finally come, the Named.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90553755-ec7e-4c6a-be65-c24383987ea2"
msgid ""
"{n}The elf looks at you with expectation from under his hood, and speaks almost "
"impatiently.{/n} \\\"We are ready. Command us to begin, and we shall fulfill the "
"will of our master, the Named. The ritual that will bind you to Abraxas may be "
"carried out at any moment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5fbd0da9-3ab8-447f-8688-2e4bd871dfb4"
msgid ""
"\\\"You were chosen by Abraxas himself. The signs showed us the way. Your deeds "
"are proof to any with eyes to see: here is the one who knows no boundaries! Here "
"is the vessel worthy of the forbidden knowledge possessed by the blackest and "
"cruelest of demons. Tales of your glory has reached Abraxas — and he led us here "
"to prepare the ritual and await your coming.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c91b04c-99b0-4abe-97c4-8a88ff50bbb2"
msgid ""
"{n}The elf lowers his head.{/n} \\\"You joke with us, the Named. We are the hand "
"of Abraxas, Master of the Final Incantation and keeper of forbidden knowledge. We "
"are the ones who shall led the way for the Named, who will embody the wisdom of "
"our lord.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a48939f1-5672-4b04-92ef-5775df2958ee"
msgid ""
"\\\"The great lord of the {g|Abyss}Abyss{/g}, more ancient than the world itself. "
"Witness to history, he discovered mysteries long buried under the ashes of ages. "
"His mind stores forbidden knowledge which he is ready to share with his chosen "
"ones – those who have no fear of his gift. And he has chosen you, the Named.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e27b7652-619b-4335-8eda-274a1e62e73e"
msgid ""
"\\\"For such is the will of our lord.\\\" {n}The elf sighs, as if gathering his "
"strength.{/n} \\\"We mustn't waste time: we have prepared for your arrival, o the "
"Named. We are ready. Are you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9bf626f0-8b15-4732-9c40-059b9e1bef98"
msgid ""
"{n}The elf looks up, his voice is trembling with anticipation.{/n} \\\"Then step "
"into the magic circle, the Named, and accept your fate!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08119cdf-7d8d-4ee2-8d1a-9e29bc7b3bd1"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's no soul blacker than yours in all of Avistan. You came here following "
"the trail of innocent blood. You are ready to accept the gift of Abraxas. As soon "
"as we begin reading the spell, step into the circle — and your mind will become a "
"vessel of power unknown to all of Golarion! Abraxas himself will share his wisdom "
"with you and bestow upon you knowledge other mortals can only dream of!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39b261d1-b8ea-41c2-9b41-012059c31a24"
msgid ""
"{n}The elf hisses through his teeth.{/n} \\\"False prophet! We will wash away this "
"insult with your blood!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3a7561d-881d-4b73-bcc0-1dcb971d3999"
msgid ""
"{n}The light in your eyes dims, and your mind is filled with a horrendous torrent "
"of noise, which threatens crack your skull open from the inside. You try to move, "
"but your body refuses to obey. You are bound by another's will. Through the "
"excruciating pain that pulses in your temples, you sense a strange, dark presence."
"{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "494bb54f-266b-4d06-867b-633716c75967"
msgid ""
"\\\"You cannot just turn away from your fate, the Named. Accept your fate – or pay "
"for your deception with blood!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c81bdd2-fcee-4605-995d-348c164a063a"
msgid ""
"{n}The deafening noise begins to fade, and the pain in your temples diminishes. "
"You catch echoes of strange thoughts and knowledge in languages you do not speak, "
"too complex and strange for you to comprehend. At last you feel the farewell touch "
"of the evil being that only a moment ago fully possessed you. The strange mind, "
"having bestowed its gift upon you, leaves you with his final message.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31df1d0b-23c1-4e29-a747-6b777c588168"
msgid "\\\"...kill... them... all...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88c2cdab-28dd-4991-9911-83b3681aa965"
msgid "\\\"Death to the renegade!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea1a76a0-0bf1-400a-af66-20e4ddb48d09"
msgid "\\\"Traitor!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d21bf6a0-6a2f-49cd-8734-8e10f93c522b"
msgid "\\\"{mf|He|She}'s here!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f44351c-0ad2-45ed-9f91-96f7f6726b2a"
msgid "\\\"Look! It's the chosen one!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96813b6d-21fc-4c2f-a4c1-43c8ca8b6fd7"
msgid "\\\"The will of Abraxas will be fulfilled at last!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9263e7d-9f37-4b22-8d0c-1d15705d029f"
msgid "\\\"What brought you here from Nex to the Stolen Lands?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ee3f7a3-6eb5-4e05-a307-28d144d4eb42"
msgid "\\\"Don't be afraid of me. Just tell me why you're here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f62526c0-2e27-4139-98d1-40decdc21728"
msgid "\\\"I don't want to waste my time on you. Guards, take him away!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a41fbf7-3431-4647-a60e-13370162f353"
msgid "\\\"What will I gain by building this vault?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "565b488a-5389-4418-b8e9-a71a5776d0f0"
msgid "\\\"You have my consent. Tell your brothers that I will need their help.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca5e185d-cf6e-4a6d-a0dd-563ebaeff660"
msgid ""
"\\\"The dark knowledge placed in my head will pass into eternity along with me. "
"Take your blueprints and go home.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f37cd06a-0d4a-4f47-a3b2-f4a27cdae498"
msgid "\\\"Why do you think I need any help?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a2069ddb-f702-42e8-b483-efcd50f7afb1"
msgid ""
"{n}This dark-skinned, wily halfling is quite different from his kin who you've met "
"in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. He's constantly looking around, even "
"beneath his feet, and rubbing his palms together as if the action is about to "
"commence.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3657c0bb-c071-402b-9ed3-bfc838d1f8ab"
msgid ""
"{n}The halfling dares to look up at you — and you see servile admiration in his "
"eyes.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Illustrious Grace|Your Illustrious Grace|Your Resplendent "
"Highness|Your Resplendent Highness}, what... what an honor to meet you in person!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eaeff5d9-af3e-4809-9b2f-cc46a3246b5c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have just arrived from Quantium, the capital of faraway Nex. I am sure you "
"have heard of this land... Ah, but of course you know all about the place where "
"they store... where they cherish – as the apple of their eye...\\\" {n}The "
"halfling becomes confused and licks his slips nervously.{/n} \\\"Forgive me... my "
"words fail me. In your presence I feel as a wretched worm, unworthy of even your "
"casual glance!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2488bce-2902-489f-857d-1b8de228ca18"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have arrived as a messenger from a small group of wizards and wise men, who "
"have devoted themselves to the search for greatness and might. Our patron is the "
"great demon lord Abraxas, Master of the Final Incantation. For many years we "
"believed that the largest collection of forbidden books and ancient sources of "
"knowledge was stored in the secret library in Quantium... but then we caught news "
"of the Named.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c771d0c3-716f-4feb-9eae-64b7412254fd"
msgid ""
"{n}The halfling takes a deep breath.{/n} \\\"You are not only great, but merciful, "
"{mf|Your Illustrious Grace|Your Illustrious Grace|Your Resplendent Highness|Your "
"Resplendent Highness}. Lucky are those who you command!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52fb9322-c6a0-4197-b640-dfaf52d5789b"
msgid ""
"{n}The halfling drops to his knees and prostrates himself before you.{/n} \\\"I "
"beg you, just a moment of your time! Give this poor soul a chance to perform a "
"sacred duty, which I owe to my brothers in faith!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29d0d056-f870-4990-baf6-7eeacb2e5170"
msgid ""
"\\\"The messengers of Abraxas informed us that a ruler of a faraway land had "
"become the keeper of knowledge, bestowed upon {mf|him|her} by the Master of the "
"Final Incantation himself. We know that your mind has become a vessel, but "
"understanding all that is stored within it – this would require ciphers... and the "
"will of Abraxas...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5a3ee9b-d05e-49a9-8167-9320fa8785fd"
msgid ""
"\\\"I was sent to propose to you...\\\" {n}The halfling pulls out a roll of "
"leather.{/n} \\\"These are the blueprints of a vault, similar to the one in "
"Quantium. Its special chambers are designed to explore the forbidden... and summon "
"those who can help decode signs and symbols which our limited mind has no power "
"over. The servants of Abraxas are cruel, but they open doors to places which the "
"weak of spirit and mind cannot reach.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b7db5c2-af22-431b-9184-042019d7decc"
msgid ""
"\\\"We... that is, you will have a chance to comprehend the essence of the gift "
"that was bestowed upon you by Abraxas. The demon lord selected you for a reason: "
"your very being is similar to his own. The only thing that remains is to extract "
"his knowledge... line by line, image by image... and comprehend what has been "
"hidden from mortal eyes for ages! Just imagine the power that awaits you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "841e487a-b6b0-44da-a509-cfb6a89d0047"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, I assure you, {mf|Your Illustrious Grace|Your Illustrious Grace| Your "
"Resplendent Highness|Your Resplendent Highness}! Each of us will deem it a great "
"honor to serve the Named in this matter! I will give the blueprints to your "
"advisors, and set off immediately to Quantium with the good news.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a3eb903-4d79-480f-9b61-d8fd9306cc6e"
msgid ""
"\\\"But how... How?! If you decline, no one... no one will be able to unseal this "
"box of ancient mysteries!\\\" {n}The halfling is almost crying.{/n} \\\"You will "
"thwart so much effort... So many deaths – all in vain!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bba0e4b-67e0-4303-b9a8-7a2388551339"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will depart from your lands... but I will leave you the blueprints. Perhaps "
"one day, the thirst for knowledge will possess you once more. — As it did when you "
"first agreed to become a vessel for the mysteries of Abraxas. I will pray for this "
"day to arrive as soon as possible, and will be the first to come to your call!\\"
"\" {n}The halfling bows deeply and takes a few steps back.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62fc004e-045e-44e6-9780-8a07f0b68009"
msgid ""
"\\\"I look forward to the moment when the vault is completed and ready to summon "
"demons. We will do everything in our power to solve the mysteries stored in your "
"head!\\\" {n}The halfling bows deeply and takes a few steps back.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5b044bc-9ac2-4df0-9aaf-c22cd0fd16a0"
msgid ""
"\\\"No offense was intended, {mf|Your Illustrious Grace|Your Illustrious Grace|"
"Your Resplendent Highness|Your Resplendent Highness}... but it will take years of "
"diligent work to understand the essence of Abraxas' knowledge. Such is its nature. "
"– And I mean knowledge laid out on paper, not hidden inside someone's head!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e044799c-6cfe-4bae-9bd8-55e2a084edd5"
msgid ""
"\\\"You won't be able to make full use of the gift you've received the Master of "
"the Final Incantation – until you comprehend the very essence of this forbidden "
"knowledge. You could greatly benefit from us — for we have devoted all our lives "
"to the secrets of the magical sciences. You will require servants of Abraxas — "
"demons capable of lifting the veil in return for sacrifice. And it will take you "
"many years to fully embrace the powers that have been bestowed upon you. You are "
"yet far from the heights of your powers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7b4ab1d9-008e-4749-8518-2c9be61a5fe3"
msgid "\\\"Where are you from, Jase?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe4568ec-e9a8-4ca9-ba4d-307efd5f4b49"
msgid "\\\"What good are shrines if we already have pubs and taverns?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b8916e65-f03c-4e5f-be52-fb8933cdd470"
msgid "\\\"Why do you propose this to me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a194120f-f222-4f32-b12e-f8397578b4e7"
msgid "Refused to build shrines to Desna on grounds of greed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6526539b-84c4-4e76-aba0-59fd01406719"
msgid "\\\"I've no wish to waste money on such nonsense.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aae8d1cc-9f17-4b26-91e9-c33a9046c7fd"
msgid "Allowed the building of shrines to Desna."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f7b95c5-bd9a-42b8-8ef0-a96ae1e6db8e"
msgid "\\\"Building shrines is a fine idea! Of course I will help you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61a8167b-e0c4-4b9e-8a3d-1852873da234"
msgid ""
"Allowed the building of shrines to Desna – on the condition that their visitors "
"abiding by the law."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b3fe176a-2855-4308-bd5e-f1f4e7486a87"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will help to build these shrines, but only if those they welcome will abide "
"by my laws.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "098975f1-ca92-4e43-a290-1fad9d89eafa"
msgid "Remained indifferent to the ideas of Desna cleric's."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "273b428f-ebee-4ee0-89c6-3e19699d3a14"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've no wish to interfere in Desna's matters. I'm sorry but I will not help "
"you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b5cfb1ed-02dd-423a-a8cf-9debec35a25b"
msgid ""
"{n}A middle-aged halfling woman in tattered traveling clothes bows before you.{/n} "
"\\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! Thank you "
"for agreeing to see and hear me out!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c552cc25-9022-477f-8608-ea9d4a6816ac"
msgid ""
"\\\"My name is Jase. I am a priestess of {g|Desna}Desna{/g}, goddess of travelers "
"and luck, who accompanies us on our journeys. The fame of your lands has called me "
"to your door – with a request.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f227e370-a3d8-470a-8553-5437ee87305e"
msgid ""
"{n}Jase folds her arms across her chest.{/n} \\\"{g|Desna}Desna{/g} protects those "
"who spend their night out in the open. Please help me and my associates create "
"shelters for such travelers – roadside shrines to the goddess! It will not take "
"much, but the hundreds of travelers who pass through your lands will thank you in "
"their prayers!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd8820bb-18a3-48ef-a616-5851ee5d344d"
msgid ""
"{n}Jase shakes her head.{/n} \\\"And what if the seeker has no coin? Or the owner "
"refused him entry because he had no means to wash? No, a shrine of {g|Desna}Desna{/"
"g} is more than just a hotel. It's a place where every tramp is welcome, for the "
"mistress of the shrine makes no distinction between rich and poor!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5b5631f-9aa8-4eae-94d9-ccd02e8a1dc3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Making a shrine is easy, of course. — We'll build an altar, pull out some "
"stumps, clear the area — and we're done! But the unseen presence of {g|Desna}"
"Desna{/g} will remain, protecting every corner of your lands. None will dare "
"attack anyone sleeping in the shade of such a shrine!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d1cf309-a437-482e-80c4-049370bcc80f"
msgid ""
"{n}Jase looks at you in surprise.{/n} \\\"Because everyone in these lands knows "
"you are a good {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}! One who will protect every soul, "
"and who will not simply leave the poor and sick to fight their fates alone! Your "
"subjects follow your example, and are likewise kind and hospitable. I have no "
"doubt that {g|Desna}Desna{/g} loves you — and all those who travel in your lands!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0369c7ef-d8b3-4dd8-bf70-f5bd41ab28dc"
msgid ""
"{n}Jase can't help but clap her hands joyfully.{/n} \\\"I knew it! I knew you "
"would agree! May {g|Desna}Desna{/g} keep you and your loved ones safe!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2392473-4751-49e3-9915-b2400875af03"
msgid ""
"\\\"My companions and I will await your news. When you are ready, we'll begin "
"right away. You'll have shrines in all every corner of your state!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "472038df-0298-4cfe-9392-12e1837cd026"
msgid ""
"{n}Jase nods seriously.{/n} \\\"The road tempts all kinds of travelers. But are a "
"few lost sheep reason to deny care and protection to everyone? I do share your "
"hope that evil-doers will steer clear of these lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a200d12f-3b42-401f-a2d7-6e93b91371e7"
msgid ""
"{n}Jase sighs.{/n} \\\"Well then I won't waste any more of your time, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Farewell!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a749755c-2ee9-4553-a812-c1e29f028c4e"
msgid ""
"\\\"From far away, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. There "
"was once a time that I, like my ancestors, served a noble family in {g|Cheliax}"
"Cheliax{/g}. But, praise {g|Desna}Desna{/g}, I escaped, and was picked up by a "
"caravan of {g|Varisia}Varisians{/g}. Ever since then, fate has led me along many "
"roads in many lands — both bad and glorious ones. And truth be told, I've no wish "
"to recollect my 'homeland'.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "255c8a5e-3fa5-4a4c-b32b-20a9bd0f2df3"
msgid "\\\"Who are you and what caravan is this?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d832e6d-1f88-4c95-84e3-09ecfc9c879b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've no need of dirty tramps in my {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}. Get out!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1943e40f-f1d0-46ed-98f2-127943ea0615"
msgid "Drove the Varisian traveling caravan from the Stolen lands."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "540a859f-ed47-4b1e-b688-faee3f1c5c51"
msgid ""
"\\\"It doesn't matter what I thought. Your kind only brings trouble. Get out of my "
"lands!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12ff17b0-8482-4669-a632-5780b33661e5"
msgid "\\\"You're right. Forgive me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b8c7efd9-8b79-4dc0-96bf-4e2aed2df48b"
msgid "Killed everyone in the Varisian traveling caravan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0dd2567d-2def-4899-ac68-2c468cf7631c"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"Death to thieves and vagabonds!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1af20e88-b121-49ac-b770-e4a036ff9d10"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm looking for a thief who robbed a few of my subjects. The evidence says "
"he's one of yours.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c48e270-67f5-4cf6-8819-36b7bd142b79"
msgid "\\\"Don't mess with me, Zandu. That usually ends badly.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ca1d364-7e1b-4a1d-ab21-d1a1e9607d6c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Listen, I have no wish to be your enemy. But one of your companions stole "
"something, and is now hiding in your camp!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a3cbe97-32af-41a4-ad0b-157610e003da"
msgid "Killed everyone in the Varisian traveling caravan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73df73f5-a770-47b9-b552-b94f448b7292"
msgid ""
"[Attack] \\\"If I'm not going to get any answers — then I'll just kill you all!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27846597-0182-44fb-9ef0-5578c6072f50"
msgid "\\\"Fine, don't tell me if you don't want to.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6cfe594f-5013-49d7-aa05-7286a181e1e8"
msgid "Allowed the Varisians to deal with the thief themselves."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d3cec2a-3190-4e39-bb29-296b428950c1"
msgid "\\\"Fine. Deal with your black sheep as you see fit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5de92187-17a7-4126-add1-7bcc3d9df3c3"
msgid "Put the thief on trial."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9dbdcd2-00bc-4892-a348-566cb8c14e64"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have no reason to trust you. Tell me where this hiding place is. Lorre will "
"be given a fair trial.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f69cfac-0c16-4f50-bcb0-63b81d3b3fd8"
msgid "\\\"Your family includes elves and halflings?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79a51cec-6bcc-4c1b-8ad6-f1aec09b04d7"
msgid "\\\"So you're traveling... and where have you been?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "567b679a-6dae-481b-977d-8fc98fe91a28"
msgid "\\\"Numeria is not the most hospitable place, is it?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "849a33dd-a92b-4090-ba55-6bdeb4640587"
msgid "\\\"What the hell did you do in Cheliax?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89e6c8a6-2eed-4e01-91f5-d29cf6d136b9"
msgid "\\\"Why did the Starlings leave their homeland of Varisia?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b433b8f-3a52-4a07-bf8e-2765b0b09588"
msgid "\\\"Enough about your travels.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9b6f15f-52ea-4937-bade-187eef3f3bda"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wait... so the Starlings are the same caravan who picked up Jase when she "
"escaped?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3de04bff-3ee6-4430-816f-4085822395b4"
msgid "\\\"You have interesting tattoos...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f199d827-29fb-4b45-9a5e-9b99cb4acbd5"
msgid "\\\"I must go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08990a6f-76dd-4e71-b62a-669c4d558910"
msgid ""
"{n}A dark-haired, dark-skinned {g|Varisia}Varisian{/g} stands before you, wearing "
"an expensive but rather road-worn doublet, a leather belt, and dusty baggy pants. "
"Tattoos that look like cuneiform writing wander up the man's neck and onto his "
"cheeks. The Varisian is holding a deck of cards, springing them from one hand to "
"the other with a faint rustling sound.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27c6ea32-dbe3-41cb-be25-4b552513893f"
msgid ""
"{n}The stranger looks at you askance, squinting and sneering with a corner of his "
"mouth.{/n} \\\"Look who we have here! My regards, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}, join our circle! Call me Zandu Starling.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62e3589c-6974-4d7d-8f8c-f6776fc83b35"
msgid ""
"{n}Zandu's brows fly up.{/n} \\\"Really? Then why did you build shrines of our "
"patroness along all your roads? You hoped they would bring travelers with deep "
"pockets?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fd80b8c9-3376-403e-8420-f56676789e3a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ha, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, if you only knew "
"what I have heard in my travels, you would not apologize for this small matter. "
"Consider it forgotten.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c3eb396-1889-40e6-ab6d-5476d3327a05"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why should I want to remain? To quarrel with the likes of you? I've no "
"interest in this. — Honest people are welcome in many places. Hey, Starlings! "
"We're leaving!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf0003b0-2d62-49f8-96d7-49207f6550bd"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have... we have a little brother. His name is Lorre. A halfling. He came to "
"us six months ago. He's a smart fellow, but willful. He's good with his hands, and "
"thinks fast. But he decided to put his talents to ill use. We caught him stealing "
"back in {g|Galt}Galt{/g} — and almost lost our heads because of the little rat!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49513074-68bf-4f28-ba24-d485c82c1e61"
msgid ""
"{n}Zandu examines you with his eyes.{/n} \\\"So, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}. We're nomads, so it's all right to blame all the evil in "
"your lands on us?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b090771f-2297-46b2-a4cb-ff300472eb15"
msgid ""
"{n}The man's glance becomes heavy.{/n} \\\"Let the test begin then, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Perhaps this time {g|Desna}Desna{/g} will "
"smile upon someone other than you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1269f302-221a-42d7-a8a8-4c4d1a4979d9"
msgid "{n}Zandu gives you a long look and then sighs sadly.{/n} \\\"Fine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f458409-48be-4f5e-80c2-d38e167d6594"
msgid "{n}Zandu starts whistling carelessly, looking at the cards in his hands.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69af8982-2a55-45cb-ae0a-bad7f3f5df9a"
msgid ""
"{n}Zandu casts a glance at the other members of the caravan.{/n} \\\"So be it, {mf|"
"Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, you win. Just don't harm the "
"others, they have nothing to do with it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "36c82945-3065-4090-a865-d844d4c1b4c9"
msgid "{n}Zandu turns away, but you notice a smug smile on his face.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d95c33b9-463f-4fd7-9083-d164794599e0"
msgid ""
"\\\"I told him last time: we Starlings don't do such things. We may not have much "
"respect the law, but we live by our consciences. Lorre just nodded, like he was "
"agreeing. But your presence here means he's up to his old tricks. That must be why "
"I haven't seen him around lately! I'm sorry I didn't tell you right away — I was "
"hoping I was wrong to suspect him. But truth be told, none of ours would do these "
"things. And I'm not his mother to cover for him his whole life!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dbfffbba-ab96-4fb7-a660-8548ab76738d"
msgid ""
"{n}Zandu stands up straight.{/n} \\\"Listen, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}. I know where he might have a hiding place. — He hinted at "
"such a place but I pretended I didn't understand. But it's... our business. Family "
"business. Don't send your soldiers after Lorre. The Starlings will deal with him, "
"and we'll return what he stole. I give you my word — there won't be any more "
"thefts here. The Starlings will track down rotten rascal ourselves!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed2ce62f-5b78-4b3f-bd19-0e3c72a53f3c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, {mf|Baron|Baroness|King|Queen} {name}. I still hope Lorre can be "
"reformed. He is a good lad. He just got some bad ideas about easy money when he "
"was a kid.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da370ea4-c064-4d3e-84ba-e52a8e0f02cb"
msgid ""
"{n}Zandu frowns.{/n} \\\"You don't trust me? Or the Starlings? Or anyone who's not "
"to your liking? Too bad you tar everyone with the same brush, {mf|Your Grace|Your "
"Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}... Lorre might have made a mistake, but it "
"seems you're treating others just as poorly.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7cc3b50a-eb90-4187-abad-4596d987acbf"
msgid ""
"\\\"One's family is not just the ones you share blood with. Yes, I have sisters "
"and brothers, but Starling recruits are not kin by parentage, but by spirit and "
"conscience. Every one of our caravan is as good as family. And if someone has "
"pointy ears or hairy feet — why should I care?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d9a62613-58e2-432e-a2be-14f20c51e0c1"
msgid ""
"{n}The man runs his finger along the lines on his neck.{/n} \\\"Yes... In case you "
"don't know, it's a hereditary trait. Some {g|Varisia}Varisians{/g} have tattoos "
"even in birth. No one knows why. My mother told me that I was born with only small "
"streaks on my skin. And now look – I am covered in wisdom that no one has yet been "
"able to decipher.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "414f1014-9b71-4b97-8067-cb4d702af1de"
msgid ""
"\\\"And you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness} – you really "
"are just like the people say. You're not torturing people for no good reason, and "
"leave them free to live by their wits. Who would ever guess I'd say this, but I "
"like this {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2158af8a-cc8b-44e8-a79b-dd15fc567376"
msgid ""
"{n}Zandu lets out a brief laugh.{/n} \\\"It's easier to say where we haven't been. "
"From {g|Cheliax}Cheliax{/g} to {g|Numeria}Numeria{/g}, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}. We've walked all of {g|Avistan}Avistan{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a47d0b36-4044-4d59-9a20-054ccb5ccb2b"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you say.\\\" {n}Zandu throws his cards skillfully into the air and catches "
"them with one smooth movement.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f546e46-f07f-45de-a5c7-72a92bb2a041"
msgid ""
"{n}Zandu wrinkles his nose.{/n} \\\"Truth be told, it was not what, but whom. You "
"see, the Starlings stand for freedom. So sometimes we visit the lands where this "
"freedom is being trampled. We pick up fugitive slaves, and when we can, we get "
"down to business and free someone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e7e0596-cdbf-48ef-b683-12df55ce72de"
msgid ""
"\\\"We walked all the roads there many times, and eventually became bored. And so "
"we decided to look farther afield, to see what's going on out in the world... and "
"we got carried away.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9321240e-80ce-4805-94f6-34202bcfe3c3"
msgid ""
"\\\"You are right about that.\\\" {n}The man scratches the back of his head.{/n} \\"
"\"I've been to many places, seen many things... but I saw such things in {g|"
"Numeria}Numeria{/g} as cannot be believed. The Starlings have no business there.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94daa644-2d98-4b9b-8dc4-5dc82c08f9b2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Are you talking about my family?\\\" {n}Zandu nods at the others.{/n} \\\"We "
"are the Starlings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. We are "
"from {g|Varisia}Varisia{/g}. We live on the road, traveling the world. We heard "
"that life here is easy, so we decided to come see.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "160bcf14-ca94-4f67-b8f9-323a42af6d96"
msgid ""
"\\\"Lorre spoke of a ravine where the river is shallow. Send your dogs there. "
"Meanwhile I will prepare to leave – before you begin to hunt any of my other "
"people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "976c5420-7cc0-4519-9aa8-0d4585014a31"
msgid ""
"{n}Zandu salutes you jauntily.{/n} \\\"May {g|Desna}Desna{/g} keep you safe, {mf|"
"Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! And thank you for not keeping "
"your distance! With such a {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen} I could even start to "
"believe in law and order! And don't worry about scoundrels like Lorre: we road "
"people keep a watchful eye on our brothers!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4260709c-949d-4e6d-bbd7-ae9b42c056a5"
msgid ""
"{n}Zandu nods, pleased.{/n} \\\"That's right! The poor thing had it tough on the "
"run – with shackles on her feet! But we nursed her back to health. And so she "
"turned to {g|Desna}Desna{/g}. — She believes it was the goddess who sent us to her!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bb2e98a3-5f19-4efe-858e-c6f77834548d"
msgid "\\\"Who was your son? Did he have any enemies?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e00ee62e-fad4-456a-987a-de3316a44ae5"
msgid "\\\"How did your son die?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b09d02ec-ae7b-4978-8a40-8ee738009a1c"
msgid "\\\"What mysterious deaths are you talking about?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e74041a5-c7a6-4f5d-93ff-6a9955d708bc"
msgid "Promised to investigate the suspicious death personally."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1d220cb9-3a1d-4b30-a5ad-f91557ed09f8"
msgid "\\\"I will try to get to the bottom of this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b99147e-ae7c-47ca-b84a-388fab743126"
msgid "Let the guards perform their duties."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e55fba50-5061-4502-b5ee-8367bda4df03"
msgid "\\\"I'll leave the guards to their duty.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a4db9c5-e11b-43d6-8425-ac78bc49dd24"
msgid "Threw the Alnavi family in prison for trying to flee the country."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62715a58-2889-4f3e-834d-1d2f1023f5dc"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're not going anywhere. Guards! Place this witch and her kin in chains!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e91e8370-07a5-45a2-9691-56a2e894ee72"
msgid ""
"{n}The woman standing before you isn't young. Her irreproachable poise and velvet "
"attire attest to her wealth and nobility. But the creases on her face bear witness "
"to a secret grief.{/n} \\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. Let me introduce myself. I am Jaronna Al'navi, head of the Al'navi "
"family.\\\" {n}She sighs deeply.{/n} \\\"But my name is of no importance. My "
"family and I are to leave your domain today.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e6edf005-7ecb-484a-aa67-eea68e52a34e"
msgid ""
"{n}The woman eyes you solemnly, but without affront.{/n} \\\"My son mysteriously "
"died a week ago. His body was examined; the death appeared to be natural. But it's "
"obvious to any reasonable person that a man in his prime can't just drop dead.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dda8b582-2c52-42ef-95e3-e931ece8b509"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your subjects have failed to show me mercy or understanding. Now I fear that "
"such 'sudden death' may find my other relatives as well. – Especially now that "
"mysterious and inexplicable deaths are growing more common in your lands. My "
"departure is a settled matter, but I still believe in law and justice. Perhaps now "
"you may choose to step in and protect those who are relying on you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "653e9fd0-cefc-4903-a318-f4093b98c701"
msgid ""
"\\\"My son was a lawyer. He promoted various interests and handled the affairs of "
"several merchants. He could hardly practice his profession without making some "
"enemies. However, I'm not sure I could point to anyone in particular.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6642d1e5-0286-4a57-8210-aff92b00fb95"
msgid ""
"\\\"During a hunt, surrounded by friends. They say they found my poor son in the "
"morning. His body had was already in rigor, and his face... his face was frozen in "
"the last expression he had – terror. There wasn't a single mark on his body, and "
"his food and wine had been shared with the others.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2dccc741-ee47-472b-a2d9-3d8e5fb7bd1d"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaronna purses her lips.{/n} \\\"There's no containing gossip, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Over the past few weeks, many fine ladies "
"and gentlemen have died under mysterious circumstances.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77fa2b1d-70af-4e54-89a3-6373c5e2bd0b"
msgid ""
"\\\"You... Filthy tyrant! I should never have sought justice from you! I curse you!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35feeac4-2b23-41b6-8993-d7271dc5752d"
msgid ""
"\\\"As you wish. But from now on I will put my life in the hands of more competent "
"law enforcers than yours. Farewell, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee1d9100-2498-4cbf-add1-1308c46a5189"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaronna's expression softens.{/n} \\\"I was hoping to see justice done after I "
"spoke with you. Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. "
"May {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} be with you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f118e18-c1de-43cd-bd6e-d538159b638b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The guards declared that all cases were but mishaps. I find it quite "
"suspicious that experienced riders fall from their horses and break their necks, "
"or young beauties die from minor cuts they get on a promenade.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8d7f7f1-d7a3-4850-8eb2-88a195c694cd"
msgid "\\\"Who are you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5bae2b19-e650-4f94-8a5a-87e102821bee"
msgid ""
"\\\"You won't confuse me with your shallow courtesy, Invri. I'm looking for "
"murderers – and I believe I've just found one.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "348ddc83-6f8c-4379-a81a-71c7e78e0a2a"
msgid "Destroyed a band of rogue Calistrians on the spot."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4af6e376-66f7-43ad-8641-e4c23bc81aed"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"I've got nothing to discuss with a bunch of thugs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "795eb4f3-aa88-4df8-8e13-012a95ba8fcf"
msgid "\\\"What are you doing in my domain?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99d4ff52-24f1-48b3-b403-19f21a4c1942"
msgid ""
"\\\"Given your 'craft', I'd expect you to be worshipping Norgorber, not Calistria."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6ff6505-3881-4941-81b0-0ccd343ef5b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"The guards in charge of the investigation, and even the priests, failed to "
"identify them as murders at first.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e5811c66-562b-4f13-8118-5aafe4453d6f"
msgid "Convinced the Calistrians to leave peacefully."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a445207-2083-45a9-b109-57164c029c19"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't need any new deaths, you included. Leave my lands immediately, and I "
"will let you go in peace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ca21c50-a7d3-4066-ad71-59b15ed73a67"
msgid "Struck a deal with the Calistrian hunters."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6e616a9-de4b-4d4c-b6f2-e7434f7e06b0"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know what... Stay in my lands, do your jobs, and I'll see to it that "
"you're left alone. It will cost you seventy percent of your profit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f1826c3-d17c-477c-9f0f-abe9b0415bd8"
msgid "Killed the Calistrian hunters on the spot."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94f520e7-5883-4caf-bf11-16ea0cf5648d"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"I will rid the world of you and your vile 'religion'!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "03600dc2-2bfd-45ad-af0d-681265d4df04"
msgid "Tried to arrest the Calistrian hunters."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a12f19f-ec5c-454f-af24-872a8dce6713"
msgid "\\\"You committed a crime you must be punished. Drop your weapons.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79400e5d-4d0d-45ad-a28a-5ffa55335369"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Calistria}Calistrian{/g} hunters, killing for revenge? Is this how you make "
"sacrifices to your goddess?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b314e3c6-3561-48a6-8421-a4d536e27e33"
msgid ""
"{n}A tall and well-built half-elf with a scar under his left eye is watching you "
"with great interest.{/n} \\\"What a surprise. The {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} "
"{mf|him|her}self! That's someone you'd never expect to meet you in the middle of "
"nowhere...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a8579bf-223a-4161-b522-99329641291b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Allow me to introduce myself, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. My name is Invri.\\\" {n}The half-elf bows to you, touching his weapon "
"and keeping his eyes fixed on you.{/n} \\\"I'm suspect I already know the answer, "
"but still: to what do I owe the pleasure?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8af839e1-d164-458d-af0c-8955a7770503"
msgid ""
"\\\"Allow me to introduce my comrades by the campfire. They are followers of the "
"goddess who respects freedom and pleasure, free from rules and hypocrisy, from "
"excessive regulations and outdated attitudes. I'm sure you know who I'm talking "
"about. We are the {g|Calistria}Calistrian{/g} hunters, the favoured of the Savored "
"Sting.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2048b964-7bb2-4a42-99fc-e0bb101f90e3"
msgid ""
"{n}Invri lifts his hand in a conciliatory gesture.{/n} \\\"Allow me, if you "
"please, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. We are still "
"talking, not fighting – which means we might yet find a common language. Clearly, "
"we've gotten off on the wrong foot.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52673675-a305-44b9-b0c1-69447080a108"
msgid ""
"{n}Invri lets out a disappointed groan.{/n} \\\"I expected better of you, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}.\\\" {n}The half-elf draws his "
"weapon in one smooth and swift motion.{/n} \\\"Oh Savored Sting, accept this "
"offering!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e491de7b-14f4-4c87-80bf-51241edf8a6a"
msgid ""
"\\\"We are here for a reason, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. I've heard much about your country's morals... so I thought the likes "
"of us might find shelter here – and some work to do. Very well-paid work.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27378d37-a0bc-4379-99c2-6642636fd8ca"
msgid ""
"{n}Invri squints one eye.{/n} \\\"You clearly know what you're doing, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Bargaining with you is not just "
"risky, it's plain dangerous. Very well, we'll do it your way."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "877b00b9-85a2-40bd-8ff5-9676822a8516"
msgid ""
"{n}Invri tut-tuts.{/n} \\\"No, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. Religious ecstasy is one thing, but I'm also fond of material things. "
"Equal shares is only fair.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0560db3f-9967-45d3-ad2b-a0db6cd05a7f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let's discuss something else. You're a rational ruler, so you must refrain "
"from openly mingling with assassins. That's your business, it concerns me not. "
"Just be sure to call off your watchdogs when we ask. Your guards are not very "
"clever, but they're persistent. Sooner or later, they will hunt us down and drive "
"us out. That is when I'll remind you of our deal. I'll be relying on your "
"assistance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3287f299-693a-4255-8dca-11312dc1cc2b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well! If we're done here...\\\" {n}Invri makes another bow.{/n} \\\"It's time "
"for us to go. We may have become friends today, but let's remain distant friends "
"for now. You know what they say, separation makes the heart grow fonder.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5d7e97b-8247-46c4-96ff-c4c9289a4388"
msgid ""
"\\\"But like any ruler, you can't do without your law enforcers. These dumb "
"officers are the reason we stay away off the streets during the day.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06014d16-35d2-4302-947e-2d6d35f118c3"
msgid ""
"\\\"The narrow-minded might think us mercenaries, killers, thugs... but believe "
"me, we're far from ordinary criminals. We're paid for our work, much like "
"executioners carrying out sentences. We are, so to speak, wish-fulfillment agents."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f0c67f0-ea9e-401a-905b-0243c48d4bef"
msgid ""
"{n}Invri winces.{/n} \\\"Not at all, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. Our delightful and gracious goddess couldn't be compared to that moody "
"loner. {g|Calistria}Calistria{/g} gives pleasure in exchange for carrying out "
"retribution. Is that not a pure and noble cause?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e48807d4-edfa-49f2-8987-4f5230a48ac9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I admit, I wasn't planning on getting to know you any better. But as it turns "
"out... well, I underestimated you. So, you've found us. What are you going to do "
"now?\\\" {n}Invri's smile is polite and almost gentle, but he keeps his relaxed "
"hand on the hilt of his blade.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e240095c-c891-43ce-9e80-257f4a39c786"
msgid ""
"\\\"Is that a compliment? Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}! I confess we do like to think of ourselves as artists. But if you "
"expect me to reveal our secrets...\\\" {n}Invri shakes his head and smiles.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8265a0a7-21b2-4708-b304-2dcb50fed605"
msgid ""
"{n}Invri keeps watching you for a while. Then he makes a decision, sighs and "
"removes his hand from his weapon.{/n} \\\"Such a shame, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}. You seemed so... promising. At least you didn't "
"begin our conversation by swinging your weapon. And now I'll take my leave.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e01c48aa-c676-4b1a-927d-609b7b62bccb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not exactly, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. But since "
"you asked...\\\" {n}Invri takes a deep breath.{/n} \\\"My goddess favors those who "
"embrace passion, whether spiritual or intimate. It is common for the narrow-minded "
"to reduce it to sexual pleasure... but {g|Calistria}Calistria{/g} is mistress of "
"all manner of passions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2924c548-2838-4aa7-a4e4-70794928448c"
msgid ""
"{n}Invri slides a finger across his lips.{/n} \\\"Tell me, what can compare to the "
"feeling when an abuser is given their due? When someone who has crossed you lies "
"choking on their own blood? The blood hammers in your temples, your heart bursts "
"from your chest, a cry of joy escapes your lips...\\\" {n}The half-elf bites his "
"lip passionately.{/n} \\\"If you've never allowed yourself to take revenge... then "
"you simply don't know true joy and divine rapture. We bring our... clients a taste "
"of this joy, and they entrust us with their vengeance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0264179-46f8-4262-a248-b4e366f43eaa"
msgid "\\\"What's going on here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ce3a18d-e4f7-447c-b8bf-9af353781d0b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I would recognize that armor anywhere. What is a hellknight doing in my lands?"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fbcb33d6-a3b3-4d23-8f30-a5e2e5138f15"
msgid "\\\"Why did you attack this knight?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa115b15-82f1-426b-a04d-b3b081982cd4"
msgid "\\\"Stranger, identify yourself!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2b4de44-0cdf-4cb1-9454-5dd28c3ebacf"
msgid ""
"[Attack the peasants] \\\"You broke the law by attacking this knight. The sentence "
"is death!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7eaf255f-c1bd-4160-b098-a7148d5e15ff"
msgid ""
"[Attack the hellknight] \\\"Fellows, let's show this hellknight how we handle his "
"filth in the Stolen Lands!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76d36ec3-e8a2-4e5e-af95-62ec67187776"
msgid "\\\"I have no wish to interfere. Deal with this yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c37b0fd3-5cda-44e5-b94a-af2b0d39e9db"
msgid ""
"{n}One of the peasants, who is armed with a weapon, jumps up in alarm as you "
"approach.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b475b258-1071-4f87-b1bd-cf40eb62f82b"
msgid ""
"{n}You look upon knight in pitch black armor, a monstrous snarling snout "
"emblazoned on his breastplate. He doesn't turn to you — all his attention is taken "
"by multiple adversaries. Nonetheless, you hear a muffled voice from under the "
"visor.{/n} \\\"Praise {g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g}! {mf|Baron|Baroness|King|Queen} "
"{name}, I presume? My regards. Please accept my apologies for not greeting you as "
"the etiquette requires. I'm a little... busy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56d98985-bdf8-4bc2-81f0-db61049c0452"
msgid ""
"{n}Another peasant takes a moment to quickly wipe the sweat from his forehead.{/n} "
"\\\"You're just in time! Look... Look who we've caught here! Look at the "
"disgusting creature. He isn't afraid of anything!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "762ec3db-3825-43a3-a2dd-ff32eea47c3b"
msgid ""
"{n}You hear a chuckle from under the visor.{/n} \\\"I intended to come directly to "
"your court, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Unfortunately, "
"I was detained.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "760158cd-ae7c-459c-962e-8cf06a6571f2"
msgid ""
"\\\"These degenerates have never before set foot in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen "
"Lands{/g}. — But there, this devil's spawn was walking right in the middle of the "
"road. And we became so angry...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de45db32-bdc0-485a-944c-5e7658a4d665"
msgid ""
"\\\"Right, we figured we could gang up on him... But you could help, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! We're shedding blood for your "
"lands, after all!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3fdd0bed-7004-4941-8f48-07fa3c2c99b3"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is a {g|Hellknights}hellknight{/g}! These wretches have dealings with "
"devils!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c607a30f-29cc-4882-8165-987e57c20eb2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well... you know... they trample everyone whose lands they visit! Wherever "
"there's one, there will soon be a hundred – in a blink of an eye! They crawl like "
"locusts, with their executions and their laws!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5cc1e82-4789-48f0-8858-e1abfcdceb92"
msgid ""
"{n}The {g|Hellknights}hellknight{/g} laughs dryly.{/n} \\\"Of course. Savages like "
"these fear laws even more than fire or sword. Listen, {mf|baron|baroness|king|"
"queen}, isn't it time to put this bandit trash in its place? You are too soft for "
"such a savage land as this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21815e5e-f8d3-493e-b5fa-8fcc25b65f52"
msgid ""
"\\\"Kayse Berro, maralictor of the {g|Order of the Nail}Order of the Nail{/g} of "
"{g|Hellknights}hellknights{/g}.\\\" {n}The warrior pauses.{/n} \\\"I hail from {g|"
"Varisia}Varisia{/g}, if {mf|Your Grace| Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness} "
"cares to know. I've come under direct orders of the paralictor, in order to hold "
"negotiations.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08253fa9-6b88-4dbf-a4e7-8e16d1c54bf7"
msgid ""
"{n}The knight clenches his weapon.{/n} \\\"My commander made a mistake in "
"evaluating your potential, {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}. {g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/"
"g}, give me the strength to stand against these savages!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cad5fcf1-8b3c-4582-934e-b8a0a7ca0c2e"
msgid ""
"{n}The {g|Hellknights}hellknight{/g} clenches his weapon.{/n} \\\"Not the fairest "
"trial, but it's acceptable. Please allow me to help, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}. Weeding is our job.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "95c8bb05-d479-4338-a504-3f6e6c6fd3b3"
msgid "\\\"So... so you're just going to stand there and watch us die?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4c726bb-d53e-4c08-8745-e02ba19c46d8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let's beat {mf|him|her} up for abandoning {mf|his|her} subjects when they're "
"in trouble!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b71d3f2-bb09-4a08-9398-cf7a963a9c12"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yeah, right, keep listening to him! These scoundrels mean to conquer us. "
"That's why they're nosing about! That's why!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48521687-74af-493d-bfc8-dd37cf2a5312"
msgid ""
"{n}The {g|Hellknights}hellknight{/g} seems to not hear his adversaries.{/n} \\\"I "
"ran into some unexpectedly aggressive local fauna. Luckily, I was prepared for "
"such a turn of events. The {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} are said to be full of "
"surprises.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29910452-8486-4332-8d9a-c4f7d72dfee3"
msgid "\\\"Glory to the Order of the Nail!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e36098f0-dcb8-4730-ac2a-14102f609475"
msgid "\\\"Look out lads!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8abab428-61d3-4292-a3d4-f2b1b77f463d"
msgid "\\\"He's wounded. Come on, lads, give me a hand!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e405fba1-1d78-44c1-aae7-ffd07ba4ec80"
msgid "\\\"What's the matter, you scoundrel? Don't like our hospitality?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "433c67db-7583-4f3c-ad0c-c62b85a35c20"
msgid "\\\"Dirty, cowardly dogs...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce98f4c1-f038-4d3d-83a9-c5023251c033"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}. It's a pity we had to meet like "
"this. But all can still be mended.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d51176f3-a929-41be-baa6-0716fa8d9918"
msgid ""
"\\\"I shall pay you an official visit in the nearest future. We will soon meet "
"again, under less chaotic circumstances.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9b51c4f-4ec3-4364-877b-9aa68e765a72"
msgid "[Spit on the body of the hellknight]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eeb32693-5058-45db-ae4c-26213a95da06"
msgid "\\\"Go to your Hell, scumbag! Serves you right!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e370749-3ce1-4bcf-a8db-4975dc10266d"
msgid "\\\"What does your help imply?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6ae0bc4-b9be-4f6d-8d73-2c5e7f2a0ae5"
msgid "\\\"How would you benefit from an alliance with me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f284b981-dd0e-409f-a989-d5fb2013a3a1"
msgid "\\\"I want to know more about your Order.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82a78de3-99b1-4d26-8f44-52a6e5d9c5f8"
msgid "\\\"Do Hellknights obey demons, like others in Cheliax?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5013638-7de5-4d03-a193-0142031f9788"
msgid ""
"\\\"But you associate with Hell and its denizens? Aren't you afraid to draw the "
"wrath of those who would confuse you with devil worshipers?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b41394ae-81b0-4c9c-a0df-83a8f3f731b0"
msgid "\\\"Why did you become a knight?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff24b325-181f-4553-8a3a-916b533ae722"
msgid "\\\"How does one become a hellknight?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4fb5b407-cc27-4a5a-85e1-809068126f2b"
msgid "\\\"Enough. Let's return to discussing your proposal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48e3e19b-ba33-4a64-a224-1ae2558bc183"
msgid ""
"Refused to enter an alliance with the Order of the Nail, because of their brutal "
"methods."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a38af2b7-77f1-4b69-b391-9c9092294b24"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for your offer, but I cannot embrace your radical methods. The Order "
"of the Nail has no place in my lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f064088f-cba5-4582-9c19-b40b5ac962f8"
msgid "Refused to ally with the Order of the Nail on moral grounds."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a16c9ba1-5df9-446e-a2b3-5a6a807114e5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Order is a nest of tyranny and cruelty. Leave my lands at once and forget "
"the way here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c2910d2-c0a1-43d2-b99c-6b1cf76a55a2"
msgid "Entered an alliance with the Order of the Nail."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4f3d0ed-03f7-4747-bfb4-fd34af3f0e93"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will accept the Order of the Nail's proposal. Together we will bring these "
"lands to heel!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9d544f27-e83c-4cd9-8447-976a6e3a5291"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't like the idea of inviting an order onto my lands, if it refuses to "
"obey my commands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f255cc4-fc78-49af-9005-d231fd277d64"
msgid ""
"{n}A dignified half-elf wearing familiar black armor bows to you ceremoniously. "
"This time his armor is clean of dirt and blood, and he holds his helmet at his "
"side. It is the first time you see the {g|Hellknights}hellknight's{/g} face. Your "
"guest has light hair, transparent blue eyes, and scars from three claws that once "
"disfigured his face.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c43ff02-a360-426e-8dc6-4a284fa90941"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings on behalf of the {g|Order of the Nail}Order of the Nail{/g}, {mf|"
"Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Our first encounter was most "
"improper, and I dare recommence our acquaintance.\\\" {n}The half-elf lowers his "
"head.{/n} \\\"My name is Kayse Berro, and I am here under official orders of my "
"commanding paralictor. We have heard much of you and your method of rule. — It is "
"most unusual for this region.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed1704b6-40c1-46c7-a5c7-b23c0bdbe7f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"The {g|Order of the Nail}Order of the Nail{/g} knows about your service to law "
"and order. We also know the integrity that imbues all your deeds and orders. Our "
"order greatly values such rulers as you. — Especially those who are not afraid to "
"weed out barbarity even in dangerous borderlands like the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen "
"Lands{/g}. With our deepest respect, I, maralictor of the Order of the Nail, offer "
"you our aid. Together, by fire and sword, we can tame this land and bring it under "
"the law.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8e66bf56-386b-4661-b184-9fd527a740aa"
msgid ""
"\\\"We will deploy our own garrison in your capital. We will gather a squad – "
"train new recruits if necessary. We will make the {g|Hellknights}Hellknights{/g} a "
"symbol of power and law in your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}. Believe me, "
"such an alliance will increase your power a hundred times over. Public punishments "
"and executions instill respect in the law, even among the dumbest members of the "
"society.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd960bc3-cd30-488e-9183-32f0281511c0"
msgid ""
"{n}A half-smile appears on Kayse's face.{/n} \\\"But know this: the {g|Order of "
"the Nail}Order{/g} will never swear fealty to you. We are united by common goals — "
"to stamp out the vestiges of barbarity in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. "
"Our methods are similar and we don't expect any disagreement. But we do not wish "
"to complicate this alliance with oaths of fealty.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62621c75-3b6a-4b6d-a378-5637b7b4bdbe"
msgid ""
"{n}Kayse considers the answer for a while.{/n} \\\"'Savagery must be quelled, "
"across the land, at home, and in one's own mind.' It's a beautiful motto, isn't "
"it? I've lived my greatest years by it. My brothers live by it. The goal of my {g|"
"Order of the Nail}Order{/g} is to destroy all threats to civilization, order and "
"law. We need no divine guidance to serve this mission faithfully: our minds and "
"our consciences guide us, and they have brought us here to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "083635b0-6879-4532-b695-670d19dfa1e8"
msgid ""
"\\\"You are a beacon of order in lands where once only chaos reigned. I do not "
"know how, but you managed to crush all the forces that opposed you, and you have "
"since then ruled with an iron hand, with no concern that your actions might seem "
"willful or over-zealous. The {g|Order of the Nail}Order{/g} values such powerful "
"allies. Give us the right to enforce the laws in your lands — and you can forget "
"about such uncontrollable beasts as those who attacked me on the road.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e16be58c-1f32-4180-b754-5bb8f271c476"
msgid ""
"\\\"The {g|Order of the Nail}Order of the Nail{/g} is one of the oldest among the "
"{g|Hellknights}Hellknights{/g}. Like many others, our order traces its roots to {g|"
"Cheliax}Cheliax{/g}. The glory of our knights is so great that the rulers of the "
"lawless and savage {g|Varisia}Varisia{/g} once begged for our help — and we "
"crossed half the continent for an opportunity to suppress barbarity and bring the "
"savages under law.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "072ccd45-60b8-4400-a721-1cb87e84c5cc"
msgid ""
"{n}Kayse's cheek twitches, but his voice is calm and measured.{/n} \\\"I will not "
"unburden you of your other delusions about {g|Cheliax}Cheliax{/g}, but I will "
"clarify one thing. The only power we answer to is the leader of our order – be he "
"a lictor or a vicar. And the order itself serves only one master — the law.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9d67b5b-375b-45e1-b2c1-84c3ea1703f3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes, we draw much inspiration from {g|Hell}Hell{/g}. Why not? In the entire "
"world, there are no greater rules than those created by the Dark Prince and "
"enforced in his kingdom.\\\" {n}Kayse raises his brows.{/n} \\\"I myself venerate "
"{g|Asmodeus}Asmodeus{/g}, but my faith is a personal choice, and not the "
"reflection of my membership in the {g|Order of the Nail}Order{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41eb1d5b-eff8-4218-a069-0defa04cc395"
msgid ""
"\\\"The fears of the peasants do not concern a ruler — I'm sure you know this "
"well. To fear philosophy is the natural lot of narrow-minded simpletons. All we do "
"is turn theory into reality, but it is only a means to an end, and justified by a "
"higher purpose.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "157f25ac-2108-4e7b-8394-768ac5b1a5b6"
msgid ""
"\\\"I was seeking... order. Calmness. Reliability. Those who raise their voices to "
"freedom have rarely seen its ugly side.\\\" {n}The half-elf squints, and an angry "
"sneer crosses his lips.{/n} \\\"A half-blood learns to deafen his ears to the "
"witty insults of those who imagine themselves pure. But the fools fall mute when "
"they see a half-blood wearing black armor with the face of a devil on the "
"breastplate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4417d04-7716-4f57-8bfc-60a332157b2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Through sweat and blood. Anyone who wishes to be worthy of the armor must "
"sacrifice everything that stands in the way of this goal — weaknesses, "
"attachments, pity to himself and others. I trained like mad, rubbed my hands sore "
"on sword handles. I studied the laws and rules at night, and every day I carved my "
"mind and body to become perfect instruments of the {g|Order of the Nail}Order{/g}."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "022432ed-437f-4d7a-9e4e-81e27f66929b"
msgid ""
"{n}Kayse runs his hand over his face, and his fingers linger for a moment on his "
"terrible scars.{/n} \\\"I earned my knighting into the {g|Hellknights}Hellknights{/"
"g} in a ceremonial battle against a barbazu, one of the denizens of {g|Hell}Hell{/"
"g}. Everyone worthy of wearing the armor undergoes this ritual. The others become "
"toys for devils, and a disgrace to their families.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dbfcbbfd-667b-4477-aa60-59b76e707f49"
msgid "\\\"As you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a2bc665-8b50-4fe2-8523-8c79f937814a"
msgid ""
"{n}Kayse smiles thinly.{/n} \\\"I understand. But we cannot take the risk of "
"submitting to someone outside the {g|Order of the Nail}Order{/g}. Mortal flesh is "
"week, and the mind even weaker. What will become of us if we stray from our "
"destined path? We serve a higher purpose and cannot risk it for your convenience.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf39ad2e-e525-4023-b066-4c4496747472"
msgid ""
"{n}The eyes of the {g|Hellknights}hellknight{/g} grow cold, and he bows "
"ceremoniously.{/n} \\\"Then there is nothing keeping me in your lands. Farewell, "
"{mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d326b21-7ad8-45d6-8fb5-986f76b3e332"
msgid ""
"{n}The eyes of the {g|Hellknights}hellknight{/g} grow cold, and he shakes his head."
"{/n} \\\"Oh, really? I will obey only half of this order. I will keep the memory "
"of how to get to you. I expect I shall see you again, along with the rest of the "
"{g|Order of the Nail}Order{/g}. Farewell, {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "799ae8dc-8752-4b26-acf1-eebd97b02bd0"
msgid ""
"{n}Kayse lowers his head.{/n} \\\"So be it. My commanders will rejoice in your "
"wisdom!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44f91738-91ac-490e-a38c-8ce452fe1170"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will immediately return to {g|Cheliax}Cheliax{/g} with this news. We already "
"have a reserve at the ready. I will return to the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} "
"with a garrison of {g|Hellknights}Hellknights{/g}, and our mission will commence "
"as soon as we enter your lands. My regards, {mf|Baron|Baroness|King|Queen} {name}. "
"I will not be gone for long.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4c1bec5-00c6-4dcf-ac8c-b57d5939af54"
msgid "\\\"What is it?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa9c58b2-8dee-4767-b357-60d053546ffc"
msgid "\\\"You are wasting my time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2538f77f-d6f4-4cfc-a2b1-481de35a5b0d"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"You forget you place, rabble!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6183e526-b217-40c7-9d0b-cbd4219f4ca0"
msgid "\\\"What people from Mendev? What are you talking about?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e01669f2-d413-4959-97a5-e609072a732a"
msgid "\\\"Volunteers go to Mendev of their own free will.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8cb9cab9-5125-4fb9-a7aa-e0584d3bd875"
msgid ""
"Agreed to expel the Mendevian Crusaders from the Stolen Lands, because of your "
"subjects' pleas."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f580c86-5a03-4c90-931a-3837d94c85ad"
msgid ""
"\\\"I understand your concerns, and I share them. I will order the agents of "
"Mendev to leave my lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "379c460c-5256-45b5-8632-46af97428bb8"
msgid "Refused to expel the Mendevian Crusaders from the Stolen Lands."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7438041c-4ed9-49af-8178-d7015a92c5b9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will not stand against the missionaries of Mendev. They protect the whole "
"world, putting themselves on the line for all others!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a17d6714-de72-4e7d-9f6d-4dc63fcc3d69"
msgid "\\\"And who are you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f5b1baa-141f-4c99-b604-540e7a1aae96"
msgid "Refused to share your 'cannon fodder' with the Mendevian Crusaders."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85ced0f1-9f5c-46b6-96ae-30f3e736df2c"
msgid ""
"\\\"My subjects will die for no one but me. I will immediately drive the henchmen "
"of Mendev from my lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ceab023-f317-4837-b10a-5b591f36442e"
msgid "Refused to intervene in the affairs of the Mendevian Crusaders."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "146edbb4-1fe5-47c7-bc4a-62b2a31587a8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let the missionaries from Mendev do what they've come for, and let the "
"volunteers do as their conscience demands. I will not interfere.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15261533-71f8-424b-bf52-e0d1e458b5de"
msgid ""
"{n}A angry crowd of peasants is in uproar, and its leader, a rugged young man, "
"takes a few steps forward and speaks up.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}, wait! We need to talk to you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3e4ec0c-40f5-49cf-810d-8845f1a07ab3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Forgive us for... ambushing you like this. But your guards and advisors "
"wouldn't let us talk to you at the castle. So we had to wait here until you walked "
"past.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "650fef54-af7b-4e66-ac7a-985c4346a187"
msgid ""
"{n}The man turns gloomy.{/n} \\\"And you are wasting lives! It wouldn't hurt you "
"to hear us out!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "086af565-9730-47e3-83ae-957245160d41"
msgid ""
"\\\"Here's what I wanted to ask you about... It's a those people from Mendev you "
"love so much... why don't you have mercy on your people, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}!? They're dragging our children into someone else's "
"war! And you just go along with it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9baceb1-d9db-4727-af9c-c631c24c69d8"
msgid ""
"{n}A peasant draws a weapon from under his clothes.{/n} \\\"Then hell take you, if "
"you won't listen! We'll slaughter you first, and then those kindhearted Mendev "
"creeps! Hail to Areelu! Hail to Deskari!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdc4cc27-e95f-421e-9d2e-8e9b6d56471d"
msgid ""
"{n}The man shakes his head.{/n} \\\"Oh, so you've already forgotten about it! The "
"recruiters you supported not long ago — you said it's all right for our boys to go "
"off to Mendev, and die from demon's claws and teeth! They haven't left. They're "
"still walking around villages, telling tales of heroism and duty.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5469afd-bcbc-4ca8-8bb6-992fcf88722d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you know who listens to their stories the most? Children! Young lads and "
"lasses – as soon as they hear about battle glory, they abandon their families and "
"their work, and run off to Mendev... To die for nothing!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88332cb3-775d-46f4-acce-c1b6922e61d7"
msgid ""
"\\\"We are your subjects, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! "
"The ones who live here, plow your land, bow to you when you pass! We just can't "
"take it anymore, those people from Mendev! So we decided to join together... And "
"come to see you...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55565270-8285-4672-a1d8-845c73b2c47c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Come, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. What free will? "
"Our foolish youth are so naive — just call them, and they'll come running, even "
"into a demon's maw! No, their deaths are on your conscience, not their own!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "671047c1-2920-493d-99d1-03cd2a9ceab6"
msgid ""
"{n}The man winces.{/n} \\\"Thank you for this, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}. It's better to lose your head for your own lands than for "
"a stranger's!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2757309-dadc-4949-8fac-36d3db69cf54"
msgid ""
"{n}The man bows, and the crowd behind him roars approvingly.{/n} \\\"Thank you, "
"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I just knew we only had to "
"talk to you in person, and not through your advisors! Believe me, our children "
"will have better lives without those bloodthirsty do-gooders!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "200b3321-3c25-40e7-a8de-773cb33c2b65"
msgid "\\\"Hit {mf|him|her}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49c09bcc-e347-43b2-bb33-87612dc60ca6"
msgid "\\\"What a wretch! Away with the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b5c6fd89-cad8-465b-8962-14c876148fb5"
msgid "\\\"Sold us to strangers, like cattle! Hit the scumbag!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "443c6a60-3104-48fd-bc4f-0d6cd46047db"
msgid "\\\"Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0edaccf-3a0d-4309-a57c-52229e8ceb7e"
msgid "\\\"Praise your name! Our protector!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ccc9acc-5458-4f46-90ac-19765bb3b8f0"
msgid "\\\"Right, these scoundrels can go on back to Mendev! Get out of here!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f4c86ef3-1a9f-4222-960f-11f650dd3c13"
msgid "A faded letter, smelling of smoke"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dbb7d3c0-7cc0-4c7f-bd57-fd4ba3368d2d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Scouts report the adversary sent troops to recruit help in nearby countries. "
"The General demands they be stopped before they find allies. Your group is in the "
"Stolen Lands. Do not allow the Mendevians to recruit new forces there. Do whatever "
"it takes.\\nRemember: another mistake — and both of us will be given to the vrocks "
"and ripped to pieces.\\nDo not fail me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6374f41f-476b-4363-91f1-34d7e70c1b31"
msgid "\\\"Thank you, Fes. Your gift will be very useful.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88b4f14d-f115-4a97-bb91-13fe19fd13a0"
msgid "\\\"I don't need your veterans or their wisdom.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "574107b2-f688-4d59-a8a7-4bdadde5438a"
msgid "\\\"How are things on the front?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cee45f1-9cd9-4392-add1-1eeeaebe20e4"
msgid "\\\"You send me cripples and old men as a sign of gratitude?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6d85f5cc-bda9-4cdf-b65e-cdff3d4397fc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Agents of the Worldwound come to my lands — and they even attacked me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08802829-8867-4e5a-8639-9ac22ae7bc1c"
msgid ""
"\\\"The leader of cultists who ambushed me on the road mentioned two names: Areelu "
"and Deskari.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b8ab69a-eb6f-4393-9f88-51bb5881efeb"
msgid "\\\"A crusading aasimar. Sounds like a life's calling.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0560f49a-a099-4d19-96ce-0fd3891915be"
msgid ""
"{n}The aasimar before you is wearing armor regaled in the colors of Mendev, and {g|"
"Iomedae}Iomedae's{/g} symbol upon his breastplate. The visor of his helmet is up, "
"and you remark the unusual lips and eyes of the messenger, that appear as though "
"cast in metal. The aasimar salutes you in military style.{/n} \\\"Greetings, {mf|"
"Baron|Baroness|King|Queen} {name}! Allow me to introduce myself: Fes Aldragem, "
"commander of the Mendev army. I have come here on behalf of my knightly order, "
"with an official acknowledgement.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c604d7e5-f3f5-4b96-b5a9-08fa2a46f5b4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not long ago, our missionaries entered your lands to find brave men and women, "
"ready to challenge the {g|Abyss}Abyss{/g} itself. You did everything you could to "
"reinforce the ranks of Golarion's defenders, and many of your people stood ready "
"to serve a higher goal. Our missionaries visited many lands, and few if any have "
"done as much as you, for our common good. You have acted nobly, {name}, and have "
"proven yourself a loyal ally of Mendev.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc137996-016f-4c32-81c8-8af638ff767c"
msgid ""
"\\\"We value every soul who serves to protect {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g} from the "
"demon hordes. However, we felt we simply must thank you specially for showing such "
"valor and nobleness. I have something for you: a few veterans from Mendev have "
"come with me. They are ready to remain here and train your soldiers in military "
"skills. Any country could benefit from the knowledge these worthy officers "
"possess. They only left the battlefield to make room for soldiers stronger and "
"younger.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "092702cd-2a36-4308-a134-badc1fb5d962"
msgid ""
"{n}Fes smiles, but his eyes are tired.{/n} \\\"Our forces need aid. Every day, new "
"hordes of demons come to the {g|Worldwound}Worldwound{/g}, ready to rip to pieces "
"anyone who stands in their way. This is why we value every volunteer who is ready "
"to stand under Mendev's flag.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "03a38f5a-4af5-41da-8be7-a202d52a4953"
msgid ""
"{n}Fes shakes his head.{/n} \\\"The {g|Abyss}Abyss{/g} reaches its tentacles far "
"and wide. We recently lost two recruitment teams who were supposed to return to "
"Mendev with help. I'm glad you didn't suffer their fate. The {g|Stolen Lands}"
"Stolen Lands{/g} would be unlikely to survive such a loss.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eece4636-f935-4472-822b-72cf35c9cfd0"
msgid ""
"{n}Fes knits his brows.{/n} \\\"Your reproach is groundless, {mf|baron|baroness|"
"king|queen}. Each of these warriors have been through everything one can face of "
"the field. They have seen terrors enough for ten mortals. Many warlords would pay "
"any amount for such trainers. Their experience is truly priceless.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ab07cde-49f2-4c9d-8d5d-12965eb918bd"
msgid ""
"{n}Fes bows.{/n} \\\"My regards. Now it is time for me to return to Mendev. I "
"shall go with a light heart, in hopes that the alliance of our states will remain "
"strong, no matter what our enemy plots. Farewell!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dfb3b44a-42d1-4f49-83a5-676b5405fd2d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmm. I am sorry to hear that. Nonetheless, my companions will enjoy the "
"hospitality of the locals and remain in these lands — just in case you change your "
"mind and decide to take advantage of their knowledge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53e32825-b12d-406e-8490-d474da31ba05"
msgid ""
"\\\"Those filthy names are known to everyone in Mendev. Deskari is the demon lord "
"who stands behind the {g|Worldwound}Worldwound{/g} – one of the greatest spawns of "
"the {g|Abyss}Abyss{/g}. The vile lech Areelu Vorlesh is a corrupt witch, one of "
"the most celebrated denizens of the Worldwound. I've heard of the atrocities she "
"commits upon her prisoners and even her own slaves...\\\" {n}Fes shudders.{/n} \\"
"\"The sooner this evil is destroyed, the better.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f25c74ce-0d1c-4fe0-8d47-e28cc4e6b03c"
msgid ""
"{n}Fes curves his metallic lips in a smile.{/n} \\\"You could say so. Blood "
"seethes in my veins when I anticipate a fight against the spawns of evil. I'm "
"happy I've managed to direct my passions in the right direction.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea9311de-30be-4003-a181-b936e7085e9a"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about yourself and your crew.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a3f67e8f-c9c7-4456-b1bb-eb987d0ccd05"
msgid ""
"Allowed the mining brigade to camp and prospect in the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|"
"kingdom}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bde94e16-e0a4-40f6-8ff0-5e6fad4609f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've no reason to prohibit you anything. Respect the local laws, and you will "
"be welcome anywhere in my {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8b51bcf1-74e2-4bda-90fd-dccc48f49f6e"
msgid ""
"Demanded an impossible cost for prospecting in the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|"
"kingdom}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33311365-d6bf-476f-b0cb-b1be123b7d2b"
msgid ""
"\\\"You can stay only if I have my cut. I require three quarters of your profits.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a8e0d8bb-29ad-4f39-8ced-5b67c0eb0cb2"
msgid "Sheltered the mining brigade in the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e940e22e-53b1-4597-bf1c-ce4956bf0915"
msgid "\\\"I'm glad to give shelter to travelers seeking a new home!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33f3f096-acc7-4dd4-a5da-3a85e7b6dbc5"
msgid "\\\"What's wrong with the River Kingdoms?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87583a2a-abc8-458b-b9f6-33fed1482ac8"
msgid "\\\"What are you looking for in the Stolen Lands?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f87021d0-c58f-4a42-8186-29ccdb08ce07"
msgid ""
"Forbid the mining brigade to prospect in the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81af23e3-009b-46ce-909e-6d02286c5722"
msgid ""
"\\\"You will not be allowed to set up camp on my lands. Take yourself elsewhere.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "117228f2-0c2a-4c62-905e-c1445ee7cf11"
msgid ""
"{n}A dwarf in worn clothes and a dusty cloak clears her throat before she speaks.{/"
"n} \\\"Your Honor! I am so happy to be allowed to speak to the {mf|baron|baroness|"
"King|Queen} in person! I'm sorry if I sound clumsy. I'm just a common woman, don't "
"know no courtesies. I'm Dri Stinvag, head of a mining crew. I only troubled you to "
"make you a business offer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1de973a6-f379-4be0-815b-1a6722db1125"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're good at finding ore. We've been hoping to dig for ore in the {g|River "
"Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}, but there are local laws...\\\" {n}The dwarf waves "
"her hand in frustration.{/n} \\\"It hasn't been easy, you could say. We were about "
"to head out north, but then we heard about {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|"
"Your Highness}. Aren't we lucky? The most criminal lands of the River Kingdoms are "
"now full of order and peace. So I decided to try my luck out here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b0c1036-329f-48e4-9d0f-e131417b5ca3"
msgid ""
"{n}Dri hesitates and then bows clumsily.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}, allow us to set up a camp in your domain! It'll be safer "
"under your protection. And you'll benefit from it, too! If we discover an ore "
"deposit, we can start mining! Just help us find a spot of land. We're no cheats! "
"We'll do the right thing and sign whatever agreements you got! What do you say? Is "
"it a yes?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04e53c6b-3b43-4fbc-8c4d-65e905c458a4"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's nothing much to tell, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}! I come from Brunderton, east of {g|Rostland}Rostland{/g}. Half my crew "
"comes from there too. The others are just a mixed lot – {g|Torag}Torag{/g} knows "
"where from. But you know what's good about us? Every one of us is a true master of "
"their craft. We're a great team of miners, dowsers, and mages – you couldn't find "
"another like it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0feaefa5-4a1d-40f7-acd0-30bd5ff54f92"
msgid ""
"{n}Dri cringes.{/n} \\\"You never know if you'll even survive through the day! One "
"kingdom bans religion. Another declared that the local king was a god. A third one "
"is under water! No way, thank you. Their lands seem promising, but I'm not risking "
"the heads of my crew. We can stand up for ourselves, but we're not warriors, you "
"know. We're miners.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c00da296-988b-42fe-bd84-7cb1f127fd27"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well...\\\" {n}The dwarf crosses her arms and stares at the ceiling pensively."
"{/n} \\\"We've got to dig in before we know for sure, but I expect we'll find "
"anthracite and iron ore here... Besides, {g|Numeria}Numeria's{/g} not far away! "
"Who knows what could have fallen from the skies long ago! We could even strike "
"adamantium and be rich!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48ab54c1-325f-426b-adb7-37dc871e8e06"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. It won't be "
"any trouble for you to assign us a location! After that, there's nothing to worry "
"about – our bookkeeper will work out all the details with your advisors!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac7c1ef6-0dcd-4de2-8dc5-45dbd2459773"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a deal.\\\" {n}Dri shuffles her feet.{/n} \\\"I'll be on my way then. "
"Thank you again, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! We'll set "
"off to work as soon as we finish the camp. Well, take care now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6d2e45e-4211-417b-84cf-b5c09a0b2e59"
msgid ""
"{n}Dri cringes.{/n} \\\"Well, that's a nice trick. What shall we live on? Charity?"
"\\\" {n}The dwarf falls silent for a while and then utters a sigh.{/n} \\\"No, {mf|"
"Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, it won't do. We'll have to "
"find ourselves another place. You can do whatever you want.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e144029-0762-4af3-a45e-44beb53b0981"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's... not good. Ah, whatever. We'll find ourselves something else. "
"Goodbye, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I won't annoy you "
"any further.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cdf3a99f-100a-4ef1-82d8-a380143cd9fe"
msgid "\\\"Stop yelling and explain what partners you're talking about.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4f7fab67-71b4-4df8-bfae-ca7720c2d40d"
msgid "Killed the druids without even giving them a chance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "701e18cb-ae4d-4d6b-93f3-cb1b7ff8ed2c"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"What makes you think I'm talking to you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fccb9482-c46f-446d-a137-1235b9bd31cd"
msgid "\\\"Who are you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37ffe2be-1735-432f-9d86-eef95b02a6f1"
msgid "\\\"The dwarven miners can hardly be causing as much damage as you say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b18e1b68-85ad-4c96-a44f-fd22dcd9ef71"
msgid "Protected the miners' right to prospect and mine minerals."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24266a21-86f2-4f17-bee8-a06b0bc64c44"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm sorry, but the miners will keep working. They have my consent, and the "
"right to work.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0730b0e4-6f36-474f-845d-2957642fd103"
msgid "Prohibited prospecting and mining because local druids were against it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "335373f7-1726-4e28-9116-a3255105809e"
msgid "\\\"If it makes you so upset, I'll send the miners on their way.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6ef27e0-be98-453e-a966-27706ea0b27d"
msgid "\\\"What has the mining crew done to you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55969046-2c8d-457f-9f73-f5b14c7c5f33"
msgid "Threatened the druids with execution."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0a651a7-6c45-4103-b0c7-95cf2ddcd3a6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Enough with this nonsense. Leave my lands before I change my mind and send you "
"to the scaffold.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a859a93-1d1f-43e5-b926-2237feddf64b"
msgid ""
"Prohibited local prospecting and mining because of the damage it would cause "
"nature."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25af7513-d2bd-48c1-b3d2-5b7f7ff789a2"
msgid ""
"\\\"The things you're saying… It's awful. I shall immediately prohibit this "
"devastation of my lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f104bbea-904a-4381-a521-5439797c8feb"
msgid ""
"\\\"What shall the people of the Stolen Lands do? We can't live without metal!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ff7141d-74b6-421e-98e4-a01ada67d9f8"
msgid "Killed the druids without even giving them a chance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1d180f34-d712-44e0-a06a-0e7325d6fa81"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"Are you done whining? It's time to die!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "956ed20c-6e9f-48ee-ae53-cd86a080b477"
msgid "\\\"What have you done to the lost miners?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "80ff62f1-93fb-4495-90cb-373999a3a0f6"
msgid "\\\"You're... not very polite.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "841daa0a-8504-4e31-a440-33745b62bc6a"
msgid ""
"{n}A girl in a dusty robe is staring at you with clenched fists.{/n} \\\"You! "
"You're the one who thinks they're the ruler of these lands! Why are you here? Did "
"you want to head a greedy mob and clear yourselves a road to bounty?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b46eb5ad-07b4-4bf3-92ca-6bba106addea"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl tries to catch a breath, but gasps with rage at your words.{/n} \\"
"\"I'm talking about the mob you let onto these lands! The little bearded men who "
"think they can grab whatever they want!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ac01326-fb9d-4062-b12c-0c36b36b267e"
msgid ""
"\\\"The dwarves that came to you... Didn't you think to wonder why they'd walk "
"such a long way? I'll tell you why. They're locusts! They come to an innocent land "
"and rip it apart like a dead body! They rip up the mountains, mutilate the fields, "
"cut down the forests! And all for profit – for the unborn children that the earth "
"was carrying under its covers!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8101513-fb6f-49d6-8778-d8bf4bafd896"
msgid ""
"{n}She sobs.{/n} \\\"Is it not enough what the earth freely gives? The ores and "
"gold that lie on the ground? Why would your subjects want to completely consume "
"all our natural resources? They wound the earth so deeply, it will take centuries "
"to heal!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8540bfeb-a398-4524-a76c-39339420c163"
msgid ""
"\\\"They have come from other lands they've devastated, only to mutilate this "
"country, too! They use their contracts with the authorities to gut the bowels of "
"the earth, and destroy anything that stands in their way – and they get away with "
"it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3acaa521-0906-4aeb-85b2-9f4235408e48"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl shakes her head.{/n} \\\"When the earth is torn apart, it suffers "
"greatly. Once it loses its strength, water and wind finish the job. Did you know "
"that the dwarves uncovered an acidic stream that poisoned several nearby creeks? "
"Did you know that their ore-rinsing elixirs burn the grass and turn good, rich "
"soil into lye?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7b146734-fb10-4f42-82f0-40924143d816"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm sure you didn't. All that people like you can see is the gold they pay for "
"their mountain treasures. Just think about it for a minute. What's to become of "
"your land when your children's children inherit it? What will they be getting? A "
"green country that's full of life – or a dead wasteland that's empty like an "
"eggshell?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ee8fe6e-bd10-4646-b446-2e4a24d892a9"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're the ones who protect the land against vandals like you and your dwarves. "
"We are followers of {g|Gozreh}Gozreh{/g}. We hear the whispers of the sky and the "
"rivers. We protect our lands against all intruders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad9b01e1-9192-455d-aa59-4689bc923ac9"
msgid ""
"{n}Girl's face turns dark.{/n} \\\"They came to deliver pain, and it's the pain "
"that they shall receive. An eye for an eye. A tooth for a tooth.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b1a3826-314e-4dc5-b656-c3b67eefc6a3"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl clasps her hands.{/n} \\\"Aren't the hillside deposits enough? Why gut "
"the earth, while other sources of ore which it uncovered freely have yet to be "
"depleted? There's already more than enough for your and for all your {mf|barony|"
"barony|kingdom|kingdom}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "603d8898-d63c-456b-baf4-1571e184af75"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl looks at you in astonishment.{/n} \\\"R-really?\\\" {n}Her clumsy "
"smile makes her look even younger.{/n} \\\"I didn't... We didn't know we could... "
"just ask! Thank you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. "
"Believe me, you're doing the right thing by listening to us. Those... those "
"vandals – they do not belong here!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79c388a8-743f-4e26-9a33-5ea2ce81d369"
msgid ""
"{n}Her eyes fill with tears, and she gasps and turns away.{/n} \\\"I'm ready to "
"die... but I can't risk the lives of my brothers and sisters. You and your dwarves "
"can burn in hell.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54e719df-e69d-41c2-9374-2ddda07502a5"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl lowers her head. You can almost hear her gritting her teeth.{/n} \\"
"\"It means... we're fighting to the end.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62056c26-0e0f-4fb8-9fd1-2e47a0745a67"
msgid ""
"\\\"Polite? You and your minions bring only pain and misery to these lands. You "
"decided to come in person and crush us, so you and your gang can continue injuring "
"the earth and the mountains! Shameless, vile, disgusting murderers – that's what "
"you are!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56627444-88eb-4042-b022-b96f8bf55567"
msgid "\\\"You can't stop nature's wrath!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f75f182-81eb-4e28-9be1-a9da155e4d66"
msgid "\\\"Death to the invaders!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6d71617-a4e1-45a6-b7f0-e0423aeceac1"
msgid "\\\"Who are you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f14a49c-aa8b-4a8b-91d0-7b02405e946e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} of these lands. Apologize immediately!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb79090c-d5fe-4bd8-9b8f-bae155108211"
msgid "Killed the travelers in the camp."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b11f0408-4ac7-4295-9020-5f398eb26534"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"You should watch your language.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eaa429da-6af7-43eb-83a0-4ae2c03ce21b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I know who you are, Kaleena. I'm here to kill you and report your death to "
"Areena Korvosh.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4f2d2f3-7c8f-4ffd-9c67-3dd78e821068"
msgid ""
"\\\"I know who you are. Your head is worth a lot of money. Care to make a counter-"
"offer?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee35a678-f509-49d4-a63a-0e4af17016e4"
msgid "Killed the travelers in the camp."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11343a82-464b-4e9e-99fc-cabdf83ae1a6"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"Enough of this drama!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c495d7f6-8bf6-432a-98ec-34bd73c5471c"
msgid "\\\"I'm going my way.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "627a8d67-f98a-4c52-a34c-3216b96957d9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Jadwiga? The White Witches? I don't understand half of what you're saying.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b75bd1a0-8ae5-49a4-b832-eb0acb1a5ba4"
msgid "Let Kaleena Jadwiga go without any harm."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38af7412-fcba-4972-86f9-419b37112e7f"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm letting you go, but I won't help you in your scheming against your sister."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f460dcd-8a2a-4e9b-b5f6-b90b829f259d"
msgid "\\\"I'll help you get rid of your sister. What am I to do?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6d0473b-64aa-4d87-944f-00287f6e8c0f"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't care about your family feud. However, I do care about the trade "
"contract Areena offered me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a57900dc-bc38-4fd2-8724-8f6e970608cd"
msgid "Refused to betray Areena Jadwiga."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d5ffd8d-3479-47c0-ab3d-3f1a24ee780d"
msgid "\\\"I promised to help Areena, and I'll not go back on my word.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7d8e23b-49e4-4f75-93f4-ac4a5745f0df"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's your life we're talking about, remember? How about a better offer in "
"exchange for my cooperation?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7be116fe-bd50-4cc1-a01d-dcd5f1825dac"
msgid "Betrayed Areena Jadwiga for her sister."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6536f84b-8547-4501-aa2e-0c515863f265"
msgid "Refused to betray Areena Jadwiga."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3279cfcc-3537-4323-bd2c-ad9f42b2bfe6"
msgid "\\\"I changed my mind. No deal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fcd16778-feac-4e17-b305-8d0612cff399"
msgid ""
"\\\"You do realize that if you try to cheat me, I'll contact your beloved sister's "
"grieving friends?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8fe0a332-3637-47de-a8cb-e67fe474faea"
msgid "Betrayed Areena Jadwiga for her sister."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "453b437a-81e3-480e-a011-4ba72550eb7f"
msgid "\\\"Deal. I'll order my advisor to inform Areena of your death.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6de69ae-71f0-4bef-80d1-a83ad28e839f"
msgid "\\\"What are you doing here? Get lost before I lose my temper!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a5847e5-6bd4-449c-ab08-e9087a3048e7"
msgid ""
"{n}A thin, pale woman with an upright posture looks at you with the eyes of an "
"angry cougar, blue as ice. Her bright ginger hair rustles like quiet fire over her "
"white skin.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb2d6c18-cee1-4d81-90cb-cc510a68f9c7"
msgid ""
"{n}Your words make the woman cower. She shrivels, fear in her eyes.{/n} \\\"I beg "
"your forgiveness, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. We've "
"been troubled quite a lot of late. It's made me a little... edgy. We must rest and "
"regain our strength before we head south. We've a long road ahead, but don't "
"worry, we'll be on our way soon.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "affe2c84-f2f9-48dc-bc23-6a414fe908e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why do you care?\\\" {n}The woman looks you up and down and continues in a "
"calmer tone.{/n} \\\"Just travelers, {race}. We've been troubled a lot lately. I "
"just want to be left alone. We need to rest and regain our strength before we head "
"south.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e196d1b-6b75-436a-9afc-4f7f92a9d063"
msgid "\\\"What is it?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f7578c8-096f-4dac-bf8b-73109ce572c5"
msgid ""
"{n}Kaleena licks her lips.{/n} \\\"Oh, really? Then why aren't you attacking me? "
"It seems you're in no rush to obey the tramp's orders. Very good – that's the "
"right thing to do!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d26a5ea9-67e7-4ea6-833d-9b5498cbdc4a"
msgid ""
"{n}Kaleena blinks, then squints.{/n} \\\"So that's how it is. I see you have a "
"good head for business! Straight to the point. It's a good thing I decided to hide "
"out in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "983a3501-7a6a-480f-9ac0-2682b86ca9ba"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't know what lies Areena told you, but I bet she didn't tell you I'm "
"Jadwiga as well. I'll tell you more – I'm Korvosh. We're sisters, falling out over "
"our inheritance. An old story, yes? As soon as our dear mother departed, my "
"deceitful sister announced that I had joined the Heralds of Summer's Return – "
"traitors who look to overthrow not only the Queen herself, but the White Witches "
"altogether!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b9a621f8-34d7-47fe-be9b-927df3d8763d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I care nothing about those madmen, but in {g|Irrisen}Irrisen{/g}, the "
"accusation of being involved with the Heralds is certain death. They let the "
"winter wolves loose upon me. Luckily, I had some money, so I bought the loyalty of "
"a few mercenaries.\\\" {n}Kaleena looks you up and down.{/n} \\\"I'm sure I can "
"repay you for your assistance. But it will take more than simply releasing me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "732f1f29-61ca-4008-8b5e-5e9baa10f944"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm no wealthier than a beggar now, but if you help me get rid of Areena... I "
"can tell you this: I'll outbid her offer by half. Whatever she offered, money, "
"slaves, trade interest... it doesn't matter. You'll getting it all, plus another "
"half. I'll need lots of resources. Areena has many friends, who will be furious if "
"she dies. I must be prepared.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e26a56e6-425e-463e-aafe-4b0ea9ffb60c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I bet it's for the grain... Your soil is more fertile here than we have back "
"home.\\\" {n}Her tone turns from musing to pleading.{/n} \\\"Don't be hasty. I "
"promise the same contract if you help me. – No, an even better one. I'm bargaining "
"for my life, you know.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0af23165-9436-4cac-a1e8-c4f7a9c307fa"
msgid ""
"\\\"Must I explain every little thing?! The Jadwiga are the nobles of {g|Irrisen}"
"Irrisen{/g}, the cream of their society, the blue bloods. The White Witches are "
"the Jadwiga supremes: they stand by the throne of Queen Elvanna, they enforce the "
"law in Irrisen and they are the vilest bitches in all the lands, from the Crown of "
"the World to the Kodar Mountains!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "077ccf92-2e12-495d-81a6-c8f9e0daf441"
msgid ""
"\\\"Phew... All right, thanks for that at least! I won't try your temper further. "
"Farewell!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19b429e8-8064-479c-805a-0c54903bd169"
msgid "\\\"Oh you vile creature... Die!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "373f5106-edfd-48bc-9add-71dd36f8a430"
msgid ""
"{n}Kaleena curls her lips in a cold smile.{/n} \\\"Wonderful. There's only I thing "
"I need from you. Write Areena a letter – tell her I'm dead. Tell her you've sent "
"my body with a sentry, but there's been a delay along the way. She's an arrogant "
"fool. She'll assume it's all over and call off her dogs. In the meantime, I'll "
"sneak back to {g|Irrisen}Irrisen{/g} and strike back!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b180a4d6-ab31-4abe-bdd7-cd286b4d9280"
msgid ""
"{n}Kaleena grits her teeth.{/n} \\\"Very well. I'll double Areena's offer. I only "
"hope she didn't offer half of our family's realm...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ddfddb1-dd44-4091-88d0-0016f811182c"
msgid ""
"{n}Kaleena stares firmly at you.{/n} \\\"I've given you my offer. I'm not changing "
"it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a57aee6b-14e7-41dd-bbb6-0e9ce03d1733"
msgid ""
"{n}Kaleena rubs her hands together.{/n} \\\"Then I should get moving. My beloved "
"sister must be missing me terribly. Oh, she'll be so surprised to see me!\\\" {n}"
"The woman salutes you and calls out to the others.{/n} \\\"Let's pack it up. We're "
"heading home.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f2321aa-9745-4302-a55a-85781703ac91"
msgid ""
"{n}Kaleena groans, annoyed.{/n} \\\"Of course, I understand. But I'd place more "
"trust in strangers than my own people. At least I know you won't be talking. My "
"death will profit you nothing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14472dd4-3a02-4b2f-b213-631ddeb0674c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Don't worry, we won't tarry long. We'll head north as soon as we break camp.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c02be8e-997a-423a-8765-9785ef7ef0cd"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's highway robbery! I'll be subject to Areena's whim without getting "
"anything in return!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8ed8879-cba2-4e2b-a3ce-b6223a2aea70"
msgid "[Continue listening to the ambassador]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a48e199-48dd-4ae5-a78e-0820fd1c23cc"
msgid "\\\"All right, go on.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "690b16d8-f5a3-4dae-bef5-4744ce2dd483"
msgid "\\\"No. I refuse.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d64d930d-ff40-40bc-a0f6-67f01da90547"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm not sitting around listening to insults. Throw this frosty worm into "
"prison!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f442de95-3df2-484b-825e-419c873b2d42"
msgid "\\\"I agree.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ccc00850-ce81-4cb1-ab64-1d7f3d922549"
msgid ""
"\\\"Have our special arrangements with Kaleena been included in the contract?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b413260b-f607-45bf-8e39-e3437859020b"
msgid "[Continue listening to the ambassador]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b4f5a50-0ee0-4886-98a6-74568e6c1579"
msgid "\\\"I'm not signing a trade agreement with Irrisen. Leave my lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49688d67-e6e2-4168-a378-8cc81df5e92e"
msgid "\\\"In that case, there won't be a deal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39eca811-9b7d-49a9-b027-312eb13b357f"
msgid ""
"{n}A blond man dressed in furs and brocade bows ceremoniously.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I am happy to greet you on behalf "
"of her Excellency Duchess Korvosh.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2153b30-901f-45ab-a772-fe4ecb870f7c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am honored to represent Areena Korvosh, the head of the noble house of "
"Hoarwood. My mistress rose to power after her poor mother died and her ungrateful "
"sister fell from grace – may her name be blotted from the history of the house.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b66b9278-0640-49d0-8c68-1d27c82ff551"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am honored to represent the interests of Kaleena Korvosh, the head of the "
"noble house of Hoarwood. My mistress courageously took the position left to her "
"after the deaths of her mother and sister. You supported her Excellency in her "
"hour of need, and now may enjoy a special honor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bb809134-f54e-49d2-89f7-c97ffb42ab32"
msgid ""
"{n}The ambassador retrieves a scroll from the folds of his luxurious attire, opens "
"it and clears his throat.{/n} \\\"As arranged, my mistress grants you a trade "
"contract, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Very well...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "652db449-2da6-4ee4-b465-98cbe5b36500"
msgid ""
"{n}The ambassador's clear dark eyes go to you.{/n} \\\"I don't think you heard me "
"correctly, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. My mistress "
"grants you the honor of trading with her family, the noble house of {g|Irrisen}"
"Irrisen{/g}. This privilege is offered to very, very few. I didn't come here to "
"negotiate the terms. I'm merely informing you. If they're not good enough for you, "
"it is none of my concern.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca62dab7-69ed-4bfb-bdd3-822c6969f6b2"
msgid ""
"{n}The ambassador grins, rolls the scroll and makes a bow.{/n} \\\"As you wish, "
"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Your rejection will hardly "
"affect my mistress.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d22d679-aed7-4a69-bba8-07313fffca01"
msgid ""
"\\\"Where was I? Oh yes. Special privileges for the ambassadors of {g|Irrisen}"
"Irrisen{/g} in your lands...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7b48347-088d-44ef-8d18-7cae8247abe8"
msgid ""
"{n}The ambassador utters an angry shriek.{/n} \\\"You're going to be sorry! My "
"mistress will learn of this, I swear it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3af5d330-3d63-49ce-b339-82935799eaee"
msgid ""
"{n}He finishes reading the scroll, rolls it up and turns to you.{/n} \\\"Well, {mf|"
"Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, do you agree to commence "
"commercial relations with the noble house of Her Excellency?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9957d820-b53a-47b8-acb7-62043cc5ad80"
msgid ""
"{n}The ambassador's chilly smile barely conceals his discontent with being "
"interrupted.{/n} \\\"Of course. My mistress remembers perfectly well about your... "
"merits, and your power to jeopardize her. Everything has been arranged.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "630bfced-71c9-4284-8178-f0218f438a34"
msgid ""
"\\\"Congratulations to you and to your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} on your "
"new trade ally. May the relationship between our lands be eternal.\\\" {n}The "
"ambassador bows deeply.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff71cf30-e2de-41dd-b14a-1e258fdc1f0b"
msgid ""
"\\\"According to the terms, you shall deliver a monthly load of vegetables and "
"grain to {g|Irrisen}Irrisen{/g} in a timely fashion. Failing this, you will be "
"penalized. Your merchants shall pay all fees associated with Hoarwood trading "
"rights. Otherwise, a prison sentence is due. The cargo shall be paid for within an "
"eighteen-month timeframe...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f473a9c0-3e04-4f1a-b364-00fc985c45c1"
msgid ""
"\\\"The noble house offers you special terms of trade, including tax exemption and "
"assistance in delivery to the place of destination. According to the agreement...\\"
"\" {n}The ambassador dives into numerous clauses and items of the trade agreement. "
"He doesn't seem to care if you're listening or not.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c07b908c-003f-4ee6-9185-588f2db75827"
msgid "\\\"Who are you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "015def25-71ef-4f8c-beb7-86f121122b45"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let me guess — you're the hero who's been knocking heads together in my lands?"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44bb262b-90b3-45ea-b268-23344b9b49cd"
msgid "Killed the masked hero."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0cc69a62-da4e-41fb-a473-cd0ac032a603"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"First impressions can be deceiving.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84e5e044-cecc-4b71-ace8-63a93a232f4c"
msgid "\\\"Why are you wearing this weird costume?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e834a9c-f4c6-47cf-b915-b6cbf7411164"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're dressed in strange clothes, hunting bandits... an odd thing to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f370aeff-cecd-470b-b385-de377edc1866"
msgid "\\\"Who attacked you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c37be44a-0f98-47ff-90cc-f03d62509a0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"You must be one of the locals. Otherwise, why perform such feats in my lands?\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6941474-3b10-43b5-a602-44c2672a021f"
msgid "Praised Osprey for his deeds."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1d60f2a6-a346-4da7-a3d6-322e5d7a3b9b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I like what you're doing. I hope the Stolen Lands will change for the better "
"thanks to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e41cb6d4-ea9e-4691-bcd8-5c825485ba8b"
msgid "Neither supported Osprey nor turned him away."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d61217f-8ab9-4020-852c-c0700b858bfb"
msgid ""
"\\\"I won't interfere, but don't expect any help either. I don't know your "
"motives, so I'm wary of you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8bd5b935-305d-4fe6-a7cf-b771c49e6fa2"
msgid ""
"Kicked Osprey out of the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} for being too "
"uncontrollable."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cdc49572-dae6-4332-a9b6-9b0975f060e4"
msgid ""
"\\\"You make my guards and I look like helpless children. I don't need amateurs "
"working to preserve law and order.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82f5ebeb-6670-4524-8551-6b1ba8fd7080"
msgid "Killed the masked hero."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89fd61e4-6ee1-4730-aa72-4446f3ce4d7c"
msgid ""
"[Attack] \\\"It's time to put an end to the story of the little hero bird.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd79073b-eae2-4206-a8df-47ada0352b47"
msgid "\\\"I can't help asking... 'Osprey'? Why?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64144eb1-1e56-4159-ab3f-f91a19342ac9"
msgid ""
"{n}The tall man bows to you politely, face hidden behind an iron helmet.{/n} \\"
"\"The rumors are true, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. "
"You're as noble as they say!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59729ac6-9faa-49fa-bfaa-5d89e745e59e"
msgid "\\\"You may call me Osprey, {mf|Baron|Baroness|King|Queen} {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dcfee714-4862-4f6d-bbd1-0ce0261044f8"
msgid ""
"{n}The man laughs out loud.{/n} \\\"You could say that! Although I hope my efforts "
"resulted in more than just a few headaches.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc727a23-9ee4-4aa4-80e3-c361be2160fe"
msgid ""
"{n}Osprey looks at his attire and shrugs helplessly.{/n} \\\"Believe it or not, "
"I'm not the last remaining member of high society. I could hardly do what I do "
"without changing my appearance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "064ff6e6-dd66-4bd1-bd5e-2691168c0ac3"
msgid ""
"{n}Osprey grins.{/n} \\\"Not the first time I've heard those words! I might look "
"odd to a stranger. Or even crazy. But still...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "689b9b8d-d4d6-451d-91eb-a3c1d66d037a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Common cutthroats sell their conscience for a handful of coins. I'm sure the "
"local merchants hate that the common folk have their own man who can't be bribed.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bfe9a96-9d35-44ca-b0dd-ffc0c77193e2"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Golarion}Golarion{/g} is full of injustice. There are those who take "
"advantage of oppression. There are those who overlook evil right in front of them. "
"And then there are those who commit their time and effort to making this world a "
"better place. I think I'm the latter, regardless if I'm considered weird or mad.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5823089-befa-4a58-9a5b-6dd6376e14a8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Besides, as you can see, my profession can be dangerous.\\\" {n}Osprey points "
"at the robbers' bodies.{/n} \\\"I don't want my most active enemies paying a visit "
"to my friends or family. Let them hunt me instead, if they so desire.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "004940b5-9dd3-40de-8b43-674d622dfdea"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let's put it this way: you rule these lands better than dozens of other {mf|"
"kings|queens} could. But like any other mortal, you're not almighty. And you're "
"not alone. Osprey circles high in the sky, deadly and invisible. I can see in the "
"distance what you don't. I'm the hand of your people, ready to help our just ruler."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8f4924c-c6ea-436d-a35d-b975c6ef710d"
msgid ""
"{n}Osprey looks you up and down.{/n} \\\"Ambition and power corrupt even the "
"purest souls. I'll take my leave, but don't expect me to stop helping and "
"protecting those in need. Farewell.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ab6699d-3011-4651-9eaa-95d831449319"
msgid ""
"{n}The man nods.{/n} \\\"I understand. It isn't easy to trust someone who won't "
"reveal their face, is it? I do, however, hope my deeds speak louder than my words. "
"Farewell.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "030315cc-ae8d-4329-a8ce-d84599ff7cde"
msgid ""
"{n}Osprey bows, this time sincerely.{/n} \\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}, if it is so, it will be thanks to our combined deeds. You "
"set a fine example and give hope that the whole {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} "
"can live guided by conscience rather than heartless legislation. It was a pleasure "
"meeting you, {name}. And now... I must go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f29b2678-691e-49ac-9e31-383046de255d"
msgid ""
"{n}You hear a muffled chuckle from behind the visor.{/n} \\\"A good bird. Sharp-"
"eyed. Swift. Proud. Can't stand bad people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f48440f8-794a-4a25-92be-eb7dc58e9560"
msgid "\\\"Get him! Get him before he flees!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "babf5e8d-b2e5-4598-8728-3e2a0301553d"
msgid "\\\"End of the road, Osprey! You've really done it now!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a70ef92-c6e3-4ea8-9b26-fbc88500547f"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, thank you! My luck "
"nearly ran out today!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f50deda6-8e54-4acb-9c25-2f17fc963c1c"
msgid "\\\"I'd like to know more.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "09c594e6-b2ac-45ee-a0f5-103dc93fb51d"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about Andoran.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23a85a31-9f16-4e45-8ac2-0fad3233b14b"
msgid "\\\"Why my {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97154a2a-a08c-45c7-9de2-f42f58dc6ce8"
msgid "\\\"What profit do I get from your bank?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eeaab8cd-def5-43ae-95f6-8ceca6663c35"
msgid "\\\"A family bank, you say?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0ba98c1-e84b-4ad7-8e30-a739ae5986b9"
msgid "\\\"That's all that I need to know.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16d6ba03-29e1-408b-b534-c7567864e7d5"
msgid "\\\"I agree to open a bank in the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b7cf576-51d4-4754-9d00-4faea4f9aa68"
msgid "\\\"If I remember correctly, Andoran was once a colony of Cheliax.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63a94c60-6336-4f4b-abc8-be6c417d919c"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about these opportunities you mentioned.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ae34029-7b96-426a-8ce8-8daa8affc9a2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't like you or your Andoran propaganda. Take yourself from my lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a933de05-2e0f-45aa-86d1-495c1f03098e"
msgid "\\\"What is this lifestyle?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11131042-224b-4435-9ef0-dee8657afa2b"
msgid "\\\"This is very interesting, but I'd like to go over other issues.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45ba6baa-2b8f-4090-b7a0-9bfea927f20c"
msgid "\\\"I need time. I can't say yes right now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65fd7c7e-2bfd-46e4-9e2e-6c18174ba98c"
msgid ""
"{n}An exquisitely dressed man flips the pinned cape off his shoulder and bows "
"deeply.{/n} \\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! "
"My name is Alex Covenorb. I traveled a difficult road from {g|Andoran}Andoran{/g} "
"just to meet you in person.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e65cfa90-c497-434e-ac88-0e84ee7411b4"
msgid ""
"{n}Alex shows you a heavy folder full of papers.{/n} \\\"I am the official "
"representative of the family bank called 'Heritage and Honor'. It is based in "
"Augustana, but we do business well beyond the borders of {g|Andoran}Andoran{/g}. "
"I'd like to open an office of our bank in your capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e67502c-f2dd-4364-a102-b7c27c0c8da0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Absolutely! However...\\\" {n}Alex weighs his folder thoughtfully.{/n} \\\"I "
"don't wish to bother you with boring figures and terminology. I'd rather hand the "
"papers to your Treasurer, who can confirm everything I say. Please, ask about any "
"concerns you may have!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb3d4171-3251-423f-b70d-e06315418ffa"
msgid ""
"{n}Alex eyes you for a few seconds before answering.{/n} \\\"If you think I've "
"made a random choice, perhaps you should think again. I've put much effort into "
"making sure you're following my people's principles.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "817de430-54ec-40f3-8aed-97cb4905f90f"
msgid ""
"\\\"We don't just store your money, but put it into use to make more money! We "
"make it work for you. We make it bring profit. Such promises might at first sound "
"like sweet lies to the locals, but I'm prepared to wait patiently while people "
"change their attitudes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c9e0aac-966c-4074-a07f-0cf87ac243da"
msgid ""
"\\\"The bank was founded by my father, a respected man, a wise accountant and a "
"perspicacious businessman. Father let me take over the business, now that he's "
"resting on his laurels. He didn't merely raise my sisters and me – he passed on "
"his spirit of enterprise, a gift I will never be able to repay.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0d4afc3-ff8a-4a50-92cc-c016bf2068eb"
msgid ""
"\\\"I hope you've liked what you heard. Well, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}, are you ready to sign our contract?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7462a44b-ab30-4354-a617-5ff6d8c01038"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't mean doctrine or legislation. I mean human values, which my country "
"got through our revolution, and which we strive to preserve, whatever it takes. "
"Honor. Nobility. Equality. All these notions fit with your {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom} very well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dfeb8c94-b22b-41b2-9323-7fcac0de8bba"
msgid ""
"{n}The banker rubs his chin.{/n} \\\"In a nutshell, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your "
"Highness|Your Highness}, it's my motherland. It's where I grew up and learned the "
"principles that I live up to even today. It's a beautiful country, always happy to "
"welcome good travelers. It offers many opportunities for a hard-working person.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "07915c80-7533-49a6-a4fc-4a979fc098e8"
msgid ""
"\\\"It was a part of {g|Taldor}Taldor{/g} before. Yes, {g|Andoran}Andoran{/g} kept "
"changing rulers over the centuries. Luckily, the people managed to break the cycle "
"and opted for independence. Revolution brought us new problems, but at the same "
"time, a unique social order.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "839b1a62-0b4a-4196-98fa-4b225ae761cb"
msgid ""
"\\\"With all due respect, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, "
"the very essence of the modern governance in {g|Avistan}Avistan{/g} is wrong. It "
"allows some to rise above the others, to force their will upon them, to determine "
"their fate. {g|Andoran}Andoran{/g} is free from such tyranny. It's not the king or "
"the emperor who rules the country, it's the people!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b8c0e208-e9d2-45fe-ae99-5b98a40420fa"
msgid ""
"\\\"The People's Council runs the country. It consists of three hundred and fifty "
"advisors elected by the citizens. Among them are former aristocrats and regular "
"craftsmen, wealthy merchants and respected mayors. The People's Council appoints "
"the Supreme Elect, the official head of state, along with ministers, governors and "
"advisors. There are no privileges or patronage. Everyone gets what they deserve.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44b84ebf-c823-4334-998d-bf39e2007501"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you know how our family became bankers and took our place in society? We "
"didn't possess titles or family heirlooms. My grandfather worked as an ordinary "
"falconer for the rich aristocracy. But we had fire running through our veins! We "
"decided to take a crazy risk and invested in our own business. As you can see, it "
"paid off.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f8a8bef-10e9-4774-a245-163fabb84178"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you roll up your sleeves and get to work, and earn a good reputation, you "
"can do anything. {g|Andoran}Andoran{/g} appreciates the noble and bold of spirit.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1829712e-6933-4f70-957d-164bc9027fa0"
msgid ""
"{n}Alex turns pale.{/n} \\\"I'm afraid you misunderstood my words, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. I may sing the praises of my motherland, "
"but {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} forbid if I ever engage in cheap propaganda! I will not "
"trouble you with my presence any further, but please allow me to leave these "
"papers with one of your advisors! I hope you will consider all the benefits after "
"your temper settles.\\\" {n}The man bows politely.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08278085-25f3-4404-938c-3d5701e491b2"
msgid "{n}Alex nods.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81406380-7e81-4ba7-bbe6-c965f27c13f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Reasonable care never hurt anyone. I'll pass the papers to one of your "
"advisors. If you decide to accept this offer from the 'Heritage and Honor' bank, "
"we'll return to this issue.\\\" {n}Alex bows politely.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a0044c3-0cfb-43d0-a832-0aba32d3212d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for your trust, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}. Rest assured, your subjects will appreciate the opportunities our bank "
"has to offer! I won't waste any more of your time. The final details can be "
"discussed with your advisors.\\\" {n}Alex bows politely.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50d0a013-772a-48a1-a2e7-48d7b61bd9eb"
msgid "\\\"Where did such a monster come from?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "512e181c-3c78-4367-9157-31fd4c10224a"
msgid "\\\"And who are you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acb72bf5-e354-407f-ad12-e465c6127307"
msgid "Killed a group of travelers."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99011b1e-7d69-40d0-be76-9c93b9cf44dd"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"I was only getting warmed up!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97e1c350-a47c-4861-8949-293523732d5a"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fac65258-d5ba-499c-ba69-795128a865c9"
msgid "\\\"I am {mf|Baron|Baroness|King|Queen} {name}, ruler of this land!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c0e8bc3-8b33-4fd4-9d0c-a2550a523a67"
msgid "\\\"What exactly are you doing here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d398fd87-1cc6-475f-95ae-97827de66b2c"
msgid "\\\"What society are you talking about?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9920302-70e8-4afc-aa34-ba09fdaa9151"
msgid "\\\"Well, it was nice to chat, but I have to go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab62ee00-abbf-4c11-9288-cdaf06388666"
msgid "\\\"Could you use any assistance?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc3338a3-fa0f-4c34-922d-9361d92eda47"
msgid "Expelled the Pathfinders from the Stolen Lands on suspicion of spying."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6efc3ec-d462-454d-a802-dc78c31fb481"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't need spies from some society sneaking around here. Get out of my lands "
"immediately!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "146c386a-844e-4fcc-9982-b4ec251b850d"
msgid "Killed a group of Pathfinders."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d574a9f5-fe06-4db8-97cd-c57a140fd14e"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"I'm tired of you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a20c619a-81c8-4fb0-9a1f-d06b1af58c66"
msgid "\\\"The tomb?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e6998341-c6e3-4c9a-abe5-7970c1ac9036"
msgid ""
"{n}A half-orc is wiping the sweat from her brow with a bright jacket decorated "
"with many badges and patches.{/n} \\\"U-u-ugh, that handsome lad gave it to us "
"good! Almost slaughtered us all! Good thing you came by!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ae4778e-2abd-41b6-adc2-17a0b91c69dd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Us? We're a group of Pathfinders from the {g|Pathfinder Society}Society{/g}. "
"We're here on special orders from the Grand Lodge to explore this godforsaken land!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d9040152-b030-40e3-8d28-d98b040e07f9"
msgid "\\\"Yeah... I guess it followed us... walked with us from the tomb!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6bc51df8-35c5-477d-9fc4-1955cd3cbaf9"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc stretches out her hand.{/n} \\\"Wait! I didn't even thank you! I "
"don't know who you are, but thank you for your help. I've never met monsters like "
"this one before, though it's not my first year in the {g|Pathfinder Society}"
"Society{/g}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "299c2b5c-51fd-40ad-9c48-dbfc9ff11d6e"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc freezes for a moment, and then begins to speak again, choosing her "
"words more carefully.{/n} \\\"I didn't mean to offend you, Your... {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}? I've been to many countries, and they "
"address rulers differently everywhere — forgive me if I've made a mistake!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8b127f51-5b64-4e84-a7f8-658cc30a8967"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've come from afar — from {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g}, to be specific. We've "
"heard many interesting tales about the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}... so the "
"{g|Pathfinder Society}Society{/g} decided we should update our maps and surveys! "
"We've no wish to harm or indeed, to bother anyone. We thought it might be easiest "
"if we just came here and performed our duties without getting into all the fuss of "
"an official visit!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "406cbd81-cddf-4911-9c4c-7ff6584d3bb1"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc waves her hand vaguely.{/n} \\\"There's this one place, not far "
"from here. It's labeled with a question mark on all our old maps. So we decided to "
"see what's there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9cae613e-1ce7-48aa-94d7-eb241dda251f"
msgid ""
"{n}The Pathfinder laughs joyfully.{/n} \\\"And just imagine — we didn't find "
"anything. Just the ruins of some old building, and signs of an ancient portal... "
"It appears to be one of the places where the border between worlds is particularly "
"thin. The beast must have smelled us and leapt out to have itself a snack!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42286c04-e52b-47b2-a55d-1ccf8693a0f8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Don't tell me you've never heard of the {g|Pathfinder Society}Pathfinder "
"Society{/g}! We stand at the helm of civilization! We cut the paths to the unknown "
"and unveil even the gloomiest secrets, from which the weak of heart shy away in "
"fear! We...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70351199-533d-4723-9bc2-cc2b0839bf27"
msgid ""
"\\\"But never mind all that. Enough accolades. Here's the truth: the {g|Pathfinder "
"Society}Pathfinder Society{/g} explores {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g}, seeking to "
"reveal its greatest secrets. And we — Pathfinders, lovers of travel and adventure "
"— are the ones who do it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1320e5f-38fa-4e5a-b3d7-64232d8ca5d4"
msgid ""
"\\\"No, no, don't worry yourself! We'll just catch our breath and go... The "
"bruises will be gone by sun up!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8743abde-ab88-48a0-947e-2e7fee0e874a"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc looks around and purses her lips.{/n} \\\"You shouldn't bother... "
"of course, it'll take some time to drag our unlucky friends to the temple... but "
"it's fine — it won't be the first time!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a15c31ee-2f79-43e1-9273-53ec2c57c91a"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc bows to you ceremoniously.{/n} \\\"My regards! If it's {g|Desna}"
"Desna's{/g} will, we will meet again!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f901ce62-a0d6-4e8e-ba56-fc870391b74e"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc becomes gloomy.{/n} \\\"How could you! To accuse the agents of the "
"{g|Pathfinder Society}Society{/g} of espionage?! We'll not set foot in your "
"backwards country ever again!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e23c2da9-a88d-4754-96e8-3169aafc60e8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, yeah, the tomb! It's right there!\\\" {n}The half-orc waves her hand "
"vaguely.{/n} \\\"Anyway, there's nothing interesting in there. Don't waste your "
"time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea13c806-7d0b-4340-ae33-e5830bf321a6"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-orc is wearing a bright jacket decorated with many badges and patches. "
"She looks around and sighs.{/n} \\\"Heh, we suffered some losses... Oh well, on "
"the other hand we got the beast! Thank you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "04233a94-cd8f-46da-a15c-fe4d1e85abad"
msgid "\\\"Hit him!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25809894-d655-4748-a52e-0b5b191f0381"
msgid "\\\"Go for it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1082e85d-8133-47c5-bfc6-ee9e95a1741d"
msgid "\\\"Careful!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c26b8e20-07e5-4a2c-8d46-84f872c81887"
msgid "\\\"Thank you so much, traveler!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c8847ca-9c2a-473c-b44d-a04da4dc1b1a"
msgid "\\\"Ugh... a good fight!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b62554dc-d9f2-4fa6-b08e-f83ed8aab8bd"
msgid "\\\"Anoriel, is that you? I hardly recognize you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c02af37-f748-46a2-b519-8f18696b60e9"
msgid ""
"Allowed the venture-captain to found a Pathfinder Society lodge in the Stolen "
"Lands."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3603e30e-47a3-4c67-af29-7fd88c1b294a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will be happy to see the Pathfinders in these lands. I will allow you to "
"found a lodge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69880e49-70f0-411b-b5df-279c270b91d3"
msgid "\\\"And who exactly will be the Society's representative here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0de7acb5-bc4e-4953-b306-d15301c8eea6"
msgid "Ordered the venture-captain to leave on suspicion of espionage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c666cbe-d310-4a42-9036-37b842216ac3"
msgid ""
"\\\"I trust neither you nor your Society. The Pathfinders are not welcome in my "
"lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "029d892b-dba1-4915-a646-e80c5109d932"
msgid ""
"\\\"How can you guarantee that if I let you in, I won't be letting a wolf among "
"the sheep? Perhaps Absalom is seeking to place a spy in the Stolen Lands?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6f419e3-6586-48cd-a243-bd2ca2882afa"
msgid "Expressed a desire to become a Pathfinder."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ba0cfe0-4655-4423-aef2-6ea18ef6f4c0"
msgid "\\\"I also want to be a Pathfinder. How do I join the Society?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a60fd0c-c15d-4ea1-9595-e64c70558462"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about the Pathfinder Society.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b9ce474e-c2a0-47e3-a73b-f197b7d7b51c"
msgid "\\\"What exactly is this Lodge you want to found?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7fc31739-5fd3-4c1d-a836-355ac91a2b7a"
msgid ""
"Didn't allow the venture-captain to found a Pathfinder Society lodge in the Stolen "
"Lands, because of the dangerous methods of the Pathfinders."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f6bf072-d90e-412e-9f01-c0b40f1b3151"
msgid ""
"\\\"I can't put my subjects at risk. If the Pathfinders make another mistake, and "
"set another affliction loose upon the population, innocent lives might be lost. "
"The Society must accept my refusal.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0818ebaf-81d0-4eb1-bede-20ddb8690136"
msgid ""
"\\\"So members of your Society go to strange lands and make trouble by interfering "
"with things that are none of their concern?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c07d29fc-5843-4046-8dd7-73f85a706422"
msgid "\\\"Enough.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0758f84e-ce9b-422a-abf0-bd444c085576"
msgid ""
"{n}An elf dressed in a neat but somewhat worn doublet stands at attention, then "
"bows to you — his movements precisely measured.{/n} \\\"Greetings, {mf|Your Grace|"
"Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}! My name is Anoriel Eight Eyes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1452aacf-4c2e-4bbb-b872-ba572bdd0ebb"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am here as an official representative of the {g|Pathfinder Society}"
"Pathfinder Society{/g}, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. "
"It's become known in {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g} that certain members of the Society "
"were bothering you of late — or, to be more precise, you were troubled by the "
"consequences of their indiscretion. I formally apologize to you and your subjects, "
"and would like to extend to you, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}, an offer that will be of benefit to all interested parties.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3203a395-ccd9-4e1f-aa9f-733f5c8cb8e0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Please allow a representative of the {g|Pathfinder Society}Pathfinder Society{/"
"g} to remain in the city and lead a local Lodge, to coordinate with other ordinary "
"Pathfinders. We would prefer not to act in this region without the support of the "
"local ruler. The goal of the society is to explore the world we live in, not cause "
"unwanted conflict.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0a1422e-6751-41a5-8635-05e6d98f8400"
msgid ""
"{n}Anoriel giggles and sheds the put-on formality.{/n} \\\"Forgive me, but I'm on "
"a mission from the {g|Pathfinder Society}Society{/g}, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|"
"Your Highness|Your Highness}! After those simpletons in the {g|Valley of the Dead}"
"Valley of the Dead{/g} brought trouble to your door, the Society decided to found "
"a Lodge here — and someone remembered about me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26ac19a8-a472-46ff-8f46-390a94e72523"
msgid ""
"{n}The elf clears her throat.{/n} \\\"I am ready to begin my duties the moment you "
"give your consent. I have been a Pathfinder for many years myself, and have seen "
"many things — things far scarier than what the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} "
"can boast, if I may say so. I'm more than capable of taking care of any newcomers."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab9d43d1-e201-4518-b20a-d843362b6f05"
msgid ""
"{n}Anoriel lowers her head pensively.{/n} \\\"The {g|Pathfinder Society}Pathfinder "
"Society{/g} has upheld a fragile but working truce with dozens of countries for "
"many years. Our reputation guarantees that we will not interfere in your internal "
"affairs.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb22576f-7572-41cc-bf28-9f83eb03a87f"
msgid ""
"{n}The light in Anoriel's eyes fades, she lowers her shoulders as if an invisible "
"burden lay heavily upon them.{/n} \\\"I... will convey your answer to the Grand "
"Lodge. Forgive my intrusion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "93948f65-6543-4093-a7b0-a730217e6c2e"
msgid ""
"{n}Anoriel lights up.{/n} \\\"Thank you! If I may, I will say goodbye for now, and "
"proceed immediately to my duties as venture-captain!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75c77c3a-b8b9-4e9d-a0e6-f832e58c416b"
msgid ""
"{n}Anoriel opens her mouth in astonishment.{/n} \\\"But...\\\" {n}Her expression "
"of surprise is replaced with a mischievous grimace.{/n} \\\"You know, {mf|Your "
"Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}, I would be very happy to have a "
"colleague like you. But you would hardly be able to venture across all the world "
"while you're also ruling an entire country. But when you grow tired of sitting on "
"the throne — then come to me, and we'll talk!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ccf07be-9a2e-456b-84dc-4d5213d45873"
msgid ""
"\\\"Pathfinders are those who can't live at peace in a world full of secrets and "
"riddles. Curiosity drives us from our warm homes, and beyond the rivers and seas, "
"even to the end of the world – and sometimes even beyond! There are plenty of "
"mysteries in the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} — and for the Pathfinders "
"determined to solve them, we should open a local lodge."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca5f6a84-1131-4520-ab1d-f1e9ee99d492"
msgid ""
"\\\"A sanctuary for Pathfinders. A quiet byway, where any member of the {g|"
"Pathfinder Society}Society{/g} can find shelter, protection and a good company. "
"Besides, we'll have a small library devoted to these lands — the flora, fauna, "
"geographic and climatic peculiarities, history and traditions — all of this "
"knowledge will be stored at the lodge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7978d3f9-9257-4d35-9ca5-f58d5d6cacd6"
msgid "\\\"As you wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63a89d03-34ec-4c89-a900-3f2d968251de"
msgid ""
"\\\"Events related to... um... oh yes, the {g|Valley of the Dead}Valley of the "
"Dead{/g}… That was a tragic accident no mortal could escape. Sometimes, evil lurks "
"in the depths, and bursts upon us from nowhere. Though it's true that some "
"Pathfinders are not so concerned about the safety of others...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f30058e-05ec-4705-9d73-650dd1deadd3"
msgid ""
"{n}Anoriel Eight Eyes looks unusually neat: her hair is clean and brushed, her "
"clothes spotless, and her elven face is lit with unusual enthusiasm. When she "
"speaks, it becomes clear that she's choosing her words much more carefully than "
"usual.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a2d2539-82ff-4e9f-a2c6-9c4055aae919"
msgid ""
"\\\"I received a message from the Society just yesterday. If you agree, I will "
"become the local venture-captain!\\\" {n}The elf shakes her hair.{/n} \\\"And you "
"know what? I've idled about enough. You can't undo what's done, and I'm no good as "
"a Pathfinder any more. But at least I can serve others. I learned a lot about the "
"Stolen Lands in the years I spent here — enough for a couple of textbooks! So if "
"you agree to the Lodge...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "157ae67e-0d40-40e6-9bd5-5ef4d26ac8a1"
msgid ""
"\\\"But the {g|Pathfinder Society}Society{/g} is what it is. It accepts any "
"applicant who wishes to become a Pathfinder, and sends its followers to all the "
"corners of Golarion. — That's the only way to preserve balance. And without "
"balance, the Society would have become advocates of this or that idea a long time "
"ago.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "939f39c9-667a-4c8e-9320-27ebdeefda5e"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c38ad5a1-2e11-43a7-8545-f80d251a79b6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your {mf|grace|grace|highness|highness}! Thank you for finding time to visit "
"this humble corner of your gods-blessed {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}! How "
"can I be of service?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9dca56d1-5a0c-40ac-91bd-135a06eeafa0"
msgid "\\\"May the gods never abandon you in their mercy!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6e47720-e843-4a49-9ab2-edaba74dec34"
msgid "\\\"What is this place? Where is it?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19f468fb-c0e4-493b-bd30-9aab3660886a"
msgid "\\\"I will go there as soon as I am able.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c549e4a5-be2f-437d-95d2-0806e8c3f8ed"
msgid "\\\"Well, what do you suggest?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de392d28-db71-47dc-b047-83798113d93f"
msgid "\\\"I'm not interested.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19be5e35-9438-417c-a39b-caf5b71a5236"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace! Allow me to congratulate you on receiving the title of baron{mf||"
"ess}! I am confident that you will be able to bring order to these troubled lands."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "773d848f-9065-469e-921a-5662d1204dd9"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod stumbles slightly.{/n} \\\"Though to be honest, that isn't exactly what we "
"wanted to speak to you about. Tristian and I have been talking a great deal about "
"what happened at the Temple of the Elk. It doesn't all make sense to us yet, but "
"one thing is clear — there's a powerful curse at work. It corrupted the very "
"essence of that sacred place, steeping it with putrescence. Ugh! I am disgusted "
"with whoever could do this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4aca7af7-19ed-4638-be24-dc9bc1bf8f6f"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod exhales loudly, catching his breath.{/n} \\\"And now there is a new woe! "
"Tristian and I believe the curse did not simply disperse of its own accord! There "
"is a place near the capital rumored by the locals to be cursed. Tristian and I "
"visited this dreadful place, and we felt the same putrescence as at the Temple of "
"the Elk!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "604440fc-76f0-46da-9886-4d41e5deeda8"
msgid ""
"\\\"I would be happy to accompany you, but I would not expect to see anything new "
"there at present.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aca77cb7-78e0-4721-8560-3117b00368c2"
msgid ""
"\\\"There is a Bald Hilltop not far from here, to the north of the capital. Its "
"crown is entirely barren of life. The locals believe that rituals glorifying the "
"dark gods were held there, back in ancient times. There is no longer any trace of "
"such rituals, but the air around the hilltop is heavy to the point of stifling. "
"This place is like a rotting wound, closed but not healed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a9cbed4-7016-45b8-b0ac-880f311809fc"
msgid ""
"\\\"And this wound will undoubtedly open again! Tristian and I felt something "
"approaching... Something ominous. The curse will soon return to plague us once "
"more – I swear by {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02301d0c-904f-4ad9-b4c4-b654f4289847"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian looks at you, confused.{/n} \\\"Are you sure? The threat could be even "
"more serious than we imagine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3300265-aeb3-4a46-97e1-8dddd8b75fe0"
msgid ""
"\\\"In any case, we can't do anything right now anyway. Tristian and I have been "
"to this hilltop. There's nothing there!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44648bff-4317-4493-95d5-7df285e9fcd4"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agree with Tristian! We have been to this hilltop. It's barren, but filled "
"with a dense atmosphere of unease!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91ed19b7-6fbc-4c5b-ae6e-0c57cde64487"
msgid ""
"\\\"The curse will grow in strength, and we predict it will reach the peak of its "
"strength in about one month. That's when we should visit the Bald Hilltop and "
"resolve this issue.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20d40806-d737-4454-a566-c5d11aa7501d"
msgid "\\\"For now we can only wait. And prepare.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02931bcf-5fef-4cd1-a690-c24d7d30a1b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"We beg your pardon, Your Grace, for intervening with you getting the grasp of "
"your barony. I'm sure you have even more pressing matters at hand right now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ecaeb81-3632-4b97-8a7d-bb2919fabcb8"
msgid "\\\"What? Again?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4bcc95ca-ff58-4f38-a55e-68f3e2af5d70"
msgid "\\\"How much time do we have?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96ca607b-8568-453f-99c5-54eaf67b94f7"
msgid "\\\"Well, let's prepare for the next attack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c009a0d0-91e2-4bc6-8905-55c8bc170ba7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I want to deal with this problem once and for all. What do you recommend?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f1d6f22-60f3-42c8-8822-8ee4a61c4706"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, we are victorious! We fought off the spider invasion, and defeated "
"the strange dryad who led them! As a sign of gratitude, your subjects have a "
"special reward for you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29d66635-bdf6-4a58-b6ab-da7822a51a5d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, we've finally cleared all of the spiders from the barony – though "
"it wasn't easy. Several people died, poisoned by spiders. Some cattle perished... "
"But for the most part, everything worked out.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22a0510f-78ca-4c96-8f46-e5a3ea81fb09"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace! The barony suffered huge losses during the spider invasion. Their "
"poison killed everything – people, and livestock alike. Thank the gods that the "
"spiders suddenly disappeared a few days ago, as if they had never been here at "
"all. I don't even know how we managed to survive this invasion. But I do know this "
"– a great many of your subjects will henceforth recoil in fear whenever they see a "
"spider.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8beb46f9-76e9-4650-9b12-0e7c24cd7ed2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I wonder – was this flood of spiders truly caused by that curse? I mean, the "
"curse must be ancient and very ominous. The spiders were definitely scary as well, "
"but they weren't ancient and ominous.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8522c05-a0d6-4979-90ff-4497f1610643"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agree with Linzi. This does seem strange. Seems more like the plot of an "
"insane dryad than a true curse.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a2397197-71a2-40b4-af49-781bb1c6fa84"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then how can we explain the dismal atmosphere on the Bald Hilltop? The "
"pressure both of us felt there, Jhod? Maybe the curse drove the poor dryad insane, "
"causing her to lead this spider invasion into the barony?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fbc1858b-a5ba-4815-8746-f8ece36e05a3"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian shakes his head incredulously.{/n} \\\"In any case, I have alarming "
"news. As soon as the spider invasion was over, I visited the Bald Hilltop again. "
"It's grown quiet once more... and just as gloomy as before. I don't think the "
"curse is broken, just laying low — like a monster that rests before it feeds again."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94aa26d6-4240-4fbf-946c-760a04d9d40e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I... am sorry for bringing the bad news. Unfortunately, we failed to defeat "
"this curse for good.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b13c586-f591-4445-91de-a9cfb6669964"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian nods.{/n} \\\"Very wise. If only we knew more about the curse – we "
"might figure out some way to fight it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0508d165-0e19-44d5-a709-a43b9093a6d1"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi frowns.{/n} \\\"I don't understand. I spoke to the locals — they never "
"had any spider invasions before. And nothing ever happened on the Bald Hilltop "
"before, either. Now both spiders and the curse — right when the new barony "
"appeared in the Stolen Lands. All of this seems highly coincidental!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a5b4a85-5fe6-4fa2-a1f6-44558547253e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, a fair amount! I'd say half a year, or even more. Now that the Bald "
"Hilltop is quiet again, I can barely feel its evil will. I'm sure we will have "
"enough time to prepare for the next attack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "403cffeb-d83d-4edd-899a-f2502e75a65f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes, let's level the Bald Hilltop to the ground and put an end to the curse!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d10307b-05b2-4334-905f-33054ddcd953"
msgid ""
"\\\"I doubt we will be able to defeat it in such a... straightforward fashion. The "
"heart of the curse is undoubtedly centered on the Bald Hilltop, but the spiders "
"appeared all throughout the barony. I don't think we are going to do any damage to "
"the curse by destroying the hilltop. I would expect exactly the opposite — we'd "
"only provoke it into attacking again, immediately on the heels of the last. No, "
"the best we can do for now is make sure we're prepared for the next attack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3274ef2f-5ae2-4264-a00d-5c74689c4d77"
msgid ""
"\\\"Don't be such a pessimist, Tristian! We might truly be able to overcome the "
"curse — but only by studying it thoroughly. Your Grace, I will gather all the "
"information available on this situation and get to work.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a7f66af-336c-47c3-904f-20c8536eb0d6"
msgid "\\\"Do we still know nothing about this curse?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65ae87ae-8c8e-440f-a97a-840464d729b6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Looks like we don't have a choice, then. We'll wait and prepare for the next "
"attack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5cbe9768-3e16-4d11-87ec-174f7cb2cd97"
msgid "Supported Tristian."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84420d5b-23b3-433a-85f3-b9217c8ce963"
msgid "\\\"Linzi is right. You're too hard on yourself, Tristian.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02364389-2617-4009-a3c6-095aa4d95c81"
msgid "Asked Tristian to focus on finding a solution to the curse."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30b42fdb-c49a-49e9-84f0-a41ca004db69"
msgid ""
"\\\"You should focus on solving the problem, Tristian, rather than blaming "
"yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3924fbd6-7f8d-4e34-bc95-be9759defba7"
msgid "Accused Tristian of laziness in handling the curse."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "077d2ce6-8436-4779-a10c-89f4ded853f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're idling, Tristian. Your negligence is only helping the curse defeat us.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96b2f47c-ebdd-47e9-9df9-bff12a2f7b46"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian's face glows with happiness.{/n} \\\"We made it! The second cursed "
"attack was repelled, and the grateful citizens of the barony have a special reward "
"for you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "307ed4f7-3c47-4c58-b1f9-47f0b5c8ff35"
msgid ""
"\\\"The second attack is over. It wasn't easy, but the barony endured it – thanks "
"in great part to the strength and bravery of your subjects. After surviving this "
"cycle of assaults, they are not easily caught off guard. It's a relief, but I "
"don't think it's something we should necessarily be celebrating."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f74556bf-c68d-46f8-a84d-b0eae4a6152b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The second attack was especially brutal. With great difficulty, your subjects "
"managed to fight off the invasion of wild beasts. Many perished... I pray Sarenrae "
"accepts their souls.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d72e7fbd-2376-4870-8909-32a07b619625"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian looks at you thoughtfully and sighs.{/n} \\\"Unfortunately, I must "
"bring you bad news again. The Bald Hilltop lays silent for the moment, but another "
"attack is certain to come soon."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ab129a1-9701-4a7f-861b-293a8f5feab6"
msgid ""
"Well, nothing that can help us contain it. Once every few months it drives nearby "
"animals, monsters, and other beasts insane, sending them into a bloodthirsty "
"rampage. I... don't know what action we can take on this. The only way I can help "
"is by roughly predicting when the next attack will begin. Forgive me, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51cc6acf-3e44-4a86-a650-d59e10127fd5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Don't be so hard on yourself, Tristian! Even knowing when to get ready is an "
"important thing to know! I don't know how we'd handle these attacks if they "
"happened without warning.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "10a23adb-d81b-478a-9750-092242271249"
msgid "{n}Tristian just nods, looking down gloomily.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "abdb10c0-f705-4365-9199-712817cb1e91"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian lowers his head.{/n} \\\"Thank you. Your support means much to me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2da30448-d867-44a1-a866-25e3dc0ab6bf"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will do everything in my power to free these lands from the curse. – I "
"promise!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3b45eac1-d5be-4a1d-91f9-a948c8a618e7"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian winces and takes a step back.{/n} \\\"I... forgive me. Please forgive "
"me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ebb1ccd-9dd0-44b5-821c-479eb68a9d80"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't have anything useful to add. The locals are either oblivious to the "
"curse's origins, or they're too scared to talk. I'd be better off reading ancient "
"books on curses...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1954c011-fafb-4869-b631-b781b0225eda"
msgid "\\\"If this isn't a curse — then what could it be?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af3ee414-1e3a-4e5a-916a-b72dd574997e"
msgid "\\\"I'm more interested in defeating it than understanding it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b88531a4-40b4-4ca6-a25c-1af6e3df538f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Whoever or whatever caused these attacks, I am sure they will continue. We "
"must be ready to repel the next one.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fea6ef94-2b28-4d7c-9f88-d279ee040b58"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hooray! We did it! Another attack has been repelled, and the barony is "
"stronger than ever! Your grateful subjects even brought you a gift to honor this "
"outstanding success!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d464471f-6b3f-45a7-867f-28bc90781cf3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Alas, despite our best efforts, the latest assault rolled through the barony "
"like an invading empire. We did fight it off eventually, but at a cost. Let's "
"prepare better next time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e18b2e8a-d65c-4a61-b75f-7fc78f7ed7ba"
msgid ""
"\\\"This curse and its attacks — they're getting more and more vicious! The "
"monsters ravaged many villages and slaughtered scores of subjects. To be honest, "
"I'm not sure we'll be able to endure another one.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bee6d9a0-8b52-46a7-af0c-3d9ce8536f81"
msgid ""
"\\\"Unfortunately, now is no time to rest. While everyone was preparing for the "
"last attack, I was looking for a way to overcome the curse. I read some ancient "
"books, talked to the locals... and then I had a word with our Storyteller. And we "
"decided that... Well, he'll tell it better.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc4fef12-f831-4a18-999d-3391a9ac0ce8"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller clears his throat.{/n} \\\"I am a keeper of stories, Your "
"Grace, and I have amassed a respectable collection over my long life. There are, "
"of course, stories of curses among them — ancient and dark, having taken thousands "
"of lives, destroyed kingdoms and brought down...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7bdec1d9-5dc3-4e6f-97ef-6e8aff3b0661"
msgid "{n}Tristian turns pale.{/n} \\\"It's not a curse? Then what is it?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f8e85c7-69d4-40a6-97b8-ecbfb68d388d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, our curse isn't exactly a real curse. We think there is someone specific "
"behind these attacks! Oh, I'm sorry.\\\" {n}Realizing she interrupted the "
"Storyteller, Linzi turns bright red.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ffcabb9b-be7b-41aa-aa45-7b11ea71f9d1"
msgid ""
"\\\"We don't know yet! But that part doesn't matter!\\\" {n}Linzi waves her hand "
"carelessly.{/n} \\\"What's important is that we're finally making some real "
"progress!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3feac68e-3286-4469-8ea5-23113f60e85d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I would imagine that the person behind these attacks is someone harboring "
"great evil against you and your barony. I would not be surprised if it's the same "
"adversary who was behind the Bloom.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f98cca1a-9483-4a0a-8b28-27ef871543d0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Pff! With swords and spells, of course! You can't chop an ancient curse to "
"bits, but I'm sure the villain behind the attacks would suffice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c692605-363e-485b-81f8-2eef5c420143"
msgid ""
"\\\"Linzi, I think the baron{mf||ess} is asking whether we yet know the name of "
"our adversary. Alas, the answer to that question is no, at least for now. "
"Personally, I believe it is the work of some fey. – I recognize their hand, so to "
"speak.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "069a80a4-4c2b-4fc8-a1c8-20c651effaff"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's exactly what we'll do! Sooner or later, the villain will show himself. "
"Once he slips up, we can finally punish him for all the trouble he's caused!\\"
"\" {n}Linzi frowns belligerently.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb84dcd0-39f3-448b-8100-6fa099d82412"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian chuckles faintly.{/n} \\\"I didn't expect such vitriol from you, "
"Linzi. In any case, I would advise hearing this villain out before punishing him. "
"We still have no idea why this unknown enemy is targeting us in particular.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bc18d2a4-40a4-4212-816c-b07f1ba649e8"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm sure we'll know our foe's face soon enough. We've repelled his attacks "
"three times now. He must be reaching the limits of his patience! He won't get away "
"with this forever!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e20d2274-ccd3-4dae-8c0b-5ed2b39e076d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agree! After the last attack, I got the feeling that the owlbears and "
"manticores came here as revenge for what we did to the Everblooming Flower.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ccb0dea3-5756-4585-9166-9d39fdd37e57"
msgid "\\\"The attacks will continue?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a8bf1ad-ae24-4f0f-aced-47ee13a397c6"
msgid "Assured Tristian of your support."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dcbc9e67-f039-43bd-8889-53c2ba719056"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tristian, I will help you earn forgiveness. Together we will defeat Nyrissa.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "921eeca4-605f-411c-8078-abc5113c0e99"
msgid "Advised Tristian to let go of his past mistakes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6676f715-d10e-47be-bdf7-d1a5df9a9f6d"
msgid "\\\"Forget about your past mistakes, Tristian. Focus on your future!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b03f6f73-ae61-46da-a7da-723feb6078d9"
msgid "Threatened Tristian with execution if he fails to redeem himself."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9609f7b3-68ea-4319-abcb-a553927c4148"
msgid ""
"\\\"You'd better work hard to atone for your mistakes, Tristian – unless you want "
"to beg for my executioner's forgiveness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f66bbf92-277e-4ff2-a3b3-1c9f7e7384e0"
msgid ""
"\\\"We will prepare for the next attack. It doesn't matter who's behind it. We "
"won't let them win.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c61c9d54-bb58-451d-9032-1bc702a6eb33"
msgid ""
"\\\"A new day, and a fresh victory, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your "
"Highness}! Another attack has been repelled, and your grateful subjects have a "
"special reward for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b8a7889-3a37-4f7c-9081-a74474dece39"
msgid ""
"\\\"The fey who attacked you did significant damage to your {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom}, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Through "
"the great efforts of yourself and your subjects, the attackers were defeated. "
"Those who were not killed on the battlefield fled to shelter in the nearby "
"forests. We've earned a well-deserved respite.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b403382-d88b-4b64-8734-f0d561e11fdf"
msgid ""
"\\\"The fey who attacked you did significant damage to your {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom}, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}. Your "
"subjects were left to fend for themselves or flee, and some of the villages have "
"been reduced to rubble. In others there are nothing but empty houses. Entire "
"families have abandoned the {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom} for safer lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7c71411-94c8-4f64-a447-1840521c1aab"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi gives you an oddly serious look.{/n} \\\"Well, we know who was behind the "
"attacks. It was Tristian, wasn't it?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3a5e511-aad5-46d3-8f7f-61c28bd5de9e"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi gives Tristian an oddly serious look.{/n} \\\"It was you who was behind "
"the attacks, wasn't it? But... why?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4b6040b-cc20-4217-99b6-5013d81ac98a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I can't wait to see Tristian again – and ask him all the questions that are "
"swimming in my head. Why did he betray us? He was so gentle and kind. We were "
"friends!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "278944de-b977-498a-b9ea-52df0d1c41a7"
msgid ""
"\\\"He was so soft and kind... He was our friend. My mind is telling me he's a "
"traitor, and we did the right thing to get rid of him. But my heart doesn't want "
"to believe it. I... I miss him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "062e8e94-695b-460d-bb8c-b3d0e2a8c064"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller's voice is quiet but firm.{/n} \\\"In any case, I doubt that "
"Tristian's absence will in any way prevent the next attack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1d261e1b-b466-4458-8ffd-2905073ea38b"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian drops his head limply.{/n} \\\"Yes. At least, to a certain extent. "
"My... lady...\\\" {n}Tristian's lips curve scornfully.{/n} \\\"Nyrissa ordered me "
"to open the way for creatures from the {g|First World}First World{/g}. I've often "
"traveled between worlds, so it was not a difficult thing to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "245e160a-2987-4edf-a903-487ede67c05a"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Golarion}Golarion{/g} is closely connected to the First World. Spontaneous "
"portals between the two worlds are not uncommon. – All I did was give one such "
"portal some extra stability. Once every few months it opened wide enough to allow "
"Nyrissa's creatures to come charging through.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e6164efc-3cda-4046-b8f4-7ffc014d3cb0"
msgid ""
"\\\"What I did was terrible. People were dying all the time – because of me! And I "
"could do nothing but warn them of the next attack. I mourn the losses every day. "
"My only hope is that one day I will be able to make up for these evil acts.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46578834-411b-4a8f-ac41-b9a9a4956f4b"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller's voice is quiet but firm.{/n} \\\"In any case, I doubt that "
"Tristian's repentance will somehow prevent the next attack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ceb0e65-5c6a-49ab-8480-9aaa9bc7b7e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"As with the Everblooming Flower, I only helped Nyrissa open a portal from the "
"First World to Golarion. I am not the one leading her armies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15290d76-ca62-4b98-8bef-a92093cb62f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"I seriously doubt that Tristian was the one behind the attacks. I said before "
"that I detected the magic of the fey, and I remain sure of it. I think Tristian "
"was only an accessory to our true foe.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c7d282e-eeb6-42ad-9602-f06fa9b16da1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't deserve your help… But as Sarenrae is my witness, I am eternally "
"grateful to you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ebc6e7e-31ee-455c-b87c-eee879629433"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian chuckles joylessly.{/n} \\\"That is not as easy as it seems. My "
"mistakes will stay with me to the end of my days. But I refuse to spend my time "
"wallowing in despair. — I will dedicate myself to repairing what I've done!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b9bfde4f-60e7-4672-a46a-92bf429745e9"
msgid "{n}Tristian turns even paler, but answers with a determined nod.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bbc4cb1f-dc0e-46fb-97fe-892a84537ffc"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller nods.{/n} \\\"I am sure of it. Your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|"
"kingdom} is far stronger than your enemies imagine. – As you remind them from time "
"to time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7bb67c5c-a048-417f-96fc-11e5588efb83"
msgid ""
"\\\"How soon until Nyrissa is able to bring the full power of her army down upon "
"us?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e19a8d5-3be6-4746-8400-7ca3bf7b9092"
msgid "Assured Tristian of your support."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44b9ece2-d8dd-4b0f-b442-b7f6405ea97a"
msgid "Advised Tristian to let go of his past mistakes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "188c63c7-f8c3-446e-a624-533a6b1fd93f"
msgid "Threatened Tristian with execution if he fails to redeem himself."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ce5b05f-8af7-4b43-87e6-05a38fe915a6"
msgid "\\\"We must prepare for Nyrissa's next attack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd40b47d-850a-449c-863f-3a55b84ffede"
msgid "\\\"Why do you think the attacks keep getting more dangerous?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "582eafee-66b9-491b-9246-b73994871089"
msgid ""
"\\\"Can we use the portal on the Bald Hilltop to get to the First World and battle "
"Nyrissa?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "faf47551-3b10-462d-950d-8e51c4bead87"
msgid ""
"\\\"No matter what curses the denizens of the First World cast upon you, no matter "
"what cruel tactics they use, you repel them all with valor! Bravo, Your Highness. "
"Accept this humble gift as a sign of gratitude from your subjects.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63644296-0e5b-4c25-88cf-9b0e28a9a05e"
msgid ""
"\\\"The attacks on your kingdom grow more and more brutal, and increasingly harder "
"to repel. Fortunately we stood our ground again, but will we be able to keep it up?"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d56ddfca-7fe3-411b-bdfa-950b3a955ac2"
msgid ""
"\\\"The attacks on your kingdom grow more and more brutal, and increasingly harder "
"to repel. I have a feeling that we're just biding our time until the end.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "866fa257-2145-4ab8-b34a-cd23592a1d44"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi chuckles carelessly.{/n} \\\"Whatever Nyrissa has planned, I'm sure we "
"can handle it. Each of her attacks is stronger than the last, but we're getting "
"stronger too!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca4db7f0-634f-4105-9134-30f7469f16b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd assume her strength has nearly reached its peak. We might not be there "
"yet, but the next assault will surely be especially dangerous.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31d5e3d7-75c2-4407-a421-495c5ac648d1"
msgid ""
"\\\"We will prepare well! Just let her try to come at us again! — We'll beat her "
"back to where she came from! I'll cap our victory by writing a song about her, a "
"really funny and embarrassing one! Everyone in the First World will be singing it "
"for her!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f07520f2-81ae-4e8e-91a1-25223d024ff8"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian's whisper is barely audible.{/n} \\\"In any case, it won't be long...\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c5b449c-bc1e-4837-8855-11cc7a8fa707"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think Nyrissa has been playing with us! If she attacked at full strength a "
"few years ago, when the barony of {kingdomname} was still in the cradle, we "
"couldn't possibly have endured. I bet she still needed to keep us alive for "
"something. But now that we've lost our usefulness, she's decided to finish us off."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a02e19e-5294-4b78-b8c5-d4b38039a715"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have a different theory. This 'curse' from the Bald Hilltop is an unstable "
"portal, a bridge between {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g} and the {g|First World}First "
"World{/g}. And the more it is used, the more firmly anchored it becomes, which "
"allows Nyrissa to send through more and more powerful armies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "532118d9-09c6-41e5-9907-5e853b443c73"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think both of you are right. The stability of the portal does play an "
"important role in the increasing power of Nyrissa's attacks. However, it is true "
"that she allowed the barony of {kingdomname} to get on its feet — at least when it "
"was newly formed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70ebcb75-0ffa-4ed0-bdb9-c0abaff36075"
msgid ""
"\\\"Alas, not yet. The passage between worlds is not reliable. We can't be sure of "
"where it will take us, or if it will activate at all. Such is the nature of "
"unstable First World portals.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bc69ae0-7671-4aec-a656-fb7f6f418e93"
msgid ""
"\\\"Such a portal is unreliable even for denizens of the First World. We only see "
"a small portion of the hordes that Nyrissa sends through the portal to attack us. "
"Nyrissa... doesn't care what happens to the countless who go missing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "012c2f33-ea8d-4abe-8166-b721ba43539e"
msgid ""
"\\\"However, with each attack the portal becomes more and more stable. I would "
"imagine that soon the passage will become a steady bridge between Golarion and the "
"First World. We only need to wait for that moment to attack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "93ee04a5-ab07-4745-9439-1bfb6642384f"
msgid "\\\"Can we use the portal on the Bald Hilltop to get to the First World?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc489a82-5a80-4d6e-9ff7-15b4bd7b59bc"
msgid "\\\"In any case, first we will have to repel the attack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45aaae2a-0916-4353-afb9-7fcd8bda4d62"
msgid "\\\"Do you think Nyrissa will appear personally to command the attack?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a2376ab-95e5-4cef-9116-4a42f7c9f05c"
msgid "\\\"Are you sure this attack will be the Last?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25541b1d-a453-4d94-abbd-515cf42573ad"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, the Wild Hunt has been defeated! Your quick and effective "
"actions left the attackers no hope. Your grateful subjects would like to present "
"you with this humble gift.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acea2fe3-7595-46f1-ace2-0e37f62ca827"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, after sustained fighting, the Wild Hunt has finally retreated. "
"We were successfully able to protect the kingdom, but the price we paid was dear. "
"Still, our victory gives me hope.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18ccc901-3b2c-400a-859e-23ff802fb770"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, the Wild Hunt ravaged your kingdom with fire and sword. With "
"great difficulty we managed to repel them, but the losses we suffered were "
"tremendous. I shudder to imagine what the next attack might bring.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41e8e272-a0d1-4378-bdc3-de8f45015373"
msgid ""
"\\\"Another attack awaits, though I doubt it will come soon. I have a feeling that "
"Nyrissa won't hold back this time. It will be the most terrible blow yet. I only "
"hope we can survive it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6c95304-f7e2-4d2e-a9a4-e2b17451035f"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agree with the Storyteller. I've visited the Bald Hilltop, and the portal to "
"the First World is almost stable. It appears that by the time of the next attack, "
"it will be steady enough to become a permanent bridge between Golarion and the "
"First World.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5b233dd-5dd4-41ca-ad2a-d327468fcfbc"
msgid ""
"\\\"The way I see it, we've had enough of being afraid of her! If Nyrissa wants to "
"attack us herself — then let her come! But she won't, will she? She's going to "
"hide from us, tucked away in the First World until the bitter end! I suggest we "
"deal with her army here, and then move immediately to counter-attack! – Before she "
"musters the strength for another invasion!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6eed18ff-ded3-4bf8-9508-faccc5325acd"
msgid ""
"\\\"I suppose so. The portal used to snap shut after every attack, but by now it "
"should be a reliable passage to the First World. It probably leads directly to "
"Nyrissa's lair, wherever that may be!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43a7d690-fb51-4a76-9dfc-6248e284e426"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian's face is determined.{/n} \\\"I agree with your plan. We will enter "
"the portal I helped create, and end the war I helped begin.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84120e5e-3096-4c31-80af-18e4d799693d"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller nods gravely.{/n} \\\"This will be a difficult battle. We "
"shouldn't underestimate the enemy — especially one as cunning as Nyrissa.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4fb2f55e-c6d1-463b-9bf8-f1e474535040"
msgid ""
"\\\"I bet she won't. It isn't her style. She likes just watching from a distance "
"while she plans her next insidious trick. But I think she's just plain afraid of "
"us!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3be652f4-7143-4499-9571-2739e2b5734f"
msgid ""
"\\\"When you deal with the fey, you can't be sure of anything. My guess, however, "
"is based more in fact than speculation. Never before has there been a portal to "
"the First World that is so stable…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "67a1ebfe-5edf-421c-a42e-e4abab9049a9"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've also cornered Nyrissa like never before! I'm bet she's absolutely beside "
"herself!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2a891a4-c14b-40fd-a77a-2ef8678fb54e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tristian, you helped Nyrissa open portals to Golarion. Can you open a portal "
"to the First World?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b81fbba0-fd8b-4375-8156-2ef1f740cc84"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nyrissa deserves a thousand executions after all she's done to my kingdom. And "
"I will be there to carry out her sentence personally.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27c1b96e-f50f-4960-9f22-dc33b5d8f321"
msgid ""
"\\\"Creating a portal, hiding behind the myth of a nonexistent ancient curse... "
"Nyrissa is cunning! I would applaud her, if we weren't sworn enemies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e236b89-63d4-4e9a-935c-56b48a83589f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ha! All the forces she sent to challenge me have failed. I can't wait to meet "
"her. – I'll see her bathing in her own blood."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d83c1ad4-eabc-4d4a-b369-818d7b344f76"
msgid ""
"Expressed your opinion about the destruction of the portal on the Bald Hilltop."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fed49a07-6961-4e2c-8f2e-963ff7bbc151"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nyrissa won't escape justice! We repelled her attacks – this time it's her "
"turn to repel ours!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2951c11-c158-460c-8630-9f60f08a2b27"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nyrissa failed to push her advantage, and made a strategic mistake. You "
"shouldn't attack if you're unsure of victory.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "01b66513-a28e-4a24-ad43-9d06043d404c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, Nyrissa's army has been crushed! Even their Jabberwock was "
"slain! This victory is a major triumph for your subjects, and they have a special "
"gift for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91689d81-3f3a-4bb5-b6f7-45fe60a6c231"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, we protected the kingdom! Nyrissa's Jabberwock-led army was "
"powerful, and the battle was grim. Nevertheless, our foe was defeated, and the "
"portal on the Bald Hilltop was destroyed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a11bcbdc-a61f-4996-885d-5e3cf079a5e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness! Nyrissa's attack was devastating. I... I don't know how we "
"managed to survive. And I don't know if we'll ever fully recover. Only the death "
"of the Jabberwock finally broke the resolve of her forces.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7d496b6-b73f-4b97-9c3e-d956551bc48e"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a pity the portal to the First World was destroyed! I wish I could go "
"there right now and look that witch in the eye myself! I bet she was so terrified "
"of us that she destroyed the portal herself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1f58f92-a32c-453a-b407-37b553bf96c2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Or perhaps the death of the Jabberwock caused the portal's destruction. It's "
"unlikely we'll ever find out.\\\" {n}Tristian's voice fills with resolution.{/n} \\"
"\"It's all right. We will find another path to Nyrissa's lair. She won't be able "
"to avoid retribution forever.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9540afa9-af7c-451d-bc6d-15f62b1255bb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Portals to the First World are complicated and unpredictable. I managed to "
"open two with some degree of success — for the Everblooming Flower and at the Bald "
"Hilltop. However, those were the only two cases of success among dozens of "
"failures. Besides, the task would require much more time than we have. I prepared "
"both of these portals a long time ago, then waited for the right time to use them."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08ef72fc-67df-4fe0-b046-ee76729b8421"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian sighs.{/n} \\\"Also, I just don't feel comfortable doing it. Portals "
"to the First World are dangerous, and I've caused enough harm to give me pause "
"before attempting another dangerous move. I'm sure there must be another way to "
"the First World.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0824410a-4ee8-4c79-89bf-0e6131a314d9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I agree! I couldn't have said it better myself! Let's show that villain she "
"picked a fight she couldn't win!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eeacc08c-2d26-4e78-a0fe-943921f7ab37"
msgid ""
"\\\"I would put it differently, but I support the sentiment! Let's show that "
"villain she picked a fight she couldn't win!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6e08d8f-f5d1-44b6-a7f8-247c5ee98117"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hey, what's wrong with you? Don't applaud her! Villains don't deserve praise! "
"She deserves a beating for all the trouble she's caused – and the sooner the "
"better!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "045c8915-42ad-43ec-9b06-27a233370629"
msgid "Unstable portal"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ed0e9a5-eff6-4cd5-abd2-04f27d04e128"
msgid ""
"The portal to the First World was destroyed. It will probably never operate again."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3c1c392-e552-4131-8e5f-64a5dc0ff5b1"
msgid ""
"A fragment of an ancient pillar, covered with eroded letters of unknown language."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e910ad8-14a4-4d60-9576-7cc78b8b10ed"
msgid ""
"\\\"Remember this Tuskgutter I wanted to slay? I mean that big boar. Well, forget "
"about it. Some hunters have got him already. And… Never mind, it doesn't matter "
"anymore.\\\" {n}With a sour face, the barbarian waves her hand.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d98f5858-f5db-43bf-a25d-8d0f6e6c516a"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri looks unusually grim today.{/n} \\\"Listen… We need to talk. But not in "
"front of everyone. After the council ends — come to the tavern. It's about my "
"tribe. My old one from before.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf4a21a2-07f8-4793-ad38-c73d5971e962"
msgid ""
"\\\"I kind of... I wanted to ask you something about my tribe... It's — forget it, "
"it doesn't matter anymore. They're gone now — so hell with them! We have enough to "
"do without those scums, right?\\\" {n}Amiri tries to force a grin, but fails. You "
"can see that she's upset, but not inclined to talk about it.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed449e48-1bc9-4e05-9ee3-7c564541550e"
msgid ""
"\\\"About my tribe... Forget it, it doesn't matter any more. They're gone now. To "
"hell with them — I don't want to see them anyway!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5bab3fb-0d19-4224-a0ed-db855f65f5a5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Come to the tavern after the council. We need to talk. About my damn tribe, "
"and {d|Nilak}Nilak{/d}. And about the ghost. Will you come? I will wait. I will "
"try not to get drunk, but I really want to.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61af482e-11de-462c-b285-32e1a3a5a721"
msgid ""
"Agreed that throwing a party to cheer up Ekun is your duty as his comrade-in-arms."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "258e5b39-b98a-49b8-8c64-a7791a8b7441"
msgid ""
"\\\"Helping Ekun is our comradely duty. And if we need to throw a feast to do that "
"— then that's what we're going to do!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb1f04ae-dd61-4640-8884-7a5f56770213"
msgid "\\\"What are you getting at?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f8dbf3a-d021-4a08-8dbe-0598064da3a4"
msgid "\\\"Wonderful. What does this have to do with me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25b948dd-67d1-41bd-b788-a193df49a7d4"
msgid "Refused to help cheer up Ekun."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9166762a-0c10-43a2-a94f-d2470baeebd0"
msgid ""
"\\\"No. My responsibilities do not include consoling or entertaining any of you.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d1d81333-f862-491e-a03e-060b2818f6a3"
msgid "Agreed to throw a party to cheer up Ekun."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87db5ad9-c62b-4a0b-8360-7b1b815a10ec"
msgid ""
"\\\"You are right. I can't stand looking at Ekun's glum face any longer — time to "
"cheer him up!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c1cbbd0-c64c-470a-b323-f49f29a88558"
msgid "Agreed to throw a party for Ekun to help him restore emotional balance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "248ea128-9952-4705-8496-d8f3c5bd6a65"
msgid ""
"\\\"Neither grief nor joy should be excessive. I think you've got a point.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23937a51-5587-47f6-bd79-aff8c711083b"
msgid "\\\"I don't have time for this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a84d52d3-4265-4ca6-9f17-a4b1ecf4fabb"
msgid "Agreed to organize a feast for Ekun, but purely for your own reasons."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4440b5d-28d2-4c12-bf06-42d193fa5b1e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't care about Ekun's inner turmoil, but that's no reason to turn down a "
"good party.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a8defe4-ed0c-42f7-97ff-8ff84d876cce"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hello, Your Grace! ...Hmm, feels strange! It's amazing I can just go and have "
"a chat with an actual baron{mf||ess}...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d86c824-6ffd-4984-be26-09ac8e3f7efa"
msgid ""
"\\\"I wanted to talk about Ekun. I'm worried about him lately... Although "
"'worried' might be too strong a word. He is way too gloomy — even more so than "
"usual, if that's possible. Life without a family must be hard for him...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "846bc14f-f907-4ac6-a8b5-b3aced3fa451"
msgid "\\\"I'm not sure I'd put it like that... but I'm glad you agreed!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8771eca6-fcd0-4882-9cd9-6597781d75b8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, for one, he is your companion! Second, I can't abide him scowling "
"another instant! Lastly? I want to know that when my ally is fighting beside me, "
"they won't break — and Ekun feels too close to it already.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a413b10-2287-42f4-b5ab-521664b21de2"
msgid ""
"\\\"But he is not completely alone! He has us! I know we can't replace what he "
"lost, but we must remind him that we are here and he can talk to us!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ebaa9aab-9df2-4d2c-afcf-201c644159f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"What I'm getting at is that we should hold a merry revelry and use the "
"opportunity to talk to him, heart to heart! If we just invite him for a drink, "
"he'll no doubt refuse. So we must organize everything in secret! We'll gather "
"guests, prepare food and drink, bring Ekun — and have so-o-o much fun! I'll even "
"bring my lute! What do you say?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fac4a1ea-decd-42fd-a620-bc51bb37d970"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've talked to Elina the innkeeper and she's happy to help us. Although… "
"between us, I'm not sure what made her so enthusiastic... Anyway, you should talk "
"to her. And I should go and think what I'm going to play!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58e5b9b8-c40c-4038-9734-f889023a73c5"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi's face brightens with a smile. {/n} \\\"Wonderful! As we know, great "
"minds think alike!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5982e3d3-40de-4c92-b6e3-92fc6eed05a8"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi looks away, and her voice falters a bit.{/n} \\\"Well, if... if that's "
"how you feel about us...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cde9ad85-4715-4b10-9f0e-06da4884c5ad"
msgid ""
"\\\"And one more thing, don't be late! I fear if we don't pull Ekun out of his "
"mood now, it'll be too late!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f381ea14-9c65-4b44-9581-c8095454cd1c"
msgid "{n}Linzi shakes her head, displeased.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87876f12-3d99-4d32-a2fa-09902fe27d76"
msgid "\\\"Pity. Well, I did what I could...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ea59275-19fe-4103-9e9c-6cb15144a08b"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi is trying not to look at you.{/n} \\\"I'm... well... it's about Ekun's {d|"
"Ekun Feast Ok}party{/d}. Of course, now's not the time... and I'm sure you have "
"other things on your mind... so let's just forget about this, all right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "931791f7-b451-445f-ab49-ed190ba07f15"
msgid ""
"{n}Ekun barely looks at you.{/n} \\\"I am back, {name}. Forgive me if you were "
"worried. I needed to... rest. From everything. And say farewell to Ntavi.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bbf1fec2-34bc-4372-9355-3019350dca7a"
msgid "\\\"What do you mean 'missing'?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13033b90-caa9-4f21-914b-23bdd30130a7"
msgid ""
"Thanked Elina for staying vigilant and promised to search for Ekun straight away."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fddcad3a-68bd-4698-9cb8-0f6a622dd600"
msgid ""
"\\\"You did your duty by warning me, and I'm grateful. I'll set off to find them "
"immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ba25aca-ea4e-4758-922e-ed08fd3412ba"
msgid "\\\"Where do you think they may have gone?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1f3564fd-2469-468d-82b8-6e7d94768929"
msgid "Decided to look for Ekun to not miss any of the fun."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3216542c-7b59-40a8-af40-1ed43edf64b2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmm... what if they got into a battle without me. Can't let them have all the "
"fun — let's go find them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "134c1e8e-210b-42b8-8fcd-5f95b29e5b98"
msgid "Refused to search for Ekun and Ntavi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ba99b7e-02b8-4112-bf6e-1d5609dca427"
msgid "\\\"They can fall into Rovagug's jaws for all I care. Get out of here!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d50bd513-d2e9-449b-a10b-85390af25662"
msgid ""
"Explained to Elina that a ruler cannot abandon their responsibilities to search "
"for their subjects."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a2e4fbf-cb78-4cad-9598-e2ab55ea126b"
msgid ""
"\\\"They will have to deal with it themselves, I can't leave my responsibilities "
"here to chase Ekun.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "966596e4-00bf-4fa0-8812-0a60fd52430d"
msgid "\\\"I'll see what can be done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ba44c15-25f9-4787-94ff-6feef41f4715"
msgid ""
"{n}Elina's face is pale, and her red hair is a mess.{/n} \\\"It's awful, Your "
"Grace! Ekun is missing, and {d|Ntavi}Ntavi{/d} too!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2de78c92-20be-4b3c-8bc1-05b55bf2ca75"
msgid ""
"\\\"He was happy for a while after our fest. Things were going well... but then he "
"started feeling down — restless. His thoughts may have turned to his family again. "
"And then this... {d|Ntavi}Ntavi{/d} kept turning up.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac64952e-682d-48fd-8473-9900e9ea6846"
msgid "{n}Elina looks surprised.{/n} \\\"A-As Your Grace wishes... thank you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8f659d4-5d8a-4c42-804f-010bf38a96c2"
msgid "\\\"Praise {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g}! Thank you, Your Grace!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71fc8c02-03bd-4523-82c2-337a47e88c33"
msgid ""
"\\\"If only we knew for sure, Your Grace! There is one spot though — a bridge over "
"the {g|Gudrin River}Gudrin River{/g}... travelers have gone missing there, they "
"say it might be the work of giants. Ntavi was close when some woodcutter told me "
"about it. And I'm thinking, maybe this woman dragged Ekun there?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8c0380c-c50d-4a79-9333-0c5e1c343ceb"
msgid ""
"\\\"And the more he talked to Ntavi, the worse he got. She was whispering "
"something in his ear, and he kept ordering more and more wine... then last night "
"they left the inn, armed to the teeth! I tried to stop them, but I couldn't... "
"they haven't been back since!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba563ecb-021a-49c6-be72-2b73275c4de0"
msgid ""
"\\\"In {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g}'s name, Your Grace, please find Ekun! My heart says "
"this won't end well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a22c77f7-69a8-4439-90aa-ac4711c0a404"
msgid ""
"{n}Elina looks at you, terrified.{/n} \\\"F-Forgive me, Your Grace... I'm "
"leaving...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0287ca0d-8908-4f04-8e59-c0b00aecfac7"
msgid "\\\"I... I see, Your Grace. Oh, I hope nothing bad happened to them...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "843b8e26-b487-4300-ad1d-91e6b6f0bf1c"
msgid "\\\"Why do you ask this?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3ce660b-9af5-447e-9287-1edfdf599ff9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course, Harrim. If I find any dwarven ruins, I'll take you to them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af3d5494-274c-4ccc-8af8-898e438ff7e4"
msgid "\\\"Don't, Harrim. It will bring you nothing but pain.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff428ce2-b02f-4968-ab1a-453b1429c87b"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim looks embarrassed. He runs his fingers through his beard and clears his "
"throat a few times, then speaks at last.{/n} \\\"I heard... Not that it is "
"important, but... Well...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe810be7-5f4d-4b61-996c-f82cf8342fae"
msgid ""
"{n}He clears his throat again.{/n} \\\"I heard that an ancient trade road built by "
"the dwarves of {g|Five Kings Mountains}the Five Kings Mountains{/g} runs through "
"these lands. I don't know what happened to them, or where they went. Unforgiving "
"time spares no one... But the road itself is still here. And possibly not only the "
"road.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45df7714-5573-4e0a-b24a-54f45024d49d"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim holds his beard in his fist.{/n} \\\"Well... {Name}, I have a request. "
"If you find any dwarven ruins in the area, I'd like to see them with my own eyes.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f14c8e68-159f-4acf-aa6c-bf1a9f250086"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim fiddles with his beard again.{/n} \\\"I shouldn't, probably. But it's "
"like a wound that's never healed. You know it will only hurt more, but you still "
"need to scratch it... Of course it's foolish, foolish and vain... But still I wish "
"to look at them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff34fc4c-f7e8-440c-ae20-1e8fe8283cc5"
msgid "\\\"Thank you, {Name}. I, well... Ahem! Thank you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a8046b8-3dc2-42fb-85bf-d44c267b6f4b"
msgid ""
"\\\"You are right, {Name}, I know you're right... And yet I want to go there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "93da6096-8dcc-4570-b046-a78e3c346356"
msgid ""
"\\\"About the dwarven ruins... Do you recall that I wanted to see them? I have "
"thought about it for a while and realized that I shouldn't. It's all nonsense, "
"dust and ashes, vain and pointless. Why look to ruins for purpose, if the whole "
"world is soon to join them?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2dbad44d-3d6d-45a3-bc07-ad2e9f8d4a91"
msgid "\\\"I'm not going to help you. Get out!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "176cd3a0-a1bb-43a3-93df-a3e17aa09f49"
msgid "Executed the Skjegge clan's emissary."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "460618ac-c610-4bf7-916f-a4ab4c528e33"
msgid "\\\"I think you're a spy. Guards! Hang her!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6d23f68-0612-4578-83e1-6b35edca96c9"
msgid "\\\"So what's this trouble you've gotten yourselves into?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7b755dcb-2cb3-4e52-a920-5f217cfba2b3"
msgid "\\\"All right, I'll help you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bb82230a-318b-4c02-93e8-0f044ae09031"
msgid ""
"\\\"What? No! I swear I'm not a spy! Don't!\\\" {n}Ignoring the dwarf's screams, "
"the guards drag her away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2cacc3f9-84a7-456b-9b9c-c10723a5c653"
msgid "\\\"Your Grace, I beg you...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c10ce65-aa4f-4ded-a76c-b39791e81de0"
msgid "\\\"Serves her right.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "95508936-4b51-4908-a0a5-0cd68988267b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Many ages ago, our ancestors, together with the other clans, built a road "
"here, and a chain of fortresses along it. Unfortunately they were forced to leave "
"these lands. But now that you've established order here, we decided to return, to "
"rekindle our clan's legacy. We found the entrance to the Adamantine Shield "
"Fortress, but when we tried to enter...\\\" {n}Rudrin winces and touches her "
"bandaged arm.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ef1943e-a47a-470f-a216-9545b7cbf0c2"
msgid ""
"\\\"When our ancestors left, they charmed the gate of the fortress and locked it "
"with a key – which has long been kept safe by our clan as a relic. We brought it "
"with us, but when we inserted it into the lock and turned, something incredible "
"happened! The gate fell to ashes, and we saw that the lock was upon the chest of a "
"huge golem – which attacked us immediately!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c5c8d0f-fc71-4cac-be17-b6d694c2f8c5"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim snorts.{/n} \\\"I'm sure the creator of this golem prayed devoutly to {g|"
"Torag}Torag{/g} while he made it... Never thinking for a moment that this piece of "
"iron might someday turn on his own. How dwarvish!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0d56711-7877-494c-b9f1-6019d3592b93"
msgid ""
"\\\"We managed to hide up on a hill, but we'd backed ourselves into a trap: the "
"golem just stood below, waiting for us to come down. Two of us sacrificed their "
"lives, distracting it to give me a chance to escape and find help... Please, save "
"them! You are our only hope!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32890058-70ee-43ae-8d47-00ba392a7472"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim interrupts her sternly.{/n} \\\"We told you no! Now leave! You and your "
"clan are not welcome here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8412dd4d-dbab-499a-a15c-0d151dcd1b77"
msgid "\\\"As you say. Forgive me for troubling you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47799653-f064-44fd-8cb0-929dfab704f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, Your Grace! The Skjegge clan owes you. Here's a map. It shows where "
"to find the fortress...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d4e67ecd-39b3-4453-825b-f5c5bc99be04"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim fiddles with his beard pensively.{/n} \\\"I would ask you – if you go to "
"help them, take me with you. I know it's folly to gloat, but I would see with my "
"own eyes our proud guests from {g|Five Kings Mountains}the Five Kings Mountains{/"
"g} caught in such a mess... – And then send them home with my own tongue. I hope "
"you will allow me this small pleasure...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b12943f-dad6-4c27-86bb-57b7c1be27c0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, I must warn you... This is no ordinary golem. He's made of "
"adamantine. He's almost impossible to destroy, even with magical weapons. But if "
"you wear it out for long enough in battle, it will collapse for a while to restore "
"its strength. At that moment, you'll need to pull the key from its chest. If I "
"know anything about mechanics, that should switch it off!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9dc57ebb-78f3-4908-86dc-bc8c036cff7f"
msgid ""
"\\\"And if you don't?\\\" {n}Harrim's gloomy question hovers unanswered in the "
"silence.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06e1dd6f-32ad-4574-8137-42f0b92f2894"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim appears in the doorway, loudly shouting down the corridor, and trying to "
"block a visitor's way. However, they don't budge, and finally the priest is pushed "
"backwards into the room, shouting all the while.{/n} \\\"Away! Go away, I'm "
"telling you! The baron{mf||ess} isn't seeing anyone! {mf|He's|She's} busy! And "
"isn't here!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14a75bb6-5d92-416e-a6a6-57727787d848"
msgid ""
"\\\"Forgive me, respected Harrim, but I must speak to the baron{mf||ess}!\\\" {n}A "
"young dwarf limps into the room. She doesn't look well: her face is bruised, her "
"armor crumpled, and her arm is dressed with rags, brown from dried blood. "
"Nevertheless, she begins with a ceremonious bow.{/n} \\\"Your Grace! My name is "
"Rudrin, of the Skjegge clan, and I've come to beg your help. My kin are in grave..."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c3d8f5d-2574-4f9a-8c41-06ab2258b705"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim interrupts her with indignation.{/n} \\\"How do you know my name?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cab76781-27df-4c79-bfdf-4aef66791fe5"
msgid ""
"\\\"I was told of you by our leader – the revered Jarmuld, {g|Torag}Torag's{/g} "
"paladin. He is hoping to meet you in person. He has so many questions for you! A "
"dwarf who rejected Torag, became a priest of {g|Groetus}Groetus{/g}, and now sits "
"in an important position at the court of a baron{mf||ess} – such tales are rare!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e4c838c-502e-4d27-a9be-df0109fadeb9"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim's face is exploding with red and white spots. He furiously grabs his "
"beard.{/n} \\\"{g|Torag}Torag's{/g} paladin?! And he wants to talk to me?! What "
"impudence, what shameless... Brazen... Although...\\\" {n}Harrim turns to you.{/n} "
"\\\"You know, perhaps we should help them! I want to see this paladin with my own "
"eyes – and the trap he walked his congregation into!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02ed26ae-c3da-4310-89c8-254a2f1fc624"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim fiddles with his beard pensively.{/n} \\\"Do you remember the Skjegge "
"clan who came to us, begging us to save them? You agreed to help them back then, "
"but we never got around to it. Sometimes I wonder what happened to them...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b7fb679-5cee-4c27-b8ff-46699e39ea96"
msgid ""
"\\\"They probably died. Or returned home in disgrace... But what's the difference? "
"There's a lesson for all of us, {Name}: don't go after the treasures of the dead, "
"unless you are ready to join them. It was their pride that unmade them. Pride and "
"greed...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26e8b6c7-49b3-4e3f-b073-9561dae21b99"
msgid ""
"{n}Rudrin Skjegge looks much better than she did on your first meeting. Back then "
"she could barely stand for the wounds she'd received fighting the golem. Now the "
"dwarf stands proudly at attention before you in polished armor.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0448fa85-7daf-4e6f-84f1-d548c33b1794"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness! My dear Sir Harrim, deeply respected servant of {g|Groetus}"
"Groetus{/g}! The Skjegge clan has sent me to you to express our gratitude for "
"everything you have done for us, and present you with this humble gift. We crafted "
"this for Sir Harrim personally, from the metal of artifacts unmade by him.\\\" {n}"
"Rudrin hands a small but heavy chest to Harrim and bows.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ca0b3b3-866a-493c-a878-c4e33668f82a"
msgid ""
"{n}Harrim frowns, trying to hide his confusion, then nods and accepts the gift.{/"
"n} \\\"Well... I'm glad you're all right. It's nice to see someone managed to make "
"something useful out of those worthless scraps.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c6f4f99-8b6a-4eff-aa3b-e3cb701d4ff6"
msgid "\\\"Yes, we need to go and check on them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e4b5cee-d625-48d6-a262-7cb6fea39528"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm sick and tired of these Skjegge. They may as well fall into the Abyss. – "
"I'm not helping them any more!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1abff9d-ebbb-4b5a-ba62-c6bcb82a7e3b"
msgid "\\\"You are right. Let's go and see what happened.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b424db6a-4b20-460b-b5d9-7eb774fd362a"
msgid "\\\"I don't think it's anything serious.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "101f6340-6659-4a0c-9231-0aa4ed2df5dc"
msgid ""
"{n}A strange golem enters your throne room. It is seriously hurt, barely moving "
"its legs and swaying as if it's drunk.{/n} \\\"Help... Us... H-Help... H-Help...\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8e5c783d-ba3b-4c4e-b86b-d2c90e4505f4"
msgid ""
"{n}A frowning Harrim quickly responds.{/n} \\\"How do you like that? Again, "
"someone needs our help, and again it has to do with golems... Does any of this "
"seem familiar, {Name}? Those simpletons from the Skjegge clan must have dug up "
"something else. And got themselves into trouble again...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08016da5-cfb7-486d-9ce6-b3f0fa04e104"
msgid ""
"{n}The priest's remarks are punctuated by a terrible clanging sound as the golem "
"collapses on the floor in pieces.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb400e4f-18d6-47a2-a194-cd4554ae1b1d"
msgid ""
"\\\"And I warned them they were wooing death. I warned them... Let's return to "
"that little fortress that they couldn't get inside, and see what's happened to "
"them this time!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f9085d9-fbb1-4b91-87a7-c598d204bd39"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just don't go without me, all right? I want to see with my own eyes what "
"catastrophe they've wrought this time, all the while praying to their {g|Torag}"
"Torag{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "93660b3f-e243-45a7-97d0-2a734639fa29"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes, quite right... But on the other hand, you do know these treasure hunters "
"were looking for trouble. What if they dug up some new golem as tall as a tower, "
"and it's already on its way to destroy the capital? We should go and see. These "
"are your lands, after all!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c4791b2-98d6-4b5e-ac5a-97cf76aae480"
msgid "\\\"Hmm... Well, as you say, as you say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63c1def0-16e6-4310-8fa7-a77269c6ae4f"
msgid "\\\"I don't care to waste my time on this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ccbf92e8-33ca-47d4-b266-abb4e8a28b04"
msgid "\\\"Let him speak, Jaethal. Anger will not help us learn the truth.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4b8b56d-cdf4-4909-b98e-ef8ae2fb720e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Jaethal, listen to reason. If Enneo was involved in your death, he wouldn't be "
"openly offering your dagger for sale.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94905eec-ce1d-4b7a-a43e-c9087eea5982"
msgid ""
"\\\"We will investigate this matter further. Let's start by checking Enneo's "
"story, and seek out this unfortunate boar.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72a7baeb-dc84-4654-b746-c40004dcf199"
msgid "\\\"Where exactly did you find this carcass and dagger?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e80ddcdb-590d-464c-9216-127938040bb9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Enneo, you face serious accusations. Are you sure you can say nothing more in "
"your defense?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd3fbcc1-daf3-4e5c-98e2-c625c43f67d0"
msgid ""
"{n}Enneo, a half-elf merchant who recently appeared in the capital, falls to the "
"floor in front of you. Jaethal stands beside him, looking quite unlike her normal "
"self. Usually cold and stiff, the face of the undead elf now burns with rage. "
"Despite his nearness to his furious undead captor, Enneo looks concerned but "
"unafraid.{/n} \\\"If you allow me to speak, I can explain everything.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59f69e25-42de-4f0a-881b-53bcdf262dd3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Was it poison? Magic? Illness? Whatever stole my life away, it left no trace. "
"I thought this mystery would haunt me forever. But then I entered the shop of this "
"half-blood... Seeking some reminder of {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}... and what did I "
"discover there? My very own dagger!\\\" {n} Jaethal shows you an elven-crafted "
"dagger with a chipped blade and empty sockets, where once gemstones adorned the "
"handle.{/n} \\\"This dagger disappeared the same night I was taken by death. How "
"could this half-blood have obtained it?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f089ac47-f94f-434b-9977-63a40155ef3e"
msgid ""
"\\\"I hope you can, half-blood, otherwise...\\\" {n}Jaethal hisses and turns to "
"you.{/n} \\\"Have I told you the sad story of my death? It is sad most of all "
"because I do not remember how my life ended. I wandered, exhausted, through the "
"wastelands beyond the borders of {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}, until I could barely see my "
"path. I stopped to rest, or perhaps I lost consciousness... When I came to my "
"senses, I heard the call of my goddess, returning me from the dead.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eeb6677e-fd8a-4ab4-83a1-b5af331fc266"
msgid ""
"\\\"That is why...\\\" {n}Jaethal pauses.{/n} \\\"Respecting your authority, I "
"have brought this pathetic huckster here, rather than getting the truth out of him "
"by my own methods...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99ee69dc-ce51-4617-9c5b-1c7a1a11cac8"
msgid ""
"{n}The half-elf rises to his feet and sighs, putting his clothes in order.{/n} \\"
"\"Thank you for allowing me to speak, Your Grace. The story is not very exciting, "
"certainly not as exciting as my tale of the drunken regatta within the Eye of "
"Abendego! ... Yesterday, north of the city, I stumbled upon a dead boar. There was "
"no one around, but the dagger was protruding from the miserable beast's neck. I "
"don't know why the owner would have left it in the carcass. Perhaps the beast "
"escaped from the hunter, taking along the weapon that had injured it? So I... "
"inadvertently decided to keep the item I'd found, thanking my luck — and never "
"suspecting the price I'd pay for it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ac97fd4-85ed-4d16-b989-787ce57df8b8"
msgid ""
"\\\"You are very attentive to the troubles and needs of your faithful companions.\\"
"\" {n}You detect poisonous notes in Jaethal's voice, but she restrains herself "
"quickly.{/n} \\\"Very well, let's not distract the {mf|baron|baroness}, half-"
"blood. Let's go and talk somewhere alone!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "95b50a23-2c47-4da8-ad55-4534ca9a41a0"
msgid ""
"{n}Your words set Jaethal on her heels. She frowns, but calms down.{/n} \\"
"\"Perhaps that's logical. This one would have to be a useless fool to do such a "
"thing, and useless fools do not easily survive the road. Still, his story should "
"be verified. It must be. And in any case, the dagger may lead... to my killer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45dd3a50-28f6-4980-8ad2-13860000293f"
msgid ""
"\\\"In the vicinity of the Old Sycamore. Of course I'm sure you know where that "
"tree grows. I found the boar to the west of the Sycamore, in the direction of the "
"{g|Thorn River}Thorn River{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eac52667-c759-43e7-b6ee-a35432353c7b"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal bows gracefully.{/n} \\\"I am... grateful. It's important to me. And "
"you, half-blood, should pray for our success. If you are lying, I shall find a "
"surer way to get the truth from you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "804e654e-35de-4b4a-a13b-64336c62802c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I would be glad if I could, but alas.\\\" {n}The bright yellow-green eyes of "
"the half-elf are calm.{/n} \\\"The dead boar is my only witness. But I believe in "
"your justice, {mf|baron|baroness}. I have faith that you will investigate my story "
"and sort everything out.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f185ea7f-973d-4e66-866f-b468d862b248"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a pity you couldn't find time to investigate my murder. Our primary piece "
"of evidence — the wild boar's carcass in the Old Sycamore — was torn to pieces, "
"either by local wildlife or starving peasants. Enneo the merchant managed to flee, "
"as well. All the clues have been lost. Now we may as well forget about it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74117b64-3022-42b9-9418-49fb950d4669"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a pity you couldn't find time to continue investigating my murder. I've "
"learned that a group of travelers visited the bank of the {g|Thorn River}Thorn "
"River{/g}, exactly where the boar appeared before the Old Sycamore. But now the "
"travelers are gone. Enneo the merchant managed to flee, as well. All the clues are "
"lost.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5c7301f-cff4-4975-b6ff-cae4d8291707"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a pity you couldn't find time to visit Enneo the merchant. He managed to "
"escape, and his possessions were stolen by some petty thieves. All the clues are "
"lost now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "376d8d3f-6dec-458c-84d1-1447e508baf2"
msgid "\\\"So, where is he?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "efff3920-6e1e-48f4-951d-d77016d76e9a"
msgid "\\\"I don't want to get involved in all this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f922b077-8885-48b3-a4a6-50f4df10dff6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Fine. As soon as the opportunity arises, we'll visit the Valley of the Dead.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "639b72c1-d6ab-4b7d-875a-9a9261ee7543"
msgid "\\\"I will not help you in this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58ff0b39-2f87-4576-a164-9db62bffa968"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal crosses the throne room, her gait determined and confident. It seems "
"clear that the inquisitor has something pressing on her mind.{/n} \\\"Finally I "
"have news about the half-blood. I expected him to seek shelter somewhere far from "
"your lands, but no — he was spotted not far away.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f36cf3e-7e14-4fd6-8b41-e16765c05512"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not far from the {g|Valley of the Dead}Valley of the Dead{/g}. What a fitting "
"place for a Pharasmite, desperately trying to rid this world of the undead. Such "
"determination might have been an asset in dealing with Vordakai... But I wish to "
"discuss something else. The half-blood was spotted chasing some pauper pilgrim "
"woman. Judging by the things my agent managed to find out, the woman herself may "
"turn out to be quite interesting.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49898c89-395c-42a9-8225-b5e61fd32d1d"
msgid ""
"\\\"How could this be, after all he's done to fool you and drag you into his "
"schemes?\\\" {n}Jaethal can't hide her disappointment.{/n} \\\"Very well, as you "
"wish. But this is a short-sighted decision. Very short-sighted.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "865070d3-5a85-49d4-a155-c7e8d84ab71d"
msgid ""
"\\\"To track down the half-blood, I had to deal with a whole range of scum — "
"thieves, vagabonds, grave-robbers. One of them located Enneo, but then preyed upon "
"the pauper woman — couldn't miss a chance to rob her blind. In her handbag the "
"thief found some ominous writings. Thinking the papers were cursed, he decided to "
"rid himself of them by giving them to me. Do you know what they turned out to be? "
"Excerpts from \\\"Serving Your Hunger\\\", the sacred text of {g|Urgathoa}"
"Urgathoa's{/g} followers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45f44f4e-86fc-40d4-9296-4c17ed40159c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've examined the stolen papers closely, and now I believe that their owner is "
"a high-ranking priestess of {g|Urgathoa}Urgathoa{/g}. It seems this half-blood "
"persists in his desire to rid the world of all my goddess' followers. He's skilled "
"at covering his tracks, but now we have a chance to intercept him. Let's go to the "
"{g|Valley of the Dead}Valley of the Dead{/g} and find this priestess before he "
"acts. Then, when he comes for her... well, the servants of any deity should be "
"able to stand up for their faith, is it not so?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "685346aa-134e-4928-b98f-a888635b60a5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you. I want to say — this... this is important to me. I've grown tired "
"of drowning in silence, hearing never a word from my goddess. I wish to speak with "
"this priestess, and try to discover what {g|Urgathoa}Urgathoa{/g} may be expecting "
"from me. I want answers. — Answers from my murderer, among others.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c6703c71-22b2-490d-aaf5-9bc063504056"
msgid ""
"\\\"It appears that we've hopelessly lost the opportunity to hunt down the half-"
"blood. My agents discovered the dead body of a priestess of {g|Urgathoa}Urgathoa{/"
"g}, who he'd been chasing. As for Enneo himself, he's disappeared without a trace, "
"just like last time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9bc7b898-c64e-46c5-a874-0dc9258aec04"
msgid "\\\"Fine. We'll meet with these elves.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ae1fd3a-f318-4a52-b20f-bc729cd45ca4"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's not my concern. I've already had enough trouble because of this story.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e98a3e5a-008e-4940-8142-63e08462fa1c"
msgid "\\\"Does this situation somehow threaten me or my kingdom?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "671b483f-e350-47eb-9091-f1d750e1b009"
msgid "\\\"Fine. We'll meet with these elves if circumstances permit.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "075ecdd8-6d61-488f-bffb-d74409fadbb5"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm not going to meddle in your affairs with the elves. This is my final "
"decision.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8213bdc-6e1a-44c5-b975-73110db9de24"
msgid ""
"\\\"I bring news,\\\" {n}Jaethal reports abruptly.{/n} \\\"Not unexpected. A "
"sizable group of elves from {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} has crossed the border into your "
"kingdom. They send {g|JaethalQ3}a message{/g} to you. You may read it, if you "
"wish, but I can state the substance in a few words: \\\"We demand you turn over "
"the murderer. We await your response.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "242b1a08-3937-46a4-9729-59a9a7cfec60"
msgid ""
"{n}Jaethal stares at you closely, as if trying to assess something. Is she "
"studying you, or considering the larger situation?{/n} \\\"I... suppose we should "
"meet with them. Back then, near the {g|Thorn River}Thorn River{/g}, after the "
"battle with the elven youngsters, I felt {g|Urgathoa}Urgathoa's{/g} presence again "
"— for the first time since I was reborn. Now I feel something similar. A command. "
"Or the shadow of one. Besides, I don't like to leave my affairs unfinished. Let us "
"put an end to this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4f7e7afb-b91f-480f-9ad7-239b013e759f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Is there a chance I might change your mind? I can't see any reason for you to "
"say no. This mission is extremely important to me. We'll both win if we resolve "
"the situation — one way or another.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a65e653-b705-4107-afbf-a7bafa63f190"
msgid "\\\"I am ready to strike out at a moment's notice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45af26e2-1897-4160-90e3-7eb451ccd9eb"
msgid ""
"\\\"I doubt it. They are not official emissaries from {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}. — If "
"they were, then their interference would look quite different. Most likely these "
"are the families of those foolish youngsters from the camp near the {g|Thorn River}"
"Thorn River{/g}. I assume they're inclined to fight, but they won't set ambushes "
"or try to stab you in the back. First, they will surely try to negotiate. Elves, "
"you know...\\\" {n}Jaethal allows herself a sarcastic smirk.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8a150d4-fedd-4799-b401-e0bf15111c19"
msgid "\\\"As you wish… I don't dare to distract Your Highness any further.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f9094103-72dd-4e0f-8197-5ddfd9e7a6de"
msgid ""
"\\\"You want to use this opportunity to find out why the gnomes left the First "
"World – and how they might return. Right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d543b45-a860-4171-bea5-9c6fb436faa7"
msgid "\\\"I don't. Tell me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61b6a2c8-fbf2-48a0-a174-5e82491a1302"
msgid "\\\"I don't know and I don't care. I'm not doing this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2677ee15-6d15-48ce-bf29-ea682a20fa14"
msgid "\\\"Any information about the First World would be useful.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a37e514-919e-40aa-b4bb-838bdc42b233"
msgid "\\\"The Inconsequent Debates? What's that?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39dfd8e6-d2ac-43e2-b4cb-e1093db8ee4f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you know anything about these debates? Or are we completely in the dark "
"here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba44d404-bc97-40b1-b576-d5323e8f8c16"
msgid "\\\"Can participating be dangerous?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0438448a-ac62-4607-8c70-21c4cdc1725b"
msgid "\\\"We can't pass up such an opportunity. I agree to participate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e976014b-11db-4234-a927-e645b8db7484"
msgid "\\\"I see no point in this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "964beb5e-fe03-460b-9cc3-cd126a4c2245"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've heard about them. Strange entertainments, held on Golarion by fey lords "
"from the First World. Strange tests with various unique rewards...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b0c73d2-bbb9-44d2-9b67-85705ba78fc0"
msgid "\\\"Keep your riddles to yourself. I'm not interested.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d4a2d915-5421-4e68-928d-0caf8a333f94"
msgid "\\\"Who do you think we should take as our third?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2dfdb3f4-7e6c-412c-8b01-16f024e5187f"
msgid "\\\"Fine, tell me about the debates.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4ac831f-14f0-4d07-92a4-4ea8b7a8c6c8"
msgid "\\\"And yet, I don't care.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "be1d4cd2-4412-41e0-9d32-47a4760063a9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Amazing. You managed to save your barony from an invasion of monsters from {g|"
"First World}the First World{/g}. But you were not able to protect it from the "
"attention of the First World's more powerful denizens. Believe it or not, but "
"{kingdomname} has been chosen as the next location for the Inconsequent Debates!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3b073f9-bccf-4932-82e6-636b2c84c085"
msgid ""
"\\\"A curious phenomenon that isn't very well known. They say it's based on a bet "
"made by the {g|Eldest}Eldest{/g}, the rulers of {g|First World}the First World{/"
"g}, quite a long time ago. One day one of them sent a delegation of fey to {g|"
"Golarion}Golarion{/g}. They announced where the competition would take place."
"\\nDon't let the name fool you, it's anything but debates. The contests begin as "
"soon as they have enough participants.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da762970-5e51-45e1-bf45-7d5d808bfaa7"
msgid ""
"\\\"The contests and the reward are different every time. Although 'every time' is "
"a stretch — only three such occasions are known over thousands of years. Anyway, "
"it's happened again! And this time the reward is a chance to ask any question "
"whatsoever of the Host, the competition's mastermind. This creature, whoever it "
"is, speaks on behalf of the {g|Eldest}Eldest{/g}. Do you see why we can't miss "
"such a chance?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a95f9b8-0ecd-4a4f-9e37-bc3f1c0d9072"
msgid ""
"\\\"But...\\\" {n}Jubilost loses his usual confidence for a moment.{/n} \\\"It's a "
"chance to gain new unique knowledge! What could be more important? Anyway, I'm "
"obviously talking to the wrong person. Waste your time playing at war and running "
"around swamps if that's all you care about.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b077422-e665-41e8-94d3-c692b3a248ed"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nice to see our association has left a mark on you. Yes, of course! I'm none "
"too happy that we'll have to play by the {g|Eldest}Eldest's{/g} rules. You know my "
"opinion of the fey lords isn't very high. But if that's what the truth requires, "
"then so be it. In the end, who would best know the answer to my question, if not "
"the self-appointed deities of {g|First World}the First World{/g}?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bcad88e3-23c6-414b-9be7-15f294ba8656"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just think! We have an opportunity to ask a question of the Host — the "
"messenger of the self-appointed deities of {g|First World}the First World{/g} — "
"and demand an answer! The gnomes originally ventured from the First World, lost "
"their immortality because of it, and received our curse in exchange. — the {g|"
"Bleaching}Bleaching{/g}. No one has discovered the reasons for it — and none can "
"stave off its consequences. But if we managed to win the competition...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c175b454-c879-40f1-a0cb-55029a7f041c"
msgid ""
"\\\"You never know what mad ideas the fey might have cooked up. I only know one "
"condition: only teams of three are allowed to participate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb3975f2-fbb9-4c65-986b-8f95da0b4e79"
msgid ""
"\\\"Considering that the fey are involved — absolutely. But if the chronicles are "
"true, no one has died in any previous debate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47a35210-aecc-4cd3-8497-e3a7d68a60d4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Great! I'll mark the spot on the map where the competition will take place. "
"The sooner we arrive there, the better. The fey lords won't wait forever!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8385683-019b-4ae2-a1d9-ed54f57bdfe5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your knowledge is — well, pleasantly surprising! It's true, the Inconsequent "
"Debates are anything but debates. They say that the {g|Eldest}Eldest{/g} once made "
"a bet. No one knows what it was, but sometimes one or another of them sends a "
"delegation of fey to {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g}. Here they hold insane competitions "
"for those who volunteer to enter, and present the winners with whimsical awards.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a14c915-84d0-44c6-840a-7ed7afab1ed5"
msgid ""
"I think we should take Linzi. Something tells me fey are not likely to hold "
"competitions in rope pulling or beer drinking. But the skills of a bard might come "
"in handy. Besides, we should give the young lady a chance to channel some of that "
"energy!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b39d1bb4-23c7-40ae-8ade-0a617ac10cdb"
msgid ""
"\\\"I insist that we take this chance. It's an opportunity to learn the secrets of "
"the fey, and possibly alter the fate of an entire race.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17da6360-fdda-45ed-a576-2cde01e3f428"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost looks very irritated.{/n} \\\"Great! While we were busy with needless "
"and unsophisticated pastimes like chasing an ancient cyclops, the Inconsequent "
"Debates have ended! The Host has returned to {g|First World}the First World{/g}. "
"We're left with nothing! Congratulations.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b18c280-eab4-499a-9e09-55e5b263c12b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Obviously that part about 'he who is born twice, will twice be defeated' "
"referred to Armag...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b50a34c8-01a8-4127-ab01-8b85c372149e"
msgid "\\\"I'm sorry but I don't have the time or interest for this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cbe37f8a-db04-4cb3-a8f0-1fe2dac02b8c"
msgid ""
"\\\"All right. I will look for Gunderson's books and try to make some sense of "
"them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "531d2148-cd55-4b12-b59f-0f395895dc48"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you think 'a dozen times in a dozen' is about something that happens every "
"month? There's a twenty-fourth day in every month – and there are twelve of them "
"in a year.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22b5e85b-1738-43b5-b252-553655df1154"
msgid ""
"\\\"You do remember our little adventure with the fey lords and their Inconsequent "
"Debates, damn them? Before you ask, by 'damn them' I meant both the debates and "
"the lords. Anyway, I've been thinking about that dreadful verbiage we received as "
"a 'reward' for the trials – the answer to the question about the fate of the gnome "
"race. Allow me to remind you of the text...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62884ddc-2c0c-4938-bfd8-fc49b7123fdd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Numbers will help you on your way,\\nOne of them is fifth in ten,\\nIt will be "
"easy to find if you read\\nWho opened the road for the ancient dead man\\nAnd his "
"black-feathered messenger.\\nThe second is a dozen times in a dozen\\nAnd is "
"thrice the number of those who lost their faces.\\nDon't try to guess it now – "
"it's not yet time.\\nWait until he who is born twice,\\nWill twice be defeated."
"\\nPut the two numbers together.\\nWhen the Moon leaves her path,\\nNear the "
"waters of the {g|Candlemere}Candlemere{/g}\\nFind the one who will open the secret."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11f8c42f-8660-4df8-abdf-416b2d90b914"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not a single reasonable creature would spend valuable time solving this sort "
"of phrase-mince. If only someone knew how much effort it required to treat the "
"matter seriously! But it paid off! It's obvious that the part about 'opened the "
"road for the ancient dead man and his black-feathered messenger' refers to {d|"
"Willas}Willas Gunderson{/d}, who awakened Vordakai. This guess led me to think...\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4676503f-c587-40ee-b9f7-2cfb5b962ca1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Exactly! We couldn't have known that at the time of the debates, because we "
"hadn't even met Armag yet. Which makes me wonder who this respected Host might "
"be... But that's neither here nor there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "452102a1-ad71-48c6-b0dd-b7abbf5b1bbc"
msgid ""
"\\\"So, what do we know? The riddle recommends we start looking after the twice-"
"born is twice defeated, and that's happened. The other part – 'thrice the number "
"of those who lost their faces' – that's also only clear now. It's twenty four – "
"three times the number of the Defaced Sisters there were! But the rest... What "
"does it mean, 'when the Moon leaves her path'? And how does a dozen times in a "
"dozen equate to twenty four? I'll have to study some astronomy reference books and "
"write to some priests of {g|Desna}Desna{/g} that I'm acquainted with. It's "
"probably about some rare celestial phenomenon.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af28fef4-ef3e-499d-b759-27978c8bc288"
msgid ""
"\\\"I meant to ask you to deal with the first part of the riddle – the one about "
"{d|Willas}Willas Gunderson{/d}. Remember the riddle – we don't need to find him or "
"talk to him, just read him. Here is what I think it means: I discovered that the "
"poor fellow wrote and published a few horrendous books. Perhaps the answer is "
"hidden in one of them? The very thought of digging through that parody of "
"literature is disgusting. I'd very much appreciate – yes, appreciate – some help. "
"Perhaps some book-lover in this city will have a volume or two of his 'work'?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "882b16ce-2f39-4b1d-85a8-ce6791fc5712"
msgid ""
"\\\"Good luck on this difficult quest! I remind you: the riddle says we need to "
"find something 'fifth in ten' – and somehow related to Gunderson's writing. We put "
"it together with the number 'twenty four' and go to the {g|Candlemere}Candlemere{/"
"g}, 'when the Moon leaves her path'. I hope this isn't some elaborate fey prank. "
"Because if it is... I won't have to do any more research to understand what made "
"the gnomes leave {g|First World}the First World{/g}. It was the stinking neighbors!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0ed37b7-2d86-4ef9-9e59-91a1d3c28c41"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course. How dare I distract {mf|His|Her} Highness from such obviously "
"important things! Well, I think I'll manage without you. When ever have I not?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15226290-272b-40ca-918a-ee99135ec3a1"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost looks at you with suspicion.{/n} \\\"Everything can't be that simple. "
"Or can it? With the fey you never know! Well, it's a good guess, but it still "
"doesn't spare us the need to look at the dreadful books.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5d8ab80-9f2b-44dc-9aae-5072665ec5e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Bad news, Your Grace: there is a thief within your close circle. A significant "
"shortage has been discovered within the treasure. An investigation is already "
"underway — the guilty party will soon be brought before you for judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22a63872-f14f-4c1c-a27c-1259614643fe"
msgid ""
"\\\"Unpleasant but, alas, expected news: someone with access to the treasury seems "
"to have appropriated a large sum from it. The circle of suspects is not "
"particularly wide — I believe we will soon discover who was responsible.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17601e66-9596-4dd1-8ed8-84fb6992a480"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm sure it's unthinkable to you, but someone from your court has sticky "
"fingers! A large sum has vanished from the treasury. I've already started looking "
"for the responsible party.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35b4dc3d-c724-42be-b075-485526435409"
msgid ""
"\\\"I... Umm... I think I might know something about this, um, sad — no, shocking! "
"— most shocking event. Can we discuss it one-on-one, maybe? I'll wait for you at "
"the inn after council!\\\" {n}Without waiting for your reply, Linzi runs out of "
"the throne room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cfd6bcfc-6275-44ae-82ef-ae13b77c9c90"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil stares after the bard, surprised.{/n} \\\"I'd have never imagined she "
"would find herself connected to such a crime...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37a0cc59-dc3e-451d-8358-8bd3a2e46c58"
msgid "{n}Shandra silently raises an eyebrow, but she refrains from commenting.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c91462af-979b-42f7-b7b0-f35b6320c6cf"
msgid "\\\"Oh? Perhaps this investigation will be quicker than I thought!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b980491-a66a-4e1d-a3ba-e4cf93e3bcfb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Remember how I wanted to talk to you about... well, about... No. No, forget "
"it. It's been a while, so it's probably not that important now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec692d45-4996-49f1-8a42-06817ddf3ce1"
msgid "\\\"Who's Eobald the Insightful?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37ea223e-8f40-4af1-95fb-912f8d283e1a"
msgid "\\\"Why did you run from Irovetti?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed709f64-ff69-46fb-94f3-2efec2b2a8ec"
msgid "\\\"Why didn't you send word in advance?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1d39e8b-951c-459a-ac93-9d8c8a822a39"
msgid "\\\"Is something wrong, Linzi?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8245eff0-70dd-40a3-af35-9c66292e1fee"
msgid "\\\"Where will we find Eobald and his students?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de6bac68-6426-4e33-a51f-91b6e44d3db6"
msgid "\\\"Fine, we'll help your teacher.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b30d24df-fde0-4fd9-8023-589876af0ae8"
msgid "\\\"Get out. I don't care about you, or your teacher!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a2f0e8e1-f4e6-4831-989b-47a0df6fda47"
msgid "\\\"I said no.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0623a3e-2a6e-4d22-bc49-7afa5a7b35b1"
msgid "\\\"Why come to my lands?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c970dd92-1b32-4307-aefa-3dd56afbe340"
msgid ""
"{n}A young man runs into the throne room. His clothes, formerly stylish and "
"sophisticated, are torn and muddy.{/n} \\\"Your Grace! Praise {g|Shelyn}Shelyn{/g} "
"I made it here alive. I beg you, please help us!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5bbc1aeb-e039-4d8f-8909-d13eefeb3954"
msgid ""
"\\\"Alondi? What... what in the Hells are you doing here?\\\" {n}Linzi blurts out "
"angrily.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3244a045-d629-4fa2-b6a2-632e79d023d9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, Linzi! I'm so glad to see you... Forgive me, Your Grace, for my lack of "
"decorum. My name is Alondi — I attended the {g|Pitax}Pitaxian{/g} {g|Academy of "
"Grand Arts}Academy of Grand Arts{/g} with Linzi. Our teacher, Eobald the "
"Insightful, has been forced to flee the wrath of King Irovetti along with a group "
"of his students. We almost made it to the capital, but we were caught. Only I "
"managed to escape to find help!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3c4bb60c-c3df-4a51-8977-a3e573b13b0f"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi opens her mouth, about to say something harsh, but she realizes the "
"gravity of Alondi's words and interrupts herself.{/n} \\\"You... What do you mean? "
"Professor Eobald is in trouble? {Name}, we have to help!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fefb38fd-828f-45cc-8694-88b32da2093e"
msgid ""
"\\\"He's a prominent researcher — a gatherer of myths and legends, author of many "
"essays on history and literary theory... Any cultured ruler would be glad to "
"welcome such a beacon of learning!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8572bcd8-981a-4d71-8080-1ea72de9e5d8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Professor Eobald was one of the wisest people in the whole {g|Academy of Grand "
"Arts}Academy{/g}... maybe in all the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}! I knew "
"the king would kick him out sooner or later. Like I told you, Irovetti isn't "
"interested in sages and scientists — he just wants bootlickers and toadies!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7e758e8-7951-45ff-8b72-9dec85a5cc62"
msgid ""
"\\\"King Irovetti's a jealous ruler — he doesn't intend to hand the title of the "
"region's cultural capital over to anyone. He may have thrown our teacher out of "
"the {g|Academy of Grand Arts}Academy{/g}, but he would rather see Eobald dead than "
"working for any of Pitax's neighbors. And if the refugees return to {g|Pitax}"
"Pitax{/g}, they won't be spared the chopping block!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6d8b3318-454f-4de3-8654-9240a39ff453"
msgid ""
"\\\"Irovetti has spies everywhere. If our teacher had tried to contact you, we "
"wouldn't have made it out of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} at all.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c368c74b-8e56-46d9-9d50-7aa785da688b"
msgid ""
"\\\"No. Yes. Not important right now! We need to save Professor Eobald as soon as "
"possible!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f42b4dfd-b695-4088-973b-40c23c127ace"
msgid ""
"\\\"Irovetti's thugs caught up with us near a giant tree — a sycamore, I think. If "
"you go immediately, you should have time to intercept them!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fddd35c0-9ffc-4458-b6dd-43d7394f2bc4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Please don't let Irovetti get Professor Eobald! He's a shining beacon, you'll "
"see!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e098d8a-bbea-435d-91be-4edeeafda0c4"
msgid "{n}Sniffling, Linzi runs out of the throne room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e4b208d-f7b1-425f-b941-39f93f85dc59"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, Your Grace! You won't regret it! I'll hurry back to the tree.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18a5e5dc-bf18-41a4-9c39-e1eee0b79f51"
msgid ""
"\\\"I can't believe Irovetti actually kicked out Professor Eobald... Well, it's "
"his loss! We'll save him! Just don't go without me — I miss my old teacher "
"terribly!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b10c4ad4-f193-4d5d-b863-ea9658e0a1dd"
msgid ""
"\\\"One of the {g|Academy of Grand Arts}Academy's{/g} most talented students "
"already found shelter here after fleeing the tyrant's wrath.\\\" {n}Alondi bows "
"politely to Linzi.{/n} \\\"Your books are quite popular in {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} — "
"they're a living reminder that culture yet blooms beyond Irovetti's reach! We had "
"hoped, Your Grace, that you would take us under your protection as well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86492930-442a-4ce7-8627-75369907b5e5"
msgid "{n}Linzi winces but says nothing.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8eeaefb4-760a-4a3e-8ac5-51a5d658b930"
msgid ""
"\\\"I just heard... King Irovetti caught Professor Eobald and... and... executed "
"him. We were too late. Forgive me, Teacher...\\\" {n}Linzi sniffles loudly, "
"covering her face.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f27f378-8a18-45a8-a6c7-409bb79c5f6e"
msgid ""
"\\\"So, King Irovetti invited you for a visit? I have the perfect gift for him!\\"
"\" {n}With a smug look, Linzi shows you a thin paperback.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "479e046e-e7ae-424f-a377-3892ff8c8778"
msgid ""
"\\\"Look through it when you have the time. The entire truth of the {g|Academy of "
"Grand Arts}Academy of Grand Arts{/g} and its so-called patron, Irovetti. I hope it "
"gives him a stroke when he reads it — then all your problems will have solved "
"themselves!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79635421-7333-4b8d-9e3d-5fa0d8e0e01d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Look through it when you have the time. The entire {d|Linzi Book True}truth{/"
"d} of the {g|Academy of Grand Arts}Academy of Grand Arts{/g} — the truth about "
"what the students, teachers, headmaster, and their great patron Irovetti himself "
"are doing behind their pretty facade!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c85960a9-501c-49a3-99f1-ce565a8e866b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The first press run is already on its way to {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}. When you go, "
"don't forget to take me with you — I want to see the effects of the book Professor "
"Eobald and I wrote with my own eyes. I'm sure it'll be explosive!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28f0ab2b-6aa1-4dd0-aa8e-a3bee79060f7"
msgid "Agreed to listen to Nok-Nok's plea."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "203cf607-fb33-4bd1-966c-5d59d575bdcc"
msgid ""
"\\\"He helped us against the goblin tribes... I think I should return the favor.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ad4f632-679d-4f20-9244-a44b35db19ff"
msgid "\\\"I'll hear what he has to say. Send him in.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d2eebec-03fd-45a7-a8fc-4b2b54ea1337"
msgid "Ordered to trick Nok-Nok and chain him in the dungeon."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59ece8df-02b4-4522-a781-f3475a4d3c7c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tell him I await him in the dungeon, and when he enters a cell, shackle him "
"there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b4e6ff7-aee6-48e7-b266-dd828cabf3fc"
msgid "Ordered Nok-Nok's execution."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f21c3a3-604d-4e50-8ea3-1158bfa5df47"
msgid "\\\"He has served his purpose. Have the guards take him and execute him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1063031b-a822-47c1-bb06-c81a5a8edb82"
msgid "\\\"Turn him away, I don't have time for him right now. Or ever.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7e2b743c-dc58-4974-ab5d-e02aca09c012"
msgid "\\\"How can you help?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77a913f9-d624-4376-8d8f-333ff6789d73"
msgid "Ordered to chain Nok-Nok."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4b33db1-6d96-4f05-8db6-0eb0bf1d5ee9"
msgid "\\\"Guards, have this creature thrown in chains.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19d82252-1851-49de-ade8-6c86a41fcfaf"
msgid "Ordered Nok-Nok's execution."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "743e7aac-71ad-4aad-92d2-5cbc83f276b7"
msgid "\\\"Guards, have this creature executed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "edbe09cd-09a9-4610-8d5c-dbd560a69b83"
msgid "\\\"Very well. We'll travel to Oleg's soon.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "662c7721-f3c8-4c37-a8ec-f243363c7aed"
msgid "\\\"Very well. I have instructions on how I want you to handle it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3b3d686b-df26-4fdb-97d9-ae5e54fb9328"
msgid "\\\"If it keeps you out of here, go attend to it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0107104-37e2-4724-9a47-46482a539a70"
msgid "\\\"I'm not doing it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32a54d15-570d-46b7-b344-561fa0ca7ebd"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll make you my specially-designated Warden, drive them out. By force, if "
"necessary.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2c03f14-49c2-4909-8ec4-eb9bdfa47d5a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tell them you are my Councilor. Ask them, politely, to move elsewhere – I "
"don't want any bloodshed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5808d433-316f-424b-a6d0-6e183350be6f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Represent them as my Grand Dipl- er, Diplomat. Tell them they can set up a new "
"tribe, but at least twenty leagues from Oleg's. Downwind.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f0987c88-92d3-418a-9657-2db7b1188ad5"
msgid "\\\"Not today, it's not worth our time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74ccb407-6719-469d-85f0-257c76c412ba"
msgid "\\\"'We'? No, this is a mission for you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d07977d5-8774-41e4-b387-9041805698c9"
msgid "\\\"A Hero grows on his own – and through his accomplishments.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8930ee7e-986c-4997-a4a3-94053ecfca4a"
msgid "\\\"It may be wise if I shepherded... er, accompanied... you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ea61291-2f64-4c0e-8aa1-82e7dddea163"
msgid "\\\"Yes, let's resolve this quickly.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f8c1a93-e9b1-432b-82e7-a64dfd447ebf"
msgid "\\\"We'll depart when I say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "768c74cb-4519-4df7-8870-cd6e0bd02fd5"
msgid "\\\"No, I have other things to attend to.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "465a071f-01a7-43b9-a508-48852bcde870"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace...\\\" {n}Kesten coughs politely.{/n} \\\"The goblin... the one you "
"found, has asked to see you. He claims you are in need of... training. I think he "
"is rather in need of a bath. Several.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dcd8e334-af71-466d-ab0e-2fa6e5334758"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace...\\\" {n}Jhod coughs politely.{/n} \\\"The goblin... the one you "
"found, has asked to see you. He claims you are in need of... training. I think he "
"is rather in need of a bath. Several.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "985fc0e3-11aa-4fba-980c-a6242daf10ee"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace.\\\" {n}Kesten gives a nod, then nods to the guards, who file out "
"of the room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4854b0a-533d-430b-b20d-b6a44d5c4f99"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace.\\\" {n}Jhod gives a nod, then nods to the guards, who file out of "
"the room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "138175a2-527d-44ef-9e7b-c7c35fefcafe"
msgid ""
"{n}You hear the sounds of weapons being drawn, a plaintive screech, and a crash of "
"metal, then silence. After a moment, a guard returns, nods, then resumes his "
"stance. After another moment, there is another screech, a loud clang, then "
"silence... then nothing.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2808284-ab3d-43e3-8fb3-2d63982464eb"
msgid "{n}You hear Kesten give a sigh of relief.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54cae58e-9397-4fb0-b2ec-868148b7419f"
msgid "{n}You hear Jhod give a sigh of relief.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3441965e-7849-4116-b7c0-c18b845f3604"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok strides in, as best as his short legs can manage, then his gait slows, "
"then strops as he takes in the throne room – his eyes and ears swivel "
"independently, as if trying to take every direction in at once – after scanning "
"the area around him, he looks upward, and squints, as if uncertain if there's a "
"ceiling above him or not. He stands still, swaying slightly, eyes affixed on the "
"ceiling.\\nOthers in the throne room are disdainfully silent, some wrinkle their "
"nose and take a step back. Some of the guard's hands fall to the hilt of their "
"blades.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58959dd4-0a7a-4d3e-b358-b35132d935a2"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok's head snaps down, then seeing you, he gives a sickle-grin, his eyes "
"gleaming.{/n} \\\"Sidekick? Almost didn't see among all longshanks.\\\" {n}He "
"frowns at your throne, then cocks his head, confused.{/n} \\\"Why in my chair?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c23b1c78-015a-480d-a3c9-f794c17e9671"
msgid "{n}There is a light chuckle from someone in the room, quickly silenced.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25448da9-d27e-45a6-a1a8-f177fcacc955"
msgid ""
"\\\"Took a while to find way here...\\\" {n}Nok-Nok glances around.{/n} \\\"...but "
"now here to take rightful place, be a Hero – and show you how to be a Hero.\\\" {n}"
"He nods sharply, and hooks his fingers in his belt.{/n} \\\"I can help, like "
"before, side by side, Big Hero...\\\" {n}He points to himself.{/n} \\\"...and not "
"Big Hero.\\\" {n}He pauses.{/n} \\\"You need it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee8e1ab7-5cbf-4b1a-af02-60547155ebde"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten frown.{/n} \\\"Actually, Your Grace, if you are considering accepting "
"assistance from this... this...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c6bc420-16ed-4c48-b636-062846041807"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod frown.{/n} \\\"Actually, Your Grace, if you are considering accepting "
"assistance from this... this...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c5912bfb-05b8-45cf-8c2e-370df2c9ea4d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nok-Nok.\\\" {n}Nok-Nok raps the ground with his heel twice for emphasis, then "
"winces.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f9b91403-d1db-45ed-9db8-bc137029b4b6"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten's frown deepens.{/n} \\\"If this 'Nok-Nok' TRULY wishes to be of help "
"and is one goblins might listen to, there have been sightings of goblins near "
"Oleg's... possibly dispossessed by our recent encounter-\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "221bacf1-5d47-45cc-9abc-aaee7bd31a56"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod's frown deepens.{/n} \\\"If this 'Nok-Nok' TRULY wishes to be of help and "
"is one goblins might listen to, there have been sightings of goblins near "
"Oleg's... possibly dispossessed by our recent encounter-\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38d8e217-bce4-4cab-857f-5cb6c025ec36"
msgid ""
"\\\"Massacre,\\\" {n}Nok-Nok corrects brightly.{/n} \\\"Chopped them all up except "
"those who ran fast. New tribe probably have very long legs, very hard to catch.\\"
"\" {n}His eyes alight, and he grins.{/n} \\\"But not for me, I can round them up!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7525d6a0-8c8c-4112-b616-0979e2b437f8"
msgid ""
"\\\"But...\\\" {n}He frowns again.{/n} \\\"But unless they were still being "
"chased, it's not like them to keep moving. Tires one out. They'd better stay in "
"the capital, like Nok-Nok, even if...\\\" {n}He wrinkles his nose.{/n} \\\"...it "
"smell bad here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce712f8b-d36f-4f79-ba2f-0182e136da54"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ah... yes. Oleg has sent word of these goblins via courier, but he has been "
"reluctant to leave in case they raid the Post in his absence. Apparently, they've "
"been quite diligent in trying to raid his storeroom. If your goblin ally could "
"deal with them...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7115df90-7ae5-4f9f-bba0-27c18ac3c15d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ah... yes. Oleg has sent word of these goblins via courier, but he has been "
"reluctant to leave in case they raid the Post in his absence. Apparently, they've "
"been quite diligent in trying to raid his storeroom. If your goblin ally could "
"deal with them...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "972ccce4-8df8-4cc9-bb8c-2052dcb3627a"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok nods, then pauses as he sees you remaining seated.{/n} \\\"Do... we go "
"now?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38a365ec-0ada-4af3-bc61-a9f981753cbc"
msgid "{n}Nok-Nok's ears perk up in your direction.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61d8bdd4-0219-47d7-b2f0-760a766a7284"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok nods, standing proudly. He makes what might be a ragged salute, "
"interrupted by him noticing something on his wrist, which he rubs away with a "
"frown.{/n} \\\"As you command, as a Hero w-\\\" {n}He rubs his wrist again, then "
"grunts.{/n} \\\"...will go. Lead to post, Nok-Nok follow!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59b9dc24-49eb-446a-9a26-37f3fae44588"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok shrugs.{/n} \\\"Might want to go quick-quick, goblins not known for "
"staying in a place for too long when longshanks around.\\\" {n}He makes what might "
"be a ragged salute.{/n} \\\"When longshanks good to go, Nok-Nok ready.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ea55c74-f0b3-4ee6-a720-918b2e4a386f"
msgid "\\\"No need to save Oleg's post anymore! Goblins left.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a8bbf67-4e1e-48d5-ab60-d919bf20fb68"
msgid ""
"\\\"When you do nothing, and heroics happen themselves — is one still a Hero?\\"
"\" {n}Nok-Nok scratches his head, lost in thought.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7150006-25ac-498a-9f52-1ed06dddd7b1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, there is one small matter... a series of small matters, actually, "
"that's growing into a larger problem... your goblin... ally... seems to have "
"invited more of his tribe to the capital, and they are acting as if… as if it is "
"their home.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ae13589-579d-46c2-825e-7f096a0b0273"
msgid ""
"\\\"It seems your goblin ally and his tribe have been industrious – they are "
"erecting statues to {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g}, the Mother of Beasts right outside "
"the capital. Do... they do this with your leave?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56c9a53f-2181-4329-9487-a4caaafc0f0c"
msgid ""
"\\\"It seems your goblin friend and his allies have been industrious in their "
"latest blasphemy – they are erecting statues to {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g}, the "
"Mother of Beasts right outside the capital. It's heresy, and it is spreading fear "
"and panic among the people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a004d96-c665-42d6-a3eb-5b5218a90baa"
msgid ""
"\\\"Could you please look into the matter? The guards are hesitant to deal with "
"the one close to you personally.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a45001f2-c12a-44a6-9f1f-5baa0744b573"
msgid "\\\"I take it this is yours?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d36a8dd6-abd3-4540-a254-8e3791bfa556"
msgid "Made fun of Nok-Nok."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "524bd29b-64bd-4910-880d-b40522bce99f"
msgid ""
"\\\"So you've finally decided to show me your favorite piece of underwear?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b665aba2-ecbf-40c2-a87a-680727794d6a"
msgid "\\\"Take this trash away from me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e4bfbd2-8395-4880-b90d-843557397b67"
msgid "\\\"What's it doing here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de2eae11-b069-4631-9c0f-687ec7c05392"
msgid "\\\"Well, get rid of this excuse of a codpiece.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a48c988-3cff-446c-a550-d4a0a2046cd0"
msgid "\\\"Good for you, you got your cap back.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20949f7c-ea06-48bd-8083-3cc06f06b60a"
msgid "\\\"What do you mean, challenge?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "67a6f89f-9c0e-4429-bcce-12c270306d1b"
msgid "\\\"The King has returned? Why would he humiliate himself?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3839aed4-d1e2-4d43-8aee-46d060338fec"
msgid "\\\"Then we need to stop him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0248ea5e-f264-4cad-bde8-0c6090904994"
msgid "\\\"Then you need to stop him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b3222d0e-e925-4a82-a5e4-f9f866b9d931"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you can lead me to him, I'll go with you – but the fight must be yours.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1dacb551-caa1-4c01-b183-0570e04b7773"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't have time for goblin politics. This is your mess, you deal with it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd75c92b-a669-4dd2-a2c6-61505c467316"
msgid "\\\"You wanted to be a Big Hero, so this is it. Go, prove yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb729ea8-b255-48bd-98aa-5ab36127562d"
msgid "\\\"All right, I'll help you, but we have to be quick.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34636990-3fdf-4d37-a36e-b06de301c3d5"
msgid "\\\"That's... not ominous.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c729e641-624b-43f9-b873-1f43c925cd55"
msgid "\\\"An enchantment? This may be Nyrissa's work.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85066978-ba7e-4ea6-a84c-ed55a65bac2c"
msgid "\\\"Did your tribe ever deal with demons?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5114f2cc-4bc6-4a51-b7ec-88cbba5a5354"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok seems confused. You notice what seems to be a leather rag in his hands. "
"It smells faintly of... sulfur.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08fccdcd-23b5-434f-aa97-23cd4f50eacc"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok remains frozen as he stares at the cap in hands – he seems surprised "
"and uneasy.{/n} \\\"Was once mine, wore in the village. {d|GoblinKing}King{/d} "
"once rip it off my head, beat me across skull and face with it... then use as "
"wiperag, and hit me again. Thought was lost, long ago.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "241bf3b6-9323-4dec-83ae-8e337ed3f5ff"
msgid ""
"{n}A series of light chuckles travel across the room. The startled goblin, "
"however, doesn't react to your joke.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42aaa6ba-e382-45bd-b85e-0349e2c672c1"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok looks uneasy.{/n} \\\"It's a challenge, for ruler of tribe. The King... "
"has come back for me. But... cap look strange, smell strange. Why now?\\\" {n}He "
"glances around.{/n} \\\"Where it come from? Goblin come here, drop it off?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49401065-1ac6-4b9a-bc55-71b655523955"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok takes a deep breath.{/n} \\\"When goblins in Steal Lands fight for "
"tribes, they fight over big, best hat. Hat like crown, but not ugly and shiny like "
"yours – this is a challenge, another tribe.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9153a393-7d44-46ce-b652-5bae4961592a"
msgid ""
"{n}He swallows.{/n} \\\"Maybe he hear of our allying. Think he can get back crown "
"by fighting me.\\\" {n}Nok-Nok looks confused – well, more so than usual – and one "
"of his ears begins to twitch.{/n} \\\"But how he get power back?\\\" {n}He finally "
"shrugs.{/n} \\\"If in kingdom now, probably cause a lot of trouble.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b83f04a5-eacd-4ab1-92e7-ecc244aac38a"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok shakes head, worried.{/n} \\\"Not sure can do on own. If he back, he's "
"ready for me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4f2c39c8-a15f-4ff1-9d3e-f999b9ccb7b6"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok nods, then leans down, then with a shaking finger, turns the cap "
"over... on the inside, you see a map scrawled in red.{/n} \\\"He show us the "
"way... we meet him where {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} Shrines are. We need to come "
"together, you and me. Rules of challenge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cec6d56b-8f53-4a98-9728-282c4952450d"
msgid ""
"{n}As you glance at the map, you both are surprised as the leather cap suddenly "
"alights, burning brightly... then crumbles to ash on the floor.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47a48465-94be-469d-a191-6ed14671fbbf"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok's face collapses as he leaves you. You slightly wonder if he will "
"actually take up this challenge at all.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eafb698c-2d11-43e3-9840-2bb168b0ffda"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok nods, then leans down, then with a shaking finger, turns the cap "
"over... on the inside, you see a map scrawled in red.{/n} \\\"He show us the "
"way... we meet him where {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} Shrines were. We need to come "
"together, you and me. Rules of challenge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a66f24f3-dd92-4ef7-8503-0020458f0e43"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok is silent, staring at the ash – he says nothing. You've never seen him "
"this worried. You decide to give him space, but keep the challenge in the back of "
"your mind.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a28cc0e-fb98-49c8-bddd-d5f617372d39"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, it seems the goblin tribe has left the kingdom. Good riddance, "
"if you ask me! Everyone seems happy… except your goblin ally, perhaps.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7327e4e-9f27-4332-927e-7fb0a95233a0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, there is something transpiring outside the city. You may want "
"to go yourself – it seems your goblin... ally... has been industrious again and "
"fashioned some sort of... something.\\\" {n}He sighs.{/n} \\\"It may be best you "
"go see for yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f27acd15-f61f-4c8d-afa6-80066260590b"
msgid "\\\"Yes… you anticipated my test. Of course. Well done.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2dbc7a3e-f899-4027-9fa8-7b3bb8967a39"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not yet. Stay here while I figure out the next... more confining... challenge."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c3d1f05-0f45-48c5-9a34-e96a5c9b110e"
msgid "[Attack] \\\"I'm tire of your antics, creature. I'll silence you now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd377f19-c3ec-47bd-8ffd-7e1d57c99f83"
msgid "\\\"How did you escape execution?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c009df7c-eba5-4981-9ead-46a10ee442ac"
msgid ""
"{n}From out of nowhere, Nok-Nok is standing before you, trying to whistle, but it "
"comes out more of a warbling of the tongue. When he sees you, his eyes gleam in "
"delight.{/n} \\\"You start Nok-Nok's {d|Nok Prison}training{/d} early! Very "
"clever, longshanks keep Nok-Nok almost thinking they try to chain him up like all "
"goblin children.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f28f259c-380e-4c33-97c4-cded02f7c890"
msgid ""
"\\\"But Nok-Nok knows better, be slipping out of cage when little countless times!"
"\\\" {n}He holds up a long link of chain, then dumps it on the ground where it "
"lies like a black iron snake.{/n} \\\"Training done!\\\" {n}He pauses.{/n} \\\"Am "
"I Hero now?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "354e9fb5-5b88-43ec-b1e2-ec9ec1adb976"
msgid "\\\"Another test so soon!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b13112f0-cf8a-4fa6-a16d-015e1590efdc"
msgid ""
"{n}From out of nowhere, Nok-Nok is standing before you, looking slightly confused. "
"When he sees you, he grins, his eyes gleaming in delight.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "671c5803-a983-46da-a413-d08d43a9b738"
msgid ""
"\\\"You start Nok-Nok's {d|Nok Executed}training{/d} early! Very clever, Nok-Nok "
"almost thinking longshanks try to kill him. But Nok-Nok know better!\\\" {n}He "
"raps his head twice, winces, then his slow smile returns.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2676018c-7e61-4b73-b979-1dee3c23a693"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok pulls down the collar of his ragged vest, revealing huge bruises on his "
"neck – and then removes his cap, showing his head, which looks to have a few more "
"lumps than before.{/n} \\\"Neck tough.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "78017726-7252-4ab2-be2a-3628a07bf915"
msgid ""
"\\\"Also, when guard not looking, loosen axe head – axe fall off, guard hit me in "
"head with handle, but Nok-Nok head too tough for that... guard so surprised, Nok-"
"Nok bite him in leg, then grab teeth with keys...\\\" {n}He pauses, thinking, "
"rubbing his head.{/n} \\\"No... keys. With teeth.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b4b75b2-da13-4332-b9af-caadd6bad2be"
msgid ""
"{n}He smiles again.{/n} \\\"Guard chase, hit Nok-Nok a few times in head, but "
"can't follow in sewer. Now Nok-Nok free again. Am I Hero now?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e5190cc-6338-4458-a2bf-b9e7ad064b1d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I Hero now! Hero better than... all other heroes!\\\" {n}He doesn't seem to "
"hear you.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dcd0eee1-d0fa-4051-8125-491049fe0d62"
msgid "\\\"How do you know they're from the Technic League?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3caa92d7-80e0-4624-84a1-b2d04430d299"
msgid "\\\"What are you planning?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a0ab2e2-d842-4d8d-b48c-c819932bd466"
msgid "\\\"All right. Let's go find out what the Technic League's doing here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59358409-db01-41b5-914d-217ecf555d6a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have trouble enough without any Numerian wizards. Guards! Get down to the "
"tavern and throw this spy out of the city.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bbf4fe6b-b0fb-4171-9728-3b08147ed015"
msgid ""
"\\\"If they return, the guards will just throw them out again. Leave the past in "
"the past — we have more urgent problems.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "abc1dacc-a49c-4ec3-9349-9fd7cf8726d0"
msgid ""
"{n}Octavia and Regongar exchange a look and both start talking at the same time.{/"
"n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ebede17d-3f6b-4796-b4ff-9a0997865fb1"
msgid "\\\"Do you think...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd67a5e5-74c9-4a3e-91f2-b6cd36a40797"
msgid "\\\"We...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca3c033c-68ed-4b2d-8150-f4a5f20a98bd"
msgid ""
"\\\"We knew the {g|Technic League}Technic League{/g} wouldn't just let us go!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "353e0860-0ab1-48ae-b279-948b6e01f2d0"
msgid ""
"\\\"And they sent their agent right here to the capital! Now that's impudence!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51c91e1f-bd8c-458e-a733-f33aaa0ac932"
msgid ""
"\\\"He's sitting in a tavern, paying with {g|Numeria}Numerian{/g} gold, and asking "
"around about Reg and me all day. Even if he's not spying for the {g|Technic League}"
"Technic League{/g}, we sure have a few questions for him!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "09fbf732-a6dc-4b4c-8430-f7daac826e7b"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's Kalannah — the wretch you {d|OctReg Kalannah Alive}let go{/d} after you "
"saved us from her! She's sitting in the tavern drinking beer like nothing ever "
"happened! Does she think no one will recognize her?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dfee8315-3206-4c60-a249-d1159b9641ee"
msgid "\\\"Or maybe she expects someone to. Either way, we have to talk to her.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0dec0da1-2efe-4b90-9330-2b9db2302606"
msgid ""
"\\\"What do you think? Once you get someone outside, it's not that hard to beat "
"some information out of them...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51c4d4fe-1959-4bc4-9a93-09b480b2ebc7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Reg, that can wait. I'd like to start with a chat, try to find out what "
"exactly they have planned. They wouldn't just send one agent in. And wherever the "
"cronies are hidden...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f0802ab0-6ea7-4af5-aabb-d03fb4aaace5"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's where we'll find the big fish!\\\" {n}Regongar slams his fist into his "
"palm with a grin.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "efae37b4-80ed-49c7-8780-3acfb480a3b8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wait, don't you understand? They came here for a reason — for us! And that "
"means...\\\" {n}Regongar clenches his fists.{/n} \\\"Maestro Janush must be here, "
"too! This is our chance for revenge!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "444edd62-00d7-4a61-af76-e48a54437dfa"
msgid ""
"\\\"Regongar's right — they're here for us. Even if we were to suddenly forgive "
"Janush and forget about revenge, the {g|Technic League}Technic League{/g} won't "
"ever leave us be. They'll keep coming, again and again, attacking us and those we "
"care about. Let's just deal with them once and for all!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68bda455-c3f0-4ba1-a086-35240f3bbfbf"
msgid "\\\"Great!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76d8c5e2-9378-45f9-9109-a2a6611ce7cc"
msgid "\\\"We'll wait for you in the tavern.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98a0eddc-d5bf-4bc7-8fc5-8961010b5039"
msgid ""
"{n}Regongar stares angrily for a long moment before turning and storming out of "
"the room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc4518ad-691f-4b89-924b-9129bbf0456d"
msgid ""
"\\\"You may be right... but I'm afraid it's not so easy to let go of a past like "
"ours. And it definitely won't let go of us...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02bce14b-217b-4c26-9b49-ee309257cec8"
msgid "{n}Octavia and Regongar exchange gloomy looks.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "041aece4-2c54-4ab3-8409-d8edb234e7a6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Remember when we said we saw a spy from the {g|Technic League}Technic League{/"
"g} in the capital? We should have hustled. While we were packing, the scum up and "
"vanished.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ee38289-be30-48cc-b64e-35b7513533a3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Remember how we found out about that {g|Technic League}Technic League{/g} "
"lair, where Janush had dug in? Scouts report the wretches left the kingdom. It's "
"too late to catch them — they're probably already in {g|Numeria}Numeria{/g} by now."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd987899-704f-46f9-8189-5477ac7aa4ca"
msgid ""
"\\\"I guess we'll never know what the {g|Technic League}Technic League{/g} "
"wanted... Now if only they'd never come back. I don't think for a minute they'll "
"just leave us alone — but we'll probably never get such a lucky chance to take "
"them unawares again.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd72a601-8c66-492f-a2ca-3f31c249df51"
msgid ""
"\\\"Remember those books from Maestro Janush's study? We'd hoped to find something "
"about our past in them...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8381aed-7e37-4238-b52a-ddcf77774c35"
msgid "\\\"Well... we did. And I'm kind of sorry we looked.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e85d26f-2005-4489-8c14-b08c17824105"
msgid ""
"\\\"We actually found something, but it's... a sensitive conversation. We'll wait "
"for you in the palace garden, near the viewing point.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ebdbe047-d2b4-46f2-a0c1-1b71fd08259a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Looks like we missed our chance to find these strange cultists, discussing "
"their goddess. Let's hope we don't regret it...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "afedd18a-ea24-4932-bd5d-1cfd3f52afb8"
msgid "\\\"That insane old man, Remus — he also spoke of some Goddess...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9012f29-17ad-494f-a3ba-3f3d6606a7be"
msgid "\\\"What is this 'kingdom' the prophet is building?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff5c77fa-d03d-46f2-8dea-9e42cae49481"
msgid "Decided to remove dangerous fanatics from the streets."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "07d0fa8d-62f3-448c-8239-6a768acf208b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I cannot allow my subject to be taken in by such nonsense! I shall deal with "
"these provocations immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "060f57e9-0e50-4700-8604-ff9fb5e69ed4"
msgid ""
"\\\"The people will believe whatever they want to believe. Leave the poor souls be."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c69aabf4-7a51-4e6b-b93a-a21aadfd548f"
msgid "Decided to protect your subjects from malicious beliefs."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72396400-c543-4ba8-8ea2-664576e5433c"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's absurd, and dangerous, for the people to consider death a blessing. We "
"must get to the bottom of this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eaa3ca26-21b0-434e-a908-e90fef39b207"
msgid "\\\"I'm not going to waste my time on this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c635988-d32f-476d-8496-9fd283f79e19"
msgid ""
"\\\"Troubling news indeed. We must find out who or what is behind this Goddess and "
"her faith.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b32d6f99-9635-4c72-943f-31bb804e97df"
msgid "\\\"Fine, I'm convinced. Let's look into this matter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ff10661-fb9f-4c93-8e09-e480629c576f"
msgid ""
"Threw Tristian out of the throne room when he asked to solve the mystery of the "
"dangerous cultists."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "671c4bde-bbba-4d7c-ba5f-4f1794f9f245"
msgid "\\\"You're beginning to annoy me. Get out!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df8ba3fc-1a29-4fec-a493-4bd39c41ee4c"
msgid "\\\"I said, enough!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f33d821-f514-427e-9983-1d1598ac980f"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name}, spare me a few minutes. You are the ruler of these lands and I don't "
"dare tell you what to do, but I just can't stand silently and watch what's "
"happening behind your back!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "766e1dbc-96d4-469c-a90a-57aec16b37aa"
msgid ""
"\\\"There are rumors on the streets of a savage Goddess, enraged by your "
"appearance in her lands. They say she cursed you, and now you bring woe and death "
"to everyone around you. This used to be just idle talk. But now, when we're "
"surrounded by so much death and suffering, the people are ready to truly believe "
"it. And it seems that someone is playing upon your subjects' fears.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1348a55f-16b3-466f-b51c-12b7969c0c39"
msgid ""
"\\\"I saw barkers in the streets telling citizens of a prophet who is building his "
"own kingdom. According to them, the Goddess stands ready to grant forgiveness to "
"any who cleanse themselves of the curse... But this cleansing is accomplished "
"through a terribly cruel death.\\\" {n}Tristian gulps heavily.{/n} \\\"These "
"horrific deaths involve a wild beast appearing from inside the body... and they "
"think it's a blessing!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "700bf9d3-975f-4ad3-83fb-78660576bca4"
msgid ""
"\\\"True... Jhod told me of that preacher. Who knows, perhaps his words touched "
"people more deeply than anyone imagined.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bb9f5371-0b0b-4275-97a0-87b144f4e356"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian shrugs.{/n} \\\"I only heard fragments of conversation. I think it's "
"not a 'kingdom' exactly. More like a community. — Or a cult. I'm afraid that we'll "
"need to find one of their barkers and ask them, if we wish to find out more.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31f0a766-98fc-4f1e-b339-e7a5f9f13bb8"
msgid ""
"\\\"How could you mean this?! Innocent people are accepting a magical affliction "
"for the mercy of an unknown deity! Even worse — they are prepared to start "
"worshipping her! I'm afraid to even imagine where this might lead.\\\" {n}Tristian "
"frowns.{/n} \\\"As I said, I can't just stand idly by as this unfolds.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7f5afbc-a55e-4d9a-a6f6-6980e9ce467f"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian nods enthusiastically.{/n} \\\"Good! Perhaps after uncovering this "
"mystery we will find out more about the nature of the curses hanging over the {g|"
"Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. I mean, there must be a reason that these cultists "
"shout about you receiving the Goddess' punishment! If we wish to understand, we "
"must find one of those barkers and learn from them all we can.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90f19447-775e-45c7-a88f-bd739db13f62"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian looks confused, almost surprised.{/n} \\\"But it's your subjects we're "
"talking about! Aren't you sworn to protect them — and not only from sword and "
"fire, but from a faith that would eat away at their souls and lead them to their "
"deaths?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22ed0328-f326-4f70-986d-d900657aed7f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Who knows? Could the land itself spawn a malicious power that strengthens evil "
"words, and gives them special potency? I hope we will find an answer!\\\" {n}"
"Tristian nods at you and looks away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12b4a0d0-2162-4fc4-904f-dbbae1c18087"
msgid ""
"{n}The priest thinks intensely for a few moments, then sighs and shakes his head.{/"
"n} \\\"If you are untouched by this frightening news, then I doubt I can make you "
"change your mind. So be it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1520ca9d-2aa2-44f1-a908-9335e9ac07bb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sadly, these street preachers scare quite easily and avoid our guards. I'll "
"begin my search without delay. When you find time, look for me on the streets of "
"the capital. I hope that when we meet I will have already found someone who can "
"tell us more about this strange Goddess and her followers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c7d8f44-cc83-46c4-96c2-7d72c2c2246e"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian opens his mouth, but changes his mind and turns silently away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0f837cb-019b-4a00-b652-d2b608d103c5"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian remains silent for a long time. When he finally opens his mouth, his "
"voice is hoarse and tired.{/n} \\\"I won't take much of your time, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d12ab423-033b-4d96-ad00-79b6d225c3ad"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've been meaning to ask you about something. This might seem stupid. Or "
"arrogant. Or just insolent...\\\" {n}Tristian stumbles and catches his breath.{/n} "
"\\\"I want to talk to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3d274d4-79a3-48d6-aefb-06e037a3c680"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think you know what it's about. It's — it's what I've done. And what I "
"haven't done.\\\" {n}The priest lowers his head and grows quiet.{/n} \\\"But let's "
"speak in private, far from curious ears. I will be at the viewing point, in the "
"palace garden. Please come as soon as you can.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf478ea9-e13d-4438-b714-34f378a14fe9"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie looks gloomy.{/n} \\\"I heard rumors that my old mentor, Fredero "
"Sinnet, assembled his entourage and left the boundaries of the {g|Stolen Lands}"
"Stolen Lands{/g}. It looks like we didn't make it to the trading post before his "
"patience was exhausted.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f0fa160-8bcb-4206-b6f8-0faa622a51c4"
msgid ""
"{n}The girl waves carelessly.{/n} \\\"It might be for the best. I'm sure you have "
"enough problems without a fanatic paladin claiming rights to me as property of the "
"Order of the {g|Shelyn}Eternal Rose{/g}. Pff!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df47705d-d477-49cf-939b-5052595e9672"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie looks at you from under her eyebrows.{/n} \\\"I heard a rumors that "
"Fredero Sinnet, a paladin from the Order of the {g|Shelyn}Eternal Rose{/g} was "
"killed at the trading post. Slaughtered with his entire entourage. Oleg and "
"Svetlana are keeping silent about it, like they're afraid of snitching on someone."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb9cf33e-8970-489a-b2fa-2ef1e89cbcd7"
msgid ""
"\\\"We need to guard your lands more carefully, {name}. It's unlikely you'll ever "
"create a proper state here if such unpunished atrocities keep happening.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6106f64e-f589-40ad-a763-b0cd424d744a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, today a {g|ValerieQ1}letter{/g} from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} was "
"delivered to the castle. It was written by Fredero Sinnet, a paladin from the "
"Order of the {g|Shelyn}Eternal Rose{/g}. It appears that Sir Sinnet is claiming "
"right to one of your companions, who was brought up in his custody... Well, I'll "
"leave it to you to handle this delicate matter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77db2101-76cc-4d0a-b6a3-6981aea00d57"
msgid ""
"\\\"A {g|ValerieQ1}letter{/g} from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, Your Grace. Fredero "
"Sinnet, a paladin and mentor of the Order of the {g|Shelyn}Eternal Rose{/g}, has "
"come to your lands to retrieve your companion, Valerie. It seems he's going on "
"some sort of pilgrimage, and he hopes his former disciple will come with him. It's "
"a rather unexpected request, but you'll have to deal with it. Here's the letter "
"from Sinnet.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50fbe76c-d67f-47c2-9424-d202d712b5c4"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have an intriguing {g|ValerieQ1}letter{/g} for you, Your Grace. A certain "
"Fredero Sinnet, a paladin of {g|Shelyn}Shelyn{/g} from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, is "
"claiming right to our charming Valerie! Not in the sense that the entire "
"population of the capital is trying to, but as her teacher and mentor! Here's the "
"letter – see for yourself!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a6efa26-9187-42d0-b262-8df0f814c071"
msgid "Letter from Fredero Sinnet"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b9000c2-e5d5-488b-9d42-c58c9a6cbee6"
msgid ""
"The expensive monogrammed paper has a faint, tangy smell. The lines, in steady "
"delicate handwriting, are decorated by whimsical curves.\\n\\\"My dear {mf|Baron|"
"Baroness} {name}!\\nI write these words with a heavy heart. The reason I take up "
"my quill today will most likely upset you. Quite recently I heard rumor that a "
"lost soul, once blessed with the mercy of my goddess, has found shelter in your "
"service. I'm speaking of the daughter of one of the most worthy and generous "
"patrons of the Order of the Eternal Rose, who once made the mistake of leaving our "
"ranks. I am deeply convinced that now is the time for her to return to the path "
"destined her by divine will.\\nI am now traveling to the west, to the place that's "
"been chosen for the new Temple of Shelyn that will be occupied by one of the young "
"congregations of our church. I deemed it necessary to diverge slightly from our "
"path with but one purpose: to arrive in your lands and collect Valerie. May this "
"journey be a cleansing pilgrimage for Shelyn's chosen, whose judgment was clouded "
"by the impulsiveness of youth.\\nI request that you free Valerie of her vows of "
"service to you, for fate has destined her to serve one who is above us all. Direct "
"the girl to the trading post that's on the border between your barony and Brevoy. "
"There I will be expecting her with my comrades.\\nI pray for your wisdom and mercy."
"\\nWith deep respect and regards, Fredero Sinnet\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1b7e2ca-144c-4399-b86a-55c8123ea6ec"
msgid ""
"\\\"Good news, Your Grace. Valerie seems to have stopped behaving like a furious "
"wildcat! I don't think we need to worry any more about innocent citizens meeting "
"her when she's on the war path.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a279c1f-e692-4b3a-9336-c723a3d0195a"
msgid "\\\"Valerie, explain yourself!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dfc1055a-92a9-47c1-a976-da657fc9678e"
msgid "\\\"Eveld? Is that the character next to you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "631e0b14-85d6-4c71-b064-0a042a0226f2"
msgid "\\\"You can't handle some row without me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "998d0deb-4643-4c78-b8e0-68f8454949ac"
msgid "\\\"Valerie, you overreacted. Apologize to Eveld.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49ebbb16-80ce-4d13-9451-eeff02501395"
msgid "\\\"Eveld, apologize to Valerie immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0ac643b-8cbe-4b5f-b8f9-b51f3d2a7ead"
msgid "\\\"You. Both of you. Figure this out someplace else.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d2d4c72-1374-4b71-83fa-b32b13b2fac1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't care who said what to whom. You're going to make peace now, right here "
"in front of me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0bffd020-de95-4ce6-8900-433df1c08e90"
msgid "\\\"What do you mean, 'hasn't been herself'?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b622bdaf-80b4-4162-b66a-7c7041e0d10c"
msgid "\\\"You think Valerie could hurt someone?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea893f7b-5e57-422d-8b9b-173df8213144"
msgid "Promised to help Valerie."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3310512d-71dc-4577-bf19-0f5102f867f7"
msgid "\\\"Thank you for bringing this to my attention. I'll try to help her.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ab53ae4-f396-42f1-8465-6a1f9a33f5fd"
msgid "Waved away the captain's concerns about Valerie."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c489d00-584a-4f64-8d42-494fd76b60d2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't have time to deal with Valerie's behavior. Keeping peace on the "
"streets is your responsibility.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f70455da-fac2-4b80-bea8-9e87ac8bac95"
msgid "\\\"I will talk to Valerie when I get a chance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ef64a023-2b8e-4ead-bae1-1552d0a6bcc7"
msgid "\\\"Eveld, did you really write a pasquinade about Valerie?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de577c34-2511-4a6c-9bc2-c3f4217d8957"
msgid ""
"{n}The captain's usually untroubled face is dark with rage.{/n} \\\"Your Grace! "
"Please forgive me for distracting you from important matters, but you're the only "
"one who can talk some sense into these hotheads!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4da1222b-db5b-4e7b-827b-2a812df8b4e6"
msgid ""
"\\\"They had an argument in the middle of the street! Yelled so much your subjects "
"called the guards... but what can they do about Lady Valerie? Plus, Eveld hasn't "
"done anything illegal... it's not like I can put them in jail!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97381ea0-eed3-467e-bdb3-8fd5f1d1ec11"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, Valerie is your companion, so she gets special treatment. She "
"doesn't take orders from me, besides it would be wrong...\\\" {n}The captain rubs "
"his temple.{/n} \\\"We fought together, protected the capital together... so what "
"am I going to do now? Arrest her?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7de9295-a65f-4f2f-8dbf-c6883cb28aaf"
msgid ""
"{n}A short, rugged man in a sophisticated garment bows ceremoniously.{/n} \\\"In "
"my own person, Your Grace! Eveld the Silver-Tongued, who once served as court bard "
"at the best houses of {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, and has now traded in his golden cage "
"for the free winds of travel. But I digress...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ef3ce511-aa36-492a-a6b4-5e2dec68b0e0"
msgid ""
"\\\"This, so to speak, sweet lady insulted me, if you please, in front of my "
"audience! Halted my performance and embarrassed me in front of the entire tavern! "
"Would you please be so kind as to rein this lady in!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77ac72e4-048b-4494-b999-a6847bb24e2d"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie is apparently trying to control herself, but telltale red spots flare "
"on her face.{/n} \\\"I noticed that someone pinned a disgusting pasquinade next to "
"the tavern entrance. Something about a bright bird who lost its feathers. "
"That's... abominable insolence! Yes, I won't deny I'm guilty. I lost my temper, "
"but who wouldn't have?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e93adedf-3c0c-4dd3-a509-f1e9cd59c43f"
msgid ""
"{n}Eveld gasps with indignation.{/n} \\\"Is that so? When I smothered this lady "
"with exquisite compliments, I received only insults and jokes in return! When I "
"came to her with gifts, begging her to become the muse for my greatest work – I "
"was ridiculed and sent away like a snotty boy! And now, the moment I start to "
"pursue my art away from this good lady, she seeks me out and says I'm guilty of "
"spiteful slander! What shall I do? I'm but a slave to my inspiration, which is "
"sent to me from above!\\\" {n}Eveld smoothes down his hair and adds.{/n} \\\"And "
"while we're on the subject of my poetry, it's really not that bad...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe058bf1-06e2-43ff-b2a1-a38e58b69e51"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie looks down, ashamed.{/n} \\\"I humbly beg your forgiveness, {name}. I "
"failed to control my temper and besmirched not only myself, but you as my leader.\\"
"\" {n}The girl casts a burning glance at the man in sophisticated attire, standing "
"beside her.{/n} \\\"Unfortunately, I was provoked.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "420ffc84-96fa-491d-ac57-ae701baa689b"
msgid ""
"{n}The man catches Valerie's glance and gasps with indignation.{/n} \\\"Is that "
"so?! So it's ah... Ah, forgive my manners, Your Grace! Allow me to introduce "
"myself — Eveld the Silver-Tongued, from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}. It's a pity we meet "
"under such circumstances, but...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ca1ecaf-04e1-4c0e-9697-b350c0b7c438"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hell no, Your Grace! If this rude dolt brought me here and since I'm already "
"taking up the baron{mf|'s|ess'} time, I need to make sure this lady is reined in. "
"I need protection!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3070b38c-efe1-4ae4-a174-93fed1710bfb"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie's voice rings with rage.{/n} \\\"I swear, another word from this lowly "
"scribbler, and anything could happen!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63145afe-b384-4cad-8b11-785da0578dc3"
msgid ""
"{n}Eveld opens his mouth but says nothing. Finally he starts enunciating words, "
"one by one.{/n} \\\"My only transgression is loyally serving my patroness, the "
"beautiful {g|Shelyn}Shelyn{/g} who sends me inspiration, and never hiding from "
"this world a single word that's born in my heart. But since my honesty and "
"openness are so offensive to this good lady, then so be it – I apologize for "
"insulting you, with all my heart!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a908b445-ea90-425f-8bdc-e3e4856de0ed"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie grows pale, and her lips tremble. Gathering her strength, she almost "
"pushes the words from her mouth.{/n} \\\"My deepest apologies, Eveld.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47a36675-448e-4b1c-8e2b-f0259421f39c"
msgid ""
"{n}Eveld turns to the girl with a triumphant look, about to say something, but "
"stops when he sees her face.{/n} \\\"I... I'm fully satisfied, Your Grace. I have "
"no more complaints about Valerie.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81cb496e-7a5e-410b-8763-8c72f9543bfd"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie purses her lips. She seems to want to reply to Eveld's monologue, but "
"in the end she changes her mind and just nods.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63121ff6-fff9-463f-91d6-eda9ce6b4d31"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your tongue befits your beauty, my sweet! Truly, what is a beautiful flower's "
"bud worth, if it's worm-eaten and empty on the inside?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1574f0dc-bf5e-43c3-8d60-3ce7a75b6f6e"
msgid ""
"{n}Valerie almost screams.{/n} \\\"I'm not going to make peace with this... "
"this... worthless paper-stainer! Let him spend his useless time insulting his "
"other bootlickers!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e82ab69-c5dd-411e-841c-13e3b001d3aa"
msgid ""
"\\\"Enough, both of you! First you scared everybody at the tavern, and now you're "
"embarrassing yourselves in front of the baron{mf||ess}! Apologize at once – if not "
"to each other, then at least to {mf|His|Her} Grace!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02b75542-99c1-41c6-b8f2-16662d5c3fca"
msgid "\\\"I... don't know what got into me, Your Grace. Forgive me this scene.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3cb12efe-509c-49fe-9bb5-ea02d608a404"
msgid ""
"\\\"Please forgive me, {name}. Perhaps I should leave, to calm down and come to my "
"senses.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a765b14-a585-4036-af77-6b6aedab899f"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's nice. You let some steam off, and worked some things out. At least now "
"I can let you go, hoping you won't scare our good people any more!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2584039d-328f-449b-b09b-a68bfdfffe67"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, I'll go too, but... please keep an eye on Valerie. I don't know "
"what demon has got into her, but she's not herself lately. At first she'd just "
"snap, then she started getting into fights with everyone about stupid things, and "
"now she's dragged this bard out of the tavern by his collar. I'm afraid it might "
"come to real violence!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff78a046-ea37-4ccd-adde-5c4f7c5c7781"
msgid ""
"\\\"Forgive me, Your Grace! Of course! I promise – you won't hear about Valerie "
"from me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7e3d1a93-84b4-45d6-afe4-3122db0b7eb2"
msgid ""
"\\\"If I were you, I would talk to the Storyteller. One of my lads saw Valerie "
"arguing with him. I have no idea how anyone can have a fight with such a harmless "
"elf... but she did!\\\" {n}The captain bows, finishing the conversation.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "253739ee-e900-48bb-bde8-946c24843cc9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, I wouldn't say that... the Valerie I used to know would never harm "
"anyone without good reason. But the old Valerie seems to be gone. So I don't know "
"what to expect from her.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d87f12cc-69e1-492a-bec2-dc940664afee"
msgid ""
"\\\"She got defensive. Can't say a word to her. We've been careful around her, "
"since she...\\\" {n}The captain runs a finger across his face meaningfully.{/n} \\"
"\"I'm close to ordering my lads to keep an eye out for her in the streets, to make "
"the common people's lives a little calmer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7967eae1-9393-4d4f-9ba5-3ae72705c866"
msgid ""
"{n}Eveld clasps his hand to his chest ostentatiously.{/n} \\\"Forgive me! Who "
"would I be, if I stooped to such low attacks! I won't deny that the cautionary "
"tale of this lady could inspire me...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "476cbf31-6a49-4be5-a11b-cf13bb15115e"
msgid ""
"\\\"How can you listen to this featherbrain? Of course, in the face of justice "
"he's ready to disown his own parents!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f2edfec-29d7-4134-b92b-06fb89c5af85"
msgid ""
"{n}The captain shakes his head sadly.{/n} \\\"Don't even try, Your Grace. I'm "
"afraid even {g|Abadar}Abadar{/g} couldn't get to the bottom of this ball of "
"accusations.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0ac925f-0b8f-4344-9604-830bb676f8e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"...and if I'm allowed to continue, let me say what this pasquinade was devoted "
"to: the sad position of the arts in these lands, forgive my frankness. Anyway, the "
"good lady is unlikely to understand what allegory and poetic hyperbole are!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "afd44567-fcb5-47e7-b46e-c2b46280c157"
msgid ""
"\\\"I was taken from an important affair! Embarrassed in public! And all because "
"some lady decided she can do whatever she pleases!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "800f7d31-cb03-4ae4-989c-f2c89bf338ad"
msgid ""
"\\\"Would you please behave at least in front of {mf|His|Her} Grace! We've had "
"quite enough of this manner you allow yourself with the peasantry!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7b14ff24-308e-4b17-bbcc-73adaf6db6ef"
msgid ""
"\\\"Bad news! We've heard that visitors have lately been spreading unfavorable "
"rumors about your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}. It's as if {kingdomname} is "
"a stronghold of barbarism and feeble-mindedness, where people of arts are rare and "
"endangered! Our artists are alleged by these rumors to be considered our least "
"valued citizens! Such rumors can't but affect our reputation. I'm afraid you'll "
"have to entrust one of your advisors with this matter!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90a6df78-edc8-4ff5-b6d6-8872eb58303f"
msgid ""
"\\\"An antique vendor, told me that that the Order of Prisms has been spreading "
"nasty rumors. – They're one of the branches of {g|Shelyn}Shelyn's{/g} church.\\"
"\" {n}Linzi scratches her chin thoughtfully.{/n} \\\"Here's what I've been "
"thinking... A couple weeks ago I saw Valerie tear up some letter. She was so "
"terribly angry! – Just like she was back when her former mentor came for her... "
"Anyway, I didn't ask her about it – that would be more trouble than it's worth. "
"But you'll probably be able to find out what happened, and if this has any "
"connection to Shelyn!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf2fcce6-f770-4492-9bc4-10f0e2ee1b1a"
msgid "Hurried to investigate the report of strange troll activity."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6464154-e05b-4700-bb8c-39b29fc385c8"
msgid ""
"\\\"A baron{mf|'s|ess'} duty is to {mf|his|her} people. I'll head south and look "
"into the situation.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9fb8f2b-4e8b-4ac2-9e9f-b810b5838678"
msgid "Ignored the report of strange troll activity."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35e80fff-cb64-4013-8dae-e93fe25d1689"
msgid ""
"\\\"You believe trudging through swamps and chasing rumors to be part of a "
"baron{mf||ess}'s duties?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "669910b4-5210-4a81-9062-9584934b8a44"
msgid "\\\"I may have time for this later.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5727ac07-f041-40d1-b798-d0ef6c4d75ca"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, Your Grace.\\\" {n}Kesten sighs with relief.{/n} \\\"When you "
"decide to go, please remember that trolls can only be killed with fire or acid.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aeb60a29-e70f-488c-af8b-500614299d89"
msgid ""
"\\\"Forgive me, Your Grace. However, if this problem isn't handled now, by next "
"month there may be no one left to save.\\\" {n}Kesten shifts uneasily.{/n} \\\"So, "
"if you do decide to go, please remember that trolls can only be killed with fire "
"or acid.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26fab9ce-31ae-4aaf-bb73-a9a8d41e49ab"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, I...\\\" {n}Kesten has a troubled look on his face.{/n} \\\"I fear "
"there's another matter that requires your attention. There have been reports, many "
"of them, from settlements across the {g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}. There are "
"trolls in the forest, seemingly hordes of them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88755c4d-9ff9-4ff5-8dbe-0191b6dcda2b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The common folk will hardly heed any simple exhortation — someone will need to "
"go to the {g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g} to investigate the matter. I was "
"considering the matter when it hit me: what if you were to take on this "
"investigation yourself, Your Grace?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3790ce4-2547-429b-b88b-c30c85fdbee4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Rumors claim they're more than the typical savage beasts. They almost seem to "
"show reason and tactics — they form groups, attack all at once, plunder the "
"villages, and carry away the peasants. Even stranger, kobolds have been spotted "
"among their ranks, when usually they would be attacked on sight.\\\" {n}Kesten "
"falls silent for a moment.{/n} \\\"I'm not certain any of this is reliable — fear "
"builds mountains of molehills. Some of the rumors even say these trolls carried "
"torches and burned down houses, seemingly unafraid of open flames. It's entirely "
"possible the rest of the reports could be exaggerated as well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9885eac-b39c-4333-85a9-111b6c864c21"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you would be so kind, Your Grace.\\\" {n}Kesten rubs his neck.{/n} \\\"Just "
"be sure to provision yourself properly before you go. Remember, trolls can only be "
"killed with fire or acid.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81b86d63-11d6-43c1-a6ee-8aab8fb90abd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace!\\\" {n}Kesten's face looks worried and fearful.{/n} \\\"Your "
"Grace, ill news from the {g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g} — again!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f94bb2d-608b-47b5-bb46-dc03f48c90f0"
msgid ""
"\\\"There were already many trolls there, but now people are afraid to leave their "
"houses! The wilds are said to be swarming with them. The hunters were the first "
"ones to notice, then came the merchants delivering packages and food to the "
"outskirts of the barony. Now there are more and more reports of trolls attacking "
"villages\\\"."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4da1e86f-57be-460d-9bb7-60f6d9943b73"
msgid ""
"\\\"At first, I took the reports for gossip. Thought it was just the fear talking. "
"But a local group of merchants recently reported that most of the trolls seem to "
"be lurking around the house of one Bartholomew Delgado — an odd mage living out in "
"the wilds all by himself. They're saying there are so many trolls out there, "
"nobody can reach Bartholomew for fear of the beasts!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f0c60d0-dca0-4bc1-9d70-2443b0c65910"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten's face goes dark.{/n} \\\"Those trolls are up to something, and this "
"strange Bartholomew fellow is clearly tangled up in it somehow. If the wizard's "
"gotten some idea in his head to conspire with the trolls, we should make the first "
"move and hit them with a preemptive strike. However, if the trolls are coming FOR "
"him rather than TO him...\\\" {n}Kesten sighs.{/n} \\\"It would be an enormous "
"help if you could pay a visit to Bartholomew and figure out what's going on. I "
"recommend haste — if nothing is done soon, there may be a grisly fate in store for "
"your subjects!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa2cb339-41ec-494c-b557-5415e4731e29"
msgid ""
"\\\"Local merchants reported lots of trolls lurking around the house where "
"Bartholomew Delgado lived — you know, that suspicious wizard you... Well, no need "
"to bring that back up. Anyway, I sent some reliable people there. They searched "
"his house and found a torture chamber in the basement, with a troll tied to a "
"rack. The poor beast died of hunger. Seems that's how the wizard amused himself..."
"\\\" {n}Kesten shakes his head grimly.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "80ded5c5-d2ee-4cfd-8cd6-fc048f6b1380"
msgid ""
"\\\"We're used to trolls lurking in deep marshes and forests. There were a "
"surprising amount of them around Bartholomew's house, and now we know why... But "
"whether the lack of response has made them bold or they're just avenging their "
"kin's torture, they're now attacking in broad daylight. They pillage, plunder, and "
"drag away cattle and people alike. Survivors say they seem to be taking all the "
"loot in the same direction, somewhere around here — that must be where their lair "
"is!\\\" {n}Kesten makes a mark on your map.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c9877f6-4c15-4c2f-9f7f-8859683bbaba"
msgid "\\\"Why did you bring this matter to me, Jhod?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92fabe5e-63af-441f-b846-7f6dde65ccc2"
msgid "Tried to intimidate the doomsayer."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8e20f6b-0d5c-43ed-8c6d-4d86f7e96536"
msgid "\\\"Stop talking nonsense, you old fool, or I'll cut out your tongue!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2e8a139-35af-4cc6-924b-b2b5422bb745"
msgid "Imprisoned the doomsayer."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "edd4a7d2-cf3d-491f-b92d-f91533daf7de"
msgid ""
"\\\"Give him thirty lashes for his blasphemy, then put him in chains. I won't have "
"him running free and causing more trouble.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0a65b72-fd5a-44d0-a40f-56783801147c"
msgid "Exiled the doomsayer."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9aa45a5a-1218-41b4-8a27-773bb9d5acfe"
msgid ""
"\\\"Drive the heretic from the barony — and use the whip to encourage him to make "
"haste.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a85a7c1-45cb-4c60-a5fa-33179c39d750"
msgid "\\\"I would know more about your prophecy, Remus.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "120df392-2ce2-4fd4-a203-3638482dd4cc"
msgid "Executed the doomsayer."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1eb61d3c-a0d1-42f1-8e30-7960b43dd3a9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Remus, by insulting the gods and defying your ruler, you have committed "
"treason. The sentence is death. Take him away!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32c6869d-117d-4ec3-9ea3-da130ea751c3"
msgid "\\\"Let's talk about your prophecy, Remus.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "472a0cdb-c47c-43e8-8a1b-1e36a79e4bc2"
msgid "\\\"Enough about your visions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c8f262d-0af7-4669-ba2e-811abb4f5d6c"
msgid ""
"\\\"What is this 'other world' you speak of? And what will happen to this city?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "779a3989-99b4-4041-9b31-dfede518666d"
msgid "Tried to calm the doomsayer down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28db5e80-42d9-48f2-80f8-a96df57291a6"
msgid ""
"\\\"So an angry goddess will lay our city to waste because we drained her swamp? "
"She must be a petty Goddess indeed, if she takes part in the affairs of mortals "
"even on such insignificant occasions. Perhaps you simply had a dream, and it "
"merely seemed real.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a7ec7ad-3bd0-4623-a480-16ef236d72cf"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about this goddess — I would know more about her.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3e567d7-12f4-460a-90a1-f48f9596396e"
msgid "\\\"How do you know about that?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5cab23fb-ca41-480b-b3bd-10d818327e10"
msgid "Let the doomsayer go free."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7193125f-d2e7-4aea-8cf1-9117b1115b2b"
msgid "\\\"We'll let him go, Jhod. One may speak freely in our streets.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "589fe774-7a39-4e65-8b14-83a364e2ed4b"
msgid "\\\"We've already met, just outside of Oleg's Trading Post. Remember?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5cc5f70b-8684-4b9a-a5f3-11a7d28c00de"
msgid ""
"\\\"I know you, old man. I met you near Oleg's Trading Post. And killed you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4d6d3677-ef8d-436c-97d2-ff7bf614851d"
msgid ""
"\\\"…and another world shall swallow the ugly city and its careless dwellers. And "
"only the rain shall weep for the emptiness left in their place.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c2d7e30-11e7-49c9-b9a6-674687d686fb"
msgid ""
"\\\"But… but…\\\" {n}Remus' gaze becomes clear for a moment. His shoulders slump "
"and he looks even older now, more tired.{/n} \\\"Maybe you are right. I… I need to "
"lie down.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc2236cb-5017-4ae1-9552-c9d54558bec9"
msgid "\\\"Your Grace, you have to deal with this madman!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4941f6f6-72fb-48c7-8292-38bcc8d98a18"
msgid "\\\"You don't understand! You are blind! But I'll make you see!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0955c7b0-2755-4045-a5a7-bbcf412ae17f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Her fury is like a river after a storm! Her voice, thunder in a summer sky, "
"Her touch, as cold and sharp as a sliver of ice. She is beautiful as a dream...\\"
"\" {n}Remus stutters, then blushes.{/n} \\\"It's been forty years since I last "
"longed for a woman, but Her...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b833454a-799a-427a-bc52-c8ac9d2e57b3"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Goddess showed it to me in my visions! She whispered about a beautiful new "
"world, told me She would heal nature's wounds. But I don't want it!\\\" {n}He "
"shakes his fist, threatening someone invisible.{/n} \\\"She must be stopped! "
"Sacrifices, we must offer up sacrifices. Goats, or cows, or horses... that will be "
"enough. It must be enough!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3b2476ec-3b1f-4167-8626-30262f06faa6"
msgid ""
"\\\"You are kind, Your Grace… perhaps too kind.\\\" {n}Jhod bows.{/n} \\\"However, "
"your word is law. I shall escort Remus from the castle grounds.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52f3b612-0111-4e0e-8a91-d671c005713f"
msgid ""
"{n}The old man before you is clad in tattered rags. His gray hair and beard are "
"filthy and matted. Judging by the smell, he has not bathed in some time, perhaps "
"years, and you have to fight the urge to cover your nose. Oblivious, the old man "
"picks at his beard in silence, as if trying to catch lice. You're not certain he "
"even knows where he is.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42366d6f-71d0-4ccf-ac26-517131973ab9"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's up to you to decide this homegrown {g|Aroden}Aroden's{/g} fate, {mf|Baron|"
"Baroness}. I await your command.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b350013-4d92-4a1a-b844-81e92b395492"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a harsh penalty, Your Grace… but a just one. Anyone who preaches fear and "
"causes discord must face the consequences.\\\" {n}Jhod bows, signaling the end of "
"the conversation.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fba0b517-2dc5-476b-b192-2c4c31f00d23"
msgid "\\\"{g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} have mercy, will you be silent, you fool?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b375898d-02c0-4456-aed1-b6e79731d53d"
msgid ""
"\\\"A different world, fierce and wild. Where mountains impale the sky, where "
"rivers change direction, where the very trees talk to the stars.\\\" {n}Remus "
"swallows and stares ahead, as though lost.{/n} \\\"The wild world will consume "
"this city, shape it in its own image. It will be the end of all.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "382f06fc-9525-4a2e-be84-3b596f978010"
msgid ""
"\\\"Who else can I turn to, Your Grace? This fool's words were frightening the "
"people, but alas — the crowds tend to love false prophets.\\\" {n}Jhod sighs.{/n} "
"\\\"In a sense, I saved him by bringing him here before things got out of hand — "
"just a while longer, and your subjects would have beaten him up!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0068532-9e92-4cf1-adde-9c9008a943b2"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod straightens, his face flushing.{/n} \\\"As if that wasn't enough, this — "
"{g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} forgive my words — 'prophet' blasphemed against the "
"deities, proclaiming we must bow to some false god!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce60f822-8451-40de-8c5b-0a8c47abafe1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm the only sane person in this city — this hideous, ugly city. Its stone "
"buildings claw into the soil, and thinks themselves safe. But the sky shall open, "
"the earth shall tremble, and this city shall crumble beneath its pride…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e0436ba-ca89-4349-84c8-2ae6c034bd78"
msgid "{n}Remus looks at you silently, nervously pulling at his beard.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a07e02e-3324-4769-ac72-a1c17d50b23f"
msgid ""
"{n}Judging by his flared nostrils and furrowed brow, something has upset Jhod "
"greatly.{/n} \\\"Your Grace! I have here one of your subjects — he goes by the "
"name ‘{d|Remus}Remus{/d}' — we caught him spreading false prophecies, sowing fear "
"among your people!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bc49ba7a-00dc-4cd2-bed3-27476aff3244"
msgid ""
"{n}At the mention of \\\"god\\\" the old man shudders and his eyes go wild, almost "
"feverish.{/n} \\\"The Goddess will rise from the forests! From the swamps! You've "
"cut down Her trees and drained Her marshes, but She will take no more of this! "
"Fall to your knees and repent, and She will grant you a swift death!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8af57711-a3b3-4017-a87a-a8326fcece0b"
msgid ""
"\\\"You don't understand! Nobody does! Only I do! Only I can stop what comes!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "660e3d3d-0006-450c-a811-9b06800bb6b5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Praised be {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g}! Is that a glimpse of reason? I thank you, "
"Your Grace, you have turned this poor man towards the light! I'll find him a place "
"to sleep and make sure he's fed and sent back where he came from once he wakes. I "
"think we should expect no more trouble — and no new 'prophecies'.\\\" {n}Jhod "
"smiles and bows, signaling the end of the conversation.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2f94057-cf12-4a8e-9535-ecff2dba7a90"
msgid "{n}Remus gives you an absentminded look. It seems he's at a loss.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a543872b-8a28-4b9b-9956-7ae7a5b1a4ce"
msgid ""
"{n}Remus shrugs.{/n} \\\"It's possible... Oh, yes, it's possible... I remember a "
"hundred deaths of mine, and I've forgotten a hundred more. But the goddess always "
"returns me to life. I'm Her voice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3cdcee46-4b05-4414-af66-f65045236839"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod looks to be puzzled and amused at the same time.{/n} \\\"Your Grace! I've "
"brought you an extremely unusual message.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c5b1199c-a88e-4199-b236-e23de915f42b"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's — how should I put it? — {g|JubilostReview_neutral}an essay on your "
"barony{/g}. Written by Jubilost Narthropple, and published only recently. I "
"thought you might like to see it for yourself.\\\" {n}Jhod hands you a magazine.{/"
"n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d96d3488-bb89-4c78-8c48-56714cc31900"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's — how should I put it? — {g|JubilostReview_good}an essay on your barony{/"
"g}. Written by {d|c21 Jubi pleased}Jubilost Narthropple{/d}, and published only "
"recently. I thought you might like to see it for yourself.\\\" {n}Jhod hands you a "
"magazine.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4bccae60-8c5c-46e4-935a-95524663169d"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's — how should I put it? — {g|JubilostReview_bad}an essay on your barony{/"
"g}. Written by {d|c21 Jubi displeased}Jubilost Narthropple{/d}, and published only "
"recently. I thought you might like to see it for yourself.\\\" {n}Jhod hands you a "
"magazine.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cfe6d824-c0a4-4013-81ae-55c2d5ffa4ce"
msgid ""
"Between the dense bogs of the River Kingdoms and the infertile clay soil of Brevoy "
"lies a region known as the Stolen Lands — a picturesque area combining the worst "
"features of the aforementioned countries. It's a woodland in which herds of deer, "
"swarms of mosquitoes, and gangs of bandits range and forage. The latter have "
"significantly decreased in numbers thanks to the efforts of the local baron{mf||"
"ess} — a protégé of the Restov Swordlords who's promised to bring some semblance "
"of order to these lands. Hoping to discover to what degree {mf|he|she} succeeded, "
"your faithful servant traveled to the Stolen Lands himself.\\nWhile I certainly "
"preceded my visit with a letter, as is common courtesy, the mailing service in "
"this new barony seems to operate with zero efficiency. The only party who came to "
"greet me was a horde of hungry kobolds — which, in these lands, can be found with "
"more regularity than any guards or, let's say, street cleaners. After barely "
"managing to fend off those pests, I narrowly escaped drowning while crossing the "
"river ford. It seems the only sight more rare than a paved road in these parts "
"would be a sturdy, well-maintained bridge. Every ruler should remember that their "
"realm's roads are akin to their face to the traveling public, and here they're "
"filthy and in desperate need of some good stone.\\nAfter those misadventures, I "
"finally found my way to the capital. Compared to other parts of the barony, the "
"city looks to be in relatively good shape, despite the smell. I must credit the "
"ruler's efforts — there are buildings in progress everywhere. Passing traders "
"praised the baron{mf||ess} for eliminating the bandits, and they expressed hopes "
"that {mf||s}he'll eventually deal with the wildland monsters as well.\\nDue to "
"some odd climatic anomaly, the Stolen Lands have become a land of never-ending "
"summer, though I wouldn't recommend choosing the destination for your summer "
"vacation. On the other hand, if you're tough and unpretentious, if you can work "
"hard and defend yourself, you might try your luck here — working hands are in "
"great demand in the capital. There are also plenty of jobs for free adventurers "
"and sellswords — after all, the local baron{mf||ess} was one {mf|him|her}self not "
"so long ago. As for me, I think I'll stay for a while to watch how this new barony "
"grows. If I don't end up drowned in some swamp, snacked on by an owlbear, or dead "
"of dysentery, we'll meet again in the next issue!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d80cca21-0694-492b-9a42-25e6754a4870"
msgid "Left Oleg's Trading Post for Brevoy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "086a0993-a2cf-48bb-9b89-d1aa1d3a6dce"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our barony owes much to Restov's Swordlords. We'll allow them to collect taxes "
"from Oleg's Trading Post — it's only fair.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97627b83-8242-42dc-98c5-c580baf544f6"
msgid "\\\"Oleg, which would you rather swear allegiance to? Restov, or myself?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2121585-97f9-45a9-ad56-9bdf9c78db3d"
msgid "\\\"Advisors, thoughts?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b3ee03a8-1a24-403d-bcf0-67ffec2c78ce"
msgid "Sent the guards to secure Oleg's Trading Post."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a9bf533-0ed6-444d-8a29-b58688b46962"
msgid ""
"\\\"Kesten — send guards to Oleg's Trading Post. Take what's due, then guard our "
"new subject and his goods from any further Restovic claims.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c5b0912b-b7b8-431e-9659-624a7b0ef86b"
msgid "Forgave Oleg's undercollected taxes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da82b31f-6a87-400b-ad07-1078761dc3be"
msgid ""
"\\\"We won't collect any taxes from Oleg this month. Let him go. I'll discuss the "
"matter of Oleg's fealty with the Swordlords in {g|Restov}Restov{/g} so we can "
"determine whether he should be bound to them or to me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f4660f2-c012-4e4a-850c-f2bd63046ad2"
msgid "\\\"What's the matter, Oleg?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29c43e2b-d098-434d-a9ca-5b13313373c5"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't recall granting permission to waste my time on such trivial matters.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "147a69d3-c883-4576-b277-ade245ea57e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"There can be no justification for tax evasion. There's nothing to talk about "
"here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23672c9b-25ed-416f-9862-342e589468eb"
msgid ""
"\\\"When you brought down the Stag Lord, I thought my troubles were over. But no!\\"
"\" {n}Oleg shakes his head.{/n} \\\"My whole life, I've paid taxes to {g|Restov}"
"Restov{/g}. Now, on top of that, YOUR tax collectors darken my doorstep!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "571b4a54-e8a1-4cb4-ab55-45e4a6837534"
msgid ""
"{n}Oleg smiles faintly.{/n} \\\"Well... I... I thank you, Your Grace.\\\" {n}He "
"bows awkwardly, then rises, embarrassed.{/n} \\\"That's most just of you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7b85e8e-a756-45fe-a561-5bcbf5125c88"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd certainly think twice before just giving subjects away to a rival kingdom, "
"especially a subject that could keep coins in our coffers.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4984eda-df27-48dd-8da8-dce2cd12cc16"
msgid "{n}Jhod sighs quietly, studying Oleg with a worried expression.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7dfc81d9-dfbe-40bb-8262-d1d4eef06fa6"
msgid ""
"{n}Oleg grimaces, making a clear effort to not spit on the floor.{/n} \\\"Since "
"the moment you founded this barony, Your Grace, I became your subject...\\\" {n}He "
"grits his teeth.{/n} \\\"But I'm still also a subject of the Aldori in {g|Restov}"
"Restov{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40379567-6357-4a19-80f6-ac32750eff1a"
msgid ""
"\\\"The fool didn't realize he should have come to you immediately, but even so, "
"please lend him your ear!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8214e75-99c8-4761-b6e9-225dcd18108f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oleg's Trading Post is within our borders. We have the right to collect taxes "
"from him. As for the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} — to Hell with them. They won't "
"start a full-scale conflict over some backwater trading post.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e5eafca1-f6c5-490f-8df6-65041567323c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oleg is more important than a few months' worth of taxes. Collecting now would "
"ruin a kind and honest — if somewhat clueless — man. Please keep this in mind, "
"Your Grace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af700e2b-ab1a-4495-95fd-1f203d59911e"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could have just given Jamandi a rap across the knuckles. Oh well. Diplomacy "
"it is.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4b67f194-14f0-49e3-b580-34153502d3f3"
msgid "\\\"A bad peace is better than a good war.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4257b670-8115-4ccf-8daf-5b7df010acb9"
msgid ""
"{n}You can hear Oleg's teeth clench. His hands ball into fists. While he was "
"clearly angry before, his face has turned red with fury, but he holds his tongue.{/"
"n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89640e91-71cb-431e-bd02-8f6a46f105bd"
msgid ""
"\\\"A problem demands your personal attention, Your Grace. Your acquaintance, "
"Oleg, has been refusing to pay his taxes for months now, even though his trading "
"post is located in your lands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1a56208-580d-48e0-b10a-2d2f16bf5ae1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm certain we can reach an agreement with Jamandi and acquire the trading "
"post in short order without any direct conflict with the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/"
"g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed9396c7-43fe-4adf-ba31-4c708170b631"
msgid ""
"{n}Oleg looks like he's surprised to be asked. He thinks for a moment, and you "
"realize he's making an extraordinary effort to be polite.{/n} \\\"Forgive me, Your "
"Grace, but regardless of what banner they fly, all tax collectors are little more "
"than bandits to me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e240b0d-bd5f-4a98-ab2c-b4aa99bb4788"
msgid ""
"\\\"A harsh decision, but the right one. A good ruler can't afford to fool around."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "318c8fb9-d321-4bb8-b0c3-414dc046a653"
msgid ""
"\\\"I fear this matter may be more complicated than you expect. Oleg, please "
"explain your situation.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b4dd9dd-dad2-40eb-9a06-61e64c5bd565"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, the Aldori {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} are true allies and the "
"backbone of the barony. I would hope you still value Lady Jamandi's support and "
"won't let such short-term interests undermine our alliance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a2d49bb-b51a-4922-9a76-23a78bfd5cc4"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's high time we let the Aldori know who truly rules this realm. A coach with "
"two coachmen cannot travel a straight road.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c294b86e-e354-4492-af4b-08b5ef47fb06"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra shakes her head mournfully.{/n} \\\"This is unwise. You're within your "
"rights to do this, Your Grace, but please remember — in the politics game, the one "
"who knows how to bite is the first to be eaten by the others.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0768043d-912c-4692-8d11-0be80058199a"
msgid "\\\"Thank you, Your Grace. The Aldori will not forget this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3264a70d-1493-4192-a6bd-346a6c37e0eb"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil bows his head.{/n} \\\"A wise decision. Should you wish, I will write "
"Lady Jamandi myself and explain the matter to her. Perhaps she'll agree to a "
"sensible sharing of taxes between the barony and {g|Restov}Restov{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6d55ce62-5561-493a-98d1-ea5ab47fbb16"
msgid ""
"\\\"You should be more forceful in your negotiations, Your Grace. You purged the "
"lands of bandits. You brought order to the realm. You should be the one collecting "
"taxes from the populace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a5265d9-7663-4ca3-aee8-b49fc22b2d4b"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil's face darkens, but he maintains his composure.{/n} \\\"I hope you know "
"what you're doing, Your Grace. An ally's trust costs a fortune, and a trust "
"betrayed may cost even more.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f593d8ee-6a1b-4c0e-89c9-f0274bb934e4"
msgid ""
"{n}Shandra nods approvingly.{/n} \\\"It wouldn't hurt the Aldori to learn a lesson "
"in manners. Jamandi may give an overdramatic gasp of offense, but the Aldori are "
"in no position to retaliate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "675ea1d6-266d-443d-aac8-9f947350b4a4"
msgid "\\\"Hey, take it easy on him!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "309d6004-51a4-4597-bdad-163cf4a12938"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll accept their offer and send Restov the year's taxes from Oleg's Trading "
"Post. We'll also improve the road between Restov and the post.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0119492d-2272-45b8-a41d-c04bd95de03b"
msgid ""
"\\\"In that case, we'll have to permanently station guards at Oleg's Trading Post. "
"Perhaps even turn it into a military checkpoint.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46a658fe-d0b6-4e25-a64d-0e5a88a3cdc2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've no interest in crossing the Swordlords over Oleg's Trading Post. Perhaps "
"we could send them a sum of gold as compensation.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f4ae12d0-b328-4eb8-8ed7-fd60b777013c"
msgid "\\\"This is no time to be pressuring our allies.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c123f646-55ad-4819-9c82-bec12daae3c8"
msgid ""
"\\\"So be it. I'll suggest the Aldori renovate the road to Oleg's post, since they "
"want to continue collecting taxes for the Restov treasury from him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b03fde10-18d6-402b-996d-4135d05be851"
msgid ""
"\\\"We can't openly confront Jamandi. We'll bide our time — declare we've begun "
"working on the road. There was no mention of a specific time line for the "
"renovation, was there?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2f2287b-1854-4187-b94e-1d65d857a1d6"
msgid "\\\"Thank you, Kassil. We'll repair the road.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea2ee0bb-c4c3-46df-8e10-99e39348633c"
msgid "\\\"I value what the Aldori have done for me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f33e1c05-bc88-451f-ac85-68a712bf45fc"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's all well and good, but perhaps the Swordlords should consider doing "
"something for the trading post they want to collect taxes from.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "386de9d4-f836-4674-a2b2-71368bb72061"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander purses his lips and shrugs.{/n} \\\"Pay them off? Not the wisest "
"decision, but... suit yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7adaa6cd-3668-4d7c-bf71-4b4b2d6559ff"
msgid ""
"\\\"The {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} are most satisfied by your decision to leave "
"Oleg's Trading Post under {g|Restov}Restov's{/g} jurisdiction, even though it "
"formally belongs to our barony. Here, {g|oleg_leftforbrevoy}read for yourself{/g}."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4d949698-db0e-4b1f-89bf-17db6ca8ebb5"
msgid ""
"\\\"The {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g}' reaction to your request for jurisdiction "
"over Oleg's Trading Post is... rather cold, as though they'd never considered that "
"{g|Restov}Restov{/g} shouldn't be collecting taxes from the subjects of other "
"rulers. Now they are demanding compensation — not only in gold, but also in form "
"of repairing a road from the Trading Post to Restov.\\\" {n}Lander rolls his eyes."
"{/n} \\\"{g|oleg_forgiven}Read for yourself,{/g} if you wish. It's quite "
"entertaining.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e6449391-5be5-4e51-a3bb-04d4bc388f57"
msgid ""
"\\\"Predictably, the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} are furious that {g|Restov}"
"Restov{/g} couldn't collect Oleg's taxes for the month.\\\" {n}A satisfied grin "
"curves Lander's mouth.{/n} \\\"Also unsurprisingly, there's little they can do "
"about it beyond stomp their feet and rattle their scabbards. Here, read for "
"yourself — it's a light but entertaining {g|oleg_secured}read{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ead92a2-4d4d-4535-8bf9-66aeb5ed4e67"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander doesn't even try to pretend he isn't gloating.{/n} \\\"I'm positive the "
"{g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} will hate this. I'm all for it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ddd13af-61d7-49e7-8a9a-cb4b0ee6951f"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've received a letter from {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} concerning Oleg's Trading "
"Post.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49aad8c0-e1a9-4bea-8678-cf37c902fcd4"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm still amazed by your decision, but what's done is done. A bit of advice: "
"squeeze anything you can out of Jamandi for this — anything at all. If the Aldori "
"are so proud of this alliance, make them actually contribute to it rather than "
"just keep hoarding YOUR tax money.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0c03080-3b6c-4967-aa57-bd09480afc15"
msgid ""
"\\\"I would advise you to be more... resolute, let's say, in your dealings with "
"the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g}. Don't fall for their diplomatic frills.\\\" {n}"
"Lander gives a dissatisfied cough.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fcd41b7c-5df6-4e16-ba66-d49fa4be61f5"
msgid "\\\"Perfect! The road will be of great use to us as well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30313765-eb1b-49a2-82cb-9226dbb9f12d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course, of course!\\\" {n}Lander spreads his arms in conciliation, though "
"he doesn't seem to be convinced.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3d5e6aea-08c5-4516-b74f-df17d7514b3d"
msgid ""
"\\\"You just leave that to me! They'll get their renovation, don't you doubt. "
"Believe me, I know all there is to know about showing a flurry of activity without "
"actually doing anything.\\\" {n}Lander smiles, a rare sight indeed — he finally "
"looks less arrogant than usual.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "60804f31-8922-4f02-b1c4-6026384c40fb"
msgid ""
"\\\"As expected, Swordlord Jamandi is both perplexed and grieved by your {d|c21 "
"Capture OTP}decision{/d} to take the trading post away from {g|Restov}Restov{/g}. "
"Still, you should probably read {g|oleg_secured}the letter{/g} for yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58d02fb6-d79d-4433-9239-2488ace03dfa"
msgid ""
"\\\"I must admit, Lady Jamandi wasn't pleased by your {d|c21 Claim OTP}request{/d} "
"to surrender jurisdiction {g|oleg_forgiven}over Oleg's Trading Post to you.{/g} "
"The Aldori take matters of allegiance and loyalty very seriously. Nevertheless, I "
"was able to convey your position and clear the air. I believe I'll be able to "
"persuade the Aldori to not demand a year's worth of Oleg's taxes from you. "
"However, repairing the road falls entirely to us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90922950-6940-4a27-b1d8-634059eebe69"
msgid ""
"\\\"Lady Jamandi truly appreciates your {d|c21 Left OTP}decision{/d} to not lay "
"claim on the taxes from Oleg's Trading Post. Here's {g|oleg_leftforbrevoy}the "
"letter{/g}. I was also instructed to express the lady's most sincere gratitude for "
"your loyalty to our alliance, as well as the wisdom you showed in your decision.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e9a01d3-fe01-49ae-a4aa-41eac746bbde"
msgid ""
"\\\"Lady Jamandi, in her typical sensationalist manner, expresses her extreme "
"dissatisfaction with your decision to take Oleg's Trading Post from {g|Restov}"
"Restov{/g}. Here's {g|oleg_secured}the letter{/g} — I hope you enjoy the wording.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a7238521-82b6-44f5-8981-55bac4758437"
msgid ""
"\\\"Lady Jamandi is, to put it lightly, puzzled by your request for {g|Restov}"
"Restov{/g} to surrender Oleg's Trading Post. She's demanding compensation — not "
"only in gold, but also in form of repairing a road from the Trading Post to "
"Restov. Go ahead and {g|oleg_forgiven}read it{/g} — it's marvelous.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e35b77cf-f90e-41cf-a624-c6388f171192"
msgid ""
"\\\"Lady Jamandi has written a {g|oleg_leftforbrevoy}whole two lines{/g} "
"expressing her gratitude for deciding to not take back taxation rights for a "
"trading post located in your own lands. How typical of the Aldori!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ed80375-9682-4b81-92d9-8c6ae9fc6a4f"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil's face brightens.{/n} \\\"I'm glad to hear that you still value the "
"friendship of the Aldori, Your Grace. {g|Restov}Restov{/g} is bound to accept a "
"financial compensation.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf6a1053-7ad2-4bda-9efb-e596a35d5d10"
msgid ""
"\\\"What, you've decided to go back on the issue after all?\\\" {n}Shandra purses "
"her lips.{/n} \\\"Well then. I suppose sending Jamandi a few coppers might help "
"settle her down, at least.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3546714-d910-4cb2-b085-528bc83aed3a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I cannot adequately express my worry over this decision, Your Grace. I can "
"only repeat myself: it is unwise to squander one's friends.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "227b53c1-085d-4592-b1d2-1a19e199e138"
msgid "\\\"Hard times call for hard measures.\\\" {n}Shandra nods in approval.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a372e06-44f7-4ab1-a280-2917b763fd30"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil sighs.{/n} \\\"I would advise you to not put on a show in a matter where "
"honesty would be both more appropriate and more profitable. However, the matter is "
"yours to decide. Your lands, your roads.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7b5dbd17-a161-4147-951c-d9121ab09619"
msgid ""
"\\\"I did warn you that the Aldori would find a way to turn a profit on this "
"issue, didn't I? In politics, softness is always taken as weakness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a22dc95e-64d2-44c7-8f76-9439912067da"
msgid ""
"\\\"My pleasure, Your Grace. The new road will increase trade with {g|Restov}"
"Restov{/g}, which should profit everyone involved.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72478c85-27e5-48d9-a6b2-08f247ee37ac"
msgid ""
"\\\"Half-measures.\\\" {n}Shandra winces.{/n} \\\"It would have been easier to "
"just give Jamandi a slap on the wrist at the start. But this will do as well.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d28c40fe-a00c-4068-95b4-8ed983d3e20c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Some allies can become a stone tied around one's neck. Nevertheless, if you "
"wish to play nice with Lady Jamandi, I can simply shrug my shoulders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7658f1a7-0b1a-4fb9-8332-d61331caf694"
msgid "\\\"That should prove useful to our friends in {g|Restov}Restov{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cec46d1a-6264-4c18-9e19-582d68530ae0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just as the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} value you and your friendship. You "
"can rest assured of that.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "299fca44-0c07-4a28-98bf-558670d842ac"
msgid ""
"\\\"If it's so important to you... I'll send a letter to {g|Restov}Restov{/g} "
"suggesting they repair the road leading to Oleg's Trading Post. Both sides should "
"benefit from that.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "829a57ef-be29-4b1d-8bca-bf4ba1a90352"
msgid ""
"\\\"I strongly recommend you find some way to rip her off, just to return the "
"favor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3676b47e-d72b-4ad0-a6bc-dca773d30d82"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't like the direction this conversation is taking. We'll speak again "
"later.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72cdfc9f-7a68-4dbd-954b-0c2b7fc504af"
msgid "\\\"What brings a Pitaxian noble to my barony?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf6d7fb7-e776-406a-8b60-7ef2277b1b79"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ah, yes — King Irovetti. Worry not. I'll be sure I send him a melancholic "
"missive relaying news of your tragic fate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79fd16e1-6428-4dd9-ac3e-d29f68810a00"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now, allow me to — personally — tax your cortege, so as to help improve my "
"economy. And as taxes are especially high this year, I do hope you'll be able to "
"pay — the punishment for failure to pay is imprisonment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6dc602d-ddab-41e0-8048-c10b97afeb6f"
msgid "Put the rude Pitaxian guest in his place."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf2c6da9-fc64-4490-957a-f5dd9db037f7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Sir Stefano, please be frank with me — have you ever had the pleasure of being "
"acquainted with the hooves of a jackass? Other than your own feet, I mean.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1cadce0-5cd2-41f3-8a13-9fb2b49a9019"
msgid "\\\"What news of Pitax?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3749d07e-6f99-4910-8292-4edcc2af02a5"
msgid "Met the Pitaxian guest's insult with an insult of your own."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d69e5470-08f5-4e3a-994d-a9a4467ed8ad"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd watch my tone, were I you, lest I send you back to Pitax sooner than you'd "
"planned.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "011ff0a9-bbf7-41da-b3aa-cab78479d875"
msgid "Threatened to kill the Pitaxian guest for his rudeness."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45ae6cdb-d152-428c-ae38-b4fbf5f2ec00"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd watch my tone, were I you, lest I send you back to Pitax in a box — or "
"perhaps several boxes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "05b964ad-b7d8-417d-9b3b-709dff8751cc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes, the tragic fate you met after attempting to escape your chains. Now, if "
"there's nothing more, I'd suggest you go replaster your face with whatever makeup "
"you've been using — your cheeks are so bright, the red glow must be visible from "
"Absalom.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76096759-1407-4de7-aaf7-f7f6da0b5b84"
msgid "Reacted moderately to the Pitaxian guest's rudeness."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81492b70-11e3-443c-944e-5b8e12b1ffaa"
msgid ""
"\\\"A five-year-old could tell you're deliberately trying to offend me, Sir "
"Stefano. Perhaps you could just tell us directly what it is you came here for?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c5e5ea84-dd4b-475a-a645-8b0e0002ce2b"
msgid "Told the Pitaxian guest that you are always open to fair criticism."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24be8ade-5a04-4050-a4c1-6d182195fd0e"
msgid "\\\"I'm always open to criticism, so long as it's fair and reasonable.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a30bcaf-dc86-4f88-bee5-ba868ef93bd5"
msgid "Gently answered the Pitaxian guest's criticism."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c28e9eb-1468-48f9-9212-bbbb0d0e72e4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Perhaps there's a touch of truth to your words, but my barony is still very "
"young. Everything will be different soon.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49d29eb4-e7f9-4f8b-81be-8c747fb8387a"
msgid "Threatened to kill the Pitaxian guest for being rude."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "60e7cc8c-ec36-44cb-be98-c7ddc5699cfd"
msgid "\\\"Another word and I'll send you to the gallows.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cad769ab-8352-42e8-8d2a-c81771aa948c"
msgid "Responded moderately to the Pitax guest's rude criticism."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b68db8b2-a447-4f38-ac2f-3e7c48690471"
msgid ""
"\\\"No matter how weak my barony may be, you have no right to speak to me in such "
"a tone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44cda5e2-88bb-4525-9881-e383dfe7f8aa"
msgid "\\\"I hope you've taken the hint. Get out.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe9091a7-b46c-47a2-8016-b82450d829e5"
msgid "\\\"Run along, then — go back and cry in your king's lap. Move along.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6ae76810-6239-44a7-bcc3-5425a2f61a4b"
msgid "\\\"I'll leave that to your imagination. This audience is over.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "005ab4a9-f082-4a07-bf97-d10327071ef8"
msgid "{n}Sir Stefano opens his mouth, then immediately closes it.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "667eacdd-7dfd-40f0-a2b8-382eb32fe64a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Life in {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} is splendid, thank you! All thanks to the work of "
"my king and sovereign, Castruccio Irovetti. Our city definitely prospers.\\\" {n}"
"Sir Stefano grins, staring unabashedly into your eyes.{/n} \\\"A stark contrast to "
"your own crumbling hamlet.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe008dc6-cb2c-46cc-b1b0-fb743d35cf2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"What do you mean? A noble dignitary from a neighboring state visits your "
"capital — a close friend to King Castruccio Irovetti, at that — and you can't make "
"time for a short conversation? A true host would never think to treat their guests "
"so.\\\" {n}Sir Stefano grins, staring unabashedly into your eyes.{/n} \\\"Indeed, "
"this hamlet seems to be faring even more poorly than I'd initially suspected.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25d04c01-4158-4bbe-8e2b-58d0e2dc194f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nothing. You have absolutely nothing to offer.\\\" {n}Sir Stefano continues on "
"without giving you a chance to respond.{/n} \\\"Military — weak. Culture — weak. "
"Economy — weak. You'd best pray to all the gods that my King Irovetti doesn't "
"declare war on you. On the other hand, maybe you should pray he conquers you — "
"this mess of a barony could use the rule of a proper king.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "274d0129-805d-4969-928d-f7b1cb39a68a"
msgid ""
"\\\"And now we resort to insults. Hardly surprising.\\\" {n}Sir Stefano lets out a "
"long sigh, tapping his rapier.{/n} \\\"Well, you aren't worth the glove it would "
"take to challenge you. Besides, you'd probably just run off and hawk it — it's "
"easily worth twice what you've got in this throne room.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "127ead89-4135-488d-adf3-70e2e0d8d5c6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, then, I'll gladly give you my report.\\\" {n}Sir Stefano's voice takes "
"on a condescending tone.{/n} \\\"Follow along on your fingers, assuming you can "
"count. One — your army is weak. You lack the guards to properly defend your lands, "
"so you must choose between the villages, the towns, and the trade routes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "802c8fb9-da88-4425-8d1c-16c04bab9982"
msgid ""
"{n}As he approaches, a mean, sly smile appears on his face — clearly practiced and "
"prepared in advance.{/n} \\\"Ah, the ruler of this 'barony.' I'm flattered by your "
"attention. Sir Stefano Moskoni of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}, at your service.\\\" {n}The "
"man performs a derisive bow.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0fd6eaf-446d-4010-acaf-000910f5ff73"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, I'll be on my way, don't you worry. If I were to stay any longer, I fear I "
"might pick up fleas, or lice, or whatever else passes for subjects in this place. "
"Take care! No need to see me off.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "153a0759-e7f1-49c8-a948-4762d34e3d55"
msgid ""
"\\\"Two — your economy is a shambles. You have to personally resolve an issue of "
"tax collection from some lowly inn — and it seems your treasury even depends upon "
"this handful of coins.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc7b5367-18c3-4d21-bab6-2c41b75b0054"
msgid ""
"{n}The man before you reeks of vanity. His black hair is curled, styled, and "
"generously waxed, from the hair atop his head to the points of his moustache. His "
"cheeks and forehead are powdered white, giving him a pallid look. His hand rests "
"casually on the golden hilt of his rapier.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c4cb2c2-3bb0-40fa-8187-19f6a4d1e4fc"
msgid ""
"{n}Sir Stefano, furious, starts to speak.{/n} \\\"My king will not stand for-\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c40ea05f-88cd-4fee-91bd-309d92be4eb8"
msgid ""
"\\\"I was just traveling back home to glorious {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} after paying a "
"visit to {g|Restov}Restov{/g} — all in service to King Castruccio Irovetti. I "
"thought I might take a day to visit the capital of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}'s bold new "
"neighbor...\\\" {n}Sir Stefano sniffs, then grins.{/n} \\\"I must say, I really "
"should have spared myself the trouble. It's hardly worth seeing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b6a2c7b2-ed78-4b4d-9992-d52e0d5835cc"
msgid "\\\"Wha-\\\" {n}Sir Stefano pauses mid rant.{/n} \\\"My... tragic fate?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85dd57d8-26d9-44ff-8037-9cf87986cb37"
msgid ""
"{n}Sir Stefano stares at you and snorts.{/n} \\\"You know, the initial goal of my "
"visit was to take measure of your so-called 'barony,' to see if you had anything "
"of value to offer to {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}. And do you know what I found?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f597d01-e84b-40b6-a22a-f7c15c7f127a"
msgid ""
"\\\"And three — your culture is... well, nonexistent, really. What do you even "
"have? No art galleries. No universities.\\\" {n}Sir Stefano waves his hand "
"dismissively.{/n} \\\"Your capital may as well be a cowshed, with you a donkey "
"sitting atop a heap of hay.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f7a4c1c-2e01-406c-a95b-67f162ddcb77"
msgid "\\\"I... I'll take my leave now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d8ca749-aee2-4bfe-9534-50f7b8f0f258"
msgid ""
"\\\"If anything ever changes here, it'll be the number of dung flies — and that "
"will only grow. Ah, well, I shan't continue this slaughter — no use battling "
"someone who can't even fight back. All the best!\\\" {n}Sir Stefano performs a "
"mocking bow.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ef8f577c-9104-4786-929f-0ee30a313aab"
msgid ""
"\\\"Indeed, what was I thinking? What value could there be in speaking to someone "
"who can barely understand the words of an educated noble? I've learned what I "
"wished to know — I bid you farewell.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e3a34ed8-eaf3-443a-ab2a-1c8895c7c044"
msgid ""
"\\\"Great news, Your grace! {d|Varn}Maegar Varn{/d}, lord of Varnhold, wants to "
"form an alliance with you and establish a trade route between your lands. Here is "
"{g|VarnHello}Lord Varn's letter{/g}, see for yourself!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "794562d8-462c-4821-acb6-e6f4b0c1ddc8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Good day, Your grace. A courier has delivered a {g|VarnHello}letter{/g} from "
"{d|Varn}Maegar Varn{/d}, the ruler of the colony to the east of our capital. If "
"the messenger's words are to be believed, he has a lucrative offer for you: he "
"wants to establish a trade route between your realms.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5023b13f-af54-4af7-b734-f4d4d9b5bfb8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, look: {g|VarnHello}a letter for you{/g}! Looks like it's from one of the "
"go-getters doing Aldori's bidding. Have you ever heard of a {d|Varn}Maegar Varn{/"
"d}? No? That's funny — he sure knows a lot about you. Enough to try to sweet talk "
"you into building a trade route.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eae2a5ff-0184-46be-8a7b-793274b4a4fc"
msgid "Maegar Varn's Letter"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26a41d97-2079-441c-a2aa-de0aa8f5a7df"
msgid ""
"\\\"Most Honorable {mf|Baron|Baroness} {name}!\\nThis is Maegar Varn, the ruler of "
"the neighboring city of Varnhold, writing. You might remember meeting me at the "
"reception — our encounter had a powerful effect on me. You are a brave warrior and "
"a wise ruler, which is why I hope to enlist your support and, in the future, form "
"a firm friendship. No matter whether the gods or the Swordlords have contributed "
"to us becoming neighbors, I believe that our alliance will be as steadfast as a "
"rock.\\nTo signify the formation of our alliance, I invite you to visit Varnhold "
"and see for yourself that my intentions are good. The city is still young, but we "
"have a lot to show our guests. Our cellars are full of wine barrels, and our "
"storehouses of grain and cheese. It is easy to reach my city: the path to Varnhold "
"lies in the east, past Lake Silverstep, and over the ridge of the Tors of "
"Levenies. Hard to get lost in these parts.\\nWhether you accept my invitation or "
"not, I ask of you one more thing: consider building a route and developing trade "
"between our lands. I am convinced that both of us would only benefit from this "
"union.\\nI anxiously await your visit.\\nRespectfully yours,\\nBaron Maegar Varn\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b5ba5834-0b70-44ed-8b98-a09117ee9083"
msgid ""
"\\\"Miss me?\\\" {n}Whistling to herself, Linzi enters the throne room. The bard "
"is thinner than you recall. She seems to have acquired a few scars, and her "
"clothes look no better than rags. Nevertheless, she seems as cheerful as ever, and "
"her smile as carefree.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "824f68b7-1002-4df5-a59a-e0cf4d5d612a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, I had quite an adventure in {g|Numeria}Numeria{/g}! Enough material to "
"fill a whole separate book, and then some! All those barbarians, metallic "
"monsters, {g|Technic League}Technic League{/g} agents... How I managed to make it "
"out, only {g|Shelyn}Shelyn{/g} knows!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8cc960c4-d3d9-468d-a022-34b99cffd4c0"
msgid ""
"\\\"So, how've things been here without me? Seems you've become a baron{mf||ess}! "
"You'll have to tell me later how you managed to defeat the Stag Lord, and all the "
"rest of your adventures. I'm starving for details! My book isn't going to write "
"itself, you know!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73dbd96e-9876-4abe-b6e1-bb3a85096435"
msgid ""
"\\\"Who are these Embeth Travelers, and what would they ask for their help?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b3867ae2-5b30-40c2-b299-22525d7f6f3e"
msgid "\\\"Whom will we invite for the hunt?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3fecd415-2118-4df6-b5f0-183e87aa64fa"
msgid "\\\"Why not invite Irovetti himself?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51948bea-edaf-40de-9dad-d7b0873949e1"
msgid "\\\"Aldori from Mivon? I thought Swordlords were from Brevoy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff8f232c-3292-4fd0-99ca-833e9c6ca4e5"
msgid "\\\"How would you describe the relations between Mivon and Pitax?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b5eba29-42b5-4e5f-8c94-5156d9b92e2a"
msgid "\\\"Good idea. Invite the guests.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87f73019-de5c-4caf-b59f-29ec5f8d22f2"
msgid "\\\"We don't need external help. This is our issue to deal with.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db00829b-c18b-4423-9d47-2a9ba72db556"
msgid ""
"\\\"I beg pardon for the intrusion, Your Grace, but I'm afraid I have bad news. "
"Magic beasts are attacking people across the country. No one know where they come "
"from, but if the situation continues to develop as it has, it may pose a serious "
"problem.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca695afd-816f-4c41-ba40-d42d43097e75"
msgid ""
"\\\"Fortunately, there is good news as well. The {g|Embeth Travelers}Embeth "
"Travelers{/g} have offered their help to fight the monsters. I expect this would "
"be a good opportunity to invite some guests from neighboring countries to join the "
"hunt. Would you mind that?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "226d4b47-5506-4860-9ed4-9bd80fef87bb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, we've received troubling reports. Magic creatures are attacking "
"your subjects at an increasingly alarming rate. No one knows where they come from, "
"but if we don't nip this in the bud, it could become a real disaster.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d784b351-020d-4c10-b667-202d4b62a8a5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Has anyone told you the bad news? No? I guess I have that honor. We have a new "
"problem: an invasion of wild and hungry magic creatures. There have already been "
"casualties, and if we dally, there'll be more. We have to find the hellhole "
"they're crawling out of and seal it. Otherwise, you risk becoming a ruler with no "
"subjects, I'm afraid.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4133f0d-5d35-482e-819d-85d41a80a2ab"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Embeth Travelers}Embeth Travelers{/g} have offered their assistance after "
"learning of the problem. We could invite some guests from neighboring countries "
"and turn the hunt into a diplomatic affair. What do you think?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "853e9089-4056-4344-9593-b2aa2624b530"
msgid ""
"\\\"The bright side is we've got an unexpected ally. {g|Embeth Travelers}Embeth "
"Travelers{/g} have offered to help us thin the monsters' ranks. I suggest "
"combining business with pleasure and inviting some guests from neighboring "
"countries to participate in our little hunt. How does that sound?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8c597a3-233a-40f4-8e48-a2d15e4d2ef1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Embeth Forest is south of your domain. It's a dangerous place, swarming with "
"wicked fey and other magical creatures. {g|Embeth Travelers}Embeth Travelers{/g} "
"are renowned for their mastery of eliminating such threats. They don't ask for "
"much — compensation for traveling expenses, and the right to keep any trophies "
"they hunt down. This seems a fair price to me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d70167fc-f57e-417c-a30e-b90831b20ca6"
msgid ""
"\\\"We need to establish connections with our closest neighbors: {g|Pitax}Pitax{/"
"g} and {g|Mivon}Mivon{/g}. I'll invite someone from King Irovetti's inner circle, "
"as well as some Aldori {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} from Mivon.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "175ff5f4-63bb-4a7e-a4bd-f4b3e81998ab"
msgid ""
"\\\"He would most likely reply with a polite refusal. Once he stepped foot on your "
"lands, he'd find himself at your mercy. Irovetti is a treacherous old fox, and "
"he'd expect nothing but similar treachery from others.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62221700-9c90-412f-ba73-649adfe58736"
msgid ""
"\\\"Typical for the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}. They have an armed-to-"
"the-teeth truce, with regular skirmishes along the border. They have many mutual "
"issues, but they won't grab for their swords as soon as they see each other. "
"Especially not on neutral ground.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33c33513-d979-40d1-8b82-06ae1f8767c2"
msgid "\\\"I'll give the necessary orders immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c98b9c2e-e32a-4a3f-888c-2d3324ab7dc5"
msgid "\\\"As you say.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a2dc1c87-7653-459e-8501-dbd240dcdcc0"
msgid ""
"\\\"{g|Mivon}Mivon{/g} is mostly controlled by the Aldori exiles — they descend "
"from those who preferred to flee when {g|Choral}Choral the Conqueror{/g} arrived "
"in {g|Restov}Restov{/g} with his dragons. I would advise against reminding them of "
"that shameful story.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0358945e-3202-459d-9eed-3239852cc59a"
msgid "\\\"Lamashtu? What do we know about her?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69d2b155-3454-45d7-a58a-1d02279510dd"
msgid "\\\"The goblins are behind this disaster, then?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b9ab51e7-6dda-489e-b75f-fc73d4f0ffea"
msgid ""
"\\\"So we need to find a goblin leader and press them for information. Any idea "
"where to begin the search?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74cf77b9-03b9-4255-8ec3-650f068ac62b"
msgid "\\\"Thank you for the information.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "756f21c7-b3a2-4f00-8abe-cac1952b14b9"
msgid ""
"\\\"The epidemic continues. More and more people die — more and more monsters roam "
"your lands. Some of your subjects have alread fled in search of safer havens. Your "
"barony's very existence is in danger.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08638767-8495-42f9-853c-f4e4f188b778"
msgid ""
"\\\"Whoever started this epidemic, there's no doubt their goal was to destroy your "
"young barony. As the number of monsters increases, people panic and flee to other "
"countries.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f930cb5d-d5e8-4630-bc4a-49f0b7f1b27e"
msgid ""
"\\\"If we don't do something about this epidemic, and soon, you'll have only "
"hydras and wyverns to rule over! The more folks get eaten, the more other folks "
"panic, and the more they're tempted to flee to our neighbors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aba26cc8-7109-4280-b136-1c5fdaada1bd"
msgid ""
"\\\"We do have good news, too. I managed to gather some information that, I hope, "
"will help you eliminate the threat before it's too late.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b8df195-8798-466f-94ea-49e2c27c7a3e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Shortly after the epidemic started, goblins began appearing everywhere. The "
"locals report that these goblins have been celebrating and shouting something "
"about the 'day of glory for {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g},' when all humans would be "
"eaten by monsters and only goblins would remain. Sounds disturbing, does it not?\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98ff7077-e1db-4035-9005-f27f43662a2a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Behind it? Doubtful. Benifiting from it? Quite likely. I'd surmise that the "
"true cause of this disaster is either human cultists of {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} "
"or, even worse, some supernatural creature related to her. In any case, the "
"goblins likely know enough to provide some clue.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fac5732f-39fe-4ae5-bed0-21c6e6d5cccf"
msgid ""
"\\\"She's called the Mother of Monsters. Her symbol is the three-eyed jackal head. "
"She's an ancient and extremely evil goddess, who spreads nightmares, insanity, and "
"— perhaps of most interest to us — monsters. Her worshipers are mostly of the more "
"monstrous races, like goblins, lamias, and gnolls. That said, there's no short "
"supply of secret followers and cults among more civilized peoples, too — including "
"the people of the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7bc2cdc-a51f-482b-83e7-62312efc4cfc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes. You were wise to prevent widespread panic by keeping the epidemic secret. "
"Due to that, my agents caught several goblins and learned the location of their "
"village. I'll mark it on your map.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b5afb44-0021-4beb-93ae-36be63afee06"
msgid "\\\"I hope it helps you to save the lives of your people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2686e2fd-0b87-4969-a5f3-93ef37aba33f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Happy to help. Take care, though — there's no doubt your enemies still have "
"plenty of tricks up their sleeves. If you value your throne, take them down as "
"soon as possible.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "311af08d-3bc0-4fd9-80e1-afb4ce8316f2"
msgid ""
"\\\"You're welcome! Be sure to make those goblins talk, though, or you may risk "
"both your crown and your head!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0726ef27-d4cf-4c16-884a-86ea2a74cdd4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Alas, nothing more than vague speculations. Once you alerted your subjects to "
"the danger, they began defending themselves as best they could — my agents "
"couldn't catch even a single goblin alive. But rumor has it that the goblin "
"village lies somewhere in the {g|Kamelands}Kamelands{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a6928f0-2129-478f-968b-449152989ba5"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm sorry, no. Panic spread everywhere — my agents had to run for their lives "
"after villagers mistook them for spies and well poisoners. They were almost "
"lynched on the spot. All we know for sure is that there's a large goblin village "
"somewhere within the barony. You'll have to locate it yourself, I'm afraid.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70cee091-3bed-4f73-9c3d-e752174a35de"
msgid "\\\"What do we know about this disease?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d531ba1-56d9-4dcc-a61c-b32b962200fd"
msgid "\\\"Can't you handle this without me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "edcdbf36-4005-48b9-94a1-2a869266cf8d"
msgid "\\\"Any progress curing the disease?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4f01e6a7-a21a-48f2-807f-9de5be8d12ff"
msgid "[Follow Jhod] \\\"I see. Let's go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5171b79e-f2c9-4f63-87c8-056b90219925"
msgid "\\\"Vivisection? What exactly are you going to do?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "abd81a72-cad1-4c94-a402-00850be2434b"
msgid "Advised Jhod to operate on a random patient without waiting for a volunteer."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "779334dd-8f51-41c5-a4bc-47dce12a1925"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why wait for volunteers? You could perform the surgery on a random patient "
"without waiting for them to explode.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ffca607-e434-4b28-b9e4-8c0c169dc161"
msgid ""
"\\\"We happen to have a master vivisectionist available. Send for Bartholomew "
"Delgado.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a5a888f-ed8d-42dc-9bd5-371e1e84f7b6"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod's eyes are bloodshot and his posture is slack. The wrinkles on his face "
"have deepened, and his sparse hair has gone gray.{/n} \\\"It's a disaster, Your "
"Grace. We have an epidemic developing in the country. The afflicted first get a "
"fever, then a bloody cough, then several hours later...\\\" {n}The cleric shakes "
"his head and grimaces.{/n} \\\"And that's just half the trouble. Afterward, the "
"bodies of the afflicted become like some kind of cocoon, and monsters hatch out of "
"them. People keep dying, and we haven't the slightest clue what's causing it or "
"how to deal with it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20f1e96a-0a38-47c7-b9c7-d9eeece7d327"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tristian and I established a field hospital in the building of the former "
"prison. Don't look at me like that — there were no better places to choose from! "
"Frankly, we were lucky to find this one. To cut a long story short, we have a "
"female patient who's volunteered for vivisection. It means cutting into her living "
"body to look for the source of this disease.\\\" {n}Jhod frowns.{/n} \\\"After the "
"surgery — {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} forgive us — we'll be lucky if we can close her "
"up and let her go alive and well. However, we don't want to do it without your "
"presence, Your Grace, so please try to find some time to attend.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2b65a25-52f5-44c3-b2af-a5e3e70fe93a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not much — just primary symptoms, actually. We're not even sure if it's a "
"disease, a curse, or some magic parasite. Perhaps with your help we'll manage to "
"learn more.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8729594f-9cf6-4b77-8629-45551ca1c071"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, we're not playing games here. Do you wish to keep your barony? "
"That requires taking care of its people. Whatever you may think, you have no more "
"important business at this time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a3c511f-5cf9-4781-9b45-dcbf9c5f2248"
msgid ""
"\\\"How should I put it...? We've got none! We haven't been able to save a single "
"patient yet. We're like blind kittens bumping against a wall, and we have nothing "
"to show for it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acf80a90-a04b-4271-985b-7e49e9510a2e"
msgid ""
"\\\"What...? We're going to find the source of the disease, that's what! Once the "
"monster emerges, the body of the afflicted is torn to pieces, making it impossible "
"to learn anything from the remains. But we found one brave woman who gave us "
"permission to cut her open. The straits are dire — we don't know exactly what "
"we're looking for, and the vivisection is extremely dangerous for the patient. But "
"we're left with no other choice.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f84758f-d54a-4893-aaff-d2b3d863a2f2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Bite your tongue! I'm a cleric, not some... butcher! My duty is to save and "
"comfort people not... Not...\\\" {n}Jhod goes silent and just shakes his head, "
"frowning.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "93c14d54-d97d-4d50-9c49-f6b77668a71b"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod frowns at the wizard's name, but then nods.{/n} \\\"Fine. You're right. "
"He's certainly... peculiar, but none can deny his knowledge. He may be able to "
"help us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0635fc24-3f03-47e6-b1a7-2e81dc19b467"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's one more thing.\\\" {n}Jhod hands you a battered letter.{/n} \\"
"\"Kesten, that dunce, sent {g|WitchHuntKesten}a message{/g}. He rambles from place "
"to place — these letters are all we ever receive. Well, just read it. I guess it's "
"urgent.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "afe6d7f4-1a46-4bc9-99f8-49ff3e7735eb"
msgid "Kesten's Letter"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2326dac-bbd6-4d05-821d-2e573aadddab"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace,\\nPlease, forgive me my sudden disappearance. I deemed myself of "
"more use among your subjects than at court.\\nThe people are afraid, Your Grace. "
"They believe that they've been forgotten, that their ruler couldn't care less "
"about the simple folk, even as they perish each and every day. For this reason, "
"those who can bear arms are starting to take matters into their own hands. A wild "
"mob is a force to be reckoned with, and you already have enough to worry about. "
"Fortunately, I was able to convince these people that I'm on their side. In the "
"end, I have decided to lead this militia myself, in order to be the first one to "
"know whenever the people learn something new and to protect them from making rash "
"decisions. I've led troops before, and your subjects view me as one of their own, "
"so they trust me and are willing to follow me.\\nIt was with a heavy heart that I "
"left your castle, but my hope was that once among the common people, I would be "
"able to track down the source of the disease that struck the barony. I was "
"recently informed that one of the squads scouring the outlying regions of "
"Kamelands had encountered a mysterious shrine. Our spies report that at the "
"beginning of each week, cultists gather there to worship the dark goddess "
"Lamashtu, the patroness of all manner of hideous creatures.\\nI know little of the "
"gods and their affairs, but the appearance of the Mother of Beasts and her "
"followers in a land teeming with monsters can hardly be a coincidence. As soon as "
"I've finished writing this letter, I shall lead a squad of my best men there and "
"await your arrival. I ask for your help, Your Grace, for I shall need it to "
"strangle this filth in its cradle. Who knows — perhaps, we'll capture one of the "
"cultists alive and find out if they and their goddess are behind the misfortunes "
"of your barony.\\nYour loyal servant,\\nKesten Garess\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57c90600-4c75-4b94-91fc-6e9e63c68d64"
msgid ""
"\\\"Jhod, the surgery showed that it was magic seeds causing the disease, correct?"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9e5bb2b-be63-4ef8-a29a-045c1952dec2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Kesten, we discovered that the Lamashtu cultists weren't involved with the "
"monster infestation.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82536692-eb45-4492-84c6-a610506709f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Goblins obviously like having all these monsters around. To them, it's like a "
"sign of Lamashtu's benevolence.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3068886-f163-4f97-8acc-ad9bbeefa994"
msgid ""
"\\\"So, the Bloom's essential properties are strange seeds getting into people's "
"bodies, which causes their disease and eventually creates magic portals. Now we "
"just need to discover where the seeds are coming from.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c22fdd00-f8c9-4958-bc37-c6743bf1ccfe"
msgid "\\\"Kesten, the militia most often finds monsters by the river, right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86b1d559-3076-49ed-a09e-bd4a4279be6c"
msgid ""
"\\\"There are dozens of villages along the riverbanks — hundreds of people. How "
"many are likely already infected?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1941a35d-8ccb-446b-a6e8-3d3293eb6bf9"
msgid "\\\"We have to go upstream and find the source of this blight.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a07813e9-df90-4c75-b69e-fda86add1c58"
msgid "\\\"Can we keep people calm? Persuade them to wait a bit longer?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f06a3867-1353-4332-bd11-b88748226520"
msgid "\\\"Kesten, are you still with the militia?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7407b9cd-0344-4364-bd83-a4d93a3318e5"
msgid "\\\"Jhod, how are the patients in the prison doing?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81c476cc-8e61-40b6-8732-f59802c0922d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tristian, how did you find the link between the disease and the river?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b22118b2-76fd-4ca8-801a-5af969784844"
msgid "\\\"Nok-Nok, what can you tell me of your brethren?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70fa2469-f758-4adc-8f21-4dc48adf31f1"
msgid "Allowed Kesten and the militia to take justice in their own hands."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76de8660-6c6d-48a1-b4e4-9c45236c2366"
msgid ""
"\\\"You have my permission, Keston. I won't deprive people of the opportunity to "
"find the cause of their troubles.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "227efacd-abdf-46e9-8978-bbe422750b64"
msgid "Forbid Kesten and the militia to take justice in their own hands."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0ea3edb1-ceed-4ca3-86c8-480c463da8b8"
msgid ""
"\\\"No, Kesten, we have to deal with this carefully and rationally. Go to your "
"people and await my arrival.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e6429ac3-127b-4f9d-845e-6a0e4b3935ed"
msgid "\\\"I need some time to think over your offer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb5804d2-0e26-4922-86bf-488d2bee69fa"
msgid ""
"\\\"Can you tell me where these monsters come from, Tristian? The ones that appear "
"because of this... Bloom?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2f9f689-ec5e-45d1-8811-2861b9367ccc"
msgid "\\\"Let's summarize what we've found up to this point.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bb32c757-ea0e-4cf2-87a3-92766a60be05"
msgid "Threatened to execute all rebels."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf6e4568-3e32-4e4f-b83a-f8617d4ae407"
msgid ""
"\\\"The duty of the people is to obey the laws and orders of their ruler. I'll "
"hang any rebels I find and banish their families.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f455434-c8d5-413e-81fc-fc54be239b08"
msgid "\\\"That's all I need to know about the results of the research.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ba1ecb4-f9bf-4d70-acd7-c6b629e79aef"
msgid "\\\"Jhod, how did you come about these rumors of a curse?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "086fc883-bb43-4db3-ad25-fc74ca7c13b5"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod folds his hands on his chest.{/n} \\\"Well, now that we're all here, let's "
"sum up what we know. We've each spent a lot of time and effort to learn what we "
"can about where the monsters come from and what's causing this strange disease. I "
"hope this conversation can help shed some light on the situation.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea9dd983-3e85-44c9-90db-be487b7e230f"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten shakes his head slowly.{/n} \\\"We need to hurry. If we don't find the "
"source of this blight and eliminate it, we may end up with a rebellion on our "
"hands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11a696a6-5f6e-4029-8bdd-9aa5f413b7a4"
msgid ""
"{n}Hearing the name {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} draws Nok-Nok's attention.{/n} \\"
"\"Mother is not to blame here! Told you, but who listens to me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e94a25b1-3e0c-4195-9b8c-ecd0716da2cd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Right. Judging from the location in the patients' bodies, these seeds were "
"ingested. It seems likely that they're initially extremely small, almost "
"invisible, and people simply swallow them with their food. Once the seed is in the "
"stomach, it begins to grow and cause the symptoms we've seen in our patients.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e94f66fe-31f1-4e6d-8617-b182023edf47"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian, who'd been examining the map on the table from the shadows, gives a "
"small cough.{/n} \\\"If I may... I've noticed an interesting detail. Well, two "
"details, to be precise.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "888819f5-2dcf-436c-8734-da7eef08394a"
msgid ""
"\\\"First, the seeds afflict mostly the villagers. There have been no recorded "
"cases of disease within the city limits, except for those who came here looking "
"for the cure.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "309ef4da-0269-49ff-a6d0-f2fac0b6ae31"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten nods.{/n} \\\"It doesn't mean they're innocent of other crimes, but the "
"monster invasion at least is not their work.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c63fab7-1c6e-4499-a519-f7bf168e2ff6"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok raises his head.{/n} \\\"Know what I think? I think goblin-king is "
"rotten lice-scratchter! Shaman plays him like reedpipe, babbles about {g|Lamashtu}"
"Lamashtu{/g}, then plots behind his back!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31f9d5ee-8862-47dc-b864-568a31d3d309"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod nods.{/n} \\\"That's right. Thus, we can assume a common factor in how "
"people are exposed to these seeds: many villages get their food from the same "
"territory.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51aed43d-528f-4749-ad06-44889d273164"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmm... We used to think the monsters were just coming to the river to drink.\\"
"\" {n}Kesten rubs his forehead.{/n} \\\"But if what the cleric says is right...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3e6400cd-1d64-411a-85f5-1022441e65b6"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten grunts.{/n} \\\"I'd say they're just excited by anything new that "
"happens. I wouldn't be surprised if they're linked to this story somehow. But I "
"doubt the seeds were created by goblin shamans. Besides, a plan like this seems a "
"little... beyond the local goblin chief's intelligence.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "95256a4f-8aa4-43bd-b608-69c1e3b69b40"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod looks at you closely.{/n} \\\"Are you suggesting we wait for them all to "
"succumb to this Bloom, {mf|Baron|Baroness}? Let's pray we can deal with the "
"situation before that happens!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d017abf3-b633-45cd-9c77-d7c7d1677909"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten straighten up and flexes his shoulders.{/n} \\\"If you allow me, {mf|"
"Baron|Baroness}, I'd like to take the lead on this. I'll take the best members of "
"the militia with me and sweep the woods along the river. We'll look under each and "
"every rock, if needed.\\\" {n}Kesten muffles a cough.{/n} \\\"After everything "
"they've been through, these people deserve a chance to discover the source of "
"their misfortunes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "266aaeac-fc9e-4cd7-8849-3c06ecff09e9"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten frowns.{/n} \\\"Your Grace... it's hard to expect loyalty and obedience "
"from people in times like this. They're looking for somethin — or someone — to "
"blame. I... I didn't want to be the one to say it, but...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0c8181f-ce02-4e9d-952a-8c2b6851ab91"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod cuts Kesten off with a gesture.{/n} \\\"People think you're cursed, Your "
"Grace. And it would be in your own best interests to quickly discover the cause of "
"the disaster that keeps claiming the lives of your subjects.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44b76b18-297c-4f6b-8d0d-b6c5d4d6a56d"
msgid ""
"{n}The guard hesitates, furrowing his brow.{/n} \\\"Your Grace... I understand "
"these people very well. They're tired of just waiting and hoping. But for now, I "
"can guide their eagerness for action in a positive direction. I'm glad to help "
"them avoid hasty decisions that could cause more trouble.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "023e585e-10d4-4fcc-8562-40902ed1365d"
msgid ""
"\\\"At the same time, I'm convinced that a crowd of terrified villagers who've "
"armed themselves can't truly be our salvation. This barony has a chance only so "
"long as it has authorities and laws. My top priority is helping you remain that "
"authority and that law.\\\" {n}Kesten takes a deep breath after the unusually long "
"speech.{/n} \\\"I just... wanted to assure you that I'm on your side.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1968662b-ebc5-40df-846e-942f38ac7798"
msgid ""
"{n}The cleric smiles, satisfied.{/n} \\\"After finding the source of the disease, "
"we've been working to remove the seeds from people day and night. We've saved so "
"many...\\\" {n}Jhod's face falls.{/n} \\\"But, for each patient we cure, we "
"receive two newly infected...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d755e2f3-d53c-461a-9dc6-2d70c87acbce"
msgid ""
"{n}The cleric glances pensively at the map.{/n} \\\"You see, {mf|Baron|Baroness}, "
"these seeds are not the only sign of something... abnormal at work. Remember the "
"ruins, where we first met? The glade near those ruins, full of huge flowers?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "149e5492-0946-4d2e-9a1e-fcbfe118d454"
msgid ""
"\\\"Glades such as that tend to appear all over the Stolen Lands. Seems strange, "
"does it not? Especially if we take into account that the magic seeds and the "
"portals they create look like flowers themselves. Jhod even called this disaster "
"'the Bloom.' I'd like to research this natural phenomenon, and perhaps...\\\" {n}"
"Tristian stops talking as loud, hasty steps are heard from the main entrance.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c928a5fc-a5cb-41ab-a336-308ce8be060c"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten runs into the room.{/n} \\\"Your Grace! We have trouble! The peasants "
"are rioting!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "315befa6-7d9b-4e75-95dd-d3c98f39d228"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok grimaces.{/n} \\\"Dangle-eared fool-holes! They be trusting any word "
"shaman says. They not think with their ownheads! See only big beasts, not see big "
"truth!\\\" {n}The goblin scratches behind his ear with a dagger.{/n} \\\"Great {g|"
"Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} may be happy of all big-beasties around, but it not be her "
"doing...\\\" {n}After mentioning the goddess, Nok-Nok stops talking, rounds his "
"shoulders, and looks around nervously.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6000822-2433-4c06-9d3f-3c8bc271b6ef"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ugh! That's the only solution these nitwits could come up with...? Don't "
"worry, {mf|Baron|Baroness}. As long as they're not setting fire to the streets, we "
"still have a chance of coming to a peaceful resolution. If you allow me, I'll go "
"and speak with them, do my best to calm the crowd down.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "774d6a6c-5d61-4195-9bcb-651f2cdb628d"
msgid ""
"\\\"And if peace doesn't prevail... your guards and I will stand with you. Let's "
"go. I can hear their shouting even from here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59048746-6b4e-4dfa-b5fb-1ed52eb9e3b4"
msgid ""
"{n}The throne room is full of people. Your allies stand around the throne, waiting "
"in silence as you approach. The atmosphere is tense. Today, you'll be discussing "
"the strange and deadly blight that's recently struck your barony.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c8ed466d-e4e4-4382-a0bf-a5278d991be7"
msgid ""
"{n}The gloomy silence is only penetrated by loud chewing — Nok-Nok has grabbed a "
"whole fried chicken from the table and is busily devouring it, ignoring everyone "
"else completely.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c5ee4802-34be-4370-887f-b05e4eae40ed"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian slowly shakes his head.{/n} \\\"I don't think food is the problem. "
"Take a look.\\\" {n}He points at the map.{/n} \\\"We have the most cases of the "
"disease here, here, and over here. Monsters mostly attack here and here...\\\" {n}"
"The cleric's finger travels down the map, tapping points along a fluid line.{/n} \\"
"\"You see? The situation is most dire along the banks of the {g|Gudrin River}"
"Gudrin River{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7d2e31b-141f-4b2e-8f7a-04f999edeaea"
msgid ""
"{n}Everyone examines the map closely.{/n} \\\"{g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} have mercy..."
"\\\" {n}Jhod exhales slowly.{/n} \\\"Exactly! Along the river! That must be where "
"the seeds come from. From their drinking water!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27c597d5-3e40-4c4a-9562-6b46dd70eeac"
msgid ""
"\\\"As soon as the seed gains enough strength, it sprouts and turns into a magic "
"portal. Just like a bud turning into a flower, {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} forgive me.\\"
"\" {n}Jhod stares into the distance a moment.{/n} \\\"Something must have "
"possessed me to say that — it really does look like blooming. Each seed tears the "
"body of it's victim, just as a flower tears its bud.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e88acd1c-06de-455d-a8bc-05859443c4ff"
msgid ""
"{n}Tristian raises his eyes from the papers on the table.{/n} \\\"Undoubtedly from "
"some world alien to our own. All the monsters appearing from the Bloom are "
"exceptionally large and strong — it would be rare to encounter such specimens in "
"the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}, or even on most of {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g}. "
"But it's impossible to say what it is that lies on the other side of the portals "
"that's intent on killing your people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ff7a53d-1d40-4794-9a18-2acb2041c873"
msgid ""
"\\\"I thank you, {mf|my baron|my baroness}. I hope you'll join us soon.\\\" {n}"
"Kesten gives a short bow, turns around, and leaves.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6aa17a63-364e-41f0-8586-bd9fbf87fab0"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten casts his eyes down.{/n} \\\"You... you're right, of course, Your Grace. "
"I'll order my men to get ready immediately. We'll await your arrival and then make "
"our move.\\\" {n}Kesten gives a short bow, turns around, and leaves.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "225f2f5b-7a28-4126-b377-5888cec131bc"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten bites his lip and shifts his shoulders.{/n} \\\"Time is precisely what "
"we lack... Please, don't delay too long. I'll go to my men immediately. I hope "
"you'll choose to join us soon.\\\" {n}Kesten gives a short bow, turns around, and "
"leaves.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "897e3b07-b1c4-4ad4-8b22-0700ded1c9e5"
msgid ""
"{n}Nok-Nok jumps at your words.{/n} \\\"Take me! Me!\\\" {n}The goblin bares his "
"sharp, crooked teeth.{/n} \\\"I want to settle the score with the king!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84b76472-c1cb-4261-ab85-f26d2070b3d9"
msgid "{n}Jhod, Kesten, and Tristian look at you closely.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8e86e61-a1b0-443f-b145-9173a9cbbdaa"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten and Jhod exchange glances. Tristian continues to dig through his papers."
"{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "03473928-8611-4763-9baf-a071f5f7cfae"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's a strong statement. But while you ride your high horse in here, your "
"people are dying out there, and new monsters continue to arrive. Duty of the "
"people or no, you must deal with this threat — that is the duty of a ruler.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f379c20a-d998-4d7e-9fda-8d1074cbff0a"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod bows his head.{/n} \\\"Each day, I see dozens of infected, Your Grace. "
"Many people have lost their loved ones or fear they soon will. They all want to "
"know what's going on, who deserves the blame, whose sins brought this blight upon "
"them. Trust me, every day, the number of people willing to pin the blame on you "
"grows. They say you and your barony are cursed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ec8b98a-53df-4b38-9f0e-20dd91871f05"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course, I don't believe a word of it. This isn't a curse, but some... "
"disease, which has somehow manifested itself in your barony.\\\" {n}Jhod raises "
"his eyes to meet yours.{/n} \\\"Trust me. I won't leave you until I find the "
"source of this disease — regardless of what these poor people may say in their "
"delirium.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf33b4d2-2a04-4d18-82fc-6b655298b880"
msgid "Jhod Kavken's Clinic"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06fffa66-8fe6-48d2-9e61-f91b21b42a6b"
msgid "Kesten Garess's Guard Headquarters"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1f439f1-f6be-4472-8082-de7c80315220"
msgid "An old prison — the one the Stag Lord was using for his wine cellar."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83ffcc1e-61e3-4323-a222-dff57f82e827"
msgid "\\\"What has you so excited, Jhod?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c92e68a0-00f0-4635-9be6-cab82d60ad10"
msgid "\\\"I don't have time right now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ae40006-fa72-46db-9662-741d399b33ef"
msgid "\\\"First tell me how the barony's recovery is going.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44a5ac7f-097a-4c85-8596-6a7a39d9950f"
msgid "\\\"The capital could use a clinic.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96a47d94-59c1-4ab0-be30-31bb1d7bae65"
msgid "\\\"The capital could use a guards headquarters.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b3b2b9cb-ea0b-4924-881c-d3e4e853634f"
msgid "Decided to leave the old prison as it is."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "972600cc-5564-41ec-9dd2-408c1eec5523"
msgid ""
"\\\"We can't afford extra expenditures right now. Forget about the old prison — "
"I'm sure there are other matters in need of your attention.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dae701f3-1926-4412-b7a0-02c701992035"
msgid "Decided to leave the prison as it is."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e906cce0-6e7e-4e25-8f9b-570f7b5687a2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Leave the prison as it is. I'll need a place to chain you both when my "
"patience runs out.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cbb60c5-ac4b-4267-be63-a90387846cad"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, do you have a moment? {d|c22 both saved}Kesten and I{/d} have a "
"matter to discuss with you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "375adf72-e5de-41e7-b1a3-918ccf52b792"
msgid ""
"\\\"A wise decision, Your Grace. I'll begin the search for proper healers "
"immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "219199fc-c5de-4a63-bb60-5d1a08bb76f2"
msgid "\\\"Agreed. I'll give the necessary orders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7f983f6-15dd-482b-8928-67e7828fdb47"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've argued in circles on the matter, Your Grace, but it is ultimately your "
"decision anyway. We'll abide by your orders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "101e9880-048e-4a34-8780-ea32a006fbd0"
msgid ""
"\\\"The losses were staggering. Many have died, and others have lost their homes. "
"However, life is slowly returning to normal. We've almost finished clearing debris "
"from the city, and we have guards patrolling the main routes again to help "
"refugees return home. There's still much to do, of course, but the situation is "
"improving.\\\" {n}Jhod takes a deep breath and folds his hands on his chest.{/n} \\"
"\"Now, if I may, I'd like to discuss the issue Kesten and I came to you with.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1194521d-6ef6-4841-a514-76b25bcb1d5d"
msgid ""
"\\\"In my opinion, Your Grace, our top priority should be securing the safety of "
"the people returning to the city. I believe we should convert the old prison into "
"guards headquarters.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9dccfa77-5414-4763-81ef-b0f98c10adbf"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm afraid we won't be able to resolve the situation without your help. We "
"won't take much of your time, Your Grace, we just need your input on a matter "
"we've been arguing about.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74818ad7-371b-4185-9ec6-d52a802186a5"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's about the old prison. The one we were using as a field hospital. Now that "
"the Season of Bloom has passed, the field hospital is unnecessary. However, the "
"capital would certainly benefit from having a clinic. Right now, those harmed in "
"the attack have nowhere to go to receive medical aid.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8292a1ea-fe2b-4ad8-9083-3944823cca5b"
msgid "\\\"But, Your Grace, shouldn't we put the building to good use?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ecbdc511-e99d-4ff9-8c14-275adec969d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"The baron{mf||ess} is right, come to think of it. After all the horrors that "
"took place within those walls, the building would be ill-suited to be a center for "
"healing. It would only dredge up bad memories.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2bf8b74-a8fa-4173-b995-46d748827744"
msgid ""
"\\\"I suppose that gives us our answer, then. We won't bother you with the issue "
"any further, Your Grace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad4c6469-296d-4d83-a3ad-1c3d2bc3838d"
msgid "Founded a clinic in place of the old prison."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "721af72f-6d38-4ebc-b375-f39da25638d7"
msgid ""
"\\\"We could turn the old prison into a clinic and name it after him. Would that "
"suffice?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50ca8e39-1722-4f9e-8617-0581dcbc26aa"
msgid "Preferred to save resources for the barony's sake instead of honoring Jhod."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4fd46732-4309-44dc-8ed0-a979ff4f8b87"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now isn't the best time to be looking at spending treasury funds on something "
"like a memorial.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68108830-d55d-49fe-a061-4ea278395110"
msgid "Derided Jhod's death and refused to honor the fallen."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7dbfa36a-fa14-4f9d-a648-7f4c7b19a0fe"
msgid ""
"\\\"Jhod, that useless old fool? Why would I pay for a memorial to someone I've "
"already forgotten?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b64cd5db-f302-4c07-87cd-ddcc6be4984a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Reporting in, Your Grace!\\\" {n}Kesten stands straight and salutes you.{/n} \\"
"\"The capital's rebuilding efforts are well under way. We've set part of the "
"militia to patrolling routes in and out of the city in search of any remaining "
"monsters, while others are currently assigned to helping clear debris from the "
"city. The good news is that the people are starting to recover from their shock "
"and start to get back to their normal lives. The bad news... well...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12516926-fc46-4067-b0ef-20e371c2c4b1"
msgid ""
"\\\"We suffered heavy losses — both among the militia and the civilians. It will "
"take a long time for the barony to regain its former strength.\\\" {n}Kesten "
"hesitates a moment.{/n} \\\"I... do have one other issue that's been on my mind, "
"Your Grace...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa2fb910-12b0-4a38-953b-b147dd579a95"
msgid ""
"\\\"Jhod Kavken, your advisor and a cleric of {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g}, was among "
"those who perished. He was... {d|c22 Kesten saved}torn apart{/d} by monsters. He "
"died helping the diseased and wounded to his last breath. We weren't close, but I "
"believe honoring his memory would be the right thing to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b386a42c-9756-4555-90e8-151037e3cc9c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'd like for you to find some way to help the barony that can do so in "
"Kavken's name. The man spent his entire life serving {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} and "
"his congregation — and the people of this city. It would be nice to have his name "
"associated with the good he spent his life performing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d233a57-bc2a-4adf-9d80-4ecd48fd05d8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes, that's a great idea, Your Grace. I... I think Jhod would appreciate that."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "615697fc-5ef4-4aae-ba6e-7dcefddb1bae"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten bites his lip.{/n} \\\"You're... right, of course, Your Grace. There are "
"certainly more efficient ways to use those funds. Forgive my poor judgment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6651e98f-f17e-4f47-b5d3-8f0e0b1e97f5"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten's face turns red.{/n} \\\"I never thought I'd say something like this, "
"but you're...\\\" {n}Kesten clenches his teeth, inhales deeply, then exhales "
"loudly.{/n} \\\"I must go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14d2e685-5085-4653-9dd3-9cc61ad776c4"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you have no objections, I'll take care of the arrangements personally — I "
"believe you already have enough to worry about right now. I won't take any more of "
"your time.\\\" {n}Kesten bows deeply.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e8b56cb-c475-4cf1-b6d4-fa53bb5e938a"
msgid ""
"\\\"I won't take any more of your time then. I have to get back to my duties.\\"
"\" {n}Kesten steps back and bows.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "be51db1c-1635-4100-ba0a-b30fc3a84e52"
msgid "Founded a guard academy in place of the old prison."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0164a721-d9bc-4eac-a9e9-635f17052846"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why don't we convert the old prison into a guard headquarters. We could name "
"it after Kesten.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5cf2ef91-448b-4ab7-ad84-682515e59f92"
msgid "Preferred to save resources for the barony's sake instead of honoring Kesten."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e2a9d0f-e9c7-4ff3-a997-e6c0e1914403"
msgid ""
"\\\"We don't have the resources right now, Jhod. It's going to take all we have to "
"finish rebuilding the capital.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44316f35-6d0c-492d-9f36-e6fb33b847d8"
msgid "Derided Kesten's death and refused to honor the fallen."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "883c59f2-f991-4041-9948-c6e061468f50"
msgid ""
"\\\"Kesten's death was his own fault. I won't spend our limited resources "
"glorifying such a failure.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e5a38f2d-7a43-445e-85a1-c8f438f14e21"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod's sorrow is plain on his face.{/n} \\\"Your Grace, if I may? I just need a "
"moment of your time.\\\" {n}He takes a deep breath.{/n} \\\"I feel it only proper "
"to honor the fallen.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a21057a9-213f-4d13-8ff7-487e626f4984"
msgid ""
"\\\"Things have gone horribly wrong in our barony of late. The victims are counted "
"in hundreds — it will take a long time for the barony to return to its former "
"state. We can make it, of course. But we must remember that it won't be due to our "
"efforts alone — there are those who fought and died, sacrificed themselves, to "
"make this possible. One in particular, especially — {d|c22 Jhod saved}Kesten{/d} "
"Garess.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e2bb32d-ef29-448a-a1d6-bf89367fd9cd"
msgid ""
"\\\"In our darkest hour, he stood at the head of the militia and spared the barony "
"from popular unrest. If not for him, the crowd at the square would have been much "
"bigger... and much angrier. Kesten fell defending this city, and I believe it's "
"our duty to honor his memory.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a033c6ea-f3ca-40e6-bf7c-def59edce55e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now, with the capital finally returning to a semblance of normalcy, I think we "
"should consider commemorating Kesten. I think the people would appreciate knowing "
"that we don't forget those who fight alongside us.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a3e84b5-c796-44df-8e5a-a6b2011dbc74"
msgid ""
"\\\"A brilliant idea, Your Grace. Kesten would have been proud to know his example "
"will inspire new generations of the barony's defenders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d42ec0d-796a-4e93-aef5-02d113d4aca0"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod bows.{/n} \\\"Thank you. I will personally attend to all matters related "
"to this decision you've made.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d557cd14-2b5d-4b1d-9410-bf80d51076c3"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod is silent for a moment, then sighs.{/n} \\\"There's truth to what you say, "
"Your Grace. We must think of the barony, not just our lost associates.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b791b4b7-a348-4c21-966d-b92793b23b29"
msgid ""
"\\\"You ungrateful... That 'failure' didn't hesitate to give is life defending you "
"and this barony of yours!\\\" {n}Jhod shakes his head, his face red.{/n} \\\"I... "
"have to go. I'm sorry to take your time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2abaa8a3-1ff9-42e6-bdc2-fb6912f834e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll return to my regular duties, then. Thank you for your time.\\\" {n}Jhod "
"bows and turn to leave.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ed5da95-0ddb-46c6-831e-17274f08642d"
msgid ""
"\\\"A potential threat or slander cannot be taken lightly. I will deal with this.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa2d7288-ba73-4af1-9773-dd9df84a5c32"
msgid "\\\"If I happen to be in those parts, I will find out what is going on.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77954f7f-6e81-47b1-8c17-052331ddb9a5"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is not a baron's concern. Tell me if you face a real rebellion, and not "
"just foolish rumors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a410542-6eea-42cb-a632-cb5b23521260"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, a while ago we received a message from the village of {g|Lake "
"Silverstep}Silverstep{/g}. More a denunciation, to be precise. A certain Brevis "
"informs us that the local settlers started believing in a creature called a Silver "
"Dragon.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76c4d0ab-ef45-435b-ab26-c9189d36023a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, baron{mf||ess}! I will get right to the point. We've received a "
"complaint from Brevis from the {g|Lake Silverstep}Silverstep{/g} settlement. He "
"claims that a troublemaker, a hunter named Ivar, is discrediting you among the "
"local population.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e698ab78-1ddb-47d9-bc43-2de6fe18996f"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is my pleasure to bring a most joyous piece of news to your attention! It "
"seems we now have a rebel in our barony. That's right — one rebel! Or at least we "
"have one informer, trying to get his annoying neighbor hung from the gallows.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b142c814-d4f5-4791-abf6-d0d19a0f9905"
msgid ""
"\\\"A certain Brevis from a settlement on {g|Lake Silverstep}Silverstep Lake{/g} "
"informs us in a letter that a local huntsman is openly defying the authority of "
"the baron{mf||ess}. He's encouraging the settlers to worship some Silver Dragon — "
"whose representative the hunter, naturally, claims himself to be. Being your most "
"loyal subject, this Brevis could not but inform you of this flagrant act of baron-"
"bashing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99845a56-71f5-4aae-955e-4529cb87b729"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our own messengers who have been to {g|Lake Silverstep}Silverstep{/g} recently "
"made inquiries after this hunter, but learned nothing. He rarely comes to the "
"village, and the villagers don't know anything. As for me, this nonsense is not "
"worth your attention — but it's up to you to decide, of course.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d172e513-14f5-42e1-a9f4-c41581c99882"
msgid ""
"\\\"This Ivar is persuading the villagers that the true sovereign of the lands is "
"the mighty Silver Dragon. This Dragon is stands as patron to the people, and of "
"course possesses far greater strength and power than a mere mortal ruler.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "728b700b-9781-4e27-a0e3-b001c0672921"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Dragon allegedly claims dominion over all the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen "
"Lands{/g}, thus compromising your authority. The author of the letter reports that "
"this belief is being spread by a local huntsman named Ivar.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc845a78-69c2-4506-a47a-43906fb5727b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I took the liberty of sending a few people to verify this information, but "
"they found nothing to report. The settlers wouldn't discuss it, and the huntsman "
"wasn't in the village at the time. Your Grace, the decision is yours.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ccd2c748-4f6f-49ca-bd6c-ef910f2824ce"
msgid ""
"\\\"I deeply regret that our people were unable to verify this information. But I "
"would not recommend leaving it unattended. In {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} know very well "
"how quickly rebel seeds may sprout.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d82b9b8c-777d-465b-bde4-f46460f4c058"
msgid ""
"\\\"Finally good news, Your Grace! {d|Varn}Maegar Varn{/d}, the ruler of {g|"
"Varnhold}Varnhold{/g}, has sent aid! Together with goods came a messenger with {g|"
"VarnHelp}a letter for you{/g}. Here, please, take it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a763ff66-5d57-4721-a06c-d36d17ef69df"
msgid ""
"\\\"Wagon trains from {g|Varnhold}Varnhold{/g} have arrived in the capital. {d|"
"Varn}Maegar Varn{/d} sends you his regards and asks you to accept the humble aid "
"that he hopes will last you through these tough times. I think there are more "
"details in {g|VarnHelp}his letter{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b365a819-7bc5-4d57-9d6d-ba802fd83174"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmm... looks like {d|Varn}Maegar Varn{/d} wants something from you, {mf|Baron|"
"Baroness}. Otherwise, why would he send you several wagon trains laden with "
"bundles and sheafs? Here's {g|VarnHelp}the letter{/g} — I think it'll tell you the "
"reason for Varn's fit of generosity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3d727ff4-0e25-476f-80cf-650852eff50f"
msgid "Message from Maegar Varn"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a79d504-f051-4c32-9b93-58e87ea04939"
msgid ""
"\\\"Most Honorable {mf|Baron|Baroness} {name}!\\nThis is your good neighbor Maegar "
"Varn, the ruler of Varnhold, writing. The terrible news that your lands are being "
"swarmed by loathsome monsters has just reached me. Without wishing to cast any "
"doubt on your valor and combat prowess, I nevertheless dare suggest my help in "
"these dark times.\\nUnfortunately, I cannot lend you my sword: all my warriors are "
"busy protecting our roads — there have just been too many bandits in Dunsward. But "
"as a sign of my utmost respect, I send some valuable resources along with this "
"letter. Let them serve you and your people well in these harsh days.\\nI am sure "
"that you would do the same in my place and would never leave Varnhold without "
"help. Therefore, do not perceive this as an attempt to indebt you to myself. My "
"help is free — I offer it of my own volition. Baronies like ours need to stick "
"together, in a steadfast alliance. If one falls, the other will follow. Together, "
"we can withstand any menace — even the likes that the Stolen Lands are famed for."
"\\nP.S.: I dare not insist, knowing of your hardship, but I do remind you that I "
"would be delighted to welcome you in Varnhold at any time.\\nRespectfully yours,"
"\\nBaron Maegar Varn\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e90b4ce-6216-4765-8887-e5fb0e5063d0"
msgid "\\\"Why would the Swordlords care about Varnhold?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5bc42616-17a9-4d5f-bd40-dbfe32cb1c8d"
msgid "\\\"What do we know of Varnhold?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49bf0ee1-b141-481f-8315-f0dd81ca3b72"
msgid ""
"Demanded an explanation from Jamandi Aldori about her order to visit Varnhold."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c583cd8-3ed0-4a4d-bd52-1418336d463c"
msgid ""
"\\\"And why should I drop everything and rush to help the Swordlords? I suppose "
"that question would be better addressed to Lady Aldori. Prepare the letter and "
"send it immediately — I won't let some Restovic upstarts tell me what to do, as if "
"I were some servant.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1e36225-c8ea-4c04-9e44-8aba96abe0b9"
msgid ""
"\\\"Varnhold isn't far off. We should find out what happened there before the same "
"fate befalls us too.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac33eb90-36eb-4ffe-93b5-b160a0a1383d"
msgid "\\\"What do you think has happened to Varnhold?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65e191f8-2457-4d15-b9a7-51cf2638a57d"
msgid "\\\"Maybe Varn simply decided to stop dealing with Restov?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba81152e-4e23-4162-bb75-c72e94849776"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, we have urgent news from Jamandi Aldori! The Swordlord is asking "
"for aid with an unusual problem. Here is {g|JamandiVarnholdTrouble}her letter{/g} "
"— please read it when you have a moment.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa358e07-0270-4a56-9c19-79ab6ef93c6c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Greetings, Your Grace. I have {g|JamandiVarnholdTrouble}an urgent message{/g} "
"from Jamandi Aldori. It seems the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} have — again — "
"proved their inability to rule their subjects. See for yourself — here's the "
"message from Jamandi.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb650d79-dfaf-4e67-9a01-52913623ec2b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I bring tidings in good measure — and bad. As for the good, it seems the {g|"
"Restov}Restov{/g} Swordlord Jamandi Aldori honors us with her attention. She "
"jotted you {g|JamandiVarnholdTrouble}a nice little letter{/g}. The bad tidings? "
"She wants us to prove ourselves worthy of such recognition.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cbf082d5-5904-4f05-a7c2-da36b9de314d"
msgid ""
"\\\"She writes that a while ago she stopped receiving reports from {g|Varnhold}"
"Varnhold{/g} — a neighboring barony, established by the Swordlords' protege, {d|"
"Varn}Maegar Varn{/d}. But it is not only letters that stopped coming — trade "
"caravans, couriers, all traffic from Varnhold has ceased. It is as if the barony "
"has disappeared.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "467267f9-a9cc-48fa-b99b-bd525d3f9a63"
msgid ""
"\\\"Jamandi Aldori expects your help with this matter, for she knows of your good "
"relations with Maegar. She asks you to go to {g|Varnhold}Varnhold{/g} and find out "
"why they have fallen silent.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29a3068a-0ef9-4987-930c-c27f0f1db46f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Jamandi Aldori seeks allies with anyone who has proven to be trustworthy — "
"even if only a little. Considering that {g|Varnhold}Varnhold{/g} is the closest "
"thing to an outpost on the east edge of the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}, "
"it's also useful to her in keeping an eye on {g|Dunsward}Dunsward{/g} and the "
"surrounding area.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fb0140e-fe28-4af1-95ac-eb24740ae454"
msgid ""
"\\\"I appreciate your determination in solving diplomatic issues — though, in my "
"opinion, you may wish to massage your wording somewhat. I'll send the letter to {g|"
"Restov}Restov{/g} immediately.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70b2889d-85a3-4be2-bcbc-57615119cbd7"
msgid ""
"\\\"This barony is much alike your own. It was also established by a mercenary, {d|"
"Varn}Maegar Varn{/d}. He got his title at the same event you did.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b682fa72-3ce2-4238-87ea-f5a3d36da83f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then it's time to gather a party and head to {g|Varnhold}Varnhold{/g}, Your "
"Grace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ebc3a856-8dee-48da-98cb-f40b757e8df0"
msgid ""
"\\\"{d|Varn}Maegar Varn{/d} is third or fourth son in the family, so he couldn't "
"claim his father's inheritance. Looks like he hoped to establish a settlement of "
"his own and gain wealth and prosperity that way.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd930a13-1afb-400a-a998-7bf86456601f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hmmm... a riot? A rebellion? But if that were the case, there would be "
"refugees. Whatever happened there, it must have been sudden indeed — perhaps a "
"bandit attack, barbarians, a plague… whatever it was, no one outside {g|Varnhold}"
"Varnhold{/g} seems to know what happened.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ac54445-2088-4991-be8f-97f70f6f1c5b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Judging by Aldori's letter, the silence doesn't seem voluntary. Otherwise at "
"least one person would have reached a neighbor and speak to what happened there.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a767dd3d-2943-4c82-831b-4950d52b1a78"
msgid ""
"\\\"You really know how to talk to those insolent {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g}! "
"I'll just go ahead and add some lines of my own to your letter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca272084-50b1-4c54-8391-41a6d0feb38a"
msgid ""
"\\\"How dare you, {mf|baron|baroness}?! You owe much to Lady Jamandi, yet you "
"repay her with insults? Fine, I'll compose the letter, though I'll use milder "
"expressions — as for you, you should go and solve the mystery of {g|Varnhold}"
"Varnhold{/g}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50f2f9c7-d0c1-43b5-a7b0-4cee012c9523"
msgid ""
"\\\"Lady Aldori asks you to head to {g|Varnhold}Varhnold{/g} at once — it's a "
"barony led by {d|Varn}Meagar Varn{/d}, a brave soul who carved out the settlement "
"from the wilderness. Until recently he eagerly... and frequently... relayed to the "
"{g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} his many successes, but then the letters suddenly "
"ceased. As you may expect, this is a matter of some concern!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1af8cd6-e9f1-41eb-8b71-55d020a49d26"
msgid ""
"\\\"Remember that annoying {d|Varn}Maegar Varn{/d}, who couldn't stop pestering "
"you? Seems like he grew tired of Aldori's leash, so he stopped answering the {g|"
"Swordlords}Swordlords{/g}' letters. But Varn alone wouldn't raise so much concern "
"— according to the letter, the settlement itself seems to have vanished!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0782f22f-1ba9-4d36-a41b-ac0c9b6ced44"
msgid "Letter from Jamandi Aldori"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4eed37ab-073f-41ac-a5d5-548e06736d4a"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name},\\nI have a problem, and no one else to turn to but you. I need someone "
"to travel to a town south of Restov, Varnhold. The town was founded by Maegar Varn "
"— you met him at the reception to celebrate your new title.\\nRecently, I've "
"stopped getting reports from him. I didn't pay much attention to it, but in the "
"past week, not a single traveler, merchant, or messenger from Varnhold has showed "
"up in Restov. No one knows what has happened to the town.\\nIf I were you, I would "
"make sure I was ready for this journey: the plains of Dunsward are dangerous. "
"Also, we have yet to find out what was it that cut off communication with "
"Varnhold: an attack, arcane magic, or some epidemic or plague. I would have gladly "
"investigated the matter, but the current state of affairs dictates I refrain from "
"dealing with this personally. I am counting on you and your help: head out for "
"Dunsward and find out what — or who — stands behind the vanishing of Varnhold."
"\\nYour friend and ally,\\nSwordlord Jamandi Aldori\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db81358e-3f2e-4aa5-af38-efc45f3b838e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, Lady Jamandi sent {g|JamandiExcuses}an answer{/g} to your hasty "
"message. Luckily, the Swordlord took your quick temper into account, and decided "
"to resolve the situation peacefully. Furthermore, a caravan has come from {g|"
"Restov}Restov{/g}, carrying resources for the barony! I hope now you will be able "
"to appreciate the generosity of the Aldori!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "420037a7-6903-4023-b963-93ad2c132e98"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, {g|JamandiExcuses}a letter{/g} from Jamandi Aldori arrived. It "
"seems the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} have their tails between their legs: they "
"sent a whole caravan of valuable goods along with the letter. Jamandi Aldori must "
"be in a perilous situation, if she's inducing Your Grace with gifts. Here, take "
"the letter.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "454afd1c-0d8c-4c56-a98a-3b0dadd0d692"
msgid ""
"\\\"You won't believe it, Your Grace! Today a caravan entered the city, filled "
"with generous gifts from {g|Restov}Restov{/g}! I wonder who could have sent it. "
"Maybe a certain lady was impressed by our determination? Bravo, Your Grace — I "
"salute your {d|c31 Jamandi Chaotic}aggressive diplomacy{/d} skills! Here, see for "
"yourself — it's {g|JamandiExcuses}a letter{/g} from Jamandi Aldori!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d8a5fac-026e-4bf0-927b-4d89aae5d2a8"
msgid "Letter from Jamandi Aldori"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "394187fe-e2e0-453c-9b6e-9fc311ea208f"
msgid ""
"\\\"{name},\\nI knew the day would come when you began to doubt me. At least you "
"didn't proceed immediately to bite the hand that feeds you. It is a fair question, "
"what reasons led me to write to you when I could have traveled to Varnhold myself. "
"Well then, let me lay my cards on the table.\\nThere are reasons for this, grave "
"reasons indeed. The threat of Numeria looms over Rostland. More and more, "
"barbarians make their way into our lands and attack our caravans. Our scouts "
"report that barbarian tribes gather on our borders. I would have gladly turned "
"from this crisis and dealt with Varnhold myself, were it not for my sentimental "
"attachment to my country, my city and its people, who are about to be swallowed up "
"by the Numerian hydra that crawls towards us from the east. Of course, Restov does "
"have a ruler — but it would be ignoble to leave Lord Mayor Sellemius without my "
"support in such a difficult time.\\nThere was no one I could ask for help but you. "
"I ask of you, as an old comrade in arms: gather your men and discover what has "
"happened in Varnhold — at least so that whatever devoured its inhabitants doesn't "
"find its way to your own subjects.\\nP.S. I've sent some resources along with this "
"letter. Consider them a sign of my good will, and an expression of my gratitude "
"for your help.\\nYour friend and ally,\\nSwordlord Jamandi Aldori\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2746ff87-8c47-4708-9399-b11214418589"
msgid ""
"\\\"I thank you for honoring me with your visit. To what do I owe the pleasure?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33f52db2-2793-42f2-a81f-cc208109fdfa"
msgid "\\\"What happened? Be quick — I don't have much time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1992993-4818-44ea-9297-ea4b5f040826"
msgid "\\\"I have no time for this. Come visit me next time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "67372c34-fb01-4513-b266-9f2c2af764cf"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about your brother.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d0417ab-a0db-43db-a060-de505ae95e52"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about your family.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "623d9ba4-e7d6-495a-9e07-dea1ba39ab5b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I have bad news for you. Your brother is dead. I found this letter on his body."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "923626c3-364d-4ee6-9bbf-b17527c62fe4"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about your great-grandfather.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72f93049-3994-4d79-ac2c-e52a4e18a46e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Take a look at this letter. It's related to your family. I found it on a dead "
"body lying in an ancient cyclops's tomb.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a70c01e9-3e8a-4325-9b5d-658c90893d2a"
msgid "Executed the noble from Gralton."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6fbc1ed3-7b5f-49b3-9afc-703149b072ef"
msgid ""
"\\\"Seems to me that you're not a noble, but rather a spy. Guards, come here! "
"Execute him!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40ceed9e-3806-46c8-8a26-b4ecffd36610"
msgid "\\\"I'll see what I can do for you. Farewell.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e8c797d-4220-408f-9f90-35be4cb4e21a"
msgid "\\\"Farewell.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d9252515-fcab-4679-872c-ddd86b3c8143"
msgid ""
"{n}A young man wearing fancy clothes, with delicate features and perfect posture, "
"gives you a precisely measured light bow.{/n} \\\"Your Grace, allow me to "
"introduce myself. I'm Edrist Hanvaki. I beg you to give me a moment of your "
"precious time.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf588b05-9621-4181-890b-707b8c61d284"
msgid "\\\"Did you manage to find anything?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e249006-5dda-49bd-b7d7-42baa9c9c380"
msgid ""
"{n}A surprised expression appears on the young man's face, but he conceals it "
"behind a polite smile.{/n} \\\"Such flawless courtesy! I can see you are a true "
"noble, unlike some imposters from the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}... Let "
"me get straight to the point of my visit, for it is the matter of utmost "
"importance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21d573d6-537f-4dc7-959d-154f57aeff55"
msgid ""
"{n}The young man winces, but he forces a polite smile on his face.{/n} \\\"As you "
"wish.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "720a4ae3-d778-4a62-aa36-f2ed401ae97b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace! I beg you to hear me out! It's a matter of life and death!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2122fc28-a516-490a-be84-c5404aeed30f"
msgid ""
"\\\"A tragedy has brought me here — one that has been looming over my family for a "
"while, or perhaps one that has already come to pass. You see, Your Grace, two "
"months ago my elder brother, Tomin Hanvaki, went missing. After leaving Gralton, "
"where our family resides, he headed northwest. His destination, as we found out "
"later, was a village called {g|Varnhold}Varnhold{/g}, but he never arrived there. "
"Your capital is the last place he was seen alive.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17dc3d1f-4b3d-49c2-9bed-858baedb87eb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our family, no matter how venerable, has always carried a spirit of... "
"adventurousness, if you will, in our blood — a thirst for risk and exploits. Each "
"generation has had its own daredevil who left all he owned and went chasing after "
"some ghostly treasures, completely ignoring the tears of his loved ones... I'm "
"afraid this family curse has befallen on my brother now. If only I knew what "
"exactly he was looking for, or where exactly he was going! Sadly, all I've managed "
"to learn was the name of some village out in the middle of nowhere, {g|Varnhold}"
"Varnhold{/g} — along with the fact that my brother never arrived there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "293522d7-05e8-49e3-8dfa-642335b029e0"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Hanvakis are an ancient family with a long history, hailing back to the "
"days before Gralton's founding. Unfortunately, our wealth has been depleted by a "
"series of reckless ventures — like the one my brother is partaking in right now. "
"Family archives, some heirlooms, and our honor — these are all the treasures our "
"once influential house has come to possess.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0efb6559-b432-4fb5-8c2f-e4c35645f651"
msgid ""
"\\\"Mathian Hanvaki was known for his bravery and recklessness. When our family "
"was dealing with some financial difficulties, his best idea was to leave his "
"family estate, his wife, and his children in the care of his brother and go off "
"treasure hunting with a group of... daredevils of the same kind, let's say. No one "
"has seen him since. Unfortunately, stories like this aren't unusual in our family. "
"Stories about the exploits of my great-grandfather have become legends, the bards "
"praised his courage... Too bad no one wrote any songs about his widow and "
"everything the poor woman had to endure.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4a5a72a9-5aff-4177-b866-c27cd48a275d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Is that so... My poor father won't be able to cope with such a loss... What "
"have you done, Brother! And for what?\\\" {n}After reading the letter, Edrist "
"sighs bitterly and shakes his head in dismay.{/n} \\\"So, that's how it all "
"started. My brother found our great-grandfather's letter in the family archives, "
"and he decided to follow his example... And most unfortunately, he did.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30a8be46-3736-42e2-aa81-796082b1233d"
msgid ""
"{n}Edrist grabs the letter eagerly and starts reading it line by line, faded "
"though it is with time.{/n} \\\"A tomb of cyclopes! Looks like you shed light on "
"one of the secrets of our family. The bones you found were the remains of my great-"
"grandfather, Mathian Hanvaki.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30fa1272-d66c-46ef-880c-d9b594e19629"
msgid ""
"\\\"No! No, wait! I beg you…\\\"{n}Ignoring his shouts, the guards drag Edrist "
"away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70b46d4e-cb0e-41e7-a8a6-9078683cb954"
msgid ""
"\\\"We don't know where he is or whether he's still alive. Our poor father is "
"losing his head in grief. Please, help us to learn something about the fate of my "
"brother, and you'll gain an eternally loyal ally.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4348d8d0-b962-45e1-8aec-127289cdaeb9"
msgid ""
"\\\"This means I'm the heir of the title now... But this doesn't give me the "
"tiniest trifle of joy, believe me. Well. I'll have to stay in your capital for a "
"while. If during your travels you happen find yourself in this ill-fated tomb, do "
"me a favor and tell me what two Hanvaki daredevils died for.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b7075a3-8381-4b8f-ba05-3e6bf4a7e2b3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, the picture's perfectly clear now. Oh, if only this ill-conceived letter "
"had been lost to time, if my poor brother hadn't found it and been infected with "
"this deadly craving for adventure! Well, Your Grace... Today I'll leave for "
"Gralton — the city in which, from this day on, you will have a loyal friend and "
"ally.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64542711-f880-4cdb-9b4b-ccf7d0073f76"
msgid ""
"\\\"All I can do is pray my brother has been spared the same fate. I beg you to "
"find him!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a114229c-bd74-4ba6-aa48-2eb80fbdfb8b"
msgid "{n}Edrist gives you a bow and leaves the room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24699496-ab88-48af-9562-115a908ab280"
msgid "\\\"I look forward for any news you may find.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc9b8840-578b-46d0-9851-6849e2ece6e9"
msgid "\\\"What's going on at Candlemere?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ed15a4b-4bed-4776-a467-cb10784fb422"
msgid "\\\"What's happening in Brevoy?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f82f4c3-6cc2-4d98-a803-0d5b352d1242"
msgid "\\\"Which one should I do first?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a3ab7643-226b-4eea-8235-6f72e87de436"
msgid "\\\"I must return to my own concerns.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ded3176e-6f7c-4f08-b06e-64970256e66d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I cannot go with you right now, but you have every right to go to Rostland "
"without me, Amiri. Go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e0dc3e9-c291-45e3-93e9-1adc7f405ab8"
msgid "\\\"I cannot let you go! I need you here!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3018c662-204a-4fce-9968-4fa079fa9259"
msgid "\\\"I forbid it. You are to remain here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e6ff71a7-2205-4b88-a722-ec6c7453fd08"
msgid ""
"\\\"You are right. The threat is too serious to be ignored. We're heading there "
"right now!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0fa0ac8-1b32-4c94-bb85-24eedf88e5d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace! We need to head to {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} immediately! Swordlord "
"Jamandi requires your help in fighting off a sudden attack on {g|Rostland}"
"Rostland{/g}! A treacherous invasion of barbarians has caught the {g|Swordlords}"
"Swordlords{/g} off guard — it is presently only skirmishes, but very soon there "
"will be a major battle on the {g|Glenebon}Glenebon Uplands{/g}. Restov is calling "
"for help — and I trust you won't turn your back on your old allies when they need "
"your aid more than ever!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b8ea757-f544-4692-bdb6-ac4f8b6b9aad"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ill news, Your Grace. Your subjects are once again beset by monster attacks. "
"If you don't want another Season of Bloom, you must investigate. I would start "
"your search at {g|Candlemere}Candlemere{/g} Lake — there was another strange flash "
"of light seen on the island, then shortly after, monsters began attacking nearby "
"villages.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e739595a-374b-45ec-9d12-554c45d79a7a"
msgid ""
"\\\"We've so much to report, Your Grace, I don't know where to begin. First, the "
"{g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} have requested your aid against the barbarians. "
"Secondly, monsters have started to appear within our barony again, as they did "
"during the Bloom. According to reports, most of creatures have been sighted at "
"Candlemere Lake.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b27cc38f-af21-4e58-aa79-975aa3f6b376"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's one more thing... I'm afraid the Bloom is back, Your Grace. Monsters "
"have started appearing in the barony again. Fortunately, they have been spotted "
"only near {g|Candlemere}Candlemere{/g} lake. Of course, this is highly disturbing, "
"but, my {mf|baron|baroness}, without immediate action on our part, the {g|"
"Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} may be defeated!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "569855c4-1f35-47be-b62d-5890f60e7fe6"
msgid ""
"\\\"There's one more thing, before I forget — Jamandi Aldori requests your help. "
"The {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} are readying themselves for war against the {g|"
"Numeria}Numerian{/g} barbarians. Lady Aldori hopes for a timely aid... But let me "
"tell you a secret: lady {g|House Surtova}Surtova{/g} would be pleased if you "
"didn't hurry too much with the reinforcements. Why waste your soldiers' lives? "
"Leave this honor to the Aldori troops.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f3abb959-91cd-46d7-a49b-0a97a7ac888c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I hope, Your Grace, you will decide which action to take first. Either way, "
"you should choose quickly — either deal with the tribes from {g|Numeria}Numeria{/"
"g} who are marching to us through {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, or try to discover where "
"this new Bloom originates from. Or, in other words: will you honor your alliance "
"with the Aldori? Or would you rather leave them to their fate, to the {g|House "
"Surtova}Surtova's{/g} delight?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7b399673-6e6a-4475-87d0-3f8f638f0c17"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not long ago, a bright flash was spotted on the center of the island. After "
"that, monsters started to appear in the area, attacking fishermen and travelers. "
"Someone should travel to the {g|Candlemere}Candlemere{/g} and discover where these "
"monsters are coming from — and why.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a53356f-ac30-4ca6-93c2-4cb87782428d"
msgid ""
"\\\"War in {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}, of course! Lady Jamandi's request is pressing, "
"the future of {g|Rostland}Rostland{/g} and {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} depend on "
"you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "401a174b-37c2-4a52-9acc-a82d34015645"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Bloom, of course! The barony won't survive another monster invasion. As "
"for the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g}, let's be honest — are you ready to shed your "
"blood and the blood of your people at Jamandi's whistle? The Swordlords are strong "
"enough to match the barbarians' 'offensive' and keep them from your borders.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c178d27a-fcd6-4af1-bca2-2dc3481b8662"
msgid ""
"\\\"Are you suggesting I take the throne? If I were you, I'd pay attention to "
"what's happening with our neighbors to the north. I'll send my people to {g|Brevoy}"
"Brevoy{/g} — and you should go to {g|Rostland}Rostland{/g} to give the {g|"
"Swordlords}Swordlords{/g} your support.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec0c1b45-26d9-4092-8b92-8c5055625764"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Kellid Barbarians, Your Grace. The {g|Tiger Lords}Tiger Lords{/g} tribe — "
"they sometimes serve as mercenaries in the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g}. "
"Not long ago a new chieftain rose among them, and inspired the tribe to conquer "
"new lands. His name is Armag the Twice-born, and it is said his tribe honor him as "
"a living legend. Looks like {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g} became his first target. {g|"
"Rostland}Rostland{/g}, to be more specific.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2936da1e-c514-4af2-bcf0-317ea4fde7a4"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri raises her head, her eyes blazing.{/n} \\\"{g|Tiger Lords}Tiger Lords{/"
"g}?! So, they decided to come to fight? I've heard, my... former tribe is with "
"them now — hiding from the evil spirt that haunts them. I bet the Tiger Lords "
"brought the cowardly worms here with them! If so, I'll give them what they deserve!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98729b04-25ff-4585-b25b-8b5a82d32d29"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri's jaw drops in surprise.{/n} \\\"You, giving me orders? Listen, the horde "
"of barbarians is cutting through an ally's lands, and you choose this moment to "
"show how strong and tough you are! Pah! I'll go north and scout around. You'll see "
"for yourself — by the time you join me, the battle will be over, I'll see to that! "
"Until then, 'chieftain'!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6601b3d-2aa5-40d6-957e-264e3469d7de"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri gives you a crooked grin.{/n} \\\"Oh no, you are a chieftain, tough and "
"strong. Don't pretend you can't do without me! Sure, it would be better if we went "
"together, but as long as you're stuck here... fine, you can think I'm gone "
"scouting! And as soon as you sort things out here, you go to {g|Rostland}Rostland{/"
"g} — together we'll strike these barbarians down so hard they'll join their "
"mothers in their graves! Till then, {name}\\\"."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c6c901b3-7b7d-49dc-8b50-aa4e1ea60a65"
msgid ""
"{n}Vexed, Amiri spits on the ground.{/n} \\\"Pah, it all seems wrong — to go "
"alone, without you!... But I can't wait. I can't.\\\" {n}Amiri winces.{/n} \\"
"\"Fine. You finish what you're doing here. I'll wait for you at the battlefield. "
"It will be an honor for me — to fight these {g|Numeria}Numerian{/g} dogs side by "
"side with you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "523c1808-3bb5-4377-a194-61d331ba4866"
msgid ""
"{n}She shakes her head, as if trying to cast off something unpleasant, then she "
"glares at you... but her words are carefully controlled.{/n} \\\"What I wanted to "
"say, chieftain... we need to go there, and we need to hurry. I'm going now — to "
"scout around, maybe find some help... come with me! Or else we'll live to see this "
"Armag smash the brevans and come knocking at our main gate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e67b24dd-b530-4dc4-b842-63c4c8fac6fd"
msgid ""
"{n}Amiri raises her hand, as if trying to stop you.{/n} \\\"Easy! If we go in a "
"huge group, there's no way we can scout unnoticed! In short, I go first — to see "
"their numbers, maybe smash several heads. And you come join me later.\\\" {n}She "
"grins.{/n} \\\"Just don't make me wait too long, or I'll kick all their asses "
"without you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6bd8c08-ccba-4c02-80ed-6fd84193ea6a"
msgid ""
"{n}Lander smiles slightly, submerged in his own thoughts.{/n} \\\"We are decided, "
"then. You are going to deal with the business at hand, which leaves me to find "
"someplace to put my efforts and talents as well. So Your Grace — until next we see "
"each other.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42d29729-d191-4560-9de1-c4d90104f531"
msgid ""
"\\\"And the last thing, Your Grace. This morning I received a letter that demands "
"my presence back home.\\\" {n}She pauses.{/n} \\\"My presence at your court was "
"proof that you value good relations with the {g|House Surtova}Surtovas{/g}. Now "
"you can confirm your loyalty by heeding my advice. Mind the problems of your own "
"barony and don't hurry to solve the issues outside your borders.\\\" {n}Shandra "
"bows before you with dignity.{/n} \\\"Till we meet again, Your Grace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20346e02-3371-46a1-9f2b-dc9b4c8d8c0d"
msgid ""
"{n}Kassil bows his head before you.{/n} \\\"And one last thing, Your Grace. Now, "
"in this darkest hour, I must hurry to help my countrymen. I'm heading to {g|"
"Rostland}Rostland{/g} immediately to join the {g|Swordlords}Swordlords{/g}. I hope "
"we'll meet again — and in this world!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b006b2ea-19b9-4f1a-8fcd-c191849f1406"
msgid "\\\"Let's hurry to the square.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cc36fff2-eaf8-4e6f-ba9b-ea64257acdc7"
msgid "\\\"Remind me, who's Annamede again?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58373492-398f-4123-956c-a066341d64e2"
msgid "\\\"Let her sing whatever she likes. It's none of my concern.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "583277f1-56b6-4c7f-a3c4-b7fef3ac3407"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, forgive my intrusion! We have a matter that demands your urgent "
"attention. Right now, Annamede Belavarah, the bard from {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}, is "
"singing in the middle of our main square. And her songs are… seditious, to say the "
"least.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd9d20dc-b91a-4a2f-a5af-192ee0039262"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Baron|Baroness}, you must intervene immediately! Annamede Belavarah, one "
"of King Irovetti's… favored artists... is singing in tour main square right now. "
"Her songs are far from innocent, they can plant dangerous ideas in your subjects' "
"heads.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bbc256cd-07df-4cef-8090-7447b9507082"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Baron|Baroness}, we have a situation on our hands! You need to act!\\\" {n}"
"Lander is furious, his face red.{/n} \\\"Annamede, an annoying little skylark from "
"{g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}, is giving a show in the main square, and her songs are highly "
"seditious!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea4d7804-4bfa-492c-8f4a-56ace2051e56"
msgid ""
"\\\"She's among the most talented bards of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}. But more "
"importantly, she's one of King Irovetti's most favored singers. Anything she sings "
"almost certainly promotes his agenda.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "924f8c9a-1eb4-4a99-8987-a00448e98fb2"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace… Ha, I just realized that I won't be calling you that much longer! "
"I just wanted to tell you that everything is ready for the celebration: your "
"guests have arrived, the capital is fully decorated for the festivities, and the "
"people can't wait for you to make your entrance!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2c2eca2-cb7b-4dc3-b2cd-136eae43e2ed"
msgid ""
"\\\"All right, then, now we can definitely start celebrating... it's just so "
"incredible, I'm so excited: a new kingdom is about to appear — right here, before "
"my very eyes! It's long overdue, if you ask me: my book of our adventures is "
"desperately lacking in episodes where the heroes are properly rewarded!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f58e6f1-2913-4474-8bb9-2d73662fd97d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Shush, girl, stop babbling, would you? You've been hammering our ears for long "
"enough! It's time to let others speak.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a48b2cb4-19ee-41b0-a46d-41270297327e"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten finds a suitable moment to interrupt the bard's speech.{/n} \\\"Linzi, I "
"would like to have a word with the {mf|baron|baroness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de2f6f73-9a4b-44c1-9c27-994296059c42"
msgid ""
"\\\"Enough, girl, let us say a word or two as well!\\\" {n}Jhod takes a deep "
"breath, filling his chest.{/n} \\\"So, Your Grace, are you ready to put a proper "
"crown upon your head? You have no need to answer, I can read it in your eyes: you "
"simply cannot wait!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9d325927-a417-444a-a930-b25d6ee14656"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, {name}. I didn't expect to live long enough to witness this: the {g|"
"Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} have finally gained a proper {mf|king|queen}! Now, "
"after the other monarchs have recognized you, no one will challenge your right to "
"the throne.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e755434-8383-447a-b905-6d7a7d2e4c34"
msgid ""
"\\\"May {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} guard your kingdom. Rule wisely, don't be too harsh "
"to your people without reason, and remain on friendly terms with your neighbors. "
"That won't work with all of them, unfortunately — may demons take the cursed "
"Irovetti... but if someone offers you a hand — don't reject it! All right, that's "
"enough idle talk. I see Linzi here is getting antsy!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "289da087-5cc4-45ab-9694-be7dcc7e8a94"
msgid ""
"\\\"Pardon me for my attire — all these recent events were a bit unexpected... But "
"before the politicians from distant lands start crowding around you, I'd like to "
"tell you this: many people before you tried to win the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen "
"Lands{/g}, and all of them ended up buried in its swamps, fields and hills. You're "
"the first one who didn't get {mf|him|her}self killed here, the first to bend the "
"Stolen Lands to {mf|his|her} will.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ef480062-d227-4d32-b7b3-f61b5de40def"
msgid ""
"\\\"Don't let anyone to snatch away the slightest bit of what now belongs to you. "
"No outsider \\\"Stag Lords\\\", no upstarts like Irovetti. If I could have known "
"who I'd end up serving after House Garess disowned me — well, I would never have "
"believed it. But I am happy to be your vassal, my {mf|Baron|Baroness}. May your "
"reign last a hundred years!\\\" {n}Kesten bows before you and steps aside.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f47bd5b6-2d2e-447a-a437-0b241ecc79f4"
msgid ""
"{n}Kesten nods.{/n} \\\"After everything we've been through to reach this "
"moment... Remember the Season of Bloom? What about the monster that almost killed "
"Jhod and me right in the middle of our own capital? And you even managed to avert "
"a simmering war! Yes, it's high time you get something you deserve — even more "
"than all these {g|House Surtova}Surtovas{/g} and Aldori: a kingdom of you own, and "
"indeed, your own independence.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dba6e977-8a8f-4094-b4f0-6d48942b7424"
msgid ""
"{n}Jhod gives you a tight smile and shakes his head.{/n} \\\"So much has happened, "
"and much more is still to come, mark my words... You may have dealt with the "
"barbarians, but there remain more than a few threats nearby. Take {g|Pitax}Pitax{/"
"g} for instance — a basket of snakes in our back yard!\\\" {n}Jhod waves his hand."
"{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e59837f-c4c5-4c37-acd3-bdee383e9892"
msgid ""
"\\\"But never mind. Let's stop this dark talk, at least for today. Here's what I "
"should like to say instead: though you change your baron's coronet for the royal "
"crown, stay humble. Rule wisely. Don't be too harsh to your people, and don't let "
"us down, for we believed in you from the very beginning. All right, that's it, "
"enough lecturing for today.\\\" {n}Jhod and Kesten give you a bow and allow Linzi "
"to jump back into the conversation.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9d11a615-9b37-4fd7-a0fd-3570f8fdb203"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, it's time to talk to our current ally, Lady Aldori! Jamandi wishes to "
"have a word with you before the ceremony begins. There are still some things I "
"must arrange, so I can't linger any longer. The coronation will commence as soon "
"as you arrive at the square.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b19a233f-3584-4219-aadf-433855f2578b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our new ally can't wait to exchange a word with you. Lady {g|House Surtova}"
"Surtova{/g} requests a brief audience before the ceremony starts. After you're "
"done receiving your congratulations, follow me: the coronation will commence as "
"soon as you arrive at the square.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "09adfe46-fb5f-474f-8370-16dca9579b5b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our esteemed guests, Jamandi Aldori and Natala {g|House Surtova}Surtova{/g}, "
"would like to speak with you before you greet the crowd. Have a nice conversation "
"— meanwhile, I must go and prepare for the ceremony! The coronation will commence "
"as soon as you arrive at the square.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4c3121e-a923-40cc-8e5d-3022e193b94d"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's it, the ceremony is prepared. I'll wait for you outside — brace "
"yourself and emerge in full splendor! The coronation will commence as soon as you "
"arrive at the square.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c9bf903-a1b6-4f67-8e4c-89419c263c18"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, I almost forgot! Look what I have here — something about a former "
"associate of yours, {d|c41 Lander Lives}Lander{/d}! You better {g|"
"Coronation_Lander}read it{/g} right away and then promptly forget about it. You "
"wouldn't want your mood to sour before the coronation!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d9b28d2-0ee8-48f6-a49c-0eb7e76b1e2d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, I almost forgot! Look what I have here — something about a former "
"associate of yours... {d|c41 Lander Money}Lander{/d}! You'd better {g|"
"Coronation_Sarrona}read it{/g} right away, then promptly forget about it. You "
"wouldn't want your mood to sour before the coronation!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9203c00-34f1-461b-87c1-debe4b2cfec5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, I almost forgot! Look what I have here — something about a former "
"associate of yours... {d|c41 Lander Dead}Lander{/d}! You'd better {g|"
"Coronation_Broadsheet}read it{/g} right away, then promptly forget about it. You "
"wouldn't want your mood to sour before the coronation!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c53f172b-1f4d-40b9-87e6-42fc2ee43be4"
msgid "A Broadsheet from New Stetven"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1cb0850-8bd4-41e0-b77e-60643293f6bd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Tragedy in House Lebeda!\\nAccording to our latest reports, tragedy has "
"recently befallen House Lebeda. The house's heir, Lord Lander, has been reported "
"missing. The Dowager Head of House and mother of the missing man, Sarrona Lebeda, "
"publicly announced this only a few days ago. Further details about abduction, and "
"the names of any suspects, are yet unknown.\\nAccording to rumor, shared by "
"servants of House Lebeda, Lord Lander was captured during a hunt, or abducted "
"directly from his sleeping chamber. However, another source claims that the heir "
"ran away from his house of his own volition, and was last seen in the southernmost "
"part of Brevoy. Many agree that the prolonged silence, maintained by House Lebeda "
"after the heir's disappearance, could be explained by the sensitive political "
"situation.\\nSarrona Lebeda urged the abductors to listen to the voice of reason "
"and return her son to her before she takes decisive steps to find him and return "
"him home herself. It is yet unknown if Sarrona will take matters into her own "
"hands, and if she knows anything about the abductors. In the meantime, the heir's "
"disappearance remains an absolute mystery, and a challenge to the best detectives "
"of Brevoy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "07455257-cca4-4b98-be71-d1aa42a59c0c"
msgid "A Letter from Lander Lebeda"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7c4530c-9eb1-4dbe-aa9a-ed0ffd9eaa24"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Baron|Baroness} {name},\\nfirst of all, I would like to thank you for your "
"mercy, and for the lesson you've taught to me. No one has ever done me such an "
"honor. I hope our little conflict won't cause you to reject your better memories "
"of me. Just think about all the difficulties I've helped you through, and all the "
"heroic deeds I inspired you to pursue. I dread to think how long it will take you "
"to find a suitable replacement for me. As for me, I can assure you I don't hold a "
"grudge, and will do everything in my power to avoid crossing your path again."
"\\nForever grateful,\\nLord Lander Lebeda\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c308ce1d-2486-478d-8874-55febe94fb15"
msgid "A Letter from Sarrona Lebeda"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6011114f-f255-47e0-9313-a2ae4ee3ce9c"
msgid ""
"\\\"{mf|Baron|Baroness} {name},\\nI have received your demands and accept your "
"terms and conditions. Along with this letter, I send you the entire ransom for the "
"body of my son. Also, I wish to use this opportunity to offer you a formal "
"apology, on behalf the noble House Lebeda, for the insult that my son inflicted "
"upon you and your family. There's no doubt that what Lander did was inexcusable. "
"However, if he really had intended to stab you in the back, you would surely be "
"dead by now. Apparently, my son took pity on you, so you shouldn't harbor any "
"resentment against him.\\nI must confess, I am surprised by your nobleness. I "
"sincerely hope that your mother will likewise be allowed to recover your body, "
"after you perish. If the family of the highly esteemed {mf|baron|baroness} lacks "
"the necessary financial surety, I shall purchase your body personally, to repay "
"for your kindness. Be assured, your remains shall fall into good hands."
"\\nUnfortunately, I will not be able to visit your lands in person — my doctors "
"recommend against travel in damp climates. But be assured that if I learn of your "
"presence in our realm, I shall prepare a solemn welcome for you without delay."
"\\nWith best regards,\\nSarrona Lebeda, head of House Lebeda\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4854453e-e68b-4c12-80df-b5cc564e6ff3"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about the Order of the Rack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "626c7e36-0c1d-4028-86e4-2fea10ba008a"
msgid "\\\"Who is this fugitive you're looking for?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "855c8fa4-1227-413a-ad73-a2c36ec6f01b"
msgid "\\\"Can I help you with your investigation?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fe2e8fd-9335-49b6-a938-5ede4706af33"
msgid "Allowed Linxia to carry out her investigation in the barony."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8323bb6c-9cbb-4ff3-befa-b8bcf812d7e9"
msgid ""
"\\\"I authorize you to conduct your investigation within my {mf|barony|barony|"
"kingdom|kingdom}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2ba4d57-1997-4da2-aa33-91bffada0899"
msgid "Forbade Linxia's investigation."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ca5944c-d938-4db0-9ab2-68e693e359be"
msgid "\\\"Get out of my {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f62fc4cb-da5b-4bb7-a845-949d3de8653a"
msgid "Doubted the necessity of burning all books."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7904222a-15b6-4b6b-90d3-54dfd9a1bf6c"
msgid "\\\"Catching criminals is one thing, but burning books is too much!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0cfe026-81d3-4cc9-a40c-f46cb7daae44"
msgid "Tried to reason with Linxia."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d767665a-c0be-46ab-9ffa-13f7a658bc78"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your actions in Cheliax do not concern me. But while you are on my land, I "
"demand you to refrain from such... extreme measures.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7cd53958-6d43-40bd-80bb-b57497eb8e87"
msgid "Agreed with Linxia."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af8a6e8c-aa98-4b9f-8170-653f64d78c5b"
msgid "\\\"I entirely share your opinion.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27168606-8429-4cb9-8462-1284aaf3df4b"
msgid "[Remain silent]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d0d09c8-e33e-4b87-9d66-8b9da2e9f5f6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The {g|Order of the Rack}Order of the Rack{/g} welcomes you, {mf|baron|"
"baroness|king|queen}.\\\" {n}The black-skinned woman slightly bows her carefully "
"shaved head.{/n} \\\"My name is Linxia. I come from the distant land of {g|Cheliax}"
"Cheliax{/g} in search of a dangerous criminal who is hiding in your barony.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "08a25f41-02e8-4193-9a8f-0d91c1a2fdb2"
msgid ""
"{n}She stands tall and almost motionless. The reflected torch light dances on the "
"surface of her polished black armor and in the depths of her watchful black eyes.{/"
"n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3e1e42d1-fd28-47e4-b293-e9bb66723abc"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am glad that we have met, and I believe the rule of law in your {mf|barony|"
"barony|kingdom|kingdom} is not just empty phrases. I hope for the cooperation from "
"your subjects and you personally.\\\" {n}Contrary to her words, Linxia's face does "
"not express any gladness. The corner of her mouth twitches slightly, betraying "
"carefully-concealed discontent.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2393e064-b28a-45ea-aa6c-63926d49603d"
msgid ""
"{n}Linxia's face remains as stony as ever. Only the corner of her mouth expresses "
"displeasure with your decision.{/n} \\\"You misunderstand me, {mf|baron|baroness|"
"king|queen}. The investigation will continue, with or without your permission. The "
"{g|Order of the Rack}Order of the Rack{/g} always collects. No one should stay in "
"its way.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b510764-06d1-4771-9d2d-49cadffdd2ea"
msgid ""
"\\\"A dangerous pirate, a murderer, and a rebel named Darven \\\"the Dashing\\\" "
"Fairwood. He was found guilty of inciting a rebellion and murdering a noble lord "
"in {g|Cheliax}Cheliax{/g}. The law of my Order is unwavering. The punishment for "
"such crimes is death.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0942171-3ee1-4932-8bd8-336d4244fa8f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Darven's rebellion took place in {g|Cheliax}Cheliax{/g} three years ago. The "
"{g|Order of the Rack}Order of the Rack{/g} quickly suppressed it, the participants "
"were jailed, and the instigators quartered — but their leader Darven managed to "
"escape. I have followed his trail for a long time, and now it has led me here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8686925b-3db3-4cb0-a9d9-ca41159283a9"
msgid ""
"{n}The shadow of a smile crosses Linxia's face.{/n} \\\"I and my knights are "
"perfectly capable of finding and eliminating one criminal. Your help... is "
"unnecessary.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1749dc76-413b-4ee2-a91f-ead0f0346c72"
msgid "\\\"If you want to help, do not interfere.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9392ab9-e4f4-4b2d-92b0-a40541f471da"
msgid ""
"\\\"We are the {g|Hellknights}Hellknights{/g}. We guard law and order. Legitimate "
"authorities can rely on us entirely. Criminals tremble when they hear our "
"footsteps.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91f2323b-1b65-4a40-b3ae-b74073146c95"
msgid ""
"{n}Linxia sizes you up.{/n} \\\"It is in your best interest to maintain friendly "
"relations with us. Trust me, {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f53ad6f-ffaf-4776-b6fa-fc0d24ed19ab"
msgid ""
"\\\"The Order of the Rack is a union of the knights of {g|Cheliax}Cheliax{/g}, led "
"by hatred of idleness, worthless philosophy, and useless knowledge. Indulgence "
"leads to lawlessness and insurrection. We seek out any manifestations of dissent "
"and burn them — be they books, scientific treatises... or those who create them.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7ecb6e2-6540-4899-b478-0b8538254769"
msgid ""
"{n}For a moment, Linxia stares at you with an intense look, but then blinks as if "
"suddenly relaxed.{/n} \\\"We stand on the side of legitimate authority. You need "
"not be afraid, {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "329ba244-3e9c-4dd3-a811-0c9986c8cd3f"
msgid ""
"\\\"We do not burn all books, only those that can harm society and place dangerous "
"thoughts in weak-willed minds. It's better to burn a book today than quarter its "
"reader tomorrow.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "deffc211-6fa2-4aec-9c7e-bcd87a6d5195"
msgid ""
"\\\"I... will try to fulfill your request.\\\" {n}She gives you a little grin.{/n} "
"\\\"At least — we'll let you know before we decide to burn someone.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7b31d6be-710a-499c-b304-dcb0ddae2e24"
msgid ""
"{n}Linxia raises her eyebrow for a moment, as if she never expected such an answer."
"{/n} \\\"I'm pleased to see that our judgments coincide. We will inform you if, in "
"the process of our investigation, we stumble upon any manifestations of dissent in "
"your {mf|barony|barony|kingdom|kingdom}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a169683-77b6-4765-a2cc-4415ef8146d3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}. Your good will means a lot to us.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1db6cba-03b1-4461-8441-2a1a67a09d9d"
msgid "\\\"Please don't read my letters anymore.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9b3550d9-62bf-4555-a0fa-a751667220e2"
msgid "\\\"Fine, we'll go there as soon as we have time to spare.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2270ad81-713c-4c5e-9d6a-c2393b757c25"
msgid "\\\"I don't want to have anything to do with those two.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3e052604-eafc-4e37-867d-50d996e54caa"
msgid "\\\"I'm absolutely sure. Let them both go to Hell — or worse.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "788c3a66-afa2-47fd-957a-06a16ea4ea27"
msgid ""
"\\\"Looks like we're finally about to see another part of that story about Darven "
"and Linxia. But this time, a peaceful solution seems an unlikely outcome.\\\" {n}"
"Linzi sighs.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "200ed1ac-4a71-4b41-870e-2094c9f75e90"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our esteemed {d|c41 Linxia Rejected}captain{/d} has sent us a {g|"
"darven_message}message{/g}. Here, take a look. He writes that he's built a city "
"near your border, and invites you to be his guest. But this invitation has a foul "
"smell, if you ask me — Linxia is bound to be there too. I can bet that these two "
"will be at each other's throat even before we show up.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6985080-2457-49d2-bfbe-cfc59dbc6f0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"That wretched {d|c41 Linxia Welcomed}book-burner{/d} has sent us a {g|"
"linxia_message}message{/g}. Here you are — I hope you enjoy it. She's softened her "
"tone a bit, and now she's asking us to help her. She writes that Darven has built "
"a city near your border. So she's going to assault it, and she's decided that "
"we'll volunteer to be her reinforcement.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d89df44-b88d-4a62-9685-d676920a9385"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi suddenly realizes something.{/n} \\\"You won't be offended that I read "
"your letter, right? It's just that the courier brought in an unsealed paper, so I "
"just...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "253bacfd-abd0-48c5-9261-9bddad16e63a"
msgid ""
"\\\"But I just wanted to make sure that the case was really serious. So you "
"wouldn't get distracted over nothing. Uhh…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7f30c7f-bca3-4b7e-85ce-a6921ed0e7b3"
msgid ""
"\\\"I guess we should hurry, or they'll probably kill each other before we even "
"get there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f706f80-0b57-4354-addf-f8af351190de"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, that's your right. To tell you the truth, I'm not a big fan of either of "
"them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bd2f9b1-2c08-4f09-ba99-e58642bb9418"
msgid ""
"\\\"Are you sure? Maybe we should at least go and see what's going on there? You "
"know, for the sake of curiosity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7fdc669-d213-4e12-aa60-419fd7fe8c98"
msgid "Darven's Invitation"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b180f73-e335-4a6b-92c0-ceef57b46498"
msgid ""
"\\\"My dearest neighbor!\\nNow I have every right to call you so. Brineheart is "
"located on the riverbank in the southern Kamelands — right near the border of your "
"lands. So you can congratulate me now, my dream has finally come true, and I've "
"become a legitimate ruler of my own little kingdom. I strongly recommend you come "
"and congratulate me in person — for our dearest Linxia will most definitely do the "
"same in the nearest future. And I'd love it so much if all three of us could "
"gather near the fireplace and share the latest gossip over a bottle of good wine. "
"Without you, this gathering would be incomplete.\\nI'll be happy to cover all your "
"travel expenses.\\nYour friend,\\nDarven.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "95ac7c93-d92c-4fc1-afe3-64ffeceb1f05"
msgid "Linxia's Order"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c9f22157-4b9a-4913-a96a-629dd4238285"
msgid ""
"\\\"We parted ways not on the best terms. But duty demands me to inform you that "
"the well-known criminal called Darven has founded a city in the Kamelands, in the "
"vicinity of your southern border. This hotbed of vice must be stamped out, and "
"Darven brought to justice. I'm heading to this 'Brineheart' immediately. If you "
"have even a pinch of decency, you will do the same.\\nFulfill your duty.\\nLinxia "
"Benzekri, the Order of the Rack.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ebcecac3-048d-440d-80e1-46f2269f5715"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Grace, I came to say farewell. Alas, I must return to my homeland — I "
"have responsibilities as family head. Thank you for everything you've done for me. "
"Take care of yourself.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "767dc6b0-6a1c-4e95-8be1-2b62b73f77a8"
msgid "\\\"Let's start from the beginning. How did you even come up with this?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "647b3068-81db-4335-bba9-8bff9d059b9c"
msgid "\\\"What exactly are you going to do?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68a91730-14c5-47ac-b6d4-7305436d4bce"
msgid "\\\"What will we achieve by this?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e1c7c90-8e9c-47e0-aace-eb61d8b3452e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Fine. I'll order you to be provided with everything you need. Get me results.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d08e205-6398-4d15-b125-e5b820ae253d"
msgid ""
"\\\"And then {mf|King|Queen} {name} proudly said: \\\"Your evil deeds end now!\\\" "
"Or is it better as, \\\"We've uncovered your vile plan!\\\"? {n}Linzi's trying to "
"write something on the go, but she interrupts herself and looks up.{/n} \\\"Oh... "
"Your Highness! We have unbelievably, terribly important news! We managed to find "
"out... discover... invent... Well... here,\\\" {n}Linzi points to the Storyteller."
"{/n} \\\"He'll tell you!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "014f35cf-6689-4133-a17a-b572f7321edb"
msgid ""
"{n}The Storyteller waits patiently until Linzi finishes her ardent speech.{/n} \\"
"\"I will have to begin from afar to let you see what I 'saw' with my blind eyes... "
"The {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} are like a cradle in an abandoned house, in "
"which the wind swings the skeleton of a child. No few newborn kingdoms have died "
"here, just after taking their first breath. I have collected their stories, these "
"precious stars that have been lost in the dust. And I began to notice some "
"commonalities.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f984cdec-3770-480d-a01f-38f50c468959"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is like a pattern that repeats across different embroideries. The "
"handwriting of the same author across all their stories. One word here, another "
"hint there... false visions, references to a mysterious patroness, lover, and "
"mentor... Tragic \\\"coincidences,\\\" strangely nonrandom... Peoples and "
"countries were brought to destruction along different roads, but behind them, "
"there always stood the same ominous shadow.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f312335d-3bf5-4860-bf81-9625d59ab206"
msgid ""
"\\\"And we know what that shadow is! Nyrissa!\\\" {n}The name sounds ominous even "
"in the mouth of a restless bard.{/n} \\\"The evil nymph who sent monsters to our "
"lands and did all that stuff to Tristian! But that's not even the most important "
"thing. Most importantly, if you help us a bit — we can get her!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9adb005a-a5df-47ae-94ea-ce955820ed47"
msgid ""
"\\\"Weelll, it all started with the fact that I really wanted to listen to the "
"Storyteller's stories. I've been following him for a long, long time... and "
"asked... and told him about our adventures... and sometimes I just sat beside him "
"and we chatted. Finally, after I told him about the Defaced Sisters and all the "
"horrors of the abandoned castle, he noticed that the story seemed strangely "
"similar to ones he'd heard before.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19f46f34-e0e4-4b35-a951-a9ff29d341b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"The bards know how to send messages through dreams. I try not to use it — for "
"some reason, people got mad when I appeared in their dreams to read my new poems! "
"Well, the Storyteller came up with a ritual based on that spell. We'll collect "
"everything connected to Nyrissa. Everything, starting with her every track in the "
"abandoned castle. After gathering everything, we'll unite his ability to tell "
"stories with my ability to travel into dreams. So, we'll be able to enter "
"Nyrissa's dream!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b7b9b41-bed9-48a8-a388-1046ed38ee35"
msgid ""
"\\\"Come to me after we finish the preparations, and remember that I cannot send "
"anyone except you and Linzi into Nyrissa's dream world. Whatever you have to face, "
"you will have to overcome together. And the path will likely be difficult.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8efa72b2-33e0-4de6-93ab-8c694e2edbbf"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll learn all her evil secrets! The ritual will let us see her hidden "
"thoughts and dreams. Well, theoretically... It's not like anyone's ever done this "
"before...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a048ee4d-1b31-4827-83b6-c9d886f9994d"
msgid ""
"\\\"It can be dangerous,\\\" {n}the Storyteller says quietly.{/n} \\\"In dreams, "
"monsters are more terrible than those we meet in the real world. But I urge you to "
"not neglect this chance, {mf|King|Queen}. You are opposed by a powerful enemy, one "
"who has destroyed dozens of kingdoms and empires. If you do not meet her face-to-"
"face, do not discover her weaknesses — your country will end up just another of my "
"stories.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97a68e39-2fe3-4a1d-a316-3ea79304840e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do we still have that amulet with the string of hair that she gave you before "
"the battle with the Stag Lord? That'd be great! That'll let us finish all the "
"preparations much faster and easier!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "771c4a23-8d48-4131-bf75-cd3d133213e6"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's a pity that we don't have that amulet with the string of hair that "
"Nyrissa gave you before the battle with the Stag Lord — you know, back when she "
"was pretending to be a poor suffering nymph? With that, we could have finished all "
"the preparations much faster and easier!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ae13b296-0ad1-4384-9a3b-de21e70f5007"
msgid "\\\"What happened, Linzi?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5594e6f-8635-4f38-8ce6-fb277a7fe858"
msgid "\\\"Just take some time to catch your breath and explain what happened.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1de32748-b105-4c0c-83ef-16ba47e056a6"
msgid "\\\"I don't have time to spare for your nonsense.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aed77bd1-456a-4566-a95f-298cd295809c"
msgid "\\\"What happened here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "756b5899-f150-476a-91bc-dea8c4754617"
msgid "\\\"This is... unexpected.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1cf116d-b568-428c-b1ed-d8033aac86e2"
msgid "\\\"Who did this?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5ab4654-f8d1-43a7-b020-02368f56c136"
msgid "\\\"In your opinion, where should I begin this investigation?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1047f414-53d6-4f56-8a8a-10f540b31365"
msgid "\\\"Oh, if I manage to catch this thief…\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8889338-cc5c-45bc-94cf-81d3452b56cc"
msgid "\\\"Time to get going.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "882599b0-dc1c-42db-9f53-6ab6e16f95c2"
msgid "\\\"What were my guards doing?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34711514-30f9-48dc-ad9a-9f774b7492a1"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi's eyes glitter and her nostrils flare with rage, but for some reason she "
"speaks in a whisper.{/n} \\\"Such... such insolence! Such unforgettable, "
"monstrous, unimaginable insolence!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52ed9ee3-50ff-474c-84c9-7220493bc5e8"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi suddenly and firmly grabs your sleeve.{/n} \\\"Nonsense? How can it be "
"nonsense if Your Royal Highness now has no place to, pardon my language, sit {mf|"
"his|her} royal ass on?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65dfcff8-34d9-4a19-885e-7c24ce1721d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The throne... The royal throne... It...\\\" {n}Linzi stops whispering and "
"silently points her finger to the far side of the throne room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9af6d806-33d0-4d48-8aa8-f9405457ff77"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi catches her breath and continues to whisper,{/n} \\\"Your Highness, we've "
"got a problem. A major problem. Look for yourself!\\\" {n}The bard points her "
"finger toward the far side of the throne room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20c402bd-20d8-4427-8038-f20fb2e58a19"
msgid ""
"{n}You raise your eyes. The place where the royal throne once stood is now empty.{/"
"n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac40ba35-783b-4acc-bb75-600160484863"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi shrugs.{/n} \\\"The culprit managed to escape, but I can't imagine how "
"someone could drag the throne out of the palace without being noticed by anyone!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e9dcf2f-33b6-4690-b15d-5bc033cc7f19"
msgid ""
"\\\"Insidious, shameless robbery — that's what happened here! Who would even think "
"to break into the royal chambers!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe1438c9-bec4-406a-9184-cca3941f5be1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm surprised by your self-control: if I were you, I'd go on a rampage! "
"Shameless scum, how could they go and rob the royal palace with the {mf|king|"
"queen} still alive and well!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "605a1d5e-039b-45ed-b222-c9904d8901a8"
msgid ""
"\\\"In fact, our case is blatant and extraordinary, but hardly exceptional. Word "
"on the streets is that the local population has become sick and tired of thieves — "
"they break into people's homes, bypass the locks and latches, and steal everything "
"they can! And now the scum has the guts to meddle with royal property!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54dcb5be-0352-42fe-ae57-72fd8dc4b7a9"
msgid ""
"\\\"We need to sort this out before they steal the whole kingdom one brick at a "
"time... and we need to get back your throne! It's shameful!\\\" {n}Linzi regains "
"control of herself and continues in a low whisper.{/n} \\\"I really hope your "
"people here won't go wagging their tongues and spreading filthy rumors.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "09504c3a-9012-4be3-820d-40828693dcf9"
msgid ""
"\\\"You should start with interrogating potential witnesses! I think the captain "
"of the guard was in the palace when it happened — he was the one who discovered "
"the throne was missing, at least!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7f59406-6615-442c-a041-5e3a7477c418"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then you should go to the city. I heard the smith was robbed recently too. "
"Maybe he can give you some clues? Also, if I were you, I'd talk to the trader — he "
"might have some hints as to who may be selling stolen goods. Oh, and one more "
"thing — don't forget to visit the innkeeper. Who better to glean information from "
"any troubled locals finding themselves in need of a shoulder to cry on?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e74859f-764b-4ed3-9cd8-5f9c704c521e"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi shakes her head.{/n} \\\"Whatever your upcoming plans were, retrieving "
"the throne must be your top priority! I dread to think how loud our neighbors will "
"laugh if they learn of this disgrace!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6742b559-8ad9-4abf-9dd9-5863e20ed18b"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi flings her arms up.{/n} \\\"Well, you weren't on the throne at the time "
"it was stolen, right? And our guards are trained to guard people, not furniture!\\"
"\" {n}The bard gives you a faint smile.{/n} \\\"Sure, if the throne was stolen "
"with you still sitting on it, things would be much worse. That's not much "
"consolation, though...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61e6b680-cc8b-4069-92b3-bb9d36446568"
msgid "\\\"What is this tournament?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db3cf8fd-7b5a-4373-9277-f01c1ff608f3"
msgid ""
"\\\"If Irovetti holds it once in several years, why did he wait until now to "
"invite me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4db21d4-2776-4e36-9a24-a6e66c533a9c"
msgid "\\\"Are you sure this isn't a trap?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c4b356c-0a74-4ec2-9fea-454a56b7b1af"
msgid "\\\"What can you tell me of Pitax and its king?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "939a0f69-35c8-497e-ab21-42c7cbff327a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Irovetti can go straight to the Abyss with his tournament. Write back that I "
"won't be attending.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb0d25a7-0225-425e-b25e-868616ce62a8"
msgid "\\\"Interesting. Well, If I have the time... why not?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3da546cb-3c59-4127-9c9d-d22e051c631b"
msgid "\\\"Perhaps you're right... Tell me more about this tournament.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6d17953-6bc7-496f-b84e-d29463085e50"
msgid "\\\"I'm sure. I've no interest in seeing Pitax or Irovetti.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "012d390d-d369-44f6-a159-17910fffb461"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi excitedly waves around {g|RushlightInvitation}a letter{/g} written in "
"neat handwriting on expensive stationery.{/n} \\\"I have news! Take a look! "
"Irovetti, King of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}, sent you an invitation to the Rushlight "
"tournament! We're not going to miss it, right? And you're taking me, of course!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "862bb265-b5f8-4b86-9907-7fbd808b5f6e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Irovetti holds once in several years. Guests come from all the nearby kingdoms "
"— {g|Mivon}Mivon{/g}, Gralton, {g|Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}... I haven't been there "
"personally, but I hear it's always a lot of fun!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "152bf7db-8716-4c13-98f4-67bd1b3b712c"
msgid ""
"\\\"How would I know what goes on in Irovetti's head? Maybe he just thought you "
"weren't important enough as a baron{mf||ess} — but now you're a bona fide {mf|king|"
"queen}! His equal, you could say! There's no reason not to invite you to what he "
"considers the major social event of the year.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65ff4a10-d217-4f3f-8126-2e6abb093f69"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well... Imagine a roadhouse full of pirates, mercenaries, smugglers, spies, "
"and other gentlemen of fortune. They're drinking to their successes, talking "
"business, buying, selling, hiring, choking, burying... Now take this roadhouse, "
"and imagine it's the size of a kingdom — that was {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} BEFORE "
"Irovetti.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72639bc2-8d09-412b-bd9c-fc25a8023879"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now imagine some unknown bard enters the roadhouse, pulls off a few shady "
"deals, and suddenly became its owner. Everything is the same as it was, but now "
"the walls are covered with portraits of the owner, a brass band plays music every "
"night, a juggler with a pet bear walks around the room, gnome strippers dance on "
"the tables, barmen sell a variety of racy substances from {g|Numeria}Numeria{/g} "
"beyond its beer... That's {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f9be568e-ad73-4289-b913-2fb8ee3da29e"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's certainly possible! There's definitely some catch here — this is Irovetti "
"we're talking about, after all! But I doubt he'd try to kill you at his own "
"festival, with business partners from all his neighbors present. He's more likely "
"to try to sell you on some fraudulent deal or another. So keep your eyes and ears "
"open, and don't sign anything!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ce798ad-4982-4d42-a942-6825b4a03862"
msgid ""
"\\\"Are you sure? I mean, it's certainly a trap... but imagine all the fun you'll "
"miss!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec20a883-d26c-4c4b-a94f-629cdfa039ae"
msgid "\\\"Of course! What would you like to know?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1688046f-b946-4d8b-b5fd-3a7527886700"
msgid "\\\"If you say so... I'll pen the response now.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e48f35e7-afab-4f7d-9b83-2b8e0941475f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Great! Trap or no, it'll at least be a ton of fun. You will take me with you, "
"right? Pretty please?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90ba744d-560b-45ac-a6f3-54b051efbae7"
msgid ""
"\\\"All the high society of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} will be there... including people "
"from the {g|Academy of Grand Arts}Academy{/g}! Maybe even Headmaster Atalia "
"Gitaren. I'd love to see her face when she hears about the book Professor Eobald "
"is writing with me!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0fda451-3f59-4533-9e5e-2ca63ace9a53"
msgid "Invitation to the Rushlight Tournament"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2fbab78-014a-42e6-85cd-4bf573ffdde8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Royal Highness, the much-esteemed and illustrious {Name}, tamer of "
"Dunsward and the Stolen Lands, hero{mf||ine} of the battle against the barbarian "
"hordes on the Flintrock Grassland, et cetera, et cetera, et cetera.\\nI am happy "
"to hereby invite you to the Rushlight Tournament — the most important social event "
"in the River Kingdoms, where the whole region's upper crust will gather to mingle "
"and have some innocent fun. The Tournament, as always, will take place on the "
"shore of the Rushlight River. I eagerly await your arrival, and look forward to "
"the chance to finally meet you in person!\\nCordially yours,\\nCastruccio "
"Irovetti, King of Pitax\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40f8fc3b-d55e-4d8e-b35c-5d3ae59444a0"
msgid "\\\"So you think Irovetti is behind all this?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ad5c853-5d6f-4be8-8116-524ce8006f7e"
msgid "\\\"What do we know about the monster attacks?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91f38b0f-7115-4e8f-bcda-67fd3be62a1b"
msgid "\\\"Do we know who's spreading the propaganda?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "114ddc9c-ae78-464f-bb0e-665af2f79578"
msgid "\\\"Enough talk, then. There's no time to waste.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad0fa384-d3a7-47c9-a677-24605017b9ce"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do we have any definitive proof that would allow us to formally expose "
"Irovetti?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "024b342d-e3c2-4ec1-9f99-9106c1d72542"
msgid "\\\"What is it, Linzi?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6b86cd1-85ff-403b-98ab-7057c5d0d663"
msgid "Refused to listen to reports of disturbances in the kingdom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11c1ff2c-754d-4756-ab88-d0544d8e2524"
msgid "\\\"I don't want to hear it. It's probably more nonsense anyway.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f756880-171c-42b3-9b00-d5368ec4eb5c"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ha! 'Fire, Your Highness,' 'plague, Your Highness'... I know I can always "
"count on you for good news, Linzi!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5829d759-d26d-44cc-a020-cfcaea23abcb"
msgid "Joked to lighten the mood when Linzi brought bad news."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06d0a437-8bc1-408c-8bf9-145dedf46bfb"
msgid "\\\"I mean... yes, actually.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d933099-a35e-41e1-a498-837575479d15"
msgid "\\\"Let's get to business, then. What's happened?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fd221667-6c51-4c67-baa2-df6c0715159e"
msgid "Threatened Linzi when she brought bad news."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "364eef86-68b2-4830-aa3f-01d9a0001c8d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I think the first order of business should be finding more sensible subjects. "
"All right, spill it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06752d25-04ae-4e6f-ba54-c68abe90027c"
msgid "\\\"I thought the Stolen Lands were used to dealing with bandits.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40468bd7-eed2-4bfa-add7-fd41ec413937"
msgid "\\\"Why am I just hearing about this now?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82488889-622e-4a3d-bc29-a0c9513db022"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi's cheeks are flushed and she's out of breath — it seems like she must "
"have run all the way to the throne room.{/n} \\\"Disaster... It's a disaster, Your "
"Highness!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "059f7a5a-bf4b-4854-8ec5-7e9381047cfc"
msgid ""
"\\\"The whole kingdom's on fire! Well, metaphorically speaking... And some of it "
"literally. First of all, we've got armed gangs ranging along our border with {g|"
"Pitax}Pitax{/g}, robbing and killing people, destroying food stores, and damaging "
"any property they come across! Second, there are sudden and inexplicable monster "
"attacks being reported all throughout your lands! And third, there are people out "
"sowing dissent with rumors and songs, even handing out pamphlets mocking your "
"failure to fix things — and encouraging the citizens to pledge fealty to Irovetti "
"instead!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a173f92-4261-4292-b7aa-a2b37c3aea0f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Who else could it be?! Bandit attacks are increasing along our border with {g|"
"Pitax}Pitax{/g}, and the bards spouting negative propaganda against you are "
"singing the praises of Irovetti at the same time! Hell, he even invited you to the "
"Rushlight tournament for the sole purpose of mocking you! Who else would backstab "
"their opponents in such a low, conniving way? This is just like him! That nasty, "
"slimy, fatheaded prick! If he were here right now...\\\" {n}Linzi clutches the "
"air, as though gripping the throat of an invisible enemy.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48ef4560-d1c6-489b-9d19-264ab1a6edbc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes and no. The bards handing out pamphlets and singing slander about you have "
"been seen in city streets, but none have been caught. Obviously someplace in {g|"
"Pitax}Pitax{/g} is training these people and printing up their pamphlets... and "
"judging by the style and quality of the texts, someone from Pitax's {g|Academy of "
"Grand Arts}Academy of Grand Arts{/g} was tasked with this mudslinging. I'd "
"recognize their style of verse from a mile away. If I were you, that's where I'd "
"start looking for agitators.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ae0ecdb0-1060-48fa-86f6-482a39ffd1e7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Not yet. But I'm sure the agents he hired will have something we can use! It's "
"a good idea, though — expose Irovetti, show the whole world the dirty game he's "
"playing... It would definitely help us. When you deal with his spies, be sure to "
"keep your eyes open!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1793d462-0ba9-4c3f-977e-0e9c8d856e35"
msgid ""
"\\\"What did you think, that you'd become {mf|king|queen} and just get to feast "
"every day, enjoying the fawning of your lords and ladies in waiting, and holding "
"tournaments? You sit on the throne — you could be so kind as to rule!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d10f48cb-6a0d-4f8d-b552-b2f0b02ba414"
msgid "\\\"Nonsense?! Do you have any idea what's happening?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94e3102b-5f43-470e-b58b-847de8b2a8d7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Our governors are panicking! They've had to use all the funds we budgeted them "
"from the treasury on preventing riots and mass hysteria. Several provinces have "
"already refused to attempt gathering taxes from the people, claiming that just "
"trying would be tantamount to suicide!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f8a469d3-ba8e-4de5-b653-9cb5f3cf9dab"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thing is, they may be dressed like bandits, but they're behaving completely "
"differently. Bandits wouldn't decimate the peasant population, burn their fields, "
"and poison their wells — then there wouldn't be anyone to extort next time! Much "
"more profitable to just shake them down every once in a while. That's why local "
"thugs tend to be well known. But nobody recognizes these new ones! And all that's "
"left behind after their raids are corpses and scorched fields. It's gotten to the "
"point that 'our' bandits are fighting these 'outsiders.' Some of the villages are "
"even gathering weapons and supplies to help 'our' bandits, because they at least "
"let them live... but they're still losing.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8fa2c7b-5856-4047-9f99-9d5a7c80afa0"
msgid ""
"\\\"The reports are controversial — they talk about things you wouldn't even hear "
"in fairy tales. Educated wyverns, trolls wearing armor, even undetectable goblin "
"ghosts! But all the testimonies agree on one thing: they emerge in small groups "
"literally from nowhere — in the middle of a field, in the center of a city square, "
"on fortress parapets... One inn reported monsters rushing into the common hall "
"from bedrooms and storerooms. And in a temple nearby, the monsters fell down on "
"the heads of the praying congregation, breaking through the roof with a wild roar!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d3bc894-305a-4fdb-b5a3-b0f2f347514b"
msgid ""
"\\\"At first, no one thought these isolated events could be part of some "
"conspiracy... even now, it's likely few have figured it out. But these events have "
"all developed too quickly, and in what seems like a concerted effort — as though "
"someone were pulling the strings from behind a curtain. And there's more than "
"enough evidence tying these strings to {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d005e599-cd67-478f-9b56-94c02b3f07ae"
msgid ""
"\\\"We don't have much time. There may be no troops marching against us, but more "
"of our regions are under attack each day. We may not have catapults firing on the "
"walls of our capital, but there's no doubt we're under siege. There are no "
"battlefronts and no battalions, but there are plenty of victims. We've been "
"attacked — without reason, and without declaration of war. We have only one "
"option...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6c9e915-03d5-460d-9888-37eaf84a6b64"
msgid ""
"\\\"...to kick Irovetti's ass and show everyone in the {g|River Kingdoms}River "
"Kingdoms{/g} just who's the master around here!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "841d251d-fa47-49aa-aee0-af8f5b41bdb5"
msgid ""
"\\\"Just a few hours ago, a messenger showed up at the castle with a missive "
"offering the services of a group of rangers who specialize in investigating "
"mysterious cases similar to these. For a 'small fee,' they're ready to 'facilitate "
"establishing the nature of these inexplicable events'... I suppose we should take "
"them up on it. I have no idea how else we'd go about finding the source of these "
"attacks!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c810898-47a8-4d41-984f-710f867eeca8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hurry, {name}. Your {d|c51 Rushlight Fail}performance{/d} at the Rushlight "
"tournament... well, frankly, you'd have been better off not going at all. The "
"people are laughing at you — you've completely lost their trust. The seeds of "
"Irovetti's propaganda will be falling on fertile soil.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f20e979-0faa-44b6-ac75-ee4a6fe4df6e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Fortunately, the situation could be worse. Your decisive victory in the "
"Rushlight tournament really bolstered the people's {d|c51 Rushlight Cool}faith{/d} "
"in you and your abilities. It's funny how such nonsense can affect people's minds "
"more than real feats and atrocities do. But this works out in our favor — thanks "
"to that victory, we'll have a little more time to deal with whatever vile acts "
"that madman from {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} throws at us...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dabdf574-3e27-43e0-a2cb-67affe537c0d"
msgid ""
"\\\"One more thing, {name}. Your performance in the Rushlight tournament was... {d|"
"c51 Rushlight Neutral}not the best{/d}. But at least you participated — if not for "
"that, I think it would've been even easier for Irovetti to confuse people and "
"undermine your authority as he tries to push our kingdom into the Abyss. Don't let "
"your guard down, though — we're looking at a matter of months, at best.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac02b658-422a-4e4f-8ee4-62e93e5149c3"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi's eyes flare.{/n} \\\"Sometimes I don't know why I even bother coming to "
"you at all!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4100fed-d63f-47f8-9804-212f4cba2314"
msgid ""
"{n}Linzi's laughter rings across the room.{/n} \\\"Ha ha! You dummy! This is no "
"time for jokes!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ac2ba98-ba70-422e-808b-a59edfc27142"
msgid ""
"\\\"I don't want to be a downer, but... the fate of the kingdom really is in your "
"hands here, {name}. I'm afraid to think what might happen if we don't get control "
"of the situation in the next few months...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2822b65b-0e7e-451c-a491-9dc7f01af221"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hurry, {name}. Your refusal to participate in the Rushlight tournament really "
"hurt your reputation with the populace. They think you were too scared to accept "
"Irovetti's challenge.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0345576-36da-4cd0-bc54-c8839cf5e3fd"
msgid "Appointed Gasperre Liacenza as the governor of Pitax."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51410a76-3685-4a20-8ddb-ac8be06c6b1b"
msgid "\\\"I appoint Gasperre Liacenza as governor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0195f047-dbdb-47b4-895c-593a100c63a7"
msgid "Appointed Kharne Vereel as the governor of Pitax."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de54a00d-6054-4c90-89c3-aa8792b94218"
msgid "\\\"I appoint Kharne Vereel as governor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7943ce4c-4f3a-4c4f-9fa2-73c50eee1dff"
msgid "Appointed Stefano Moskoni as the governor of Pitax."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed4fdc30-b686-4ec9-8716-b9b00dc88470"
msgid "\\\"I appoint Stefano Moskoni as governor.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "153b87fb-ec91-44df-b7b2-e2d8a4b83612"
msgid "Appointed your own viceroy as the governor of Pitax."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cd9af7e-9461-487f-bfe5-6f85095abe4f"
msgid "\\\"None of you will be governor. I will send my own viceroy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c5e38c80-0d99-4b4f-89dc-bf63c1fb27e6"
msgid "Executed Kharne Vereel."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9419b9b2-c78a-4130-a566-873fc925a55c"
msgid "\\\"Guards! I sentence Kharne Vereel to death. Take him!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "caee53e8-db91-4a83-b35f-1d7d77f2d320"
msgid "Executed Gasperre Liacenza."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e1897a6-55f9-4f38-9ed2-5496ad4bbe9f"
msgid "\\\"Guards! I sentence Gasperre Liacenza to death. Take him!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50f8712f-f2d7-484b-97b4-9de1591db019"
msgid "Executed Stefano Moskoni."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72897b7d-d0de-4486-99da-c01c474b5307"
msgid "\\\"Guards! I sentence Stefano Moskoni to death. Take him!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dafa32ca-050e-4097-9b2d-dc7b3e5661c4"
msgid "\\\"Linzi, what's next on the agenda?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3d5ca6d1-91a1-47de-9ef3-02454cbfdbea"
msgid "\\\"Annamede, I appoint you as the new headmaster of the Academy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1da3991-2645-4c3c-a410-627e65bf5771"
msgid ""
"\\\"Atalia, I refuse to accept your resignation. The Academy needs a headmaster, "
"and you are the best candidate.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a795275-a596-4a27-8d40-4264a0c4ef24"
msgid "\\\"I will trust the teachers to elect a new headmaster of the Academy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63705059-0149-4d6d-becc-90bca6c02680"
msgid "\\\"No headmaster will be necessary. I am closing down the Academy.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c10287a0-3c1b-4017-9f56-01ebdb78d3e7"
msgid "Executed Atalia Gitaren."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fe767fe-7cc8-4ce6-be22-642395b54ba2"
msgid "\\\"Guards! I sentence Atalia Gitaren to be executed. Take her away!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d566e857-92e1-4b2d-a5e9-8316c315a055"
msgid "Executed Annamede Belavarah."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdfad339-1eb9-4e3a-97f6-ecbed7baea31"
msgid "\\\"Guards! I sentence Annamede Belavarah to be executed. Take her away!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3aaa4cd-3329-4ea3-b392-99d1d6398af4"
msgid "\\\"Who else wants an audience?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62542e91-79ca-431c-ad07-b32aa2d486d5"
msgid "Accepted the River Blades gang as your soldiers and made them give up piracy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2230904-e2b0-4778-b083-5da20946c520"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll hire you, but on one condition. No more robberies. From now on you're a "
"military combat unit within my army.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ab3afb2-2db7-4ee3-adb0-0436ee858b53"
msgid "Exiled the River Blades gang."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34656f50-8de9-485c-b1e0-aa459ccf1596"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for your service, but we have different paths to follow. I have no "
"need of pirates in my kingdom.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff9da9dc-845a-4620-97d1-32fbfa26e89c"
msgid "Executed Ilora Nuski."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a59134db-b928-4751-92cd-4f0b47f84baa"
msgid ""
"\\\"You've helped me, and I appreciate that. But you are pirates, and all pirates "
"must hang. Guards, take her away! Make sure she doesn't suffer.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55de04be-2f9b-4a99-80be-26d9f0f215d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"Aren't you confused? Why are you pledging allegiance to the city and not to me?"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f581b793-7428-45f2-b2e0-ae90dde83636"
msgid "\\\"I wish to appoint a new captain of the guard.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "873962a6-ecac-471f-9b63-400ba6e0cd3e"
msgid "\\\"I accept your pledge. Serve the city as you have before.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7518e3a6-b961-42d8-bd03-0f0c628da7ae"
msgid ""
"\\\"The city is now under new leadership. I will retire the city guard, and create "
"a new one, personally loyal to me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21eef6a9-f537-4408-8d2a-ab9ff92b83d5"
msgid "Executed Irsei Caelysse."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5035fafb-8f90-4346-899f-31f49c0d8c86"
msgid "\\\"Is that a threat? Guards! Arrest that man! I sentence him to death!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73bf5669-b28f-4493-a5cd-a3be0d4382f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I didn't ask for your advice. Have a good day, former captain Caelysse.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f9f5a747-1822-46a5-940e-8f33994851b1"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've changed my mind, and I accept your pledge. Continue to serve the city as "
"you always have.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e621042d-5644-4e73-9ffe-d2fedae2caf9"
msgid "Prevented Pitax's guards from throwing Kharne's guild out of the city."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5ff8cf4-4071-4c0f-80de-e154f4be807a"
msgid ""
"\\\"They are under my protection. Do not stand in the way of honest people doing "
"fair business.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea879729-8695-41e8-b8cb-7d898854258b"
msgid ""
"Acknowledged Kharne's right to continue his dealings in Pitax as long as he "
"doesn't disturb the peace."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "658fcdc0-a30d-4262-b3f8-db0031ea2fb6"
msgid "\\\"They have every right to do business unless they disturb the peace.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81fa2443-93c7-4592-ac0d-bcb4094497ef"
msgid "Allowed Pitax's guards to throw Kharne's guild out of the city."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73bec803-9853-42a4-9807-26a33f2d1a76"
msgid ""
"\\\"You can throw them out of the city. I won't lift a finger to protect that scum."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13e0f79f-2ca4-4eb2-bad1-304027eb7248"
msgid "Allowed Ilora Nuski to continue with piracy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "184357e9-f8a1-48e0-af86-d4a7233d0382"
msgid "\\\"You can continue in your usual work – just don't forget to share!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4d1e1268-badf-4f50-b1c5-7ec5a7544433"
msgid ""
"\\\"There is a whole delegation from {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} to see you! They're "
"standing by the doors, scowling at each other. It looks like they're about to come "
"to blows!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c66a844-3a4c-4ef1-bebc-875a4b33a444"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Liacenza}Gasperre Liacenza{/d} greets you with a polite bow.{/n} \\\"Your "
"Highness. The old families, founders of Pitax, are grateful to you for sparing us "
"of the usurper's tyranny. Allow us to assure you in our loyalty. None of the trade "
"houses seek the {g|Pitax}Pitaxian{/g} crown – which is rightfully yours, of "
"course. If it would please you to appoint a governor to oversee the city, all the "
"four families humbly recommend me for this position.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eaf85d75-1070-4f1c-b140-6e6d2a30ad50"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Vereel}Kharne Vereel{/d} stares at Gasperre with dim, bloodshot eyes.{/n} \\"
"\"Your Highness... Of course, it wasn't always peaceful between us. – The thieves' "
"guild used to fight against you a little... But that's all water under the bridge, "
"right? Irovetti's rule has ended, and the guild, represented by me, promises you "
"our support and a share of our profits. Speaking of profits... If you appoint me "
"as governor, then your share will make you gasp!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ad56887-ad6d-401b-bb96-9067ac5d9687"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Stefano}Stefano Moskoni{/d} makes an formal low bow, hiding his mischievous "
"smile.{/n} \\\"Well, justice was served. The usurper is dead, long live the "
"rightful ruler! If my recollection is correct, you mentioned our arrangement in "
"the square, before the whole city – something about the governor's position? I "
"have certainly upheld my end of the agreement. Now it's your turn.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "042eb050-6e72-4ac9-8bfe-30d15220ae56"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you for your trust. Allow me to pledge our allegiance once again – both "
"mine and that of all the old families.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23f88b10-8e05-4b6f-85e3-ce9939ec046a"
msgid "{n}Kharne grinds his teeth in anger.{/n} \\\"Is that so? Very well...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "687cfa61-afc6-490a-b8e9-8dbdf274afa2"
msgid "\\\"Well... At least allow me to thank you for sparing my life.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f4df3d20-4582-419e-9a42-ac44e9ff4132"
msgid ""
"{n}The gnome smiles and rubs his hands together.{/n} \\\"Sweet, sweet... You will "
"see, Your Highness, you've made no mistake!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e510afeb-69a1-405e-b559-f24e96aa46c7"
msgid ""
"{n}Gasperre lowers his head and speaks coldly through clenched teeth:{/n} \\\"As "
"Your Highness wishes.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce3bface-2e49-486b-a35d-ccbae1ed7699"
msgid ""
"{n}A broad smile blooms on Stefano's face. He bows to the floor again.{/n} \\"
"\"Thank you from all my heart, Your Highness! I won't let you down.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9162f68e-c6ea-43e8-a7fd-bfe6e662d962"
msgid ""
"\\\"Writing this down... I'll find someone suitable from the lords and ladies of "
"the court!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6339d506-c1c2-46be-b841-81febda4efb6"
msgid ""
"\\\"So, we've decided on the governor... Would you like to say anything to the "
"visitors or are they free to go? There's a whole crowd of them waiting in the hall!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "351e389d-880c-42e8-888c-7a4abe7e1581"
msgid ""
"\\\"A wise decision, Your Highness. The city will be safer and cleaner without him."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8cb5bb7f-c7fc-4dac-9f22-8d4795ea6be5"
msgid "\\\"Your Highness, but why?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27b5072e-0f6d-418f-ad8b-d39f642e850b"
msgid "\\\"That's the fate of all turncoats.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e524cced-32ec-41bf-b1f2-94906f10c50e"
msgid ""
"\\\"You won't get away with this – do you hear me?! The guild will find you! "
"You'll be weeping blood! You'll eat your own guts!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6700845a-ef7f-463b-8366-7ea64a89c170"
msgid "\\\"Ha ha... Serves him right!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "332ddbd4-365c-4f73-9c71-67012771bb69"
msgid "\\\"That fop should have hung a long time ago!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "265c243a-fd2d-447f-b3ba-5d80f248015b"
msgid ""
"\\\"So this is what your promises are worth?! I should have guessed, and fled "
"while I had the chance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0122175b-6f16-4829-a41e-c97fef74b3b4"
msgid "\\\"I see the old families are out of favor!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79a88d56-68e7-4a69-a457-753c9c0c3f52"
msgid "\\\"Farewell, Kharne Vereel. No one in Pitax will miss you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b89ae6e8-47dc-4217-b7d9-9eaf94e9a863"
msgid "\\\"You must decide the fate of the {g|Academy of Grand Arts}Academy{/g}!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "564a3381-6d34-4f65-9ef0-ce2b101e1a3c"
msgid "{n}The guards drag away the gnome, kicking and screaming.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b29c26bc-8028-4073-936b-e64c7d94d2d4"
msgid "{n}The guards take away Gasperre, who is as pale as a sheet.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64f5c416-31e0-423c-8825-e27b0b9d9715"
msgid ""
"{n}Stefano is escorted away by the guards, his chin pointed proudly skyward.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af8be305-06fb-4325-8e38-5e362e29fe80"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your Highness, {d|Atalia}I{/d} ask that you relieve me from my post as "
"headmaster of the {g|Academy of Grand Arts}Academy{/g}. After all that has "
"happened, I am hardly worthy of keeping it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c4eefec-3311-45ea-b00b-fab0bdb2641f"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Annamede}Annamede Belavarah{/d}, the most famous bard in all of {g|Pitax}"
"Pitax{/g}, gives you a charming smile.{/n} \\\"For the first time, I completely "
"agree with my respected colleague. And if you don't have another candidate for the "
"position, please allow me to offer my services!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5eb7aea0-e2ea-4ed5-bb84-bae032089d56"
msgid ""
"\\\"It appears we don't have any candidates for the role of {g|Academy of Grand "
"Arts}Academy{/g} headmaster... Why don't we then hold an election among the "
"teachers?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ef4b76d-a141-4134-9d8f-93c98e63ef6e"
msgid ""
"{n}Atalia looks down and quietly replies.{/n} \\\"As you wish, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5840bc9a-9594-46bd-bd97-ae4273ca6787"
msgid ""
"\\\"Well, I can't say I'm surprised. Lady Gitaren is not only competent, but also "
"extremely pliable, accommodating, and efficient! Let her serve you as diligently "
"as she served Irovetti!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4cbbffd2-418d-471b-8f4d-976a14d685f0"
msgid "\\\"Is that all? There is anyone else who can't wait to be seen?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "254e3157-d986-4984-af61-33509c542e69"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, Your Highness. Lady Belavarah, I wish you all success in your new "
"role, from the bottom of my heart.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7384986-5857-4aa7-a5f4-234d4a712efc"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you, Your Highness – it's a great honor! Apparently I was right about "
"you. I shan't disappoint you either, I promise.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2335ff7-cca5-4d41-89f2-5e31dd02f308"
msgid ""
"\\\"Really? Well, that's even better! Let some other candidates have their fair "
"chance.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97106c8c-7bc5-42ad-8850-390e7b716e14"
msgid "\\\"Thank you, Your Highness. That would indeed be the right thing to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17698c8c-a352-4b8d-91df-a37ffceaf209"
msgid "{n}Linzi's face becomes a little sad, but then she nods.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30afa466-441c-451f-a844-fc4039ab7d47"
msgid ""
"\\\"That's a big mistake, Your Highness. – An unforgivable mistake. Do you really "
"care nothing of how history will remember you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a93cca59-e784-4980-bb41-85304aa9a042"
msgid "\\\"It's a pity... But maybe it's the right thing to do.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "696bf48f-c95e-45a0-b169-caa9de74a04a"
msgid "{n}Atalia lowers her head.{/n} \\\"I... Deserve this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eaff3967-398c-4da0-86d2-77e07addd161"
msgid "{n}A blissful smile glows on Annamede's face.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5918de0-0650-4c11-af3b-070600cdaa50"
msgid "{n}Atalia falls limp and leaves with the guards.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f7e000bd-6a1a-4542-b012-144bc940e7fb"
msgid "\\\"What?! No! You wouldn't dare! For what?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e5671408-e3da-400c-a3ff-3a6cf76841fd"
msgid "{n}The guards take Annamede away, swearing and kicking.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e40c5c30-e3a2-4ee2-983d-9873dd456d96"
msgid ""
"\\\"What a wonderful decision! I'm sure the teachers will elect the most worthy "
"candidate from among themselves!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5bf32067-9a69-429a-b281-72ac297091f9"
msgid "{n}Linzi covers her face and turns away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9d2629ea-8ff4-4b53-9f19-e41d459e5586"
msgid "\\\"Well, we're done with the guards. Who else is left...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c143f89-26ac-43af-9fb1-f0562bba0cc7"
msgid "\\\"Ah, yes! {d|Ilora}Ilora Nuski{/d} and her River Razors!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58ded152-9f2d-4b6e-8240-3328b9c5a462"
msgid ""
"\\\"No one else. Well, what a day! I see it's not easy to rule. I'd rather break "
"up a pack of wyverns than live through another day like this!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca8e0c59-747e-48bb-a4e2-2a6889acb35f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Hello, Your Highness! Well, I'm... What's next? To be honest, my fellows and I "
"got so much loot storming the palace that we could live in comfort to a ripe old "
"age. – But I think it's still a little early for us to retire. Will you hire us to "
"serve you? We've shown ourselves in battle, and we promise to serve you faithfully "
"and loyally!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "301f1072-f8b9-4856-bbc2-db3af14f3a8d"
msgid "\\\"It's a deal! Oh, I mean, at your orders, Your Highness!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e6f37ccc-7888-4a95-a4c0-59b4dd50bb47"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes, yes, how could I expect anything else? Very well, no hard feelings. "
"Goodbye and good luck!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72ffd689-5961-48c4-9a80-b9d31ccce6f1"
msgid ""
"\\\"What?! But I... You scum! Damn you! You and your whole blasted kingdom!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa8aa4c0-7263-4d7a-b4d4-be106b38fddf"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ha ha! As you wish, Your Highness! And don't you worry, you'll be getting your "
"share on time!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4d5604d2-1b88-4008-9f24-01c36a6f2102"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Vereel}Kharne Vereel{/d} stares at Gasperre with dim, bloodshot eyes.{/n} \\"
"\"Your Highness... I think the thieves' guild fully proved its loyalty, by "
"supporting you against Irovetti. We promise you our complete support – and a share "
"of our profits, of course. If you appoint me as governor, your cut of the profits "
"will leave you gasping!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32f6eacf-1a33-4f14-9a9e-bcae3a26fedd"
msgid ""
"{n}{d|Annamede}Annamede{/d} bows gracefully and gives you a charming smile.{/n} \\"
"\"Congratulations, Your Highness. {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} is at your feet – and as "
"promised, I {d|c51 Annamede Help}contributed{/d} to your victory. Now it's your "
"turn – will you hold up your end of our arrangement?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68d39739-0bad-4753-9496-a10a49ecf489"
msgid ""
"\\\"Because that's the order, as set by the first kings of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}. The "
"city guard has always served as a counter-balance to the trade houses – even "
"whichever one presently holds the crown. We exist to guard the city's peace and "
"prevent a bloody power struggle. That's why we answer not to the king, but to the "
"people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e993a93a-69e5-4b1d-acf0-3f6c35028978"
msgid ""
"{n}Annamede listens to your words with a crooked smirk.{/n} \\\"Well, I can't say "
"I'm surprised. This is the last time I take a job without being paid up front.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f82e685a-accf-4c6e-b6c5-51a8527efd69"
msgid ""
"\\\"Irsei Caelysse, captain of the guard, comes to pledge allegiance to his {mf|"
"King|Queen}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8bd827de-12bf-46ee-9ca7-d5805eb5b716"
msgid ""
"{n}Irsei Caelysse greets you with a reserved bow.{/n} \\\"Your Highness. According "
"to the traditions set forth by the first kings of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}, I have come "
"to pledge my allegiance to the city and its citizens, before you and the crown. I "
"shall serve Pitax faithfully and loyally, to my dying breath, and guard the peace "
"of its streets.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "191ff08c-d16c-40bc-a2a3-7fcbeb6c2b3d"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is impossible, Your Highness. The captain of the guard is elected by the "
"citizens, from candidates proposed by the officers. – And only officers of the "
"guard can demote him. This was the arrangement set forth by the first kings – "
"expressly to protect the guard's role.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "efed4926-0f34-47f8-8b97-e98c6bdd765d"
msgid "\\\"Thank you, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f70d6508-cb16-4a97-9124-f855bbded8a5"
msgid "\\\"This is a rash decision, Your Highness. It may cause civil unrest.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7f84de2-8a7c-4e7e-b51e-7741d4188c22"
msgid ""
"\\\"I admit it won't be easy with this new governor... But the city has been "
"through worse. We'll be fine.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1ce93f4-6fdb-45c8-8013-47541010abd6"
msgid ""
"\\\"I must say, now that you so wisely spared the city of that scoundrel Kharne "
"Vereel, it will be much easier to keep order.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f529de95-539b-49e2-a384-24ae80ffb9ab"
msgid ""
"\\\"I admit, your choice of business {d|c51 Drugs Kingdom}partners{/d} won't make "
"our job any easier... But the city has been through worse. We'll be all right.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "506957c2-f5d3-45ef-8bf0-ca6d68f40c9f"
msgid ""
"\\\"Allow me to ask you something. How do you feel about Kharne Vereel's so-called "
"thieves' guild – dealers who, under Irovetti, flooded the city with {g|Numeria}"
"Numerian{/g} drugs?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73846658-c6f3-48b3-ab44-00d696d76664"
msgid "Broke the promise given to Irsei Caelysse."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f253ea77-72f5-4ac7-aae8-d4bef388a5ae"
msgid ""
"\\\"This is not what we arranged before the battle... But I can't say I'm "
"surprised.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a9d51e82-b8f0-4e27-ba43-78f918bb4906"
msgid ""
"\\\"Very well, I shall take my leave.\\\" {n}Saluting you, Irsei Caelysse leaves "
"the throne room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9eb83482-161c-48cc-97c6-738265896800"
msgid "Fulfilled the promise given to Irsei Caelysse."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f191fa6-d28c-464f-ac49-70665b57d244"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's good to see that the new {mf|King|Queen} is a {mf|man|woman} of honor, "
"and {mf|his|her} {d|c51 Irsei Help}promises{/d} are worth something.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a6be490-8eff-436c-8b29-0a939674b079"
msgid ""
"{n}Pursing his lips, Irsei looks you right in the eye.{/n} \\\"I understand, Your "
"Royal Highness. It appears that not much will change in the city, despite the "
"change of ruler.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d8efc8c-70f2-434f-9149-5e65c3bf7fc5"
msgid ""
"{n}Irsei nods, and something remotely resembling a smile shows on his stern face.{/"
"n} \\\"Thank you, Your Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "387eb86a-9a57-4bf5-918b-70f24a3650fd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Really? And I thought that {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} had its worst days under "
"Irovetti. Those times will soon seem our golden age...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a39e517-a845-445a-9325-4128eaad0679"
msgid "{n}Measuring his pace, Irsei Caelysse leaves, accompanied by the guard.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4e043c1-4df3-44e9-a3f7-d2519d5bf528"
msgid "{n}With a gap-toothed grin, Ilora leaves the throne room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2100af20-86ae-459e-ac37-9da67f16ab91"
msgid "{n}The guards take Ilora away, paying no heed to her screams and curses.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af5e972a-c987-4fcd-982b-5b5f08396638"
msgid ""
"{n}The gnome smiles and rubs his hands together.{/n} \\\"Sweet, yes... There, back "
"in Pitax, you made some promises, Your Highness. Good promises, yes. I'll send my "
"people to work out the details of our deal, heh heh.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e4edc24-6a07-4014-827d-c24cb47fdcd5"
msgid ""
"\\\"You shouldn't have disbanded the guard. Can you imagine what'll happen to the "
"city without it? Oh, my poor old Pitax!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a32faca-0007-4f12-b326-54c420bf4971"
msgid ""
"\\\"You returned the city to the old Trade Houses. Frankly, under all the velvet "
"clothes and pretty words, they were just plain old bandits — but old and familiar "
"ones, at least. I guess Pitax will soon go back to what it was like before "
"Irovetti!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64a051e4-3b9c-4d15-a9a6-ae3c402c1f10"
msgid ""
"\\\"The old Trade Houses are through. I won't cry for them: under all the velvet "
"clothes and pretty words, they were just plain old bandits. You took the city away "
"from them and gave it to... Well, some new bandits, I guess? I wonder how it'll "
"change the face of Pitax!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c222d76-9757-4355-b8d2-9fd9de08f065"
msgid "\\\"I wonder: what will happen to the city now?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6bf03c3-77d7-4516-ac43-31d8e2baff23"
msgid "\\\"Very well... Tell Irovetti that I'm coming.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8aa836d0-1284-4329-9513-92a4732b9023"
msgid "\\\"He can wait for as long as he likes. He's not getting my crown.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97dca0ed-ef4c-478f-ac50-e062a9033e55"
msgid "Sent Stefano Moskoni's head to Irovetti as a message."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a82edf6-b835-48fe-8c8c-70b17d826eb6"
msgid "\\\"Guards! Take him. Send his head to Irovetti as our reply!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c5595806-26fa-41cd-9140-97e690244138"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am not keeping up with my responsibilities?! Don't be absurd! You know full "
"well that the disasters that fell upon my lands were the work of Irovetti himself!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b0cb525-6258-4119-aff4-898f89a7386e"
msgid ""
"{n}Stefano Moskoni is wearing particularly splendid attire for his visit. His "
"doublet is embroidered with precious stones, and decorated with the emblem of {g|"
"Pitax}Pitax{/g}. A disdainful smile is plastered on his powdered face. He bows "
"formally.{/n} \\\"Your Highness! I am here on behalf of His Highness Irovetti of "
"Pitax.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa6d9cd0-ce8c-427a-80a5-7c3105801673"
msgid ""
"\\\"I will pass your words to His Highness... But wouldn't it be wiser to accept a "
"helping hand while your country can yet be saved? Think about it.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a2c46ab-a99f-4542-8e64-a99462196238"
msgid "\\\"His Highness is expecting you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "227de27e-dca4-4d03-87e5-93edb12477c6"
msgid "{n}Your guards disarm the screaming Moskoni and drag him away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8b921471-4159-47e0-8adc-29467d99320a"
msgid ""
"{n}The man who enters the throne room apparently spends a great deal of time and "
"effort on his appearance. His face is powdered, his hair and foppish mustache are "
"generously slicked, and his doublet is embroidered with precious stones and "
"decorated with the emblem of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}. He bows formally.{/n} \\\"Allow "
"me to introduce myself. I am Stefano Moskoni, ambassador of His Royal Highness "
"Irovetti of Pitax.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4a6e77e-64dd-47fc-b663-4ef69ad50e94"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is an open secret that things are not going too well for your kingdom of "
"late. Bandits and monsters, which you supposedly exterminated, are swarming your "
"countryside once more. You are losing the trust and respect of your subjects. "
"Everyone sees that you are failing meet the responsibilities of a proper ruler. – "
"It's just that not everyone dares to say this out loud.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d401a9e9-e230-4db6-a621-fbcb4f682666"
msgid ""
"\\\"His Highness Irovetti is ready to lend you a helping hand. Reject this "
"unbearable burden of power, kneel to him and abdicate the crown. He will rule the "
"{g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} as wisely and fairly as he rules his own country. "
"His Highness is expecting you at his palace in {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}, ready to accept "
"your oath.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e90f2c50-beb3-481f-ab36-d3f4e9c5de87"
msgid ""
"{n}Moskoni smiles contentedly.{/n} \\\"This is slander, Your Highness. My King is "
"famous for his wisdom and fairness. – How could he have woven such a plot?! It is "
"beyond belief!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8645c396-bc21-4d3f-ab6f-fbeee28cbdf7"
msgid "{n}With a low bow, Moskoni leaves the throne room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "deec56c6-fdf7-4668-8b66-12df8f88512f"
msgid "Sent the head of Irovetti's messenger back to him as a message."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "972b34ac-8134-4139-89f7-3b34c4eaf927"
msgid "\\\"Guards! Take her. Send her head to Irovetti as our reply!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35e1dbb5-36ee-4056-838b-6672e387c349"
msgid ""
"{n}The emblem of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} glistens on the messenger's chest. She stands "
"proudly and speaks her words bold and clear:{/n} \\\"Your Highness, {Name} the "
"First! I have a message for you from Irovetti, King of Pitax.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b55cb268-3e6a-47d9-9900-ae48eb707e6b"
msgid "{n}Your guards disarm the screaming messenger and drag her away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7640827-a023-497b-8e90-9067b6c5abc2"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am sorry, Your Highness, but I do not have authority to negotiate. I was "
"only vested with the task of delivering my King's message and receiving your reply."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51504f61-224b-438b-842d-b342b8f2a9ce"
msgid "\\\"I will pass your words to His Highness.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bff25da6-9517-4eed-b3fb-01ee6a5a5543"
msgid "{n}After a low bow, the messenger leaves the throne room.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c02e8749-3237-48b8-8f16-3983763aee27"
msgid "\\\"Hello. Why are you here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68ae1d3f-617a-44bb-8f7a-65aabab49525"
msgid "\\\"Get lost, Nyrissa. We have nothing to talk about.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40e859a6-d94f-4602-b5fa-932f517e10d9"
msgid "\\\"You're trying to say that you love me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6eaec577-8e29-4c61-a666-727ec4290352"
msgid "\\\"That's enough. You're my enemy. I don't care about your feelings.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0e6c8e4-c5f9-46b8-804b-9793ee57347b"
msgid ""
"\\\"What if I'm ready to sacrifice the kingdom for you? Take it, it's yours. Let "
"the grain fall into the cup.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ebe0eaf7-f2e9-45cb-aa85-b3391d2fe415"
msgid ""
"\\\"I am sorry that everything turned out like this. I care about you, but I can't "
"let you destroy my kingdom.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7644727-8d36-40f4-a135-94485d5b506b"
msgid ""
"\\\"You've broken into my dream. Now it's my turn to enter yours,\\\" {n}Nyrissa "
"says in lieu of a greeting. You feel the air trembling around you, like in the "
"short moment of still calmness preceding the storm.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f358b6ca-4693-404d-8bac-b1cb6732ed53"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've come to say goodbye. If we meet again, it will be a meeting of sworn "
"enemies on the battlefield.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc7542b8-65cd-4f44-a7f3-2442e5bf4fa7"
msgid ""
"\\\"How sad, the fate of daring souls...\\\" {n}The nymph speaks in a singsong "
"voice.{/n} \\\"There are paths that cannot be strayed from, and words that best "
"remain unspoken. I've come to say goodbye. So I'm doing it now. The only thing our "
"next meeting will bring is death.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e95354e1-68bc-4e4b-b619-0862db059f99"
msgid ""
"\\\"I cannot love,\\\" {n}says Nyrissa in a cold and even tone.{/n} \\\"The very "
"essence was ripped from my soul and lost. But when I speak with you, when I watch "
"you facing unthinkable threats, the hole in my soul bleeds, and hurts more than "
"ever.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "00917bc3-6c3d-488e-91d3-7fa8172ee660"
msgid ""
"\\\"Do you remember the first time we met? I came to you, disguised as the former "
"Nyrissa, a tender young nymph who hadn't yet spent ages under the yoke of her "
"curse. Deceiving comes easier if your lies are familiar to you. But it seems that "
"I've played myself into a corner. Your words brought me pain. They were like sharp "
"thorns sprouting through my skin. You made me recall who I once was... and who I "
"would never be again. Now, when the end is near, I feel... anxiety. It seems it's "
"no coincidence that the last step to forgiveness must be the only death I could "
"care about.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0bfd36c1-5d11-4100-a1a4-8da8387a2702"
msgid ""
"{n}It seems you've managed to surprise the nymph. But her surprise is laced with "
"contempt.{/n} \\\"So that's how you talk.... Well, if you wish to please me so "
"much, just let the peacock finish what he started and destroy your country. But "
"you have surprised me, truly. I didn't expect you to back down so easily. Looks "
"like I was wrong to cry about that missing part of my soul. What's the good in "
"softness and unconditional self-sacrifice, if it makes you pathetic and weak?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88bca6f6-6f8d-4e46-acac-a532852a3c21"
msgid ""
"\\\"I know. Long ago, I refused to back down when the {g|Eldest}Eldest{/g} sent "
"the beast to destroy me and my realm. You and I are similar in that... maybe "
"that's why I... well, never mind. Farewell. Our next meeting, if it happens, will "
"be a very different one — much more bloody and violent, I would expect.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "60cddb3c-56d7-4602-884a-4f3f0e7aaf60"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, could I ever expect some other answer? You have every right to say so.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "320c0a40-6312-45a4-8b33-d8ce0cabe425"
msgid ""
"{n}You seem to hear thunder rumble in the distance. The nymph turns to leave, but "
"suddenly raises her eyes to you and speaks again:{/n} \\\"Do you know why I "
"couldn't immediately recognize the intrusion, when you and the foolish little "
"robin bard broke into my dreams?\\nBecause it wasn't the first time I dreamt of "
"you, {name}.\\\"\\n{n}With these words, the nymph's silhouette dissolves into thin "
"air.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a1ade48-14dc-4e7b-b739-de6ee057121c"
msgid ""
"{n}Nyrissa gives you a harsh smile.{/n} \\\"Thank you, my hound. I feel I am "
"finally rid of all doubt, and all of that excruciating, debilitating weakness. "
"Farewell!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4d5395b-5394-4e6c-965e-963843127d0b"
msgid "\\\"What do we know of the Thousand Voices and what awaits us there?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16449738-3851-4337-b467-3865a2b20133"
msgid "\\\"Will you travel with us, Evindra?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "df732161-2412-4b7a-a693-18b3941d8e52"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nyrissa has tormented my kingdom and all of the Stolen Lands for too long. "
"It's our turn now!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1af38292-20d2-458a-bd4b-6e811a6a0f9a"
msgid ""
"{n}Your comrades and advisors are gathered around the throne in breathless "
"silence. Linzi is the first to dare speak.{/n} \\\"I guess... I guess... it's "
"about time my book reached its culmination! Or... its finale...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "835c31db-b007-4205-8c0b-edc185cfa1c0"
msgid ""
"\\\"It is a time of great woe — but of great hope as well. The path to the {g|"
"First World}First World{/g} is open. This is your chance to reach my fallen sister "
"and settle your dispute over the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} once and for all."
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13328cfd-f3f4-4090-88ad-1dbface134b1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nyrissa, huh? I've been itching to tear the petals off that flower for quite a "
"while!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a25e5c31-3a15-4ffb-a9bb-86c2cb24bd0a"
msgid ""
"\\\"A ruler's duty is to end their kingdom's afflictions. And our duty is to "
"follow you, {name}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "619623d1-ce31-4623-8054-e13ba00cb644"
msgid ""
"\\\"Seems we have a promising expedition to the depths of the {g|First World}First "
"World{/g} ahead of us. If in the course of our research we render a dozen monsters "
"and one particularly annoying nymph to compost — all the better.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1fb4b98-0e88-4592-bbc6-325bbd0ee2dd"
msgid ""
"\\\"I've helped Nyrissa move between planes and portals long enough to assume "
"there must be a door in the {g|Thousand Voices Forest}Thousand Voices{/g} that "
"leads to her own demesne in the {g|First World}First World{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb8d54dd-d18b-4d6a-9038-bdaf55d6a03b"
msgid ""
"\\\"The time has come to end the thousand-year reign of evil over the {g|Stolen "
"Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}. And I as much as anyone wish to help — and hopefully help "
"repay my debts in the process.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86291fe4-dec9-4a89-a90d-bf99087797cc"
msgid ""
"\\\"It's all in our hands now! The threat may be great, but you've been fighting "
"Nyrissa for a long time now, {name}. You have the best chance of stopping her once "
"and for all.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f2ab291-2da7-4374-afc3-88e242bbd15e"
msgid ""
"\\\"Nyrissa is an interesting foe — powerful, beautiful, and unburdened by boring "
"principles or morals. I can't wait to wade through her blooming meadows with a "
"scythe.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91e0ebdd-ea7d-4a7e-86fa-c92a84e496e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Yes! That green creep's hunted us for too long — time to trade places.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "740f8090-ed27-47f0-ba91-9c33a75aa15f"
msgid "\\\"The end times near. My heart rejoices.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7af253f7-ffdc-44e1-8f3a-bbae1fff5e94"
msgid ""
"\\\"Trouble at the gates of peaceful villages. I hear the cries of children, "
"prayers for help, as though there were right here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1ad1fb2-2833-4f50-96b6-c21f2afe2ff8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Linzi again with her big bag of words — and as helpful as ever. I know what to "
"do — go kick that green witch's ass! Bam! She's gone, and we're heroes!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85e9d519-0f73-4c75-8406-94bd9d0cb373"
msgid ""
"\\\"Messengers have arrived from... well... all over the kingdom, really! The "
"Bloom has started everywhere. Monsters have appeared in every forest, behind every "
"corner, in every nook and cranny! What we went through before was like a bed of "
"roses compared to this. If we don't do something, the kingdom will simply... "
"collapse.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1c79b02-8d7e-4b9c-988b-2a296ffec2c5"
msgid ""
"\\\"We learned a lot about Nyrissa while traveling through her dreams. I think "
"she's almost done gathering grains of dust for her damn cup. {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g} "
"has fallen, and your kingdom is the last thing standing in the way of her "
"'Apology.' She's done waiting. We need to do something — and fast! I think... I "
"think we need to head out on our most heroic campaign yet. We talked it over, and "
"it seems like our best chance to reach Nyrissa is through the {g|Thousand Voices "
"region}Thousand Voices{/g}, on the western border of Pitax. It's been completely "
"overtaken by the Bloom, and it seems to be the place where the {g|First World}"
"First World{/g} is currently the closest to ours!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c77a3e58-ac2d-4cb7-916b-8517e74973e3"
msgid ""
"\\\"One thing is clear — it won't be easy! Not for us, or for the kingdom. I... "
"hope something's left to celebrate our... heroic return to...\\\" {n}Linzi hides a "
"sniffle by pretending to rub her nose.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f89692fe-5bc9-4068-b970-3c475b0f52b0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Many beasts serve Nyrissa — and you would be hard-pressed to find more "
"dangerous ones. She has even created some semblance of one of the Tane, the {g|"
"Eldest}Eldest's{/g} chained beasts. You must prepare to meet all these monsters "
"along your way, either in the {g|Thousand Voices region}Thousand Voices{/g}, or in "
"the {g|First World}First World{/g}, should we make it there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2f6f7b1-e2ad-46a2-a314-3a5a111194fe"
msgid ""
"{n}The nereid closes her eyes and sighs softly.{/n} \\\"Yes. Of course. My duty "
"now is to fight the evil that has enslaved Nyrissa. But I will not be traveling in "
"the typical way with you. You are aware that creatures of the {g|First World}First "
"World{/g} return to life in their homeland if they die somewhere the Bloom is "
"especially strong, yes? I'll find such a place and... end my life there, thus "
"returning to the First World. I will meet you there. This way, I'll be able to "
"bypass the portal guards, learn more of Nyrissa's plans, make preparations. Death "
"is not a pleasant prospect, and it will take much of my strength... but it could "
"give us a significant advantage. Take care. And wish me luck.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "183e04d6-4f3f-4a28-bea5-136b5c8b3a8a"
msgid ""
"\\\"We'll be fine! We'll return and throw a huge feast — and we'll celebrate for a "
"whole month, and then another month, and then on the next month, we'll just do "
"nothing but rest! I'll finish my book, and they'll read it all across {g|Golarion}"
"Golarion{/g}, and... and... {n}Linzi gestures vaguely.{/n} \\\"I don't know what "
"then, but it'll be even better!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f152f6b-080d-4a04-8998-63a1592a8094"
msgid ""
"\\\"Everyone's so serious! Pff! Let me put it simply – we need to do some "
"housekeeping. Cut some lawns, burn some fallen leaves – and get rid of some "
"vermin. Ha ha!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6d0f35cd-aa25-4231-a80a-deb85812c1fd"
msgid ""
"\\\"I always thought that evil was ugly and cold. And yet right in front of me, "
"the incredible beauty of the First World is bringing chaos and death to our "
"peaceful lands. Well, we'll stand in its way and hold it back, whatever it takes.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21247271-907e-4c01-9511-1090fb9dafd3"
msgid "\\\"Who are you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa3cef14-1ed0-4b11-bcc9-4cc01f1204e9"
msgid "\\\"Tell me about those who tricked you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e04cbec-ba42-42da-b6b4-c813c350e3ad"
msgid ""
"\\\"You don't seem like a local. Why would you keep these possessions of yours on "
"the island in the middle of Candlemere Lake?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba53a5b5-da85-4f1d-81c7-67aff8f79096"
msgid "\\\"Fine, I'll try to figure it out.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5b513ac-b1d0-4900-b514-a6de3a384764"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'll need someone to show me the way. Would you go to the island with me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f9c9f78-7c5a-4766-b402-3ce36e51d6d4"
msgid "\\\"This whole story sounds strange. I don't really want to get involved.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64d0a178-eb11-478e-926e-9fff4a89e148"
msgid ""
"\\\"I visited the cursed island. It's swarming with monsters, the whole crew is "
"dead, and the ruins are empty — except for some ancient magic in the tower walls.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d2115fe-cccd-4f07-a592-93b58e044f92"
msgid "\\\"I have to go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b45f2b3-f190-4108-90e9-b8d929d8084d"
msgid "\\\"Can you tell me more about them?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1d69901a-9d77-4017-a1d0-7327a3e774e6"
msgid ""
"\\\"A paladin and a cleric who willingly took a job running errands for you? "
"Sounds strange, if you ask me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "60e5edaa-199f-48f3-abf8-784978dc683c"
msgid "\\\"Let's go back to my other questions.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6d914a3-f659-4e09-b484-8786b389eba9"
msgid "\\\"Which deity was this temple dedicated to?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3d11688a-042c-430b-854a-e536c2cfec4b"
msgid ""
"\\\"Correct me if I'm wrong, but you believe that some sacred relics from the "
"temple of an unknown deity belong to you? By what right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f484b75-3fe6-4803-908a-7bc3a94e60d7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Someone offered sacrifices there — and I suppose we're not talking about "
"animal sacrifices?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8fb2d6a3-df30-4cd7-bb51-a1a5d9107933"
msgid "\\\"What ghostly lights are you talking about?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1c2a9c36-c857-4e9f-af67-dd3224f698a9"
msgid ""
"\\\"You mentioned a flash of light over the ruins. Did you see it with your own "
"eyes, or just hear about it from someone else?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb72df85-7823-4eeb-ac9d-4761250b9a5d"
msgid "\\\"I guess that's all I need to know about the island.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c0d726ac-5456-447c-8ca7-36922895158f"
msgid "Confirmed the curse of Candlemere's island as the result of past evil deeds."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8c22472-0bf3-46a5-a485-301af92c5fcb"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course, it exists. This island has seen too much sorrow and suffering — now "
"any living creature who sets a foot there is doomed. The locals should stay away "
"from the place to avoid the dormant evil within the tower.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e4387c4-8de2-431e-bda7-b8eec7e3ce00"
msgid ""
"Denied the existence of the curse on Candlemere's island, which can affect a "
"person's destiny."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d29a5b85-7d6f-40b6-b2e8-3515c9dea856"
msgid ""
"\\\"There is no curse. Bad things just happen to people sometimes — it's as simple "
"as that. These three went somewhere dangerous and failed to overcome its dangers. "
"It's sad, but hardly supernatural.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0be65f7f-cbd8-4bba-903e-436326d18836"
msgid ""
"\\\"You know, it just occurred to me... You sent those poor sods to the island, "
"right? So it was you who doomed them and sent them to certain death — and then you "
"sent me there, as well. So now I'll have to spend my own resources paying for a "
"purification ritual, and you're just going to leave like nothing happened?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d411a5c0-a79e-44cf-8f6b-56cf528788b4"
msgid ""
"\\\"I visited the cursed island. It swarms with monsters, the ranger and the "
"paladin are dead, and the cleric of Nethys left in voluntary exile. The ruins are "
"completely empty — no treasures.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd7a12de-a77f-4d26-a06d-6c60b40d4b93"
msgid "Scoffed at the ill fate of the explorers on Candlemere's island."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "05debc84-17e0-4d92-9bde-23d24d9fb967"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why should I care? Three idiots dead, end of story. What about my reward?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77b87f12-f41c-49a8-a456-a80250b5f416"
msgid ""
"Declared to Willas Gunderson that destiny, fate, and curses have no hold over a "
"person's life."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eed6bace-32e7-4013-a67e-99f0f9cc5c86"
msgid ""
"\\\"Whether it exists or not — are you going to spout nonsense about fate and doom "
"now? The world's full of strange things, and looking for logic and consistency is "
"a waste of time — people just do what they like. Some people sacrifice victims on "
"an altar, others search for treasure among ruins, and some just grow sick and "
"tired of listening to some boring idiot — so let's switch topics to something more "
"interesting, like the reward for my work.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49ef5003-d97d-4c7e-bce7-5eb905101687"
msgid ""
"{n}A plump man in his thirties approaches you. His hair's untidy, road dust covers "
"his worn clothes, and his boots have seen better days. The stranger speaks to you "
"in unusually high-pitched voice.{/n} \\\"Your Grace! I demand justice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ee65b1a-9cb2-42c1-ac5e-888bf317c4ef"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas raises his eyes, and his face lights up.{/n} \\\"{mf|My baron|My "
"baroness}! Have you changed your mind?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1fbbea69-83bf-4c80-a8b7-f0bd3639c669"
msgid ""
"\\\"Crime in the barony is on the rise!\\\" {n}The man shakes his clenched fists, "
"then drops his hands helplessly.{/n} \\\"In open daylight I was tricked, robbed, "
"and if that weren't enough, humiliated!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4bbff448-8323-4d0e-9098-93c4558c58ed"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas raises his head and gives you a nervous smile.{/n} \\\"{mf|My baron|My "
"baroness}! I was waiting for you! Any news?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85849c63-4867-4c9c-b4a9-0fce96556564"
msgid ""
"\\\"A gang of local thugs tricked me into trusting them. They found out about my "
"possessions and disappeared with my treasures! I sent them to the island on {g|"
"Candlemere}Candlemere{/g} three days ago, and they just vanished into thin air!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2d29cb3-56ba-4fac-a14d-2d6515c6f13d"
msgid ""
"\\\"I beg you — find these scoundrels and retrieve my treasure! I'll pay a "
"handsome sum to be sure these villains are brought to justice!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d26a042-e884-43f1-b248-4e7680579815"
msgid ""
"\\\"Willas Gunderson, Your Grace! I'm a scientist, an explorer, an adventurer, and "
"a renowned expert in treasures and artifacts of virtually every era and culture.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61d63a6c-cc34-4ea2-88c0-04bfd4e759e5"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost eyes Willas up and down.{/n} \\\"So many titles for a single piece of "
"mediocrity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "860abbfa-142a-40d9-9491-cac5079e6e09"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas blushes and pretends that he just noticed the gnome.{/n} \\\"S-sir "
"Narthropple! Y-you're here! What a nice s-surprise!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d1dc5c43-57be-4cbe-9a37-7c6e522a399d"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh really? In case you hadn't noticed, I've been here from the start. Or "
"perhaps after the open lecture in the Forae Logos in {g|Absalom}Absalom{/g}, "
"you've lost not only the rest of your mind, but also your eyesight?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8e563c3-6b6c-4c4d-bce1-e3996bdd1f86"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas straightens his jacket indignantly and lifts his chin.{/n} \\\"I see "
"your manners haven't improved since last we met! Well, happily, I no longer "
"consider you the beacon of knowledge you once were. You can joke however you like "
"— I'm above such discourse!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0a943408-cca5-4632-82ac-0980b49308a0"
msgid ""
"{n}Jubilost grins.{/n} \\\"The only thing that puts you above me is your size, "
"Willas. And even that isn't so impressive for a human.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46ec9ec2-f7e3-406b-8cc7-88c868e7ad19"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas face turns dark red and his eye starts to twitch. Pressing his lips "
"tightly he turns back to you.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "022797fb-6d62-4d2f-9837-fafa36390e72"
msgid ""
"\\\"They were a trio I hired to retrieve my possessions from {g|Candlemere}"
"Candlemere{/g}'s island turned out to be a bunch of tricksters. You must know the "
"place — in the center of the lake, with the ancient temple ruins. So they took my "
"money, jumped into the boat, and — whoosh! — gone with the wind. So many days have "
"passed, and not a single word from them! And they had the nerve to call themselves "
"a paladin and a cleric! Scum is what they really are!\\\" {n}Willas stamps the "
"ground in anger.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f21a5fd7-e623-49f4-969a-ef9ddeee527d"
msgid ""
"\\\"A ranger, a paladin of {g|Irori}Irori{/g}, and a cleric of {g|Nethys}Nethys{/"
"g} — you know, that two-faced god. Frankly speaking, that one gave me creeps from "
"the very beginning — half of those servants of Nethys are real psychos. Today they "
"agree to help you, and tomorrow they change their minds at the drop of a hat. And "
"this one played his tricks on me, too.\\\" {n}Willas sighs.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b74deaa7-85bb-40aa-b640-91dcebc569d3"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas mulls over your words for some time.{/n} \\\"You know, Your Grace... "
"When I mentioned the old temple, they exchanged a glance — like I was talking "
"about some hidden treasure... I was such a fool! I should have realized from the "
"start that they had their own agenda!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ade20e50-489b-47ed-983b-9bcae567cead"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas bites his lip, as if caught doing something wrong.{/n} \\\"Well... "
"ahem... You see, these aren't EXACTLY my possessions right now. It's just... I "
"learned from the locals about the ruins of an ancient temple on the island. And "
"everyone knows, where there's a temple, there's always the hope of some treasure.\\"
"\" {n}Willas rubs his palms.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6b0aae3-0345-4d61-8d93-dd5b159c53c8"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas looks around, scared.{/n} \\\"Wait, me? Come with you? No way! Three "
"armed men went and never came back! And I can't even swing a sword, or cast the "
"simplest spell... Oh no, You Grace, you'll need to find someone more experienced "
"for that!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fcbed2a1-f646-4946-83f4-d48f8581c08d"
msgid "\\\"As you wish — whatever you need to catch these thieves!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2aba5381-cbd6-4ab5-a7c3-9826a5a60a95"
msgid ""
"\\\"Who cares...\\\" {n}Willas interrupts himself and sighs.{/n} \\\"I don't know! "
"I never asked! All I heard is that long ago the locals used to perform some "
"rituals there, dedicated to some ancient deity.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c771f3d9-e311-4474-826f-7fbc5b68d275"
msgid ""
"\\\"By the right of finding! I dug up all the stories about the temple! I hired "
"the crew! I pointed out where to start the search! Besides, no harm done. No one "
"ever really goes there anyway — there aren't many volunteers willing to visit a "
"cursed island!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0d60e57-ab1c-4a75-b39e-b4672a6d363f"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas shrugs reluctantly.{/n} \\\"The locals say… things… Something about that "
"being why the place is cursed.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "153e73dc-2108-483a-9fbc-bd13e7f7b3bc"
msgid ""
"\\\"The lights were strange, you know?\\\" {n}Willas frowns, as if recalling "
"something.{/n} \\\"They were brighter than fireflies, and different colors. You "
"can see them even from the shore. During the day, they're barely visible, but at "
"night... People say they're the restless souls of those who met their deaths on "
"the island.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1fac804-07db-4ff8-9845-19364ee87f9b"
msgid ""
"\\\"I saw it with my own eyes, and just recently! Almost blinded me — like half "
"the island suddenly burst into flames! When the locals saw it, they fell to their "
"knees and started to pray — they said that the old god had returned.\\\" {n}Willas "
"scoffs.{/n} \\\"Dimwits — what else would you expect from them.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dfc1286a-a3ba-4e6a-9882-d244a899eebe"
msgid "\\\"Whatever you say, {mf|my baron|my baroness}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f44a9a06-66bc-40a9-90f3-f6b9d43fc0d2"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas sighs, relieved.{/n} \\\"Praise {g|Desna}Desna{/g}! Don't let those "
"scoundrels leave with my treasure!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "738ae8a0-308a-4f8c-b41b-080f787ec3e8"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas's jaw drops in surprise — it seems he was sure you'd help him. After a "
"moment, his face falls, almost like that of a wronged child.{/n} \\\"{mf|My baron|"
"My baroness}! Don't turn away from my pleas! Don't leave me helpless! I have no "
"one here — no friends or relatives! Your Grace is my only hope!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73330c8d-7ce5-4f22-9ffa-646504a325b0"
msgid ""
"{n}For several moments, Willas is silent, trying to wrap his head around what you "
"said. He finally shudders and hugs himself, as though he suddenly grew cold.{/n} \\"
"\"That means...\\\" {n}He gulps.{/n} \\\"That means the curse really exists...\\"
"\" {n}His eyes meet yours.{/n} \\\"Right?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4bda4123-f86d-4cdd-acee-c0eaae1577e0"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas shakes his head.{/n} \\\"If a cleric and a paladin together were unable "
"to put an end to this curse, it would truly be unwise to try and go there again... "
"Too bad, too bad! Well, here's your reward, as promised.\\\" {n}Willas gives you a "
"pouch of coins.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cee82ecf-c605-422e-8a9c-2a38ea9cca9c"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas stares at you in admiration.{/n} \\\"You're so strong, Your Grace! Tough "
"and strong! Praise be to {g|Desna}Desna{/g}, you managed to come back to your "
"subjects alive and well! Please accept your reward!\\\" {n}Willas presents you "
"with a pouch of coins.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7844eb39-c1a1-46d2-8a7e-7cbc35d8a778"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you manage to learn something new — please let me know! I'm staying at the "
"tavern in the center of town — that's where I'll wait for good news!\\\" {n}Willas "
"bows and steps back from you without straightening back up.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5eb5a726-68eb-4cee-bcf0-c696ac2da244"
msgid ""
"\\\"I'm staying at the tavern in the center of town. I beg you, if you change your "
"mind… if you decide to look into it... I'll wait.\\\" {n}Willas gives you an "
"awkward bow and leaves.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e0317f2-7f0c-4076-9fff-5206c5865f47"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas's jaw drops.{/n} \\\"What?! But... I just...\\\" {n}The man seems to "
"shrink in terror.{/n} \\\"No! Of course not, Your Grace... I'll... I'll compensate "
"you... now... Here, Your Grace.\\\" {n}Willas dugs a pouch full of coins from his "
"pocket and hands it to you, barely avoiding dropping it on the ground.{/n} \\"
"\"Here... this must be enough.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4a4e3b5-d330-47c7-b479-5e8437007e10"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas looks shocked at first, but he soon regains his composure.{/n} \\\"I "
"suppose, Your Grace, that the cause of all the troubles must have been something "
"else... Maybe weather conditions were unfavorable, or... actually, I think you "
"have nothing to worry about.\\\" {n}He casts an unkind glance toward you and digs "
"out a pouch of money.{/n} \\\"Here is your reward. As promised.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb7b7324-cc12-4ac4-a487-ba7601c06ced"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas looks around, slapping his pockets.{/n} \\\"Seems I've had no luck with "
"this island — no profits at all! I guess I should move further to the east. People "
"say the {g|Tors of Levenies}Tors of Levenies{/g} have plenty of places where an "
"inquisitive mind might find something of value. And right now, if you don't mind, "
"I could use a drink.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "847f16bd-0b02-4c9f-8a39-ba08c59ed426"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas purses his lips, obviously dissatisfied with such a short answer. He "
"digs a pouch of coins out of his pocket and gives it to you.{/n} \\\"Here, Your "
"Grace. I keep my word.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69edd756-4738-471d-89fe-da3bac9d30f9"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas opens his mouth, then closes it, then opens again, as if failing to find "
"the right words. It seems that your answer sent him into a stupor.{/n} \\\"You... "
"you really think so?\\\" {n}Gunderson's face lights up, as if you've removed a "
"huge invisible burden from his shoulders.{/n} \\\"Your words are the balm for my "
"soul! Everyone around keeps talking about obligations and promises, and the truth "
"is, anyone should do whatever they feel like!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9d0061e4-d045-4e18-b01a-ddcb0d5e7261"
msgid ""
"{n}Willas digs out a pouch of coins.{/n} \\\"Here is your reward, {mf|my baron|my "
"baroness}. And this...\\\" {n}He takes a parcel out of another pocket.{/n} \\"
"\"This is a small gift from a kindred spirit. It's a true rarity, to meet such a "
"wise person as yourself! This is something I snatched up at... Well, the location "
"isn't important. I think it may be of use to you.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f151c552-bd8b-4f37-8191-1a22fdf74549"
msgid ""
"{n}It seems like Willas is talking about will-o'-wisps — malevolent creatures made "
"of light that feed on fears and other negative emotions.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b398f0f8-4f9d-4c90-82b2-9f1ab66665c7"
msgid ""
"{n}You're not sure what Willas is talking about. Maybe the island is really "
"haunted with the spirits of the deceased?{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6479485a-4ce4-4c2c-9e70-3a37478c9019"
msgid ""
"\\\"Typical for Master Gunderson! I wouldn't be surprised if, after this "
"conversation, our poor timid friend will need a companion to guide him to his own "
"door!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32f0908d-3d14-4172-94d8-a531e591adc1"
msgid ""
"\\\"Some rituals, some ancient deities… Now that's what I call getting into "
"details! With deep knowledge like that, you could easily write a book! You could "
"call this opus magnum of yours 'Some Encyclopedia'!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7324f4f4-4250-4408-8fd4-fc69b698fc32"
msgid "\\\"…Says the king of dimwits.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "05baa2b7-38aa-45f4-a9ba-1299782af1f1"
msgid ""
"{n}Noticing the change in your face, Willas restrains himself.{/n} \\\"Oops, I'm "
"just talking gibberish! Heard some gossip somewhere — and here I am, spilling it "
"all on you!\\\" {n}The man utters a phony giggle, then gulps.{/n} \\\"It's... "
"nothing, Your Grace. Just a big fat load of nothing. Some empty talk about someone "
"sacrificing someone else there... And as for the ghostly lights, I'm sure there's "
"a rational explanation for that... Same with the flash of light over the ruins...\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20404be3-5dc7-449c-9048-29044ef06e41"
msgid ""
"\\\"Remember that strange Gunderson fellow? The one who kept asking you to go to "
"{g|Candlemere}Candlemere{/g} Lake and get his not-exactly-his treasure? Well, he "
"got peeved with you and left! He said he's headed east — for more treasure again, "
"I'd guess! Here, he asked me to give you this farewell {g|gunderson_farewell}"
"message{/g}.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4d021de6-f4d4-4586-9c21-b754105dbbe5"
msgid "Willas Gunderson's Farewell Message"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cdeabefd-50ed-4da3-93c4-b48fd74d2eec"
msgid ""
"\\\"Your esteemed Grace!\\nIt is with deep regret that I must inform you that I "
"can no longer await your decisive action in relation to restoring my right to the "
"valuables located on the island of Candlemere Lake. Please be informed that I "
"shall be leaving the borders of your barony and heading into the dominion of "
"Maegar Varn — a well-respected lord and a valiant warrior, quite worthy of his own "
"chronicle. As I'm sure I can expect to make a name for myself in the ranks of "
"Varn's army, I have decided to magnanimously renounce my claim on the treasure to "
"be found at Candlemere Lake. It is yours to deal with at your sole discretion."
"\\nWarmest regards,\\nWillas Gunderson\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2f175109-b4d8-4e84-818f-1d229d5c31e9"
msgid "\\\"Do you have any idea where he might be?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c2f42078-3a93-4579-a4a8-5da8b6b4a500"
msgid ""
"\\\"The witch couldn't have taken your son. I killed her with my own hands.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa505e01-cae3-4568-a1ac-ffc68890d640"
msgid "\\\"I paid a visit to the witch. Your son isn't there.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "513612f6-d46f-442b-b78a-2f00adfa76b1"
msgid "\\\"I'll try to find him.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "181d04f7-b6ab-4947-b502-f3d0439cab1b"
msgid "\\\"I don't have time for this.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b60e935-8457-4762-8737-0d97d8d1b830"
msgid "\\\"I couldn't save your son. I'm sorry.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23a5b856-ef3c-495b-8adf-679f2a4f02b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"I found your son. He's alive, but the lizardfolk are holding him captive.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56b75652-8d0d-4757-8414-a931cc4d7cbf"
msgid "\\\"I need to go.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90b2d420-b8eb-470f-9e27-2db00ad6226e"
msgid "\\\"Do people disappear frequently here?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e47a8664-844b-41f1-9f19-54c5c4f07575"
msgid "\\\"Calm down, Jenna. Tell me, what did you hide from me?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bf131388-0b69-4cd0-94a2-bd48ea6ac4e0"
msgid ""
"{n}A peasant woman, her face soaked with tears, approaches you quickly.{/n} \\"
"\"Oh, Your Grace... woe is me! I've met my darkest hour. You're my last hope! By "
"all the gods ever prayed to, don't leave me in need!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d88ac14-af20-4ae0-b79d-80b7f76671c1"
msgid ""
"{n}Jenna looks at you with eyes red from tears.{/n} \\\"Have you found my little "
"boy?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7d43e41-bb9b-472b-bea8-2bdb7e0bf22b"
msgid ""
"{n}Jenna looks around cautiously and whispers,{/n} \\\"There's this old hag in the "
"{g|Narlmarches}Narlmarches{/g}... a swamp witch! I won't say her name out loud, "
"don't you even ask! The mere thought of her chills the blood in my veins! She has "
"the evil eye, and she eats people! She even turns into a black raven and soars in "
"the sky. It's sure as day that she took my boy!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8eff00b0-ba94-40cd-b81d-d6e544c5bb01"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh my!\\\" {n}Jenna flings her hands up in surprise.{/n} \\\"Good riddance! "
"Thank you, Your Grace. She was a menace to us all! But if it wasn't her...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f2d81c7-41f4-45b9-bc50-672e8093ec5f"
msgid "\\\"How can that be? And I thought... But... But if wasn't her, then...\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "491ecf22-d7fb-4086-aa58-a440c7da32df"
msgid ""
"\\\"Then that means that... that...\\\" {n}The peasant woman's face turns pale, "
"and she covers her mouth with both hands.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73397704-60d2-42b8-ac6d-c5eadb1513de"
msgid ""
"\\\"My name is Jenna, Jenna Tannersen. Our village is a short way from here. It's "
"been two days since my boy, Tig, ran away — and I haven't seen him since! We've "
"searched and searched, but it's no use! If you don't find him, no one else will!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02108888-cc2a-4228-891d-f8dd09cdf054"
msgid ""
"\\\"My boy...\\\" {n}Jenna sobs.{/n} \\\"He was... He's such a little mischief-"
"maker! That day... that day he was especially loud, kept running around the "
"house... He flipped a tub of dough... And, well, I... Oh gods, what have I done!\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fce68aca-d12a-45d8-ba57-2cdfcdc558ab"
msgid ""
"{n}For a long time, Jenna stands still, staring in front of her. Then, without a "
"single word, she slowly walks away.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f87db00-74e5-4ae4-adf3-08bbdc94e159"
msgid ""
"\\\"I lost my temper and I shouted at him. I told him he can go drown himself in "
"{g|Candlemere}Candlemere{/g} Lake! His own mother, wishing he was dead! But how "
"could I have known it would all come true?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb70a104-e0ef-412e-a5a6-1eff83c1784f"
msgid ""
"\\\"If you find him, I beg you — tell him I love him more than life itself! Never, "
"never again shall I say anything mean to him, just bring him back home safe and "
"sound!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92731ab9-2615-4493-b5c4-40ac1a9d3d40"
msgid ""
"{n}As soon as the peasant woman sees you, she falls to her knees, trying to kiss "
"your hand.{/n} \\\"Oh! Your Grace! Our deliverer! You saved him, you rescued my "
"little one! What would we ever do without you! Every day until the day I die, I "
"shall pray to all the gods for your health!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f52ad1a1-8de3-4425-8c42-d065718fb7e8"
msgid ""
"{n}Jenna looks at you with eyes red from tears.{/n} \\\"Have you changed your "
"mind? Will you look for my boy?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa734138-78ed-4cb7-a358-c4187514fb2a"
msgid ""
"\\\"Of course, of course, you're so busy... But if you find the time... I still "
"have a bit of money left to pay for a room in the tavern... Please, I beg you, "
"don't leave us in need!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a954262d-00a4-466b-95dc-fb5407baf3dd"
msgid ""
"\\\"Goodness gracious! Lizardfolk! But they... they eat people! Oh, in {g|Erastil}"
"Erastil{/g}'s name, I beg you, save him before those lizards... before they...\\"
"\" {n}The peasant woman cries uncontrollably.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1335a39e-8d2f-4f5b-93b6-2936f0a9905d"
msgid "\\\"May {g|Erastil}Erastil{/g} help you...\\\" {n}The woman sobs.{/n}"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fc81d80c-dce2-4b16-af2d-9c635a619a37"
msgid ""
"\\\"They sure do! There are so many hazards around, it's hard to name them all! "
"Wild beasts in the forest, and monsters, and some troblins, and bandits, and "
"whatever... Even adults have hard time surviving here, and for a little kid... Oh!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1cbef96-ee0a-4bae-9843-b46bed1849b7"
msgid ""
"\\\"Oh, Your Grace... Thank you, thank you so much! I'll be praying to {g|Erastil}"
"Erastil{/g} to grant you long life! If there's any news, I'll be nearby, in the "
"tavern... May the good gods help you!\\\" {n}The sobbing woman leaves.{/n}"
msgstr ""

