msgctxt "6118b705-c386-4345-8727-e1595cedb0a0"
msgid ""
"\\\"Bring it before us as an offering so that an Eldest may sip from it,\\\" the "
"curse said. Having filled the cup, Nyrissa {d|c61 Nyrissa Left}appeared{/d} before "
"the gods of the First World. That was when the Lantern King played another joke — "
"he announced that the nymph, cursed for her attempt to become one of the Eldest, "
"would now get to be one! The Eldest of dust and trampled hope, doomed to drink "
"from her own cup and suffer terrible pain. Well, everyone got what they wanted: we "
"got a peaceful kingdom, Nyrissa got her status as an Eldest, and the Lantern King "
"got a finale to his horrific performance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5db8ab23-b591-4194-97c3-de6c29c177d8"
msgid ""
"\\\"Bring it before us as an offering so that an Eldest may sip from it,\\\" the "
"{d|CURSE}curse{/d} said. Having filled the cup, Nyrissa {d|c61 Nyrissa Left}"
"appeared{/d} before the gods of the First World. That was when the Lantern King "
"played another joke — he announced that the nymph, cursed for her attempt to "
"become one of the Eldest, would now get to be one! He commanded her to drink from "
"the cup, and he was probably about to deliver some pompous speech, but..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9d2cc8e2-460e-4cc7-81c8-064b3e2e46d5"
msgid ""
"Now that the Eldest and other spiteful beings wouldn't be bothering us, the {mf|"
"king|queen} returned to {mf|his|her} subjects and celebrated the victory and the "
"end of the kingdom's miseries with great fanfare!\\nEverything gradually returned "
"to normal, including our exciting lives — not always peaceful, but also not "
"troubled by invasions from another world. And little by little, our heroes and the "
"common folk began to forget the sorrows of the past."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5067494-3788-4d22-9bdd-8b7f75f81434"
msgid ""
"So the kingdom returned to Golarion, but not without taking a piece of the First "
"World with it. Miracles and strange occurrences, both kind and cruel, became the "
"norm — not that the citizens hadn't grown used to that! And the {mf|king|queen} "
"became the Lantern King's herald. Who knows what mission was assigned to {mf|him|"
"her}? Our scouts now sneak across Golarion with secret tasks, and our fighters and "
"wizards spend plenty of time in the First World. But we became something straight "
"out of legends — a country with a mysterious, immortal {mf|king|queen} whose "
"existence spans two worlds!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f05ecf9-e6a2-4e47-b4cc-6655e168daf6"
msgid ""
"So the kingdom returned to Golarion, but not without taking a piece of the First "
"World with it. Miracles and strange occurrences, both kind and cruel, became the "
"norm — not that the citizens hadn't grown used to that! Of course, the Lantern "
"King wasn't thrilled with the way things worked out, but who cares? {Name} and {d|"
"c61 Nyrissa Evil}Nyrissa{/d}, the {mf|cursed king and queen|cursed queens}, are "
"ever ready to face the power of the Eldest. Until that time comes, our leader "
"spends a lot of time in the First World, learning its secrets and testing {mf|his|"
"her} new powers. The immortal {mf|king|queen} and {mf|his|her} kingdom became a "
"legend come true in Golarion!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e5092785-649f-42ac-847a-fb86f69ce496"
msgid ""
"That's how the story ended. The Lantern King vanished without a trace, and we "
"never heard from him again. {d|c61 Nyrissa TE}Nyrissa{/d} helped return the "
"kingdom to Golarion and followed her beloved there. After celebrating the victory "
"with great fanfare, everyone began work on restoration efforts. Nyrissa helped the "
"{mf|king|queen} in every way possible, and she quickly came to be loved across the "
"country. No one would have thought this kind nymph was a former villain, so "
"recently guilty of causing all those afflictions!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3f6f396-29e9-431b-a22c-40be06b7b084"
msgid ""
"The kingdom built by our hero{mf||ine} became an example for all its neighbors. "
"What else would you expect? The Stolen Lands became the only place where the "
"citizens sincerely toast the health of their ruler! The citizens lived trouble-"
"free, and taxes made it to the treasury without losses. A powerful army guards the "
"peace, exploration of magic is on par, the temples are flooded with their "
"congregations, and — most importantly — our cultural contributions are at least "
"the equal of Absalom!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7267c0e8-6745-4193-85bf-d6253ab7d02f"
msgid ""
"Under the wise leadership of the {mf|king|queen}, the Stolen Lands became a true "
"country! There was still much to be done, of course, and some of it will need to "
"be finished by our hero{mf||ine}'s descendants, but there are no longer cutpurses "
"on every corner, and the peasants aren't afraid some new self-proclaimed chief "
"will show up and strong-arm himself into power!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0803b29-28c7-4388-892c-8745abfe761b"
msgid ""
"Sadly, the numerous misfortunes that befell the {mf|king|queen} took their toll on "
"the Stolen Lands. Matters left to luck and state problems left unattended meant "
"the Stolen Lands would remain a lawless realm. It turns out you can't be both a "
"great hero{mf||ine} and a successful ruler at the same time — or the hero{mf||ine} "
"of this story couldn't, at least."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5857c049-74d2-439d-b319-3fc617392c54"
msgid ""
"The Stolen Lands still remain a domain of bandits. However, every outlaw in the "
"area {d|Kingdom Mafia}knows{/d} that if you don't bow to this new chief who wears "
"a crown and calls {mf|him|her}self {mf|king|queen} — you're in trouble! The "
"cutthroats know their place and unfailingly respect the hierarchy, but the "
"kingdom's neighbors think it beneath their dignity to consider the {mf|king|queen} "
"a true monarch."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3383dd63-8b1a-4022-985c-4f06e19292f5"
msgid ""
"The {mf|king|queen} firmly eliminated banditry in the Stolen Lands, to the delight "
"of the long-suffering {d|Kingdom Citizens}locals{/d}, and brought peace and law to "
"the area. That peace didn't last long, however — a \\\"jolly gang\\\" appeared in "
"the Narlmarches, claiming to fight the \\\"tyranny\\\" of the {mf|king|queen} \\"
"\"for the good of the common people.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29458507-a7dd-4b46-bb1d-2f6d60eacbe3"
msgid ""
"The Stolen Lands are called the \\\"land of popular rule,\\\" for in these lands, "
"{d|Kingdom Folk}common people{/d} feel fully in control of their fates! "
"Unfortunately, the total absence of authority allowed one of the richest regions "
"of the kingdom to proclaim itself an independent republic, and retrieving those "
"territories came at a rather high price for the {mf|king|queen}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96b33970-34a1-4632-aa45-3adb22ef718d"
msgid ""
"The {mf|king|queen} did the right thing, leaning on {d|Kingdom Merchants}the "
"richest{/d} citizens of the Stolen Lands in {mf|his|her} ruling. Thanks to their "
"many trade relations, money floods into the kingdom, and the fact that the private "
"mercenary armies bought with the merchants' money continue to gain power can still "
"be overlooked."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2821415e-189b-4cbd-9fd7-583690b23639"
msgid ""
"Just half a year after the war with the First World, Galt moved its troops to the "
"southern border of the kingdom. Their attack was rebuffed — the enemy state's "
"infantry could do little against {d|Kingdom Might}soldiers{/d} who were skilled "
"with their swords and knew the military arts better than the alphabet! Since then, "
"Galt hasn't risked crossing any borders again, fearing cruel retaliation for "
"further insolence."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28d0daca-7934-487b-802d-465aeca5aef8"
msgid ""
"Just half a year after the war with the First World, Galt moved its troops to the "
"southern border of the kingdom. Their attack was rebuffed — the enemy state's "
"infantry retreated when the army's {d|Kingdom Magic}wizards{/d} brought down rains "
"of fire and magical arrows on the heads of the flabbergasted enemy soldiers! Since "
"then, Galt hasn't risked crossing any borders again, fearing cruel retaliation for "
"further insolence."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58961764-8555-4c40-b726-bb6a62c3f8af"
msgid ""
"The kingdom's treasury had been properly filled due to the efforts of the "
"Treasurer and the {mf|king|queen}, until a scandal broke: for several years, the "
"court's {d|Kingdom Official}advisors{/d} had been pocketing tax money! News of the "
"noisy case echoed throughout the area, and for quite some time, neighboring states "
"snickered at the {mf|king|queen}'s \\\"incorruptible government.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88404ce0-c5eb-4ca2-bb61-8190fe6ba9b1"
msgid ""
"The {mf|king|queen}'s subjects praise {mf|his|her} {d|Kingdom People}generosity{/"
"d} — while citizens of neighboring lands groan from crippling taxes, citizens of "
"the Stolen Lands have it pretty good! Truth be told, the treasury isn't always "
"capable of paying the royal bills, and the throne room's adornments are clearly "
"decaying, but sometimes you have to buy the people's love — literally!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7cf5a726-06b9-4e97-88bc-a399f9f6f0ff"
msgid ""
"As the years went by, the Stolen Lands saw fewer small unknown cults and more "
"temples devoted to {d|Kingdom Religion Control}famous{/d} and powerful gods. "
"Followers of half-forgotten religions prefer to avoid the area, as the locals are "
"a bit overzealous about the \\\"religious purity\\\" of their homeland."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bbc1239e-cfe3-4a85-8929-d22b0efa4cd9"
msgid ""
"The {mf|king|queen} decided to {d|Kingdom Religion Liberty}stay out{/d} of the "
"religious lives of {mf|his|her} subjects — and so small cults and sects began to "
"blossom in the Stolen Lands. More and more often, the theological arguments "
"between feuding congregations would turn into full brawls — I could only hope the "
"guards had enough power to keep the rage of the fanatics at bay..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "432bb83b-be64-463b-959a-3910b1c1ba73"
msgid ""
"The tribulations suffered by the citizens of the Stolen Lands made them true "
"patriots — intolerant to strangers, and ready to fight to the death for their "
"homeland. Foreign ambassadors were reluctant to accept invitations to visit these "
"lands, as they knew well that the kingdom's citizens prefer to solve their own "
"problems and {d|Kingdom Isolation}stay out{/d} of external affairs."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8881e30b-a622-4279-852c-fde265cdf2c3"
msgid ""
"Who'd have thought that some tiny barony founded in the Stolen Lands by an "
"adventurer would become a real kingdom, playing a prominent part in {d|Kingdom "
"Open}world{/d} politics! Of course, not everyone likes the proactive stance of "
"this young, bold state, but the fact of the matter is they can't afford to ignore "
"the {mf|king|queen} and {mf|his|her} diplomats."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d56e5e3c-7098-499c-a31f-aaf87baebce3"
msgid ""
"The kingdom reached incredible {d|Kingdom Arcane Liberty}heights{/d} in the "
"development of magical arts. Sorcerers, wizards, and other initiates feel like "
"kids in a candy store in the Stolen Lands. Sadly, ordinary subjects aren't so "
"thrilled — they have to deal with the consequences of careless experiments and "
"failed magical tests!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f4d073d4-78c9-4516-a433-36dbd95b7a60"
msgid ""
"The {mf|king|queen} thought it best to {d|Kingdom Arcane Control}limit{/d} the use "
"of magic by regular citizens. That decision, oft criticized by prominent minds in "
"Brevoy, more than once proved to be the right one in the end — the kingdom is "
"reliably protected from any magical \\\"incidents\\\" that might be caused by "
"unskilled wizards or nefarious infiltrators."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3322739-e11c-429c-991c-a9211a8fdb02"
msgid ""
"How do you turn the Stolen Lands, savage and unruly, into a stronghold of safety "
"and stability? The {mf|king|queen} found an answer: by creating a police state! "
"There are always some who are unhappy with the \\\"excessive {d|Kingdom Source}"
"interference{/d}\\\" advisors have in the citizens' lives, of course, but their "
"protests are easily overlooked."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33000ba9-80d7-4567-8252-e06d512c1c8f"
msgid ""
"How do you turn the Stolen Lands, savage and unruly, into a stronghold of safety "
"and stability? The {mf|king|queen} found an answer: by tripling or even "
"quadrupling the number of {d|Kingdom Defense}guards{/d}! These guards consider "
"themselves something of a privileged class, of course, allowed much more leniency "
"than anyone else, but the ordinary citizens, feeling safe and secure, prefer to "
"just overlook the discrepancy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5579e2cb-7d8a-4629-859e-25eebb0b6cf1"
msgid ""
"Generously {d|Kindom Culture Money}sponsored{/d} by the state, many bards, "
"musicians, poets, and other servants of Shelyn create an abundance of artistic "
"works praising the ruler and {mf|his|her} wisdom! Unfortunately, these creations "
"are significantly less popular outside the kingdom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b69a0ebe-3a5f-4960-bfca-ad4e224cb7e4"
msgid ""
"Although the state doesn't directly {d|Kingdom Culture Liberty}support{/d} "
"creators, the kingdom's freedom of speech and self-expression became fruitful soil "
"for dozens of talented people across the Stolen Lands. Many creators achieved "
"recognition and fame due to their efforts, but the most talented soon left the \\"
"\"edge of the world\\\" in search of a more worthwhile audience."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ee71a45-142d-4029-9851-e223d9e58395"
msgid ""
"The mysterious \\\"Minister,\\\" whose actual line of work is still an enigma to "
"the {mf|king|queen}'s other advisors, took care of securing the state from the "
"schemes of spies and other provocations. Their {d|Kingdom Plotting}stratagems{/d}, "
"political intrigues, and diplomatic leverage bore interesting fruit, as other "
"states decided they'd rather steer clear of a kingdom known for its ability to "
"excel at shady games."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "791c0134-03b5-4d42-95ac-618cfc9e27bd"
msgid ""
"The \\\"Minister,\\\" whose responsibilities are hidden even to the {mf|king|"
"queen}'s other advisors, did much to let the subjects sleep well at night. It "
"didn't come without a cost, however — outside the Stolen Lands, the kingdom is "
"known as home to the {d|Kingdom Violence}cruelest{/d} investigators and "
"inquisitors, who zealously persecute any enemies of the state!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "350e5590-d995-410b-8d50-925649c8470a"
msgid ""
"The {mf|king|queen} became a true patron of fine crafts. Over time, the castle "
"treasury filled with wonderful gifts from the best masters in the area. Armor, "
"weapons, even magical artifacts — and the collection is still growing!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed67d7df-6532-4270-874e-5da6ddd6755b"
msgid ""
"No kingdom can function without its nobility, and the kingdom in the Stolen Lands "
"is no exception. Landowners, ready to share the burden of ruling alongside the {mf|"
"king|queen}, grew to be more and more influential over time — and the more pompous "
"the court balls and receptions held by dukes and baronets became, the more "
"eventful were the lives of the schemers and freeloaders who always live within the "
"shadows of the powerful!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "10fb8627-ebec-4a33-a96f-ac5a18f0aefe"
msgid ""
"Using necromancy in service to the state is a solution as bold as it is desperate! "
"Pharasma's church still makes frequent — and frankly, reasonable — plans to send a "
"massive crusade against the Stolen Lands to cleanse the nest of vice. The "
"kingdom's citizens, however, not only yielded to the use of an undead workforce, "
"they actually supported it! After all, someone has to do the most dangerous, most "
"unpleasant work!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b538fcfa-f4db-4104-ae3d-46713ce097db"
msgid ""
"The feud between Brevoy's north and south, which had been smoldering for ages, "
"finally sparked the fires of civil war. Our troops lent {d|c41 Choose Aldori}aid{/"
"d} to the forces of Restov, led by Swordlord Jamandi Aldori. After several bloody "
"battles, House Surtova was forced to recognize Restov's independence. The victory "
"came at a high price, but we have no more loyal ally than once more free Rostland."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b439c16f-a057-410c-a658-e507b363e4da"
msgid ""
"The feud between Brevoy's north and south, which had been smoldering for ages, "
"finally sparked the fires of civil war. Our troops lent {d|c41 Choose Surtova}aid{/"
"d} to the forces of House Surtova, suffering terrible losses as they took the "
"brunt of the damage from the Swordlords' forces. The rebellion was soon crushed, "
"and Jamandi Aldori was beheaded in Restov's central square — and for a long time, "
"any hope of an independent Rostland died with her."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d63bcb8f-54ee-4d19-8a30-effccfef9edf"
msgid ""
"The feud between Brevoy's north and south, which had been smoldering for ages, "
"never sparked the fires of civil war. Through great effort, our {mf|king|queen} "
"managed to bring both parties to the {d|c41 Brevoy Neutral}negotiating table{/d}. "
"While Rostland didn't regain its independence, it did receive wide autonomy "
"rights. Our relationships with both House Surtova and the Swordlords are "
"respectful, but they've become lukewarm — because of us, neither side got "
"everything they wanted!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22b93480-2d03-4217-9531-682edcef604c"
msgid ""
"The feud between Brevoy's north and south, which had been smoldering for ages, "
"finally sparked the fires of civil war. We {d|c41 Independence}didn't interfere{/"
"d}, watching as the forces of House Surtova and the Swordlords slaughtered each "
"other. Alternating between brief truces and fresh fights, Brevoy was flooded with "
"blood and grew weak. Its leaders could only watch helplessly as their border "
"territories were slowly annexed by neighbors — until they fell to squabbling among "
"themselves. The carnage in Brevoy jeopardized the peace of the entire region."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55843c36-0259-4d48-95b1-a322106cf664"
msgid ""
"Taking advantage of the tension in his homeland, the restless, {d|c41 Lander Lives}"
"unlucky traitor{/d} Lander Lebeda abandoned his domain again and set off to "
"attempt another scam! Our kingdom, along with Brevoy, actually proposed to "
"celebrate the day he disappeared as a national holiday, but the initiative was "
"shot down by the vigorous protests of House Lebeda!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38fcb659-6fe7-43b9-ae07-b2267a20844a"
msgid ""
"The Tiger Lords found it difficult to recuperate after what Armag did to them. The "
"barbarians remaining in Numeria weren't very happy that we sheltered the deposed "
"chief and his supporters, but they were too afraid of {d|c41 Chief Armag}him{/d} "
"to attack us over it. That bomb has a long fuse, but it's definitely burning — I'm "
"afraid that a few generations down the road, the grandchildren of the current "
"Tiger Lords may want to retaliate against us for their grandfathers!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "314bae19-37a9-4b3a-9ce9-f25bdbd5d107"
msgid ""
"Amiri didn't remain {d|c41 Chief Amiri}leader{/d} of the Tiger Lords for long — "
"ruling was certainly not her calling! The years she spent with them were enough "
"for them to regain their forces, though, and they recovered to be one of the best "
"mercenary armies in the region again. They revere her as a great hero, even more "
"than they once worshiped Armag. And they respect our {mf|king|queen}, of course — "
"{mf||s}he was a comrade in arms of the great Amiri, after all! Their tribe came to "
"be loyal allies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5f3a8bbc-582f-41f9-81ec-df674292a9b9"
msgid ""
"{d|c41 Chief Ashman}Led{/d} by careful, level-headed Dugath, the Tiger Lords tribe "
"reunited and started to lick the wounds left by the erratic Armag. Little by "
"little, they once again became one of the strongest mercenary armies in the "
"region. Dugath always assures our {mf|king|queen} of his friendship, but the {mf|"
"king|queen} always stays on {mf|his|her} toes, understanding that anything could "
"happen when that old fox is around!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88661525-ee29-44fc-850e-52d35f65721c"
msgid ""
"The Tiger Lords never fully recovered from the damage Armag did to the tribe. "
"Lacking a strong leader and torn by infighting, the barbarians sank into a short "
"but fierce internal war. Their lands were quickly appropriated by neighboring "
"tribes, and the Tiger Lords were scattered across Numeria and the River Kingdoms, "
"little more than pitiful remnants of a once great tribe."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2322ba1b-833c-4db1-86f5-5d5038730db6"
msgid ""
"Pitax almost returned to its former state — a joyful city filled with beer of "
"dubious quality and deals of questionable legality. The old trade houses lost the "
"crown, but they retrieved the property Irovetti had taken from them. Soon, Pitax "
"became almost like a second capital in the kingdom, a thriving city through which "
"rivers of money from across the region ran."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "290a8b84-9e32-48c0-95d9-26ccb1640809"
msgid ""
"Without a city {d|c51 No Guards}guard{/d}, Pitax was plunged into chaos. Soon "
"another power was born from among the gangs fighting to redistribute the wealth, "
"and a much more dangerous one — revolutionaries, dreaming of regaining Pitax's "
"independence. Troops had to be stationed in the city, and the rebels responded "
"with arson and political assassinations throughout the kingdom. Pitax became a "
"headache to us for a long time."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9bf7ea43-4e90-4f7e-b496-b0e3b639d62c"
msgid ""
"Pitax had never been a paragon of law and order, but now it had become one giant "
"bandit den. That has its benefits — a good share of the profits makes its way to "
"the treasury without fail, and the black markets holds anything you could hope to "
"find. But Pitax brought a lot of trouble, too, as thieves, extortionists, and drug "
"dealers spread their tendrils throughout the entire kingdom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2b93b640-1413-43ed-aa59-722c56305626"
msgid ""
"Pitax never regained its former stature. In their fight for power, both bandits "
"and the relatively honest merchants lost all their strength, scaring away both "
"customers and suppliers. Trade routes began moving through other cities. Pitax "
"fell into decline, and the citizens quickly forgot all of Irovetti's atrocities, "
"remembering his rule instead as a golden age for the region."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8e06ce27-5430-49ea-b919-b56047ebc226"
msgid ""
"Amid chaos and fighting, Headmistress {d|c51 Atalia Rules}Gitaren{/d} managed to "
"preserve the Academy of the Arts, though not its reputation. Only sycophants "
"willing to dash off odes to the highest bidder (primarily our {mf|king|queen}) "
"stayed to work and study under her tutelage. One could say the academy still "
"flourishes — though in the same way a pond covered with duckweed turns green on a "
"sleepy summer day, slowly becoming a swamp. No one dreams of studying at the "
"academy anymore — but for those more concerned with reality than dreams, it will "
"always have a comfortable room."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "359196f3-bd69-41b8-ac8c-c616dca9ca95"
msgid ""
"Maestro {d|c51 Annamede Rules}Belavarah{/d} gave the Academy of the Arts a second "
"wind. Throwing out mediocre students and sycophants, she gathered within its walls "
"talented visionaries, rebels, and freethinkers — those whose gifts felt cramped "
"within the walls of more respectable institutions. She managed to do what Irovetti "
"never could, namely make the academy truly famous, albeit scandalously so. And so "
"what if, instead of odes to the {mf|king|queen}, the academy releases sneering "
"pamphlets and revolutionary leaflets? It only helps {mf|his|her} reputation as a "
"true patron of the arts."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66876dda-4bf4-4dcf-8991-3155e6173196"
msgid ""
"{d|c51 Academy Elections}Self-administration{/d} turned the Academy of the Arts "
"into a strange place. The court sycophants were quickly ousted — it turned out "
"they weren't welcome when there wasn't someone like Irovetti constantly ordering "
"odes to themselves. In their place came a motley, unpredictable crowd: essentrics, "
"fashionable authors of popular prints and cheap novels, charlatans, scribblers "
"with delusions of grandeur, as many as three feuding \\\"experimental\\\" "
"theaters... and even a few truly unappreciated geniuses! The academy is not only "
"highly esteemed — there's no place like it, even in Absalom!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6549af27-9348-46eb-9a61-f16196d1a607"
msgid ""
"There was no place for art in the new Pitax. Students and teachers from the "
"academy were scattered to the winds. Some found a place in neighboring courts, "
"while others set off to earn some coin in roadside taverns. A third group, "
"harboring anger and resentment toward the {mf|king|queen}, began weaving "
"revolutionary plots. The {d|c51 No Academy}ruins{/d} of the Academy of the Arts "
"still stand in the middle of the city, overrun with ivy — empty and unwanted."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7364763b-89e3-4311-bf47-0ffbdf3d6226"
msgid ""
"Trolls and kobolds, two of the most savage native peoples living in the "
"Narlmarches, were completely exterminated in the region. The forest paths became "
"much safer, and the peasants' cattle have stopped going missing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75afbed5-87d0-4ec5-b3df-6818a2dc77f4"
msgid ""
"The Stole Lands managed to eliminate kobolds, but not quite all the trolls. Even "
"nowadays, unlucky travelers and hunters sometimes stumble across one of these huge "
"man-eaters in the depths of the swamps and forests. Do they have some {d|c21 "
"Hargulka Exiled}leader{/d} hiding out there? No one knows for sure, and likely no "
"one ever will."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d92e354b-6956-4a87-a5ee-e7e402373ed1"
msgid ""
"Hargulka, the troll king, still {d|c21 Hargulka Lives}lives{/d} in the Stolen "
"Lands. Amazingly, he managed to bring his savage kin to heel, even organizing "
"trade with nearby settlements of ordinary citizens! The common folk aren't exactly "
"excited to have such neighbors, but they'll settle for trolls who've switched "
"their menu to forest game and the cattle people sell them!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aca5f02c-d708-4a99-adc4-abe75b3e2626"
msgid ""
"The dangerous, man-eating trolls disappeared entirely from the forests and swamps "
"of the Stolen Lands. Kobolds, though, being sneaky and clever, are still sometimes "
"met by travelers and hunters who wander off the beaten track. Some even say the "
"short reptiles still praise the \\\"great king\\\" {d|c21 Tartuk Exiled}Tartuk{/"
"d}, but no one knows for certain — as soon as anyone approaches the kobolds, they "
"forget their military honor and turn tail!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7c50953-a218-4aef-86b7-a561ab100c18"
msgid ""
"Bartholomew Delgado still serves the {mf|king|queen} loyally. From time to time, "
"he orders peculiar mechanisms and substances from all corners of the world. After "
"receiving them, he spends a few days bragging about some great discovery he's "
"about to make, then ends up gloomy for a few months. Then he receives another "
"package, and the process repeats itself. At night, chilling screams are often "
"heard from his laboratory."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db66f61c-e2c0-4b83-bd2f-97394fd28cca"
msgid ""
"After enduring so many storms and troubles, Varnhold eventually turned into a real "
"city. Daring settlers decided to conquer the vast, wild expanses of Dunsward, and "
"despite all odds, they succeeded! The modest colony that {d|c31 Maegar Saved}"
"almost{/d} vanished at the hands of an ancient lich turned everything around to "
"become a thriving city with lively river trading."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "efd71eee-40d3-4ca8-8813-33edde4050e8"
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, without its founder, Varnhold never really recovered from the blow. "
"Over time, the colony withered away — all the more so when its dwellers continued "
"to disappear under mysterious circumstances! It took less than two years for "
"Varnhold to permanently become a ghost town. The only person happy about the news "
"was the {mf|king|queen}'s new advisor, a mysterious and powerful {d|c31 Vordakai "
"Hired}wizard{/d}, who still serves the ruler loyally to this day."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ccdc68f8-c22c-436e-9179-6f3c424aa4da"
msgid ""
"{d|c31 Agai Lives}Agai{/d}, the spriggan leader, learned a valuable lesson after "
"surviving his meeting with the {mf|king|queen} and even regaining his tribe's home "
"— don't try to occupy seemingly empty settlements anymore! Instead, the spriggans "
"settled across Dunsward's wild borderlands and proclaimed it as their domain! "
"Keeping the peace in a situation like that seems like the stuff of dreams — as "
"evidenced by the occasional lost patrols and stolen cattle!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3bab0ce-bfb7-4d36-af04-9078251c43d6"
msgid ""
"{d|c11 Peacemaker}Peace{/d} reigns in the caves beneath the Old Sycamore. The "
"kobolds and mites continue to explore the depths and learn simple crafts from each "
"other. Rumor has it the first mite-kobold wedding even happened not long ago! That "
"said, settlers still aren't rushing to build new homes in the area. Some kind "
"souls even put up warning signs along the roads: \\\"Beware, traveler! Steer clear "
"of the Old Sycamore!\\\" Another inscription soon appeared over the sign, though: "
"\\\"no keep gowing trezzur ahed honest!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "599d6d16-911e-43f1-9328-ed4cf02b04ee"
msgid ""
"{d|c11 Mites Final}Mites{/d} led by Warrior Queen Bdaah keep causing trouble in "
"the vicinity of the Old Sycamore. They scare the fishers, hold centipede races, "
"and drag anything they find lying about back to their caves — clothes left out to "
"dry, dog kennels, even anvils! When the {mf|king|queen} visits them, they seem to "
"calm down... for about a day. Sometimes even two!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad119cd4-b00f-481d-b4c1-c555d08a3c1a"
msgid ""
"{d|c11 Kobolds Final}The Sootscale kobolds{/d} think themselves the masters of the "
"area around the Old Sycamore, and they aren't very friendly toward travelers. It "
"hasn't come to bloodshed yet, but many careless travelers have broken an arm or a "
"leg in the kobolds' traps! When the {mf|king|queen} visits, the kobolds usually "
"calm down a bit and even take down their traps, but it never lasts long."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a5c97de-02c8-4cca-a101-6e19d124edba"
msgid ""
"After the kobolds and mites {d|c11 Kill Both}disappeared{/d}, the empty caves "
"beneath the Old Sycamore quickly became home to all kinds of disgusting critters "
"(giant centipedes being the most innocent and pleasant of them!). Attempts have "
"been made to clear out the caves, but it never takes long for something to take up "
"residence again. In the end, the decision was made to block the entrances and burn "
"the giant tree down, destroying the roots that held up the ceiling of the caves."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "427e72cd-7c67-4f2f-91bd-3f264cd3d898"
msgid ""
"Due to tumult on both sides of the border, Oleg's {d|c21 Left OTP}trading post{/d} "
"gradually fell into desolation. Regretfully leaving its walls, for which so much "
"blood had been shed, Oleg and Svetlana left the backcountry that was so dear to "
"their hearts and returned to the noise of the big city."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac5dcc4a-ddd4-4f11-bf92-4c058dd3700a"
msgid ""
"Oleg's {d|c21 Claim OTP}trading post{/d} continues to thrive, attracting ever more "
"travelers. Much to its owner's displeasure, a small town is springing up around "
"it. Despite Oleg's grumbling, he and his wife are well regarded by everyone, and "
"Svetlana was even elected town chief!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0c15a85e-faee-40b0-9549-b7630e425e23"
msgid ""
"Oleg's {d|c21 Capture OTP}trading post{/d} now resembles a border stronghold more "
"than a haven for merchants and travelers. A town sprung up around it, from which "
"the leader of the guard operates. Oleg and Svetlana aren't too happy about it, but "
"at least they don't have to fear for their lives anymore."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa687267-bc97-4734-949a-1b55da197346"
msgid ""
"Jhod remained loyal to the {mf|king|queen} to the end of his days, healing the "
"sick and generously sharing his austere wisdom with anyone who wished to hear it "
"(and some who didn't). Having fulfilled his duty to the ruler, Erastil's priest "
"peacefully departed this world, surrounded by friends and disciples."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2ece1ee-c8b6-4db6-beb6-70a017c03c40"
msgid ""
"Kesten Garess took a post as chief of the kingdom's guard. The former heir to a "
"noble family never returned to Brevoy, severing all ties to his kin. However, a "
"few years after the victory over the First World, a girl arrived from Brevoy and "
"soon married Kesten. They say Kesten started smiling a lot more after that."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24ff9e9e-abd7-49d9-bbda-6a017ebf9d15"
msgid ""
"Jhod and Kesten, after {d|c22 both saved}surviving{/d} the Bloom, remained loyal "
"to the {mf|king|queen} they followed through thick and thin, and they continue to "
"serve as court advisors to this day. The austere priest and the gloomy warrior "
"regularly argue over the proper way to govern the state, as well as which of the "
"two the ruler should hear out first. Some things never change."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e938eb7-f4c8-4100-bb73-819c8d251205"
msgid ""
"Tsanna, Lamashtu's priestess, didn't remain in the {mf|king|queen}'s service for "
"long. One night, she just disappeared from the castle and set off for the "
"kingdom's borders, preaching to anyone who would listen and granting the needy the "
"blessing of the Mother of Monsters."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "de4bc8ef-d018-4f45-8834-955cb0e5cae7"
msgid ""
"Having participated in Lamashtu's {d|c22 Olika Ritual}ritual{/d}, {d|Olika}Olika{/"
"d} gave birth to a strong and healthy baby. Sadly, the child grew into an unruly "
"and violent adolescent. Having maimed a peer at just ten years of age, the boy "
"escaped to the Narlmarches, fleeing the rage of a mob that tore his mother to "
"pieces instead. No one knows what happened to the lad, but legends of Lamashtu's "
"Child, who sometimes kills lost travelers and sometimes leads them to safety, are "
"passed on by word of mouth throughout the area."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "962653ab-cbc5-4991-80cb-48510f257cf6"
msgid ""
"Brineheart became a loyal {d|c41 Darven Nice}ally{/d} and trade partner of the "
"kingdom, and Darven himself has been seen as a frequent guest in the capital. The "
"elegant monarch of the neighboring kingdom has broken many hearts at court — after "
"his visits, many young guards and servants have been seen staring through windows, "
"sighing wistfully about something."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33606d16-0544-4883-b0fb-a573f3d4ca11"
msgid ""
"The fey took a fancy to the kingdom, feeling totally at home here! They often play "
"various pranks, but they never do any serious harm."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "610cd215-2e74-4cb5-837f-3228c15fd170"
msgid ""
"The lizardfolk of the Longtail tribe returned to live on the shores of Candlemere, "
"but they couldn't return to their ancient way of life. Living alongside people, "
"the lizardfolk adopted their behaviors, habits, and even religion — more and more "
"of the Longtail tribe pray not to the spirits of their ancestors, but to Erastil, "
"or Gorum. They even began to forget their original language. I hope someone writes "
"down their songs and legends before they all sink into oblivion..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dee9d8b9-cc10-4813-9216-909e3c23994c"
msgid ""
"The goblins who put so much effort into preserving the {mf|king|queen}'s lands "
"obviously felt that gave them the right to do whatever they wanted in the kingdom! "
"Travelers are careful to move in groups when they can, and any peasants who spot "
"at least one particularly toothy stranger immediately raise the alarm — for if you "
"see one goblin, there's likely a whole gang!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a60b112-511d-4b69-85a3-7a56ecbc65ac"
msgid ""
"A delegation of wizards from Absalom and other areas appeared in the kingdom one "
"day, asking for permission to examine the lair of the lich Farnirras the "
"Thoughtful. After completing their research, the wizards spent a long, long time "
"thanking the {mf|king|queen} for freeing the world of that monster! In their "
"opinion, he'd been capable of causing the end of the world — maybe even two worlds!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7742c9ee-34fe-48c7-be2d-92fce312a095"
msgid ""
"{d|Evindra}Evindra{/d} was glad to see the Lantern King's plans turned to dust. "
"She spent some time helping restore the kingdom after the calamity, then returned "
"home to the First World. They say the rebellious spirit of her cousin Nyrissa "
"awoke within her as well. Evindra is said to recount our story to the fey, "
"encouraging them to question the power and might of the Eldest."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd506b73-9200-42ee-a957-ece8440dad14"
msgid ""
"{d|Evindra}Evindra{/d} settled down in the Tuskwater and visits the capital often. "
"She became a friend to the people of the kingdom, helping them and teaching them "
"how to treat the lake life with care. Parents allow their children to swim in the "
"Tuskwater at any time, day or night, secure in the knowledge that she'll look out "
"for them."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eeb147a1-7f10-4a3e-a1c1-e6d1af0f988c"
msgid ""
"After the victory, the Storyteller abandoned his affairs and began spending a lot "
"of time alone in contemplation. He eventually bid farewell to the {mf|king|queen} "
"and left {mf|his|her} lands, but I suspect the inhabitants of Golarion haven't "
"heard the last of this mysterious traveler, for his own story is hardly finished."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6890c9bc-a2ce-4d4e-82ae-8ed24a4adeaa"
msgid ""
"Amiri stayed close friends with {d|Nilak}Nilak{/d}, but she remained a pariah to "
"all the other members of the Six Bears tribe. Despite all the wisdom of their new "
"chief, the tribe never found its place among the unfamiliar plains and cities, and "
"they soon broke apart. The two friends left the kingdom together, setting off to "
"find their own adventures — enough that it would take a separate book to tell them "
"all!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fbab154c-f629-4fd0-9687-fa8e59c96342"
msgid ""
"Amiri remained a pariah to her native tribe, but she stayed close friends with {d|"
"Nilak}Nilak{/d}, who ruled the Six Bears wisely and taught them to survive in the "
"unfamiliar plains and cities. The restless barbarian would often travel for long "
"stretches of time, but sooner or later she would always return to her old friends, "
"bragging about new scars and recounting new feats, many of which Nilak "
"immortalized in song."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "396672c5-7c92-4672-86e6-2bbbdb33820c"
msgid ""
"We never saw Amiri again. Perhaps she got lost somewhere in the First World, or "
"maybe she found some other way back — who knows? I doubt that stubborn barbarian "
"would just vanish without a trace. As for the Six Bears, they returned to the "
"mountains, out to the farthest, wildest backwoods they could find, and lived there "
"ruled by their primal laws."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "780b5c86-aa53-41f6-85c3-f9791f9cdeac"
msgid ""
"Valerie stayed to serve the {mf|king|queen}, and to this day, she continues to be "
"a {d|Valerie Shelyn}muse{/d} to many people — not just bards and admirers, but to "
"warriors as well! Honest and resilient, Valerie is not just famous for her feats "
"in battle, but also for her patience and kindness, which she says the {mf|king|"
"queen} helped her discover within herself!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d06ae83-1a58-40df-af25-4fdcba30523f"
msgid ""
"Valerie stayed to serve the {mf|king|queen}, and to this day, she terrifies any "
"who would dare break the law. {d|Valerie No Shelyn}Forceful{/d} and assertive, "
"Valerie has finally shed her crowd of admirers and set herself upon the path of "
"ultimate law — the same path so honored by the austere Hellknights. Need I even "
"mention that Valerie eventually decided to try on their black armor, only to find "
"that it was a perfect fit?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f6a1c356-cf9f-4dfe-ba06-92f04fbb921b"
msgid ""
"Harrim became famous, {d|Harrim Neutral}respected{/d} by dwarves throughout our "
"kingdom as well as our neighbors, even as far as the Five Kings Mountains. He's "
"often been asked to help out or teach others, and he's never denied anyone, "
"despite his grumbling. Some people even listen to his preaching — lucky for us, "
"there's a lot less howling about the end of the world now, and more wise words of "
"moderation and humility. Not all of his disciples turned to Groetus, but everyone "
"took away something useful from his teachings."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fd7e0628-9d90-4fda-a768-3719bca25d37"
msgid ""
"Harrim went completely {d|Harrim Badabum}mad{/d}... or perhaps understood the true "
"wisdom of Groetus — I'm not really sure if there's a difference. He left the "
"palace, barefoot, taking only a cane with him as he went off to preach. He died "
"destitute, somewhere along the side of the road — but they say you can still meet "
"a ghost with a disheveled beard along the kingdom's roads, mumbling something "
"about the end of the world. And if something suddenly breaks in someone's house, "
"people commonly say, \\\"Harrim touched it!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0e6db11e-9d10-4825-9486-52a36eabac76"
msgid ""
"Jaethal spent some time at the {mf|king|queen}'s court, but it became "
"progressively harder for her to hide her true {d|Jaethal Kills Daughter}nature{/d} "
"from the omnipresent servants of Pharasma. Realizing the risk, she reluctantly "
"left the kingdom, and she soon sent a message from Geb. In a country populated "
"mainly by undead, Jaethal fit in well, especially with her skills and Urgathoa's "
"blessing. She quickly gained fame and influence there, even gaining the favor of "
"Arazni, the de facto ruler of Geb."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b257b85-823b-4a44-8cdc-ad889fb433c4"
msgid ""
"One moonless night, Jaethal mysteriously disappeared! Soon, frightened fishers "
"discovered her body (really truly dead now). A young elf named Nortellara came to "
"the funeral, claiming to be the daughter of the deceased. She didn't grieve for "
"her mother overmuch, and she began carousing almost straightaway, moving from "
"balls to feasts to hunts! She acquired a crowd of admirers and treated the {mf|"
"king|queen} as though they'd known each other a hundred years or more. Some even "
"assumed they were — ahem — particularly close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94981bca-182d-48a5-a6ef-300399b98cc3"
msgid ""
"Jaethal spent some time at the {mf|king|queen}'s court, but she then left to... do "
"whatever it was her new goddess required. She must have become a great inquisitor "
"for Pharasma, as no one would know the ways of the undead and Urgathoa's cultists "
"as well as a {d|Jaethal Pharasma}former{/d} undead cultist would! She was also "
"seen in the company of Salim Ghadafar — it's unlikely the two became friends, "
"being so different from one another, but it's a known fact that they worked "
"together."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2a3cb3c-5aef-4272-a75f-76c5dbc58f7d"
msgid ""
"Octavia didn't stay still for very long — soon, she and Reg went to Numeria and "
"started a huge slave rebellion there. They didn't manage to destroy the Technic "
"League, but to this day, slaves speak their names with admiration, and slavers "
"with terror. Over the course of their journey, the two grew as close as ever, "
"leaving their quarrels and resentments behind. After returning from Numeria, "
"Octavia settled in her mother's house and became the {mf|king|queen}'s advisor and "
"loyal companion."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3ddcd1e8-9156-4e49-8d3b-9f92dd424176"
msgid ""
"Octavia stayed in the capital as the {mf|king|queen}'s advisor and loyal "
"companion, a true socialite, and one of the most influential (and desirable!) "
"women in the entire kingdom. The balls put on by Octavia were frequented by "
"nobility from every neighboring country — and she enjoys bragging to barons and "
"counts alike that she achieved her status all on her own, a common half-breed from "
"no family to speak of. Only Regongar spoils her happiness — they fight constantly, "
"and she fears that his drinking or some other stupid trick of his will drive him "
"to an early grave."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a3c4b92-bbe3-4798-959c-8f7e0cb6d73c"
msgid ""
"Regongar left for Numeria with Octavia to start a slave rebellion. Over the "
"journey, he really matured and learned to understand others, as well as to control "
"his anger. After he returned, he took a position in the {mf|king|queen}'s court — "
"being both formidable and charming, he inspired fear in the hearts of some and "
"lust in others. There are even some rumors that he almost talked Octavia into "
"marrying him... and possibly even continuing the Della Fiorni line!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "992060fc-863b-4384-970a-3fefb2c17fd9"
msgid ""
"Regongar hung up his sword and began the life of luxury he'd always wanted. "
"Admirers lined up outside his door — women and men alike. He indulged in every "
"pleasure, wearing luxurious clothes and hosting orgies that would make Calistria "
"blush. He quarreled more and more often with Octavia, who feared his drinking and "
"unruly temper would drive him to an early grave — after these fights, he'd drown "
"his resentment in wine. These days, he's hardly ever sober, and his trembling "
"hands can barely even hold a sword."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b68ee54f-a8c7-4d59-84b1-a0a80917a310"
msgid ""
"Once the war was over, Tristian kept his {d|Tristian Angel}promise{/d} to "
"Sarenrae. In the middle of celebrating the {mf|king|queen}'s victory, the priest "
"suddenly disappeared in a flash of light — vanishing forever. I hope Sarenrae "
"didn't take the movanic deva's memory, so her servant might still remember us and "
"the Stolen Lands... or if she did, I hope he was at least able to forget "
"everything about the lands in which he endured so much suffering."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "109b7e48-a9a2-486c-bca3-468044fb2f7b"
msgid ""
"Tristian {d|Tristian Mortal}stayed{/d} in the Stolen Lands. Endowed with a special "
"blessing of Sarenrae, the priest became known as a great healer and went on to "
"perform many more miracles. I'd say the movanic deva deserves the right to rejoin "
"Sarenrae's divine army — I hope the goddess will think the same when Tristian's "
"hour comes and his soul is up for a new judgment!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba2dec94-e401-41cb-bbb2-0da95f6036f9"
msgid ""
"Ekun spent a few years in the Stolen Lands, and in that time won glory as the most "
"rugged monster {d|Ekun Hunt}hunter{/d} in all the River Kingdoms! The ranger "
"exterminated even the most harmless of the monsters around the capital, then moved "
"on to other lands and new victories. They say the ruthless avenger and slayer of "
"wild monsters made it as far as Katapesh! That's where his trail went cold — I'm "
"afraid Ekun may have become the prey of one of his targets..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5be8f400-efab-46ae-a92f-fc07c0feb497"
msgid ""
"After the war ended, Ekun hung his bow on the wall and {d|Ekun Ritual}traded{/d} "
"the path of the ranger in for the craft of the carpenter. It may not be the most "
"heroic ending to a tragic story like his, but as Torag is my witness, Ekun's happy "
"with it — as is Elina, who became his wife and is bearing his child. Any baby born "
"into this family will be pretty lucky, since the {mf|king|queen} {mf|him|her}self "
"still visits {mf|his|her} old friend, and will likely become the child's patron!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99a8718b-246c-43b6-a216-7e1b3fafb5d4"
msgid ""
"Jubilost {d|Jubilost Immortal}devoted{/d} himself to exploring the First World, "
"and his works became a real sensation! But with each year, his appearances both in "
"our kingdom and in Absalom lessened. He spoke often of strange, obscure things, "
"and grumbled that the others just didn't understand him. It seemed almost as "
"though his former friends, and even our world itself, didn't interest him anymore. "
"One day, Jubilost set off on another expedition... and got lost. No one in "
"Golarion has heard from him since."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a5e9953b-6ee7-429f-a4f8-d498f20b7bfe"
msgid ""
"Jubilost returned to the life of a traveling explorer, frequently visiting his "
"favorite kingdom — he said so himself! — {kingdomname}. His famous works studying "
"the First World all opened with a dedication to his long-time companion, {mf|King|"
"Queen} {name}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2f4de2a-ee35-4391-833c-e7d5c3c4eaf8"
msgid ""
"As for Nok-Nok — apologies, I mean \\\"{d|Nok Hero}Hero{/d}\\\" Nok-Nok — he "
"continued his questionably heroic efforts in the Stolen Lands. Despite whatever "
"mess he fell into, no matter the danger he leapt into, he always seemed to scrape "
"through just a little better off than before. Like true heroes, he simply never "
"gave up, struggling on and meeting the challenge of each new day with a spirit "
"that no mishap or misfortune could ever quell."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec4be0fb-9a76-4789-ad36-5256755e9c08"
msgid ""
"The {mf|king|queen} had to make a lot of difficult decisions, but Octavia was "
"always there to make {mf|his|her} life easier. Closer than any other advisor and "
"more loyal than any other ally, she prompted an elegant exit out of difficult "
"situations a good many times. Such love could only be envied by the monarchs of "
"more noble families, themselves tied down with the bonds of dynastic marriages!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a8fe0edc-ccef-42de-b550-001bffe25e01"
msgid ""
"Regongar was by the {mf|king|queen}'s side day and night — {mf|his|her} right "
"hand, closest friend, and most trusted companion. He didn't interfere in ruling "
"the country, but there were rumors of secret assignments he completed under royal "
"orders... not to mention the festivities he hosted when there weren't any matters "
"of state to attend to!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91307e2c-61bb-41e2-94ec-93282204ebd6"
msgid ""
"Octavia and Regongar were by the {mf|king|queen}'s side day and night — {mf|his|"
"her} most intimate partners and most trusted companions. Coming together over so "
"many battles, they could even finish each other's sentences, ruling the kingdom in "
"the same dashing manner that they once killed monsters. Such love is rare for two "
"— and simply a miracle for three!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ceefbf3-8dbb-4462-a1ee-9762650f2df4"
msgid ""
"Beyond the many advisors and companions, there was always someone else near the "
"queen — a faithful truelove, who devoted his worldly life to the one he cherished "
"with all his heart. Wherever the queen went, whatever trials fell upon her, "
"Tristian was always near, ready to support and protect his chosen one."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8b0ec555-32b9-4743-81b5-dce682ae5865"
msgid ""
"The king and Valerie stayed together — lovers and companions, bound not only by "
"love, but by common duty. The amazing union underlies dozens of ballads and poems "
"written by delighted subjects and echoed all throughout Avistan. There's more "
"fiction than truth in those poems, of course — our hero and his beloved keep their "
"relationship well behind closed doors."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c11f060-43ad-448b-932f-35dcb3a74173"
msgid ""
"Nyrissa and her beloved {name} live happily together, setting up the kingdom hand "
"in hand. Their union somehow linked the unruliness of the First World with the "
"order of Material Plane. Nyrissa managed to bring forth the daring vision for "
"which she had once been cursed — the creation of her dream country. {kingdomname} "
"is now a flourishing land, taking the best of both wild nature and structured "
"civilization, and our capital is an amazing garden city, which visitors from all "
"over Golarion come to see!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac4222c0-d815-40a8-bd86-8b5e8f8b5899"
msgid ""
"Despite all the woes that befell the country, {mf|King|Queen} {Name} remains a "
"strong leader. Many noble houses from neighboring lands wouldn't hesitate to be "
"related to {mf|him|her}, and they regularly send a variety of marriage proposals."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "416a968f-7383-4b36-b754-af312a642c2e"
msgid ""
"As for myself — the author of this book, Linzi-who-never-chose-a-fancy-nickname... "
"I'm still here, inside my creation within the capital library. I live just like I "
"always dreamed — surrounded by people and books. And not a day goes by without "
"someone turning my pages. My story inspired many others to take up the quill. My "
"readers have written many fierce books, articles, and pamphlets, flinging {d|Linzi "
"Chaotic}truth{/d} in the faces of tyrants! What more could I dream of? I hope, oh "
"honored reader, that this story offered you some daring ideas... or at least some "
"entertainment! In any case, it's time to set the final period."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca3584e2-fd89-411d-b968-2af8fe53d78e"
msgid ""
"As for myself — the author of this book, Linzi-who-never-chose-a-fancy-nickname... "
"I'm still here, inside my creation within the capital library. I live just like I "
"always dreamed — surrounded by people and books. And not a day goes by without "
"someone turning my pages. My story {d|Linzi Good}inspired{/d} many others to take "
"up the quill. My readers have written many beautiful books and poems, transporting "
"prisoners of humdrum lives into worlds of endless fantasy. What more could I dream "
"of? I hope, oh honored reader, that this story inspired some creativity in you... "
"or at least offered some entertainment! In any case, it's time to set the final "
"period."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b59d37db-b14f-4572-b826-d6ef551010b4"
msgid ""
"As for myself — the author of this book, Linzi-who-never-chose-a-pretty-"
"nickname... I stayed here, within my own book, to watch what happens in the "
"kingdom and one day write this epilogue. I hope, oh honored reader, that you "
"learned something important from this story... or at least were entertained by it. "
"And now that it's concluded, I have only to set the final period and go silent "
"forever."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "601ad162-b758-4a67-98df-b485fc2a476e"
msgid ""
"Kassil Aldori, who lost an arm during the war, became a permanent ambassador of "
"Rostland at our court."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a038ca5b-5aae-42ae-8cc3-8496cddbcdf3"
msgid ""
"Shandra Mervey became an ambassador at our court once more. That arrogant harpy "
"misses no chance to remind us that House Surtova considers us nothing more than "
"vassals!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7c5fb7f-b002-46e9-8237-7be72ce7cb11"
msgid ""
"Kassil Aldori settled in our capital, though he left politics to teach dueling."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91b2574c-3b59-4e8f-be66-a5b3b4ebb0a1"
msgid ""
"Shandra Mervey returned to our court, but just half a year later she was poisoned "
"— no one ever found out who did it or why."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ebc31822-8a02-4a0e-b512-3bf2dffe9aff"
msgid ""
"Governor {d|c51 Governor Moskoni}Moskoni{/d} dips into these rivers with both "
"hands, of course, but the {mf|king|queen} looks the other way, since he's loyal "
"and he governs the city well."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff4af8a2-cdd8-4b0d-a909-90e93bccdc8b"
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, we get much less of this money than we would like — Governor {d|c51 "
"Governor Liacenca}Liacenza{/d} turned out to be helpless against widespread "
"embezzlement."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45e54a72-0ba0-456f-ac75-835c74b3bdcb"
msgid ""
"{d|c51 Governor Vereel}Kharne Vereel{/d} wasn't governor for long. Walking around "
"the city one day, in a drug-induced delirium, he grabbed a tin of solvent from a "
"construction worker in the street. Taking it for mead, he drank it. An ignominious "
"— if somehow fitting — death, to be sure."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "275e4e9e-f700-4cce-9d9f-d5671d3a740d"
msgid ""
"Governor {d|c51 Governor Moskoni}Moskoni{/d} tried to gain control of the "
"situation at first, but one day he simply left the country, taking the city "
"treasury along with him."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55814179-c699-4d74-9cd3-577f9dd6148d"
msgid ""
"Governor {d|c51 Governor Liacenca}Liacenza{/d} became one of the first victims of "
"the revolutionaries — a fireball was thrown into his carriage in the middle of the "
"street."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22be2931-c9a3-4a32-9835-c735c36d1e64"
msgid ""
"Governor {d|c51 Governor Vereel}Kharne Vereel{/d}, fearing for his life, locked "
"himself in his chambers. A week later, they found him dead, surrounded by empty "
"bottles and bloodbrush extract vials."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "871acd00-6e61-47f9-ab99-e62913289e28"
msgid ""
"Governor {d|c51 Governor Moskoni}Moskoni{/d} is so fat now he can barely walk. "
"Citizens pronounce his name in a respectful whisper."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a876edd-9ba7-41ec-863f-176256d4913f"
msgid ""
"Gasperre {d|c51 Governor Liacenca}Liacenza{/d} is governor in name only — he "
"gathers taxes, but he has no real influence over the city, which is divided up by "
"the gangs."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3a1b8eda-2e43-40b7-881d-302635d5065e"
msgid ""
"Kharne {d|c51 Governor Vereel}Vereel{/d} wasn't governor for long. He was found "
"hanged in the central square, with a sign on his chest saying \\\"Irovetti's "
"Bootlicker.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "368a882a-70ee-4c2e-83ad-973dd1aab4b3"
msgid ""
"Governor {d|c51 Governor Moskoni}Moskoni{/d} still tries to attract attention to "
"the city by holding the Rushlight tournament every year — but it's not very "
"popular these days."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "177d0768-650f-4a35-9fcb-946cb15a5a37"
msgid ""
"Governor {d|c51 Governor Liacenca}Liacenza{/d} remembers what the {mf|king|queen} "
"did for him and serves {mf|him|her} truthfully and loyally."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ad09d5a-b0dc-45b1-baec-aea5e4a1feb7"
msgid ""
"Only Governor Kharne {d|c51 Governor Vereel}Vereel{/d} is happy — his poison is in "
"pretty high demand in a boring city with no prospects."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a676cc35-a9a1-4234-93e0-4ff12ee097fd"
msgid ""
"Making sure her sister was safe, the former bandit {d|Kressle}Kressle{/d} traveled "
"south. Her trail went cold somewhere in Absalom's docks. They say she changed her "
"name again and now serves on a trade ship, hiding from old acquaintances."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "abe1e51b-5d04-4570-aa50-27af147dadc8"
msgid ""
"Well, there are many like Tsanna in the Stolen Lands, now — because the {mf|king|"
"queen} announced their religion lawful within {mf|his|her} lands! I'm afraid the "
"ruler and {mf|his|her} advisors would regret that decision on more than a few "
"occasions — in the last year alone, three squadrons of Iomedae's paladins arrived "
"in the kingdom!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e97a3646-fcba-4733-9faa-ea0eb4e7baa0"
msgid ""
"Falchos and Tiressia managed to restore the magic forest, once freed of the anger "
"of the {d|c21 FT saved}Scythe Tree{/d}. People returned to the abandoned village, "
"and it became a haven of friendship between the fey and ordinary people, just like "
"old times."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26ed9da3-c60e-42d6-a508-62955f60e048"
msgid ""
"After Nyrissa's curse was lifted, the maimed face of the last Defaced Sister began "
"healing, little by little. She still keeps her distance from people, but she's "
"always glad to see the {mf|king|queen}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bedcefb5-5d44-4203-b14e-8a0a1ebb3a15"
msgid ""
"The ancient artifacts gathered by the {mf|king|queen} built the foundation of a "
"museum collection that has become famous even in far-off Absalom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69607548-7b9e-437d-ba5e-90e44d75d907"
msgid ""
"The Tiger Lords revered Amiri as a great hero, but she didn't stay chieftain for "
"long — after all, she was much better at crushing skulls than giving orders!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8836014a-52cb-4836-8ec4-52c6dea88af0"
msgid ""
"Sometimes, during Jubilost's performances, all kinds of chaos would break loose! "
"Viewers turned into unicorns, or would be teleported to the top of a cliff. Later, "
"Jubilost would be seen arguing fiercely with a pretty gnome named {d|Jubilost Nyrd}"
"Nyrd{/d}. The arguments looked very... sweet, and intimate!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5145f512-c20a-40c9-a3cf-f9c7d4a70408"
msgid ""
"Another name was also mentioned — \\\"To {d|Jubilost Xae}Xae{/d}, my guide and "
"inspiration.\\\" Admirers would ask Jubilost many times about this mystery lady, "
"but he would only chuckle, hitch his knapsack on his shoulder, and return to storm "
"the vast expanses of the First World once again!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0957678b-e3d7-4263-9631-9007a24c228a"
msgid ""
"Their wedding was legendary. Octavia became a real queen — only old friends would "
"be able to recognize the grand dame as that giggling lass they used to share tales "
"with by the fire."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f187750f-37f6-47a9-9c01-92d987ad7f1c"
msgid ""
"Not to mention the festivities he and {Name} held to celebrate the marriage! It "
"must be said, he refused to call himself a king, instead taking the title of "
"Prince Consort."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94c15969-a8a6-4083-a95f-b8b7d9fe7dc9"
msgid ""
"In the neighboring lands, their triple wedding was a scandal — but who would dare "
"try to forbid THEM from doing anything? They still rule together — the incredible "
"{mf|kings and queen|queens and king} of an incredible kingdom."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87ce57ee-6f3e-4bb8-a865-1a1822f82e5b"
msgid ""
"And no wonder — soon after the war ended, the queen and Tristian took their "
"wedding vows! And though Tristian never claimed any power over the kingdom, his "
"common sense and kindness always played a part in the queen's decisions."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20b7ae5c-7706-4869-b545-8beb8f15c0e4"
msgid ""
"The only thing kept in the chronicles in the truest detail is the grand royal "
"wedding! Valerie became a worthy and honest ruler (like anyone doubted she would), "
"and while their subjects can't wait for an heir, the beautiful royal couple seems "
"to be in no hurry to continue their lineage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6fe9dcce-cc5b-4ecc-a8b6-7998d44e44bf"
msgid ""
"Valerie stayed to serve the {mf|king|queen}, but not for long — she soon laid down "
"her weapon to start her own family. Valerie married a simple farmer and bore him "
"two beautiful children. The settled away from the capital, where she was soon "
"forgotten."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63bddddd-6243-4fa2-84f0-652e10a75868"
msgid ""
"...Sometimes, on clear spring nights, the {mf|king|queen} saw... dreams. In them, "
"the nymph {d|c61 Nyrissa Briar}Nyrissa{/d}, pale and exhausted, walked through "
"endless mist as she helplessly searched for salvation."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd20e778-4a9f-4b5d-a627-0dc3f275819c"
msgid ""
"...Sometimes, on clear spring nights, the {mf|king|queen} saw... dreams. In them, "
"the nymph {d|c61 Nyrissa Evil}Nyrissa{/d}, fierce and wounded, battled the "
"Jabberwock, died, and returned to life... again... and again... and again..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4d7dd47-38db-49b4-b2ee-6f59dba32946"
msgid ""
"As for Nok-Nok — apologies, I mean \\\"{d|Nok Jester}Jester{/d}\\\" Nok-Nok — he "
"continued to be a great source of entertainment for the kingdom, both in and out "
"of the throne room... sometimes even on purpose.\\nHis antics in the kingdom had "
"an additional effect — aside from bringing joy and amusement to the citizens, it "
"also softened the common view of goblins. They even became welcome in the streets "
"of the city — for a time. While he may not have become the \\\"Hero\\\" he "
"envisioned, Nok-Nok did find himself and his inner strengths thanks to his {mf|"
"king|queen}. If you should ever find yourself in the kingdom, be sure to seek him "
"out — he'll gladly regale you with some new tale of adventure, one that will "
"surely make you smile, whether our foolhardy, clumsy, well-intentioned goblin "
"means to or not."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cffa9e27-ac00-4bc4-a129-7bf12d6dc424"
msgid ""
"The... slightly inaccurate... {d|Nok Statue Ok}statue{/d} of him and the {mf|king|"
"queen} still stands in the square to this day, the two figures side by side. I've "
"always felt that, while the heights may be a bit... off, let's say... it "
"accurately reflects the size in spirit of the goblin hero who'd been nurtured by "
"the teachings of his {mf|king|queen}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bcca74ae-20ca-425b-a0cd-e9c50999c8c0"
msgid ""
"But at that moment, Shyka broke {d|c61 Crown Shyka}the First Crown{/d}. You "
"remember, of course, that she is — I mean, they are — the Eldest of time, right? "
"They broke the crown in the past and the present, allowing the elf king to return "
"to his subjects and save his kingdom. A single grain of dust disappeared from the "
"cup. And with the condition for forgiveness no longer fulfilled, Nyrissa dropped "
"dead, having barely touched a drop. The Lantern King's performance was ruined, and "
"the other Eldest all laughed at him. Serves him right!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa9abce5-c665-4dbc-90e2-df342fd08c21"
msgid ""
"Love can bring anyone together, even creatures of different worlds. The queen and "
"Tristian, joining their hearts, knew the truth — but they decided even the short "
"time Sarenrae would give them was worth the torture of parting. The goddess was "
"merciful, waiting a full year after the victory before returning the movanic deva "
"to her flock, but the queen's heart was still broken."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11bd3677-d7bd-48b8-bca9-d8e19a32fc90"
msgid ""
"There was no place for art in the new Pitax. Students and teachers from the "
"academy were scattered to the winds. Some found a place in neighboring courts, "
"while others set off to earn some coin in roadside taverns. A third group, "
"harboring anger and resentment toward the {mf|king|queen}, began weaving "
"revolutionary plots. The {d|c51 Academy Died}ruins{/d} of the Academy of the Arts "
"still stand in the middle of the city, overrun with ivy — empty and unwanted."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cbb049df-0ce7-4b36-8298-ad04bfb3e10f"
msgid ""
"The Sweet Teeth departed on a journey, hoping to see as many wonders as possible — "
"of this world and others! They keep sending us news from every corner of the map. "
"Their bright-painted wagon, drawn by a bull mastodon, crisscrosses Golarion, "
"somehow appearing in the center of one incredible story after another."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06b42ff2-2ce0-439c-9ac2-efb54fb88162"
msgid ""
"Kalikke remained in the kingdom, though her desire to witness the world's wonders "
"keeps driving her to take long journeys! But when she is home, she spends much of "
"her spare time with her sister. They don't quarrel any more, and have stopped "
"dragging each other into trouble."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb259ce6-48c2-48b1-9bdc-8f20e6b7da28"
msgid ""
"Kanerah settled down in the capital, and became a very busy entrepreneur. It seems "
"as though every hour is planned, meeting with rich merchants, or inventors whose "
"work she's promoting. But on her way home, she never fails to stop at the market, "
"to personally buy some sweets for her sister."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "abbd2961-8e67-4e8a-86b7-f3c13ae46e4c"
msgid ""
"Between Kanerah's business sense and Kalikke's charm, they've founded and "
"successfully run not one but three organizations: a trading house, a shelter for "
"tiefling children, and a school of magic devoted to Nethys."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b6533b7d-cba0-4409-b685-f3d89a0ce2f4"
msgid ""
"Kalikke has became calmer and wiser, but her friends no longer hear her singing by "
"the fire any more. If she does write poems, she keeps them hidden away. She "
"doesn't quarrel with her sister, but perhaps because she's grown weary of "
"fighting, and not because they've truly made peace."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94868fa5-bab5-4203-bde6-3992180d2abf"
msgid ""
"Kanerah's precocious spirit seems to have evaporated. She doesn't jeer and mock "
"others as much as she used to, and her friends mourn her sharp wit. She's grown "
"amicable with her sister, but her liveliness, emotional tantrums and deep caring "
"have given way to a calm, almost businesslike acceptance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a52c5464-72a7-4ea6-beac-1cf5d97569b7"
msgid ""
"Absent her sister's influence, and after enduring their {d|TTQ3_KanerahAgreed}"
"break{/d}, Kalikke has become harsher and more intolerant of evil. She used all "
"her influence as the legendary {mf|King|Queen}'s companion to create a string of "
"shelters for young tieflings. These children have become her personal army, and as "
"they matured, many have devoted their lives to fighting evil — especially devils "
"and their plots."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b903aa84-94d0-46ab-966d-3900c4214b69"
msgid ""
"Kanerah {d|TTQ3_KalikkeAgreed}stayed{/d} on at the court, believing the young "
"kingdom was perfect ground for sowing the seeds of her own power and prosperity. "
"Caravans of Kanerah's trading house crisscross all of Golarion, and even into "
"other planes, as she herself bathes in luxury and the attentions of her admirers. "
"But those who know her better whisper how cold and dispassionate this powerful "
"woman has become."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe5fee65-3ea5-4a49-b00d-778c6a4c8e8f"
msgid ""
"Kalikke did not remain in our lands for long. She never lost hope of discovering "
"some news of her sister's fate, and the sorrow in her heart drove her to restless "
"journey. One day she left without saying goodbye — no one knows where — taking "
"along only the simple things she fled with from Qadira."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fa0210bc-9940-4534-9ffd-2434f0172a4d"
msgid ""
"Many years after, we received news of the sisters' fate. As it turned out, Kanerah "
"was {d|TTQ3_KanerahDevil}killed{/d} by the Forefather, and her soul, after "
"enduring terrible suffering, was used to create a new she-devil. Somewhere on the "
"roads of Golarion, this terrifying creature crossed paths with Kalikke, but no one "
"knows how this meeting ended."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb5629c9-fc6c-401e-a89a-a0ed23cf6dd8"
msgid ""
"Kanerah celebrated the victory along with everyone else, but was soon consumed by "
"black thoughts about her missing sister. One day we discovered her house empty, "
"her things sold, and Kanerah herself gone. All that remained was a short goodbye "
"note."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2626a384-7c2e-407c-91d7-05f4f9d21b00"
msgid ""
"The note explained that Kanerah had sold her soul to one of the most powerful "
"devils in Hell. With his help, she hoped to {d|TTQ3_KalikkeDevil}save{/d} Kalikke "
"from the Forefather. 'In case of failure,' Kanerah wrote in her usual no-nonsense "
"manner, 'my soul will be in Hell, and my sister and I will at least share the same "
"fate.' Alas, a search turned up nothing, and we never discovered how their story "
"ended."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f46f2f98-7f69-453b-b782-d1264e6f702c"
msgid ""
"The kingdom's bards wrote a thousand ballads about love of the {mf|King|Queen} for "
"the beautiful tiefling from Qadira. Kalikke herself shies from attention, and "
"hiding away from the public eye. She instead spends all her time on her shelter "
"for tiefling children, while supporting the {mf|King|Queen} in all matters. The "
"grand royal palace has become much cozier, with the sound of her soft songs "
"echoing below its vaults."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b76c265d-0105-4e5c-9513-5c9a25a9725e"
msgid ""
"Even the wedding, and her new title of Princess Consort, hasn't diminished "
"Kalikke's love of solitude. She often makes tea and prepares dinner for her dear "
"{mf|husband|wife}. Beautiful parks were laid out in all the kingdom's cities "
"according to her wishes, where lovebirds stroll in the sunlight."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7b6249ef-7112-45d4-958f-cd37fda75066"
msgid ""
"It seems there is no happier couple in the world than {name} and Kanerah! The "
"ardent tiefling girl now manages a vast number of trade deals, even as she dotes "
"upon her beloved. Those who knew her before are surprised – for few expected ever "
"to see so much sincere love in the eyes of the calculating, shrewd Kanerah!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7572380e-5927-4a43-a8a3-ba039e280ac5"
msgid ""
"Theirs was the most joyful royal wedding in all the lands, though the royal "
"dressmakers had to use all their wits to answer the orders of the lucky bride. – "
"Her dresses and accessories had to account for her tail, after all!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "386424c5-6c8a-465f-9122-e07a9dd27aa5"
msgid ""
"Word of the glorious {mf|King|Queen} traveled far — and stories of {mf|his|her} "
"tiefling partner spread just as quickly. Many of these tales were spoken in hushed "
"whisper, for no one wanted to incur Kanerah's displeasure by a careless word. "
"Being one of the most influential figures in the kingdom, she uses her powers "
"skillfully and prudently to increase its wealth and the influence of its {mf|King|"
"Queen}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed70d847-c6ee-462a-b0de-d835de8445ef"
msgid ""
"The crown on her head only strengthened Kanerah's position. Those who know her "
"well often wonder if there is more cold calculation in the royal couple than love. "
"But none doubt the strength of their union."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9721b81f-83c9-49eb-b5cf-a7b2df3382bb"
msgid ""
"It must be said that {name} found a double happiness in {mf|his|her} beloved twin "
"tieflings. The three of them are rarely seen together, because Kalikke looks after "
"her shelter for tiefling children, while Kanerah busies herself with trade deals — "
"and both sisters serve as patrons of a school of magic devoted to Nethys. But when "
"the incredible trio do happen to be seen together, just looking at them makes "
"everyone smile!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "efb536cd-da19-4433-9f12-77549a410911"
msgid ""
"And their common wedding was nothing short of spectacular! The magical fireworks "
"at its finale were the stuff of history, and ever since, many brides and grooms "
"across the neighboring lands have made it a habit to decorate their wedding hats "
"with little horns."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee00508c-b204-4d82-b33f-770b72543535"
msgid ""
"No one knows what happened to the vanished dwellers of Varnhold. It feels like "
"everyone just keeps trying to forget about them. There are still those who blame "
"the {mf|king|queen} for their disappearance... but they prefer to do so very, very "
"quietly!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "423adfb5-1d33-461e-8bdf-e7c1756831b4"
msgid ""
"{d|c21 Tartuk Lives}Tartuk{/d}, who never succeeded in restoring his gnome "
"appearance, seems to have completely forgotten about who he once was. It no longer "
"bothers him, for now the purple kobold has become a real king to his tribe! "
"Keeping his word to the {mf|king|queen}, Tartuk and his subjects behave "
"themselves, living peacefully with the citizens of nearby settlements. Some of the "
"reptiles even managed to find work digging wells and dungeons in people's "
"settlements — for a small fee, of course!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "669d7db2-e831-439c-858b-a62b31cfdcd0"
msgid "...asked the old man who he was."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dc27ebec-c91e-40cd-ad04-8d7d50e5155c"
msgid "...asked him how he could help us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d5e7843a-cc7e-4279-9f0f-65b9001e7aff"
msgid ""
"...bid the strange old man farewell and hurried to get as far away from him as "
"possible."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "760d8861-561a-49f6-95aa-911bee452ab3"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a803ac4f-8c79-47ab-b161-ea0ec572fac4"
msgid "...accepted the cleric's challenge and chose a diver from among our company."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5110a9b2-b512-4433-b621-7ee3bb2972ca"
msgid "...instead offered the old man a generous donation."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c95f625-00f3-48d4-9986-d8d3475039ee"
msgid "...kept on bearing the challenge."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "773eda88-f527-41fe-9bf5-826af07c315b"
msgid "...preferred to pay rather than put our lives at risk."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76cc0b16-68b6-4590-989e-f4b05c906543"
msgid ""
"...was unable to take any more and tried to break free of the old man's grasp."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cafc2b19-672e-48bc-8429-4ad6010404c4"
msgid "...preferred to drown rather than give in."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "277b3cb0-712a-4e88-b379-707440dbf049"
msgid ""
"While trying to cross a small river — there were tons of them in those parts — we "
"met an old man that would be considered suspicious even by local standards. He had "
"a gray beard, and his straw hat sat above a head of coarse, dirty, tousled hair. "
"The man was skillfully guiding a small raft along the river with a long pole, and "
"a fat water rat sat near his bare feet. Noticing us, the old man approached the "
"shore and hailed us in a local dialect so strange we could barely understand him. "
"\\\"Ah ah ah, good folk, where ya headin'? Fleein' somethin', or lookin' fer "
"somethin'? Ahhh, yer lookin', I can see it in yer eyes! Well, as the sayin' goes, "
"those what seek'll find! I can help ya, surely, if ya can pay me the right price!\\"
"\" After hearing the old man's colorful speech, we..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf311e5b-78c7-4d9d-8b5e-bdb118d95976"
msgid ""
"The old man set out a confusing explanation. It was difficult to follow, but we "
"gathered that he wasn't just a river rafter. He was a cleric in service to a minor "
"deity that was almost unknown outside the {g|River Kingdoms}River Kingdoms{/g} — "
"Hanspur, guardian of waterways and river travel. Neither good nor evil, and tricky "
"as the great Sellen River itself, this god could safely guide your boat past "
"sandbanks, rapids, and bandit ambushes to your final destination... or drown you "
"in the stillest backwater! Many river travelers raise prayers to him in their hour "
"of need, but few dare worship him openly — rumor has it that Hanspur is no "
"stranger to human sacrifices, and he takes toll from his followers in the "
"collection of those who've drowned."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71f5f46c-89f8-4cb7-9dbb-5c9d4156622f"
msgid ""
"With a sly smile, the old man waved to us with his crooked palm, then pushed off "
"the shore with his pole and began guiding his raft downstream. Soon, he had "
"disappeared from our sight."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72c5d41e-b257-4591-92eb-7fc099627115"
msgid ""
"\\\"Let's have a bet, eh? Yer all busy-hasty, tryin'a catch a livin' barbarian "
"with a dead name. But can ya dive? I'll maybe drown ya a little in the {g|River "
"Kingdoms}Father Sellen's{/g} waters, let ya know the taste of the river. If ya can "
"take it, I'll help in yer searchin'. If not — well, that's that, and we never see "
"each other again!\\\" The game offered by this cleric was a dangerous one — one of "
"our companions would have to put their life on the line to get help in our search "
"for Armag! We..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8af1a364-6b13-4d99-b75f-e5d9c15fe755"
msgid ""
"\\\"Ah ah ah, ya scared of divin'? Think ya can pay yer way out of it? Well ya "
"can! S'not cheap though, not at all. Divin's much the cheaper!\\\" The old man "
"giggled and proposed a staggering price for his help — 15000 gold coins! We..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1031371f-19bf-47a9-bf3b-4c2fdd0a6835"
msgid ""
"We needed the money, but we needed our lives more. So with heavy hearts, we paid "
"the hefty sum. Once he'd hid the heavy purse, the old man silently raised his "
"rough, crooked palm, and a vision engulfed us all."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea22b8c1-f378-4fc0-9502-3219c6e1e882"
msgid ""
"{name} bravely went to the old man. The cleric wasted no time, grabbing {name} by "
"{mf|his|her} hair and plunging {mf|him|her} headfirst into the muddy river, up to "
"{mf|his|her} shoulders."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0a0e53c-ab58-492d-9081-7500b31534b0"
msgid ""
"Water plants tickled {mf|his|her} face, and {mf|his|her} ears filled with the "
"whisper of sand rolling along the riverbed. {name} took it in stride, so to speak "
"— {mf|his|her} lungs held enough air to hang on for quite a while. A hazy vision "
"suddenly engulfed {name}'s mind — {mf||s}he saw {mf|him|her}self floating above "
"the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}, seeing the country from a bird's-eye view. "
"Another moment, and it seemed as though {mf||s}he would be able to focus {mf|his|"
"her} eyes and see Armag's tomb! {name}..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "662bbff6-3d12-4cf0-b0f2-479e1d44f625"
msgid ""
"{mf|His|Her} lungs were on fire. {mf|His|Her} heart pounded madly in {mf|his|her} "
"chest, as if trying to break free of this madness. {mf|His|Her} head started "
"ringing, and a single thought boomed through {mf|his|her} mind — air! Need air! "
"The vision was so close, though. Just a few more seconds were all it would take to "
"locate those damned barbarians... But even a few more seconds seemed impossible. "
"In this crucial moment, {name}..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b3f4a9ef-2d66-463c-9b67-8dba8a059a08"
msgid ""
"The cleric let his victim go with a grunt. \\\"People're so soft nowadays. How ya "
"manage to survive, bein' so feeble?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b977d9de-1f00-4e59-915f-061d826b676e"
msgid ""
"{name} parted {mf|his|her} lips and let the river water enter {mf|his|her} lungs. "
"On the verge of losing consciousness, {mf||s}he finally managed to catch the "
"elusive vision — and in that moment, everyone else saw what {mf||s}he was seeing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7ae00185-7998-44ac-9729-64dda329cf42"
msgid ""
"The wide and hilly {g|Glenebon}Glenebon Uplands{/g}, strewn with stones and carved "
"up by small rivers. In the central part, north of Flintrock Grassland, a barely "
"noticeable rock held an entrance like a gaping mouth that led underground. Some "
"grim barbarians sat near the entrance, as though waiting for something. This had "
"to be Armag's tomb — we'd finally located it! If we swept through the area, we "
"couldn't miss it — at least, that was our hope."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c29f6ee-4af1-4712-9695-b4e6897c938a"
msgid ""
"We wanted to thank the old man, but he was already on his way downstream, guiding "
"his raft around riverbanks with his pole as he hummed some melancholic song under "
"his breath."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5dc54d6d-6a73-4fb4-8879-67a99803ba7c"
msgid ""
"When we came back to our senses, the old man was already on his way downstream, "
"guiding his raft around riverbanks with his pole. {name} laid still, {mf|his|her} "
"face in the water. {mf|He|She} wasn't breathing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3454e751-2797-446f-96b5-bdb11df94d70"
msgid ""
"Paying no mind to the pain in {mf|his|her} chest or the blood rushing through {mf|"
"his|her} ears, {name} concentrated on the vision, trying {mf|his|her} best to put "
"it together, to focus on the mad chieftain's elusive tomb. Just as {mf||s}he "
"thought {mf||s}he would surely drown, the picture finally emerged — and when it "
"did, everyone else saw what {name} was seeing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af086aa2-bd27-4b4d-ae26-231306dafd99"
msgid ""
"The old man let his victim go. {name} pulled {mf|his|her} head from the water as "
"quickly as possible, gasping for air. The cleric grinned, took his pole, and "
"pushed off from the bank. He waved to us with his tanned, crooked palm as he "
"disappeared from our sight."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "699a14ae-f27e-4a64-9b7f-2d2aa272f746"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81ef2c2c-5797-4d13-be5a-c204f5a116fb"
msgid ""
"The familiar road rolled out before us as our hero{mf||ine} turned toward {g|"
"Brevoy}Brevoy{/g}. At {mf|his|her} back, the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} had "
"yet to reveal all their secrets to the daring adventurer who had decided {mf||s}he "
"would be the one to conquer them..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3c73a72-af94-40a0-a711-649d73da1837"
msgid ""
"But really, what would be the point of such a strange endeavor? Much easier to "
"just return to the reliable shelter of {g|Restov}Restov{/g}'s walls, set up shop, "
"maybe start a family, and live out the rest of your days like any other citizen — "
"in peace, warmth, a bit of boredom, and the full confidence that tomorrow will be "
"just as orderly and predictable as yesterday..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "500fcc76-00ee-4176-a94a-f12088fd4ec4"
msgid ""
"Hey, did you really think I'd choose a hero{mf||ine} like that for my book?! "
"Ridiculous! No, our daring leader, after indulging in a bit of nostalgia for that "
"old {g|Restov}Restov{/g} flair, turned {mf|his|her} back on faraway {g|Brevoy}"
"Brevoy{/g} and followed the call of destiny — to the unpredictable, wild, "
"beautiful {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ffb1bdde-b30f-4234-b9eb-2434fd01ca33"
msgid ""
"One daredevil among us was ready to climb down first to help the rest afterward."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca276da1-5ebe-44f1-8d4c-3d3e5c6cc93a"
msgid ""
"The place gave us a bad feeling, so we took out our map and thought about where we "
"should go next instead."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1727539-530f-4b0e-99d8-a1f8cbbf0426"
msgid ""
"The easiest way down would be to tie a rope to one of the trees growing along the "
"cliff. We decided the one to tie the knot and make the first descent would be..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3183aabb-0bb2-4d7d-bd83-24902f46ca6c"
msgid "Continue."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39f65ae9-ac0b-48bc-9965-73df96a97280"
msgid "One by one, we started climbing down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e8ee0f86-3f4d-4bea-b532-9faa9fe40345"
msgid "We decided to leave the place."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2546edd8-96b0-4ed1-8193-9d588e2dd30b"
msgid "We scattered and looked for shelter!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3bd3609-6e17-496d-bc26-3d165d471f1b"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7881899-b242-49c6-b5c7-f769c77802ba"
msgid "We started climbing back up the cliff!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a82ae10-bc5f-4294-8aeb-1e23ed435661"
msgid "We ran along the crevice floor!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e7b9cd81-361f-4972-8f9c-5742888d7d94"
msgid "It occurred to us that it might be time for a tactical retreat."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4c010074-7cfe-440b-be54-cf4afce842e6"
msgid "It was time to make ourselves scarce!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3cb8cd6a-f7ef-4d48-ac0e-e413a538f937"
msgid "And then {name} screamed what we were all thinking: \\\"RUN!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "316da1fe-23d7-4485-8d33-1cf98ca73117"
msgid "We examined the body below."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5ad04654-86b3-4782-a656-9afac67e2072"
msgid ""
"We inspected the wall of the gorge, trying to determine how difficult climbing "
"down would be."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1710dad6-7b74-4638-9eb4-8f6d647cf5a7"
msgid ""
"One of us agreed to be the first to climb down the path we'd chosen so they could "
"help the rest afterward."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31263713-a14b-4c2c-adfc-e2a7ecd632ac"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2e4dabc-219f-4e89-979c-6528e2b2cf0f"
msgid "We rushed to search the corpses."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e3360ea-1441-4aa9-99b4-41fd2299b33e"
msgid "We decided to break the eggs!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63ba8478-365e-4c1a-b67a-558d7c8108fe"
msgid "We tried to determine what the eggs were."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "195fcd2e-f07b-4e1f-bcc0-94908d66fb5e"
msgid "We decided to enter the hole in the rock."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa325b04-2534-45ae-8dd8-a77fa2d58855"
msgid ""
"We searched the dead body and looked at what had been scattered across the sand."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5754ab3c-377f-4325-b29b-4a2c94850977"
msgid ""
"Our way was blocked by a huge crevice in the ruddy rock, carved out by wind and "
"rain. As wide as three or four humans lying end to end, and at least three times "
"as deep, it stretched in both directions as far as we could see. Looking down over "
"the cliff, I saw something that made me wince — among the rocks on the sandy, "
"yellow-ocher floor was a body."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06529a00-a95b-4ac3-bb2d-2eb577050c17"
msgid ""
"The loose-fit embroidered frock and bronze skin marked him as a man of {g|Taldor}"
"Taldor{/g}. His knapsack lay half open nearby, and a variety of random things were "
"scattered along the floor of the gorge. Judging by the body's position, the poor "
"man fell to his death. It couldn't have been long before, as the rocks and sand "
"near his body were still dark with blood. Had he simply gotten too close to the "
"cliff and stumbled? Or did he try to climb down the rock face — and if so, why?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41a7416d-8e29-4c73-a1bb-f294f1dbc758"
msgid ""
"After rubbing some dust on {mf|his|her} hands and peeling off {mf|his|her} boots, "
"{name} dropped below the cliff edge and started climbing down. {mf|His|Her} deft "
"fingers found purchase in even the smallest cracks, and {mf|his|her} feet found "
"secure footholds along the way. Soon {name} smiled and waved up to us from the "
"bottom of the gorge."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb3af4c4-6320-4fad-834c-7128dfe47ef0"
msgid ""
"After rubbing some dust on {mf|his|her} hands and peeling off {mf|his|her} boots, "
"{name} dropped below the cliff edge and started climbing down. However, {mf|his|"
"her} way down was doomed from the start — ledges that seemed secure crumbled "
"beneath {mf|his|her} feet, and {mf|his|her} sweaty fingers slipped on the rocks. "
"By the middle of the climb down, {name} lost steam completely. {Name} cried out as "
"{mf|his|her} grip failed and {mf||s}he lost {mf|his|her} balance on one of the "
"ledges, crashing down heavily onto {mf|his|her} back. Fortunately, {mf||s}he "
"landed better than the stranger had, whose dead body lay nearby..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2f77cb9-ca04-4cec-bc05-bd99e12d07c9"
msgid ""
"Once again, a length of rope proved itself indispensable for adventuring — "
"especially when the adventurer knows how to tie a good knot! The climb down was "
"rather easy as we pushed our feet against the rock wall and descended into the "
"crevice. It took just half an hour for us all to climb down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e97317c-f0c6-4129-ba9c-d1d5b4196d82"
msgid ""
"{Name} prepared {mf|him|her}self quickly. After wrapping the rope around {mf|him|"
"her}self and taking a deep breath, {mf||s}he climbed over the edge and started "
"down. {mf|He|She} had made it halfway down when we discovered that one of the "
"knots had been poorly tied — it came undone, dropping {name} into the chasm! "
"Fortunately, the fall wasn't as bad as that of the unknown traveler still lying at "
"the bottom of the gorge... We retied the knot (better this time!) and continued "
"making our way down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1e9f1fe-83a0-4f49-8f25-3fbd62ee179b"
msgid ""
"After a brief rest, {name} caught the knapsacks we threw down to {mf|him|her}. "
"Spreading our blankets and coats on the ground and strategically scattering what "
"pillows we had around, {mf||s}he prepared to help us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0e059d7-f5ea-4212-bd56-870c72901e41"
msgid ""
"Voices echoed among the rocks — advice from those who'd reached to bottom mixed "
"along with some good-natured teasing, laughter with arguing...\\nSuddenly, a stone "
"slipped from under someone's foot and fell right toward the heads of those already "
"on the ground! Oh, poor {name}! {mf|He|She} had just started taking a drink of "
"water and wasn't paying attention..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ba2ca00a-9468-4b38-ae70-9ecad1622e93"
msgid ""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a51f583-f77e-4865-95fd-8b33fe555126"
msgid ""
"We all pushed the stone together, and it moved with ease — only to immediately "
"release an incredible stench into the air! We'd found a small cave, but what was "
"in it... Gods, it was full of charred, half-decomposed bodies! And lying among "
"them were huge gray eggs, covered with some sticky slime!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99376015-f514-4d59-90ae-68c846d2d4c0"
msgid ""
"That was when we heard some strange sounds — like someone moving huge mounds of "
"sand nearby. And the sound was coming toward us quickly!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c2008de-12da-496e-b134-d77379de56db"
msgid ""
"It smelled definitively of death, so we decided not to press our luck. But once "
"our team was outside, they made it less than a hundred steps before the ground "
"shuddered. A fountain of sand and dust erupted from the gorge, and we heard "
"strange sounds, as though the ground itself were muttering in some otherworldly "
"language with a dry, coarse tongue. We decided then to just trust our instincts "
"and leave the crevice!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25426079-1189-45f8-b4da-555ebeed0501"
msgid ""
"Don't underestimate the dexterity and reflexes of a seasoned adventurer, though! "
"Hearing our cries, {mf||s}he immediately jumped away and drew {mf|his|her} weapon, "
"looking around in a panic as the stone landed beside {mf|him|her} with a loud thud!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f2da0153-33b2-44cf-bac8-94c7c2b2914a"
msgid ""
"Our whole team finally made it down to investigate the dead man's body. We'd "
"guessed right — the poor fellow had clearly died on impact. A lot of different "
"types of gear had been scattered around in the sand — armor, tools, even scythes "
"and hammers... It was clear that this was much more than a single person could "
"carry."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89cc3405-f287-42a9-a552-2aeba8f77506"
msgid ""
"The noise continued to grow louder, emphasized with strange, dull sounds — as "
"though the ground itself were muttering in some otherworldly language with a dry, "
"coarse tongue.\\nAnd then a wave of sand rose from the far entrance of the gorge, "
"and the crest of the wave was coming straight for us!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "638886ed-0322-4008-895c-d2aaebff2e66"
msgid ""
"A fountain of sand and dust erupted not a hundred steps from us. From the ground "
"emerged a gigantic oblong head, attached to a long, muscular body with no "
"shoulders... The creature clearly resembled a worm, but it was thick as a century-"
"old oak! Its hide was covered with warts and oozed a sticky yellow secretion, "
"leaving a wet trail along the sand. Lightning shot from its gaping mouth, lighting "
"up its immense throat. The air took on the smell of a storm as the monster "
"barreled toward us!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7f24ecf9-bb45-408a-9f73-17a62da9475c"
msgid "\\\"But where?!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea3ad417-0201-4f28-8d43-7afa35706e57"
msgid ""
"The stone hit {mf|his|her} left shoulder, hard enough to draw blood. A bit more to "
"the right, and things could have ended much worse!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dde09baf-68b2-4734-814b-571f63e695d5"
msgid ""
"Bare rocks, narrow ledges, imperceptible cracks... The sheer rock wall promised a "
"difficult descent."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4f60d760-d8ef-4e96-9b91-9e81a55c3f61"
msgid ""
"It wouldn't be easy to climb down where we were, but a few dozen steps away we "
"found a good combination of bulges, cracks, and ledges that would make for a "
"somewhat more convenient path. After a bit of planning, we'd plotted a route that "
"even an amateur climber could handle."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66cf5963-1624-46fb-b416-892fdeeca61a"
msgid ""
"We'd never seen anything like them! But one of our party members recalled a story "
"they'd heard from a traveling scientist late one night a roadhouse. Drunk as could "
"be, the gnome laughed as she recounted a tale from some desert nomads about a "
"gigantic worm capable of killing you with a single touch and shooting lightning "
"from its eyes. Any time a caravan was lost to the sands, the nomads blamed it on "
"these worms. The female worms were said to gather dozens of corpses together to "
"keep their eggs warm, with the extra benefit of providing a food source for newly "
"born worms (other than their own brothers and sisters). Most citizens and academia "
"at large dismissed the story as superstition, of course."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bb640675-59a3-4bbd-8637-b4dc17f939bf"
msgid ""
"None of us had ever seen or even heard of eggs like these. The only thing we could "
"tell for certain was that these were left by some huge insect — they were made of "
"a silky skin, rather than shells."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1a7ee11-59f6-4c9d-9a67-96f767ef6101"
msgid ""
"We drew our weapons and struck the disgusting eggs! Our steel sank into the hard "
"skin, and gooey green slime oozed from the eggs. There was suddenly no air to "
"breathe — tears streamed from our eyes, our throats grew raspy, and we started "
"coughing — it wasn't long before we had to evacuate, but not before we'd managed "
"to destroy over half the clutch!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dcd1b7e6-fd8c-477c-8d2b-f22285a2c504"
msgid ""
"The gear in the knapsack and on the man's body were well preserved, but most of "
"what we found lying on the crevice floor was corroded and useless! Spearheads and "
"swords crumbled at the touch, and the armor had so many holes it looked like "
"delicate lace. If not for the poor condition, there'd have been enough to outfit a "
"whole regiment!\\nWe also noticed something that couldn't be seen from above — a "
"large stone stood blocking a hole in the wall. A sickly sweet smell leaked out "
"from the dark, narrow crack that remained."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63ca4b1b-14e4-4ed0-ac95-8bfc8af454d9"
msgid ""
"The corpses had been ravaged, covered with gigantic tooth marks and burned by "
"electricity and acid. Most of the clothing and items were unrecognizable, they "
"were so eaten by the acid — even the cave walls had been polished down by it. We "
"did manage to find a golden ring with a gemstone on one dead woman's finger, the "
"corrosive substance unable to damage the \\\"king of metals.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9445dce5-a8e5-4d43-b2a1-ab0622688050"
msgid ""
"We'd never climbed so fast in our lives! The worm was almost as fast, rapidly "
"crawling to the wall and reaching for our feet, trying to grab any of us it "
"could..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eecf1e41-bcbe-4e5c-ae97-073106adccd3"
msgid ""
"We'd never climbed so fast in our lives! The worm was almost as fast, rapidly "
"crawling to the wall, reaching out for us — and {name} was caught! Huge jaws "
"closed on {mf|his|her} foot. With a thunderous cry, {mf||s}he kicked the huge "
"muzzle with {mf|his|her} free foot — once, twice, thrice! But as the worm swung "
"its head, {name}'s arms flailed through the air as {mf||s}he disappeared..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec638f4e-8fdd-406c-9dda-b5e8f19b1fd4"
msgid ""
"We flew like the wind, pushed to amazing feats of agility despite our heavy gear! "
"We heard the crackling sound of electric discharge and the chomping of massive "
"jaws behind us as we fled."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91cecc21-2a42-40cc-8e4b-50b81f87b2cb"
msgid ""
"Most of the team dropped their backpacks and slipped into a crack in the crevice "
"wall... but {name}, trying to enter last, couldn't fit in no matter how hard {mf||"
"s}he tried! Swearing profusely, {mf||s}he laid prone behind the huge boulder that "
"covered the entrance to the cave. We all held our breath...\\nThe worm was so "
"close, we could see its dull, tiny eyes. Only the giant beast's heavy breathing "
"and the hissing sound of sand dissolving as acid dropped onto it broke the "
"oppressive silence. The monster swayed its head back and forth, seeking, until it "
"hit its nose on the boulder {name} was hiding behind..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "634c9cc3-2cf4-4ea7-95cf-882dd8c923bd"
msgid ""
"After making it up to the top of the cliff, we kept running until we were out of "
"breath. It was only then that we felt safe."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7b112c2-9ce9-4192-ba70-e18c6402b132"
msgid ""
"{Name}'s iron self-control didn't fail {mf|him|her} — {mf||s}he stayed motionless "
"on the ground behind the boulder. It felt like an eternity passed before the worm "
"turned and continued its search along the gorge..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e054bd06-705e-4ee1-b246-5b2af0994a8c"
msgid ""
"The worm grabbed at our feet several times, but it couldn't catch us! And finally, "
"the walls of the gorge dropped and the sand was gradually replaced by soil. We "
"weren't sure how we eventually lost the monster — we just ran and ran until we'd "
"left the gorge far behind us. Out of breath, our strength failing, we fell to the "
"ground."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94a797ec-f11a-482c-ab86-ddf6087c7367"
msgid ""
"{name} was running on {mf|his|her} last legs, and {mf||s}he fell further and "
"further behind us. In one great surge, the worm caught up to {mf|him|her}, and "
"{name} let out a bloodcurdling scream as {mf||s}he was pulled into the air, arms "
"flailing... We're not sure how or when we finally lost the monster."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db8e9019-7679-4ee5-abca-318075d2a27d"
msgid ""
"We waited for night, and after making sure we could see and hear no trace of the "
"worm in the area, we returned to recover our friend's body from the gorge and "
"rushed to leave the damned place."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74831b3a-2b0f-452a-ad67-f3482de2f0ae"
msgid ""
"As soon as the monster was gone, we carefully scaled the rock wall and escaped the "
"damned place."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "10243c44-af02-46f7-afbf-4843285643ae"
msgid ""
"...and {mf||s}he flinched. The leviathan let out a wild roar and flung the boulder "
"aside before loosing a lightning blast on our companion! We heard a bloodcurdling "
"scream, and...\\nWell, after a few hours, the monster went back underground. We "
"waited for night, and after making sure we could see and hear no trace of the worm "
"in the area, we picked up our companion's lifeless body and rushed to leave the "
"damned place."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b39fd9fb-003a-4b8c-beac-bc47d5cb50d7"
msgid "We determined that we should explore the lowland."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7087b3f-fbfa-485b-9b2c-17dd8b6c80c8"
msgid "We had more important things to attend, so we turned around and went back."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "931ce1ef-53db-4ab2-94ee-955f757c9cd9"
msgid "We examined the surrounding dwellings."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "368454ba-6c4f-40d4-a5dd-d7d720a1d57d"
msgid "We deemed it better that we stop struggling to push further."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83d0d7ee-202f-4fb6-98ff-4dfcb520a4c0"
msgid ""
"We would not retreat, and moved ever forward, toward the tall tree, determined to "
"visit the big hut on our way there."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "00ad91d5-f578-4a8e-bfce-b09f451f8ddd"
msgid "We hurried to the rescue — sensing that time was short!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29b1484b-51c6-4052-a7aa-62240cd05ffb"
msgid ""
"Wary of another of us getting sucked into the bog, we decided to form a living "
"chain. Standing next to each other and holding hands, we began to pull up our "
"fellow traveler."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43404aac-2577-4622-9234-56625c1662a4"
msgid ""
"Standing one behind another, and tied together with a rope, we continued on our "
"journey."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92f9b62e-93b7-4ac5-9c0e-828a6d877149"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fb0a85b3-6681-410b-8385-eebd8b0dbc8e"
msgid "Continue."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd6611fc-eeaf-452c-9db5-352c326f1671"
msgid "We moved forward, seeing we'd drawn so near our goal!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59d86bce-480c-43bc-af09-44a37c268bb4"
msgid "We peeked inside the hut."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8522fe45-864e-4d15-b714-d0b7f0bc39d7"
msgid "We drew our swords and tried cutting a way through!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4ebc6318-f083-4103-b868-a4beef65c89f"
msgid ""
"We ran forward, waving our torches in hopes of searing or scaring off the ravenous "
"plant!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c74356c5-ac7e-4668-9a0f-a5c5204a7fd1"
msgid "Continue."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "545c0313-1286-4370-bf11-75d619cecf2f"
msgid "We tried to glean what sort of idol it might be."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "726f51d5-e8d5-4444-bb87-0ecc44b5b38b"
msgid "Destroyed the sinister swamp idol."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "faa2e6f7-8f0e-407b-8304-797f7b1448bd"
msgid ""
"The idol reeked of evil, to say the least. We were certain we must destroy it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1eff7701-c866-48e2-91ea-8821dc41c0b5"
msgid "Ate the hallucinogenic blue dragonfly sent by the sinister swamp idol."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33ab4565-2467-445b-9279-fa255500e708"
msgid ""
"Suddenly {name} grabbed the dragonfly and held it in front of {mf|his|her} "
"mouth... oh gods, did {mf|he|she} just decide to eat it?!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf61cad4-e865-4f40-a311-fb45b76a9b6d"
msgid "Left the sinister swamp idol alone."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "417aefd6-1503-448b-a81a-59572b7f0c21"
msgid ""
"We thought better of interfering with the sinister idol, and continued our journey."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf447663-be44-4472-b8e8-d41604e5cae9"
msgid ""
"We carefully examined the clay figurines, trying to fathom who they might portray."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d38980c3-e74c-4c3f-8300-033e4ae5570e"
msgid ""
"We ran forward, as fast as our legs could carry us — flying towards the closing "
"passage!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c1e05e8-19c4-4f07-a770-ab0676834026"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff1e742b-38cf-433b-89fe-47d0039b6cf4"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6aa96c80-e810-4609-9862-44ed3dc20780"
msgid "Continue."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff29604a-7aee-47fd-8d74-66ee2bf75ce3"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd45aae1-4ce9-4185-b503-16753722a70a"
msgid ""
"We walked across the heath for a long time, yet no sight sprang up before our "
"eyes. By turns we discovered a verdant lowland, with several nearabout springs "
"streaming down behind another hillside. And then, in the distance, in the center "
"of the lowland among the bush, there stood a single dry tree — a true giant! Its "
"magnificent outline resembled an animal's paw, clawing at the sky. But what was "
"truly remarkable — the flat landscape was dotted by mysterious dark humps. They "
"were piled about the height of a man, and scattered around in abundance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a7a10270-ad9b-4909-becb-2cadedf4ebcc"
msgid ""
"The further we trecked, the softer the land became. Step by step, heath grass gave "
"way to moss, low-growing shrubs and ferns, and then sloshy puddles of stinky swamp "
"water. The muddy ground sucked at our feet, and soon our party was jumping from "
"hassock to hassock.\\nFinally we reached the first group of mysterious humps... "
"and learned they were no mere hills, but dugout dwellings!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "263b08c7-febc-458f-8aee-9bd7fa5b977f"
msgid ""
"Inside, the dugouts were frowzy and dark, darker than holes, and filled with "
"absolute desolation. There were no windows in these mud walls, no furniture or "
"other homely items, except for the odd piece of tattered wicker. But every "
"dwelling had a large hollow dug right in the center of the dirt floor, like a fire "
"pit, but taking up the greater part of the space. They were filled with standing "
"water and reeked beyond description."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3bd56ca3-55ef-4ca7-b2ae-e75d8b07c356"
msgid ""
"We moved with great care towards the center of the lowland, and there the real "
"swamp began! On the way toward the mysterious giant tree we saw the foggy outline "
"of another hut — this one much bigger, and surrounded by small clay statues."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a6108320-3a81-47a9-89ba-29fc93f06e1a"
msgid ""
"We walked slowly, carefully choosing our way, keeping to drier ground as much as "
"possible. But the further we went, the more difficult it became, and soon we were "
"wading waist deep through the cattails. Frogs croaked loudly as we peered "
"anxiously into the cloudy water, struggling to make out what shadows flitted along "
"the bottom..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "635580cf-bf8e-4bfc-82ec-98ddc1b0e123"
msgid ""
"Suddenly {name} staggered, spit out an oath and flailed {mf|his|her} arms. {mf|He|"
"She}'d made a wrong step, and unable to pull out {mf|his|her} foot, {mf|he|she} "
"called out loudly — and began to sink into the vile green slush!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e0afd4ce-d57e-43ed-938a-71abee800a14"
msgid ""
"This ominous swampland was truly a deaththap! We turned around, and retraced our "
"steps back to the familiar path. We had no further adventures on the return "
"journey."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "203cd3b1-8032-466a-a67f-2c674944af77"
msgid ""
"We often stumbled and lost our balance, but our trusty rope, and the aid of our "
"friends, saved us from being lost to the bog."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1a260d79-d7cf-4034-ad32-f2716e8cda19"
msgid ""
"It has oft been said that a fool in haste takes the slowest path. In the "
"commotion, one of us slipped and went under the vile water, and another tripped "
"against him, then grabbed the third as not to fall and drag him down... and "
"meanwhile, poor {name} just stood there, sinking ever deeper as we floundered!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e835185-b05a-40d3-97fa-48ff7e406b68"
msgid ""
"The insatiable bog gurgled hungrily after us, but we didn't look back.\\nSodden "
"and weary, we finally made it back to solid ground. And a palace of sorts rose "
"before our eyes! — A spacious hut made of mud like the rest, but decorated with "
"pebbles, bones, cattail spikes and snail shells.\\nIn front of the \\\"palace\\\" "
"was a wide and shallow reservoir. Its green water reflected the leaves of huge "
"ferns and primitive clay figurines."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c26c5582-f625-4952-8fec-8e5c734904cf"
msgid ""
"The buzzing of gnats was nearly deafening. We were not far to the center of the "
"swamp — and a firm and steady path led there through the thick bushes. At its end, "
"that tall dry tree stretched mightily upwards, clawing at the firmament."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ceb85f5b-f63c-45da-ba68-65941bb0c284"
msgid ""
"Luckily, {name} managed to keep {mf|his|her} head above the water, while we "
"struggled to rescue {mf|him|her}. Grabbing the nearest hand and pulling with all "
"{mf|his|her} strength, {mf|he|she} freed first one foot, and then the other."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "00304efb-f8a0-480d-9880-85a0fb828332"
msgid ""
"{name}'s head was sucked below the deathly icky water, but our hands were just in "
"time. We pulled with all our strength, and {mf|he|she} emerged, gasping above the "
"frothy muck. {name} was rather green by the time we'd lifted {mf|him|her} out, but "
"found the strength to thank us once {mf|he|she}'d caught {mf|his|her} breath."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2fb16571-c50e-4410-9729-da481fb01e89"
msgid ""
"It was ever so lovely to walk once again along the well-trodden path! Our soaked "
"clothes imagined being dry, and our mood at once lifted. The bushes that bordered "
"the path seemed to wave at us amiably, with their juicy green leaves and shiny "
"bright red berries. A fresh wind puffed away the rotten smell, and it finally felt "
"like the swamp might be nearly behind us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6043fa98-86ea-4f58-bc79-0fabaff57a16"
msgid ""
"But then the wind stopped blowing — and the thorny branches continued to move... "
"And we heard a loud shout!\\n{name}, who was watching our rear, pointed to a "
"surging, crawling wall of green, filling in the path behind us! The surrounding "
"thicket was coming to life. Its branches reached out with a soft swishing sound. "
"Drops of sap oozed from their thorns, gleaming in the emerald dusk... The path was "
"disappearing. There was no way back, and the clear space ahead was closing!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0846138-8b92-4f34-9cb2-a384701e4f64"
msgid ""
"What were we thinking?! The damp foliage and marshy brush were impossible to set "
"ablaze, and the bloodthirsty bush was unafraid! The only thing left was to run…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9368e82d-c84f-45a3-8ee1-1962ef2ba0ff"
msgid ""
"We drew our swords, and set to clear the way. Our steel proved more than a match. "
"No matter how many branches the bloodthirsty bush offered us, we turned them all "
"into chopped salad! Slowly but steadily we moved forward."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "200b3f23-9be3-4604-92a0-bacea95fc447"
msgid ""
"Alas, we'd merely wasted precious moments! No matter how many grasping green "
"shoots we cut, more only grew in their place. The only thing left was to run for "
"our lives!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "006b5709-cd03-4462-ae0e-4a0c5b2b40be"
msgid ""
"Finally, after what seemed an endless trek, we came upon the gigantic dry tree "
"that had so intrigued us from the beginning. Lo and behold, we saw an idol cut in "
"its trunk: a huge, horned, three-eyed toad. Its googly eyes made it look both "
"cruel and dumb, almost idiotic. Its muzzle hung half-open, sharp-toothed with "
"several hanging tongues. Deep-brown streaks oozed from the corners of its mouth."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "912f4a71-ffcf-4a05-a7dc-ceef6dd08d9c"
msgid ""
"There could be no doubt — this was {g|Gogunta}Gogunta{/g}, master of the great "
"swamp in the demon {g|Abyss}Abyss{/g}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1613b76-cdbe-46ef-b5d7-43d77b8fcefb"
msgid ""
"I heard a wet crunch... and I winced before I could look. I turned around, hearing "
"a faint cry — {name} had turned white, and started to collapse. We barely had time "
"to catch {mf|him|her}!\\nAfter returning to life in a few hours, {mf|he|she} told "
"us amazing things. It turns out that boggards' priests ate blue dragonflies to "
"fall into hypnotic trances, where they could hear the will of the \\\"goddess\\\" "
"— the demon lord Gogunta, the creator all of boggard-kind. In {mf|his|her} dream "
"{name} saw ancient times — how the boggards built their settlements, how they "
"raided the neighbors and enslaved their children, how they held bloody rituals to "
"honor bloated amphibian monsters, the roar of their laughter throughout the dark "
"centuries... And {mf|he|she} saw a priest bury a stash of plundered jewelry in his "
"hut, rather than offering it to his cruel \\\"goddess\\\". In return, the wrathful "
"Gogunta set a horrible plague upon his tribe, and that priest would be their "
"last...\\nWe turned around to leave the abominable swamp. The flesh-eating bush "
"grew quiet and gave way. On the journey back we were sure to look inside the "
"priest's hut, and dig out the treasure that had once wiped out his entire tribe."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "629d0c8c-04f0-4dec-9785-8c4aaaa7c39b"
msgid ""
"Finally, we'd managed to get back on solid ground... but not before each of us had "
"swallowed some of that disgusting swamp water!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2ed4c4e-5b0d-461d-9c73-b47e527ce2ec"
msgid ""
"Finally, we managed to get back on solid ground... though we feared for {name}, "
"who'd swallowed some of that disgusting swamp water!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f18b22ca-c261-4b01-b6d1-964eaa76ead4"
msgid ""
"Goggle eyes, flat heads, with no necks, ears or chins, ugly long legs, unnaturally "
"bent... these sculptures could only be the work of boggards. Primitive, cruel "
"boggard tribes had inhabited the swamps of {g|Garund}Garund{/g} and {g|Avistan}"
"Avistan{/g} since the olden days. Pitiless to others and to each other, they were "
"led by the darker instincts of their insane priest-kings. They are known to grow "
"young fry in the pools inside the houses."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c9675fa4-f4e1-4cdb-9c7f-8af394a53871"
msgid ""
"Goggle eyes, flat heads, with no necks, ears or chins, ugly long legs, unnaturally "
"bent... these mysterious clay sculptures depicted some uncanny cross between a "
"frog and a human."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2569df4e-6eef-462b-8164-cd5f4bf68452"
msgid ""
"The \\\"palace\\\" was twice the height of other huts, and its entrance was wide "
"enough that three could walk abrest. The walls were decorated — an unknown builder "
"had scratched drawings in the clay while it was still wet. The faded scrawl "
"depicted huge amphibians devouring smaller figures — some frog-headed, others not. "
"Three of the four rooms boasted large holes filled with water, just like the other "
"dwellings — though here there were steps descending into them, cut into the dirt."
"\\nIn the furthest room we found equipment decorating the walls — leather armor, "
"spears, clubs... To our surprise, a number of items were well preserved. The hut "
"was clearly deserted, so we felt no shame in taking some of it with us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0491f443-f57d-4c80-aace-19f49a8e2794"
msgid ""
"As any experienced traveler can tell you, sometimes you walk, and sometimes you "
"run! The branches snatched at our backpacks and clothes, and the sprouts tangled "
"at our feet, but we slipped their grasp, we were too quick!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30d70703-56eb-4723-845e-798ee886f9df"
msgid "Alas, we were not quick enough."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6b1c83ad-f66d-48d2-80ba-496d7a76772a"
msgid ""
"Green walls closed in around us. Branches grabbed at our sleeves, wicked thorns "
"scratched our hands, and our faces burned with acidic sap. Roots tangled our feet, "
"and our blood fell on the leaves, but with great effort we broke away at last from "
"the grasping green."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f3cdc000-bd91-4ff9-8849-424a84520f1a"
msgid ""
"But what is this? While we were examining the idol, a large bright-blue dragonfly "
"came out of a hollow in the tree and sat invitingly on the very tip of one of our "
"noses. It was so remarkably strange — it didn't react to our movements, and seemed "
"quite content to remain where it sat."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c818e4e4-6ae3-4d39-a76f-39c5a6047cc1"
msgid ""
"Why awaken mysterious ancient forces? We turned around and went back — this time "
"avoiding the flesh-eating bush..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a1e15e40-4f36-4948-b5cd-0ae5e3b14d8d"
msgid ""
"Clearly we could not leave such an obscenity unscathed. We drew our swords, and "
"slashed at the wooden face... and from it oozed black, sticky blood!\\nWe heard a "
"great clap of thunder, and a thick fog arose from nowhere. The birds screamed "
"furiously. More thunder soon followed, and with each strike the sky grew darker "
"and darker. Soon we couldn't see the sun through the fog. The air shuddered again "
"— but was it still thunder, or the creaky voice of the monstrous toad?\\nStill our "
"iron blades dug deep into the blood-soaked wood, and at last the idol was smashed "
"into splinters..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acdcca33-2a05-407f-9fcc-2b65ffdf95e9"
msgid ""
"The fog cleared away and silence descended. Suddenly we realized that every frog "
"in the swamp had gone quiet. We turned almost with a sigh of relief... and saw "
"that the flesh-eating bush had withered away. Satisfied with a job well done, we "
"returned to where we'd come from."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "172d3632-8810-45a3-8c6c-69feb852854c"
msgid ""
"Sadly we failed to glean whom the idol was devoted to — but it was surely not one "
"of the lighter gods."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "efce5f94-8414-4e7c-a2f0-d301a5d43578"
msgid ""
"Keeping our wits, we tugged on the rope... but the poorly-tied knot quickly came "
"undone!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff12bc3e-b8d7-4538-bfa5-009316ab266b"
msgid "Drove away the feasting goblins."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57bb8bd4-1bcf-457a-81df-86d6ce17209b"
msgid "Frowned, bared {mf|his|her} weapons, and charged into battle."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c64a0b4-1814-44a6-bc2e-cc3b57ce799d"
msgid "Joined the goblins' feast."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d3968fa7-e339-42e8-beff-8554f03cebf5"
msgid "Smiled, muttered \\\"why not,\\\" and took a place near the fire."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7d2a3f59-1085-4114-87f6-8364ae6541cc"
msgid "Spat on the ground and moved on."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "892a0b27-37fe-4919-b0d2-8a3bec021abd"
msgid "Laughed and accepted the invitation."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e249f2fa-fe6a-47ab-8a1e-30f82966f203"
msgid "Bravely filled the keg from the barrel."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1dcf6f36-7303-4a88-8226-54dddc6b17bb"
msgid "Firmly rejected drinking THIS."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0356b0a0-5134-4515-a23a-db93fd6daf1d"
msgid "Drained the first keg to its dregs."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a0f2b756-6758-47ca-b5af-d124a5f33d31"
msgid ""
"Was already going to sip, but smelled the ale, shook {mf|his|her} head, and poured "
"the beverage back in the barrel."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8f2ebdd-c64f-452c-96bb-3485b8c06cb5"
msgid "\\\"Why not!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "066a15e8-1b15-4716-9df6-e6809ddd4b7e"
msgid "\\\"I'm too tired to sing. You sing, I'll listen.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "05bf4a72-6496-47dc-873a-d519e29bc882"
msgid "Goblin lasses be all impressed!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2be4e49b-6d90-472f-b17a-a4c27938f633"
msgid "And Lamashtu be impressed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ca7cf23-2f64-4779-b0cb-85e7cbfe4b54"
msgid "And pass all your stupid tests."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1706da31-e482-400a-b653-0dc9320bb068"
msgid "Get away from me, you pest!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8f196100-b641-462a-93b8-890af66423cd"
msgid "Um, do I really have to rhyme here?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "473c5ecb-44f3-4caf-8b38-d7b75189b557"
msgid "Is to kill! And kill! And kill!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "10d0b3d9-9e11-46ba-93f5-2b40f9217d3b"
msgid "Is that his belly's hard to fill."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73bea575-c66d-415e-a7dd-0465584fe108"
msgid "Is to ransack a windmill."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "426390e5-115b-4896-a1e7-5c1c3482fcdc"
msgid "Hey, you, I want my mug refill!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "335b7a4a-82fc-42ad-bf11-66bf0ab19889"
msgid "Scream like hell and run away!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2b7256e-6a67-43e4-9aed-2f9d961f7241"
msgid "Quickly hide and sneak away!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37525d51-2867-41e7-b8f4-762e8d8899a0"
msgid "Kiss your life farewell and pray."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c82dbf09-8c35-4108-b1f4-5cef8e0c95e2"
msgid "Tell him you wants to parley!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cfa5e0cc-8d5e-4b1c-a06f-39ea19cb7d3b"
msgid "Do a belly dance!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12e0232f-bc5a-4947-80d1-7e147e99334f"
msgid "So, a toast to Goblin King!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b1f46a8d-9042-4627-95ca-c39d141cffcb"
msgid "We stay here till next spring!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49469b49-168a-4484-8eb9-7aa8b7906aec"
msgid "By the way, your ale stinks."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf0c20a0-68f1-42fc-9c38-4cc96fa98a24"
msgid "And pull each other's nose rings, ha ha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5747342d-265f-4410-a724-f91c6c2dad73"
msgid "Hic! What?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "adb36e2c-fd2c-4967-b164-c99e74f24d23"
msgid "And your belly will stay fulls."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f9813729-93ce-4c11-9b3c-399edacd61cb"
msgid "To be smarts and no fools."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ec9def18-1aa1-4754-9ad7-3d7d235e488f"
msgid "Also, learn to wipe your drools."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94de0461-8f47-415e-b04e-a62c451e3558"
msgid "Pass me another keg, would you?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "120e8cd9-2e5e-48b3-9eaa-9d6e6b12a8a1"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70839b52-7ce1-427b-954b-cb2eec54d4e0"
msgid "Finally, the song was over."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0b3babe2-7c66-4da1-bdbb-83d661b0e132"
msgid "Drained the second keg."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3650951a-37f1-434a-98e2-1822995129c5"
msgid "Drained the last keg."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e44b029-75df-4ac2-8ac2-28ac7db5d9b6"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82104124-7799-49e9-ab70-6e77da5f62e3"
msgid "Ugh. To annoy people, I guess?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "da4473b0-1f4e-4472-8a98-58005eabed59"
msgid "Also, never skip your schools."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a95160b-47ff-4041-b3c3-3fbe1c57970d"
msgid "Literally kicked a dog."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "843395ea-9170-4db0-bbdb-693c784a0a7a"
msgid "Kicked the dog and took the plate."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2e9a547-2cb1-46d4-9c89-4f7937a52c04"
msgid "Answered that {mf|he|she} didn't feel like it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cde1cacd-c134-466b-b9ed-d40c17e92f42"
msgid "Snuck up to the plate to snatch it from under the hound's nose."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d216bd3-12f3-4ffa-aefa-bd75af7e2cf4"
msgid "Took the plate, ignoring the dog completely."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "02074eb7-ee03-4a76-86d7-81ac2f5db18f"
msgid ""
"While passing the windmill, we saw a curious thing. Goblins were squatting in the "
"shadow of the building, doing what goblins do best — stuffing their faces. They "
"had gutted sacks of flour and were spreading the wealth — some fried pancakes on "
"an open fire, others threw pieces of dough into a bubbling pot making some kind of "
"dumplings, yet others just rolled around in the white powder, shoving clumps down "
"their throats. All of them, without exception, were guzzling ale from kegs nearby, "
"spilling it over each other and bellowing songs. When they spotted us, the merry "
"goblins — possibly due to the ale — stood their ground. Instead of fleeing, they "
"started to whistle and wave, inviting us to join their feast. In response, the {mf|"
"baron|baroness}..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55d2ff99-f9d3-4014-aead-e203415900fe"
msgid ""
"I'd never been at a goblin party before — but it proved little different from the "
"late-night {g|Academy of Grand Arts}Academy{/g} reveries. Using their crippled "
"speech, the flour-drenched merry-goers explained the miller invited them to his "
"house, told them to take whatever they wanted, and was 'polite' enough not to ruin "
"the fun — and left soon after that. The food tasted as foul as to be expected, but "
"ale was passable, so soon all of us were tipsy. After these little troublemakers "
"unmistakably recognized {mf|baron|baroness} as our leader, they offered {mf|him|"
"her} to pass several tests to become, um, part of the tribe. For the first test "
"they demanded {mf|him|her} to deal with a terrible beast — the dog (goblins and "
"dogs, well... they don't get along — neither with horses, and... well almost any "
"animal that doesn't sting, bite, or hiss). The {mf|Baron's|Baroness'} task was to "
"steal the miller dog's food plate. So, {mf|he|she}..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25b78b33-ea38-4549-95db-921fc5633a21"
msgid ""
"The barrel smelled horrible. The goblins were scooping the ale in their dirty "
"hands, and when that proved not enough, they dipped their entire heads in, fishing "
"toads out the barrel, with their teeth, licking the toads' ale-blistered skins, "
"and tossing them back in. The {mf|baron|baroness}..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e8259ab-0d82-43b3-b4e0-4f2619a53b64"
msgid ""
"The dog proved rather big, but lazy and quiet. It was slumbering in the kennel, "
"paying no heed to the nearby party. The dog's plate, covered in bones, lay before "
"the kennel. The {mf|baron|baroness}..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "487da23d-d1d8-41e5-a82a-e518678cf176"
msgid ""
"It was the perfect crime — as silent as a shadow, {mf|baron|baroness} swept up the "
"plate. The dog didn't stir."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a8c8a622-e4a8-4ef2-8c1b-55aa49e1bde2"
msgid ""
"Noticing someone trying to steal its plate, the dog opened its eyes. It raised its "
"head, gave a half-hearted bark, then laid its head back on the ground and closed "
"its eyes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fe94302c-d5db-42ac-bd16-fecc7f1b9595"
msgid ""
"With a yelp, the dog leapt up and fled with its tail between its legs. The goblins "
"cheered and whistled as it ran off."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "584aa2b3-2778-46b5-ab83-f568887f373d"
msgid ""
"After the goblins praised the {mf|baron|baroness} for {mf|his|her} brilliant "
"performance during the first test, they announced it was time for {mf|him|her} to "
"taste their ritual drink — a really nasty thing called \\\"jagwart.\\\" At first "
"glance, it proved to be ale... until we saw the dead toads bobbing in the barrel "
"for \\\"flavor.\\\" Judging by the toads' color, they were poisonous. After the "
"{mf|baron|baroness} saw the brew and smelled it, {mf|he|she}..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c3201309-f797-437a-852d-ce389cb03d50"
msgid ""
"The goblins burst into laughter, applauded and announced that the {mf|baron|"
"baroness} has passed the first task brilliantly — just like a \\\"real goblin.\\"
"\" (Apparently, if a real goblin doesn't feel like passing some stupid test, he'd "
"never do it, especially if it demands they stop eating and drinking.)"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "00afd784-65e8-403f-b645-75e47f501191"
msgid ""
"The goblins did not insist — the laziness in their pantheon seemed to be at least "
"as important as {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} herself. Without making us join along, "
"they started to shout a song — it was so loud, atonal, and odd, that it couldn't "
"be written down by anyone short of a master ethnographer, who really loves their "
"job."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92d890da-e501-4d0f-8749-25004b5bda03"
msgid ""
"Goblins didn't like the rhyme — instead of singing on, they started to whistle, "
"and throw flour at us… and each other. In a heartbeat, the impromptu concert "
"turned into a skirmish."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e749b647-416b-47c2-a7f1-98316216a2b8"
msgid ""
"Finally the food and ale were exhausted. Casting sad glances at the empty sacks "
"and barrels, an elder goblin sighed and started a speech about how he remembered "
"the happy old times when they were full, but no one seemed to be listening. As the "
"old goblin rambled on, another goblin, slurring his words, invited us to the next "
"party in their village, and (after many false starts) gave us directions on how to "
"reach it — a dubious honor, indeed, but a useful bit of information! After that, "
"the sodden merry-goes stumbled away, burping and licking their fingers happily."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5c22621e-d558-4e70-9a2b-da9e3787f037"
msgid ""
"My ears almost bled from the rhymes, but the {mf|baron|baroness} kept calm — to "
"the goblins utter joy, {mf|he|she} finished the song, and got a standing ovation "
"as a reward!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f55e908c-8026-4976-aa55-5962de4e079a"
msgid ""
"I'd drop dead just having smelled it, but the {mf|baron|baroness} downed the "
"horrific beverage without even wincing. Clapping their hands, goblins brought {mf|"
"him|her} another keg. {mf|He|She}…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb3afbcf-036d-4240-8146-6cd25ee7863d"
msgid ""
"The {mf|Baron|Baroness} turned pale, drops of sweat appeared on {mf|his|her} "
"forhead, but {mf|he|she} drained the second keg without complaint. But those "
"little bastards seemed determined to send {mf|him|her} to an early grave — they "
"were already handing {mf|him|her} the third keg. The {mf|Baron|Baroness}..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fad611d2-0f85-454c-b644-e0bb270c1561"
msgid ""
"I bet {mf|his|her} stomach was lined with dwarven steel — after the third keg of "
"the horrific swill, the {mf|baron|baroness} grunted, wiped {mf|his|her} lips, and "
"smashed the keg over the nearest goblin's head, making others laugh and applaud."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "355311ec-7d11-44ec-bb99-c284ac9ab376"
msgid ""
"The {mf|Baron's|Baroness'} face turned pale, then red, {mf|his|her} eyes brimming "
"with tears. Unable to keep it down, {mf|he|she} spat the horrible beverage into "
"some goblin's face and started to cough. The goblins hurried to whack {mf|Baron's|"
"Baroness'} back, laughing — either to help {mf|him|her} to clear {mf|his|her} "
"throat, or congratulating {mf|him|her} on passing another test."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6cca5e67-9dd9-4542-afdd-280934cd4c50"
msgid ""
"\\\"Now be third test!\\\" The goblins howled and cheered — it seems they decided "
"they had tortured the art of cooking enough for the day, so now they sought to "
"abuse the art of poetry instead. They were going to sing a song, and {mf|baron|"
"baroness} was offered to improvise and add the missing lines. {mf|He|She} "
"answered..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5437b984-617d-4888-913d-d34e0020a950"
msgid ""
"Shrieking, the goblins scattered and ran, kicking up clouds of flour. When the "
"cloud settled, of the goblins there was no sign."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "741c9050-bf50-4881-8c3f-6ecfa7e4ebd0"
msgid ""
"The goblins weren't offended. Laughing and screaming, they bellowed, \\\"more for "
"us!\\\" Then they started to slurp that dreadful swill — one of them even dived "
"into the barrel to bob amongst the toads."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a8f1ff00-1974-4c31-9b88-b493444f950a"
msgid "Goblin lasses be all impressed!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "baa2b803-1416-4fec-9475-b8c1fd291bf9"
msgid "And {g|Lamashtu}Lamashtu{/g} be impressed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b7333d48-5543-4c72-adb3-f2b1e5cd601b"
msgid "Is to kill! And kill! And kill!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1b865b6e-a2fb-42a3-91df-6ea7e827128b"
msgid "That his belly's hard to fill."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d0f1c660-5c63-4b16-9506-3bb40df5a77f"
msgid "Quickly hide and sneak away!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4f73d84e-fc3f-459d-b3d9-97eef73eeaac"
msgid "Scream to the hells and run away!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2d95b826-95c0-44b5-a497-489547702f27"
msgid "So, a toast to Goblin King!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed6763a9-b47b-4dd8-aff0-a949423e0c42"
msgid "We stay here till next spring!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9dd06682-c7ba-411f-b45d-7877353e7443"
msgid "And your belly will stay fulls."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50ba16e5-2e91-4500-9788-a7f9cd09b12b"
msgid "To be smarts and no fools."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f29f04b8-67eb-4645-b708-68d1bbb5bf72"
msgid "Drained the last keg."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57faaf8c-3454-4f7a-afce-dc02d1f582ac"
msgid "Drained the second keg."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bde6a981-3dc4-467f-8900-fb9202c8af62"
msgid "Drained the first keg to the dregs."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a649c443-3274-4b63-901f-d53912ea2649"
msgid ""
"Goblins sing for you this song\\nHow be smart and fit and strong\\nHow be the "
"goblin best"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9ad89cb9-2583-4e51-958d-6935efbe9c68"
msgid ""
"Goblins fight and goblins bite\\nGoblins steal and goblins hide\\nBut the bestest "
"goblin skill"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e9e8fd02-4256-4dd1-9131-ab313aa05b8d"
msgid ""
"Manticore deep in the wood\\nEats goblins for food, not good\\nSo as not to be his "
"prey"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "db519c0d-0204-4738-be4e-e00544915bee"
msgid ""
"Goblin King be strong and wise\\nManticore he want, full-sized!\\nBut we better "
"eat and drink"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8089ab8a-345c-43e1-a119-8b7e0855b2e2"
msgid ""
"Goblins sang this song to you\\nIf you be a goblin new\\nAlways heed these simple "
"rules"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6f0a1d84-14e8-4ae2-838b-64e276577af2"
msgid "After the song was over, the goblins laughed and applauded."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1dac2b11-85ae-45c3-aa86-1cedea2e8e00"
msgid ""
"Accompanying the song with percussions (percussions were everything the goblins "
"could reach — sticks, branches, forks, pans) they started to croak out a rhythm — "
"as well as they were able."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1988daa6-2691-440c-a1a6-8679eeeddee5"
msgid "We decided to follow the path and explore the mysterious island."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5b2483a5-a37b-4a20-ac34-080b05b8101e"
msgid ""
"After a brief discussion, we turned back — this island and its mysteries could "
"wait."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c51e584e-7e15-4d91-bb66-3dbc61013f6a"
msgid "{name} decided to break through the fog and try to catch up to everyone."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a3fe597-a82e-449f-b1f1-1453d11bd7b3"
msgid ""
"Moving forward in such conditions was too dangerous — {name} decided to stay put "
"and call out to {mf|his|her} friends to stay where they were."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0586a311-f67f-44d9-9f96-18bd25796f05"
msgid "Continue."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4f151b0-bf04-43ef-b39a-1a5c0b6cd090"
msgid ""
"\\\"But look at the bag — it's covered in mud, like me, but this impostor is "
"completely clean! {mf|He|She} pushed me down in the fog and stole my bag!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4bc8a6be-012b-4fcf-9efc-cd95bc5bc294"
msgid ""
"...nothing! Instead, {mf||s}he jumped over the fire and attacked {mf|his|her} "
"adversary with {mf|his|her} fists alone!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a7dcbbf5-1b2f-49cc-903c-cb5f97da20cd"
msgid ""
"\\\"I can tell you exactly how many meals we carried with us, down to the last "
"pack of hardtack. Can {mf||s}he do the same?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5897369d-d5c3-4ff8-903f-b53324bf06c7"
msgid "Promised to execute everyone who didn't immediately attack the impostor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4ea4730-8287-4752-b252-126b3b3d9bc3"
msgid ""
"\\\"Seize this impostor immediately. I'll personally execute anyone who disobeys "
"me.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4d8dd615-873f-4774-98d2-faf88e39922c"
msgid ""
"Suggested that the party should tie up and interrogate both you and the impostor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b574c74b-f8b4-43ac-bf6a-364a60f2e693"
msgid ""
"\\\"Why not tie us both up and interrogate us? You'll soon discover which of us is "
"the doppelganger that way.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53618633-9adb-4137-bf64-f47f9bc4b41b"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf0a0e1c-82eb-46d6-8fa9-f893088f9978"
msgid ""
"Reaching the wooded isle, we stopped to look around. The locals living around the "
"lake fully believed the place was cursed — day and night, colored lights "
"supposedly appeared around the island, and some brave souls would even watch them "
"fly over the water. The local legends said that anyone who saw those lights would "
"definitely disappear — if not that night, then within the month for sure..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2af442b4-3689-47f8-ae07-0fc48270eac1"
msgid ""
"We didn't see any lights at all, though — the island seemed forlorn and completely "
"uninteresting. Silent, gloomy pines loomed over the gray, rocky shore. A narrow "
"path disappeared into the woods."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e5a5806b-b474-41db-a281-2e9d0ed3a7f7"
msgid ""
"Whoever made the path clearly didn't use it often — we could barely make it out "
"among the ferns. We had to walk single file along the path as branches from the "
"crowded bushes grabbed at our sleeves and backpack straps, only to hit the next "
"person in line once we'd passed. The forest grew taller and thicker, and ever "
"darker."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2582650a-c241-4531-8121-bd3d805f5a78"
msgid ""
"The air suddenly grew intensely humid as clouds of milky white, incredibly thick "
"fog flowed up from the ground! And believe me, dear reader, when I say \\"
"\"incredibly thick,\\\" we're not talking like how an innkeeper might talk up his "
"soup — it became impossible to see past our own noses, and it was like our ears "
"had been stuffed with cotton! The air itself became so dense it was like walking "
"through water! We had to navigate by touch, and we could move only half as fast as "
"we'd been going.\\n{name}, who'd been walking last, was forced to stop. With great "
"difficulty, {mf||s}he could barely make out the muffled and worried voices of {mf|"
"his|her} friends ahead. Something had to be done — but what?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bf7a0c6-10b7-4e3e-b3bd-cb80aca1c3a0"
msgid ""
"{name} continued forward through the fog, but progress became more difficult with "
"each step! {mf|He|She} felt a sudden movement of air to the left before {mf||s}he "
"flew forward, having been pushed hard in the back!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e01b060d-7e80-4480-9eae-dfa667c29415"
msgid ""
"But our brave leader's dexterity didn't fail {mf|him|her}! {name} kept {mf|his|"
"her} feet and turned sharply, managing to spot a shadow disappearing into the fog!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22a0f7d0-7fd6-4474-9c0f-831dee5839b2"
msgid ""
"{name} continued forward through the fog, but progress became more difficult with "
"each step! {mf|He|She} felt a sudden movement of air to the left before {mf||s}he "
"flew forward, having been pushed hard in the back!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c93f254e-6e3b-4382-8551-be28ccd77009"
msgid ""
"No matter how loud {mf||s}he screamed, {name}'s voice couldn't penetrate the thick "
"blanket of fog. {mf|His|Her} companions' voices grew fainter and fainter, until "
"they died out entirely. {name} felt the sharp realization that {mf||s}he was "
"completely alone."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9be435a6-4886-4a5a-bbb6-ae64c9fa489e"
msgid ""
"The fog finally began to clear, and soon there was no trace of it. {name} looked "
"back, and {mf|his|her} friends were nowhere to be seen. But up ahead, {mf||s}he "
"could just make out a blinking, welcoming light!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f734f81-c03f-4b3f-a176-dcb8b333d3f9"
msgid ""
"As {name} approached the light source, it quickly became clear that the light was "
"a bonfire! Soon, {name} entered a brightly lit clearing and saw... all of us!"
"\\nBut why, then, did no one jump up to greet {mf|him|her}, or give a welcoming "
"yell, or a hug, or even offer a cup of hot tea? Why had everyone frozen in their "
"seats, spoons lifted in the air? Why the deathly silence?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cbe7b4dd-72e7-4729-b76a-35e2c37e9d5e"
msgid ""
"Imagine {name}'s surprise when {mf||s}he finally saw why {mf|his|her} appearance "
"had caused such a strange reaction — it seemed {mf||s}he hadn't been missing at "
"all! {mf|He|She}'d been sitting with us all by the fire, watching {mf|his|her} "
"exact copy emerge from the forest!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f017d075-9ce0-421c-a795-5e0fa2c8ef37"
msgid ""
"Yes, dear reader, just imagine it! Two copies of the {mf|king|queen} met in the "
"clearing, seemingly identical! But which of the two was real? The {mf|king|queen} "
"sitting by the fire said..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "36f43d1f-c229-4a0c-9e04-e8b3b0d03934"
msgid ""
"The mask dropped, and we saw a short, pale man with blond hair and parrot-like "
"wings with bright feathers!\\nWe all went after him together, but {name} held onto "
"him most tightly — {mf|his|her} hands gripped the joker's wing in an iron grip."
"\\nThen an ear-piercing whistle sounded from all around us, and stones began "
"raining on us from above! The impostor was aided by his winged kin, who grabbed "
"him by the hands and began pulling him up. We didn't give up, but in the end, we "
"were overpowered. There were just too many, dear reader — they quickly reclaimed "
"our prisoner from us. Soaring into the air and shaking their fists at us, they "
"flew off.\\nWe sat a long time around the fire, laughing and chatting about how "
"{name} cleverly dispelled the illusion. And when morning came, as we looked around "
"at the rainbow-colored feathers left behind by our uninvited guests, I noticed one "
"of them had lost a valuable bracelet in the fight! We'd ended up with a trophy, at "
"least."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2584e053-611b-416d-8ee0-bf7b2b2b335e"
msgid ""
"\\\"How can there be any doubt? I'm the real {mf|king|queen}, of course! Look, "
"I've got my bag with all my things!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2ff25a5f-c8bf-4035-909a-5fa70264981a"
msgid ""
"\\\"How can there be any doubt? I'm the real {mf|king|queen}, of course! Devils "
"know who just walked out of the forest, and you're ready to believe them over me? "
"So much for good friends!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4301496c-c05f-43b5-9dec-93d21cc0a047"
msgid ""
"Credit where credit is due, {name} fought like a raging lion, and it was no easy "
"task to catch and immobilize {mf|him|her}.\\nThen we heard a sharp whistle "
"followed by wild, deafening laughter. Stopping in the middle of the fight, we "
"looked around and gasped — dozens of fey flew around us! Pale, blond-haired "
"creatures with rainbow-colored wings, like those of an exotic parrot! The person "
"sitting by the fire dropped {mf|his|her} mask, and in the place of the false {mf|"
"king|queen} was another one of those jokers! Grabbing the bag with all our food, "
"he soared into the air.\\n\\\"Farewell, sirs and ladies! And thank you for a "
"wonderful performance — my friends and I haven't laughed like that in quite a "
"while!\\\"\\nThe fey vanished into the air, and the rest of the fairies followed "
"suit. Needless to say, it was at least a week before any of us could look our "
"leader in the eye again..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3fc04b95-f210-41e8-8434-8b076e598f5e"
msgid "And what did the {mf|king|queen} who walked out of the forest answer?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acf9e4fc-cf3c-4dfe-9a89-7a942a34b2ee"
msgid ""
"How should I put this, dear reader? Either the {name} who walked out of the forest "
"seemed newer to us, or maybe the tone of {mf|his|her} voice lacked its usual "
"confidence... but in the end, the words of the {mf|king|queen} who emerged from "
"the forest just didn't convince us.\\nAll together, we went after {mf|him|her}, "
"yelling all the while, \\\"Onward! Tie up the doppelganger!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c5050d1-e9c9-4748-8f1b-b637007232a6"
msgid ""
"A deafening silence hung in the air. One could hear the thoughts churning through "
"our brains...\\nAnd then the {name} sitting by the fire laughed in a strange "
"voice. {mf|He|She} stood up and... began rising into the air?!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f638947b-202f-415c-9f07-a19ab50c0287"
msgid ""
"How deftly {name} jumped over the bonfire! Before we knew it, {mf|his|her} fist "
"had connected with the face of the other {name}, and their face began to morph "
"before our eyes!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b3f7d0e3-8aa2-4c3a-88e9-b3c7b84f7bdd"
msgid ""
"But the {mf|king|queen}'s deft jump wasn't deft enough — {mf||s}he stumbled and "
"fell right into the open fire! Cursing and rolling to the side, {mf||s}he started "
"to get up as our entire crew converged on {mf|him|her}!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43ddf278-7d4d-4c88-8957-9ec559ef233c"
msgid ""
"Failing to keep {mf|his|her} balance, {name} fell into the sticky mud. At that "
"moment, {mf||s}he just barely spotted a pair of pale hands reach out, grab {mf|his|"
"her} bag, and disappear back into the fog!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce4b061b-2ca3-4ba0-ae60-926bdd8553b4"
msgid "Losing no more time, we crossed the river."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21aa3113-b539-4301-b01e-082daf2e3c98"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e4aa5126-d267-4c28-b810-2361e322bc5a"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d8d39ab0-b82f-4ce4-b16e-21739c0744ae"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b2e27289-1156-4832-96cd-5bccb5f6b18a"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f27df3eb-b54e-4686-98ce-8c2ecdd20fb2"
msgid "Paid respect to the kobold shrine."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6979d927-6028-4b1c-b95f-a1a3de536b31"
msgid "The baron{mf||ess} deemed it proper to respect the kobold shrine."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9811d7b6-3649-431a-bec1-428849087d9c"
msgid "Left the kobold shrine alone."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5136d113-de41-4c27-9bed-adab57562005"
msgid "The baron{mf||ess} left, leaving the kobold shrine untouched."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19519652-fd60-440b-9ab1-8952e72b1ccf"
msgid "Destroyed the kobold shrine."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "825c99eb-5329-492d-8436-4c9f1649dd5e"
msgid "The baron{mf||ess} decided to destroy the kobold shrine."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a25d9101-f9a1-4871-ad46-67b080319b7f"
msgid "We carefully examined the branch that would help us cross the river."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3f484842-f84c-4be5-88f4-39348c8c9be2"
msgid "Before deciding how to proceed, we carefully examined the river."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "490e8dad-cbab-44cc-b0b6-84deefe8c1ff"
msgid "Refusing to give up, we went in search of another way to cross the river."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c11da9d6-c787-4321-a640-a272d4c7ab70"
msgid "Defying all danger, we followed the path."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ff1b6df8-25be-4971-b3e2-f02c50d8823d"
msgid "It wasn't long before we found where the mysterious kobold path led."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17660fde-9ddc-4e44-98f9-6f0fbd93e2d1"
msgid ""
"...flail {mf|his|her} arms about wildly, trying to regain {mf|his|her} balance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a222c22-5bc8-40a9-902c-5bd2ce254277"
msgid "We decided we'd had enough adventure for one day and turned back."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bdf75bb6-47aa-49c8-8107-aa22bcc4f048"
msgid "We turned and went back the way we'd come, leaving the Pale Hills behind."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cd0df45e-3668-44ed-af06-aefd8906759c"
msgid "We left the strange path be and turned back."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46a1923c-755b-4273-be08-120fe8a03158"
msgid "The {mf|hero|heroine} tried to grab on to the floating branch."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b17a1986-eef8-4ff7-bdc6-1489b6c48fd8"
msgid ""
"The only option left was to hold {mf|his|her} breath and attempt to dive under the "
"oncoming branch."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "efa8749c-c849-48f2-9e07-d182d89fb207"
msgid ""
"We instantly began pulling the rope, praying that {name} would be able to hold on!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94fd9b2e-32ea-471b-bae0-485f17671822"
msgid ""
"All we could do was pray to every god we could think of and wait for the outcome "
"of this unexpected swim."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9c9e09cd-159d-47fb-a0ac-631112435ee5"
msgid "...jump to the other side."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61974f12-0358-4cd3-b81a-69350e983495"
msgid ""
"[Choose a character] We talked it over and chose a volunteer to try crossing the "
"river."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6774d1d8-491f-48ad-9ba9-9e7da83740a4"
msgid ""
"Precautions were definitely in order. We readied a rope to ensure the daredevil's "
"safety."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb187c3b-0e18-45e2-8baa-1d5cb3f38d84"
msgid ""
"Without a word, the baron{mf||ess} turned and followed the same trail of dead that "
"had led us to the heart of the Pale Hills. Let time, the elements, and the gods "
"decide what to do about the kobolds, their strange religion, and their nascent "
"artistic ability — {mf|His|Her} Grace would just watch from a distance.\\nWe "
"didn't waste any time with the dragon head, and on our way back, our luck finally "
"turned. A family of wild boars had decided to take a rest right in the middle of "
"what they must have thought was a long-abandoned path. One lucky shot and a plump "
"piglet made its way to our backpacks, soon to be a hearty meal."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43539bb5-ae0d-4114-9af9-a55facf68d00"
msgid ""
"Following my advice, the baron{mf||ess} adjusted the dangerously loose bone in the "
"hope of reinforcing the remarkable composition. {mf|His|Her} Grace was standing to "
"leave when a glint from the dragon's jaw drew {mf|his|her} attention.\\nCarefully "
"reaching inside, the baron{mf||ess} pulled out what seemed to be a dirty stone. "
"Beneath an outer layer of clay, we found a large, finely cut emerald — it seemed "
"the kobold spirits decided to grant us a gift!\\nStowing the offering in {mf|his|"
"her} bag, the baron{mf||ess} turned and left. We dutifully followed our leader, "
"and soon the bizarre kobold burial ground was far behind us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "990aa53f-2189-4a7f-b914-aa369baca2da"
msgid ""
"There's no place for idolatry in our baron{mf||ess}'s lands! One good hit to the "
"foundation of the dragon head and the kobold creation fell to a formless pile of "
"bones at our feet. And good riddance!\\nAmid the rubble, we noticed a dimly "
"glittering stone. It seems the kobolds had been hiding a small treasure in their "
"construct! We pulled a large ruby from the ruins of the dragon head, then headed "
"back."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d7081d3a-6dd2-498d-b947-9be1f4b4b5ee"
msgid ""
"Foresight had always been among our esteemed baron{mf||ess}'s strongest virtues."
"\\nWith the practiced motions of a seasoned adventurer, {mf|he|she} pulled a "
"length of rope out of {mf|his|her} pack and prepared it to be tied around the "
"waist of whoever would prove brave enough to step on the branch and attempt to "
"cross the river. That would at least help reduce the risk of drowning!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "366ce610-9b5d-4237-8afb-0151625211bc"
msgid ""
"What would we find if we followed this strange path, surrounded by all these piles "
"of kobold bones? Nothing good was my bet! On the baron{mf||ess}'s orders, we "
"turned back, leaving the Pale Hills behind us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4acb2853-4b01-4a7f-bad3-2f8e63308573"
msgid ""
"Of course, such an intense swim would have a cost. {name} was practically "
"freezing, and bloody scratches covered {mf|his|her} skin.\\nNevertheless, the "
"consequences could have been far worse, and {name} was ready to continue."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "679dcaba-ed62-4090-acb5-28310519f476"
msgid "It was time to decide on our next step."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4674dd77-4cdb-4f30-9422-9e330f9f9354"
msgid ""
"We were surprised and relieved to see that {name} had escaped, shaken but "
"unscathed. {mf|He|She} was perfectly fine, even after such a violent swim in the "
"raging river!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d85559eb-fcb9-4141-a2ac-14c257271cf5"
msgid ""
"Of course, such an intense swim would have a cost. {name} was practically "
"freezing, and bloody scratches covered {mf|his|her} skin.\\nNevertheless, the "
"consequences could have been far worse, and {name} was ready to continue."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24fd2acf-5fe2-4917-9fda-1760dfefcc1e"
msgid ""
"The ordeal had cost our hero{mf||ine} dearly — {name} was freezing, and {mf|his|"
"her} head and shoulders were bleeding from hitting stones in the river. {mf|His|"
"Her} gaze was distant and distracted, and {mf|he|she} was having trouble speaking. "
"It would clearly take some time, care, and patience before {name} would be back to "
"{mf|him|her}self again."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4e8351fe-e819-407b-9139-09d1ebac88cf"
msgid "It was time to decide on our next step."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1ab7b268-3925-4bbe-b8d4-f0f545e33a83"
msgid ""
"The ordeal had cost our hero{mf||ine} dearly — {name} was freezing, and {mf|his|"
"her} head and shoulders were bleeding from hitting stones in the river. {mf|His|"
"Her} gaze was distant and distracted, and {mf|he|she} was having trouble speaking. "
"It would clearly take some time, care, and patience before {name} would be back to "
"{mf|him|her}self again."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c72a6d45-c158-41cc-81ad-5b4cc5c876f5"
msgid ""
"We were surprised and relieved to see that {name} had escaped, shaken but "
"unscathed. {mf|He|She} was perfectly fine, even after such a violent swim in the "
"raging river!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2449ed22-5ed3-4034-9e0a-9da6a2af4076"
msgid ""
"Seek and ye shall find, even if it takes a couple hours to get there! After a long "
"walk down the stream, we managed to find a crossing — not very convenient, but at "
"least it seemed to be safe. Soaking wet and at risk of falling ill, we finally "
"managed to cross that accursed river and get back to the mysterious trail marked "
"with those sinister bone pyramids."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e52a876-6e0d-4112-8e62-ffe64d6078a2"
msgid ""
"Seek and ye shall find, even if it takes a couple hours to get there! After a long "
"walk down the stream, we managed to find a crossing — not very convenient, but at "
"least it seemed to be safe. Soaking wet and at risk of falling ill, we finally "
"managed to cross that accursed river and get back to the mysterious trail marked "
"with those sinister bone pyramids."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97919287-0c20-457e-91fd-cc7960b15eb7"
msgid ""
"I don't know how, but we lost the trail and began wandering aimlessly. I blame "
"those cryptic pyramids — I think they dampened our spirits. It took a few hours "
"for us to find the path again and make it to a mountain river crossing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9e86b1cb-9d4f-43cd-b365-fefd4767cf69"
msgid ""
"Trying to brush away thoughts on who may have polished the kobold vertebrae and "
"why, we quickly moved along the path leading through the Pale Hills. It didn't "
"take long for us to reach a mountain river with a bridge crossing over it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2e57f28c-55cd-4f35-9474-d4c99b9ce167"
msgid ""
"Trying to brush away thoughts on who may have polished the kobold vertebrae and "
"why, we quickly moved along the path leading through the Pale Hills. It didn't "
"take long for us to reach a mountain river with a bridge crossing over it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4138d78-f09d-401f-af8d-eaede949ae02"
msgid ""
"The branch did have one thing going for it, though — being so thick, it happened "
"to be quite sturdy. But that didn't make the flimsy crossing any less slippery or "
"challenging to anyone daring to set foot on it. I wonder how many kobolds have "
"slipped on the wet bark and found a watery grave in the ice-cold river?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49f2a4a7-bf88-4ec2-ba94-39c411ebc20a"
msgid ""
"We quickly discovered that the river was quite deep — I plunged my arm shoulder-"
"deep into the water and couldn't even feel the bed! It was fast, too — the current "
"pulled a dried leaf off my sleeve, and it was gone from my sight in a blink! And "
"it was cold — very, very cold. Frankly, none of us were interested in taking a "
"swim."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29586d3b-c9f3-47ac-92b1-9fe03e8feed9"
msgid ""
"One small pyramid made of polished kobold bones may be a bit spooky, but it's not "
"unbearable. But how about thousands?\\nWe found ourselves looking over a proper "
"kobold graveyard, each little pyramid a mark of a kobold death, and that mark made "
"out of their own remains. Yeesh!\\nThe real enigma, though, waited in the heart of "
"the burial ground. The centerpiece was made of hundreds, maybe even thousands of "
"polished bones, all put together to form the head of an enormous dragon. Imagine "
"it — these small, nonsensical reptiles somehow managed to create a sculpture both "
"fearsome and magnificent. Such might, and yet — such frailty, as well. If a single "
"bone were to be removed from the foundation, this beautiful statue would crumble "
"to dust. And I even spotted one such flimsy bone...\\nRegardless, we'd come face-"
"to-face with irrefutable proof — the kobolds, for better or worse, were changing. "
"This news had no impact on our search for the trolls, though — the land was "
"clearly sacred to the kobolds, and it seemed unlikely they would bring their new "
"friends here.\\nBut how would the baron{mf||ess} deal with the structure we found "
"in {mf|his|her} realm?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac387543-901d-4278-9a84-079e41255e9e"
msgid ""
"Oh, the lengths we'll go to in our efforts to keep our pride untarnished and our "
"pants dry! One incredible jump, and {name} was on the other bank!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0240dbfd-995b-48fd-9f58-444b4c051256"
msgid ""
"{name} was unperturbed by the thin branch and the speeding current. After a deep "
"breath, our volunteer set forth along the precarious crossing. One step, then "
"another... a few feet crossed with no trouble, and I started to think that maybe "
"things would be fine. That's when the branch jerked and started to shake — it was "
"rolling over! With no time to think, all {name} could do was..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9d8b915c-b98f-470b-9b72-5769f49fa604"
msgid ""
"Some days we rise, some days we fall. Today seemed to be one of the falling ones — "
"the branch flipped out from under {name}'s feet.\\nA desperate scream, a splash, "
"and {name} disappeared beneath the water before we knew it, a victim of {mf|his|"
"her} own bravery."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1635ca2f-f334-4b75-aa3b-2d26b43e6d26"
msgid ""
"{name} took a moment to catch {mf|his|her} breath and turned {mf|his|her} "
"attention back to the crossing. As soon as the rope was securely fixed on both "
"banks, the branch didn't seem as much a deathtrap as it had before."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40c67fc1-80e2-4fd7-bb83-21d446629f3d"
msgid ""
"{name} took a moment to catch {mf|his|her} breath and turned {mf|his|her} "
"attention back to the crossing. A nearby shrub concealed an amusing kobold "
"contraption — a crooked ladder, built from random planks and sticks. It seems the "
"kobolds crossed the river in much the same way we had — sending their most agile "
"companion across to fling the ladder over to the other side."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d14dac6-3277-4eaf-9653-bdf94a7dbbeb"
msgid ""
"Some days we rise, some days we fall. Today seemed to be one of the falling ones — "
"the clumsy jump ended with a plunge into the ice-cold water.\\nA desperate scream, "
"a splash, and {name} disappeared beneath the water before we knew it, a victim of "
"{mf|his|her} own bravery."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "361d3779-8ee8-4eb3-b6b7-dae662df4065"
msgid ""
"{Name} reached out to catch the branch, but the treacherous limb flipped, turning "
"it sharp knags toward the swimmer. A hit — deep red gashes bloomed across the poor "
"{mf|fellow|thing}'s shoulders!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9a723883-2243-4dc5-92ef-29deb7170986"
msgid ""
"{Name} nimbly caught on to the branch as it floated by. Having caught {mf|his|her} "
"breath, {mf|he|she} swam toward the bank."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d4e6ce6b-b6b9-4e30-b022-50796591afb5"
msgid ""
"{Name} dove beneath the rapidly approaching branch, but {mf|he|she} reemerged too "
"soon. The branch, swirling wildly in the current, hit {mf|him|her} with its sharp "
"knags and gouged {mf|him|her}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "212fcaaf-7926-41bb-81ed-46f0fd7824e6"
msgid ""
"{Name} held {mf|his|her} breath and dove beneath the branch as it raced toward {mf|"
"him|her}. A heartbeat later, and we saw {mf|him|her} emerge on the other side of "
"the floating threat!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1039fed3-c007-422e-9df9-c85735ae6929"
msgid ""
"Well, \\\"bridge\\\" may be a bit generous — it was actually just a long branch, "
"about as thick as an arm, spanning from one bank to the other. It may have been "
"enough for a kobold to cross, since we could see another of those small bone "
"pyramids on the far side, but it didn't look nearly strong enough for our party to "
"cross."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62223750-cc21-4878-b15c-af972c92bc3f"
msgid ""
"Well, \\\"bridge\\\" may be a bit generous — it was actually just a long branch, "
"about as thick as an arm, spanning from one bank to the other. It may have been "
"enough for a kobold to cross, since we could see another of those small bone "
"pyramids on the far side, but it didn't look nearly strong enough for our party to "
"cross."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1747c5b4-fd19-48f8-93e7-64725bd5d3d6"
msgid ""
"And if that weren't enough, someone must have knocked the flimsy bridge down "
"during all the chaos, and it had fallen into the water. No longer spanning the two "
"banks, the thick branch was rapidly moving toward our swimmer, who was still busy "
"fighting the current!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "418d6e04-088d-4df9-8ed1-d69b4c911d61"
msgid ""
"And if that weren't enough, someone must have knocked the flimsy bridge down "
"during all the chaos, and it had fallen into the water. No longer spanning the two "
"banks, the thick branch was rapidly moving toward our swimmer, who was still busy "
"fighting the current!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cb191c62-f043-44e5-aa04-10aea12d4bdc"
msgid ""
"Alas, this wasn't the last misfortune to befall us. Keeping hold of the rope in "
"the middle of the raging current as {mf|his|her} companions tried to pull {mf|him|"
"her} out was no easy task, and it proved too much for the unskilled swimmer. To "
"make things worse, the rope also separated — whether it snapped or simply untied "
"from {mf|his|her} waist, our unfortunate friend started moving down the river."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4837941-eb35-49df-8fa4-474ce1251165"
msgid ""
"Drowning in a river out in the middle of nowhere is a grim idea, and the thought "
"of it must have given our companion strength. Holding fast to the rope tied about "
"{mf|his|her} waist, {name} didn't let go until we'd pulled {mf|him|her} back onto "
"firm ground.\\nOnly once {name} was back on the bank with us did we notice that "
"the treacherous branch was gone — most likely flipped over by someone's foot "
"during all the chaos. It must have fallen into the river and floated away. Our "
"only hope of reaching the other bank was no more."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ca2ed4c4-d277-44e5-812c-39632954d8e5"
msgid "At last, after a few agonizing moments, {name} made it to shore."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d6c083ab-852a-471a-bcc0-b642afbcca34"
msgid "At last, after a few agonizing moments, {name} made it to shore."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7467dc37-d379-4198-bbad-18201a359c8c"
msgid ""
"When we'd just started looking for the trolls' lair, Ekun had strongly recommended "
"visiting this hidden corner of the wilds. Since we'd already dealt with the lair "
"and didn't want to miss a local landmark, we decided to go for a walk."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a77e5a6-3308-4251-bf08-99a943faddc8"
msgid ""
"The hills seemed pleasant, even welcoming — no gray doom and gloom, just walking "
"along the path and enjoying the view of all the cute little white pyramids, built "
"out of pebblestone — or wait, was it pebblestone?\\nHorror of horrors, what I "
"mistook for pebbles were polished bones! All along the path, the grass was riddled "
"with pyramids made of polished kobold remains.\\nIt got us to thinking — is it "
"wise to follow such a grim path, the way marked by death itself?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "695cdb08-23ed-48c6-bedd-ae74ea85a05f"
msgid ""
"Ekun had pointed this place out on the map first. \\\"Kobold territory. Pale "
"Hills. Kobolds share paths with trolls now. Maybe here, too.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91657650-713f-4b4a-a201-dd0d84033012"
msgid ""
"A few agonizing moments and — oh, joy! — {name} emerged from the water, barely "
"breathing, exhausted, but very much alive!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e1efb12a-6655-46f6-9cad-bef0dcfb4473"
msgid ""
"Gods favor the brave — or is {name} just a good swimmer?\\nWhatever the case, our "
"fearless hero{mf||ine}'s head appeared above the water a few moments later, this "
"time much closer to shore! {Name} finally set foot on firm ground a short while "
"later, quivering from the cold and trying to shake off the water."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c4b962ad-20ed-4bbd-8831-0bc98afe33b2"
msgid "Having prepared our ambush, we waited."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9dac5c1e-4884-42de-b7bc-76f51b5d6e9a"
msgid "We made note of the place so we could return later."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d962e90d-0a7f-4cb7-8451-7dac364d53a6"
msgid "We continued waiting."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8d442035-b9f4-4735-8e53-e9167afd62df"
msgid "We stopped waiting and left the glade."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06d37692-59d1-4956-8ce2-5f0fc4d2bfa8"
msgid "We decided to stop wasting our time and left the glade."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0bb28f2-5f7f-4205-a6ee-aef110b1e5a0"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6fc44152-06c2-4254-be62-2b1d5a998621"
msgid ""
"\\\"Thank you,\\\" the ranger said with a nod. \\\"That was cowardly of me. {g|"
"Torag}Torag{/g} teaches not to give up. We will wait, and we will get what we "
"waited for.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8b9710a3-8a08-4f94-940b-796f0781229d"
msgid "The fruitless waiting began to tire us out."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eec29abb-7ab7-4772-a375-816e2fdd1443"
msgid ""
"Ambushes take time. We continued waiting in the hope that the trolls would show "
"themselves eventually."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b6a58675-2c02-4f23-ac64-2fa7fafbf199"
msgid ""
"The trolls may indeed visit the place occasionally, but we couldn't wait forever. "
"We packed up and left."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "aa529de7-3d47-4daf-971a-6eaedc5c0471"
msgid ""
"As the sun set, the glade was still empty. Darkness spread across the scraps of "
"the trolls' feast, and the grass began to fill with the dim lights of fireflies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76559051-f843-4f60-b00c-094236380061"
msgid "Loud snoring came from the bushes in which Jubilost had hidden himself."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9f7fd5f7-37b5-4023-8937-8e17a31bb03d"
msgid ""
"Amiri prodded the gnome in the ribs to wake him. \\\"Hey! No sleeping! Why are you "
"so weak? Back home, everyone trained with runs up the hill before dawn! In full "
"gear! Day and night! You became a real warrior, or you dropped dead!\\\"\\nThe "
"gnome moved further away from the barbarian. \\\"Whatever,\\\" he said. \\\"I was "
"taught to wash my hands before a meal, but do I come and lecture you?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3c246109-393f-4ca6-8722-4f34d4a35cc4"
msgid ""
"Arrows buzzed through the air, but none hit the target — the animal disappeared "
"behind the trees immediately. After all that waiting, we clearly weren't in top "
"form. Perhaps it was best that it hadn't been the trolls after all."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84f3802e-c112-482b-abba-3713cbfbd8a0"
msgid ""
"For two hours, Jubilost had been reading a book. He held it closer and closer to "
"his eyes as the sun went down. When his nose finally bumped into the book, he "
"slammed it shut and stowed it in his backpack. \\\"Can we be on our way? It's "
"clear we won't be getting any bites here.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f1a73d8a-28cd-4131-9ba9-537c9425dc6a"
msgid ""
"Hearing the deity's name, Harrim gave a disdainful snort. Ekun paid him no mind "
"and continued waiting."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7997b346-1455-4488-8aea-094dc2f82bb0"
msgid ""
"Who knows how often trolls actually used the place? We could have waited days or "
"even weeks for the next feast. Refusing to lose any more time, we left the glade."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ee623495-de50-429a-9cc6-1e900c96e4e2"
msgid ""
"Harrim ran his hand across one of the skulls. With a sad smile on his face, the "
"priest slowly shook his head. I got chills just imagining what thoughts might be "
"crossing his mind at that moment."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4d44133-3a68-4f4f-9584-e25315eea729"
msgid "Amiri killed time sharpening an already razor-sharp blade."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "205d79ae-69a5-46e5-a78e-9e2231f9ba80"
msgid ""
"Having caught a firefly, Octavia entertained herself by watching it crawl across "
"her slim fingers."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9474140f-8780-41ab-a662-9928a516ec5c"
msgid ""
"With little hope remaining, we decided to give the trolls one more chance to show "
"up."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d2f5964b-28aa-4321-aa28-9b5bc0de8997"
msgid ""
"\\\"What's your problem, trolls?\\\" Octavia yawned. \\\"Are you coming or not?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "301f2c67-d7c9-456e-bd21-3ec9398f547e"
msgid ""
"\\\"They might still come to this place,\\\" Ekun said, slightly disappointed, \\"
"\"but I won't argue. Searching for them may prove more useful than waiting here.\\"
"\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18c624d2-2be5-4ddb-83e0-f4760e9fe53c"
msgid ""
"\\\"I made a mistake,\\\" Ekun said, bowing his head. \\\"We should look somewhere "
"else.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5343e162-3523-4e1d-8526-4beaad61229c"
msgid ""
"Ekun's usually expressionless face turned into a disgusted grimace. You could see "
"the pain he felt as he looked upon the remains of the trolls' victims. Finally "
"looking away, he said, \\\"They'll come back. We need an ambush.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ab258424-f086-4e16-bf8e-4ed413273c1a"
msgid ""
"It was late at night. We listened to the sounds of the forest, waiting to hear the "
"roar of a troll at any moment. Instead, all we heard was the hooting of owls. Our "
"muscles grew numb, and our eyelids grew heavy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9444da6c-8199-495a-a60b-f0df19c3bc3f"
msgid ""
"Of course, we'd already found the trolls' lair, but this spot would give us a "
"chance to catch a few more of the beasts by surprise."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "255b247a-185e-447c-ba4e-c7ace22cde28"
msgid ""
"The trolls were really taking their time. The sun rose higher and higher, but we "
"heard nothing from the woods but birdsong and the buzzing of insects."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70dc33a4-12af-4bb0-b0fe-ba16eed0cdfc"
msgid ""
"Jubilost sighed ostentatiously. \\\"Indeed, why hurry? We'll just hang around here "
"and wait for the bodies of our enemies to float on down the river. I mean, first "
"we'd need a river to wend its way through these parts. But we're patient, aren't "
"we? We can wait for that as well!\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b71b130a-231c-4b25-a0df-d710f75a0a42"
msgid ""
"The sky began to lighten. The hooting owls gave way to twittering morning birds. "
"We rubbed our eyes as we looked around the glade yet again... Suddenly, a loud "
"cracking sound came from the bushes. Alert now, we reached for our weapons, but "
"instead of trolls, what we saw jump into the glade was a huge deer!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d447eda-7513-4c10-9e0a-dc5b81efa850"
msgid ""
"Octavia looked around impatiently, tugging on her long hair occasionally. She was "
"clearly bored out of her mind."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42bf51e5-eea5-4fa9-9b2f-b66ab6ea0d32"
msgid ""
"Ekun froze, keeping his bow at the ready as he gazed into the woods. His eyes "
"would focus every now and again on the remains hanging from the trees. His "
"expression was one of strong determination — he would wait for the trolls, and he "
"would kill them all."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ea14dfc9-24f3-4229-ae4d-1499363f49da"
msgid ""
"Harrim yawned loudly. \\\"Like all else,\\\" he said in a melancholic tone, \\"
"\"this too shall pass.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "355fa82c-3cba-4371-af3d-dac0ca94cc9b"
msgid ""
"Arrows buzzed through the air, and the animal fell to the ground. It seemed the "
"ambush hadn't been a complete waste, at least."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2984b72e-42ef-4e8c-8fd5-3a8c69240902"
msgid ""
"The small glade showed signs of brutal troll feasts. It was littered with gnawed "
"bones, the ground was furrowed with marks from huge feet, the trees held gouges "
"from sharp claws, and the branches had been adorned with the skulls of humans and "
"animals — both old and new. Unfortunately, the trolls' tracks vanished outside the "
"glade, but we could tell that the trolls used this place often."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8ca7ab6a-7999-4d99-8e54-79fdbc5858b0"
msgid ""
"Ekun flexed his muscles, tired of the long motionless wait. \\\"I could be wrong,\\"
"\" he said regretfully. \\\"We may be waiting in vain.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69a60da6-377f-4613-a622-8d15b36e8190"
msgid ""
"Everyone was exhausted after the long wait. The last thing we wanted then was to "
"fight any trolls — what we wanted was rest. Regretting the time we'd lost, we left "
"the glade."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "acca89fd-dc7f-4d84-9b25-8d7a97712fa0"
msgid "The fog is still too thick to find a way."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8993a241-acaf-4080-87af-ae5d28fa505b"
msgid "[Detect Magic] One of us used magic to analyze the fog."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bd3386ce-c362-4651-a49f-b33883134222"
msgid ""
"Fortune favors the brave! Having formed a single line, with our hands on each "
"other's shoulders, we moved forward carefully."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e5bc857a-941a-4b2d-b22a-105bd87611ba"
msgid "[Close] There was nothing left to do but turn around and find another way."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "09a67cb9-7de2-40a4-bb77-5f995895caea"
msgid "We tried to light our way with a torch."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "debd2641-cce2-4dcf-ba32-d88f892fdfd9"
msgid "[Close]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6587370d-46d3-4f53-8337-f3edf04521e0"
msgid ""
"Having reached the edge of the milky-white blanket, we stopped. I have never seen "
"a denser, thicker fog in all my life! Stretching my hand forward, I could hardly "
"see the outline of my fingers. — And if my arms were as long as my companions', I "
"don't think I'd even see my elbows!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c1680751-a9f6-465d-bedf-38624b16e1a1"
msgid ""
"Soon the air became so damp it was hard to breathe, and we were soaking wet in the "
"blink of an eye. With each step our eyes told us less and less, until finally we "
"were completely blind. It was positively impossible to continue in this way!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bc243212-af56-4876-8e9d-07f91c0036f1"
msgid ""
"The fire colored the fog in homely warm tones, but this did not improve the "
"visibility."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81c356b1-443f-4cfd-9446-fb562ff8613b"
msgid ""
"After a roll-call, having made sure all of us were in place, we tried to turn "
"around and walk in the opposite direction. Alas! We may as well have had our eyes "
"closed. Stumbling and cursing anything and everything, we strayed for half the "
"day. It was only by sheer luck that we managed to come clear of that place — and "
"exactly in the spot we started out from! Tired, wet and hungry, we swore that "
"there was nothing that would make us walk back into that haze."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dd186ba3-41ae-4085-bd85-47f6e42ac2eb"
msgid ""
"It was clear the gloom was of unnatural origin. But who or what could have spawned "
"such a thing?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e93011d1-43d3-4d3a-ae56-e06092fa761f"
msgid ""
"We exchanged hesitant looks. It would be impossible to find one's way through this "
"haze."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "be75a1d7-418b-45e0-a9d1-488f322f9324"
msgid "...drew our weapons!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dbfcbc28-3950-451f-a5e4-a30a2d1aa632"
msgid "...threatened Walsh that we would return with an army of our own."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ffd1a99d-7125-442b-80df-8a98a782f316"
msgid "...politely asked Walsh to let us enter."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9d5af4c0-c8de-4283-b4a0-68f23cb71e67"
msgid "...kept what remained of our dignity and turned away."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3bccf3ce-5409-4af3-92ab-4300901014f9"
msgid ""
"...told Walsh we needed to discuss a few things with him regarding the river "
"pirates."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "774de237-28d0-4c99-8774-b13b17fd3d62"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b0ef53b6-55ed-41c0-9bca-3a262ca572ee"
msgid "Enter the city!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a43b8d12-55e7-4433-b023-8a4ae77ad1b1"
msgid ""
"A whole army of mean-looking guards awaited us at Pitax's gates. They were led by "
"a pompous buffoon named Walsh Celoway, a Pitaxian magistrate no less.\\n\\\"Leave "
"now, Your Highness. King Irovetti's orders,\\\" he said.\\nWe looked at each other "
"and..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fde1ffed-8755-49f4-9ef3-6d8b58e96fe5"
msgid ""
"\\\"I would advise you to reconsider,\\\" said the magistrate. \\\"Somehow, I "
"don't believe you're capable of defeating the whole Pitaxian army by yourself.\\"
"\"\\nThen we..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f682da1f-920d-4dd3-8e4e-05fe04fe2dfa"
msgid ""
"This time, Magistrate Walsh Celoway didn't even bother greeting us. Meeting the "
"unfriendly gazes of the Pitaxian soldiers, we decided to turn away."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ce16005d-3120-4061-b486-154fb2e8a3db"
msgid ""
"A cunning smile crept over Walsh's face.\\n\\\"You're welcome to try, of course. "
"However, I've heard that your kingdom is suffering some hard times. Your people "
"consider you inferior to King Irovetti. Your subjects don't obey you, and your "
"soldiers desert your army. Why, we even have a sizable community of your former "
"subjects here in Pitax. If things keep progressing along these lines, your kingdom "
"will soon enough become part of Pitax on its own.\\\"\\nHe wasn't necessarily "
"wrong. We could do little more than envy this villain's familiarity with our "
"situation. We gritted our teeth and..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dfd412a0-509d-4ca1-bc20-3f00022699d6"
msgid ""
"\\\"The river pirates are Pitax's concern, not yours! You would do better to mind "
"your own kingdom, Your Highness!\\\" Walsh said, taking a step backward to be "
"closer to his soldiers.\\nRealizing we wouldn't get anything else from him for "
"now, we..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fd52a0eb-81ae-46ad-a9cd-2df2ef352c26"
msgid ""
"Approaching the city, we found the gates wide open. There was no one there to "
"greet us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58466281-8969-4b2e-906d-db0ecc74c4fa"
msgid ""
"Alas, one can't get anything in this life with the help of mere politeness. The "
"magistrate didn't even bother answering, but his eyes grew even more impudent, and "
"his smile more contemptuous.\\nThen, we..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30c5ebd7-f28d-47d3-ba6e-a1fa4a579943"
msgid ""
"Before someone could disgrace us with an ignorant question about the tournament, I "
"gave my friends a short lecture."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6e4d78db-c71d-4a09-a50f-85c511053814"
msgid ""
"The {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} specifically asked what would happen if we "
"violated the ban."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "03f4f505-2132-40d5-9b21-5045812e7148"
msgid ""
"Unable to stop myself, I blurted out: \\\"Could it be that the true reason for "
"this ban is to prevent King Irovetti's subjects from leaving the country?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cbd728ea-7277-4538-994d-047ea5dd2662"
msgid "[Close] Having no reason to violate the ban, we turned back."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "af3089f8-775e-45dd-a6f8-772434f646e8"
msgid ""
"Our road once again led us to the border of {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}, where bandits, "
"unconcerned for the law, often lie in wait for innocent victims. Imagine how "
"surprised we were when instead of bandits we bumped into a guard patrol! Could it "
"be that King Irovetti was determined to restore order along his border? I've seen "
"all sorts of miracles, but this would be hard to believe."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6a2c5709-683a-44ce-9aa8-fc66272bbabf"
msgid ""
"The guard kindly informed us that the borders were closed due to a travel ban. "
"This was not because of a war or plague, but because of the celebration. The "
"kingdom was preparing for the Rushlight tournament, and the king was busy giving "
"personal consultations to painters, artists, and the masters of the stage who "
"would be responsible for the event. The {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} and I "
"exchanged smiles. Too bad for the poor artists."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "06883853-cad8-4fd8-a927-d32a78c76fe4"
msgid ""
"According to the guard, the king ordered the borders closed to keep secret the "
"details of his coming triumph. The guardsmen were polite but adamant. Fortunately, "
"we had no reason to challenge him and fight our way into {g|Pitax}Pitax{/g}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5a053702-5c4c-47e3-b71d-45bf79dc734a"
msgid ""
"Trying to avoid overcomplicated vocabulary, I explained that the tournament was "
"founded by King Irovetti, and is held on the {g|Rushlight river}Rushlight River{/"
"g}. All sorts of champions gather, from across the {g|River Kingdoms}River "
"Kingdoms{/g}. There they compete in fishing — a highly respected talent in those "
"parts — the art of boasting, and the skill of fighting when you're so drunk that "
"you can hardly stand on your feet. (I still don't understand why everyone thinks "
"it's so funny!) There are many other interesting competitions in the same vein."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ccc97162-e4d0-4b35-8aa9-b7ff512f1d72"
msgid ""
"The guard frowned: \\\"Most probably, we'd have a fight, and you would win. Then a "
"diplomatic crisis would follow, and in any case, you'd be expelled from {g|Pitax}"
"Pitax{/g}.\\\" We discussed the situation and decided there was no need to derail "
"our relations with Pitax without a good reason."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "fbf5a021-2b67-4a17-a491-f63f04b722bf"
msgid ""
"The guard spared no effort to assure us that this was just rumor and speculation, "
"coming from unproven sources. But of course, we knew full well that it was no "
"rumor. In fact, many refugees had fled Irovetti's kingdom, to find a new home in "
"our lands. I myself am living proof of that!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5d8a1e05-0448-40bb-8b7c-219ec7860cf5"
msgid ""
"The {mf|baron|baroness} gave us a sign, and the whole party froze, listening for "
"any sound."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a2b2fa03-2a8a-4cc6-9db9-7e7576b25f93"
msgid ""
"The {mf|baron|baroness} shouted out, asking if there was anybody on the opposite "
"bank, and if there was a chance we might part ways peacefully."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b4752fa5-8517-41b2-b444-67e206b54862"
msgid ""
"The {mf|baron|baroness} boldly stepped into the water, and we followed, hoping we "
"would all make it safely to the opposite side."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6c3a19cf-3478-48dc-93d9-053616dc522e"
msgid ""
"[Close] We discussed the situation, evaluated the threat of an ambush, and decided "
"there were more pressing matters at hand. The western bank could wait."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8a6b362b-dffa-4a8b-a588-5cb02e1d9e30"
msgid "[Close]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5e88ded2-a25e-4ffd-ae0c-e2e19a223ce8"
msgid "[Close]"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e110a446-11ba-466d-8d1f-9770f5e0c06d"
msgid ""
"We stopped on the banks of the {g|River Kingdoms}Sellen River{/g}. It was quiet — "
"too quiet. It was no secret that a whole flotilla of pirates called the Sellen "
"their home, and King Irovetti hadn't lifted a finger against them."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bb30f5b6-3990-4b8e-b1bc-be95ecd0cd41"
msgid ""
"The oppressive silence and the sense of a looming threat were like a weight upon "
"our backs. I began to count how many unfinished tasks we had on this side of the "
"{g|River Kingdoms}Sellen{/g}. Why must we go west at all? No one was waiting to "
"greet us on that foreign land."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2a112ee8-b790-4849-9ab8-32e04f197139"
msgid ""
"Above the splashing waves, we could barely make out the creak of a bowstring and "
"the sound of a paddle slapping the water. Pirate boats were most definitely "
"waiting for us, hidden along the opposite bank."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7485d117-2bc1-48b5-9ab0-74b48da7b9da"
msgid ""
"Silence reigned for a time, and then an answer came from the opposite shore. A "
"harsh and rather rude voice informed us that if we wanted to cross the river, we'd "
"have to pay. Alas, the price — everything that we had — seemed rather high."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "914a22bb-7b91-49b6-ac9d-9270f48d0a5d"
msgid ""
"The moment we left the shore behind, arrows started to peck the water around us. "
"Black pirate boats emerged from the overgrowth along the opposite shore. "
"Fortunately, they'd made their move too early, and we had enough time to turn back "
"and reach the shore. If we'd swum a little further, the pirates would have caught "
"us, and we'd all have met an inglorious death from a paddle blow to the head. The "
"crossing was impossible, and we had no idea on how to deal with the bandits. "
"Surely they'd prepared ambushes all along the opposite bank. But we were resolved "
"that someday we would bring order to the {g|River Kingdoms}Sellen{/g}."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eef8fce2-011e-4118-8464-13df11086e47"
msgid ""
"On the bank, to our utter surprise, we saw a ferry. Its rough-sounding ferryman "
"smelled like onions and trouble. He told us that the problem of pirates on the "
"river had been resolved. A group of {g|Numeria}Numerians{/g} has gone downstream, "
"and scared off all the pirates. He told us then a heartbreaking story of his "
"friend, who once robbed travelers, but was wise enough to yield to the Numerians, "
"and now was living the miserable life of an honest man. Against all my "
"expectations, we got to the other side without any trouble."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7707b0b2-a557-4c49-81d2-7d5f71b788bc"
msgid ""
"If there really were some pirates on the opposite shore, we didn't see a trace of "
"them. I began to wonder how much truth there was in the rumors I'd heard. Is it "
"possible that the pirates themselves had spread these rumors to scare off their "
"enemies?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c7db79a6-e7cf-437a-ba1b-1fe04a94a4ad"
msgid ""
"To tell the truth, we had more important things to do than to chase a flighty "
"gnome."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15ef5066-0637-4ee0-b9b6-ec06642ae6de"
msgid ""
"But we would not give up so easily. Whether the trail went cold or not, it was one "
"we had to follow!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ad92aad8-758b-4edd-bf9d-cc2ca828b212"
msgid ""
"We stood a while in thought, then followed the single set of footprints, down into "
"the gully."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7527721b-5ea2-4e67-a8bf-6ff2df5aebb2"
msgid ""
"After idling in thought, we decided to follow the bigger trail, along the path "
"beside the gully."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "d192c583-2ef4-4db0-8a95-5b0038139aa0"
msgid "We carefully studied the trail that led down into the gully."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "deab20ab-3cb6-4eea-adfd-c6291c578ba2"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ed02b046-d2b1-42f1-9c84-b7c4269e28db"
msgid ""
"There was one brave hero among us, who decided to try {mf|his|her} luck and climb "
"the root."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8efc644d-db76-442d-94e5-b2c8a508b7b6"
msgid "We examined the path that snaked along the gully."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82761e5d-3d9b-4847-9043-2133c7506e4b"
msgid "We tried to imagine who or what left those claw marks…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1566a836-5ea5-4c8c-b863-eb9c451db1dc"
msgid "[Detect magic] We tried to find any traces of magic in the surroundings."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e22aa61f-1552-4c23-9ef0-d82ab40df5eb"
msgid ""
"How sweet, the first breath of fresh air, after the stale, damp stuffiness of that "
"tomb! Before us stretched an unending heath, replete with hills and gullies, and "
"patches of low shrubs. Already, the trail of Tartuccio and his companions had gone "
"cold."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "471e9b90-7413-4f51-b8e4-9cdb39a2d322"
msgid ""
"No blade of grass was bent. It must have had enough time to straighten back up, "
"since whoever last passed through. But the heath's dry earth preserved the prints "
"of little shoes! Our eyes to the ground, we followed the trail..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "b6c90958-c3f7-451f-a41f-d528768bb730"
msgid ""
"We walked and walked, until finally we came to a huge gully — the dried up bed of "
"a river of yore. But what is this? At the edge, the grass was trampled down, and "
"the soil turned up, and claw prints — lots of them! We'd stumbled upon a fresh "
"battlefield!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2dded45-0e41-40c3-b437-be490aee7b6f"
msgid ""
"Alas! No matter how long we stared into the wavy sea of grass, we could not divine "
"which way Tartuccio had gone. Despite our resolution, this time we had to taste "
"defeat."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "912d637b-edf9-4984-a8a7-5f99922e391d"
msgid ""
"And here the trail split. One set of footprints walked away from the battle, and "
"down into the gully. The brave footprints, that faced down their enemies, followed "
"the path along its edge."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8e75af0d-8fb6-47a6-82fa-e1d751796dac"
msgid ""
"The way down was steep, and it took some time to reach the bottom. Walking on the "
"loose soil was difficult, but the clawed footsteps were easy to spot."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ddd9dc8a-dd34-4303-b236-ec3483fcfd73"
msgid ""
"The bottom of the gully went downhill, deeper and deeper. Finally the footprints "
"turned, whirled up the steep slope, and disappeared at the gully's edge.\\nWe "
"couldn't but admire the animal agility and clever claws of the creature we were "
"following. The slope before us was as tall as two tall men, and ended at a hanging "
"crest. Climbing such a slope would be no easier than climbing a sheer wall!"
"\\nHowever, a long, steady-looking root stuck out of the ground from the top."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "c26a43cf-f8d6-42db-9a66-24619ca4d2f2"
msgid ""
"At first the path went right along the steep edge, but soon it turned, circling "
"around a thick and prickly bush. No sooner had we turned than we ran into a band "
"of kobolds, who were approaching from the opposite direction! If there were any "
"more footprints on the path, the kobolds surely trampled them. But we had no time "
"to concern ourselves with that..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "bcb81d45-c470-45d7-99e9-888083a19b52"
msgid ""
"The path was frequently used. In its dust we saw both sets of footprints together. "
"It was clear that those who had no claws left the battle surrounded by those that "
"did."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a28d39df-3194-4410-81fd-cdc47bc593de"
msgid ""
"With a loud groan the gully crest started to collapse, and {name} rolled back "
"down, head over heels — a landslide fast behind {mf|him|her}! More and more soil "
"cascaded down, and our hapless companion was all but buried, head to toe!\\nWe "
"rushed to dig {mf|him|her} out. Luckily, digging the loose soil was quick work, "
"and in a moment we pulled {mf|him|her} out — dirty, scared, but happily unscathed. "
"After recovering our senses, we clambered up the slippery slope, but the trail had "
"washed away."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2cc4a47c-ba97-4865-9310-aa657a4ccdda"
msgid ""
"After tugging on the root, {name} took a deep breath, grabbed it with both hands "
"and began the difficult ascent.\\nPushing with {mf|his|her} feet against the "
"slope, and grabbing the root with both {mf|his|her} hands, {mf|he|she} climbed "
"higher and higher.\\nOnly {mf|his|her} heavy breathing and the faint creaking of "
"the root broke the deadly silence. Suddenly, dust poured down from the top of the "
"slope, and the root began to slide from the ground!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "e2f70a07-0bb4-47c9-be22-392b13bdf7a8"
msgid ""
"Keeping {mf|his|her} wits, {name} shifted {mf|his|her} weight to {mf|his|her} legs "
"and froze. After a tense moment, {mf|he|she} continued {mf|his|her} journey, and "
"soon had reached the top of the slope. After catching {mf|his|her} breath, {mf|he|"
"she} lay on the ground and offered {mf|his|her} hand to help the next of us up."
"\\nAfter climbing out of the gully, one by one, we easily found the clawed "
"footprints again, and moved forward. The air grew tense. We sensed that we were "
"approaching our target. And our intuition proved correct..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a4913443-6bfa-44ce-aad0-a294d3e62e2f"
msgid ""
"After taking in the vast expanse, we took out our map and considered where we "
"should go next."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9fe5acf6-fba7-431c-937a-bfc4e4eb89ef"
msgid ""
"To our surprise, we discovered that the little shoe prints turned into little "
"clawed footprints, on their way to the gully. It was as if someone from "
"Tartuccio's band was wearing shoes, and then either took them off or grew claws — "
"then jumped into the gully to avoid the battle."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7a9ed1ff-3c9c-4a09-a9a6-87e55c88cb00"
msgid ""
"The claw marks were not deep — the attackers were small and lean. And more, these "
"creatures walked on two legs. Finally, the form of the prints left no doubt in our "
"minds: we'd stumbled onto kobold lands!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0d76297c-5b02-4e01-9f8d-04b54c21de42"
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, we could not determine who attacked Tartuccio and his companions. "
"However, we could discern that there were plenty of attackers — and they were "
"rather small."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "422334f5-15cf-4d16-8e31-16d0843ec8e2"
msgid "We took out our map and began to ponder where we should go next."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "220b09a1-49e0-47cf-a420-bb44bb3aa9c0"
msgid ""
"We went back along the bottom of the gully and climbed back up where we'd just "
"climbed down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7c4aa6bb-9bdf-46cd-bd60-c73e2ed74045"
msgid ""
"We discovered traces of a spell, apparently from the Illusion school of magic, "
"near where the lonely trail descended into the gully."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "477edbfb-3d8f-40b8-a46a-356d3702cc68"
msgid ""
"Tried to understand, based on what we've seen, what kind of spell Kalannah used to "
"get away, and where it could bring her."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "059103ad-3425-427d-9bac-1d2f0b26e0e9"
msgid "Tried to find anyone who could have seen these despicable people."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "f5cde29c-52bc-4469-a20b-67f8c116cc23"
msgid ""
"Searched for signs or trails that our abducted companion could have left for us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "cf0b95fd-f08a-498a-a612-fde0ec663d62"
msgid ""
"Without searching for other ways to simplify our work, we followed the trail of "
"the Technic League."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8c5af659-0a36-42ce-b5df-ff6ad8824c6b"
msgid "Close."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63119c0a-3c02-4d4b-93e3-14624ff345d2"
msgid ""
"The insidious henchmen of the ominous {g|Technic League}Technic League{/g} have "
"disappeared into the thick wilderness of the mysterious {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen "
"Lands{/g}! But not for long! Soon we'd be upon them. First, though, we'd have to "
"pick up their trail. To do that, we..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "948bea1b-0e31-4357-a25e-3d1a7198b019"
msgid ""
"We easily realized that the spell Kalannah used to flee had a small range — no "
"further than six hundred feet. We checked our surroundings in this range and "
"quickly found the place she teleported to, as well as a trail leading from there. "
"Inspired by our success, we..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "ac7630a1-d79f-447c-9399-63720095071c"
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, a spell is such an elusive thing, it can hardly be called a thing "
"at all. No matter how hard we thought, we still had no idea what exactly she used. "
"We had to find another way. We..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72a068c4-95b9-41d9-a52d-525876849575"
msgid ""
"Hooray for spycraft! Not far from the abduction site, we found a familiar token "
"our companion must have dropped, and a little farther along, a scrap of cloth, "
"obviously torn off intentionally. Now, knowing which direction to search, we..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1e6f7b21-c360-4d72-b03f-8247ad8b8f21"
msgid ""
"Either no one ever told our companion tales of breadcrumbs, or we didn't look "
"carefully enough, but we couldn't find any trails. But there are other ways to "
"search! We..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4523cfcc-615d-4102-b6fd-dd1f9cda725a"
msgid ""
"This wilderness only seems deserted at first glance. Wandering around the area, we "
"met a few mushroom gatherers and hunters, who told us where they'd seen our "
"quarry. We hadn't discovered the exact position of their camp, but we were closing "
"in. After this we..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33f74fe5-f7ed-401a-8a29-f5164e47a01f"
msgid ""
"Sadly, the wild woods of the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} are not like city "
"streets, where you can talk to passers-by, go to the tavern, question the "
"drunkards and order a beer. In the whole area we only met a single mushroom "
"gatherer, who seemed suspicious that we were armed, turned around and ran. No one "
"was going to help us, so we..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2c29cbde-942e-4672-abcd-e49553f2a418"
msgid ""
"As I have written before, the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g} are a mystery "
"covered in thicket, and not just any thicket, but an especially dense one. The "
"henchmen of the ominous {g|Technic League}Technic League{/g} (who, as we recall, "
"are insidious) used this peculiarity of the landscape to cover their trail. We "
"wandered in the forest for a long time, soaked our feet in a swamp, and got "
"scratched all over by wild raspberry, but at last we found their camp."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0f9b88a6-8180-471c-b923-9f82b18a659b"
msgid ""
"The henchmen of the ominous {g|Technic League}Technic League{/g} are truly "
"insidious, and the {g|Stolen Lands}Stolen Lands{/g}, a mysterious thicket. But "
"true heroes think nothing of such things! We easily picked up the trail of those "
"scoundrels, and soon found their camp."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1175db10-2327-490f-955b-46494cecab6f"
msgid "The baron{mf||ess} took the opportunity to learn the reason for such caution."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "645338dd-564c-4de0-8506-1c96ac39d0f5"
msgid "[Close] We agreed to let the guards escort us safely to Varnhold."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89dddb90-bf60-4b0f-8168-c16356cbba0f"
msgid "[Close] We turned back and returned to the baron{mf||ess}'s lands."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "858a032f-bee2-4209-a317-9592c71ef727"
msgid ""
"Our travels took us east. Leaving the mountain ridge behind, we came to {g|"
"Dunsward}Dunsward{/g} — a wild land, far less populous and civilized than the "
"barony that had grown so dear to us! It wasn't all bad, though — the roads in "
"Dunsward were well guarded, and we soon met a well-armed patrol."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a256810f-f038-4351-a53e-8807b38eded4"
msgid ""
"As we approached, one of them raised a hand. \\\"Stop! Turn back! The road to {g|"
"Varnhold}Varnhold{/g} is closed.\\\"\\nThe second guard was in less of a hurry to "
"drive us off. He squinted and studied our leader. \\\"Wait... you're {name}! My "
"respects, Your Grace! If you're here, traveling so far from your land, I have to "
"assume you've come to visit our ruler, Maegar Varn.\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "abaaa9ac-b7aa-4219-b172-45cfd0809f28"
msgid ""
"\\\"You may continue on, of course, but please allow us to accompany you to {g|"
"Varnhold}Varnhold{/g} — for your own safety. Are you ready to continue?\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7209521c-4ff7-49df-bb16-486d4de76f71"
msgid ""
"Just as we turned toward {g|Varnhold}Varnhold{/g}, we ran into a patrol — again. "
"We exchanged the usual pleasantries, and they offered to accompany us to the city."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2bb4c922-7bee-46d8-9491-e6ae2e4eb5f4"
msgid ""
"\\\"Bandits, Your Grace.\\\" One of the guards muttered. \\\"All sorts of rabble "
"make their way here from {g|Restov}Restov{/g} — we don't get a moment's peace. The "
"river and roads are crawling with their lot... Until we clear them out, we thought "
"it best to patrol the tracts and the river. But we're not here to hold you up with "
"that — we'll be happy to accompany you on your journey to {g|Varnhold}Varnhold{/g}!"
"\\\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "a35580a8-95f6-49ff-a22b-8f4f63346d05"
msgid "The Road to Glory"
msgstr "영광을 향한 길"

msgctxt "3a2e1107-244a-4feb-8e67-7f8af99951d1"
msgid ""
"Our story started at the mansion of an Aldori Swordlord. Drawn by the promise of a "
"most dangerous task and a equally substantial reward, heroes of all stripes "
"gathered here..."
msgstr ""
"우리의 이야기는 알도리 소드로드의 저택에서 시작되었습니다. 가장 위험한 임무와 그에 "
"걸맞는 보상에 이끌려 가지각색의 수많은 영웅들이 이곳에 모였습니다..."

msgctxt "89d44ff3-3024-4aa4-9919-e7539a5fb9f7"
msgid "Continue."
msgstr "계속"

msgctxt "8a298d62-70fe-44a7-99e6-fcc16bae6d12"
msgid "Stolen Land"
msgstr "훔쳐진 땅"

msgctxt "df90652f-db4b-4ccb-8b70-333b5e7027eb"
msgid ""
"Victory! The Stag Lord's dead, and the capital of the new barony has been built in "
"place of his fort. That was how the long and challenging taming of the Stolen "
"Lands began."
msgstr ""
"승리했습니다! 수사슴 군주는 죽었고, 그의 요새가 있던 자리에 새로운 남작령의 수도가 "
"지어졌습니다. 이리하여 길고 만만치 않았던 훔쳐진 땅을 길들이는 과업이 시작됐습니다."

msgctxt "d7768e2e-8297-4d3e-ad40-bef7af39bbbe"
msgid "Stolen Land"
msgstr "훔쳐진 땅"

msgctxt "e403832b-0173-4293-8668-23e2fbf012eb"
msgid ""
"Surviving a terrible night, our small team set off to brave our fate. Beware, "
"Stolen Lands! Heroes are on the way!"
msgstr ""
"그 끔찍한 밤에서 살아남은 후, 우리의 작은 팀은 용감히 운명에 맞서 나아갔습니다.  각"
"오해라, 훔쳐진 땅(Stolen Land)! 영웅들이 나가신다!"

msgctxt "049a14a5-1db1-4531-a623-1841d2934a9e"
msgid "Troll Trouble"
msgstr "트롤 문제"

msgctxt "350fc59c-37aa-4b9a-b16d-e3b99c61d924"
msgid ""
"With the troll menace ended, all our woes were in the past, and there was nothing "
"left endangering our young barony... Ha ha, as if! The true hardships were yet to "
"come!"
msgstr ""
"트롤의 위협이 끝나자, 우리의 고통은 과거의 일이 되었고, 우리의 새 남작령을 위협하"
"는 존재는 모두 사라졌습니다...라고 할 줄 알았나요! 하 하. 진정한 고난은 아직 나타나"
"지도 않은걸요! "

msgctxt "05949644-6d2c-4fc3-abc8-2ff643597674"
msgid "Troll Trouble"
msgstr "트롤 문제"

msgctxt "41763e56-6dd7-4617-be2b-fcdb58f287f6"
msgid ""
"Trolls who didn't fear fire? That sounded terrible. And dangerous. And terribly "
"dangerous! If we couldn't rein them in, our young barony would be eaten up in a "
"snap!"
msgstr ""
"불을 두려워하지 않는 트롤이라니? 정말 끔찍했습니다. 위험하기도 하고요. 끔찍하게 위"
"험했지요. 이들을 막지 못했다면, 우리의 새 영지는 한입거리 식사가 되버렸을겁니다!"

msgctxt "26857516-4d6b-475d-bf83-e95683ea2f73"
msgid "Season of Bloom"
msgstr "개화의 계절"

msgctxt "b784d4fe-151a-4ba9-bb18-33673c928b7e"
msgid ""
"The season of Bloom was over, its invasion of magical beasts stopped. Finally "
"getting a break, it was time for us to restore the capital and count our losses."
msgstr ""
"개화의 계절이 막을 내렸습니다. 마법 야수들의 침공은 멈췄습니다. 드디어 숨돌릴 시간"
"이 주어진겁니다. 우린 수도를 복구하고 희생자를 헤아려야 했습니다."

msgctxt "78209612-0b0b-4251-ba8b-014eba0938d3"
msgid "Season of Bloom"
msgstr "개화의 계절"

msgctxt "f520d8af-b80e-4148-b048-0c2252b3c05e"
msgid ""
"Hunting together with foreign guests would not only help in solving the problem of "
"rapidly multiplying magical animals — it would also improve our relationships with "
"our neighbors! But little did we know that this innocent fun would be the start of "
"a real catastrophe..."
msgstr ""
"이방인 손님들과 함께한 사냥은 급격히 늘어나는 마법 야수 문제를 해결하는 데 도움이 "
"되었을 뿐 아니라 — 우리 이웃과의 관계에도 도움이 되었습니다! 하지만 이 악의없는 유"
"흥이 진정한 재앙의 시작이었음을 그 때는 전혀 알지 못했었습니다 ..."

msgctxt "ef218569-358f-4fce-8808-ee69ea69dae5"
msgid "The Varnhold Vanishing"
msgstr "실종된 반홀드"

msgctxt "ba8fa6d5-3bc4-4e14-abfd-8dfdf596f3a1"
msgid ""
"The ancient evil was defeated — the dead tyrant Vordakai wouldn't be threatening "
"us or anyone else any longer. Alas, our friend revealed himself to be an enemy! "
"How could you, Tristian? We trusted you!"
msgstr ""
"고대의 악이 패배를 맞이했습니다 - 언데드 폭군 보데카이는 더 이상 누구도 위협하지 못"
"할 것 입니다. 아아, 하지만 우리의 친구가 적이었음이 들어났습니다. 어떻게 그럴 수가 "
"있나요, 트리스티안? 우린 당신을 믿었는데!"

msgctxt "5cce20d7-0d35-43a1-b489-0a48ae2647d4"
msgid "The Varnhold Vanishing"
msgstr "실종된 반홀드"

msgctxt "c0510be2-ebaa-4074-8503-53968b036df2"
msgid ""
"This time, the disaster didn't hit us, but our neighbors. Varnhold, a small town "
"east of our barony, had been deserted in an instant."
msgstr ""
"이번엔, 우리가 아니라 우리의 이웃에 재앙이 닥쳤습니다. 영지 동쪽에 있는 작은 마을"
"인 반홀드가 순식간에 황량한 폐허로 변해버렸습니다."

msgctxt "cd3785af-e336-410f-8cb9-016f92de7329"
msgid "The Twice-Born Warlord"
msgstr "두번-태어난 전쟁군주"

msgctxt "a2fc5483-aff6-4629-ad15-000bdb8bed49"
msgid ""
"This was a true triumph! Forget some simple barony — our ruler now wore the crown "
"of a monarch! The time had come for royal feats — and equally royal dangers!"
msgstr ""
"진정한 승리였습니다! 조그마했던 남작령은 기억에서 잊어버리세요 - 우리의 통치자는 군"
"주의 왕관을 쓰게 됐습니다! 왕의 역량과 그에 걸맞는 위협의 시대가 도래한 것입니다!"

msgctxt "93cb48f2-2d82-4835-93dc-dabe1fcc0772"
msgid "The Twice-Born Warlord"
msgstr "두번-태어난 전쟁군주"

msgctxt "e61b3d1e-2839-4f6a-af97-a1bb119a38f6"
msgid ""
"Meanwhile, barbarian hordes had been gathering near Brevoy's borders. We had a "
"difficult choice to make: was it more important to chase a traitor — or to fulfill "
"our duty as allies?"
msgstr ""
"한편, 바바리안 무리가 브레보이의 국경에 집결했습니다. 우린 어려운 결정에 직면했습니"
"다 : 어떤 일이 더 중요했을까요? - 배반자를 쫓아야 했을까요? 아니면 동맹으로서 의무"
"를 다해야 했을까요?"

msgctxt "7be15ec8-350d-47fe-b6b4-c6a03667b2d6"
msgid "War of the River Kings"
msgstr "리버 킹덤의 왕들의 전쟁"

msgctxt "f9a155c6-fc4b-46f0-a7f7-95c6aad8f452"
msgid ""
"Irovetti was dead — and good riddance! Our ruler added the crown of Pitax to the "
"crown of the Stolen Lands. But behind the dead monarch loomed the shadow of a much "
"more dangerous foe..."
msgstr ""
"이로베티는 죽었습니다 - 아주 후련한 일이었지요! 우리의 통치자는 훔쳐진 땅의 왕관에 "
"피탁스의 왕관을 더했습니다. 하지만 죽은 군주의 배후에선 훨씬 더 위험한 적의 그림자"
"가 도사리고 있었습니다."

msgctxt "33ad7bc2-63e3-4e37-b145-c74fd017e071"
msgid "War of the River Kings"
msgstr "리버 킹덤의 왕들의 전쟁"

msgctxt "30245441-fe60-45c0-a41e-7656790d6d0a"
msgid ""
"Irovetti, King of Pitax, invited our {mf|king|queen} to a tournament. But why? A "
"demonstration of neighborly amiability, perhaps? Unlikely — the ruler of Pitax was "
"renowned for his devious guile..."
msgstr ""
"피탁스의 왕인 이로베티가 {mf|king|queen}을 토너먼트에 초대했습니다. 하지만 목적이 "
"뭘까요? 이웃간 정다움을 표시하고 싶었던 걸까요? 그럴 것 같지는 않았습니다 - 피탁스"
"의 통치자는 간교한 속임수로 악명이 높았기 때문입니다 ..."

msgctxt "dcaaf4ea-71d2-484e-811f-1ea99f1b76d1"
msgid "Sound of a Thousand Screams"
msgstr "천 가지 비명에서 들리는 소리"

msgctxt "235746cf-4f60-4353-98b1-cea505e51364"
msgid ""
"It was time to meet the real mistress of the Stolen Lands — the one who'd been "
"pulling the strings to create and destroy kingdoms for ages now."
msgstr ""
"훔쳐진 땅의 진정한 여주인을 만날 순간이 찾아왔습니다 -  수세대에 걸쳐 왕국을 건설하"
"고 파괴하게끔 배후에서 조종한 장본인 말입니다."

msgctxt "45da42a7-5461-404f-b1ac-fb93e2fdf34f"
msgid "Sound of a Thousand Screams"
msgstr "천 가지 비명에서 들리는 소리"

msgctxt "3cbe1c51-199d-4443-a87f-349c82593cfb"
msgid "The Cursed {mf|King|Queen}"
msgstr "저주받은 {mf|King|Queen}"

msgctxt "9c06ab18-3139-4a97-aa0f-3d36de6e0493"
msgid ""
"The ages-old drama had drawn to its finale. The story of Nyrissa's torment was "
"complete... and now it was time to face the most difficult trial yet."
msgstr ""
"수세대에 걸친 드라마가 대망의 피날레에 이르렀습니다. 니리사의 고통에 관한 이야기는 "
"끝을 맺었습니다.. 이제 한번도 경험하지 못한 가장 어려운 시련을 마주할 순간이 찾아왔"
"습니다."

msgctxt "6f28f7fe-5b83-4346-a998-f1f5df5aabe0"
msgid ""
"Defeating Nyrissa, we brought upon ourselves the anger of a creature much more "
"ancient, powerful, and frightful. We took the Lantern King's favorite toy — and "
"now the full power of his curse came crashing down on us!"
msgstr ""
"니리사를 물리치고, 우린 니리사보다 더 강하고, 더 무시무시하고, 더 고대에 존재했던 "
"자의 분노를 샀습니다. 우리가 렌턴 킹이 가장 아끼던 장난감을 앗아갔기 때문이지요. 그"
"러자 온 힘을 다한 렌턴 킹의 저주가 우리에게 떨어졌습니다!"

msgctxt "b470c0bc-e7a9-43b7-ad21-6ed887771d8d"
msgid "We can cross this task off our list."
msgstr "이 일은 이제 할 일 목록에서 지워도 되겠네요."

msgctxt "8d91932c-e78d-4e30-9461-194bca865d47"
msgid "Other Quests"
msgstr "그외의 임무들"

msgctxt "aec4de0f-868f-4c44-929b-421f9b05a525"
msgid "War of the River Kings"
msgstr "리버 킹덤의 왕들의 전쟁"

msgctxt "d7a9042e-c640-47a0-8488-b237987a8276"
msgid "Sound of a Thousand Screams"
msgstr "천 가지 비명에서 들리는 소리"

msgctxt "086117bc-1cdf-4db9-80ca-4fe6d2efcfb7"
msgid "The Cursed {mf|King|Queen}"
msgstr "저주받은 {mf|King|Queen}"

msgctxt "241274f1-fb77-40ef-86d1-6bfb6894d2c7"
msgid "Prologue"
msgstr "프롤로그"

msgctxt "30c0a77e-e9bd-4630-ae9b-bc51c4a4759b"
msgid "Stolen Land"
msgstr "훔쳐진 땅"

msgctxt "5e7a97e5-781c-4145-b6de-91337810734d"
msgid "Troll Trouble"
msgstr "트롤 문제"

msgctxt "2317a79c-ca88-485e-ba57-0bb18b6e5769"
msgid "Season of Bloom"
msgstr "개화의 계절"

msgctxt "4533b220-3bc4-4eea-87d1-2a5d5d451d71"
msgid "The Varnhold Vanishing"
msgstr "실종된 반홀드"

msgctxt "2e4e80e3-2672-4742-9b55-ee2e38a76a4f"
msgid "The Twice-Born Warlord"
msgstr "두번-태어난 전쟁군주"

msgctxt "c4d9e4b8-662d-4fae-9d2f-b1504bae83d9"
msgid "Kingdom Quests"
msgstr "왕국 임무"

msgctxt "8c857f8a-e260-447b-91eb-a31db9b196b7"
msgid "Companion Quests"
msgstr "동료 임무"

msgctxt "97f025cb-c71c-4637-9829-680b48c14b21"
msgid "Errands"
msgstr "심부름"

msgctxt "857fe9cc-2d22-4232-8c31-b759f08f8cef"
msgid ""
"It's been quite some time. I wonder if the Sweet Teeth have returned from their "
"task…"
msgstr ""
"어느덧 꽤 시간이 지났습니다. 스위트 티쓰(Sweet Teeth)가 임무를 마치고 돌아왔는지 궁"
"금해지네요."

msgctxt "07012867-5a9d-4b77-bc12-72dd821d2b36"
msgid ""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "eb29d69b-3162-43f7-87a6-0064c3c874af"
msgid ""
"The Sweet Teeth must have returned from their task. It's time to check on them."
msgstr ""
"스위트 티쓰(Sweet Teeth)는 분명 임무를 마치고 돌아왔을 겁니다. 확인 해볼 때 입니다."

msgctxt "9911af7e-065c-49d4-9b83-0617a694208b"
msgid ""
"We need to check on the Sweet Teeth. They must have carried out their task by now!"
msgstr ""
"스위트 티쓰(Sweet Teeth)를 확인해 봐야 합니다. 지금쯤 분명 임무를 마치고 돌아왔을겁"
"니다!"

msgctxt "6f262b72-a860-4b62-8330-34e07cd4f1a3"
msgid ""
"It's about time to check on the Sweet Teeth, to find out how they handled the task "
"we gave them."
msgstr ""
"우리가 내린 임무를 어떻게 처리했는지 알아보기 위해 스위트 티쓰(Sweet Teeth)에게 찾"
"아가봐야 할 때가 되었습니다."

msgctxt "feb19990-90bd-43cd-a45f-71b474f23e81"
msgid ""
"The Sweet Teeth must have returned from Oleg's Trading Post by now. It's time we "
"check on them."
msgstr ""
"지금쯤 스위트 티쓰(Sweet Teeth)는 분명 올렉의 교역소에서 돌아왔을겁니다. 확인 해 "
"볼 때입니다."

msgctxt "e45a9550-b5fb-4b59-b859-fed435f405f9"
msgid ""
"We tried everything we could! I suppose the Sweet Teeth will stay as our guests "
"for a while."
msgstr ""
"우리는 할 수 있는 일은 다 시도해 봤습니다! 스위트 티쓰(Sweet Teeth)는 당분간 우리"
"의 손님으로 머물 것 같군요."

msgctxt "f2e456ab-779c-4569-aceb-59cfb11afe16"
msgid ""
"For some reason Kaessi doesn't want to see her friends, the Sweet Teeth. She's "
"asked the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} to send them off on errands, far away "
"from the capital!"
msgstr ""
"어떤 이유로 카에씨는 그녀의 친구들인 스위트 티쓰(Sweet Teeth)를 보기 싫어 하는 것 "
"같습니다. 그녀가 {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}에게 잡일을 시켜 수도에서 멀리 떨어"
"진 곳으로 보내달라 요청했거든요!"

msgctxt "bfdf54c3-db9c-4292-8ab5-c5097bbfa012"
msgid "A Task for the Sweet Teeth"
msgstr "스위트 티쓰를 위한 임무"

msgctxt "e47793ba-51a1-4bb9-b140-051959089810"
msgid ""
"The {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} sent the Sweet Teeth to polish linnorm bones. "
"That will keep them busy for a while!"
msgstr ""
"{mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}은 린놈의 뼈를 광내는 임무를 스위트 티쓰에게 내렸습니"
"다. 당분간은 바쁘게 지내겠지요!"

msgctxt "69a6d96d-5d45-4dc7-8663-08962a61f6ce"
msgid "Wait until all the linnorm bones have been polished"
msgstr "린놈의 뼈를 광내는 일이 끝날 때까지 기다리시오"

msgctxt "c7572965-45b7-4308-8d2e-267395d69157"
msgid ""
"Their labors are over! It's time we talk to the Sweet Teeth and ask them not to "
"bother Kaessi. Maybe we should have just done that to begin with!"
msgstr ""
"그들이 맡은 일을 다 끝내버렸네요! 이제는 스위트 티쓰에게 가서 카에씨를 더이상 괴롭"
"히지 말라고 부탁할 수 밖에 없습니다. 처음부터 그렇게 말할 걸 그랬네요!"

msgctxt "64a826dc-9cca-4081-a266-054b94c4d76b"
msgid "Have a frank conversation with the Sweet Teeth"
msgstr "스위트 티쓰와 진솔한 대화를 나누시오"

msgctxt "129cb44e-6686-4276-b51c-5999d93a9f57"
msgid ""
"The {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} sent the Sweet Teeth to measure Lake "
"Silverstep. – An important and very demanding task, for true professionals!"
msgstr ""
" {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}는 스위트 티쓰를 실버스텝 호수로 보냈습니다 - 전문성"
"을 필요로 하는 매우 중요한 임무이지요."

msgctxt "00e5c73e-2dca-456f-9d6b-dcd93cfd7ec6"
msgid "Wait until the lake has been measured"
msgstr "호수의 측정이 끝날 때 까지 기다려라"

msgctxt "e24bcddd-3f1f-4f4a-96e7-4fc31f517a88"
msgid ""
"The {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} sent the Sweet Teeth off to weed the "
"Narlmarches! That should keep them busy for a while!"
msgstr ""
" {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}는 스위트 티쓰에게 날마치의 잡초를 제거하는 일을 맡"
"겼습니다! 당분간은 바쁘게 지내겠지요!"

msgctxt "b8e09694-5269-4dc2-8d1a-d9abad83f591"
msgid "Wait until the Narlmarches have been weeded"
msgstr "날마치의 제초작업이 끝날 때까지 기다려라"

msgctxt "c6e31d63-e1ed-49f5-a152-a191652d1cfb"
msgid ""
"The {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} sent the Sweet Teeth to fix the fence at Oleg's "
"Trading Post. I hope Oleg forgives us!"
msgstr ""
"{mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}는 스위트 티쓰에게 올렉의 교역소의 울타리를 수리하라"
"는 임무를 내렸습니다. 올렉이 우리를 용서해줬으면 좋겠네요!"

msgctxt "de9153fe-2b90-463e-88d6-92d74c2b5bc3"
msgid "Wait until the fence at Oleg's trading post has been fixed"
msgstr "올렉의 교역소에 있는 울타리가 수리될 때까지 기다려라"

msgctxt "9c8e0d9d-7271-4c83-9c0d-129e0f6c7997"
msgid ""
"We need to talk to the Sweet Teeth, and try to find a way to spare Kaessi of their "
"troublesome presence."
msgstr ""
"스위트 티쓰에게 말해, 카에씨가 그들의 존재로 골머리를 앓지 않게 할 방법을 찾아야합"
"니다."

msgctxt "6168eff7-bc20-409a-9ebb-6d716cedf9e2"
msgid "Talk to the Sweet Teeth"
msgstr "스위트 티쓰와 대화하시오"

msgctxt "aa49bb2d-0ba9-4ceb-9ea8-367da9b3bd54"
msgid ""
"The {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} sent the Sweet Teeth to look for a road to "
"Talon Peak. I hope nothing bad happens to them along the way..."
msgstr ""
"{mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}는 스위트 티쓰에게 탤론 봉우리로 가는 길을 찾으라는 "
"임무를 내렸습니다. 가는 길에 나쁜 일이 생기지 않았으면 좋겠네요..."

msgctxt "8b0f7385-3a1c-42db-872f-f011184d43b8"
msgid "Wait until a road to Talon Peak has been found"
msgstr "탤런 봉우리를 찾을 때까지 기다린다"

msgctxt "da294781-65ed-421a-9502-1af67ef95459"
msgid ""
"It's not easy to get rid of the Sweet Teeth. But our {mf|baron|baroness|King|"
"Queen} wasn't born yesterday! I'm sure {mf|he|she}'ll be able to come up with "
"enough important and demanding tasks for the silly troupe."
msgstr ""
"스위트 티쓰를 내보내는 게 쉽지는 않아보입니다 하지만 우리의 {mf|baron|baroness|"
"King|Queen} 는 경험없는 애송이가 아닙니다! 분명 {mf|he|she}는 이 어릿광대들을 위해 "
"충분히 중요하고 요구되는 임무를 찾아낼 것 입니다."

msgctxt "ad5cc379-aa2e-4d3e-824e-3e275a87aa9e"
msgid "Come up with some errands for the Sweet Teeth"
msgstr "스위트 티쓰에게 시킬 잡일을 찾아라"

msgctxt "c2a2322e-17b0-4a0c-ad57-fbeb0a19bfac"
msgid ""
"It seems our {mf|King|Queen} had an embarrassing conversation with our comrade-in-"
"arms Kanerah. She would never open up to anyone but her sister. Kalikke must know "
"what is happening to Kanerah!"
msgstr ""
"우리의 {mf|King|Queen}는 동료인 카네라와 낯부끄러운 대화를 가진 것 같습니다. 그녀"
"는 그녀의 자매말고는 누구에게도 터놓고 얘기하지 않었지요. 칼리께는 분명 카네라에게 "
"무슨 일이 생겼는지 알고 있을 겁니다!"

msgctxt "33f8955c-11e5-4900-9aaa-94ae891c2cfb"
msgid "Talk to Kalikke about her sister"
msgstr "칼리케와 그녀의 자매에 관해 대화를 나눠라"

msgctxt "dc86bfc9-b957-434a-8b31-869536d5f69c"
msgid ""
"Kaessi is going to settle in the capital, and asked the {mf|baron|baroness|King|"
"Queen} to visit her – to discuss the details of a future expedition to seek an "
"artifact! Her house can be found near the capital square, to the right."
msgstr ""
"카에씨는 수도에 자리잡기로 마음먹고, 유물을 찾기 위한 원정대의 세부사항을 논의하기 "
"위해 찾아와 달라고 부탁했습니다! 그녀의 집은 수도 광장 근처의 우측 부근에서 찾을 "
"수 있을겁니다."

msgctxt "1f42f6c4-f8c4-42db-8fc9-9e507ca6a10f"
msgid "Find Kaessi in the capital"
msgstr "수도에서 카에씨를 찾아라"

msgctxt "a74b5a79-bdda-4001-aaa0-3b4242806e4e"
msgid ""
"The mysterious tiefling will be waiting for the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} at "
"a place called Sorrowflow."
msgstr ""
"신비로운 티플링이 소로우플로우(Sorrowflow)라고 불리는 곳에서 당신을 기다리고 있을 "
"겁니다."

msgctxt "06fb1200-868f-416f-879a-f447db643592"
msgid "Travel to the Taldan Ruins"
msgstr "탈단 유적지로의 여행"

msgctxt "87d449b3-e40a-46bd-955c-fdb869100885"
msgid ""
"The ruins of a tower on the cliff are all that's left of a Taldan settlement, "
"destroyed long ago by a flood. It's very sad! But what treasures could the tower "
"be hiding?"
msgstr ""
"탈단 거주지에 유일하게 남은 잔재는 -홍수로 오래 전에 파괴된 - 폐허가 된 절벽 위의 "
"탑 뿐입니다. 참 슬픈 얘기지만, 이 탑에는 어떤 보물이 숨겨져 있을까요? "

msgctxt "3e9b4c95-997f-44e5-92e5-e1e80912a2c4"
msgid "Climb up the cliff and look around"
msgstr "절벽을 올라가 주위를 둘러보십시오"

msgctxt "ebb550f3-ae6e-4cdb-8bed-48984696c8b1"
msgid ""
"There! The treasures from the tower – and even the artifact our tiefling friend "
"seeks – were stolen by a horrible gargoyle! We need to think of a way to recover "
"the Disk of the Eclipse and the other valuables!"
msgstr ""
"저런! 끔찍하게 생긴 가고일이 탑에 있던 보물을 - 우리 티플링 친구가 찾던 그 유물인"
"데! - 훔쳐갔습니다! 이클립스의 원판(Disk of the Eclipse)과 다른 귀중품을 되찾을 방"
"법을 찾아봐야겠습니다!"

msgctxt "4cd6ef30-f0b0-459e-91de-5050a2644fb9"
msgid "Deal with the gargoyle and recover the Disk of the Eclipse!"
msgstr "가고일을 상대하고 이클립스의 원판을 되찾아라!"

msgctxt "27ef5c79-261c-4386-bf87-e3a02c8ae151"
msgid "Maybe the elementals we freed will help us?"
msgstr "어쩌면 우리가 해방한 엘리멘탈들이 우리를 도와줄 수 있지 않을까요?"

msgctxt "0d74b7d9-5ffe-4390-aa8f-5fd55776a11e"
msgid ""
"Another adventure is over! We didn't get the artifact, but we do have a new member "
"in our party. Something tells me we won't be getting bored with her around!"
msgstr ""
"또다른 모험이 막을 내렸습니다! 유물을 갖진 못했지만, 우리 일행에 새 일원이 들어왔습"
"니다. 제 감으론, 그녀랑 함께라면 지루하지는 않을 것 같다는 느낌이 드네요!"

msgctxt "11783337-5a50-49bf-b60e-0c281a96bcfe"
msgid ""
"Interesting things are happening. – Kaessi, a tiefling from Qadira, came to us "
"asking for help in finding an artifact in an ancient treasury! It seems like a "
"normal errand... so why do I feel it's more complicated than it sounds?"
msgstr ""
"흥미로운 일이 생겼습니다. – 카디라에서 온 티플링, 카에씨가 고대의 보물창고에 있는 "
"유물을 찾는데 도움을 요청하러 왔습니다! 평범한 일거리 같은데... 일이 더 복잡해 질 "
"것 같은 기분이 드는 건 왜일까요?"

msgctxt "8f97bf4a-ff0c-4f3d-926c-c087a4bf9c2d"
msgid "Sorrowflow"
msgstr "소로우플로우(Sorrowflow)"

msgctxt "0b24b5a6-82a5-4875-a94b-a52704a7bc65"
msgid ""
"If I understood the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} correctly, we need to go with "
"Kalikke to the barrens near the Southern border of the Kamelands. There we'll deal "
"with a horrible soul eater! But by the way, who is Kalikke?"
msgstr ""
"제가 {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}가 한 말을 정확히 이해했다면, 우린 칼리께와 케임"
"랜드(Kamelands)의 남쪽 국경 근처의 황무지로 가야합니다. 거기서 우린 끔찍한 소울 이"
"터를 상대할 것이고요! 그나저나, 이 칼리께는 누굴까요?"

msgctxt "d04411f1-18f0-44bf-973b-3a0af204babb"
msgid "Take Kalikke to the Southern Barrens"
msgstr "남쪽 황무지로 칼리께를 데려가라"

msgctxt "72b5f734-d3f8-4539-b959-caa00c932dd3"
msgid ""
"The devil tricked us! Well, not exactly... but he did arrange a dreadful surprise! "
"The soul eater attacked the poor Sweet Teeth! What's the {mf|baron|baroness|King|"
"Queen} going to do?"
msgstr ""
"악마가 우릴 속였습니다!  뭐, 정확히 말하자면 그렇게 얘기하기 어렵긴 하지만.. 어쨌"
"든 그는 끔찍한 기습을 가했습니다! 소울 이터는 불쌍한 스위트 티쓰를 공격했습니다!  "
"{mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}는 어떤 행동을 할까요?"

msgctxt "85c7d32c-7254-4257-8736-96081d743ac6"
msgid "Do something!"
msgstr "뭐라도 조치를 취하시오!"

msgctxt "83d21bdf-51b6-4cc1-804a-6f1f7b65324b"
msgid ""
"What do you know! All this time, the person we were calling \\\"Kaessi\\\" was in "
"fact two different people! And the Forefather arranged all this horror with the "
"soul eater, just to reveal their secret to everyone! Now they're pretending that "
"nothing happened – but maybe the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} will be able to "
"get them talking..."
msgstr ""
"이건 예상치 못했겠죠! 내내, 우리가 \"카에씨\"라 불렀던 인물은 사실 완전히 다른 두 "
"사람이었습니다! 그리고 조상(the Forefather)이라는 자가 소울 이터를 가지고 이 모든 "
"공포를 계획했다고 하네요, 그저 카에씨의 비밀을 모두에게 폭로하기 위해서요! 지금 카"
"에씨는 아무 일도 일어나지 않은 것 처럼 굴지만 - 아마 {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}"
"는 그들과 대화를 해볼 수 있지 않을까 싶습니다만..."

msgctxt "1aecd871-da9d-4935-8f04-1598c0d7a822"
msgid "Talk to the twins alone"
msgstr "쌍둥이와 단 둘이서 대화를 하라"

msgctxt "f849d499-0731-49a5-afda-a40361240f40"
msgid ""
"For better or for worse, the Forefather, that devil, succeeded with his plan. – "
"Now everyone knows Kanerah's and Kalikke's secret. This means Nethys's condition "
"has been broken. The Forefather promised this isn't the end. What will happen next?"
msgstr ""
"좋은 건지 나쁜 건지 판단하기 어렵지만, 조상(the Forefather), 그 악마같은 자의 계획"
"이 성공했습니다 - 이젠 모두가 카네라와 칼리께의 비밀을 알게 되었습니다. 그건 네티스"
"의 조약이 깨졌다는 걸 의미하고요. 조상(the Forefather)은 이게 끝이 아닐꺼라 단언했"
"습니다. 다음엔 무슨 일이 생기는걸까요?"

msgctxt "374ef299-e6a6-4963-889d-e9bcdf8e9911"
msgid ""
"You won't believe what's just happened! A real devil came to see the {mf|baron|"
"baroness|King|Queen}! No one knows what they talked about, but I sense that a new "
"adventure is brewing…"
msgstr ""
"무슨 일이 벌어졌는지 믿지 못할껍니다! 진짜 악마(devil)가 당신을 보러 나타났습니다! "
"무슨 얘기를 나눴는지 아무도 알지 못합니다만, 난 새로운 모험이 기다리는게 느껴지는군"
"요..."

msgctxt "0c7acf16-873e-4d48-887f-0efc84809867"
msgid "A Matter of Principle"
msgstr "원칙의 문제"

msgctxt "066cd8dc-a14f-45d0-b471-a7060cc2c3c9"
msgid ""
"We won't let the Forefather escape! We know where to look for him – near "
"Sorrowflow and the ruins of the old Taldan tower..."
msgstr ""
"조상(the Forefather)이 도망가게 나둬선 안됩니다! 우린 어디서 그를 찾을 수 있을지 알"
"고 있지요 - 바로 소로우플로우(Sorrowflow) 근처의 탈단 탑 유적입니다..."

msgctxt "a78ad705-a3aa-4142-bb09-b0ef011a4af1"
msgid "Chase down the devil!"
msgstr "악마를 쫓아가라!"

msgctxt "68dff418-c243-4dee-8076-62d8463aab93"
msgid ""
"The fates of Kanerah and Kalikke lie in the hands of two powerful creatures – a "
"deity's herald and a spawn of Hell. But the {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen} can "
"surely do something! Can't {mf|he|she}?"
msgstr ""
"카네라와 칼리케의 운명이 두 강력한 존재-신의 전령과 지옥의 자손-의 손에 놓여있습니"
"다. 하지만 분명 {mf|baron|baroness|King|Queen}에게 무슨 방법이 있을껍니다!  과연?"

msgctxt "01ca0aea-8196-41ac-a50f-1871faaf051f"
msgid "Deal with the Forefather's claims"
msgstr "조상(the Forefather)의 주장을 상대하라"

msgctxt "04ac4006-b1d2-489d-9d60-097ff91d4b73"
msgid ""
"The fate of the sisters has been decided. It's so difficult to find balance when "
"people are so different yet dear to each other!"
msgstr ""
"자매의 운명이 결정됐습니다. 서로를 진정 아끼지만 너무나 다를 때, 균형을 찾는 일이"
"란 매우 어려운 일입니다! "

msgctxt "21d2a9fb-b069-444b-abe2-a9d01e1dd4b9"
msgid ""
"Oh no! The Forefather, that blasted devil, abducted Kanerah and Kalikke! Surely he "
"wouldn't dare defy the Herald of Nethys himself. But what is his plan? – And how "
"can we stop him?"
msgstr ""
"오 안돼! 조상(the Forefather), 그 망할 악마가 카네라와 칼리케를 납치했습니다! 분명 "
"감히 네티스의 전령을 거역할리가 없는데 말입니다 무슨 계획일까요? – 그리고 어떻게 막"
"을 수 있을까요?"

msgctxt "6d349c1e-4d50-4ead-8c62-8ab126229ae5"
msgid "Equilibrium"
msgstr "균형"

